
#bookname=indian-epigraphical-glossary (sa-en)
#stripmethod=keep
#sametypesequence=h
#description=Data from https://www.sanskrit-lexicon.uni-koeln.de/ as on 2026-06-25

आबाध|आबाधः
ābādha (CII 1), illness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आबाधा
ābādhā (EI 15), same as bādhā or vādhā; obstacle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अबातमाल
abātamāla, abātamālā, Prakrit; meaning doubtful (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 272; ZDMG, Vol. XL, pp. 345-46); explained as a kind of sculptured slab (LL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्दप
abdapa (IA 16), the entrance of the sun into the Aries (Meṣa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्दपूजा
abda-pūjā (EI 32), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आब्दार्खानह्
ābdārkhānah (IE 8-3; EI 31), Persian; ‘water-house’; cf. Pānīy-āgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्धि|अब्धिः
abdhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आब्दिकश्राद्ध
ābdika-śrāddha (CII 4), an annual rite in honour of a dead person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभाव्य
ābhāvya (EI 11, 16), income or proceeds; cf. rāja-rāja-puruṣ ādibhiḥ svaṃ svam=ābhāvyaṃ parihartavyam; see also rāja-bhāvya, etc. Cf. ‘the income (ābhāvya) derived from the loads on bullocks going on their way or coming to Nāḍlāi’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 36).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभय|अभयं|अभयः
abhaya (EI 24), pose of hand (mudrā); see abhaya-mudrā.<BR> (SITI), place of security to persons in distress; called añjinānpugal-idam in Tamil. Cf. abhaya-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभयहस्त
abhaya-hasta (SII 2), pose of hand known as abhaya-mudrā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभयमुद्रा
abhaya-mudrā (HA), pose of hand offering protection, in which the palm of the right hand, facing the devotee, is held with fingers upwards. Cf. abhaya-hasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभयशासन
abhaya-śāsana (EI 12, 27; SITI), ‘grant of shelter’, ‘charter of security’; a deed offering protection; a grant recording the provision of shelter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभिगामिकगुण
ābhigāmika-guṇa (CII 3, 4), certain attractive qualities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिघात|अभिघातः
abhighāta (LP), an injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिहार|अभिहारः
abhihāra (CII 1), a reward.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिज्ञान|अभिज्ञानं
abhijñāna (LP), a token by which the identity of a person is recognised.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिकार
abhikāra, cf. kṛt-ābhikāra (CII 1), probably, one who has committed an offence under the instigation of another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=001" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिलेखितक
abhilekhitaka (IE 8-8), probably, a written complaint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिनव|अभिनवः
abhinava (EI 5; IA 18), name of a tax; cf. abhinava-mārga-ṇaka-prabhṛti-sarv-ādāyair=upetaḥ, epithet of the gift village. It may also mean ‘new’ and the reference may be to the new mārgaṇaka tax. See abhinava-mārgaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिनवमार्गणक
abhinava-mārgaṇaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 264, note 1), name of a tax. See mārgaṇaka, mārg-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिप्रेत|अभिप्रेतं
abhipreta (CII 1), intention.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभीर|आभीरः
Ābhīra (IE 8-3), member of the cowherd community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिरक्त
abhirakta (CII 1), beloved one.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेक|अभिषेकः
abhiṣeka (EI 4), coronation; cf. abhiṣeka-kkāṇi, abhiṣeka-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; presents offered to the king at the time of his coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेकमण्दप
abhiṣeka-maṇḍapa (SITI), a hall where ceremonial baths are taken; the coronation hall; also called tiru-mañjana-śālai and kul̤ikkum-iḍam in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेकनामन्
abhiṣeka-nāman (SITI), the name or title assumed by a king at the time of his coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषिक्त
abhiṣikta (CII 1), cf. dvādaśa-varṣ-ābhiṣikta, ‘when one has been anointed twelve years’, ‘when twelve years have elapsed from one's coronation’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, pp. 333 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभीष्टदेवता
abhīṣṭa-devatā (IA 18), same as iṣṭa-devatā; the favourite deity; the tutelary^1 deity.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिस्थान
abhisthāna, correctly abhiṣṭhāna; used in the sense of adhiṣṭhāna, ‘the residence’, ‘a city’, or ‘the headquarters’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 219.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभित्वरमाण
Abhitvaramāṇa, Abhitvaramāṇaka (IE 8-3; EI 31; HD), the letter-carrier or a special kind of messenger. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321 (dūta-praiṣaṇika-gamāgamik-ābhi-tvaramāṇaka); Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 125-26.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभोग|आभोगः
ābhoga (IE 8-4), a territorial unit; similar to bhoga; cf. Gorajj-ābhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्र|अभ्रं
abhra (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यङ्ग|अभ्यंग|अभ्यंगः|अभ्यङ्गः
abhyaṅga (IA 22), smearing the body with oil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तर|आभ्यंतर|आभ्यन्तरः
Ābhyantara (HD), an officer specially intimate or in close contact with the king. Cf. Antaraṅga. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 426. But cf. also Ābhyantarika, Abhyantar-opasthāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरभाण्डाराधिकारिन्
Abhyantara-bhāṇḍār-ādhikārin, cf. Bhītara-bhaṇḍār-ādhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 28).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरादाय
ābhyantar-ādāya, cf. bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya (IE 8-5); internal [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-003" target="_blank">Page-003+ 40</a>] revenue income of a village; probably, taxes payable to the village authorities as against those payable to the king. Cf. antar-āya, abhyantara-siddhi, antaḥ-kara, etc. See bāhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=002" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धि
abhyantara-siddhi, abhyantara-siddhika (IE 8-5; EI 20, 22), same as ābhyantara-siddhi; internal income or revenue, or taxes payable to the village authorities as against those payable to the king; cf. tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi, bāhy-ābhyantara-siddhi, bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya; also sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi (EI 20), and antaḥ-siddhika (CII 4), a privilege of the donee of rent-free land. According to some (CII 4), it refers to the privilege of the donee offering full power of adjudication in law-suits. But expressions like tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi (q. v.) render it doubtful. See bāhya, siddhi, siddh-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरसिद्धि
ābhyantara-siddhi (CII 4), same as abhyantara-siddhi; explained by some as ‘the powers of adjudication’; probably, taxes payable to the village authorities as against those payable to the king. See abhyantara-siddhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरिक|आभ्यन्तरिकः
Ābhyantarika (IE 8-3), a guard of the inner apartments of the palace; cf. Ābhyantarikā. See Ābhyantara, Abhyantar-opasthāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आभ्यन्तरिका
Ābhyantarikā, a female guard of the inner apartment of the palace; probably also a concubine (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरोपस्थायक
Abhyantar-opasthāyaka (LL), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यासिन्
Abhyāsin (SII 13), a student.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यवहारमण्डप|अभ्यवहारमण्डपः
abhyavahāra-maṇḍapa (EI 3), dining hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्युपागम
abhyupāgama (IE 8-8), arrival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यूष|अभ्यूषः
abhyūṣa (EI 7), a cake.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्युत्सर्पित
abhyutsarpita (CII 2-1), same as utsarpita; erected.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्युत्थित
abhyutthita, cf. abbhuṭṭhio khāmavo (HA), obeisance to one's teacher (i. e. a Jain monk) with formal query about the his health and confession of one's own weakness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्ज|अब्जः
abja (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अब्जदल
abja-dala (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आबोटी
Āboṭī (EI 11), an inferior class of Brāhmaṇas in Rajasthan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्क्कम्|आचन्द्रार्कम्
ā-candr-ārkkam (SITI), ‘so long as the moon and the sun last’; ‘in perpetuity’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचलप्रवृत्ति
acala-pravṛtti (SII 11-1), cf. ‘was administering Pandigol̤a as acala-pravṛtti’; a kind of tenure; probably, a permanent holding. See vṛtti, the same as pravṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार|आचारः
ācāra (IE 8-5; EI 30), a custom or customary law. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-004" target="_blank">Page-004+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 20), religious practice, being regarded as five in number.<BR> Cf. navanavaty-ācāreṇa (LP), ‘99 per cent’, i. e. ‘certainly’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=003" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचारपात्र
ācāra-pātra (EI 30), same as sthiti-pātra, ācāra-sthiti-pātra, etc.; a document relating to customary laws.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचारस्थितिपात्र
ācāra-sthiti-pātra (IE 8-5), same as ācāra-pātra, etc.; regulation regarding customary laws; cf. sthiti-pātra, a charter relating to customary laws (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्य|आचार्यः|आचार्य्य|आचार्य्यः
Ācārya (EI 33; BL), title of a religious teacher; used commonly by the Buddhists and Jains (LL; SII 1).<BR> (CII 3; EI 32; ML), a spiritual guide or teacher; a preceptor.<BR> Same as Sthān-ācārya (EI 17), a temple priest.<BR> (EI 8; IA 14), an architect; used in the sense of ‘a master’, i. e. ‘a master-mason’; cf. Ācāri (EI 17), an artisan. Pāli Ācariya is explained as ‘a master goldsmith’ in the P. T. S. Pāli-Eng. Dict.<BR> (LL), title of a sculptor.<BR> (HA; IA 19), Jain; a Sādhu who has the right of both reading the sacred texts publicly and explaining them authoritatively.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यकुल
ācāryakula (LL), a Buddhist temple; cf. devakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यपीठ
ācārya-pīṭha (EI 16), a holy site; a site sanctified by a religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यपूजना
ācārya-pūjanā (SITI), honorarium payable to priests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आच्छन्न|आच्छन्नं
ācchanna (EI 30), a word of doubtful import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चु
accu (IE 8-8; SITI), Tamil; name of a coin; cf. ānai-accu, nall-ānai-accu, pal̤amudal-ānai-accu, pal̤añjalāgai-accu, paducca-lāgai-accu, amudan-accu, uṇḍi-accu, etc. Cf. also pañcālav-accu (SITI), name of a coin probably struck by the body called pañcālattār or pañcakarmāra; uṇḍiy-accu (SITI); val̤udiy-accu-varggam (SITI), a group of taxes payable in Pāṇḍya coins; yakki-accu (SITI), from Sanskrit Yakṣī; name of a coin current in the Koṅgu country.<BR> (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुपन्नाय
accu-pannāya (EI 16), department of taxation or coining.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुपन्नायदधिष्ठायक
Accupannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; superintendent of the revenue from mints; sometimes also called Mahā-sāmantādhipati, Mahāpradhāna, Bhānasavěrgaḍě, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुवरि
accuvari (SITI), Tamil; probably the same as pŏnvari; the duty payable for minting gold into coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आछु
āchu (CII 4), same as āsu, the name of a coin; cf. Tamil accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचित
acita (SITI), damage; injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आड
āḍa, aḍḍa (CITD), Telugu; a measure of capacity equal to 2 mānikas or one-eighth of a tūm; half, especially half of a fanam or a certain measure called kuñcamu; a weight representing the eighteenth portion of a varāha (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदान|आदानं
ādāna (IE 8-5; EI 12; CII 4), a levy or impost; same as ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आडाणक
āḍāṇaka (LP), same as aḍḍāṇaka; cf. āḍāṇake muktā, mortgaged; valitāya āḍāṇake muktam, Gujarātī val̤at dāṇ mukyuṃ, ‘something morgaged, the produce of which will pay off the debt in course of time’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदत्त
ādatta (IE 8-5), adattā (EI 33), ādattā (EI 28), a tax of uncertain import; probably, interest or fine on arrears of tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदाय|आदायः
ādāya (EI 33), income or impost; cf. bhūta-bhaviṣyad-vartamāna-niḥśeṣ-ādāya-sahita (IE 8-5); cf. also viseṇim-ādāya (EI 21), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्भुत|अद्भुतं|अद्भुतः
adbhuta (EI 33), same as utpāta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्भुतधर्म|अद्भुतधर्मः
adbhuta-dharma, cf. abbhuta-dhamma (EI 33), Buddhist. Cf. Childers, Pāli-Eng. Dict., s. v.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्भुतशान्ति|अद्भुतशान्तिः
adbhuta-śānti (EI 33), a ceremony to avert evil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डचिन्न
aḍḍa-cinna (EI 18), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डग
aḍḍaga, aḍḍuga (CITD), Telugu; half a fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डाणक
aḍḍāṇaka (LP), a mortgaged thing; cf. gṛh-āḍḍāṇaka-patra (LP), deed for mortgaging a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदेशकारिन्
Ādeśakārin (EI 10), an officer or agent, or a representative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदेशनैबन्धिक
Ādeśa-naibandhika (EI 7; CII 4), official designation indicating the recorder of orders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदेय
ādeya (EI 7, 12, 15; CII 3), ‘what is to be taken or levied’; a fiscal term meaning the same thing as ādāya, i. e. income or impost; dues (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आ
ād̤ha (IE 8-6), same as āḍhika or āḍhaka; a measure of capacity; a land measure also called āḍhavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आ
ād̤hā (IE 8-6), Bengali form of āḍhaka and āḍhavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधः|अध
adhaḥ, cf. s-ādha-ūrdhva (IE 8-5); what is below the surface of the ground; root-crops.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आढक|आढकं|आढकः
āḍhaka (IE 8-6; EI 27), a measure of capacity; often [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-006" target="_blank">Page-006+ 40</a>] regarded as equal to 264 handfuls and to one-fourth of a droṇa; 16 to 20 seers according to Bengali authors; also used as a shortened form of āḍhavāpa or ādhakavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=005" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधान|आधानं
ādhāna, cf. dān-ādhāna-vikraya (IE 8-5); mortgaging. Cf. n=ādheyaṃ na ca vikreyam (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 218).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधवाप
ādhavāpa, also called āḍhakavāpa (IE 8-6), ‘an area of land requiring one āḍhaka measure of seed grains for being sown’; a land measure which was not the same in all ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधि|अधिः
Adhi (LP), contraction of Adhikārin, regarded by some as ‘a revenue officer like the Māmlatdār’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधि|अधिः
Adhi, Ādhi (IE 8-1; 8-8), shortened forms of Adhikaraṇika or Ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधि|आधिः
ādhi (SII 2; LP), a mortgage or deposit; ādhau kṛtam, ‘mortgaged’; cf. ādhau muktam, ādhau dattam. Cf. vinaṣṭ-ādhi-sakta (LP), used in connection with a lost thing which had been given in mortgage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिक|अधिकं|अधिकः
adhika (EI 3), intercalary [month].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकाक्षर
adhik-ākṣara (LP), ‘with words in excess’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकपडि
adhika-paḍi (CITD), Sanskrit-Telugu; an extra allowance in food (grain, salt, vegetables and all that is required to prepare a meal, including firewood), sometimes also in money, granted to servants, friends or poor people.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकार|अधिकारः
Adhikāra, cf. Tamil Adigāram (EI 25); same as Adhikārin (SII 1), explained as ‘a magistrate’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारमेलेळुत्तु
adhikāra-mel-el̤̣uttu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; revisional order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरण|अधिकरणं
adhikaraṇa (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28), an office; cf. rājakule='dhi-karaṇasya, apparently referring to an office. See adhikaraṇ-āva-dhāraṇā, ‘official investigation’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 267).<BR> (EI 24), a court or department.<BR> (EI 30), a law-court.<BR> (SITI), a class of law courts; probably, the chief court.<BR> (EI 30, 31), an administrative office or a board of administration.<BR> (EI 31), a district.<BR> (SII 2), same as Adhikārin, a magistrate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरणदण्ड
adhikaraṇa-daṇḍa (SITI), fine imposed by the adhikaraṇa or law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरणलेखक|अधिकरणलेखकः
Adhikaraṇa-lekhaka (EI 30), a scribe pertaining to a law-court or office. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-007" target="_blank">Page-007+ 40</a>]<BR> (HD), the official recorder or scribe [who drew up deeds of sale and the like after having measured the land to be sold]. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 38; Viṣṇu Dh. S., VII, 3.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=006" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकरणिक|अधिकरणिकः
Adhikaraṇika, Ādhikaraṇika (IE 8-1; EI 28), an officer belonging to or in charge of an adhikaraṇa or office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारवर्त्तना
adhikāra-varttanā (SITI), customary payments made to an officer at stipulated periods; probably the same as Sanskrit-Tamil adhikāra-pper̤u, adhikāra-ppŏn, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारिक
Adhikārika, Ādhikārika (IE 8-3; EI 2, 23, 28; CII 4; BL; HD), ‘an officer’; same as Adhikārin, Niyogika, Adhyakṣa, etc., regarded as meaning a minister, magistrate, superintendent, governor or director. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 184.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारिमुख्य
Adhikāri-mukhya (EI 33), explained as ‘the chief minister’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारिन्
Adhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 28; BL), ‘an officer’; same as Ādhikārika; cf. Kannaḍa Věrgaḍě, etc., and Sanskrit Adhyākṣa, meaning a superintendent, governor or director.<BR> (ASLV), explained as ‘a special officer or royal agent’.<BR> (EI 7), explained as ‘a minister’.<BR> (SII 2), explained as ‘a magistrate’.<BR> Cf. Viḍaiy-adhikāri, Viḍaiyil-adhikāri (SITI), an officer issuing royal orders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकृत|अधिकृतः
Adhikṛta (EI 23, 24), ‘an officer’; cf. Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिमहाराज
Adhimahārāja (EI 15), royal title. Cf. Adhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिपति|अधिपतिः
Adhipati (LL), a king; cf. pati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधिपत्र
ādhi-patra (LP), a mortgage^1 bond.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिराज
Adhirāja (IE 8-2), sometimes used as an imperial title, but sometimes as the title of a feudatory. Cf. Adhimahārāja.<BR> (BL), title of a subordinate ruler.<BR> (LL), designation of a supreme king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिराजराज
Adhirājarāja (EI 9), royal title. Cf. Rājarāja, Rājādhirāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिराज्य|अधिराज्यं
adhirājya (EI 24), a realm or kingdom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आधिराज्य|आधिराज्यं
ādhirājya (CII 3), a derivative from the title Adhirāja; supreme sovereignty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिस्थान
adhisthāna, adhiṣṭhāna (CII 1), cf. dharm-ādhisthāna, dharm-ādhiṣṭhāna, ‘the establishment of morality’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिष्ठान|अधिष्ठानं
adhiṣṭhāna (IE 8-3; EI 24, 28, 31; LL), the capital or headquarters of an administrative unit; a city or town; the chief city. See abhisthāna.<BR> (EI 9), probably, residence.<BR> (EI 8), same as sthāna. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-008" target="_blank">Page-008+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 24), cf. adhiṣṭhānam, ‘under the supervision of’.<BR> (SITI), the base of the vimāna in a temple; a seat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=007" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिष्ठानाधिकरण
adhiṣṭhān-ādhikaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 23; BL), administrative office or board at the headquarters of a territorial unit; office of the administrators of a city; the city office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिष्ठायक
Adhiṣṭhāyaka (EI 16), official designation; same as Adhyakṣa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिवास|अधिवासः
adhivāsa, cf. adhivāsa-sakta-cāturvarṇya-samakṣam (LP), ‘in the presence of the people of the four castes living in the vicinity’; cf. adhivāsa-saktīya (LP); neighbours.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्वप
Adhvapa (EI 20), official designation; same as Mārgapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यक्ष|अध्यक्षः
Adhyakṣa (EI 24; CII 4), the head of a department; the superintendent of a department; a superintendent or director; sometimes mentioned in the list of officials (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 80). Cf. Mahādhyakṣa.<BR> (IA 20), explained as the Dūtaka or Ājñapti, i. e. executor of grants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यक्षप्रचार
Adhyakṣa-pracāra (EI 12, 15), a list of superintendents of departments; probably also a notice setting forth the distribution of the Adhyakṣas in various departments and stations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यापक|अध्यापकः
Adhyāpaka (EI 32), a teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्यातम्
a-dhyātam, ‘without any consideration or hesitation’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 239).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययन|अध्ययनं
adhyayana (SII 1), study of the Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययनभट्ट
Adhyayana-bhaṭṭa (IA 12), assistant officiating priest (also called Sādhācārya) at the temple at Rāmeśvaram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययनाङ्ग
adhyayan-āṅga (SITI), same as adhyayana-vṛtti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्ययनवृत्ति
adhyayana-vṛtti (SITI), tax-free land endowed for reciting the Vedas in temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अध्येतृ
adhyetṛ (EI 32), a student.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदि|आदिः
ādi (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिकार
ādikāra (CII 1), an initiator; one who starts a practice or to do a particular deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिकर्तृ|आदिकर्त्तृ
Ādikartṛ (CII 3), ‘an originator’; epithet of the Jain Tīrthaṅkaras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिराज|आदिराजः
Ādirāja (EI 12), an ancient king, e. g., Bharata, Nala, Nahuṣa, etc.; founder of a royal family (Select Inscriptions, pp. 412, 415).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदित्य|आदित्यः
āditya (IE 8-2; EI 33), ending of royal titles like Vikramāditya, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-009" target="_blank">Page-009+ 40</a>] Kramāditya, Mahendrāditya, etc., probably popularised by the Imperial Guptas in the fourth century A. D.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=008" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदित्यकाच
āditya-kāca (EI 32), probably, the jewel called sūryakānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिवराहद्रम्म
ādivarāha-dramma (EI 30; CII 4), name of a coin (dramma) styled after Ādivarāha, i. e. Pratīhāra Bhoja I (c. 836-85 A. D.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अद्रि|अद्रिः
adri (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आद्वलिश
ādvaliśa (IA 17), or dvaliśa; regarded as a word of doubtful meaning; but really, a geographical name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आद्यमाष
ādya māṣa, the original māṣa 5 ratis in weight, later its weight being regarded as 6, 7 or 10 ratis (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 139). See māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
ādya-stamba, ‘covered with original shrubs’, i. e. yielding no revenue income, never cultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=556" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग|अगः
aga (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR> (SII 3), earth or land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगम|आगमं|आगमः
āgama (SII 1), a doctrine; cf. Lākul-āgama (EI 32), the doctrine of Lakula (Lakulīśa). Cf. āgama-samaya.<BR> Cf. s-āgama-nirgama-praveśa (IE 8-5), ‘together with approaches, ingress and egress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगमनिगमदान
āgama-nigama-dāna (LP), tax for importing and exporting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगमार्ग
agamārga (SITI), a variety of dance performed in the presence of the gods in temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगमसमय
āgama-samaya, cf. Lākul-āgama-samaya (EI 32), the tenets of Lakula's doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आगामिन्
āgāmin (IE 8-5; EI 19; SITI), future income, future benefits; one of the 8 kinds of rights in the property; cf. aṣṭa-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगर
agara (EI 19), a corrupt form of agrahāra, often noticed in Tamil inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगरब्रह्मदेय
agara-brahmadeya (SITI), village granted to Brāhmaṇas; also called agara (agrahāra) and brahmadeya. See agara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगरप्प
agara-ppar̤r̤u (SITI), Tamil; same as agara or agrahāra; land granted to Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगसालि
Agasāli (EI 28), a goldsmith; same as Akṣaśālin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आघाट|आघाटः
āghāṭa (EI 16), boundary; cf. āghāṭana, āghāṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आघाटन
āghāṭana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 264, text line 42), same as āghāṭa, boundary; see also āghāṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आघाटी
āghāṭī (EI 23), same as āghāṭa; boundary; see also āghāṭana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अघोष|अघोषः
aghoṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’ [being the number of surds in the Sanskrit alphabet].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्नि|अग्निः
agni (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=009" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निचयन|अग्निचयनः
agni-cayana (EI 32; IA 19), a sacrificial rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निचित्
Agnicit (SII 2), title of a Brāhmaṇa. cf. agni-cayana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निहोत्र|अग्निहोत्रं|अग्निहोत्रः
agnihotra (EI 22; CII 3, 4), offerings to fire; a particular sacrifice, often mentioned as one of the five sacrificial rites (mahāyajña) which are the daily duties of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निहोत्रिन्
Agnihotrin (CII 4), epithet of a Brāhmaṇa performing the agnihotra sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निकार्य|अग्निकार्य्य|अग्निकार्य्यं
agni-kārya (EI 33; SII 3), fire-oblation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निकुल
Agni-kula, ‘a family, the progenitor of which was born from the fire pit of a sage’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 162, for a 12th century ‘Fire family’ in the Nanded District, Maharashtra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निकुण्ड|अग्निकुंड
agni-kuṇḍa (CII 4), fire-pit; an emblem of the worship of the Fire or Sun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निस्कन्ध
agni-skandha (CII 1), masses of fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निष्ठा
agniṣṭhā (SITI), firewood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निस्थितिका
agni-sthitikā, fire-place (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्निष्टोम|अग्निष्टोमः
agniṣṭoma (CII 3), a particular sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्न्याहित
Agnyāhita (EI 15), same as Āhitāgni, ‘a Brāhmaṇa perpetually maintaining and consecrating the sacred fire in his house’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्र|अग्रं|अग्रः
agra (EI 24), same as agra-bhāga; the king's share.<BR> (CII 1), cf. anyatra agreṇa parākrameṇa, ‘without a great effort’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रभाग|अग्रभागः
agra-bhāga (CII 2-1; ML), the principal share; same as agra, agra-pratyāya, the king's share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रभागप्रत्यंश
agrabhāga-pratyaṃśa (CII 2-1), same as agra-bhāga, agra-pratyaṃśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रभृति
agra-bhṛti (CII 1), a superior personage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रधर्मराजिका
agra-dharmarājikā (ML), the chief Dharmarājikā (a stūpa enshrining the relies of the Dharmarāja or Buddha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अगहर
agahara, agāhara, āgahara (Chamba), corruptions of agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहर
Agrahara (EI 24), a collector of the king's share. See agra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहार|अग्रहारः
agrahāra (IE 8-4; EI 30; CII 4; SII 1; HRS; Chamba), rent-free land given to Brāhmaṇas; a rent-free village; a Brāhmaṇa village; sometimes suffixed to names of localities especially in South India. It was primarily, ‘a rent-free village in the possession of Brāhmaṇas’; but there are occasional references [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-011" target="_blank">Page-011+ 40</a>] to dev-āgrahāra (rent-free holding in the possession of a deity), vaiśy-āgrahāra (rent-free holding in the possession of the Vaiśyas), etc.; sometimes spelt agrāhāra (CII 3). See mah-āgrahāra, brahmapurī, caturvedi-maṅgala, etc.; also aṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=010" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारप्रदेयांश
agrahāra-pradey-āṃśa (EI 33), a small rent payable for land granted to Brāhmaṇas and declared rent-free.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारिक
Agrahārika, Āgrahārika (IE 3-8; EI 23; HD; CII 3; etc.), the owner of an agrahāra; sometimes probably, the superintendent of agrahāras; same as Agrahārin. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 127.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारिन्
Agrahārin, Agrahārīṇa (EI 23, 24), the holder of an agrahāra; headman or owner of an agrahāra village. Cf. Agrahārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रहारीणमहत्तर
Agrahārīṇa-mahattara (EI 24), headman among the Agrahārīṇas, i. e. owners of an agrahāra (rent-free village in the possession of Brāhmaṇas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आग्रहायणी
āgrahāyanī (EI 8), Mārgaśīrṣa su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रज|अग्रजः
agraja (EI 23), the elder brother (or cousin); rarely used wrongly in the sense of ‘the eldest son’ (EI 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रजन्मन्
agrajanman (EI 9), same as agraja (q. v.); wrongly used to mean ‘the eldest son’ instead of ‘the elder brother’ (cf. agraja).<BR> (EI 24), a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमहादेवी
Agra-mahādevī (SITI), chief queen of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमहामहिषी
Agra-mahāmahiṣī (IE 8-2), title of a chief queen; cf. Mahiṣī, Agra-mahiṣī, Mahāmahiṣī, Agra-mahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमहिषी
Agra-mahiṣī (IE 8-2; EI 22; LL; ML), designation of the chief queen; cf. Mahiṣī, Agra-mahādevī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रमण्डप
agra-maṇḍapa (SITI), front hall of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रप्र
agra-prasāda, same as tala-vṛtti (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 166, note 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रप्रत्यंश
agra-pratyaṃśa (EI 23; CII 2-1; ML), principal share; same as agra-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रप्रत्याय
agra-pratyāya (EI 23), principal share or income; same as agra-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रशाला
agra-śālā (SII 3), a temple-kitchen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आग्रयण|आग्रयणं|आग्रयणः
āgrayaṇa (EI 7), the first Soma libation at the agniṣṭoma sacrifice; oblation consisting of first-fruits at the end of the rainy season.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रिक
agrika (LP), ‘the previous one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=011" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रिकपाया
agrika-pāyā (LP), original foundation; cf. Gujarātī pāyā, foundation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अग्रोनोमोइ
Agronomoi (IE 8-3), Greek; probably the same as Rajjuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहाड
āhāḍa (EI 1), probably, a quarry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहंवीर
Ahaṃvīra, see Amīra. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 178.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहन्
ahan (CII 3), ‘a day’; used to denote the solar, or more properly civil, day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहार|आहारः
āhāra (IE 8-4; EI 27; CII 1, 3, 4), a district; cf. āharaṇī.<BR> Cf. grām-āhāra (IE 8-4), a group of villages.<BR> (IA 17), cf. s-āhāra in Buddhist literature explained as sa-janapada. Āhāra = [land for] food; cf. bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहरणी
āharaṇī (IE 8-4; EI 16), a district or its subdivision; cf. Hastakavapr-āharaṇī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 109); also cf. āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहारविषय
āhāra-viṣaya (IE 8-4), originally an āhāra, but later a viṣaya; cf. Kheṭak-āhāra-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आहवनीय|आहवनीयः
āhavanīya (EI 32), the sacred fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहि|अहिः
ahi (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहिदण्ड
ahi-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28, 33), professional tax levied from snake-charmers or levy for their maintenance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐडूक|ऐडूकं
aiḍūka, same as eḍūka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐरावत|ऐरावतं|ऐरावतः
airāvata (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; sometimes hastin, etc., are used in this sense though they really mean ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐश्वर्याष्टक
aiśvary-āṣṭaka (EI 33), same as aṣṭa-bhoga (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऐतद
aitada (EI 28), derived from elad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आजिवककासु
ājivaka-kāsu (SITI), same as Tamil āśuva-kkāśu, āśuvikal̤-kāśu, āśuva-kkaḍamai; tax payable by Ājīvakas or for the maintenance of Ājīvaka monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञा
Ājñā (IE 8-3; EI 27; BL; CII 3), an order or command; same as ājñapti or ājñāpti supposed to be connected with giving the order for the drawing up of a charter; person receiving a king's order regarding the preparation of a charter; usually translated as ‘executor of a grant’; standing alone, the word is supposed to indicate the office of the Dūtaka, though the latter seems to have been additionally responsible for giving the donee the possession of the gift land. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 362 (of the Gaṅga year 149) where the words are ājñā mahāmahattara-Śivarmā; also svayam=ājñā (CII, Vol. III, p. 115; Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 19) taken to mean that the king employed no Dūtaka to convey the details of his grant to the local officers, but that he gave the details in person. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-013" target="_blank">Page-013+ 40</a>] The expression sva-mukh-ājñā (literally, the oral order of the king) is also explained in the same way. The suggestion that Ājñādāpaka sometimes occurs as a synonym of Dūtaka is wrong. See Ājñapti, Ājñā-sañcārin, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 143-44.<BR> Cf. Tamil āṇai (EI 23), sign; the insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=012" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञाभोगिक
Ājñā-bhogika (EI 21; BL), Ājñā and Bhogika wrongly made into a single official designation. See Ājñā and Bhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञादापक
Ājñā-dāpaka (BL; HD), wrongly taken as a compound expression meaning an officer (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 161). See Ājñā and Dāpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञाधारक
Ājñādhāraka (ASLV), an executor of the royal order; cf. Ājñā-paripālaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञापरिपालक
Ājñā-paripālaka (ASLV), an executor of the royal order; cf. Ājñā-dhāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञप्ति|आज्ञप्तिः
Ājñapti, Ājñāpti (IE 8-3; EI 24, 27, 30; SII 1; HD), ‘the agency that obtains the command’; the executor of a grant; one who communicates, at the order of the king, the details about a land grant to local officers; probably the same as Dūtaka. Cf. Ājñā; also Tamil Vāy-kkel̤vi, Vāy-kkel̤viyār. See Ind. Ep., pp. 143-44; Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 184; Vol. VIII, p. 146. Cf. Ājñā-sañcārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञासञ्चारिन्
Ājñā-sañcārin (EI 23, 24, 27), same as Ājñapti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञाशतप्रापयितृ
Ājñā-śata-prāpayitṛ (EI 12), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आज्ञात
ājñāta (IA 18), ‘an order’; sañcaritaṃ c=ājñātam, ‘and the command has been communicated or carried into effect.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकालिक
a-kālika (CII 1), ‘not restricted to time’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकार|आकारः
ākāra (CII 1), same as prakāra, a way or kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकर्षक|आकर्षकः
ākarṣaka (EI 5), probably, the extent [of a piece of land].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाश|आकाशं|आकाशः
ākāśa (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशमुखिन्
Ākāśamukhin (ASLV), epithet of certain Śaiva ascetics, also called Ākāśavāsin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशपातालोत्पत्ति
ākāśa-pātāl-otpatti (EI 30), fruits and roots produced in a piece of land. Cf. ākāś-otpatti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशवाणी
ākāśa-vāṇī (IA 11), an unearthly voice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशवासिन्
Ākāśa-vāsin (ASLV), same as Ākāśamukhin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आकाशोत्पत्ति
ākāś-otpatti (HRS), ‘produce of the sky’; fruits; wrongly regarded by some as the same as bhūta-vāta-pratyāya (q. v.). See ākāśa-pātāl-otpalli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अखण्डदीप
akhaṇḍa-dīpa (EI 30), a lamp to be perpetually burnt before a deity in a temple, the installation of which was regarded as a meritorious act; same as nandā-dīpa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=013" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अखसालि
Akhasāli (EI 7), same as Akṣaśālin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चिद्ग्राह्य
akiñcid-grāhya (HRS), same as akiñcit-kara, ‘free from tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्कर
akiñcit-kara (HRS), same as akiñcit-grāhya, ‘free from tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कम्
akkam (SII 3; SITI), Tamil; name of a coin; one-twelfth of a kāśu; a mint (cf. akka-śālā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कशाला
akka-śālā (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; a mint; cf. akkaśālai-vari (SITI), charges payable to the mint for minting coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कसालवरु
akkasālavaru (CITD), cf. Telugu agasāli, akkasāla, akasālě; also Kannaḍa agasālavāḍu; a goldsmith or his workshop.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कसालिग
Akkasāliga (EI 7), a goldsmith; same as Akṣaśālika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकृति
akṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्ष|अक्षं|अक्षः
akṣa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटल|अक्षपटलः
akṣapaṭala (BL), the department of records and accounts. See Akṣapaṭalika, etc. Cf. Mahāsāndhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलादाय
akṣapaṭal-ādāya (IA 18), levy for the maintenance of the akṣapaṭala department or the Paṭvārī. Cf. akṣapaṭala-prastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलाधिकृत|अक्षपटलाधिकृतः
Akṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (CII 3; HD; BL), an officer of the akṣapaṭala department or the officer in charge of it; same as Akṣapaṭalika, etc. See CII, Vol. III, p. 257; Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 301, 397-98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलाधिपति
Akṣapaṭal-ādhipati (BL), the head of the akṣapaṭala department; same as Akṣapaṭalin, etc.; also called Akṣapāla (cf. karaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलाध्यक्ष
Akṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa (HD), the superintendent of records and accounts. Cf. Arthaśāstra, II. 7; Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 143.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलप्रस्थ
akṣapaṭala-prastha (IA 18; HRS), contributions paid by the villagers at the rate of a prastha of grain (probably, per standard measure) for the expenses of the akṣapaṭala department (probably for the maintenance of the Paṭvārī). Cf. akṣapaṭal-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलिक
Akṣapaṭalika (EI 30; CII 4; HD; BL), same as Akṣapaṭal-ādhipati, officer in charge of accounts and records. Akṣapaṭala means ‘accounts office’ (Stein) or ‘records office’ (Bühler). There is Grām-ākṣapaṭalika in the Harṣacarita (VII, para. 2) probably meaning the Paṭvārī, and a section on the superintendent of the akṣapaṭala in the Arthaśāstra (II. 7). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, p. 128; Vol. IX, p. 305. Cf. Mahākṣapaṭalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आक्षपटलिक|आक्षपटलिकः
Ākṣapaṭalika (HD), same as Akṣapaṭalika; officer in charge of the accounts and records office. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, pp. 316, 318.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=014" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षपटलिन्
Akṣapaṭalin (EI 19; BL), same as Akṣapaṭal-ādhipati, Akṣapaṭalika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षर|अक्षरं|अक्षरः
akṣara, cf. hast-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a deed for borrowing money; also kṛṣṇ-ākṣarāṇi (LP), the record containing a censure; also ujjval-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a certificate of good conduct; also viśuddh-ākṣarāṇi (LP), an acknowledgement. Cf. uttar-ākṣarāṇi (LP), same as Marāṭhī utarāi; probably, a deed by which land is given at a favourable rent to merchants, etc., who helped the government with money.<BR> Cf. guṇ-ākṣara, also called guṇa-patra; see also gupt-ākṣara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षरपल्लि
akṣarapalli (IA 11), the system of writing numbers by syllables; name applied to the system of writing numbers as found in inscriptions before the popularisation of the decimal system, though the symbols employed in the Brāhmī inscriptions do not appear to be akṣaras in all cases.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षशालिक
Akṣaśālika (EI 29), same as Akṣaśālin, etc.; a goldsmith.<BR> (HD), explained as ‘an officer in charge of the gambling-hall’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षशालिन्
Akṣaśālin (EI 29; BL), same as Akṣaśālika, etc.; a gold-smith; from Telugu-Kannaḍa Akkasālě (EI 3), Agasāli, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 173.<BR> (HD), explained as ‘an officer in charge of the gambling hall’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षता
akṣatā (IA 11), probably, rice grains mixed with red powder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षततृतीया
akṣata-tṛtīyā (EI 24), same as akṣaya-tṛtīyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षौहिणी
akṣauhiṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षावाप|अक्षावापः
Akṣāvāpa (HD), superintendent of gambling. Cf. Hist. Dharm., Vol. II, p. 1216; Vol. III, p. 112.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनी
akṣayanī, akṣayaṇī (EI 32), modified forms of akṣaya-nīvī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनिधिधर्म
akṣayanidhi-dharma (EI 12), same as akṣayanīvī-dharma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीका
akṣayanīkā (EI 30), corrupt form of akṣaya-nīvikā, a perpetual endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीवि
akṣaya-nīvi, akṣaya-nīvī (CII 3, 4; HRS), a permanent endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीवीधर्म
akṣayanīvī-dharma (EI 29), the nature of a permanent endowment; also called akṣayanidhi-dharma (EI 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयनीविका
akṣaya-nīvikā (EI 24, 30), same as akṣaya-nīvī; a perpetual endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=015" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयपूर्णमासी
akṣaya-pūrṇamāsī (EI 23), probably, the same as Māgha su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षयतृतीया
akṣaya-tṛtīyā (EI 4, 23; CII 4; IA 18; BL), same as Vaiśākha su-di 3; see akṣata-tṛtīyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षि
akṣi (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षीणिन्
akṣīṇin (IE 8-5; EI 19; SITI), actual or fixed income; regarded as one of the eight rights of ownership. Cf. aṣṭa-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षोटभङ्ग
akṣoṭa-bhaṅga (HRS), same as khoṭa-bhaṅga and ukkoṭa-bhaṅga (Abhidhānarājendra, s. v. parihāra). Cf. utkoṭa and bhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलगच्चु
al̤ag-accu (SITI), Tamil; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलम्
alam (CII 1), ‘capable’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलम्बन|आलंबनं|आलम्बनं
ālambana (LL), the base stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवण
alavaṇa (IA 19), probably a Sanskritised form of ar̤uvaṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलय|आलयं|आलयः
ālaya, cf. ālai (SII 3), a temple; a contraction of dev-ālaya. Cf. āyatana, bhavana, pura, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलेपन
ālepana (SITI), anointing; coating the image with unguent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलि|आलिः
āli (Chamba), wet land, irrigable land; also called kohlī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलिनी
alinī (EI 26), ‘a swarm of bees’; female Jain devotees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलीपक
alīpaka, also read as alīyaka (EI 32), a fiscal expression of uncertain import; see nidhān-ālīpaka. The word alipaka means ‘a bee’. Thus ālipaka may refer to the right over wax, bee-hives, and honey. Alīyaka, from ali, ‘a bee’, would mean the same thing^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलिय
Al̤iya (EI 15), an official title. Cf. alīpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलीयक
alīyaka, cf. alīpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्लवाट
allavāṭa (IE 8-8; EI 30), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्पभाण्डता
alpa-bhāṇḍatā (CII 1), moderation in the hoarding of wealth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्पमिरै
alpam-ir̤ai (SITI) Sanskrit-Tamil; a minor tax payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमा
amā (EI 21), abbreviation of amāvāsyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
ā-mā, abbreviation of ādya-māṣa (i.e. the original māṣa of 5 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=556" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमच
Amaca (HD), Prakrit Amacca = Sanskrit Amātya (q. v.). Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol VIII, pp. 71, 73.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमलसारक
amalasāraka (CII 4), the circular fluted disc on the spire of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमलिमन्
amaliman (EI 12), purity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमान्त|अमान्तः
amānta (CII 3), the technical name for the scheme of the lunar months in Southern India, according to which a month ends with the new-moon day, and the bright fortnight precedes the dark. According to Fleet, it is always this arrangement [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-017" target="_blank">Page-017+ 40</a>] that is taken for calculation in astronomical works, though, even in Southern India, the arrangement was not applied to the Śaka years, for the civil reckoning, till between 804 and 866 A. D.; on the other hand, according to him, even in Northern India, this arrangement was used in Nepal with the years of the Newār era, though it was abandoned there when the Newār era was followed by the Vikrama era in its northern variety. For its prevalence in Indonesia, see Sel. Ins., p. 470.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=016" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमर|अमरः
amara (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’ [being the original number of the gods].<BR> (SITI; ASLV), land or revenue granted by a ruler to his retainers for military service; land assigned to military officers who were entitled to collect only certain revenues with the obligation to raise a contingent of army ready for service whenever called upon and also to pay tribute to the king; same as amara-māgaṇi. Cf. Amara-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमरमागणि
amara-māgaṇi (SITI; ASLV), same as amara; estate given to an Amara-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमरनायक
Amara-nāyaka (EI 16; SITI; ASLV), a retainer chief enjoying amara, i. e. land or its revenue, for military service to be rendered to his master.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमारिरूढि
amāri-rūḍhi (EI 11), Jain; an edict for the non-slaughter [of animals].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमात्य|अमात्यः
Amātya (IE 8-3; EI 28, 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD; LL), a minister; sometimes, officer in charge of a district; explained as deś-ādi-kārya-nirvāhaka; in some cases, called Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally. Cf. Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 114, note 150. See Mahāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमात्यसभा
amātya-sabhā (EI 32), same as mantri-pariṣad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमावास्या
amāvāsyā, cf. ṣaṣṭhī amāvāsyā, caturthī-amāvāsyā, nava rātri-amāvāsyā, mahānavamī-amāvāsyā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बोक
ambaka (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बाकपीलिका
ambā-kapīlikā, same as āmra-pipīlikā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बर|अंबर|अंबरं|अम्बरं|अम्बरः
ambara (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्भोनिधि|अम्भोनिधिः
ambhonidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; cf. sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बिकाजनिक
ambikā-janika (CII 1), ‘mothers and wives’; women in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बुधि|अम्बुधिः
ambudhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बुराशि|अम्बुराशिः
amburāśi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंहति|अंहतिः
aṃhati, also spelt aṃhiti (EI 4), a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=017" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आमि
āmi (EI 28), same as Arabic amīn; an officer of the revenue or judicial department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमीर
Amīra (IA 11), Indianised form of Arabic Amīr; often found in the form Hammīra in Indian records and rarely as Hambīra, Haṃvīra and Ahaṃvīra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 178).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्म
amma (EI 24), literally ‘the mother’; a village goddess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्मनगन्धवारण
Ammanagandhavāraṇa (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; ‘the musk-elephant of the father’; subordinate title; also found in the form Appanagandhavāraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्नात
āmnāta (EI 12), cf. śrī-Mālava-gaṇ-āmnāte praśaste Kṛta-saṃjñite; explained as ‘authoritatively laid down’ or ‘constantly used’; cf. sthiti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्नाय|आम्नायः
āmnāya (CII 4), a Jain sub-sect.<BR> (IA 20), same as kula or kula-krama; generations, successions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्रपिपीलिका
āmra-pipīlikā, cf. aṃbā-kapīlikā (EI 2; CII 1), usually interpreted as ‘the mother-ant’; but really, big red ants generally living in large numbers on mango trees. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 99-100.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आम्रेडन|आम्रेडनं
āmreḍana (EI 12), repetition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमृतगण
amṛta-gaṇa (SII 12), same as Tamil amirta-gaṇattār (SITI), members of the committee for the management of village affairs; members in charge of the cash-receipts of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमृतपडि
amṛta-paḍi, cf. Tamil amuda-ppaḍi (SII 1; SITI), raw rice; food offering to a deity; (CITD), paḍi is an allowance in food (i. e. all the necessary commodities to prepare a meal) and sometimes also in money and amuda-paḍi is an endowment often made in favour of a deity for daily offering of food as bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमृतयोग|अमृतयोगः
amṛta-yoga (EI 9), a particular time regarded as auspicious.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंश|अंशः
aṃśa, a small territorial unit (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 297, text line 26).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशबृहद्भोगिक
Aṃśa-bṛhadbhogika (IE 8-3; EI 28), probably, the shareholder of a big jāgīr. See Bhāgika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशगण
aṃśa-gaṇa (EI 33); a class of metres; cf. mātrā-gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशपति
Aṃśapati (EI 30), co-sharer of a gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अंशुकभाण्डारकरण
aṃśuka-bhāṇḍāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of clothes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमुकाकसक्त
amukāka-sakta (LP), ‘belonging to a certain man’, sakta being often used for satka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=018" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाच्छेद्य|अनाछेद्य
anācchedya (IE 8-5), ‘uncurtailable’; ‘not to be resumed’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 267, note 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनादेश्य
anādeśya (EI 12), ‘not to be pointed out (or, ordered)’; epithet of gift land; same as anirdeśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाहार्य|अनाहार्य्य
anāhārya (IE 8-5), ‘unresumbale’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आणक|आणकः
āṇaka, see anna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनक|अनकः
anaka, anikā (EI 20), Prakrit suffixes to male and female names respectively, known from early South Indian inscriptions; same as annaka, annikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनल|अनलं|अनलः
anala (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आनन्दनिधि
ānanda-nidhi (EI 24), a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आनन्दथु|आनंदथु|आनन्दथुः
ānandathu (EI 12), joy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनन्त|अनंत|अनन्तं|अनन्तः
ananta (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनन्तनिधि
ananta-nidhi (EI 24), mistake for ānanda-nidhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आनन्तर्य|आनंतर्यं|आनन्तर्य्य
ānantarya (CII 1), quickness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनासेध्य
anāsedhya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 267, note 4), free from legal restraints (e. g. kāl-āsedha, ‘limitation of time’; sthān-āsedha ‘confinement to a place’; pravās-āsedha, ‘prohibition of removal or departure’; and karm-āsedha ‘restriction from employment’); epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाथसंरक्षण
anātha-saṃrakṣaṇa (EI 23), ‘protection of the helpless’, mentioned as the purpose of a donation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आणत्ति
āṇatti (SITI), Tamil; Sanskrit ājñapti; an executor of order; royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनावास
anāvāsa (CII 1), ‘habitation which is quite unsuitable for one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्धारुवा
andhāruvā, āndhāruvā (IE 8-5; EI 12), variant readings of arthāruvā or ārthāruvā (q. v.); Od̤iyā name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आन्ध्रदण्ड
Āndhra-daṇḍa (IE 8-5), a tax; cf. Turuṣka-daṇḍa and Tigul̤a-daṇḍa. There is also reference to ‘an assembly of Āndhra-daṇḍa’, the meaning of which is doubtful unless daṇḍa is taken here in the sense of ‘an army’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अण्डिका
aṇḍikā, weight equal to (1/4) of a māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48); same as the copper paṇa (ibid., Vol. II, p. 7); also called dhānaka and regarded as equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or to (1/12)th suvarṇa (ibid., p. 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनेकान्तमत
anekānta-mata (SII 1), same as syādvāda-mata (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनेसाहिणिवेर्गड
Aněsāhiṇi-věrgaḍa (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12), Kannaḍa; official designation; same as Sanskrit Gaja-sādhanik-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्ग|अंग|अंगं|अङ्गं|अङ्गः
aṅga (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-020" target="_blank">Page-020+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 15), an abbreviation of aṅga-bhoga; cf. gātra (IA 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=019" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गभोग
aṅga-bhoga (EI 17; CITD), often associated with raṅga-bhoga as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga, usually explained as ‘decorations and illuminations of a deity’. That aṅga-bhoga means decoration of the image of a deity is clear from the fact that a queen is known to have received a village as an agrahāra for her aṅga-bhoga, i. e. as her pin-money (Bomb. Gaz., Vol. I, Part ii, p. 448). Sometimes the land granted for the aṅga-bhoga of a deity came to be known as the deity's aṅga-bhoga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 182); cf. aṅga, same as gātra (IA 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गडसिद्धाय
aṅgaḍa-siddhāya (CITD), Telugu-Sanskrit; fixed revenue from shops.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गदेवता
aṅga-devatā (SITI), attendant deity of a superior god; same as parivāra-devatā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गज|अंगज|अङ्गजं|अङ्गजः
Aṅgaja (EI 16), same as the god Kāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गमणि
aṅga-maṇi (SITI), property owned by a woman; cf. aṅga-maṇi-dravya (SITI), dowry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गनिगूहक
Aṅga-nigūhaka (BL), an official designation of uncertain import; probably, a kind of spies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गार|अंगार|अंगारं|अंगारः|अङ्गारः
aṅgāra, aṅgāraka, cf. a-carm-āṅgāraka (IE 8-5; EI 15); charcoal for cooking, which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरचना
aṅga-racanā (HA), adorning of the various limbs of an image of the Jina with marks of sandal paste or leaves of gold, silver, etc., and with additional ornaments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरक
Aṅgaraka (SII 11-1), corruption of Aṅgarakṣa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गारकी
aṅgārakī (IA 26), same as ba-di 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरक्ष
Aṅgarakṣa, Aṅgarakṣaka (IE 8-3; EI 15, 29; SITI), body-guard; the king's body-guard, or the head of the body guards.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरङ्गभोग
aṅga-raṅga-bhoga (EI 23; SII 1), decorations and illuminations of a deity; various kinds of enjoyment provided for a deity; sometimes explained as ‘worship to include all kinds of enjoyments’ (SITI). Cf. aṅga-bhoga-raṅga-bhoga, raṅg-āṅga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरङ्गभोगवैभव
aṅga-raṅga-bhoga-vaibhava (EI 3; SII 1; SITI), enjoyments of all kinds provided for a deity; same as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गरङ्गवैभोग
aṅga-raṅga-vaibhoga (EI 3; SII 1; SITI), same as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga, i. e. aṅga-bhoga and raṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=020" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गशाला
aṅga-śālā (SITI), same as aṅka-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गवैद्य
Aṅga-vaidya (SITI), same as Tamil Aṅga-vavicciyar; a physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आङ्गीकरणिक
Āṅgīkaraṇika (IE 8-3), officer in charge of administering oaths in a court of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गुल|अंगुल|अंगुलः|अङ्गुलः
aṅgula, aṅguli (IE 8-6), a linear measure equal to the breadth of the middle finger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गुलि|अंगुलि|अंगुलिः|अङ्गुलिः
aṅguli (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’; sometimes used to indicate ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिकेतोस्
Aniketŏs (IE 8-2), Greek; royal title; ‘unopposed’; translated into Prakrit as Apadihata (Sanskrit Apratihata).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिमेषानोकह
animeṣ-ānokaha (EI 4), same as sura-druma, i. e. kalpa-vṛkṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिवर्तकनिवर्तयितृ
Anivartaka-nivartayitṛ (CII 4), ‘repeller of the unrepellable’; title of a ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनिवृत्ति
anivṛtti (LP), anxiety.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनियत|अनियतं
aniyata, cf. niyat-āniyata (IE 8-5); occasional taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनियुक्त|अनियुक्तः
aniyukta (IA 9), cf. niyukt-āniyukta-rājapuruṣa; probably refers to officials of the king, who were not actually appointed by the government, but occupied posts by virtue of heredity or election.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्जष्टसभा
añjaṣṭa-sabhā, añjaṣṭa-śattu-sabhai (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; village committee of five or eight members. Cf. pañca-kula and aṣṭa-kula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्जुवण्णम्
añjuvaṇṇam (SITI; EI 35), Tamil; Sanskrit pañca-varṇa; the five artisan classes; called hañjamāna in Kannaḍa inscriptions; sometimes regarded as a form of Persian anjuman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्क|अंक|अंकः|अङ्कः
aṅka (IA 19), a name, appellation^1 or biruda.<BR> (IE 7-1-12; CII 4), ‘nine’.<BR> Cf. aṅke, aṅkena, aṅkataḥ (IA 15), ‘in figures’.<BR> Cf. aṅka, abbreviation of Telugu-Kannaḍa aṅkakār̤a; same as Sanskrit gaṇḍa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 270), ‘a hero, champion or warrior’. See aṅkakāra.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्कदण्डखण्डन
aṅka-daṇḍa-khaṇḍana, translated as ‘faults, fines and divisions’; cf. pañch-āṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्ककार
aṅkakāra (EI 3, 4), a champion; same as Telugu-Kannaḍa aṅkakār̤a, sometimes explained as ‘a soldier or warrior who took a vow to defend his master and fight in the latter's cause to death’ (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34). See aṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्कशाला
aṅka-śālā (SITI), probably, the place where duels were fought; cf. aṅga-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=021" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्न|अन्नं|अन्नः
anna, Anglicised form of āṇaka; (1/16)th of a rupee (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 142).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्नक
annaka, annikā, cf. anaka, anikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अण्णनसिंह
Aṇṇanasiṃha (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa; ‘the lion of the brother’; a subordinate title. Cf. Ayyanasiṃha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्त|अंत|अन्तं|अन्तः
anta (IE 8-4; CII 1), a state beyond the borders of one's territories, or a bordering district; also its people; cf. pratyanta.<BR> (CII 1), cf. Anta-mahāmātra, officer employed in districts bordering on the frontiers of one's kingdom.<BR> (EI 3), a neighbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःकर
antaḥ-kara (CII 4), explained as ‘excise duty’; probably, ‘internal revenue’ or revenue income; same as antar-āya, antar-ādāya, abhyantar-ādāya, etc.; cf. antaḥ-kara-viṣṭika (EI 6), antara (EI 15), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःप्रतीहार
Antaḥ-pratīhāra (IE 8-3), officer in charge of defending the back gate of the palace or of the palace-gates as distinguished from the gates of the capital city.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःपुर|अन्तःपुरं
antaḥpura, cf. karaṇa (LP); the royal harem.<BR> (ML), the household; same as avarodhana in Aśoka's edicts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःपुराध्यक्ष|अन्तःपुराध्यक्षः
Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3; EI 13; SII 11-2), superintendent of the royal harem; same as Āntaḥpurika, Stryadhyakṣa, etc., and Sanskrit-Kannaḍa Antaḥpura-věrgaḍě (IE 8-3); sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Mahāpasāyita, Hěri-Lāl̤a-Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin, Maně-věrgaḍě, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आन्तःपुरिक
Āntaḥpurika (EI 13, 14, 18, 19, 23; HD), officer in charge of the royal harem; cf. Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःपुरमहामात्र
Antaḥpura-mahāmātra (HD), officer in charge of the royal harem, mentioned in the Masulipatam plates of Amma II (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276). Cf. Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra of Rock Edict XII of Aśoka (CII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तःसिद्धिक
antaḥ-siddhika (CII 4), same as abhyantara-siddhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तमहामात्र
Anta mahāmātra (IE 8-3; CII 1), executive officers in charge of the bordering districts of an empire and probably not ambassadors at the courts of neighbouring kings. Cf. Antapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तपाल|अन्तपालः
Antapāla (EI 9), frontier guard; explained by some as ‘an officer in charge of the boundaries’ (HD). Cf. Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (one of the 18 tīrthas); II. 21; V, 1; Kāmandaka, XII. 5; Mālavikāgnimitra, Act I. See Anta-mahāmātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=022" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तर|अंतर|अन्तरं
antara (CII 1), a period of time.<BR> (EI 15), name of a tax; cf. antar-ādāya, antaḥ-kara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरा|अंतरा
antarā (CII 1), ‘in the interval’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरादाय
antar-ādāya (CII 4), explained as ‘excise duty’; but same as antaḥ-kara, abhyantar-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तराल|अंतरालं|अन्तरालं
antarāla (EI 1), part of a temple; cf. antarāla-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरालमण्डप
antarāla-maṇḍapa (SITI), portion of a temple connecting the garbha-gṛha and the mukha-maṇḍapa; also called ardha-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरङ्ग|अन्तरंग|अन्तरङ्गः
Antaraṅga (IE 8-3; BL), explained as ‘a privy councillor or a physician’, though the same person is known to be called Rāja-vaidya (i. e. the royal physician) and Antaraṅga; probably a private secretary; but mentioned along with Vaiśvāsika (EI 3); regarded by some as a class of royal servants very intimate with the king, probably the same as Ābhyantara (HD). Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 286; Vol. XII, p. 99.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आन्तरावड्डि
āntarāvaḍḍi (IE 8-5; EI 12; 33), a variant reading of āturāvaḍḍi (q. v.); name of a tax; cf. rintakābaḍḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरविनियोग
antara-viniyoga (SITI), individual share to make up the shortage in the total revenue occasioned by the grant of exemption of antar-āya or ul̤vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तराय|अंतरायः|अन्तरायः
antar-āya (EI 22, 23; SII 1, 2), explained as ‘a tax’, ‘revenue’ or ‘a kind of revenue’; same as antar-ādāya; also explained as internal revenue or taxes levied by local bodies, called ul̤vari in Tamil (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरायक्काशु
antarāya-kkāśu, antarāya-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; explained as ‘internal taxes or minor taxes like the profession tax, etc., payable to the village assembly’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरिका
antarikā (CII 1), a period of time passed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरिक्ष|अंतरिक्षं|अन्तरिक्षं
antarikṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरीप|अन्तरीपं|अंतरीपः|अन्तरीपः
antarīpa (EI 12), an island.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तर्वंशिक|अन्तर्वंशिकः
Antarvaṃśika (HD), officer in charge of the inner apartments or harem. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (mentioned among the 18 tīrthas); Kādambarī (para. 88); Daśakumāracarita, III; cf. Antarveśika in the Amarakośa, Kṣatriya-varga, 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तेवासिन्
Antevāsin (LL), a male pupil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तेवासिनी
Antevāsinī (EI 25; LL), a female pupil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुबन्ध|अनुबंधः|अनुबन्धः
anubandha (CII 1), same as krama, order.<BR> (SITI), help.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुभवन
anubhavana (IA 18), ‘the time or period of office [of a person]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=023" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुभोगप्प
anubhoga-ppar̤r̤-ŏl̤̣ugu (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; renewal of title deeds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुचित
anucita (SITI), evil; damage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यै
anudhyai (IE 8-2), ‘to meditate’, etc.; ‘to favour’, etc.; cf. anudhyāya (IE 8-2), ‘having favoured’; also Svāmi-Mahāsena-Mātṛgaṇ-ānudhyāt-ābhiṣikta (IE 8-2), ‘favoured and anointed [as king] by the lord Mahāsena and the Mothers’; also anudadhyuḥ (IE 8-2), same as anujagṛhuḥ, ‘[they] favoured’. See anudhyāna; also pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यान
anudhyāna (IE 8-2), same as anugraha; favour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यानरत
anudhyāna-rata (IE 8-2), see pād-ānudhyāna-rata, ‘engaged in meditating on the feet of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्यात
anudhyāta (IE 8-2), see pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुध्येय
anudhyeya (IE 8-2), same as anugrāhya; ‘to be favoured’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुदिवसम्
anudivasam (CII 1), daily.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुदृश्
anudṛś, cf. anudarśayanti (EI 15), ‘inform [as follows]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुगजीवित
anuga-jīvita, spelt in Kannaḍa as aṇuga-jīvita or aṇuṃga-jīvita (SII 11-1), a fief held by a king's subordinate for his maintenance; similar to bīl̤a-vṛtti, bīl̤-ānuvṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुग्रह|अनुग्रहः
anugraha (IE 8-2), same as anudhyāna; favour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुग्रहस्थितिपात्र
anugraha-sthiti-pātra (IE 8-5), same as sthiti-pātra or ācāra-sthiti-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुग्राह्य
anugrāhya (IE 8-2), same as anudhyeya, ‘to be favoured’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुज|अनुजं|अनुजः
anuja (Ep. Ind., Vol XXXIII, p. 271), a younger cousin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुलोम|अनुलोमः
anuloma (CII 4), name of a kind of marriage, in which the bride belongs to a lower social order than the bridegroom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुनिध्याप्ति
anunidhyāpti, cf. anunijhapayati (CII 1); explanation or exhortation; cf. nidhyāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुप्रतिपत्ति
anupratipatti, cf. dharm-ānupratipatti (CII 1), practice of morality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुपूर्वी
anupūrvī, cf. saṃvatsaraḥ dvitīyaḥ hemanta-pakṣaḥ caturthaḥ lithir=daśamī anay=ānupūrvyā. Cf. pūrvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुरूप|अनुरूपः
anurūpa (CII 1), adequate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुसंयान
anusaṃyāna (CII 1), a tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुसन्धान|अनुसंधान|अनुसंधानं|अनुसन्धानं
anusandhāna, recitation (A. R. Ep., 1959-60, No. B. 335).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुशास्
anuśās (CII 1), ‘to inculate’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुशासन|अनुशासनं
anuśāsana, anuśāsanā (CII 1), same as anuśasti, inculcation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुशस्ति
anuśasti (CII 1), inculcation, instruction; same as anuśāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुसेनापति
Anusenāpati (EI 18), probably, a subordinate of the Senāpati (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=024" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुष्टुभ्
anuṣṭubh (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुतार
anutāra (SITI), protection, guardianship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुत्पन्नदानसमुद्ग्राहक
Anutpanna-dāna-samudgrāhaka, an official title (Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 221-22); officer engaged in the forcible collection of unrealised dāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुत्तर|अनुत्तरं
anuttara (EI 18), penance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवह्
anuvah, cf. anuvahamānaka (EI 15), literally, ‘flowing on’; but actually, ‘ever-prospering’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवर्त्तना|अनुवर्तना
anuvarttanā (SITI), a class of contingent dues which come under the head varttanā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुविधा
anuvidhā (CII 1), ‘to conform to’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवृत्ति|अनुवृत्तिः
anuvṛtti, same as vṛtti; cf. bīl̤a-vṛtti, bīl̤-ānuvṛtti (SII 11-1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्वय|अन्वयः
anvaya (EI 33; SII 1), a [spiritual] race; a Jain sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यजात
anya-jāta (HRS), accidental revenue; one of the three kinds of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यत्
anyat, ‘another thing’ (Ind. Ep., p. 133, note 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यथा
anyathā (LP), ‘quite changed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्यत्र
anyatra (CII 1), ‘excluding’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपभार
apabhāra (EI 8), a burden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपचार|अपचारः
apacāra (IE 8-5), same as aparādha; cf. daś-āpacāra (EI 15), same as daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपदान|अपदानं
apadāna, cf. dharm-āpadāna (CII 1); a noble deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपग्रथ
apagratha (CII 1), same as upaghāta; injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपकृष्ट|अपकृष्टं|अपकृष्टः
apakṛṣṭa (CII 1), distant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आपण|आपणः
āpaṇa (IE 8-5), a shop.<BR> (CII 4), a market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आपान|आपानं
āpāna (EI 2; CII 1), a watering station or shed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपराध|अपराधः
aparādha, see daś-āparādha (IE 8-5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरपक्ष|अपरपक्षः
apara-pakṣa (IA 16), used to indicate ‘the dark fortnight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरिगोध
aparigodha (CII 1), same as aparibodha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरिपन्थ्य
aparipanthya (IE 8-5), ‘not to be troubled’; an epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपसरक
apasaraka (EI 1), probably, a porch or portico.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपत्य|अपत्यं
apatya (CII 1), descendants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपवाह|अपवाहः
apavāha (CII 1), the act of carrying away [as a prisoner].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपवरक|अपवरकः
apavaraka, cf. Prakrit ovaraka (EI 20; LL), a cell.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपविञ्छ्
apaviñch, cf. apaviñchya (EI 15), ‘having separated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपोहन|अपोहनं
apohana (SITI), waste or uncultivated; cf. Tamil agovana, waste land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=025" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रचराज
Apracarāja (IE 8-2, 8-3), Prakrit; Sanskrit Apratyagrāja (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रदा
apradā (EI 15) ‘[gift land] not to be alienated’; same as nīvī; sometimes used as an epithet of akṣaya-nīvī<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रदाधर्म
apradā-dharma (EI 15), custom regarding inalienable gift land; same as nīvī-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रहत|अप्रहतं
aprahata (EI 15), uncultivated; same as khila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रहर्तृ
aprahartṛ (CII 1), ‘one who observes or maintains’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रतिहत
Apratihata, see Aniketos.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रतिकर|अप्रतिकरः
apratikara (HRS), explained as ‘without the right of alienation’; ‘without yield of revenue’; but cf. pratikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रतिष्ठापित
apratiṣṭhāpita (ML), non-interred.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रत्यग्राज
Apratyagrāja, ‘having no rival among kings’; feudatory title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आप्तक्रिय
āptakriya (IA 18), a trusty agent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आप्तोर्याम|आप्तोर्यामः
āptoryāma (CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपूर्व|अपूर्वः|अपूर्व्व|अपूर्व्वं
apūrva, cf. apūrva-Brāhmaṇa (IA 18), a new Brāhmaṇa who was not fed on a previous occasion and is not to be fed again.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपूर्विन्
apūrvin, apūri (SITI), a Brāhmaṇa well-versed in the Vedas on a visit to holy shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रधन|अपुत्रधनं
aputra-dhana (IE 8-5; EI 25; CII 4), confiscation of the property of one dying without leaving a son or an heir.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रिकाधन
aputrikā-dhana (EI 3; CII 4; HRS), same as aputra-dhana; the property of persons who died sonless, which the king could confiscate; escheat of the property of females.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रिकद्रव्य
aputrika-dravya (EI 20), escheat property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराध्
ārādh (CII 1), ‘to attain’; cf. svargam=ārādhayantu; also ārāddha (CII 1), ‘obtained’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराध्य
Ārādhya (EI 15), ‘the worshipful one’; title of certain Śaivite Brāhmaṇas of Karṇāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरघट्ट|अरघट्टः
araghaṭṭa (EI 10, 14, 22), a water-drawing machine; a well with a water-wheel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरक्षाधिकृत|आरक्षाधिकृतः
Ārakṣ-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3); cf. Prakrit Ārakh-ādhikata (EI 2), a police officer; a magistrate looking after the maintenance of law and order, or the chief of the king's body-guards; same as Ārakṣika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरक्षिक|आरक्षिकः
Ārakṣika (EI 10), cf. Prakrit Ārakhiya (EI 2), a police officer; same as Ārakṣ-ādhikṛta, and also Talāra (q. v.) and Daṇḍapāśika (q. v.); cf. IHQ, December 1960, p. 266.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराम|आरामः
ārāma (LL), a park.<BR> (ML), a grove or monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=026" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरामिक|आरामिकः
ārāmika (LL), a gardener.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरण्य|अरण्यं|अरण्यः
araṇya (IE 8-5), a jungle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरण्यक|आरण्यकः
Āraṇyaka (LL), a Buddhist hermit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरति|आरतिः
ārati, ārti (EI 1), a lamp; same as ārātrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरात्रिक|आरात्रिकं
ārātrika (SII 1), same as nīrājana; cf. maṅgal-ārātrika (EI 4), ‘a lamp used in waving before an idol’; also the rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्चा
ārcā (EI 24), the image of a god; cf. arcā, adoration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चादेश
arcā-deśa (EI 24), an object of adoration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनाभोग
arcanā-bhoga (EI 23), offerings to be made to a deity at the time of worship.<BR> (SII 3, 12; SITI), land set apart for meeting the expenses of worship (arcanā) in the temple; an endowment created for conducting worship; same as arcanā-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनाविभवकाणि
arcanā-vibhava-kāṇi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; rent-free land granted to temple priests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनावृत्ति
arcanā-vṛtti (SII 3; SITI); see arcanā-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धचन्द्र|अर्द्धचन्द्रः|अर्धचन्द्रः
ardha-candra (SITI), literally, ‘half-moon’; a part of the tiruvāśi; a variety of ornament.<BR> (SII 2), the arch of an aureola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धजाम
ardha-jā(yā)ma (SII 13), midnight; midnight service in a temple; cf. ardhajāma-ppur̤am (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; land set apart for conducting the midnight worship in temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धकाकिणी
ardha-kākiṇī (CII 4), the half of a kākiṇī; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धनमस्यवृत्ति
ardha-namasya-vṛtti (IE 8-5); see namasya-vṛtti; a gift land, taxed at half of the normal rate; cf. pannāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धनारीश्वर|अर्द्धनारीश्वरः|अर्धनारीश्वरः
Ardhanārīśvara (CII 4), a form of Śiva, in which the bodies of Śiva and Pārvatī are combined into one.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धनौवाटक
Ardha-nauvāṭaka (EI 28), official designation; mentioned together with Nauvāḷaka probably in the sense of an officer in command of half of a fleet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धाङ्गी
ardhāṅgī (SITI), wife.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धपुरुषारिक
ardha-puruṣārika (CII 4), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धसीरिक
ardha-sīrika (EI 9), same as ārdhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धस्रोतिका
ardha-srotikā (EI 4), probably, a small stream or half of a river bed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धतृतीय
ardha-tṛtīya (CII 1), two and a half.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्धिक|आर्धिकः
ārdhika (EI 9), a cultivator who tills other's lands and gets half the crop as his share.<BR> Cf. Prakrit addhika (EI 1), a slave.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धोदय|अर्द्धोदयः|अर्धोदयः
ardhodaya (EI 5), the new-moon tithi falling on a [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-028" target="_blank">Page-028+ 40</a>] Sunday when, during day time, the nakṣatra is Śravaṇā and the yoga Vyatīpāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=027" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्द्रा
ārdrā (SITI), Tamil ātrai; probably, the expenses for the ārdrā festival in the month of Mārgal̤i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्गल|अर्गलं|अर्गलः
argala (IA 19), a check; used in certain dates and translated as ‘checked by’; cf. dvy-argala-catvāriṃśat-samadhika-vatsara-sahasra, ‘one thousand years, increased by forty [which have run into and are] checked by two’, i. e. the year 1042.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्घवञ्चन
argha-vañcana (EI 30), probably, fraud committed in respect of the price of articles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हदाचार्य
Arhad-ācārya (EI 29), a Buddhist or Jain teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धदायतन
Arhad-āyatana (LL), a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हद्दास
Arhad-dāsa, a Jain monk; cf. Arhad-dāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हद्दासी
Arhad-dāsī (EI 10), a Jain nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्हत्|अर्हन्त्
Arhat (EI 7-1-2), ‘twentyfour’.<BR> (CII 3; LL), Buddhist and Jain; a class of saints.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरि|अरिः
ari (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’; cf. ari-ṣaḍ-varga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिषड्वर्ग
ari-ṣaḍ-varga, also called ari-ṣaṭka (CII 3), the group of six enemies, viz. kāma, krodha, lobha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्जुनकर
Arjuna-kara A (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्क|अर्कः|अर्क्क
Arka (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR> (EI 7), explained as ‘metal’ in relation to Arkaśālika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्कशालिक
Arkaśālika (EI 7), same as Akkasāliga, Akṣośālika; a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्कशालिन्
Arkaśālin (BL), same as Akṣaśālin; a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्कसालिन्
Arkasālin (EI 29), same as Akṣaśālin; a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्णव|अर्णवः|अर्ण्णव
arṇava (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्णिका
arṇikā, weight equal to 2 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. VI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरोग्यदक्षिणा
ārogya-dakṣiṇā (ML), the gift of health.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरोग्यशाला
ārogya-śālā (EI 24; ASLV), hospital; cf. Raṅgādhip-ārogyaśālā (EI 24), ‘the hospital of [the god] Raṅganātha [at Śrīraṅgam]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरोहक|आरोहकः
Ārohaka (EI 27), official designation; possibly, same as Aśvāroha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थ|अर्थः
artha (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’,<BR> (CII 1), a cause or matter.<BR> (CII 1), business.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थाभियुक्त
Arth-ābhiyukta (IE 8-8), an accused.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थकर्मन्
artha-karman (CII 1), performance of duty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थलेखिन्
Arthalekhin (CII 4), a secretary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=028" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्थारुवा
arthāruvā (IE 8-5; EI 28), a tax of uncertain import; probably, Sanskrit artha-rūpyaka in the sense of a levy from the money-lenders on the amounts loaned out; also read as andhā-ruvā; see pratyarthāruvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्तिग
artiga, a lover (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 58).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरुहण
aruhaṇa (EI 27), probably, the tax also called āruvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आरुवण
āruvaṇa (EI 27), same as Tamil ar̤uvaṇa (IA 19), the tax of six paṇas levied on mānya lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्य|अर्यः|अर्य्य|अर्य्यः
Arya (CII 1), same as Vaiśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्य|आर्यः|आर्य्य|आर्य्यः
ārya, cf. Tamil ayyar (EI 25), the father.<BR> Cf. bhadatasa aya-Isipālitasa, ‘of the Reverend Lord Ṛṣipālita’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 29).<BR> (SII 1), a [Jain] saint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्या|आर्य्या
āryā, cf. āī (EI 9), the mother.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यगुरु
ārya-guru, cf. ajja-guru (EI 5), ‘a grandfather preceptor’; preceptor's preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यक|आर्यकः|आर्य्यक|आर्य्यकं|आर्य्यकः
āryaka, Prakrit ajjaka, ayyaka (EI 20, 28; CII 3; IA 15), the grandfather; father's father. Cf. prārya, āryikā.<BR> Cf. Prakrit ajjaka (EI 24), an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यका|आर्य्यका
āryakā, cf. Prakrit ajjakā (EI 24), Sanskrit āryikā; a female ascetic of the Jain order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यपुत्र|आर्यपुत्रः|आर्य्यपुत्त्रः|आर्य्यपुत्र
Ārya-putra, Prakrit Aya-puta (IE 8-2; EI 3; HD), probably, title of a son of the ruling king. Cf. CII, Vol. I, p. 175.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यसंघ
ārya-saṃgha (CII 3), ‘the community of the faithful (i. e. the Buddhist monks)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यसत्य
ārya-satya, cf. Pali ariya-sacca (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्यिका|आर्य्यिका
āryikā, cf. Prakrit āyikā (EI 20, 28), the grandmother; ‘father's mother’; mentioned side by side with mahāmātṛkā, ‘mother's mother’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 225).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशा
āśā (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असमीया
Asamīyā, see Assamese.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असंप्रतिपत्ति
asaṃpratipatti (CII 1), unseemly behaviour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसन|आसनं|आसनः
āsana (IE 8-8), a seat.<BR> Cf. a-cār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE 8-5; EI 15), probably, camping [of the royal officers in a village]; āsana-carma is sometimes taken as one expression meaning ‘a hide seat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसनपट्ट
āsana-paṭṭa (EI 23, 24), a seat; a slab used as a seat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसनपीठिका
āsana-pīṭhikā (LL), a bench for sitting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=029" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आषाण्मासिक
ā-ṣāṇmāsika (CII 1), ‘less than six months in age’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशापाल|आशापालः
Āśāpāla (HD), ‘the guardian of the quarters’; a chief ruling over 10,000 villages, according to the Śukranītisāra, I. 192.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशातना
aśātanā (HA), Jain; disrespect or disobedience.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसेधभङ्गाधिकृत
Āsedhabhaṅg-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 31), a police officer to check people's escape from prison or legal restraint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशेषमहाशब्द
aśeṣa-mahāśabda (IE 8-2), same as pañca-mahāśabda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशेषविद्य
aśeṣa-vidya (SII 1), belonging to all the branches of sacred studies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असिदण्डप्रहार
asi-daṇḍa-prahāra (LP), war.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असिधाराव्रत
asidhārā-vrata (EI 16), name of a vow.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसीहार
āsīhāra, cf. udak-āsīhāra-kullaka; probably, a kind of channel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसीन|आसीनः
āsīna (JAHRS, Vol. IX, Part i, p. 31, text line 12), literally ‘seated’; downcast, dejected. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 264-65.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्नव
āsnava (CII 1), sin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्फोटन|आस्फोटनं
āsphoṭana (SII 1), a challenge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्रम|आश्रमं|आश्रमः
āśrama (EI 13) a stage of life; a religious establishment (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 67); cf. Caṇḍik-āśrama-guru (IA 11), ‘the Superior of the hermitage of Caṇḍikā’.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्रय|आश्रयः
āśraya (IA 20), subdivision of a viṣaya.<BR> Cf. āśiriyam, āśiriya-kkal, āśiriya-ppramāṇam (SITI), a document by which a person submits to another's protection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्समेसे
Assamese, same as Asamīyā; language and alphabet of Assam, the alphabet being sometimes called Bengali-Assamese.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्ट
aṣṭa, cf. aṣṭa-bhoga, probably ‘all kinds of enjoyment’ (and not merely ‘eight’ kinds) ensuring tejaḥ-svāmya or ownership endowed with complete authority. Cf. aṣṭādaśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आष्टभागिक
āṣṭa-bhāgika (CII 1), ‘[a village] paying one-eighth of the produce [instead of the usual rate of one-sixth or so]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभोग
aṣṭa-bhoga (IE 8-5; EI 14, 17), privileges of the donee of a rent-free holding, believed to be grouped into eight classes which are sometimes enumerated as nidhi, nikṣepa, jala, pāṣāṇa, akṣīṇin, āgāmin, siddha and sādhya. Cf. aiśvary-āṣṭaka and aṣṭa-bhūti (EI 33); also aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya.<BR> (CITD), the eight privileges associated with the enjoyment of rent-free land, also enumerated as (1) nidhi (a treasure or a hoard, i. e. a natural hoard such as a mine), [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-031" target="_blank">Page-031+ 40</a>] (2) nikṣepa (a treasure hidden or stored up by some one), (3) akṣīṇa (permanent or lasting benefits), (4) āgāmin (future benefits); (5) sañcita (benefits already stored up), (6) jala (waters); (7) taru (trees) and (8) pāṣāṇa (stones). See JAHRS, Vol. X, p. 124. Pāṣāṇa seems to mean ‘hilly area’.<BR> (SITI), eight kinds of rights in enjoying landed property; mentioned sometimes as vikraya, dāna, vinimaya, jala, taru, pāṣāṇa, nidhi and nikṣepa, and also as nidhi, nikṣepa, jalāmṛta, pāṣāṇa, akṣīṇin, āgāmin, siddha and sādhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=030" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभोगतेजःस्वाम्य
aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya (IA 8), unbridled ownership endowed with all the rights associated with the enjoyment of property; translated as ‘with the eight rights of full possession’ though aṣṭa probably means ‘all’ and not merely ‘eight’ (cf. aṣṭādaśa, etc.); cf. aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmyaṃ ca krayeṇ=ādāya (EI 23), ‘having secured the aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya rights by purchase’; (IA 19), translated as ‘the proprietorship of all the glory of the aṣṭa-bhoga’, and aṣṭa-bhoga explained as ‘the deposits of buried treasure (nidhi-nikṣepa), water, stones, the akṣīṇī, that which may accrue, that which has been made property, that which may be made property, and augmentation’. But there is probably no justification for taking nidhi-nikṣepa as a single unit.<BR> Cf. aṣṭabhoga-tejassvāmya-daṇḍaśulka-yukta (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line 102), mentioned along with nidhi-nikṣepa-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣ-prakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita. The separate mention of these two groups shows that aṣṭa-bhoga vaguely indicated all kinds of proprietary rights.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभूति
aṣṭa-bhūti (EI 33), same as aṣṭa-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादश
aṣṭādaśa, cf. aṣṭādaśa-jāti-parihāra (IE 8-5); literally, ‘eighteen’; actually, ‘all’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 115). Cf. Od̤iyā aṭhara-gaḍajāta (EI 26). See aṣṭa, ṣaṭtriṃśat, ṣaṭpañcāśat, bāhattara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशदोष
aṣṭādaśa-doṣa (SII 1), the eighteen or all sins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशजाति
aṣṭādaśa-jāti (CITD), same as aṣṭādaśa-prajā; the 18 castes. Kittel enumerates the 18 castes of the Kannaḍa-speaking area as the Brāhmaṇa, Kṣatriya, Vaiśya, Liṅgavanta, Baṇajige, Gaṅgaḍikāra-vokkaliga, Maḍivāli, Kelasiga, Kur̤uba, Kumbār̤a, Kaṭuka, Baḍagi, Akkasālě, Toreya, Uppāra, Besta, Holeya and Mādiga. But really the number 18 means ‘all’ in such cases. The number 36 has the same meaning in the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-032" target="_blank">Page-032+ 40</a>] Bengali expression chatriś-jāti, ‘36 castes’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 115.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=031" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशप्रजा
aṣṭādaśa-prajā (CITD), same as aṣṭādaśa-jāti, aṣṭādaśa-prakṛti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशप्रकृति
aṣṭādaśa-prakṛti, cf. s-āṣtādaśa-prakṛty=opeta (EI 2); all classes of tenants; tenants belonging to all communities^1.<BR> (IA 17), ‘the eighteen (i. e. all) officials (i. e. classes of officials)’.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टदिग्गज
aṣṭa-diggaja (EI 33), eight poets at king Kṛsṇadevarāya's court at Vijayanagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्तगिरि|अस्तगिरिः
asta-giri (IA 22), the mythical Sun-set mountain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आष्टाहिका
āṣṭ-āhikā (EI 8), Jain festival; same as aṣṭ-āhnika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाह्निक
aṣṭ-āhnika, aṣṭ-āhnikā (EI 8, 33), Jain festival held in the months of Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika; also called aṣṭ-āhnika-parvan; same as aṭṭhāi-mahotsava. See the Halsi plates of Kadamba Ravivarman (c. 490-538 A. D.) in Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, pp. 25-26. Cf. The Successors of the Sātavāhanas, p. 271; Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 47 and note; cf. p. xvi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टक|अष्टकः
aṣṭaka (EI 7), same as ba-di 8; worship of the manes with oblations to them.<BR> Cf. aṭṭagam (SII 13), division of land, and aṭṭagattār (SII 13), share-holders in a land. See dvādaśaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टकुल
aṣṭa-kula, cf. Tamil ūr-ěṭṭu (SITI); the committee of eight members of the village assembly (ūr); taxes payable for the expenses of the committee (cf. eṇ-per-āyam which may also refer to the eight major items of revenue). See añjaṣṭa-sabhā.<BR> Cf. aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 31), an administrative board (like the Pañcāyat) consisting of eight (or more) members representing various classes or communities of people; cf. grām-āṣṭa-kul-ādhikaraṇa; mahattar-ādy-aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टमीपक्ष
aṣṭamī-pakṣa (CII 1), used to indicate pakṣ-āṣṭamī, i. e. the eighth tithi of each fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्तम्ब
astamba, cf. samudaya-bāhy-ādy-astamba (EI 23), ‘land originally devoid of vegetation which does not yield any revenue to the State’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टमिका
aṣṭamikā, same as śalamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाङ्ग|अष्टांग
aṣṭāṅga (CITD), the eight constituents of yoga consisting of (1) niyama (restraint of the mind), (2) āsana (a particular posture or mode of sitting), (3) prāṇāyāma (restraining or suspending the breath during the mental recitation of the names [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-033" target="_blank">Page-033+ 40</a>] or attributes of a deity), (4) yama (self-control), (5) pratyā-hāra (restraining the organs), (6) dhāraṇa (the faculty of retaining in the mind, steady abstraction of mind), (7) dhyāna (abstract contemplation, religious meditation), and (8) samādhi (perfect absorption of thought in the one object of meditation, i. e. the Supreme Spirit); mentioned in connection with obeisance, it means the 8 parts of the body, viz., the two hands, chest, forehead, two knees and two feet (cf. aṣṭāṅga-namaskāra).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=032" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाङ्गभक्तिक्रम
aṣṭāṅga-bhakti-krama (EI 19), eight forms of worship; same as aṣṭa-vidh-ārcana, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टाङ्गनमस्कार
aṣṭāṅga-namaskāra (HA), obeisance with the eight limbs (viz. forehead, chest, two hands, two knees and two feet) done by lying straight on the ground, face downwards. See pañc-āṅga-namaskāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टपरिपालन
aṣṭa-paripālana (SITI), deities of the eight cardinal points; same as aṣṭa-dikpāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टप्रहारिक
Aṣṭaprahārika (IA 17), probably an official designation; may be derived from aṣṭa-prahara; probably ‘a watchman’. The correct form would, in that case, be āṣṭaprāharika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टप्राहरिका
aṣṭaprāharikā, aṣṭapraharikyā (LP), ‘within 24 hours’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टपुष्पिका
aṣṭa-puṣpikā (EI 15), ‘eightfold offering of flowers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टावधान
Aṣṭāvadhāna (IA 11), one who has the power of listening and grasping eight things at a time; epithet of a poet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आष्टवर्गिक
Āṣṭavargika (IE 8-3; EI 7), probably, the superintendent of eight departments; mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टविधभक्तिक्रिया
aṣṭa-vidha-bhakti-kriyā (SITI), eight aspects of worship including arcanā, vandana, smaraṇa, pāda-sevana, stava, pradakṣiṇa, sakhya and ātma-nivedana or ātm-ārpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टविधार्चन
aṣṭa-vidh-ārcana, aṣṭa-vidh-ārcanā (EI 19), same as aṣṭāṅga-bhakti-krama, the eight forms of worship.<BR> (IA 14; SITI), explained as ‘worship with eight materials, e. g., jala (water), gandha (scent), puṣpa (flower), akṣatā (grains), dhūpa (incense), dīpa (lamps), naivedya (food) and tāmbula (betel)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्थानमण्डप|आस्थानमण्डपः
āsthāna-maṇḍapa (EI 4), an assembly hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आस्थायिकपुरुष
Āsthāyika-puruṣa (IA 8), official designation; probably the same as Sthāyin; may be ‘hereditary village officials’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्ति|अस्तिः
asti (Ep. Ind., Vol XXVIII, p. 302, note 2), a mere particle used to introduce the narration of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=033" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टि|अष्टिः
aṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशु|आशुः
āśu (SII 2), probably, a hilt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसु
āsu (CII 4), name of a coin; cf. āchu and accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशुद्धपक्ष
a-śuddha-pakṣa (IA 16), used to indicate the dark fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुकवि
Āśu-kavi (EI 5), epithet of a poet; cf. Sukara-kavi, Śīghra-kavi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अशुक्ल
a-śukla (IA 15), also called a-śukla-pakṣa (IA 16), the dark fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुलोप
āśulopa (CII 1), hurry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसुरक्रिया
āsura-kriyā (IA 23), the worship of spirits.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असुरविजयिन्
Asura-vijayin (CII 4), ‘a devilish conqueror’; epithet of a conqueror.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्व|अश्वः
aśva (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वाड्डाणकपत्र
aśv-āḍḍāṇaka-patra (LP), deed for mortgaging a horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वाध्यक्ष|अश्वाध्यक्षः
Aśv-ādhyakṣa (EI 18), superintendent of stables or cavalry officer; cf. Aśva-sādhanika, Aśvapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वघासकायस्थ|अश्वघासकायस्थः
Aśva-ghāsa-kāyastha (HD), a petty officer in charge of the fodder for horses. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, III. 489.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वमेध|अश्वमेधः
aśvamedha (CII 3, 4), a sacrificial ceremony centering in a horse, generally performed by independent monarchs. Kings celebrating the sacrifice sometimes assumed suitable titles (cf. Aśvamedha-parākrama and Aśvamedha-Mahendra claimed respectively by Samudragupta and Kumāragupta I on their coins). Some kings performed two, four or more horse-sacrifices. For a list of the performers of aśvamedha known form epigraphic and numismatic records, see Sundaram Pillai Com. Vol., pp. 93 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्वमेध
āśvamedha (EI 12), same as āśvamedhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अस्वामिक|अस्वामिकं
asvāmika (EI 19), anarchy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वपति|अश्वपतिः
Aśvapati (IE 8-2; CII 4)), cf. Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati; royal title; the king as ‘the leader of the cavalry’; title of the Vijayanagara kings on account of their strength in horses (ASLV); title assumed by the rulers of some royal families.<BR> (EI 9, 21; CII 3; HD), an official title meaning either the master of the stables or the commander of the cavalry; cavalry officer; cf. Aśv-ādhyakṣa (EI 18). See CII, Vol. III, p. 259.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वपतिगजपतिनरपतिमूवरुरायरगण्ड
Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-mūvaru-rāyara-gaṇḍa (IE 8-2), [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-035" target="_blank">Page-035+ 40</a>] title of the Vijayanagara kings; Kannaḍa translation of the title Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=034" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वपतिगजपतिनरपतिराजत्रयाधिपति
Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati (IE 8-2; CII 4), holder (or, lord of the holders) of the three royal titles, viz., leader of the cavalry, leader of the elephant corps and leader of infantry; title assumed by the rulers of certain dynasties. Cf. Aśvapati-Gajapati-Narapati-muvaru-rāyara-gaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वारोह|अश्वारोहः
Aśvāroha (EI 18), a trooper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वसाधनिक
Aśva-sādhanika (EI 21; CII 4), a cavalry officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वसंस्थ
Aśva-saṃstha (EI 8), a horseman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वशालाकरण
aśvaśālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of horses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वति
Aśvati (EI 9), Tamil; same as Aśvinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्ववार|अश्ववारः
Aśvavāra, cf. Asavāra (EI 2), a horseman. Cf.Bṛhad-aśvavāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्ववारक|अश्ववारकः
Aśvavāraka, Aśvavārika (LL), a trooper; same as Aśvavāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्विन्
Aśvin (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; sometimes Āśvina is also used in this sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आश्विन|आश्विनः
Āśvina (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. Aśvin. See IHQ, Vol. XXXIII, p. 101.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अश्वीय|अश्वीयं|अश्वीयः
aśvīya (EI 12), a number of horses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतपिक
Atapika (LL), a Jain monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अटवी
aṭavī (CII 1), the forest-folk. RE XIII of Aśoka seems to speak of the Aṭavī or foresters as habitually criminal.<BR> (SITI), troops.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आटविक|आटविकः
āṭavika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 303, text line 50), a kind of grains.<BR> (EI 20; HD), an officer in charge of forest tracts. See Arthaśāstra, I 12 (mentioned among the 18 tīrthas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अठगानी
aṭha-gānī, a billon coin equal to 8 copper jitals and to (1/6) of a silver ṭaṅka; there are do-gānī ((1/4) ṭaṅka), cau-gānī ((1/2) ṭaṅka), cha-gānī ((3/4) ṭaṅka), bārah-gānī (1(1/2) ṭaṅkas), caubīs-gānī (3 ṭaṅkas), aḍatālīs-gānī (6 taṅkas). See JNSI, Vol. XXII, pp. 198-99.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अथर्ववेद|अथर्ववेदः
Atharva-veda (CII 3; etc.), one of the four Vedas. See Veda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिब्रह्मण्य
Ati-brahmaṇya (CII 3), probably meaning ‘extremely friendly to the Brāhmaṇas’ and not ‘a devout worshipper of the god Brahman’. See Parama-brahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिधृति|अतिधृतिः
atidhṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘nineteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिजगली
atijagatī (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिपर|अतिपरः
atipara (EI 24), an inveterate foe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=035" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिप्रसङ्ग|अतिप्रसंग|अतिप्रसंगः|अतिप्रसङ्गः
atiprasaṅga (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 347, note 5), a case in which a grammatical rule exceeds its sphere.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिरात्र|अतिरात्रः
atirātra (CII 3), name of a particular sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिरेक|अतिरेकः
atireka (CII 1), excess; cf. mano-'tireka, ‘enthusiasm’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिसत्त्र
atisattra (EI 27), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतीत|अतीतं|अतीतः
atīta (IA 17), ‘expired’; cf. Śaka-nṛpa-kāl-ātīta-saṃvatsareṣu. The word gateṣu, sometimes additionally used, refers to the expiry of the expired years.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतीलराज्य
atīta-rājya (IA 19), indicates that so many years ‘since [the commencement of] the reign have [now] passed’; used in connection with the regnal reckoning of Govindapāla and Lakṣmaṇasena and rarely with the years of an era (e. g. the Vikrama-saṃvat associated with the reign of a legendary king named Vikramāditya). See also gata-rājya and vinaṣṭa-rājya. Cf. JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, 1954, pp. 43 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतिथि|अतिथिः
atithi (EI 10; CII 3, 4), reception of guests; one of the five daily rites (mahāyajñas) of a Brāhmaṇa. See sattra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतिथ्य|आतिथ्यं|आतिथ्यः
ātithya (HRS), land assigned to government officers for public charities, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतिवाहिक
ātivāhika (HRS), escorting fee paid by the merchants, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 77.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतियात्र
atiyātra (EI 30), same as atiyātrika; exit tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतियात्रिक
atiyātrika (IE 8-8), tax for crossing the boundary; see śulk-ātiyātrika, ‘the boundary-crossing fee’; also atiyātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्मक
ātmaka, cf. apaṇaga (ML), ‘one's own’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्मन्
ātman (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्मपतिक
ātma-patika (CII 1), independent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतोद्य|आतोद्यं
ātodya (EI 23), music.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्रि|अत्रिः
Atri (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्रिनयनज
Atrinayanaja (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टपति
Aṭṭapati (HD), the market-master. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 167.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टपतिभाग
aṭṭapati-bhāga (HRS), office entrusted with the collection of the share of the lord of the market, as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī; literally, ‘share of the market-master’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्ठाइमहोत्सव
aṭṭhāi-mahotsava (HA), an eight-day festival celebrated by the Jains especially in the months of Āśvina and Caitra according to some but Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika according to others; same as aṣṭāhnika-parvan (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=036" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अटु
aṭu (Chamba), a land measure. Cf. jilo, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतुरशाला
ātura-śālā, cf. ātula-śālai (EI 24; SITI), a hospital.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतुरावड्डि
āturāvaḍḍi (IE 8-5; EI 28), tax of uncertain import; probably, a levy related to the treatment of the king when sick; also read as āntarāvaḍḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यग्निष्टोम|अत्यग्निष्टोमः
atyagniṣṭoma (EI 26), name of a sacrifice. cf. agniṣṭoma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यन्तभगवद्भक्त
Atyanta-bhagavad-bhakta (IE 8-2; CII 3), ‘extremely devoted to the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu)’; epithet of a pious Vaiṣṇava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यन्तमाहेश्वर
Atyanta-māheśvara (EI 23; CII 3), epithet of a pious Śaiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यन्तस्वामिमहाभैरवभक्त
Atyanta-svāmi-mahābhairava-bhakta (EI 23; CII 3), epithet of a pious Śaiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यष्टि|अत्यष्टिः
atyaṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘seventeen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्यय|अत्ययः
atyaya (HRS), prescribed fine, as indicated in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 26, 108. Cf. ātyayika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आत्ययिक
ātyayika (CII 1; EI 22), a matter for urgent disposal; derived from atyaya, emergency, distress.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औदयन्त्रिक
Audayantrika (LL), cf. Prakrit Odayantrika (EI 8); the maker of hydraulic machines or the person owning or working on such a machine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औद्रङ्गिक|औद्रङ्गिकः
Audraṅgika (IE 8-3; EI 23), collector of the udraṅga tax meaning ‘tax on permanent tenants or the principal tax’; sometimes mentioned side by side with the Hiraṇyasāmudāyika or the collector of tax in cash. See Ṣaṣṭh-ādhikṛta, Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औकपिण्ड
aukapiṇḍa, cf. okapiṇḍa (CII 1), probably, household vermin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औलिकर
aulikara, cf. aulikara-lāñchana (EI 26; CII 3), the lāñchana or crest of the kings of the Aulikara dynasty of Mandasor. The real meaning of auli is uncertain; sometimes aulikara is interpreted as himakara or the moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपरिक
Auparika (EI 8-3), same as Uparika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपशतिक
Aupaśatika, cf. Prakrit Opasati (EI 16), name of a gotra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपायनिक
aupāyanika (HRS), earnings from presents, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 28, 38.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औपायिक
aupāyika (EI 25), probably, an adopted [son].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औरेउस्
aureus (IE 8-8), name of the Roman gold coin, also called denarius (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=037" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

और्णस्थानिक|और्णस्थानिकः
Aurṇasthānika (IE 8-3; EI 23), officer in charge of an ūrṇā-sthāna (wool factory) or of all the ūrṇā-sthānas. Cf. ūrṇā-sthāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औषध|औषधं
auṣadha (EI 24), medicine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औत्खेटिक
Autkheṭika (HRS), officer in charge of the collection of the impost called utkheṭana (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औत्तराह
Auttarāha (EI 8), a northerner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औत्थितासनिक|औत्थितासनिकः
Autthitāsanika (IE 8-3), same as Utthitāsanin; probably, courtier of a special rank provided with a special seat; perhaps, the chief nobleman at the royal court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवभृथ|अवभृथः
avabhṛtha (EI 9; CII 4), name of the ceremonial bath at the end of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवचटित
avacaṭita (EI 13), a crack; cf. khaṇḍa-sphuṭit-āvacaṭita-patita-saṃskār-ārtham, ‘for the repairs of dilapidated, broken, cracked and fallen [parts]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवच्छिन्न|अवच्छिन्नं
avacchinna, cf. sva-sīm-āvacchinna (IE 8-5), demarcated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवदान|अवदानं
avadāna, also spelt āvadāna (EI 28, 29, 33), Od̤iyā; a present; a tax; tax in general; also called āvedana.<BR> (SITI), same as Sanskrit avasāna; termination, end.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवदार
avadāra (EI 13), cf. paśukul-āvadāra-karmānta-koṇakalikā-gaṅgāgrāme; meaning uncertain; possibly ‘a pound’ or ‘a pen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधानिन्
Avadhānin (EI 16), title of Brāhmaṇas; cf. Śatāvadhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधारणा
avadhāraṇā, cf. adhikaraṇ-āvadhāraṇā, ‘official investigation’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 267).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधि|अवधिः
avadhi, cf. avadher=anantaram (LP), ‘after the time limit is over’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवधी
Avadhī, language of Avadh (Oudh).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवाह|आवाहः
āvāha (CII 1), marriage of a son; cf. vivāha, ‘marriage of a daughter’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवकर|अवकरः
avakara (EI 32), sweepings, a mound. Cf. avaṣkara; also niravakara, remainder after deduction (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 188).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवकाश|अवकाशः
avakāśa (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 347, note 5), ‘opportunity for a grammatical rule taking effect’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलगा
avalagā (LP), same as Gujarātī ol̤aga; cf. avalagā sad=aiv=āvalokyā (LP), ‘care should be constantly taken’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलगक
avalagaka (EI 2; HRS), same as avalagā (q. v.); sometimes regarded as presents or supplies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=038" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलगन
avalagana (EI 2; HRS), same as avalagaka and avalagā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलम्बक|अवलंबकः|अवलम्बकः
avalambaka (EI 30), probably, a rod from which loops are suspended for carrying bundles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवलोक्य
avalokya (IE 8-8), detection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवण
āvaṇa (SITI), Tamil; a document; generally, a sale-deed; also called vilaiy-āvaṇam; cf. āvaṇa-kkal̤ari (SITI), a place where documents like sale-deeds, etc., are registered; registration office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनी
avanī (EI 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR> (EI 3), a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनिमण्डल
avani-maṇḍala, cf. Kon-āvani-maṇḍala (EI 32), also called Kona-maṇḍala, Kona-sīma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनिरन्ध्रन्याय
avani-randhra-nyāya (CII 4), same as bhūmi-cchidra-nyāya (q. v.), ‘the maxim of the fallow land.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवनिवेतन
avani-vetana (SITI), police duties of a village; contribution for such duties; the same as Tamil pā ṭikāval.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवर
āvara (CII 4), a stall. Cf. āvāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवार|आवारः
āvāra (IE 8-5), cf. āpaṇeṣu āvāraḥ, ‘collections to be made from the shops in a market’. Cf. āvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवराधिक
avar-ādhika (CII 1), ‘more or less’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवरज|अवरजः
avaraja (ML), a younger brother or cousin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवरण|आवरणं
āvaraṇa (EI 17), a shield.<BR> (SITI), shelter, covering; same as prākāra or wall around the temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवर्जनीय
āvarjanīya (LP), ‘to be received’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवरोधन|अवरोधनं
avarodhana (CII 1), household; cf. antaḥpura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवरोधजन
avarodha-jana (EI 23), inmates of the royal harem or the king's wives and concubines; wrongly interpreted as ‘a watchman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवर्त|आवर्तः|आवर्त्त|आवर्त्तं|आवर्त्तः
āvarta, cf. sarv-āvarta-yutā, ‘assigned as the date of payment as it falls annually’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 310, note 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवास|आवासः
āvāsa, cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (IE 8-5), shelter or accommodation [which the villagers were obliged to provide for the touring officers of the king]; cf. saṃvāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवासक
āvāsaka (IE 8-5; EI 25), same as āvāsa or saṃvāsa, i. e. accommodation [which the villagers were obliged to provide to the royal officers on tour].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवासनिका
āvāsanikā (EI 1), a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसर|अवसरः
Avasara (SITI), an officer of the royal household having [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-040" target="_blank">Page-040+ 40</a>] the duty of bringing to the notice of the king anything that demanded his immediate attention. Cf. Kārtākṛtika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=039" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसर|अवसरः
avasara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 347), one of the periods when the worship is performed and offerings are made to the deity in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसरवर्त्तना
Avasara-varttanā (SITI), presents payable to an Avasara (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसथ|अवसथः
avasatha (IE 8-3), explained as ‘a college or a dharma-śālā’. But see Āvasathika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवसथिक|आवसथिकः
Āvasathika (IE 8-3), variously explained as ‘the superintendent of avasathas, i. e. colleges or dharma-śālās’, ‘the supervisor of the royal palace and other government buildings’ (Hist. Beng., I, ed. Majumdar, p. 284); ‘one who keeps the domestic fire (āvasathya) burning with daily offerings’ (D. Bhattacharya, Halāyudha's Brāhmaṇasarvasva, p. xx); etc.<BR> (EI 9, 11, 24), title or family name of Brāhmaṇas. Cf. Āvasathin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवसथिन्
Āvasathin (EI 23), explained as ‘one who keeps the sacred fire called āvasathya’; cf. Āvasathika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवष्कर
avaṣkara, sweepings, a mound; cf. s-oṣar-āvaṣkara-sthāha-nivīta-lavaṇākara (EI 22); also sa-gart-āvaṣkara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text line 21). See avakara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवष्टब्धि
avaṣṭabdhi (LP), detention.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवस्था
avasthā (IA 16), a territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवस्थिक
Āvasthika (EI 23), corruption of Āvasathika; same as Āvasathin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवात
āvāta (IE 8-5), same as vāta, storm; cf. udvāta. Cf. also nivāta.<BR> (EI 32; CII 3; etc.), a fiscal term referring to the income from lands as a result of changes caused by natural agencies; an income probably resulting from storms. See vāta, probably meaning ‘a storm or tempest’; also āvāt-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवतार|अवतारः
avatāra (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवतरण|अवतरणं
avataraṇa, cf. gṛh-āvataraṇa (IE 8-5), probably the same as umbara-bheda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवतारिअमावास्या
avatāri-amāvāsyā (IA 18), Kannaḍa name for the new-moon of Pauṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवाताय
āvāt-āya (HRS), ‘the income derived from storms’; cf. āvāta and bhūta-vāta-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवत्रप्
avatrap (CII 1), ‘to be disinclined’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवेदन|आवेदनं
āvedana (EI 28), same as avadāna or āvadāna of Od̤iyā records; tax in general. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 115.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=040" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवेदनक
āvedanaka (IE 8-8), a written complaint or application.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवण्डाय
avaṇḍ-āya (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 96), Telugu; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवेशनिन्
Āveśanin, cf. Prakrit Āvesani (EI 2; LL), the chief artisan; the foreman of artisans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अविमनस्
avimanas (CII 1), pleased.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अविप्रहीन
aviprahīna (CII 1), used in the sense of ahīna, ‘not lost’; undiminished.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अविरोध|अविरोधः
avirodha (SITI), not inimical; amicability.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवृति|आवृतिः
āvṛti (CII 1), order; cf. sakala-deś-āvṛtika (CII 1), ‘one whose order has reached all parts of the country’.<BR> Cf. anāvṛti (CII 1), ‘want of practice’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवृत्ति|आवृत्तिः
āvṛtti (IE 8-4; EI 26), an administrative unit like a Pargana (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 205).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अय|अयः
aya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आय|आयः
āya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR> (EI 33; CII 3; SII 1, 2), a fiscal term meaning ‘revenue’, ‘tax’.<BR> (SITI), literally, income; a general term denoting ‘taxes’; cf. val̤̣iy-āyam (SITI), tolls on the roadway.<BR> (HRS), revenue in general according to the Arthaśāstra and other authorities; a special branch of revenue according to the inscriptions of the Uccakalpa kings and later epigraphs.<BR> (CITD), profit, income, receipt; tribute; corn given by the well-to-do villagers to the hereditary servants of the village as their established fees of office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयाग|आयागः
āyāga (EI 1), an object of homage; cf. āyāga-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयागपट
āyāga-paṭa, āyāga-paṭṭa (EI 24; LL), Jain; tablet for worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयागसभा
āyāga-sabhā (LL), Jain; a hall of homage.<BR> (SITI), administration of a village by a group of officers called āyāgār (village officers and servants).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयक
āyaka (EI 21; LL), the entrance pavilion of a Buddhist monastery; a pavilion in front of the door of a Buddhist monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयमुख
āya-mukha, ‘sources of income’; cf. āya-śarīra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 26.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अयन|अयनं
ayana (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अयनांश|अयनांशः
ayan-āṃśa (CII 3), the degree of procession of the equinoxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=041" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयपद
āya-pada (LP), income; property (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 145).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयशरीर
āya-śarīra, ‘body of income’ separated from āya-mukha, ‘source of income’. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 25-26.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयशुल्क
āya-śulka (EI 33), taxes and tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयत|आयतः
āyata (CII 1), engaged or appointed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयतन|आयतनं
āyatana (EI 30), a temple or shrine. Cf. bhavana, ālaya, pura, etc.<BR> Cf. ṣaḍ-āyatana; an organ.<BR> Cf. tuṣṭy-āyatana (CII 1), same as tuṣṭi-pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयति|आयतिः
āyati (EI 14), future prosperity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुधीय|आयुधीयः
āyudhīya (HRS), land granted for supplying troops in lieu of tax, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra. See amara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुक्त|आयुक्तः
Āyukta (CII 4; HD), literally ‘an officer’. Same as Āyuktaka. Pāṇini (II, 3. 40) knows the word in the sense of a servant or office. Cf. Āyukta-puruṣa (CII, Vol. III, p. 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुक्तक
Āyuktaka (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; EI 30; BL; HD), same as Āyukta; often the governor of a district or subdivision. See Kāmasūtra, V. 5. 5; Kāmandaka, V. 82.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुक्तपुरुष
Āyukta-puruṣa (CII 3), the same as Āyukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुष|आयुषं
āyuṣa, used in the sense of āyus in the Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman, text line 10 (Sel. Ins., p. 171).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयुष्य|आयुष्यं
āyuṣya (EI 10), Jain; a variety of karman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अय्यनगन्धवारण
Ayyanagandhavāraṇa (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; ‘the musk-elephant of the grandfather’; a subordinate title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अय्यनसिंह
Ayyanasiṃha (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; ‘the lion of the grandfather’; a subordinate title. Cf. Aṇṇanasiṃha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब|बः
ba (IE 8-1; CII 3, etc.); an abbreviation of bahula or of bahula-pakṣa, i. e. the dark fortnight; used in connection with di or ti (see ba-di, la-ti) and also by itself. Cf. va.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बा
Bā˚ (PJS), contraction of the honorific Bāi (q. v.) applied to ladies (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions of Western India).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाबू
bābū (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 316), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाचक
bācaka (LP), handful; cf. Gujarātī bācko.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=042" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाछ
bācha, bāchī (Chamba), a tax in cash. See vākṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाड
bāḍa (EI 5), Kannaḍa; a town or village.<BR> (IE 8-4), Kannaḍa; a small territorial unit like a Pargana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाडब
bāḍaba (SII 1), the submarine fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदला
badalā (Chamba), return, exchange; same as parata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदर|बदरं|बदरः
badara, same as tolaka (q. v.) or tolā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बधा
badhā (LP), obstacle; cf. Sanskrit bādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाधा
bādhā (EI 15), obstacle; also spelt vādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाढतरम्
bāḍhataram (CII 1), ‘more excessively’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदि
ba-di (IE 8-1; CII 3; etc.), contraction of bahula-pakṣa-dina or ˚divasa; also spelt va-di, cf. śu-di; abbreviations of separate words (see ba, di, śu and va) and not words in themselves, ba-di or va-di referring to the dark fortnight and śu-di the bright fortnight; they denote the fortnight and the solar or civil day, with reference to the lunar tithi, in the fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बडिमाडुवुलु
baḍi-māḍuvulu (CITD) Telugu; a coin of unknown value. Baḍi means ‘petty’ or ‘a tax’ and māḍuvu may be the same as māḍa meaning half a dīnār or the tenth of a paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बागुलि
Bāguli, cf. Vārgulika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहत्तर
bāhattara (IE 8-3), literally, ‘seventytwo’, but actually ‘all’ (cf. aṣṭādaśa, etc.); see Bāhattaraniyogādhipati, Bāhattara-niyogin, Senādibāhattaraniyogādhiṣṭhāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहत्तरनियोगाधिपति
Bāhattaraniyogādhipati (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30), the highest executive officer under South Indian kings like the Yādavas of Devagiri; same as Bāhattaraniyogin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहत्तरनियोगिन्
Bāhattaraniyogin (EI 19), official designation; same as Bāhattaraniyogādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहिर्गृह
bahir-gṛha, cf. vāra-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहिरिका
bāhirikā (EI 20), a suburb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहिस्
bahis, ‘excluding’; same as Bengali baï (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 215).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहु|बाहुः
bāhu (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहुलेय|बाहुलेयः
bāhuleya (CII 3; IA 1), a bull.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहुश्रुत
bahuśruta (CII 1), well informed in various doctrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहुसुवर्ण
bahusuvarṇa, bahusuvarṇaka (EI 4; IA 19; CII 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बहुतावत्क
bahutāvatka (CII 1), ‘many times that number’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाहुवलय
bāhu-valaya, cf. pāku-valayam (SITI), an armlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाह्य|बाह्यः
bāhya, cf. bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya (IE 8-5; Ep. Ind., Vol. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-044" target="_blank">Page-044+ 40</a>] XVI, p. 276, text line 14); ‘income from the sale of things imported in a village’, same as Tamil pur̤av-āyam (SITI), ‘revenue from external sources (collected mainly in cash)’ or Tamil pur̤a-kaḍamai (SITI), ‘external taxes’, explained as taxes and fees payable to the State. But pur̤a-kaḍamai is the same as pur̤av-āyam. Bāhya and ābhyantatra may thus mean respectively taxes payable to the king and those payable to the village authorities. See ābhyantara. Cf. samudaya-bāhy-ādya-stamba (EI 23), ‘land covered with original shrubs, i. e. waste which does not yield any revenue to the State’.<BR> (HD), a class of royal servants distinguished from Antaraṅga. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 426, 680, 1542.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=043" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाह्यालि
bāhyāli (CII 4), the outskirt of a town. See vāhyāli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाइ
Bāi, Bāī (EI 8), honorific epithet or name-ending of ladies in Western India; cf. Bāyi, Bā.˚<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बल|बलं|बलः
bala, an escort; cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधि
Balādhi (LP), abbreviation of Balādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधिकृत
Balādhikṛta (CII 3, 4; BL; HD), ‘the commander of an army’. See JBBRAS, Vol. XVI, p. 108 (Balādhikṛta following Senāpati); Kādambarī, para. 74. According to some (cf. Balādhi in LP), the Balādhikṛta was probably the head of a territorial unit like the present Māmlatdār. See Balādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधिप
Balādhipa (BL), a leader of the army; cf. Balādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाधीर
Balādhīra (CII 4), official designation; probably, mistake for Balādhīśa, same as Balādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलाध्यक्ष|बलाध्यक्षः
Balādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), officer in charge of the army; mentioned along with the Senāpati who was probably a subordinate officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलदी
baladī, see valadī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलहरण
balaharaṇa, cf. balaharaṇena (LP), same as Gujarātī lāine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बालकमहाराजकुमार
Bālaka-mahārājakumāra (EI), a young prince.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलकौष्ठिक
Balakauṣṭhika, cf. Valatkauṣan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बालालय
bāl-ālaya (SITI) temporary shrine to lodge the images of gods when repairing a temple; small shrine probably consisting of a single room wherein the images of all the gods are lodged; same as Tamil il̤aṅ-koyil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलानक
balānaka (HA), a maṇḍapa above the entrance of a Jain shrine or the courtyard of a shrine, later known as ṭhākorkhānā.<BR> (BL), a stone seat. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-045" target="_blank">Page-045+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 8), same as Marāṭhī balāṇī, ‘a raised seat along the walls of the gābhāra or sabhā-maṇḍapa of a temple.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=044" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलयष्टि
bala-yaṣṭi (EI 33; CII 4), a stout memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बल्हरा
Balharā (IE 8-2), Arabic corruption of Vallabha-rāja through Prakrit Ballaha-rāa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलि|बलिः
bali (IE 8-5; HRS), voluntary gift (afterwards, compulsory contribution) and tribute from the subjects as indicated by Vedic literature; later, tax in general as suggested by the standard lexicons; king's grain share, identical with bhāga but different from kara according to the Arthaśāstra, but not the Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman (cf. bali-śulka-bhāga in line 14). The Rummindei inscription of Aśoka also distinguishes between bali and bhāga and seems to identify bali with kara (or with pilgrims' tax). See Select Inscriptions, pp. 71, 173.<BR> (EI 10, 23, 32; CII 3, 4), an offering to creatures; one of the five mahāyajñas or sacrificial rites. Cf. bali-caru-vaiśvadev-āgnihotra-kratu (EI 26), the five rites of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR> (SITI), offering of flowers, fruits, uncooked rice, etc., to the gods; same as śrībali. Cf. Nārāyaṇa-baly-upahāra in the sense of Nārayaṇa-pūjā (Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, p. 363).<BR> Cf. varāha-bali, ‘pig sacrifice’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 39). Cf. śrī-bali, havir-bali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Balisādhaka, tax-collector (Ghoshal, Ag. Syst., p. 25).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=556" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलीवर्द|बलीवर्दः|बलीवर्द्द|बलीवर्द्दः
balīvarda, cf. a-paramparā-balīvarda, etc. (IE 8-5); a pair of bullocks (which the villagers were obliged to provide for the cart of the royal officers when they camped or toured in their villages). See also vara-balīvarda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाण|बाणः
bāṇa (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बानसवेर्गडे
Bānasa-věrgaḍě (599-11-2), variant spelling of Kannaḍa Bhānasa-věrgaḍě (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्ध|बंध|बंधः|बन्धः
bandha (EI 31), a dam or highway.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धदण्ड
bandha-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12, 33), probably, ransom or fine in lieu of imprisonment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धाण
bandhāṇa (Chamba), a settlement, an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धाणपट्ट
bandhāṇa-paṭṭa (Chamba), an agreement, a deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धनीय
bandhanīya (LP), ‘to be fixed’, i. e. to be served to one; cf. Gujarātī bāndhī āpavāṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धेज
bandheja (Chamba), a settlement, an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बन्धु|बंधु|बंधुः|बन्धुः
bandhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बप्प
bappa (EI 29, 30; CII 3; etc.), a Prakrit word meaning [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-046" target="_blank">Page-046+ 40</a>] ‘the father’, often used in Sanskrit inscriptions. Cf. bappa-bhaṭṭāraka-pāda-parigṛhīta (EI 31), epithet of certain rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=045" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बप्पभट्टारक
bappa-bhaṭṭāraka (EI 4), ‘the father, the lord’. Cf. bappa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बार
bāra (EI 13), Telugu; the distance between the ends of out-stretched arms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाराड्
bārāḍ, derived from Sanskrit varāṭa or varāṭaka, ‘a cowrie-shell (used as money)’ (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 18). Cf. varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बरट|बरटः
baraṭa (CII 4), a plant grown for fencing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बार्हस्पत्य|बार्हस्पत्यः
bārhaspatya (IA 11), name of a reckoning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बर्कन्दाष्
Barkandāz, Persian; same as Pāik (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बर्तना
bartanā (IE 3-5), Rājasthānī; a blunt stick for writing on a wooden slate; same as barthā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बर्था
barthā (IE 3-5), same as bartanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बसिलेओस्
Basilěos Basilěon Měgalŏu (IE 8-2), Greek; ‘of the great king of kings;’ used in the legend on the coins of the Scytho-Parthian kings; adapted from old Persian Khshyāthiya Khshāya-thiyānām, ‘the king of kings’; translated into Prakrit as Maha-rajasa Rajarajasa (or Rajadirajasa) mahalasa (Sanskrit Mahā-rājasya Rājarājasya mahataḥ or Rājātirājasya mahataḥ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बसिलेओस्
Basilěos Měgalŏu (IE 8-2), Greek; ‘of the great king’, found in the legend on the coins of Indo-Greek kings at first translated in Prakrit as Rajasa mahatakasa (Sanskrit Rājñaḥ mahataḥ) and later as Maharajasa (Sanskrit Mahārājasya); adapted from old Persian Kshāyathiya vazrka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बति
ba-ti (IE 8-1), abbreviation of bahula-pakṣa-tithi. See ba-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बाव
bāva (CII 3, etc.), a Prakrit word denoting ‘a relative of the same generation with the father’; generally, ‘an uncle’; used in Sanskrit inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बायि
Bāyi (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 35), suffix to the name of respectable women; same as Bāi; wrongly regarded as derived from the Kannaḍa words abbě (Sanskrit ambā) and āyi (Sanskrit āryā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेहरामहापात्र
Beharā-mahāpātra (EI 28), Od̤iyā; official designation; probably, Sanskrit Vyavahārika-mahāpātra. See Vyavahārika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेन्गलि
Bengali, Anglicised spelling of Vaṅgālī; the name of the people, language and alphabet of Bengal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेण्टकार
Beṇṭakāra (CITD), same as Beṭakāra, beṭa (Telugu-Kannaḍa) meaning ‘the separation of lovers’. As an epithet of a ruler, Beṇṭakāra means ‘one who causes the separation of his [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-047" target="_blank">Page-047+ 40</a>] enemies’ wives from their husbands’; cf. ripu-nārī-vaidhavya-vidhā-yak-ācārya, ‘one who renders the wives of his enemies widows’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=046" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ|भं|भः
bha (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyseven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ|भं|भः
Bha˚ (PJS), abbreviation of Bhagavān (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भा
bhā˚ (PJS), abbreviation of bhāryā (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाडक
bhāḍaka (LP), same as Sanskrit bhāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भदन्त|भदंत|भदंतः|भदन्तः
Bhadanta (IA 11; LL), a title of monks (Buddhist, Jain and Ājīvika); cf. Bhadatasa aya-Isipālitasa, ‘of the Reverend Lord Ṛṣipālita’; also cf. Bhadantī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भदन्ती
Bhadantī (LL), used as the title of a Buddhist nun; cf. Bhadanta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्र|भद्रं|भद्रः
bhadra (SII 2), probably, an auspicious mark.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रा
bhadrā (IA 26), same as ba-di 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाद्र|भाद्रः
Bhādra (IE 8-1), same as Bhādrapada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रभोग
bhadra-bhoga, cf. ‘according to bhadra-bhoga’ (Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 215); principle of proper enjoyment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रघट|भद्रघटः
bhadra-ghaṭa, cf. Tamil pattira-kaḍam (SITI), a pot filled with water and sanctified by rites.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रमुख
bhadra-mukha (EI 16), an honorific used with personal names.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रनिगम
bhadra-nigama (LL), a righteous hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भद्रासन|भद्रासनं
bhadr-āsana (EI 25), a throne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाग|भागः
bhāga (IE 8-5; CII 3, 4; EI 30; HRS), the king's share of the produce, distinguished from bali in the Rummindei inscription and the Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman and from kara in many other records; later, tax in general, identical with bali and kara (according to lexicons); cf. references in the Arthaśāstra to (1) lavaṇa-bhāga (king's share of salt sold by private merchants), (2) udaka-bhāga (king's grain share levied as water-tax upon irrigated fields), (3) king's share of the produce of mines leased out to private persons; (4) share paid to the king by merchants for selling the royal merchandise. Cf.pāga.<BR> (IE 8-5), dues (see kara); generally, the king's share of grains, which was originally one-sixth.<BR> (IE 8-4), a subdivision of a district or a territory.<BR> (EI 23, 33), an allotment; a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागभोग
bhāga-bhoga (CII 3; etc.), a fiscal expression in which [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-048" target="_blank">Page-048+ 40</a>] bhāga means the king's share of the produce and bhoga the periodical supplies made by tenants to the king; cf. bhāga-bhog-ādika, bhāga-bhoga-kara-hirany-ādika (EI 23), meaning ‘royal dues’; see bhāga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=047" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागभोगकर
bhāga-bhoga-kara (HRS), taken by some as a single levy and explained as the king's grain-share, identical with bhāga of the Arthaśāstra and bali of the Smṛtis, though distinguished from dhānya in a Maitraka record, where it has been supposed to mean a fixed contribution in kind as distinguished from the contribution consisting of a share of the produce. If bhāgabhogakara was a single levy (and did not indicate bhāga, bhoga and kara), it may have really been a tax collected in lieu of bhāga (grain share) and bhoga (periodical offerings). In bhoga-bhāga-dhānya-hiraṇya of the Kurud plates (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 264), we have probably to understand dhānya-hiraṇya realised as bhoga-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागदुघ
Bhāgadugha (HD), an official title; probably the same as Bhāgahāra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागहर|भागहरः
Bhāgahara (EI 24), same as Bhāgin; a collector of the king's grain share. Cf. Bhāgahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागहार|भागहारः
Bhāgahāra (HD), ‘he who recovers the [king's] share [of the produce^1 of land]’; one of the six officers of each village, according to Śukra, II. 120. Cf. Bhāgahara.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागलाग
bhāgalāga, cf. bhāgalāg-ādika (LP), payments in kind or taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागकर्षण
bhāga-karṣaṇa (LP), taking away the portion allotted to someone else.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगण|भगणः
bhagaṇa (IA 19), a bangle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवद्भक्त|भगवद्भक्तः
Bhagavad-bhakta (CII 3, etc.), a Vaiṣṇava sectarian title indicating ‘a follower of the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्|भगवन्त्
Bhagavat (ML; CII 3, 4), ‘the lord’ or ‘the divine’; an epithet of divinities such as Viṣṇu, Buddha, Jinendra, Nārāyaṇa, Śiva, the Sun-god, Kārttikeya, etc; also applied to sages, etc. in the sense of ‘venerable’, e. g. to Vyāsa, the arranger of the Vedas; rarely applied to kings apparently on account of their saintliness (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागवत|भागवतं|भागवतः
Bhāgavata (LL), a votary of the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu).<BR> (CII 3; etc.), a Vaiṣṇava sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवती
Bhagavatī (CII 3, 4; etc.), feminine form of Bhagavat (q. v.); often applied to goddesses, etc. See pagoda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्पादाचार्य
Bhagavatpād-ācārya (EI 6), epithet of a Vaiṣṇava religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्पादकर्मकर
Bhagavatpāda-karmakara (CII 4), ‘a servant of the feet of the Bhagavat’; epithet of a temple official.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=048" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागिक|भागिकं
Bhāgika (IE 8-3; HD), probably, the collector of the king's grain share; same as Bhāgahāra. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 166. Cf. Bhāgin.<BR> (EI 13), mentioned along with Bhogika; probably, one getting a share [in a free-holding]. See Aṃśa-bṛhadbhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागिन्
Bhāgin (EI 24), same as Bhāgika, a collector of the king's grain share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भग्न|भग्नं
bhagna (CII 1), ‘departed’, ‘lost’, i. e. ‘inferior’; cf. the Hindī verb bhāgnā, Bengali bhāgā.<BR> Cf. bhagna-viśīrṇa-samāracana, repairs to the rents in and the wornout parts of a building (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भग्नक्रिया
bhagna-kriyā (IA 7), same as bhagna-saṃskāra, repairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाग्यरेखा
bhāgya-rekhā (EI 3), line of fortune on the palm.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भमाति
bhamāti (EI 7), corruption of brahma-hatyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भैक्षक
bhaikṣaka (EI 21), land set apart for charity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भैत्र
bhaitra (IA 14), corruption of vahitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्षण|भक्षणं
bhakṣaṇa, Tamil pakkiṇam (SITI), confection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्तादाय
bhakt-ādāya (SITI), same as Tamil pakt-ātāyam (SITI), revenue in rice or paddy. Cf. bhakt-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ताय
bhakt-āya, cf. Kannaḍa bhatt-āya (SII 11-1); same as bhakt-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्तग्राम
bhakta-grāma, cf. bhatta-grāma, provision-village; village granted for maintenance (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, pp. 8, 92; cf. Vol. XVIII, pp. 191, 193).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ति|भक्तिः
bhakti (CII 4), devotion to a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ती
bhaktī (EI 8), name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्तोद्देशक
bhakt-oddeśaka (LL), Buddhist; distributor of food.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भं|भ|भः
Bhaṃ˚ (PJS), abbreviation of Bhaṇḍārin (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions). See Bhīṇḍārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भामण्डल
bhā-maṇḍala (HA), halo, aureole; same as prabhā-maṇḍala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भमती
bhamatī (HA), same as jagatī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भंडि|भण्डि|भंडिः|भण्डिः
bhaṃḍi (CITD), same as Telugu baṃḍi, ‘a cart’; really ‘a cart load’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भानसवेर्गडे
Bhānasa-věrgaḍě (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; same as Mahānas-ādhyakṣa; superintendent of the royal kitchen. Cf. Sūpakāra-pati, Khādyaṭapākika, Mahānasika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाणक|भाणकः
Bhāṇaka (LL), Buddhist; a preacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्ड|भांड|भांडं|भाण्डं|भाण्डः
bhāṇḍa, cf. bhaṇḍa (EI 5), a bale of goods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=049" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डभृतवहित्र
bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra (IE 8-8), ‘a wagon full of pots or jars’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डाध्यक्ष
Bhāṇḍ-ādhyakṣa (EI 28), officer in charge of the store-house. Cf. Bhāṇḍāgār-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागार|भांडागार|भाण्डागारः
bhāṇḍ-āgāra (EI 23, 30), a treasury or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागाराधिकृत
Bhāṇḍāgār-ādhikṛta (EI 12; BL; HRS), an officer employed in the treasury or store-house or the officer in charge of it. Cf. Bhāṇḍāgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागारप्रथम
Bhāṇḍāgāra-prathama (HD), the chief of the royal store-house or treasury. See JBBRAS, Vol. IX, p. 219.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डागारिक|भाण्डागारिकः
Bhāṇḍāgārika (IE 8-3; CII 4; HD; BL), officer in charge of the treasury or the royal store-house. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भण्डार
bhaṇḍāra, same as Sanskrit bhāṇḍāra; cf. Bhaṇḍārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डार|भांडार|भांडारं
bhāṇḍāra, cf. Tamil paṇḍāra-kkal (SITI), stone of standard weight used in the treasury; also cf. paṇḍāra-kkaṅkāṇi, treasury officer, supervisor of the treasury.<BR> (IA 23), the five images used in the worship of Bhūtas, e. g., Jārandāya, etc.<BR> Cf. paṇḍāram (SII 1), a treasury; a Śaiva mendicant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाण्डारपुस्तक
Bhāṇḍāra-pustaka, cf. Tamil baṇḍāra-ppottagam (EI 25), literally, ‘account book of the treasury’; a treasury accountant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भण्डारिन्
Bhaṇḍārin, Bhāṇḍārin (EI 9; SITI), officer in charge of the treasury; same as Bhāṇḍāgārika. Cf. Sejjeya-bhaṇḍārī (EI 13), ‘officer in charge of the stores in the king's bed-chamber’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भङ्ग|भंग|भंगः|भङ्गः
bhaṅga (Chamba), a land measure; a share or portion.<BR> (IA 23), hemp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भानु|भानुः
Bhānu (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भार|भारः
bhāra (EI 10), a weight equal to 2000 palas.<BR> (LP), probably, a load or bundle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भरक
bharaka (CII 4), name of a measure or weight; one load (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR> Cf. mahiṣ-oṣṭra-bharaka (IE 8-8), ‘a load on a buffalo or a camel’; cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भरण|भरणं|भरणः
bharaṇa (CII 4), name of a measure.<BR> (EI 1), probably, a load [of stones].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भारतवर्
Bhāratavar (SITI), Tamil; fishermen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भरतकला
Bharata-kalā (EI 33), the art of dancing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भारतीवृत्ति
Bhāratī-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart for expounding the Mahābhārata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=050" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भर्ग|भर्गः
Bharga (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भारिका
bhārikā (IE 8-5; EI 25), cf. bhārikāyāṃ vaṇik-putrasy=āṣṭottara-śataṃ rūpakāṇām; a crime, the nature of which is uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाषा
bhāṣā (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, a written declaration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाषाभेद
bhāṣā-bheda (LP), breach of words.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाष्यवृत्ति
Bhāṣya-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart for meeting the expenses of expounding the Śrī-Bhāṣya of Rāmānuja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट|भटः
Bhaṭa (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; EI 30; HD), same as Bhaṭa-manuṣya; probably derived from bhṛta which is sometimes used in its place. Generally used along with cāṭa or chātra; literally, ‘a soldier’; but really a Pāik, Barkandāz or Piāda, i. e. a constable. It is spelt as bhaṭṭa in the medieval inscriptions of Eastern India, though rarely the two are distinguished. See Bhaṭṭa.<BR> (SITI), a personal servant or soldier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाटक|भाटकं|भाटकः
bhāṭaka (EI 30), same as prabhāṭaka; rent or hiring charges; cf. naukā-bhāṭaka (EI 14).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भटमनुष्य
Bhaṭa-manuṣya (IE 8-3; EI 31; LL), explained as ‘a soldier, policeman or warden’; a Barkandāz, Pāik or Piāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भटार
Bhaṭāra (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa corruption of Bhaṭṭāraka; also spelt Bhaḍāra and Bhal̤āra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्ट|भट्टः
Bhaṭṭa (IE 8-3), cf. a-caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-praveśa (IE 8-5); same as Bhaṭa of earlier records; but rarely distinguished from Bhaṭa, Bhaṭṭa in that ease meaning ‘a minstrel’.<BR> (CII 3, 4; etc.), a title of respect attached to the names of learned Brāhmaṇas.<BR> (IE 8-3), a minstrel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टा
Bhaṭṭā˚ (PJS), abbreviation of Bhaṭṭāraka (in medieval Jain inscriptions); an epithet of Jain teachers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टभाग
Bhaṭṭa-bhāga (EI 15), same as bhaṭṭa-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टग्राम
Bhaṭṭa-grāma (EI 15, 25), a village owned by learned Brāhmaṇas as a rent-free holding; same as an agrahāra village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टामाकुतिक
Bhaṭṭāmākutika (EI 7), an official designation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टमहत्तर
Bhaṭṭa-mahattara (EI 30), a Bhaṭṭa who was a Mahattara, or a leading Bhaṭṭa. Bhaṭṭa may not be a corruption of paṭṭa (cf. Bhaṭṭa-nāyaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टनायक
Bhaṭṭa-nāyaka (EI 9), see Bhaṭṭa and Nāyaka (chief of a district) as well as Bhaṭṭa-mahattara. Cf. also Paṭṭa-nāyaka of medieval Orissan epigraphs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=051" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टपुत्र
Bhaṭṭaputra (EI 4; LP; BL), title of Brāhmaṇas; epithet of a Brāhmaṇa whose father was famous for learning.<BR> (LP), explained as ‘sepoys or soldiers’.<BR> (EI 11), explained as ‘a panegyrist’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारक|भट्टारकः
Bhaṭṭāraka (IE 8-2; CII 3; EI 30), title used in Sanskrit but really Prakrit derived from Sanskrit bhartṛ through the plural form bhartāraḥ = Prakrit bhaṭṭāra (see Svāmin); often suffixed to the personal names of paramount sovereigns as well as of feudatory Mahārājas, or Yuvarājas (crown-princes); applied to gods and priests in the sense of ‘worthy of worship or sacred’. Cf. bappa-bhaṭṭāraka-pāda-parigṛhīta, bhaṭṭāraka-Mahāsena-parigṛhīta, etc.<BR> (EI 33), the king.<BR> (SII 1), title of Jain religious teachers.<BR> (CII 4), title of Śaiva ascetics, etc.<BR> (LP), a respected man.<BR> (EI 11), probably, epithet of the chief priest of a temple.<BR> (SITI), a deity; a spiritual preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारकपादानुध्यात
Bhaṭṭāraka-pād-ānudhyāta (CII 4), ‘meditating on (or, favoured by) the feet of the lord paramount’; epithet of the feudatories and officers of the Gupta emperors and later imperial rulers. See Paramabhaṭṭāraka-pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारकप्रभ
Bhaṭṭārakaprabha (CII 4), a title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टराणक
Bhaṭṭa-rāṇaka (EI 9) see Bhaṭṭa, Rāṇaka, Bhaṭṭa-mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टवृत्ति
Bhaṭṭa-vṛtti (EI 25; SII 1), a grant for the maintenance of the Bhaṭṭas or learned Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टवृत्तिमान्य
Bhaṭṭavṛtti-mānya (SITI), tax-free land (inām) given for the support of Brāhmaṇas; same as bhaṭṭa-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टारिका
Bhaṭṭārikā (EI 23; CII 3; etc.), feminine form of Bhaṭṭāraka (q. v.); a title of the wives of independent and feudatory rulers; often suffixed to personal names.<BR> Cf. Tamil paṭṭārikai (SITI), name of the goddess Durgā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भट्टोपाध्याय
Bhaṭṭ-opādhyāya (EI 23), title of a Brāhmaṇa teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भौलि
bhauli, bhaulī (Chamba), a share, portion or allotment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भौमयन्त्र
bhauma-yantra (IA 14), a particular mystic diagram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भव|भवं|भवः
Bhava (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाव|भावः
bhāva (EI 26), a brother-in-law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भवन|भवनं|भवनः
bhavana (LL), a temple. Cf. pura, āyatana, ālaya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भावना
bhāvanā (CII 4), sentiment, e. g., maitrī, etc.<BR> (EI 3), Jain; a method of kāy-otsarga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=052" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भवसृज्
Bhavasṛj (CII 3), ‘the creator of existence’; an epithet of the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भावशुद्धि|भावशुद्धिः
bhāva-śuddhi (CII 1), purity of mind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भवत्|भवन्त्
bhavat, cf. sa bhavān (EI 3), same as tatrabhavān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाविनी
Bhāvinī (IA 10), same as Devadāsī; a dancing girl attached to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भविष्यक्किडैप्पु
bhaviṣya-kkiḍai-ppur̤am (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax-free land set apart to enable a teacher to reside permanently in a village for teaching.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भव्य|भव्यं|भव्यः
bhavya (EI 3, 8), the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाव्य|भाव्यं
bhāvya, cf. rāja-bhāvya-sarva-pratyāya-sameta (EI 23), income, levies; same as ābhāvya. According to some, bhāvya and ābhāvya mean pāghd̤ī. Cf. talār-ābhāvya.<BR> (LP), probably the same as bhāvyapada-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेरी
bherī (SITI, ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेरुण्ड|भेरुंड|भेरुण्डं|भेरुण्डः
bheruṇḍa (EI 31), a shortened form of gaṇḍabheruṇḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेत्
bhet (IA 11), Pañjābī; low lands inundated by rivers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेट
bheṭa (IE 8-5; EI 29), presents to be offered by a subject or subordinate to a ruler on occasions; occasional offering of money or presents; same as vandāpanā. See bheṭana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भेटन
bheṭana (LP), a present or gift; cf. bheṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीदा
bhīdā (LP), ‘straitened circumstances’; cf. Gujarātī bhīd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षा
bhikṣā (IE 8-4), a grant or endowment; cf. ekādaśa-Rudra-bhikṣā (EI 32), an endowment in the gods’ name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षु|भिक्षुः
Bhikṣu (EI 7, 21; CII 3; ML), Buddhist monk, also called Śākya-bhikṣu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुहल
Bhikṣu-hala (LL), ‘the monks’ land’; rent-free land in the possession of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुहलपरिहार
Bhikṣuhala-parihāra, cf. Prakrit Bhikhuhala-parihāra (HRS), known from Śātavāhana records as a number of privileges relating to rent-free land belonging to the community of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुणी
Bhikṣuṇī (EI 25; CII 3; LL), feminine form of Bhikṣu; ‘a Buddhist nun’; also called Śākya-bhikṣuṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुण्युपाश्रय
Bhikṣuṇy-upāśraya (LL), Buddhist; a nunnery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुणीसङ्घ
Bhikṣuṇī-saṅgha, cf. bhikkhuṇī-saṃgha (EI 23), a community of nuns.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुराज
Bhikṣurāja (LL), title of a pious [Jain] king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिक्षुसङ्घ|भिक्षुसङ्घः
Bhikṣu-saṅgha (EI 26; CII 4), community of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=053" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीमप्रिय
Bhīmapriya (EI 11), name of a coin (dramma).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीमसेनिकर्पूर
bhīmaseni-karpūra (SII 13), a kind of camphor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भिषक्
Bhiṣak (HD), the king's medical advisor. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR> (EI 24), a physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीष्माष्टमी
Bhīṣmāṣṭamī (IA 17), Māgha su-di 8 or amānta Māgha (i. e. pūrṇimānta Phālguna) va-di 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीट्
bhīṭ (IA 15), see bhīṭī and bhṛṣṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भितरभण्डारअधिकारिन्
Bhītara-bhaṇḍāra-adhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 28), Od̤iyā; Sanskrit Abhyantara-bhāṇḍār-ādhikārin, ‘officer in charge of the inner store-house or treasury (i. e. one within the palace or the harem)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीतरनवर
bhītara-navara (EI 28), Od̤iyā = Sanskrit abhyantara-nagara; the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीठ
bhīṭha (EI 31), probably, a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीटी
bhīṭī (IA 15), see bhṛṣṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भित्तिचित्र
bhitti-citra, wall-painting (Journ. Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 141).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भित्वरमान्य
Bhitvaramānya (IA 17), probably, a mistake for Abhitva-ramāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोग|भोगः
bhoga (IE 8-4; CII 3; EI 23, 33), literally, ‘enjoyment’ (cf. bhukti); a jāgīr (cf. Mahārāja-Sarvanātha-bhoga, Mahā-sāmantādhipati-Śrīdhara-bhoga, etc.); possession (cf. bhog-ādhīnā gṛhītā). Originally ‘enjoyment’; then ‘property’, ‘a jāgīr’; then also a territorial unit which was generally the subdivision of a district (IE 8-4; EI 25; 28; CII 4). See bhukti, āhāra.<BR> Cf. Kaivarta-bhoga (IE 8-4; EI 2; CII 1), the fishermen's preserve.<BR> (IE 8-5; EI 29, 30; HRS), periodical supplies of fruits, firewood, flowers and the like which the villagers had to supply to the king; sometimes explained as ‘tax in kind’ (CII 4).<BR> (EI 1), [an object of] enjoyment.<BR> (SITI), tax-free land set apart for the enjoyment of a person for the performance of specified services; same as mānya. See bhogottara, Bhogin, etc.<BR> Cf. bhoge (LP), ‘for the right of enjoyment’.<BR> Cf. sa-bhoga (IA 9), privilege of the donee of rent-free land; probably refers to aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=054" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगभाग
bhoga-bhāga (CII 3, etc.,), the same as bhāga-bhoga. Cf. bhoga-bhāga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi (EI 23), royal dues; see bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगजनपद
bhoga-janapada (EI 12), probably, a free-holding in the country-side, or a rent-free area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगलाभ|भोगलाभः
bhoga-lābha (EI 33), usufruct in lieu of interest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगपति|भोगपतिः
Bhogapati (IE 8-3; EI 25, 27; HD), an Ināmdār or Jāgīr-dār, or an officer in charge of inām lands or jāgīrs, or the officer in charge of a territorial unit called bhoga. The last alternative is more probable; cf. Bhogika, etc. See also Mitākṣarā on the Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 320; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 298. See Bhuktipati, Bhogikapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगपतिक
Bhogapatika (IE 8-3; EI 23), same as Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगपत्र
bhoga-patra (ASLV, SITI), a deed recording conveyance of land; a lease deed; the deed of re-conveyance of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगस्त्री
bhoga-strī, a concubine (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 272).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगत्रा
bhogatrā (IE 8-5), same as bhogottara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगावनीय
bhogāvanīya (LP), ‘should be enjoyed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगायक
bhog-āyaka (ASLV, SITI), land held as the result of a mortgage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिजन
Bhogi-jana (EI 33), explained as ‘a village headman’. Cf. Bhogika,<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिक|भोगिकः
Bhogika (IE 8-3; CII 3; HD; BL), the owner of a bhoga or jāgīr; a Jāgīrdār or Ināmdār; same as Bhogin. See Bhoktṛ. Explained by some as the head of a district, or the collector of the State's share of the produce of lands taken in kind (Bomb. Gaz., Vol. I, Part i, p. 82). See CII, Vol. III, pp. 96, 104.<BR> (IE 8-3); EI 18; 23), a groom or horse-keeper, according to lexicons; cf. its Telugu modification Bhoi, ‘a palanquin-bearer’. But these meanings may have been derived from the first as the people appear to have enjoyed rent-free land for their services.<BR> (EI 33), same as Bhojaka meaning a Jāgīrdār or Ināmdār.<BR> (CII 4), explained as ‘the head of a bhoga’.<BR> (EI 5), explained as ‘a village proprietor’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिकपाल
Bhogikapāla, Bhogikapālaka (EI 5; CII 4; BL), superintendent of the jāgīrs and cess collector^1; cf. Bhogapati.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिन्
Bhogin (IE 8-3; EI 12, 28, 29, 30; BL), one in possession of a bhoga or jāgīr; a Jāgīrdār; same as Bhogika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगीन
bhogīna (EI 13), cf. dattidāyaka-sādhupratipādita-prāg-bhujyamān-āvicchinna-bhogīna-bhuvām [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-056" target="_blank">Page-056+ 40</a>] translated rather loosely as ‘of the pieces of land in all the places that have been obtained in good manner from liberal donors’; probably, ‘[land] under possession’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=055" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिनी
bhoginī, cf. bogi (EI 7), a concubine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगिरूप
bhogi-rūpa (EI 12, 28), one who enjoys a free-holding as a representative of the real free-holder, or a title-holder who is not in actual possession of the land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगियार्
bhogiyār (SITI), Tamil; mistress, concubine; cf. bhogyār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगोद्धरणिक
Bhog-oddharaṇika (HD), explained as ‘the collector of the king's share of the grains’; cf. bhoga, caur-oddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगोत्तर
bhogottara (IE 8-5; EI 33), corrupt form of bhogatrā; land granted to the family priest for his services; grant for the enjoyment of a Brāhmaṇa or deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोग्या
bhogyā, cf. pokiyār (SITI), a concubine; see bhogiyār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोग्यतिथि
bhogya-tithi (CII 3), the portion of a tithi that is still to run.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोइ
Bhoi, Telugu modification of Sanskrit Bhogin (q. v.); palanquin-bearer (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 308, note 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोज|भोजः
Bhoja, Bhojaka (IE 8-2; EI 1; 27; HD; LL), a Jāgīrdār; title of a feudatory; cf. the feminine form Bhojikī; also Mahā-bhoja. See Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5.<BR> (EI 3; CII 3), a priest; title of a class of priests.<BR> Cf. Tamil pośar (SITI), one who enjoys a thing; the possessor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनचतुःशाल
bhojana-catuḥśāla (LL), Buddhist; a dining hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनआक्षयणी
bhojana-ākṣayiṇī, bhojan-ākṣayiṇī^1 (EI 32), a permanent endowment created for the maintenance of the donee; cf. akṣayanīvī, grāmagrāsa, etc.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Jim Funderburk on 20160315. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/CORRECTIONS/issues/252. note: ? Bojana+akzayiRI. Note change 'ya' to 'yi'.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनमण्डप
bhojana-maṇḍapa (LL), Buddhist; a refectory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजनशाला
bhojana-śālā (EI 23), an almshouse; a free-feeding house. Cf. sattra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोजिकी
Bhojikī (LL), wife of a Bhojaka (q. v.). cf. Mahābhojī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोज्पुरी
Bhojpurī, language and people of the Bhojpur Pargana of the Shahabad District of Bihar and the adjoining regions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोक्तृ
Bhoktṛ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 193), same as Bhogin, Bhogika; an Ināmdār or Jāgīrdar; cf. Sammāṇaka-bhoktā; also Bhoktāri (EI 11), a free-holder.<BR> (BL), a proprietor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=056" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोट्टविष्टि
Bhoṭṭa-viṣṭi (HRS), known from Nepal records; forced labour for carrying loads for officers sent to Tibet. See H. Rev. Syst., p. 233.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ्रमजलगति
bhrama-jala-gati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 98), probably, a sluice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भृष्टी
bhṛṣṭī (IA 15), ‘raised ground [near a tank] for planting piper betel’; cf. bhīṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भृत|भृतः
bhṛta (LP), loaded.<BR> (IE 8-8), cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra, ‘a wagonful of pots or jars’. See bharaka.<BR> Cf. a-bhṛta-prāvesya for a-bhaṭa-prāveśya, bhṛta being used for bhaṭa in the sense of a Pāik, Barkandāz or Piāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भू
bhū (IA 17), a land measure; equal to four bhū-māṣakas. See bhūmi.<BR> (EI 9), a land measure or a plot of land.<BR> (IE 7-1-2; EI 15, 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूभृत्
bhūbhṛt (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूधर|भूधरः
bhūdhara (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूच्छिद्रन्याय
bhūcchidra-nyāya (EI 22), same as bhūmicchidra-nyāya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलन्माडै
Bhujabalan-māḍai (SITI), name of a coin of the māḍai (māḍha) type. See māḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलप्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्
Bhujabalapratāpacakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलप्रौढप्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्
Bhujabalaprauḍhapratāpacakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजङ्ग|भुजंग|भुजंगः|भुजङ्गः
bhujaṅga (IA 20), an ogre. The word bhujaṅga was adopted in Javanese in the sense of a ‘pupil, disciple, scholar; a philologist, poet, literary councillor; an officially appointed professional usually residing at or near the court’. It has been suggested on this basis that Bhavadeva-bhaṭṭa's title Bālavalabhī-bhujaṅga may really mean ‘the pupil of the Bālavalabhī school’. See IHQ, Vol. XXVII, pp. 80-82.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजिष्यपत्र
bhujiṣya-patra (EI 24), a document granting maintenance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुज्यमान
bhujyamāna (IA 18), also prabhujyamāna; ‘being enjoyed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्ततिथि
bhukta-tithi (CII 3), the elapsed portion of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्ति|भुक्तिः
bhukti (IE 8-4; EI 28, 33), a province including a group of districts called viṣaya or maṇḍala; small territorial unit like a Pargana in South India; cf. bhoga.<BR> (IE 8-3; 8-4; CII 3), literally, ‘enjoyment’; same as bhoga; a jāgīr; originally meaning ‘enjoyment’; then ‘property’ or ‘a jāgīr’; then ‘a province’. See bhoga.<BR> (BL), personal property. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-058" target="_blank">Page-058+ 40</a>]<BR> Cf. putti, pukti (SITI), the enjoyment of a property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=057" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्तिमण्डल
bhukti-maṇḍala (IE 8-4), originally a bhukti but later on a maṇḍala; cf. Daṇḍabhukti-maṇḍala, āhāra-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुक्तिपति
Bhuktipati (IE 8-3), a Jāgīrdār; or, the officer in charge of a territorial unit called bhukti. See Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमाषक
bhūmāṣaka (IA 17), a land measure, four bhūmāṣakas making one bhū (q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुम्भुक
bhumbhuka (EI 13), Kannaḍa; cf. bhuvana-bhumbhuka, probably, ‘an ornament of the world’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमि|भूमिः
bhūmi, bhūmī (EI 3; CII 3), a particular land measure; sometimes also called bhū and regarded as equal to four bhū-māṣakas (cf. bhū).<BR> (CII 4), a territorial division.<BR> (EI 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्र
bhūmicchidra (IE 8-5), sometimes explained as ‘uncultivable land’. See bhūmicchidra-nyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रन्याय
bhūmicchidra-nyāya (IE 8-5; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HRS), literally, ‘the maxim of the fallow land’; the principle of the rent-free enjoyment of land by one who brings it under cultivation for the first time. See Ep. Ind., Vol XXIX, p. 86. The maxim is based on the old custom of allowing a person, who first brings a plot of fallow or jungle land under cultivation for the first time, to enjoy it without paying rent. Bhūmicchidra gradually came to mean ‘uncultivable land’. See bhūmicchidrapidhāna-nyāya, avanirandhra-nyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रपिधानन्याय
bhūmicchidrapidhāna-nyāya (IE 8-5; EI 11), the same as bhūmicchidra-nyāya; but it means ‘the maxim of covering up the hole in the land’ referring probably to the reclamation of fallow land for the first time; cf. bhūmicchidra understood in the sense of kṛṣy-ayogyā bhū, ‘land unfit for cultivation’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, p. 86.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रविधानन्याय
bhūmicchidravidhāna-nyāya (EI 24); same as bhūmicchidra-nyāya, bhumicchidrapidhāna-nyāya. Chidra-vidhāna = furrowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिपेण्डे
bhūmipeṇḍe (ASLV), a mark of honour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिपुत्र|भूमिपुत्रः
bhūmi-putra cf. pūmi-puttirar (SITI), husbandmen regarded as the sons of Mother Earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूप|भूपः
bhūpa (IA 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुर्ज
bhurja (IE 3-2), really ‘the birch’; but same as lekhana; a written document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूस्फोट|भूस्फोटः
bhūsphoṭa (EI 9), a mushroom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=058" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूत|भूतं|भूतः
bhūta (CII 1), a living being.<BR> (IE 8-5), the element or nature.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR> (CII 3, etc.), a fiscal term; cf. sa-bhūta-pāta-pratyāya, in which we have sometimes pātta (mistake for upātta), upātta, āvāta or vāta. See bhūta-pāta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतबलि|भूतबलिः
bhūta-bali (EI 11; SII 13), explained as ‘offering of boiled rice to the ghosts’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतकोट्य
bhūta-koṭya (IA 23), the place of residence of the family ghost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपात
bhūta-pāta, cf. sa-bhūta-pāta-pratyāya (IE 8-5); often written as bhūta-vāta and bhūt-opātta; probably, an event relating to the elements, such as an earthquake. See bhūta-pāta-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपातप्रत्याय
bhūta-pāta-pratyāya (CII 4), explained by some as ‘excise and octroi duties’; but really, ‘the income resulting from storms, earthquakes, changes in the course of a river, etc’. See bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc. Pāta may be a mistake for upātta or vāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतप्रत्याय
bhūta-pratyāya (CII 3), an income derived from natural changes in the land. See bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपूर्व
bhūtapūrva (CII 1), ‘existing in the past’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतवातप्रत्याय
bhūta-vāta-pratyāya (EI 23; CII 4; HRS), ‘the income derived from the elements and the winds’; explained by some as ‘excise and octroi duties’; but really, ‘the income resulting from storms, earthquakes, changes in the course of a river, etc.’ See bhūt-opātta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतोपात्तप्रत्याय
bhūt-opātta-pratyāya (EI 32), income brought about by elemental or natural changes (e. g. storms, earthquakes, etc.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूवर
Bhūvara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 98), ‘a king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिघा
bighā, bīghā (IE 8-6), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीजक|बीजकः
bījaka, cf. bījak (EI 9), an inscribed stone or an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीजसंस्कार
bīja-saṃskāra (CII 4), an astronomical term.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीलानुवृत्ति
bīl̤-ānuvṛtti, also called bīl̤a-vṛtti (599 11-1), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; fief held by a king's subordinate for his maintenance; cf. anuga-jīvita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिल्कोडे
bilkoḍe (EI 28), Kannaḍa; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिं
biṃ˚ (PJS), abbreviation of bimba, ‘an image’ (especiacially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिम्ब|बिंब|बिंबं|बिम्बं|बिंबः|बिम्बः
bimba (IA 3; HA), same as pratimā; an image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिन्दुक
binduka, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिराड
birāḍa (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=059" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीरवणपारिखाय
bīravaṇa-pārikhāya (IA 19), levy stated to have been of four kinds; cf. nidhi-nikṣepa-jala-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-chatuṣ-prakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikhāya-sahitaṃ which is mentioned along with aṣṭabhogatejassvāmya-daṇḍa-śulka-yuktam; Sanskrit vīra-paṇa (tax for the maintenance of constables) and pārīkṣ-āya (pārīkṣika).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिरुद|बिरुदः
biruda (SII 1), also spelt viruda; ‘a surname’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिशी
Biśī (EI 24), derived from Viṣayin (Viṣayapati), the governor of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीस्व
bīsva (EI 28), a land measure equal to (1/20) of a bīghā; derived from Sanskrit viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बीटक
bīṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 279), modern bīd̤ā (i. e. a betel bīd̤ā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बित्तुवट्ट
bittuvaṭṭa (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 10), Kannaḍa; probably also called bittukaṭṭe; explained as ‘a portion of the produce derived from the lands irrigated by tanks, or wet land irrigated by a tank, granted to the person who built the tank or repaired it.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोधि|बोधिः
bodhi (LL), Buddhist; supreme knowledge^1 attained by the Buddha; the tree of enlightenment; cf. mahābodhi, saṃbodhi.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोधिचक्र
bodhi-cakra (LL), Buddhist; the wheel of enlightenment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोधिसत्त्व|बोधिसत्त्वं|बोधिसत्त्वः
Bodhisattva (CII 2-1; LL), Buddhist; a would-be Buddha in a previous birth. Cf. Chadmastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोध्यङ्ग
bodhyaṅga, cf. bojjhaṅga (EI 5), Buddhist; seven in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोडिया
Bod̤iyā, local name of the Gujarātī alphabet (Ind. Ep., p. 55).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोम्मलाट
bommalāṭa (ASLV), a puppet show.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोप्प
boppa (CII 3), a Prakrit word meaning ‘the father’; see bappa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोट
boṭa, also spelt voṭa (CII 3), a termination of geographical names; meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बोत्कट
botkaṭa (IA 19), a goat; cf. Deśī bokkaḍa; also varkara (IA 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रा
Brā, abbreviation of Brāhmaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 55).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मचारिन्
brahmacārin (SII 2; LL), a Brāhmaṇa student; an unmarried student of the Vedas.<BR> (BL), epithet of one who takes a vow of celibacy.<BR> (SII 2), a temple servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदान
brahma-dāna, cf. pirama-dānam (SITI), gift to Brāhmaṇas; same as brahmadāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदाय|ब्रह्मदायः
brahmadāya (EI 23; CII 4), gift to a Brāhmaṇa; the rent-free [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-061" target="_blank">Page-061+ 40</a>] holding of Brāhmaṇas; same as brahmadeya. See brahmatrā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=060" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदेय|ब्रह्मदेयः
brahmadeya (EI 30; ASLV; HRS; SITI), land or village given as gift (generally tax-free) to Brāhmaṇas; land to be granted to or in the possession of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मदेयक्कि
brahmadeya-kkil̤̣avar (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; sole owner of a Brahmadeya village; sometimes supposed to be the headman or chief of a Brahmadeya village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्माधिराज
Brahm-ādhirāja (SITI), title of distinguished Brāhmaṇa military commanders; also spelt Brahmādarāya in Tamil. See Brahma-mahārāja, Brahma-rāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्महत्या
brahma-hatyā (CITD), killing a Brāhmaṇa, considered to be a great sin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मकल्प|ब्रह्मकल्पः
brahma-kalpa (CITD), the kalpa or age of the god Brahman, extending to many thousands of years.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मक्षत्र
Brahma-kṣatra, Brahma-kṣatriya (EI 5, 12, 24), a Kṣatriya family claiming descent from a Brāhmaṇa parent; a family in which the blood of the Brāhmaṇas and Kṣatriyas has been mixed. See Vishveshvaranand Ind. Journ., Vol. I, pp. 87 ff., etc. In one record (Journ. Karnatak Univ., Vol. II, No 2, January 1959, p. 47), the Nāgavaṃśa, to which a Kadamba king's minister Māyideva belonged, is called Brahma-kṣatra because it originated from the intercourse^1 of its progenitor Nāgarāja with a Brāhmaṇa girl. Brahma-vaiśya should be likewise explained.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्ममहाराज
Brahma-mahārāja, cf. pirama-mārāyan̤ (SITI), title of Brāhmaṇa ministers. See Brahm-ādhirāja, Brahmarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्ममन्त्र
brahma-mantra (IA 12), five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्ममेध
brahma-medha, cf. pirama-metam (SITI), special funeral rite for a saintly person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मन्
Brahman (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मणराशक्काणम्
brāhmaṇa-rāśa(rāja)-kkāṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax payable by the Brāhmaṇa (Purohita) to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मणविंशति
brāhmaṇa-viṃśati (HRS), title upon villagers for the maintenance of the Brāhmaṇas; tenure of (1/20) of the revenue of an area granted to the Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्माण्ड|ब्रह्मांड|ब्रह्माण्डं
brahmāṇḍa (EI 16, 21), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मण्य|ब्रह्मण्यः
brahmaṇya (EI 22) ‘hospitable to the Brāhmaṇas’; see Paramabrahmaṇya, Atibrahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मण्य|ब्राह्मण्यः
brāhmaṇya (SII 1), the community of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मपुर
brahmapura (EI 2), same as brahmapurī; a rent-free village in the possession of Brāhmaṇas; same as agrahāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=061" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मपुरी
brahmapurī (EI 4, 28; SITI), also called agara-brahmadeya (Sanskrit agrahāra-brahmadeya); a Brāhmaṇa settlement. See brahmapura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मराज
Brahmarāja (SITI), title of a Brāhmaṇa minister.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मराक्षस|ब्रह्मराक्षसः
Brahmarākṣasa (EI 3, 16), a Brāhmaṇa defeated in disputations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मराय
Brahmarāya (SITI), same as Brahmarāja. Cf. Brahm-ādhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मर्षि|ब्रह्मर्षिः
Brahmarṣi (EI 22), a Brāhmaṇa sage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मस्तम्ब|ब्रह्मस्तम्बः
brahma-stamba (CII 4), a settlement of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मस्थान|ब्रह्मस्थानः
brahma-sthāna (SII 13; SITI), explained as ‘an assembly hall’; the Brāhmaṇa quarters of a village; cf. Tamil pirummastānam (SITI), the quarters of the Brāhmaṇas where the village assembly (sabhā) used to meet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मास्य
Brahmāsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मत्रा
brahmatrā (IE 8-5), same as brahmadāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मवैश्य
Brahma-vaiśya (A. R. Ep., 1919, No. 208); cf. Brahma-kṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मयज्ञ|ब्रह्मयज्ञः
brahma-yajña (EI 22; CII 4), study of the Vedas; name of a mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मी
Brāhmī, name of an early Indian alphabet, from which a large number of alphabets of India and some other countries have derived.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्रह्मोत्तर|ब्रह्मोत्तरं
brahmottara (IE 8-5), Bengali; corrupt form of brahmatrā.<BR> (IA 15), explained as ‘the sanctuary of a temple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृह
Bṛha, abbreviation of Bṛhatpuruṣa (q. v.). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहच्छुल्क
bṛhac-chulka, cf. Kannaḍa perjuṅka, perujuṅka, pejjuṅka, hejjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Bṛhad-aśvavāra, a cavalry officer (Tripathi, History of Kanauj, p. 137).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=557" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्भोगिक
Bṛhad-bhogika (IE 8-3), same as Bṛhad-bhogin; see Bhogika and Aṃśa-bṛhadbhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्भोगिन्
Bṛhad-bhogin (IE 8-3; EI 28, 29; BL), same as Bṛhadbhogika; a chief jāgīrdār; see Bhogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्देव
Bṛhaddeva, cf. Tamil Periya-devar (SITI), literally, ‘the great king’; the predecessor or predecessors of the ruling monarch; also called Periya-perumāl̤ sometimes indicating the paramount sovereign or emperor. Cf. Bṛhan-nṛpati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्धल|बृहद्धलं
bṛhaddhala (EI 7), ‘the big plough’; name of a land measure (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 125); cf. hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्राज्ञी
Bṛhad-rājñī (EI 4), same as Paṭṭa-rājñī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहदुपरिक
Bṛhad-uparika (EI 15, 26; HD), ‘the great governor of a province’; a viceroy. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9. Cf. Uparika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=062" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्वाछक
Bṛhad-vāchaka (LL), a Jain preacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहद्वाजिक
Bṛhad-vājika (LP), probably, a police officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहन्मान
bṛhan-māna (EI 23; CII 4), a measure larger than the standard one; cf. viṣaya-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहन्नृपति
Bṛhan-nṛpati (IE 8-2), predecessor of the ruling monarch; called Periya-devar in Tamil; cf. Od̤iyā Bad̤a-Narasiṃha and Telugu Pedda-Narasiṃha. See Bṛhaddeva. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 231 and note 2; JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 212.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहस्पतिसव|बृहस्पतिसवः
bṛhaspatisava (EI 22; CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहती
bṛhatī (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्कुमारमहापात्र
Bṛhat-kumāramahāpātra (EI 28), cf. Kumāra-mahāpātra which is similar to Kumārāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्पुरोहित
Bṛhat-purohita, cf. Bad̤ā-purohit (EI 24), ‘the high priest’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्पुरुष
Bṛhatpuruṣa, probably the same as Mahājana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 143-44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्सन्धिविग्रहिमहापात्र
Bṛhat-sandhivigrahi-mahāpātra (EI 28), same as Mahā-sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्तन्त्रपति
Bṛhat-tantrapati (IE 8-3; EI 33), explained by a Kashmirian commentator as the Dharmādhikārin who was a judge also in charge of charities; cf. the Muslim official designation S̤adrus̤-s̤udūr, etc., explained as ‘the chief judge and grand almoner, or the custodian of the king's bequests and charities’ (Journ. As. Soc. Pak., Vol. IV, pp. 53-54).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहवार
bṛha-vāra, (EI 31; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 125 and note), Saturday or Thurdsday (A. Venkatasubbiah, Some Śaka Dates in Inscriptions, pp. 57ff.); same as Vadḍa-vāra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृन्दावन
bṛndāvana (EI 12), a tomb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुद्ध|बुद्धः
Buddha (LL), Buddhist; a class of saints. See Bodhisattva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुद्धचैत्य
buddha-caitya (EI 28), a Buddhist shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुद्धाधिष्ठान
buddh-ādhiṣṭhāna (EI 22), a city or locality in the possession of a Buddhist monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बु
Bud̤hāleṅkā (IE 8-3), Od̤iyā; same as Mahāpādamūlika, ‘chief attendant.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुधाष्टमी
budh-āṣṭamī (IA 26), the eighth tithi on a Wednesday.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुल्लगकर
bullaga-kara (HRS), tax relating to the supervision of meals according to the Abhidhānarājendra, s. v. kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बूरेडु
būreḍu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown quantity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुस|बुसं
busa (IE 8-5), chaff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बुसिभंडालु
busi-bhaṃḍālu (CITD), Telugu; probably, stores of unhusked grain. Cf. kola-bhaṃdālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=063" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बूटीय
būṭīya (EI 32), a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चब
caba (Chamba), wet land, marshy land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चबूतरा
cabūtarā (EI 32), Hindī; a platform.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाड
Cāḍa (IE 8-3), same as Cāṭa (q. v.) and the modern Cād̤ of Chamba, the latter being the designation of the head of a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चा
cād̤ā (LP), a camp; an attacking party.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्रपवित्र
caitra-pavitra, caitra-pavitraka (EI 7, 18), name of a rite (Ind. Ant., Vol. XXXVIII, p. 52); caitra is the daman-āropaṇa ceremony which takes place in the month of Caitra and pavitra is the pavitr-āropaṇa ceremony which occurs in Śrāvaṇa (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 274, notes 12-13); cf. Kannaḍa caitra-pavitr-ābhyāgat-ādi pūje gal̤gaṃ, translated as ‘for the caitra and pavitra and the entertainment of guests and other rites’ (IA 30).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्य|चैत्यं|चैत्यः
caitya (EI 22, 33; BL), a prayer hall; usually, a place of worship in a Buddhist monastery; same as caitya-gṛha.<BR> (EI 6, CII 4), same as stūpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यागार
caity-āgāra (SII 1), a Jain temple; same as caity-ālaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यगृह
caitya-gṛha (EI 8, 33, LL), Buddhist; cf. Prakrit cetiya-ghara. (EI 24), the hall for worship or prayer; hall in a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यकशैल
caityaka-śaila, a stone pillar raised in memory of a dead person on his cremation ground (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 133). See yaṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यालय
caity-ālaya (EI 7), same as caitya.<BR> (EI 3; SII 1), a Jain temple; same as caity-āgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यपट्ट
caitya-paṭṭa (LL), Buddhist; a slab bearing the representation of a caitya. See cakra-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यशैल
Caitya-śaila (EI 24), a Buddhist school.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यवन्दन
caitya-vandana (HA), obeissance to and worship of the Jina with recitation of hymns, etc., and meditating on the qualities of a Jina.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चैत्यिक
Caityika (EI 24), same as Caitya-śaila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चकली
cakalī, a small coin, smaller than the ṭaṃka regarded as (1/20) of a rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाकान्तर
cākāntara (EI 3), a village institution of uncertain meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्र|चक्रं|चक्रः
cakra, cf. Cakrin (EI 4); a district; same as maṇḍala.<BR> Cf. sakkaram (SITI), wheel of authority; the king's order; an officer entrusted with the execution of the king's order. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-065" target="_blank">Page-065+ 40</a>]<BR> (CII 3), ‘the discus’; an emblem on seals.<BR> Cf. śakkara-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax paid by potters; also called tirigai-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=064" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रपट्ट
cakra-paṭṭa (LL), Buddhist; a slab bearing the representation of a wheel. See caitya-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रवालगिरि
Cakravāla-giri (SITI), same as Tamil Śakkaravāl̤am; a mythical mountain encircling the earth; the horizon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रवर्तिक्षेत्र
cakravarti-kṣetra (IE 8-2; EI 33), the sphere of influence of an Indian imperial ruler lying between the Himalayas and the three seas, viz. Bay of Bengal, Indian Ocean and Arabian Sea; sometimes regarded as conterminous with Āryāvarta or Dākṣiṇātya. See Sircar, Stud. Geog. Anc. Med. Ind., pp. 1 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रवर्तिन्|चक्रवर्त्तिन्
Cakravartin (IE 8-2; EI 21, 28; CII 3, 4), a title of paramount sovereignty; the title of an emperor. See Saptama-cakravartin; also Cakreśvara, Cakrin.<BR> (IE 8-2), often suffixed to expressions like Pratāpa, Prauḍhapratāpa, Bhujabalapratāpa, Niḥśaṅkapratāpa, etc., and sometimes also to dynastic names like Yādava.<BR> (EI 31), epithet of the Buddha.<BR> (IE 8-2), cf. cakravarti-kṣetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रेश्वर|चक्रेश्वरः
Cakreśvara (EI 3), same as Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रिन्
Cakrin (EI 9), same as Cakravartin.<BR> (EI 4, 19), ‘the ruler of a cakra (circle) or district’; title of a provincial ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्षुस्
cakṣus (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR> Cf. Pali cakkhu (EI 5), Buddhist; vision, five in number.<BR> Cf. cakṣur-vadha, ‘killing at sight’, ‘killing instantaneously’; or probably ‘blinding of the eyes’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 307 and note 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चलमर्तिगण्ड
Calamartigaṇḍa (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a title of the Kākatīya kings; from Kannaḍa gaṇḍa meaning ‘the husband, lord, master,’ i. e. ‘one who can control or punish’, and Telugu calam meaning ‘obstinacy, rudeness, overbearing’; translated^1 as ‘one who is the controller or punisher of spiteful men or men of overbearing conduct’.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाली
cālī (IA 15), a system of land revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चलिवंदीलि
calivaṃdīli, caliveṃdala, caliveṃdra, calipaṃdili (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; halting place for travellers, where they are supplied gratis with milk and whey^1 or with water.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=065" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामर|चामरं|चामरः
cāmara (IE 8-8), name of a coin; cf. cāmara-māda.<BR> (SII 3), a fly-whisk. See cauri, cavarālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामरकुमार
Cāmara-kumāra, cf. Cavari-kumāra (EI 10), probably, a prince in charge of the fly-whisk which was one of the royal insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामरमाड
cāmara-māḍa (EI 7), name of a coin; cf. cāmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चम्पाषष्ठी
campā-ṣaṣṭhī (EI 5), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चमूनायक
Camūnāyaka (EI 27), a general; cf. Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चमूप|चमूपः
Camūpa (IA 10), a general; same as Camūpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चमूपति|चमूपतिः
Camūpati (EI 8-3); a general, same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चण्डप्रचण्ड
Caṇḍa-pracaṇḍa (SITI), divinities guarding the inner shrine of a Viṣṇu temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चण्डेश्वर|चंडेश्वर|चण्डेश्वरः
Caṇḍeśvara (SITI), traditional executive of Śiva temples; also called Ādi-dāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चण्देश्वरप्पेरुविलै
Caṇḍeśvara-pperuvilai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; literally, the sale-price of Caṇḍeśvara, the traditional executive of Śiva temples; actually, sale-price of land purchased from a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्र|चंद्र|चन्द्रं|चन्द्रः
candra (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रादित्यवत्
candrādityavat (SITI), same as Tamil candrādittaval, candrādittavar; ‘as long as the moon and the sun last’; ‘in perpetuity’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रग्रहण|चंद्रग्रहण
candra-grahaṇa (SII 1), lunar eclipse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रहास|चंद्रहास|चन्द्रहासं|चन्द्रहासः
candrahāsa (EI 25), name of Rāma's sword.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रक|चंद्रक|चन्द्रकं|चंद्रकः|चन्द्रकः
candraka (EI 2), the young moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रकालिकम्
candra-kālikam (LP), permanently.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रमस्|चंद्रमस्
candramas (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रार्कयोगपर्वन्
candr-ārka-yoga-parvan (EI 19), same as amāvāsyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रविशद
candra-viśada (LP), ‘as white as the moon’, i. e. guiltless.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्य्
candy (IA 26), Anglicised form of khaṇḍī, a weight of different value in different parts. See khaṇḍikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चङ्ग|चंग|चङ्गः
caṅga, see chaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चङ्क्रम
caṅkrama (LL), Prakrit caṃkama (EI 24); a promenade, a walk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चपलं|चपल|चपलः
capalaṃ (CII 1), quickly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर|चरः
Cara (CII 4), a spy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चार|चारं|चारः
Cāra (IE 8-3; EI 26), a spy; same as Cara; sometimes used in place of Cāṭa.<BR> (EI 15), cf. a-cār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE 8-5), probably, passage [of royal officers through a village]; cf. also a-pār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-067" target="_blank">Page-067+ 40</a>] with pāra (probably, ferrying) instead of cāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=066" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरबलीवर्द
cara-balīvarda (IE 8-5), cf. vara-balīvarda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरण|चरणं|चरणः
caraṇa (CII 4; IA 18, 20), a Vedic school; a sect or school studying a particular śākhā of the Vedas; e. g. Taittirīya-caraṇa.<BR> (CII 1), same as ācaraṇa; cf. dharma-caraṇa for dharm-ācaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चारण|चारणः
Cāraṇa (EI 3), same as Vidyā-cāraṇa, a Jain monk endowed with magical powers.<BR> Cf. harita-pakva-sasy-ekṣu-cāraṇa-lavaṇ-opamardana (IE 8-5); grazing of cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरण्डि
caraṇḍi (EI 31), Gujarātī; a narrow passage of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरी
carī (EI 33), pasture land; same as carī-kṣetra.<BR> (EI 21), grazing tax; grazing land. Cf. cārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चारी
cārī (LP), Gujarātī cāro, grass; probably, pasture land; cf. carī.<BR> (CII 4), grazing tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्मकार|चर्मकारः|चर्म्मकार|चर्म्मकारः
Carmakāra (EI 32), a shoe-maker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्मन्|चर्म्मन्
carman (EI 15), cf. a-carm-āṅgāraka (IE 8-5); hide-seat which the villagers were obliged to supply to the touring officers of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरु|चरुः
caru (EI 10, 22, 23; CII 3, 4), an offering to the manes; one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चरुक
caruka (EI 1), same as caru, one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्या|चर्य्या
caryā (CII 4), discipline in Śaivite practices.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चस्ह्
cash (IE 8-8), Anglicised form of Tamil kāśu; name of a small copper coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चट्
caṭ, cf. alīkaṃ caṭāpitam (LP), ‘circulated a false rumour’.<BR> Cf. caṭanti (LP); ‘to accumulate’; also cf. Gujarātī cad̤hśe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाट|चाटः
Cāṭa (HD), irregular soldiers according to Fleet and Bühler. Vogel (Ant. Ch. St., pp. 130-32) points out that Chamba is the only place where the ancient word Cāṭa is still extant in the modern form Cād̤ meaning ‘the head of a Parganā’. An important privilege of a gift village was ‘not to be entered by Cāṭas and Bhaṭas’. Inscriptions (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 221) often specify that the granted land was not to be entered by Cāṭas and Bhaṭas except for seizing robbers and those guilty of harm or treason to the king (cf. a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśyaṃ cora-drohaka-varjam in op. cit., Vol. VIII, p. 287). Sometimes we have bhaṭa-cāṭa-sevak-ādīn (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211) and caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-jātīyān janapadān (ibid., Vol. XIV, p. 160). [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-068" target="_blank">Page-068+ 40</a>]<BR> (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4), generally mentioned along with bhaṭa; sometimes replaced by cāra (spy) and chātra (literally, ‘umbrella-bearer’, but really, a constable, i. e. a Pāik or Piāda); probably indicates the leader of a group of Bhaṭas, i. e. Pāiks and Piādas; a policeman leading a group of Pāiks. See caṭṭa. Yājñavalkya, I. 336, speaks of the duty of the king to protect people from the harassment caused by cāṭas, robbers and Kāyasthas and the Mitākṣarā explains cāṭa as persons who deprive people of their wealth after creating false confidence in them. According to Bṛhaspati quoted by Aparārka, ‘dangers common to all are those arising from the cāṭas and thieves’. The word cāṭa in the passage tārkika-cāṭa-bhaṭa-rāj-āpraveśya in Śaṅkara's Bhāsya on the Bṛhadāraṇyaka Upaniṣad is explained by Ānandagiri by saying that the cāṭas are those that transgress the rules of conduct for decent people and that bhaṭas are servants telling falsehood (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 296). But cāṭa is used in inscriptions in the sense of a royal official.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=067" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटापक
caṭāpaka (LP), ‘increasing [the rent already fixed]’; cf. Gujarātī cad̤hāvo.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटाप्य
caṭāpya (LP), ‘to be entered [on the back of the bond]’; cf. Gujarātī cad̤hāvavā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटी
ca-ṭī abbreviation of an expression probably meaning ‘a mound suitable for planting fruit trees’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56. Cf. ṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चटित
caṭita (LP), one who makes an attack.<BR> (LP), accumulated.<BR> Cf. khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-caṭita-pratiṣaṃskāra; a crack.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चट्ट
Caṭṭa (EI 25), Tamil corruption of Sanskrit Chātra; a student.<BR> (IE 8-3), cf. a-caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-praveśa (IE 8-5); same as Cāṭa of earlier records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चट्टना
caṭṭanā (LP), food; sauce; cf. Gujarātī cāṭvuṃ, licking.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चाटु|चाटुः
cāṭu (IA 15), probably, a spoon.<BR> (EI 32), a eulogistic stanza.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुःशाल|चतुःशालं
catuḥ-śāla, catuḥ-śālā (EI 20; SITI), a cloister.<BR> (SITI), a meeting hall; see catuś-śālā.<BR> (EI 24), same as catur-ālaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुपडि
cātu-paḍi (CITD), Telugu; an offering of food to the deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर|चतुरः
catura, cf. caturaka; a square.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरक
caturaka (LP), same as Sanskrit catvara; Gujarātī coro; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-069" target="_blank">Page-069+ 40</a>] a public place in a village, or a police station; probably, a tax for the maintenance of a police station.<BR> (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=068" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरालय
catur-ālaya (EI 24), known, especially from Tamil inscriptions, in the sense of ‘a hall or pavilion attached to a temple’; also called caṭuḥ-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुराननवदन
Caturānana-vadana (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरङ्ग|चतुरंग|चतुरङ्गं
caturaṅga (EI 2), a complete army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरशीति
caturaśīti (IE 8-4), a territorial unit like a Parganā; see caurāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्दन्तसमर
caturdanta-samara, cāturdanta-samara, a war of elephants; cf. ghoṭaka-vigraha. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्दशविद्यास्थान
caturdaśa-vidyā-sthāna (CII 3), the fourteen sections of science.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्धरप्रतीहार
Caturdhara-pratīhāra, cf. Kannaḍa Sodare-vadiyara (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34); explained as ‘the chief of the royal guards’. Caturdhara is modern Caudhari, written in Kannaḍa as Saudore, Saudare, Caudore, Cavudore and Cavudari and explained as ‘an officer of the royal guard’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्दिश
cāturdiśa (EI 23; ML), ‘belonging to all the quarters’; cf. cāturdiś-ārya-bhikṣu-saṅgha, ‘Buddhist monks of all places’; ‘all monks coming from different places’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्गर्भ
catur-garbha (LL), a four-celled building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्जातक
caturjātaka (IE 8-3), same as cauthiā, an administrative board of four members known from the Pañcāyat system of Western India; cf. pañcakula or pañcāyat. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 193. See caukaḍikā.<BR> (EI 20), four fragrant articles, viz. tvak, elā, patraka and nāgakesara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्जातक|चातुर्जातकं
Cāturjātaka (EI 1), a member of the caturjātaka or cauthiā (q. v.). Cf. Pañcakulika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 193.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्जातकीय
Caturjātakīya, same as Cāturjātaka (EI 1); a member of the caturjātaka (q. v.); cf. Pañcakulika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 193.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मासी
cāturmāsī (EI 2; CII 1), the full-moon tithis of Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मासीपक्ष
cāturmāsī-pakṣa (IA 18), the fortnight ending in a cāturmāsī (i. e. the full-moon of Phālguna, Āṣāḍha and Kārttika).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मास्य|चातुर्मास्यं|चातुर्म्मास्य|चातुर्म्मास्यं
cāturmāsya (SII 11-1, CITD), the season consisting of 4 months, viz. grīṣma consisting of the pūrṇimānta months of Caitra, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-070" target="_blank">Page-070+ 40</a>] Vaiśākha, Jyeṣṭha and Āṣāḍha, varṣā consisting of Śrāvana, Bhādrapada, Āśvina and Kārttika; and hemanta consisting of Mārgaśīrṣa, Pauṣa, Māgha and Phālguna. This was the official division of the year which was popularly divided into six seasons, viz. grīṣma (Jyeṣṭha-Āṣāḍha), varṣā (Śrāvaṇa-Bhādrapada), śarad (Āśvina-Kārttika), hemanta (Mārgaśīrṣa-Pauṣa), śīta (Māgha-Phālguna) and vasanta (Caitra-Vaiśākha). Some times, the word cāturmāsya specially means the four months of the year, containing the two seasons of varṣā and śarad, i. e. from Śrāvaṇa to Kārttika. During this period, Viṣṇu is supposed to sleep, so that religious celebrations are avoided. During the period, religious mendicants desisted from roving.<BR> (EI 7; BL), related to the cāturmāsī or the full-moon day of Phālguna, Āshāḍha and Kārttika; a rite; same as cāturmāsya-vrata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=069" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्मास्यव्रत
cāturmāsya-vrata (EI 32), a rite. See cāturmāsya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्मुखबिम्ब
caturmukha-bimba (EI 2), Jain; a four-sided slab with images on all the sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्थ|चतुर्थः
caturtha (IE 8-8), one-fourth of the standard measure [of liquids like liquor^1].<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्थकुल
caturtha-kula (EI 29), the Śūdra community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्थीअमावास्या
caturthī-amāvāsyā, cf. cauti-amāvāse (EI 5), the new-moon following the Gaṇeśa-caturthī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्वैद्यमर्यादा
cāturvaidya-maryādā (EI 27), custom relating to rent-free land granted to learned Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वर्णिन्
caturvarṇin (LL), Jain; ‘consisting of four classes’; an epithet of the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वेदिभट्टत्तानप्पेरुमक्कल्
caturvedi-bhaṭṭa-ttāna-pperumakkal̤ (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; general assembly of the Vedic scholars in a Brāhmaṇa village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वेदिमङ्गल
caturvedi-maṅgala (IE 8-4; SITI), same as agrahāra; a village owned by Brāhmaṇas, generally tax-free; also called maṅgala; written as śaruppeṭi-maṅgalam in Tamil; sometimes suffixed to names of localities especially in the Tamil-speaking area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्वेदिन्
Caturvedin (EI 23, 24; CII 3, 4; SII 1), a Brāhmaṇa versed in the four Vedas; one who has studied the four Vedas; later stereotyped as a family name among Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चातुर्वीद्य
cāturvīdya (EI 23, 32), cf. Caturvedin; ‘relating to the Caturvedin’, a community of Brāhmaṇas; cf. cāturvidya-grāma, cāturvidy-āgrahāra, cāturvidya-sāmānya (EI 22).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुरुपाय
catur-upāya (SII 1), the four expedients. Cf. upāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=070" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुर्विंशतितीर्थङ्करपट्ट
caturviṃśati-tīrthaṅkara-paṭṭa (EI 2), a slab with the images of all the 24 Jain Tīrthaṅkaras. See covīsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुष्किका
catuṣkikā (EI 19; CII 4), a hall; a hall resting on four pillars (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 75).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुष्पथ|चतुष्पथं|चतुष्पथः
catuṣpatha (LP), a place where four roads meet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुश्शाला
catuś-śālā (SITI), a meeting hall; see catuḥ-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चत्वारक
catvāraka (IA 17), used in the sense of catuṣṭaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छौ
Cau˚ (PJS), contraction of Caudharī (Caturdhara) especially in medieval Jain inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौकडिका
caukaḍikā (EI 11), a variety of the Pañcāyat system; cf. caturjātaka or cauthiā.<BR> (BL), explained as ‘a method of recovering stolen property’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौमुख
caumukha (HA), Sanskrit caturmukha (cf. caturmukha-bimba); a quadruple image called pratimā sarvatobhadrikā (LL) in the Mathurā inscriptions of the Kuṣāṇa period, showing one Jina or several Jinas on each of the four faces; also seen on the top or in the centre of representations of the samavasaraṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरचरट
Caura-caraṭa (LP), cf. Marāṭhī Cor-cilaṭāṃcā upadrav.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरासी
caurāsī (IE 8-4; EI 3, 4), literally, ‘eightyfour’; same as caturaśīti (q. v.); a group of eightyfour villages; a Parganā consisting of eightyfour villages; sometimes^1 the name of a Parganā and often suffixed to its name.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरवर्जम्
caura-varjam (CII 3; HRS), cf. cora-varjam, coradaṇḍa-varjam, cora-rājāpathyakāri-varjam; ‘with immunity from the police tax’ according to some; may really mean ‘without any right to inflict punishment on thieves and persons committing the crime of treason or to levy fines from them’; may also be connected with a-bhaṭa-praveśa so as to indicate that the bhaṭas should not enter except for catching thieves and persons committing the crime of treason; cf. Cāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरि
cauri (ASLV), spelt chowrie in English; a flywhisk; sometimes the right of its use was granted to persons as a mark of honour. See cāmara, cavarālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरिक
Caurika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), official designation. Cf. Cāmara-kumāra, Caur-oddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरिका
caurikā, cf. carma-caurikā (LP), ‘theft of skin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरोद्धरण
caur-oddharaṇa (EI 33; HRS), according to some, the right to punish or levy fines from thieves; probably, the right to recover stolen property; recovery of stolen property; cf. sa-chauroddharaṇa (IE 8-5; EI 23).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=071" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरोद्धरणिक
Caur-oddharaṇika (IE 8-3; EI 23; CII 3), an official designation indicating an officer in charge of the recovery of stolen property; a police officer; same as Cor-oddharaṇika, Caur-oddhartṛ.<BR> (HD; CII, Vol. III, p. 216), explained as ‘the thief-catcher or one who exterminates thieves’. But cf. Daṇḍ-odddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरोद्धर्तृ
Caur-oddhartṛ (HD), same as Caur-oddharaṇika (cf. Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 271; also Kātyāyana quoted by Aparārka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौथिआ
cauthiā (IE 8-3; EI 33), an administrative board consisting of four members headed by the Nagarseṭh (Nagaraśreṣṭhin) as known from the Pañcāyat system of Western India; cf. caturjātaka, caukaḍikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चावडि
cāvaḍi (IE 8-4; SITI; ASLV), same as śāvaḍi or uśāvaḍi; an administrative unit or a territorial division.<BR> (EI 16), same as rājya; a district or subdivision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवल
cavala (EI 6), name of a coin, (1/8) of a pagoda; cf. cāmara, cavela.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवरालु
cavarālu (CITD), Telugu; also called savarālu, savaramulu; the hair of the camarī-mṛga, used by women as queue; also cavara, camara or cāmara, the chowrie (cauri) or long brush or fan usually made of the tail of the yak, which was one of the insignia of royalty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवरङ्ग
cavaraṅga (EI 28), a Śaiva altar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवथे
cavathe, a levy of one-fourth; see chavathā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवेल
cavela (EI 6), same as cavala; name of a coin, (1/8) of a pagoda. Cf. cāmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चेटक|चेटकः
ceṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 78), an attendant; sometimes mentioned in the list of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छ|छं|छः
cha (PJS) written as a mark indicating the end of a section of a record or of the whole of it. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 218.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छचोकी
cha-cokī (HA), Sanskrit ṣaṭ-catuṣkikā; a hall adjacent to and in front of the gūḍha-maṇḍapa, with its ceiling divided into six sections by the pillars supporting it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छद्मस्थ
Chadmastha (HA), a would-be Jina [living a monk's life] before attainment of kevala-jñāna. Cf. Bodhisattva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाद्य
chādya, cf. tṛṇa-cchādya, thatch-covering (Ep. Ind., XXXIV, p. 145); same as Gujarātī chāj, thatch.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छल|छलं|छलः
chala (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain; probably, a pretext.<BR> (EI 30), probably, a plea, or persecution, prosecution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाली
chālī (LP), sheep.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छन्दस्|छंदस्
chandas (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=072" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छङ्ग
chaṅga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 310), a measure of grain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छन्दोविचित
chandovicita, the metrical science (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 146).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छप्पन्न
chappanna, cf. ṣaṭpañcāśat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्र|छत्त्रं|छत्त्रः|छत्रं|छत्रः
chatra, an umbrella; cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR> (EI 27), an attendant or Piāda; cf. Chātra.<BR> Cf. Varāha-kṣetra = Barāh-chatra (Sircar, Studies in the Geography of Ancient and Medieval India, p. 221); corruption of Sanskrit kṣetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छात्र|छात्त्रः|छात्रं|छात्रः
Chātra (IE 8-3, 8-8; EI 23, 30), cf. a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya (IE 8-5); literally, ‘one bearing an umbrella’ or ‘the king's umbrella-bearer’; but probably the same as the Cāṭa or the leader of a group of Bhaṭas (Pāiks or Piādas) as in a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya; a peon of the law-court. See Chatracchāyika.<BR> (CII 3), used in composition with bhaṭa and also singly; literally, ‘an umbrella-bearer’; but actually, a constable like a Pāik or Piāda.<BR> (SITI), celibate^1 (Brahmacārin) in charge of a temple and the śālai attached to it; also called Śaṭṭar, Śāttirar.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्रभङ्ग|छत्त्रभङ्गः|छत्रभंग|छत्रभङ्गः
chatra-bhaṅga (IA 8), ‘the breaking of the umbrella [of sovereignty]’; sometimes interpreted as ‘an interregnum’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्राभोग
chatr-ābhoga (IA 17), corrected from ṣatr-ābhoga and explained as ‘the expanse of the royal umbrella’; but really, ‘the ābhoga (a territorial unit) called Ṣa(Kha)tra’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्रच्छायिक
Chatracchāyika (IE 8-3; HD), an umbrella-bearer; the king's umbrella-bearer. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 128. Cf. Chātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छत्रयष्टि
chatra-yaṣṭi (LL), an umbrella on a post.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छवथा
chavathā (IA 18), cf. viṃśati-chavathā, a levy of doubtful implication; may be a levy of 6 out of a unit of 20; cf. cavathe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाया
chāyā (EI 1), an image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छायादीप
chāyā-dīpa (EI 33), a lamp held by an image, often arranged to burn continuously in front of a deity in a temple; cf. akhaṇḍa-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छायास्तम्भ
chāyā-stambha (EI 33, 35), memorial pillar bearing image of the deceased.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छेद|छेदः
cheda (EI 13), a quarter, area or subdivision; cf. Brahma-cāri-ccheda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छेण्डिका
cheṇḍikā (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छिद्र|छिद्रं
chidra (7-1-2), ‘nine’; cf. randhra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=073" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छिम्पक
Chimpaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), a dyer of clothes; same as Prakrit Chimpaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छोह
choha, same as Gujarātī cho, mortar (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छोट्यमान
choṭyamāna, cf. choṭyamāna-gṛhe (LP), ‘when the house is being vacated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छोउल्त्र्य्
choultry, Anglicised form of a Dravidian word; a dharma-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छुरिप्रबन्ध
churi-prabandha (BL), name of a grant made in favour of a Churikāra, ‘a maker of churis’. The word churi may be the same as kṣurikā, ‘a knife’, and a Churikāra may have been an officer in charge of the production of knives and swords.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छुट्
chuṭ (LP), cf. choṭanīya; Gujarātī chod̤āvavuṃ; also cf. granthi-baddhair=api drammaiḥ kṣetraṃ choṭayituṃ dhāraṇiko na labhate, ‘[when the date is already over], the debtor will not get his farm liberated by the ready money tied in a piece of cloth’.<BR> Cf. patra-grahāt chuṭanti (LP), ‘will be free from the bond’; also Gujarātī chaṭśe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिह्न|चिह्नं
cihna (EI 33), flag; cf. Cihna-dhara (BL), standard-bearer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिखि
ci-khi, abbreviation of cira-khila, ‘[land] never brought under cultivation’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिकित्सा
cikitsā (CII 1), medical treatment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीनक्कनकम्
Cīna-kkanakam (IE 8-8), Tamil; ‘the Chinese gold coin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीनपगोद
Cīna-pagoda (SII 12), ‘Chinese shrine’; name of a Buddhist temple at Nāgapaṭṭanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिन्न|चिन्नः
cinna (EI 3; SITI), name of a coin; sometimes regarded as a fanam (CITD); also spelt sinna in Telugu; a weight equal to (1/30) of a tola and called a Canteroy fanam; one-eighth part of a coin called pagoda; the weight of 4 guri-giñjas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिन्त्रिणी
cintriṇī (EI 33), the tamarind tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरखिल
cira-khila (EI 30), land which was never cultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरखिलशून्य
cira-khila-śūnya (EI 23), epithet of gift land; fallow land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरञ्जीव|चिरंजीवः
cirañjīva (EI 30), ‘long-lived’; epithet of living (not dead) persons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरन्तनलोक
cirantana-loka (LP), old men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरविद
ciravida (CITD), Telugu; name of a coin; probably a special kind of gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीरिका
cīrikā (EI 26), a document; cf. kraya-cīrikā, ‘a deed of purchase’, i. e. a sale-deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=074" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीर्णव्रतोपायनक
cīrṇa-vrat-opāyanaka (LP), the gift (upāyana) for the vows practised. Cf. Sel. Ins., p. 210, text line 14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिटला
ciṭalā (IE 8-5), a tax; cf. coṭāla, ciṭola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीठिका
cīṭhikā (LP), a chit; cf. Gujarātī ciṭṭhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिटोल
ciṭola (IE 8-5), a tax or obligation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्र|चित्रं|चित्रः
citra (ASLV), a kind of poetry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रजर्त
citrajarta (LP), various kinds of armour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रक|चित्रकं|चित्रकः
Citraka (IA 8), ‘a painter’; epithet of the engraver of an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रकार|चित्रकारः
Citrakāra, cf. Cittirakārar (EI 22), a painter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रकार्य
citrakārya, cf. cittirakāri (EI 22), painting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रभास
citra-bhāsa (ASLV), paintings on the walls and ceilings of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चित्रमे
citramel̤̣i (SITI), also spelt śittiramel̤̣i, an organisation of the agriculturists; agricultural corporation of the Věl̤l̤āl̤as; the plough which was the emblem of this organisation; the boundary stone with the representation of the plough emblem planted to mark the limits of their land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीवर|चीवरं
cīvara, cf. cīvarika (EI 8); garments of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीवरिक
cīvarika (EI 8), expenses of cīvara; Sanskrit caivarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीवरिक
cīvarikā (EI 20), a Buddhist monk's robe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोखा
cokhā (EI 11), rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोल|चोलः
cola (Chamba), rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोल्लिक
collika (EI 3), collikā (EI 10), a load [of leaves]; a quantity of betel leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोर|चोरः
cora (IE 8-5), same as caura and cora-daṇḍa; probably, the power of punishing thieves and realising fines from them; cf. cora-varja; also Cāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरदण्डवर्जम्
coradaṇḍa-varjam (HRS), same as caura-varjam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरदण्डवर्ज्य
cora-daṇḍa-varjya (CII 3), a fiscal term which means either that no fines for theft should be collected from the gift village or, more probably, that the donee was not entitled to fines realisable on thieves^1 in the gift villages. But see also caura-varjam.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरद्रोहकवर्ज
cora-drohaka-varja (CII 3, etc.), a fiscal term which is similar to coradaṇḍa-varja. The word drohaka means one committing a crime against the king. See caura-varjam, Cāḷa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरग्राह
Cora-grāha (HD), a thief-catcher (cf. Nārada, Pariśiṣṭa, verse 18; also Kātyāyana quoted by Aparārka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरराजापथ्यकारिवर्जम्
cora-rājāpathyakāri-varjam (HRS), ‘with immunity from the police tax’, according to some; seems to mean ‘without any [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-076" target="_blank">Page-076+ 40</a>] right to inflict punishment on or levy fines from thieves and rebels’. But see caura-varjam; also Cāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=075" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोररज्जू
cora-rajjū (HRS), ‘the rope for binding thieves’; supposed to be the dues collected by the superintendent of the boundaries of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोररज्जुक
Corarajjuka (HD), probably the same as Dāṇḍapāśika, an officer whose duty it was to secure robbers with ropes (cf. Arthaśāstra, IV. 13; II. 6 referring to cora-rajjū as a constituent of the rāṣṭra).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरासी
corāsī (IE 8-4), same as caurāsī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्ज
cora-varja, also spelt cora-varjya (CII 3; HRS); a fiscal term which is the same as coradaṇḍa-varjya (q. v.). See also caura-varja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्जित
cora-varjita (CII 3), same as coradaṇḍa-varjya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्ज्य
cora-varjya, see cora-varja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरोद्धरणिक
Cor-oddharaṇika (EI 28, 30), same as Caur-oddharaṇika; a police officer in charge of the recovery of stolen goods; explained by some as ‘the eradicator of thieves’ (CII 4). But cf. Daṇḍoddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोस्क|चोस्कः
coska (EI 4), a horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोटाल
coṭāla (IE 8-5), a tax of uncertain import; cf. ciṭola, ciṭalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोवीसी
covīsī (HA); Sanskrit caturviṃśati or caturviṃśati-paṭṭa; a group of the 24 Jinas carved on one stone slab or cast in bronze together.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूडा
cūḍā (IA 11), the top knot of hair; cf. cūl̤ā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूडामणि|चूडामणिः
cūḍāmaṇi (IA 26), an eclipse on certain days.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चुक्क|चुक्कं
cukka, error, fault (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 7, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूला
cūl̤ā (IA 11), tresses; cf. cūdā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चुल्लक|चुल्लकः
cullaka, cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (IE 8-5), explained as ‘a pot’, i. e. cooking pot. The villagers were obliged to supply it to the touring officers of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूमा
cūmā (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चुम्बक|चुंबक|चुंबकः|चुम्बकः
cumbaka (EI 13), the balance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूना
cūnā, same as Sanskrit cūrṇa, lime (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूणकर
Cūṇakara, same as Sanskrit Cūrṇakāra, a lime-burner or white-washer (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 145).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूरकार
Cūrakāra, cf. Cūr̤akāra (CITD), from Telugu-Kannaḍa cūr̤a and Sanskrit kāra; ‘one who has plundered’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूर्णि|चूर्णिः
cūrṇi (EI 3), an appended note. Cf. cūrṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=076" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चूर्णि|चूर्णिः
cūrṇi, cūrṇī (EI 29, 33), one hundred cowrie-shells; cowrie-shells of the value of a purāṇa or kārṣāpaṇa (kāhaṇ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दभ्रसभा
dabhra-sabhā (SII 3), the golden hall in the Chidambaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाढा
dāḍhā (CII 4), a canine tooth; derived from Sanskrit daṃṣṭrā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दधि
dadhi (IE 7-12), confused with udadhi and used to indicate ‘four’.<BR> Cf. a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); curds which the villagers (probably, the milkmen) were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दहन|दहनं|दहनः
dahana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दहरभिक्षु
dahara-bhikṣu (LL), a young Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैर्घायुष
dairgh-āyuṣa (CII 1), ‘conducive to long life’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैवागारिक
Daivāgārika (EI 7), the priest in charge of a temple or an officer in charge of temples.<BR> (IE 8-3), probably, a priest of the shrine of the king's tutelary deity; sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैवज्ञ|दैवज्ञः
Daivajña (IE 8-3; EI 7), an astrologer; sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
daivaka see rājaka-daivaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=557" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैवपुत्र
Daivaputra (IE 8-2; EI 30), same as Devaputra; title of certain kings of the Kuṣāṇa dynasty; derived from a Chinese title meaning ‘the Son of Heaven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दैव्य|दैव्यं
daivya (SITI), an act of the gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्ष|दक्षः
dakṣa, used in the late Tantra literature in the sense of dakṣiṇa, ‘the south’ (cf. Sircar, Studies in the Georgraphy of Ancient and Medieval India, p. 76, note 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिण|दक्षिणः
dakṣiṇa (EI 32), the sacred fire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणा
dakṣiṇā (EI 32), perquisite.<BR> (BL), a present or gift to a Brāhmaṇa for a service.<BR> (CII 1), cf. prāṇa-dakṣinā, same as prāṇa-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणभुज
Dakṣiṇa-bhuja (SITI), ‘the right hand’; a trusted lieutenant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणामूर्ति|दक्षिणामूर्तिः|दक्षिणामूर्त्ति
Dakṣiṇāmūrti (SII 12), an aspect of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणापथ|दक्षिणापथः
Dakṣiṇāpatha (CII 3), ‘the region of the south’; a name for Southern India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणापथसाधार
Dakṣiṇāpatha-sādhāra (CII 3), ‘the Pillar of Dakṣiṇāpatha’; title of a ruler. Sādhāra may be a mistake for sv-ādhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणावर्तशङ्ख
dakṣiṇāvarta-śaṅkha (SII 1), a conch-shell with convolutions from left to right.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=077" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणायन|दक्षिणायनं
dakṣiṇ-āyana (IA 19), the period during which the sun moves from south to north; cf. uttar-āyaṇa (IA 17).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणी
dakṣiṇī, dākṣiṇya, cf. Prakrit dachini (ML); same as dakṣiṇā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाक्षिण्य|दाक्षिण्यं
dākṣiṇya, cf. dakṣiṇya (EI 23); same as dakṣiṇā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलअधिकारि
Dala-adhikāri (IE 8-3; SITI; ASLV), Dravidian-Sanskrit; same as Sainyādhikārin or Senāpati, Dalada-adhikāri or Dalavāy, a commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलदअधिकारि
Dalada-adhikāri (ASLV), same as Dala-adhikāri or Dalavāy, the commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवाय्
Dalavāy (IE 8-3; ASLV; SITI), same as Dala-adhikāri, Dalada-adhikāri or Senāpati; the commander of forces; sometimes also enjoying the title Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवायग्रहार
Dalavāy-agrahāra (ASLV), village granted for military service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवायि
Dalavāyi (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a general, a chieftain, or the minister of state; same as Dalavāy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दलवृत्ति
Dala-vṛtti (CITD), from Telugu-Kannaḍa dala, ‘army’, and Sanskrit vṛtti; probably, a grant for the maintenance of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम|दमः
dama, cf. dāma (EI 23); same as dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाम
dāma (EI 27; CII 4), name of a coin; derived from dramma.<BR> (EI 19), abbreviation of the name Dāmodara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमनक|दमनकः
damanaka (SITI), a fragrant plant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमनकचतुर्दशी
damanaka-caturdaśī (EI 23), same as Caitra su-di 14; also called damanaka-parvan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमनकपर्वन्
damanaka-parvan (EI 23, 31), same as damanaka-caturdaśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डामर|डामरः
ḍāmara (EI 12), tumultuous, terrible; a landlord or wealthy cultivator possessing much land [in ancient Kashmir], according to the Rājataraṅgiṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्म
damma (SITI), same as dramma; name of a coin; derived from Greek drachma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दान|दानं|दानः
dāna, dānā (ML), a gift.<BR> (HRS), known from Maitraka records to mean the so-called voluntary gifts of subjects.<BR> Cf. dānā-sambandhe (LP), ‘as regards the sale-tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण
dāṇa (IE 8-5; LP), same as dāna, road-cess; customs duties; cf. the official designation Dāṇī (Sanskrit Dānin).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणचोरि
dāṇa-cori (EI 32), smuggling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानादायदानीभोग
dānādāya-dānībhoga (LP), explained as ‘local cess or road-cess’; dāya is explained as ‘a gift to Brāhmaṇas or temples’, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-079" target="_blank">Page-079+ 40</a>] dānī as ‘land tax’ and bhoga as ‘right of enjoyment’; but probably, dāṇ-ādāya means excise or customs duties and dāni-bhoga a tax for the maintenance of the tax-collector.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=078" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानाधिकारिन्
Dān-ādhikārin (EI 12), officer in charge of gifts, mentioned along with the Śāsan-ādhikārika, ‘officer in charge of grants (or their writing)’. See Dharm-ādhikārin. It may also mean ‘a tolls-collector’ (cf. dāna, Dānin).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दणाइक्
Daṇāik (ASLV), corrupt form of Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानमुख
dāna-mukha (EI 7; ML), a gift; the principal gift; same as deya-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानपलं
dāna-palaṃ (IA 11), actually dāna(ṃ*)palaṃ, i. e. ‘the dāna (levy) is one pala’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानपति|दानपतिः
Dānapati (EI 28, 30; HD), one who gives a gift; one who dedicates the images of a deity (especially as the result of a previous vow); probably, also an official designation; see Horamurta (CII 2-1), Dānādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानप्पु
dāna-ppur̤am (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; land set apart for the purpose of charity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानप्रदानक
dāna-pradānaka (CII 4), all kinds of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानशाला
dāna-śālā (IA 11), a hall for the distribution of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानवोलापन
dāna-volāpana (LP), dāna (road-cess) and volāpana (tax; cf. Gujarātī valāvaṇuṃ). See Volāpika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दनायक
Danāyaka (IA 20), corrupt from of Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्ड|दंड|दंडं|दंडः|दण्डः
daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12), fine or tax, mentioned along with suṅka (śulka); a levy or free service (cf. prayāṇa-daṇḍa).<BR> (EI 24), fines; authority.<BR> (HRS), fines; distinguished from atyaya in the Arthaśāstra.<BR> (CII 1), punishment.<BR> (ASLV), judicial punishment; sometimes possibly also ‘administration’.<BR> (EI 25), ‘five’.<BR> (EI 30; LP), contraction of Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR> (EI 28), Od̤iyā; a path (cf. daṇḍā).<BR> Cf. taṇḍu (SITI), a palanquin; a pole for carrying the vehicle on which the image of a deity is set up.<BR> Cf. daṇḍu, taṇḍu (SITI), an army; going on a military expedition.<BR> Cf. taṇḍam (SII 1; CITD); fine, penalty or punishment; a punitive tax; a fine or tax payable as penalty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=079" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डा
daṇḍā (EI 31), Od̤iyā; a boundary line or road. See daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डभोगिक
Dāṇḍabhogika (HD), same as Dāṇḍapāśika (q. v.), or the police magistrate. See Ep. Ind., Vol XIII, p. 339. May also be Dāṇḍa (Dāṇḍanāyaka) and Bhogika<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डदशापराध
daṇḍa-daś-āparādha (CII 4), fines including those imposed for the ten offences; same as daś-āparādha. See daṇḍadoṣa-daś-āparādha, daṇḍa-śulka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डादाय
daṇḍ-ādāya (EI 20), fines; see Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 253-54.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिनाथ
Daṇḍādhinātha (EI 16; SII 1; HD), same as Daṇḍapāla, Daṇḍanāyaka, etc. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 55.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिनायक
Daṇḍādhināyaka (SII 1), a general; same as Daṇḍādhinātha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिप|दंडाधिप|दण्डाधिपः
Daṇḍādhipa (BL; HD), the commander of forces; same as Daṇḍapāla, Daṇḍādhipati, etc. See the commentary on the Yaśastilaka, I, p. 91; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 151.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधिपति
Daṇḍādhipati (EI 26), cf. Daṇḍanāyaka, etc.<BR> (LP), explained as ‘a governor’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाधीश्वर
Daṇḍādhīśvara (EI 5), same as Daṇḍādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डदोष
daṇḍa-doṣa, cf. sa-daṇḍadoṣa (EI 23); fines. See daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डदोषदशापराध
daṇḍadoṣa-daśāparādha (HRS), same as daṇḍa-daśāparādha; cf. sahya-daś-āparādha; sa-daśāparādha means ‘with the privilege of remission for the ten offences’, according to some; seems to mean ‘with the right to enjoy fines for the ten offences’; cf. daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डक|दंडक|दंडकः|दण्डकः
daṇḍaka (EI 30), probably, a regulation.<BR> (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain; probably, fines.<BR> Cf. daṇḍaku (IA 16), a boundary mark or land-mark.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डक्काणम्
daṇḍa-kkāṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; amount imposed as fine; cf. daṇḍam kur̤r̤am (EI 30; SITI), a levy of fines; fine and penalty imposed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डमार्ग
daṇḍa-mārga (ASLV), military route.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डनाथ
Daṇḍanātha (EI 16; CII 4; SII 1), commander of an army. See Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 31. Cf. Daṇḍanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डनायक|दंडनायक|दण्डनायकः
Daṇḍanāyaka (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 4; BL), probably a translation of Greek Strategos; a general; a leader of forces, an army officer; a military commander; also called Daṇḍanātha, Daṇḍanetṛ, etc.; sometimes also called Mahāsāmanta, Senādibāhattaraniyogādhiṣṭhāyaka, Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, Mahāpasāyita, etc., additionally; see Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, Sarvadaṇḍanāyaka, Mahāsarvadaṇḍanāyaka. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-081" target="_blank">Page-081+ 40</a>]<BR> (LP), generally, the viceroy or governor of a province; representative of the king.<BR> (ASLV), the commander of forces and officer in charge of administration; title of the provincial governors; similar to the Mansabdār of the Mughal period.<BR> (HD), a prefect of the police, according to Stein (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 951); ‘a General or Magistrate’, according to some (cf. Kielhorn's Southern List, Nos. 291, 292, 296). In the Bṛhatsaṃhitā (7. 2-4), the queen, Yuvarāja, Senāpati and Daṇḍanāyaka are placed on the same level in the matter of the staff (daṇḍa) to be prepared for them.<BR> Cf. Taḍeya-daṇḍanāyaka, explained as ‘the general in charge of reserves’, from Kannaḍa, taḍě, ‘far, restraint’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=080" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डनायक
Dāṇḍanāyaka (EI 23; HD), same as Daṇḍanāyaka. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 269.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डनेतृ|दंडनेतृ
Daṇḍanetṛ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 233), designation of a leader of forces; cf. Daṇḍanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाल|दंडपाल|दण्डपालः
Daṇḍapāla (HD), an officer in charge of all branches of the army (Arthaśāstra, I. 12); cf. Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR> (IE 8-3), cf. Dāṇḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाणिक
Daṇḍapāṇika (IE 8-3), same as Daṇḍapāśika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपरीक्षा
Daṇḍaparīkṣā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, p. 101); Od̤iyā; a governor; same as Sanskrit Daṇḍaparīkṣaka as well as Daṇḍa-nāyaka of other inscriptions; governor of a daṇḍapāṭa or province.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाशिक|दण्डपाशिकः
Daṇḍapāśika (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), a policeman; an official who was probably the leader of a group of Dāṇḍikas; officer in charge of punishment (i. e. criminal justice), according to some; a policeman (same as Od̤iyā Daṇḍuāsi meaning ‘a village watchman’); called Talāra and Ārakṣika (IHQ), December 1960, p. 266). See Yaśastilaka, I, p. 50; Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 83; Vol. XII, p. 9. Cf. Dāṇḍabhogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डपाशिक
Dāṇḍapāśika (IE 8-3; EI 23; CII 3, 4; HD), same as Daṇḍapāśika or Daṇḍapāṇika, ‘an officer entrusted with the punishment of criminals’; see Pañcatantra II, Kathā 4 (spelt Daṇḍapāśaka meaning ‘a watchman’); Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपाट
daṇḍapāṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, p. 107); Od̤iyā; the province of a kingdom; an administrative unit under a Daṇḍa-parīkṣā; cf. Daṇḍa or Daṇḍanāyaka called Daṇḍaparīkṣā in the Orissan records; also paṭṭa in the sense of ‘a district’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डपति
Daṇḍapati (BL; HD), a commander of forces, or a governor; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-082" target="_blank">Page-082+ 40</a>] same as Daṇḍanātha, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, pp. 148, 156.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=081" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डशक्ति
Daṇḍaśakti (IE 8-3; HD), a police officer; possibly the same as Dāṇḍika or Daṇḍapāśika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 250.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डशुल्क
daṇḍa-śulka, cf. daṇḍa-śulk-ādi-vividh-āya-samanvita (EI 23); income from fines and tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डवाणि
daṇḍavāṇi (SII 2), standard gold.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डवासिक|दण्डवासिकः
Daṇḍavāsika (HD), Prakrit form of Daṇḍapāśika. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 129.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डवासिक
Dāṇḍavāsika (EI 23), same as Daṇḍavāsika, Dāṇḍapāśika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डाय
daṇḍ-āya (IA 29; SII 11-1), income from fines; explained as ‘a tax’; cf. ‘the whole of the levy called daṇḍ-āya as much as accrued in the village’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डेश
Daṇḍeśa (EI 5; SII 1; HD), official designation; same as Daṇḍanātha. See JBBRAS, Vol. XV, p. 386.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिक|दंडिक|दंडिकः|दण्डिकः
Daṇḍika (HD), same as Daṇḍapāśika. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 166. (CII 4), explained by some as a magistrate. Cf. Dāṇḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाण्डिक|दांडिक|दांडिकः|दाण्डिकः
Dāṇḍika (CII 3; HD), a police officer. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306; CII, Vol. III, p. 216; Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321. Generally Dāṇḍika and Dāṇḍapāśika are mentioned side by side (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 231); probably the Dāṇḍika was the head of a group or outpost of the Dāṇḍapāśikas. Cf. Daṇḍika, Daṇḍ-oddharaṇika (collector of fines).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिका|दंडिका
daṇḍikā (SITI), also called daṇḍu; a palanquin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिकाजीवित
daṇḍikā-jīvita (SITI), tax-free land given to palanquin-bearers for enjoyment during their life-time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डिनदारि
daṇḍinadāri (ASLV), military route. See ḍaṇḍudova.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डोद्धरणिक
Daṇḍ-oddharaṇika (EI 9), literally, ‘collector of fines’; mentioned along with Daṇḍapāśika; may be the same as Dāṇḍika. Cf. Caur-oddharaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डोपजातक
daṇḍ-opajātaka (EI 28), money exacted as fines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डोपरिक
Daṇḍoparika (EI 13), probably Daṇḍa (i. e. Daṇḍanāyaka) and Uparika; otherwise Daṇḍoparika may mean a judge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्ड|दंड|दंडं|दंडः|दण्डः
daṇḍu (ASLV), a palanquin; its use was a privilege sometimes specially granted to favourites or distinguished persons by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डुआसि
Daṇḍuāsi (IE 8-3), Od̤iyā; village watchman; derived from Sanskrit Dāṇḍapāśika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डुदोव
daṇḍudova (ASLV), a military route. See daṇḍinadāri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=082" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डाङ्ग्
ḍāṅg (IA 26), also spelt dāṅk, corrupt form of ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणि
dāṇi (HRS), known from Caulukya records and explained by some as ‘the king's dues’; perquisite of the collector of the duties called dāṇa or dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानी
Dānī (IE 8-5; EI 26), i. e. Dānin, officer collecting tax or corn; officer storing the corn collected as tax from the farmers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानिभाग
dāni-bhāga, same as dāṇi-bhoga (q. v.). See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 256.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणिभोग
dāṇi-bhoga (HRS), periodical supplies of fruits, firewood and the like by the villagers, according to some; tax for maintaining the collectors of the tax called dāna; same as dāṇi-bhoga-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाणिभोगभाग
dāṇi-bhoga-bhāga (HRS), same as dāṇi-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दानीवोलापिक
Dānī-volāpika (LP), explained as ‘the collector of dānī (land cess) and volāpanā (tax, relating to Gujarātī val̤āvaṇuṃ).’ See Volāpika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डाङ्क्
ḍāṅk (IA 26), corrupt form of ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्णाइक्
Daṇṇāik (ASLV), corrupt form of Daṇḍanāyaka; sometimes the designation of a judge at the capital of the Vijayanagara kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्णायक
Daṇṇāyaka (IE 8-3; ASLV), corrupt form of Daṇḍanāyaka; a designation sometimes enjoyed by the Dala-adhikāri or commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्त|दंत|दंतः|दन्तः
danta (EI 7), a pin.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्तकार|दंतकार|दन्तकारः
Dantakāra (LL), a worker in ivory; here danta means hasti-danta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्तिन्|दंतिन्
dantin (IE 8-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दापक
Dāpaka (EI 3; BL; HD), usually regarded as the same as Dūtaka; but really ‘one who causes another to give’, i. e. the creator of a rent-free holding which was ratified by the king. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, pp. 177, 243.<BR> (CII 1), a matter relating to giving gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दापन|दापनं
dāpana, cf. dāpanāya (LP), ‘for making one pay’. See dāvāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दापित|दापितः
dāpita (LP), ‘caused to be paid’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दारद्रणक
dāradraṇaka (CII 3), a fiscal term of uncertain implication; an agricultural cess or marriage tax, according to some. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 242.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=083" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दारक|दारकः
Dāraka (IA 18; CII 1), explained as ‘the son of a king, whose mother's rank does not assure him an official title’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्श|दर्शः
darśa (IA 17), the new-moon; cf. darśa-tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्शन|दर्शनं
darśana (IE 8-5; EI 32, 33), a levy; same as Persian nazrāna. Cf. Tamil tariśana-kāṇikkai (SITI), presents offered to a king or a chief when one meets him.<BR> (CII 1), used in the sense of pradarśana, ‘showing’.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’; cf. dṛṣti, ‘two’.<BR> (IA 14), used in the sense of ‘a religious procession for the purpose of visiting a deity’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्शपूर्णमास
darśapūrṇamāsa (CII 4), name of a Vedic sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्शतिथि
darśa-tithi (EI 13), name of a tithi. Cf. darśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दर्वीकर्मन्
Darvīkarman (EI 21), measurer of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशबलमहाबल
Daśabala-mahābala (EI 20), epithet of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशबन्ध|दशबन्धः
daśabandha (SITI), variously explained as (1) one-tenth of the revenue set apart for repairs to the tanks and wells for irrigation purposes; (2) land, the income from which would be equal to the amount thus set apart; (3) the right of collecting one-tenth of the produce of lands irrigated from the waters of a tank or well by the person who repairs the water source; also explained as tax equal to one-tenth of the income of the subject (Ray, DHNI, Vol. II, p. 1113). See daśavandha.<BR> (SITI) tax or cess levied to keep the source of water supply like the tanks, etc., in good repair.<BR> (EI 4), rent-free land or probably land paying only one-tenth of the actual rent.<BR> (EI 20), one-tenth share.<BR> Cf. daśa-bandhe (LP), ‘at 10 per cent’.<BR> Cf. daśavandha (SII 3), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशबन्ध
dāśabandha-visatia(viṃśatika) ttriprastha (HRS), kinds of tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दासभृतक
dāsa-bhṛtaka (CII 1), slaves and servants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशग्रामिक
Dāśagrāmika (IE 8-3; EI 24), the headman of a group of ten villages or the chairman of the council of a group of ten villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशहराव्रत
Daśaharā-vrata (EI 27), a religious ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशक्रिया
daśa-kriyā (SITI), work of the architects who were to look after the repairs of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशमूलिक
Daśamūlika (CII 4), official designation; same as Daśamūlin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशमूलिन्
Daśamūlin (EI 21; CII 4; BL), an official designation; probably, a physician; same as Daśamūlika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=084" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशापचार
daś-āpacāra (IE 8-5; EI 29), same as daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशापराध
daś-āparādha (CII 3, 4), literally, ‘the ten offences’; but really, the fines for the ten offences; cf. sa-daś-āparādha (IE 8-5); power to punish and realise fines for the ten offences; also called daś-āpacāra. According to the Buddhists, the ten sins were murder, theft, adultery, lying, calumny, insult, idle talk, hatred, covetousness and dogmatic error (A. Getty, The Gods of Northern Buddhism, p. xxv, note). For a Brahmanical list, see Dāśāparādhika; cf. pañca-mahāpātaka, pañc-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशापराधिक|दाशापराधिकः
Dāśāparādhika (IE 8-3; EI 29; HD), a judge dealing with the ten offences (viz. theft, murder of women, adultery, use of abusive language, violation of order, mixing of castes, illegal pregnancy, obscenity, assault and abortion, according to some). It has been said that the ten offences or aparādhas are those of which the king could take cognisance suo moto. For the ten aparādhas, see Kane, Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 264; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दसरा
Dasarā (EI 5), Āśvina su-di 10.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशरथस्त्री
Daśaratha-strī (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाशरि
Dāśari (ASLV; SITI), a class of subordinates of the headman of particular communities in the Vijayanagara empire; same as Samayācāra or Samayācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशवन्ध
daśavandha, cf. daśavanna (IA 30), explained as ‘land granted to a person for repairing or building a tank on condition of paying in money or kind one-tenth or some small share of the produce’ and as ‘land granted at one-tenth of the usual rates to a person in consideration of his constructing or repairing a tank’. See daśabandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दासी
dāsī (CITD), a handmaid, slave, concubine, dancing girl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दस्र|दस्रं|दस्रः
dasra (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दासूरिपट्टु
dāsūri-paṭṭu (CITD), Telugu; probably, silk of the Tusser variety; cf. Hobson-Jabson, s. v. tussah, tusser.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दटित
daṭita (LP), well-founded.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दत्ति|दत्तिः
datti (EI 23; CII 4; CITD), a gift; cf. Sarvasiddhi-datti (EI 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौःसाधसाधनिक
Dauḥsādhasādhanika (EI 30; HD), explained as ‘those who catch dangerous robbers whom it is difficult to secure’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211. Cf. Duḥsādhasādhanika (ibid., Vol. XI, p. 310), Dussādhyasādhaka, Duṣṭasāhanī, Mahādauḥsādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौःसाधिक|दौःसाधिकः
Dauḥsādhika (IE 8-3; HD), same as Dauḥsādhasādhanika, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-086" target="_blank">Page-086+ 40</a>] Duḥsādhyasādhanika, Dussādhyasādhaka, Duṣṭasāhani, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9. Lexicons explain it as ‘gate-keeper’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=085" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौत्य|दौत्यं
dautya, see dūtya and Dūtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दौवारिक|दौवारिकः
Dauvārika (EI 28; SII 1; ASLV; BL; HD), a door-keeper; a gate-keeper. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12; Lalitavistara, p. 136; Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 30.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दावापन
dāvāpana, cf. dāvāpanāya (LP), ‘for making one pay’; cf. dāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दावापित
dāvāpita (LP), caused to be paid.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाय|दायः
dāya (EI 23), a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दायाद|दायादः
dāyāda (CII 4), an agnate.<BR> (LL), Buddhist; an heir of the faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देनरिउस्
denarius (IE 8-3), name of the Roman silver coin and also of the Roman gold coin usually called aureus; cf. dīnāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देश|देशः
deśa (IE 8-4; CII 3, 4), a territorial term meaning a small area or a group of villages in some cases but a kingdom, district, tract or country in others.<BR> (IE 8-4), a country of which there were seventy two^1 in Bhārata or Bhāratavarṣa.<BR> (CII 1), a part of anything.<BR> (EI 24), a synonym of āspada.<BR> (ASLV), a school of music.<BR> Cf. Kona-deśa (EI 32), also called a maṇḍala, rāṣṭra, sīma, sthala, etc.<BR> Cf. deśa-bhāṣā (EI 17), ‘vernacular of a province’.<BR> Cf. teśa-kālam (SITI), locality and time; also teśa-vāl̤i, officer in charge of a village or district.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशाधिकृत
Deś-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; HD), same as Deśādhipati; governor of a deśa or a province, district or sub-division. See Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5 (Prakrit Desādhikata). See Sarva-deś-ādhikṛta.<BR> (LL), explained as ‘a local prefect’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशाधिपति
Deś-ādhipati (EI 26, 30), same as Deśādhikṛta; ruler of the territorial or administrative unit called deśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशाक्षपटलाधिकृत
Deś-ākṣapaṭalādhikṛta (EI 28), officer of the records and accounts office pertaining to a territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशकूट
Deśakūṭa (AI 7), official designation; cf. Rāṣṭrakūṭa, Grāmakūṭa, Deś-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशमर्यादा
deśa-maryādā, custom prevalent in a locality; cf. deśa-maryād-ār̤uvaṇa-ānvita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line 103), ar̤uvaṇa being a tax of six paṇas levied on rent-free lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=086" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशना
deśanā, Prakrit desanā (EI 21), exposition of the Buddhist doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशरीत
deśa-rīta (Chamba), customary taxes of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशतलार
Deśa-talāra (LP), probably, a police superintendent. Cf. Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशठक्कुर
Deśa-ṭhakkura (LP), probably, a small chieftain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशवालि
Deśavāl̤i (EI 18), official designation. Cf. deśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशायि
Deśāyi (ASLV), same as Sanskrit Deśādhipati or Deśādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशी
deśī (EI 11), a guild of local merchants. This is also the name of Prakrit words which are neither Sanskrit (tat-sama) nor derived from Sanskrit (tad-bhava).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिक|देशिकः
Deśika (SII 1), a [Jain] teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिलक
Deśilaka, official designation (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71); same as Deśillaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिल्लक
Deśillaka (EI 28), official designation as in rāṣtra-grāma-kūṭa-deśillaka-mahattar-ādhikārik-ādīn; same as Desilaka, Deśakūṭa; cf. Purillaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशिमुख्य
Deśi-mukhya (EI 31), same as modern Deśmukh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशोत्तार
deś-ottāra (LP), permission for allowing the cargo to go from one place to another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देव|देवं|देवः
deva, a god; cf. te-aḍimai (SITI), a dancing woman as the servant of a god; maid servant attached to a temple; cf. teva-kuḍimai, tenancy under the control of a temple; tevakulam (deva-kula), a temple.<BR> (EI 7), the king.<BR> (EI 3), a saint.<BR> (EI 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवभोग|देवभोगः
deva-bhoga (EI 23, 31; SITI), rent-free property of a temple; land given for the enjoyment of temples; same as deva-dāya, etc., Cf. devabhoga-hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवभोगहल
devabhoga-hala (EI 7, 8, 15, 24), rent-free land in the possession of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवच्छन्द|देवच्छंद|देवच्छन्दः
deva-cchanda (SII 2), name of a jewel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदान
deva-dāna (EI 5, 23, 25, 30; SITI; ASLV), gift made to a god; rent-free land in the possession of a temple; same as deva-bhoga, deva-deya, deva-dāya, dev-āgrahāra.<BR> Cf. devadāna-ir̤aiyili (SITI), village or land granted to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदासी
deva-dāsī (EI 22, 33; LL), a dancing girl attached to a temple; a female temple-servant. See vilāsinī, gaṇikā, mahārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=087" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदाय
deva-dāya (IE 8-5; EI 23; CII 4; SITI), a rent-free holding in the possession of a temple; a gift made in honour of a god; same as deva-deya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदेय
deva-deya (IE 8-5; HRS), grant made in favour of temples; same as deva-dāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवधर्म|देवधर्मः
deva-dharma (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 144), same as deya-dharma when the gift was the image of a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवाध्यक्ष
Dev-ādhyakṣa, superintendent of religious foundations. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 99.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवदि
devadi (IA 19), ‘the establishment of a temple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवद्रोणी
deva-droṇī (IE 8-3; EI 10), usually taken to mean ‘a procession of the images of gods’, or ‘procession or ablution of images’; but probably, ‘rent-free property of a temple’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV pp. 143-44); cf. deva-droṇī-sambaddha (EI 23). A Prakrit inscription (A. R. Ep., 1959-60, No. B 173) has deva-doṇi data = Sanskrit deva-droṇī dattā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवद्रोणीसम्बद्ध
Devadroṇī-sambaddha (IE 8-3), same as Devadroṇy-adhikṛta; officer in charge of temple property (devadroṇī, usually taken in the sense of ‘a procession of the images of gods)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवद्रोण्यधिकृत
Devadroṇy-adhikṛta (IE 8-3; BL), explained as ‘the superintendent of the procession of idols’; but probably, the superintendent of the property of a temple or of temple property in general; same as Devadroṇī-sambaddha; cf. deva-droṇī (EI 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवागार|देवागारः
dev-āgāra, cf. tevāram, devāram (SITI), a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवाग्रहार
dev-āgrahāra (IE 8-5; EI 23, 25, 30; SITI), rent-free village granted to a temple; same as deva-bhoga, etc.; see agra-hāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवगृह|देवगृहं
deva-gṛha (EI 24), a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवगृहजगती
devagṛha-jagatī (IA 14), explained as ‘a temple and its ground’ or ‘a temple with the buildings attached to it.’ But cf. jagatī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
deva-hala, same as deva-bhoga-hala; cf. hala-nyāya, bhikṣu-hala. See Suc. Sāt., pp. 84, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=557" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवक|देवकः
devaka (IA 23), the guardian spirit or a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकरण
deva-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as the deva-sthāna department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकर्मन्
devakarman (SII 1), divine rites.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकर्मिन्
Devakarmin (EI 30; SII 1, 3, 12); cf. tevar-kan̤mi, devar-kan̤mi (EI 3; SITI); a Pūjāri or temple priest, a temple servant; servant of a god; an officer in charge of the affairs of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवक्रिया
deva-kriyā (IA 23), worship of gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=088" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुल|देवकुलं
devakula (EI 9, 23), a temple; cf. ācāryakula (LL).<BR> (EI 21), a gallery of portrait statues of deified or semi-deified ancestors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलपुष्करिणी
devakula-puṣkariṇī (IE 8-5), temples and tanks [the construction of the former and the excavation of the latter requiring the permission of the king or landlord].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुली
devakulī (CII 4), a small shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलिक
devakulika (LL), a temple-servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलिका
devakulikā (EI 8; HA), a shrine; a cell; a supplementary or smaller shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुटीकाष्ठ
devakuṭī-kāṣṭha (EI 7), a measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवालय|देवालयः
dev-ālaya (EI 23), a temple; same as devakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवानांप्रिय|देवानाम्प्रिय|देवानाम्प्रियः
Devānāṃpriya (EI 21; CII 1; LL), a royal title; title assumed by the Maurya kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवाण्डज
Devāṇḍaja (EI 32), same as Garuḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवनिकाय|देवनिकायः
deva-nikāya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 115), probably, temple authorities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवपुत्र
Devaputra (IE 8-2; EI 8, 21, 30), royal title of foreign origin; ‘the Son of Heaven’; title of certain Kuṣāṇa kings; same as Daivaputra.<BR> (LL), Buddhist; an angel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवरडियाल्
devaraḍiyāl̤ (ASLV), Tamil; a dancing girl attached to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवारम्
devāram (SITI), Tamil corruption of Sanskrit devāgāra; a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवातिदेव|देवातिदेवः
Devātideva (EI 1), epithet of the Buddha and gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवटिसलम्
devaṭisalam (EI 12), a ceremony indicative of royalty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवत्रा
devatrā (IE 8-5), same as deva-dāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देववारिक
Deva-vārika (EI 33), superintendent of a temple; cf. Vārika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 142, text line 35.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देववेश्मकरण
devaveśma-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवविहार
deva-vihāra, land in the possession of temples. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 217.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देववृत्ति
deva-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart for the maintenance of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवयज्ञ|देवयज्ञः
deva-yajña (CII 4), offerings to gods; one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवायतन|देवायतनं
dev-āyatana (EI 23), a temple; same as devakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवी
Devī (IE 8-2; CII 1, 3; LL), a title originally of wives [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-090" target="_blank">Page-090+ 40</a>] of independent monarchs and later also of feudatory rulers; often used as a termination of the names of wives of rulers of all classes; cf. Mahādevī; also means the Mother-goddess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=089" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवीकर्मान्तिक
Devī-karmāntika (EI 16), a temple officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवीकुमार
Devī-kumāra (IA 18; CII 1), explained as ‘the son of a king, who has the rank of a prince’; the king's son born of a queen and not of a concubine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवोत्तर
devottara (IE 8-5), Bengali corruption of devatrā; same as deva-dāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देय|देयं
deya (IE 8-5), periodical offerings to be presented to the king or landlord; cf. ādeya, deya-meya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देयधर्म|देयधर्मः
deya-dharma (EI 1; CII 3; ML), a pious gift; an appropriate religious gift; an expression used in numerous donative inscriptions. A deity installed for worship was also called deya-dharma (sometimes deva-dharma) in medieval records. Same as dharma-deya, dharma-dāya, dharma-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देयधर्मपरित्याग
deyadharma-parityāga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 10, text line 2), donation of a religious gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देयमेय
deya-meya (HRS), known from a Śātavāhana record; king's share in kind and in cash; same as dhānya-hiranya of later records. See deya, meya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देय्यधर्म
deyya-dharma (EI 32), Pali-Prakrit form of deya-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धडा
dhaḍā, dhaḍī, a small measure of capacity (Ind. Ant., Vol. XLI, p. 20).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढक्का
ḍhakkā (CII 3), a war drum; used in the Rājataraṅgiṇī in the sense of a watch-station (cf. Sircar, Geog. Anc. Med. Ind., p. 238).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धलवादि
dhal̤a-vādi, dhala-vali (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a tax probably connected with dala-vṛtti, or at least with dala or the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानक|धानकं|धानकः
dhānaka, see hema-dhānyaka; also called aṇḍikā; equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or to 4 suvarṇas or dīnāras (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 7).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धनिक|धनिकः
dhanika, dhanin (LP), the owner; cf. Gujarātī dhaṇī; used in the sense of ‘one who is spending or lending money’ in the Maithilī documents (Proc. IHRC, Vol. XVIII, p. 90).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानिक
dhānika, a coin equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or 64 paṇas according to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K.V. Rangaswami Aiyanger, p. 125); cf. dhānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धनिकत्व
dhanikatva, cf. dhanikatvaṃ vidhāya (LP), ‘having claimed ownership’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=090" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्य|धान्यं
dhānya, cf. sa-hiraṇya-dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya (IE 8-5); produce of the fields, a share of which was payable to the king or landlord; cf. dhāny-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यादाय
dhāny-ādāya (SITI), tax payable in grains; cf. dhāny-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्याधिवास
dhāny-ādhivāsa (EI 32), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यहिरण्य
dhānya-hiraṇya (HRS), revenue in kind and in cash; same as dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya. Bhoga-bhāga-dhānya-hiraṇya of the Kurud plates (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 264) probably means dhānya-hiraṇya realised as bhoga-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यहिरण्यादेय
dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya (EI 32), tax in crops and cash. See dhānya-hiraṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यमाष
dhānya-māṣa, weight equal^1 to 1 yava or 2 taṇḍulas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यवर्ग
dhānya-varga (SITI), literally, ‘the grain group’; actually, a class of taxes payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्याय
dhāny-āya (EI 7), tax in-grains; cf. dhāny-ādāya; called něll-āyam (SII 12) in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यिक
Dhānyika (LL), a dealer in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर|धरः
dhara, cf. Vinaya-dhara (EI 33), ‘one who has committed the [Buddhist] Vinaya texts by heart’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरा
dharā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारादत्त
dhārā-datta, cf. tārā-tattam (SITI), a gift made with the ceremony of libation of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरामण्डल
dharā-maṇḍala (SII 1), a country.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरण|धरणं|धरणः
dharaṇa (CII 4), name of a coin.<BR> (IE 8-8), a silver coin weighing 24 ratis (cf. JNSI, Vol. II, pp. 28-29) or the half of a gadyāṇaka according to the Līlāvatī; silver coin of 32 ratis according Manu, etc.<BR> (IE 8-8), same as kārṣāpaṇa or purāṇa.<BR> (EI 3), a gold coin or weight (320 ratis).<BR> (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44), sometimes called śāna and ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरणी
dharaṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारणी
dhāraṇī (IA 9; BL), a magic litany usually of the Buddhists; an occult Indian charm, especially Buddhistic; a short formula intended to represent a particular Tantra text, the recitation of the dhāraṇī being regarded as equally meritorious as that of the Tantra itself (Univ. Cey. Rev., January-April, 1960, p. 62, note 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारणिक
dhāraṇika (LP), a debtor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धारापूर्वकम्
dhārā-pūrvakam, cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc. See dhārā-datta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्म|धर्मः|धर्म्म|धर्म्मः
dharma (SII 1), the sacred law; religious merit; a meritorious gift, a pious work, a charity; moral precept. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-092" target="_blank">Page-092+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 24), law or law and order.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 116) virtue or religious merit.<BR> (IE 8-2), sometimes prefixed to the titles of kings and crown-princes; cf. Dharma-mahārāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=091" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मबद्ध
dharma-baddha, cf. tarma-pattar (SITI), persons bound by the law; judicial officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मबान्धव
dharma-bāndhava, ‘one whose only friend is his religious faith’ or ‘a person who has become the friend of another on an oath in the name of his religious faith’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मचक्र|धर्मचक्रः|धर्म्मचक्र|धर्म्मचक्रः
dharma-cakra (CII 3; LL), Buddhist; the wheel of Dharma which was the symbol representing the Buddha on early Buddhist sculptures, on stone inscriptions and on seals attached to copperplate grants.<BR> (HA) Jain; the wheel of law supposed to move in the sky in front of a Jina when he goes on his wanderings from place to place; one of the members of the parikara of a Jina image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मचक्रमुद्रा
dharmacakra-mudrā (EI 29), seal bearing the emblem of the Buddhist wheel of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मदान|धर्म्मदानं
dharma-dāna (ML; SITI), a religious gift; a gift for religious merit; grant of tax-free land; same as deya-dharma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मदेय
dharma-deya (IA 9; HRS), same as deya-dharma, dharma-dāya, etc.; a religious grant in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मदेशना
dharma-deśanā (SII 1), a discourse on the sacred law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकार|धर्माधिकारः|धर्म्माधिकार
dharm-ādhikāra (EI 15; IA 9), court of law; an office relating to the civil and criminal courts as well as to religious and charitable institutions. See Dharmādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकरण|धर्माधिकरणः|धर्म्माधिकरण|धर्म्माधिकरणं|धर्म्माधिकरणः
dharm-ādhikaraṇa (EI 18, 23, 25; CII 4; LP), a law-court; a court of justice. See Dharm-ādhikaraṇin.<BR> Cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of justice.<BR> (HD), a judge. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 24-25.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकरणिक|धर्माधिकरणिकः
Dharm-ādhikaraṇika (IE 8-3), a judge; mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकरणिन्|धर्म्माधिकरणिन्
Dharm-ādhikaraṇin (HD), a judge. See Matsya Purāṇa, 215. 24. The reading is Dharm-ādhikaraṇa in some manuscripts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माधिकारिन्|धर्म्माधिकारिन्
Dharm-ādhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 33), cf. dharm-ādhikāra (IA 9); an officer in charge of civil and criminal justice as well as charitable and religious institutions; same as Bṛhat-tantra-pati, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-093" target="_blank">Page-093+ 40</a>] according to a Kashmirian commentator; usually explained as ‘a judge’; same as Dharmakarm-ādhikārin and Dharm-ādhyakṣa. Cf. the Muslim official designations S̤adrus̤-s̤udūr, Dādbak, etc., explained as ‘the chief judge and grand almoner, or custodian of the king's bequests and charities’ (Journ. As. Soc. Pak., Vol. IV, pp. 53-54).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=092" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्माध्यक्ष|धर्माध्यक्षः|धर्म्माध्यक्ष|धर्म्माध्यक्षः
Dharm-ādhyakṣa (EI 15; HD), generally explained as ‘a judge’; but he was probably also the superintendent of charities, etc.; cf. Dharm-ādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्महल
dharma-hala (EI 7), a rent-free holding. See hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मजयस्तम्भ
dharma-jaya-stambha (IA 19), ‘a pillar of the victory of religion’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकर्माधिकारिन्
Dharmakarm-ādhikārin (EI 21; CII 4), officer in charge of charities and other religious works; probably the same as Dharm-ādhyakṣa; cf. Dharm-ādhikārin, Dharma-Pradhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकर्तृ
Dharma-kartṛ (EI 19; IA 12), a temple superintendent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकथिक
Dharma-kathika (LL), cf. Prakrit dhamma-kadhika (EI 15), a [Buddhist] preacher; a preacher of the [Buddhist] religious system; same as Dharma-kathin; also spelt Dharma-kathaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मकथिन्
Dharma-kathin (CII 2-1; ML), Buddhist; the preacher of the [Buddhist] religious system; same as Dharma-kathika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मलाभ
dharma-lābha (LP), expression uttered by the Jain monks [of the Śvetāmbara sect] when they bless a householder saluting them.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मलेखिन्
Dharma-lekhin (EI 4; CII 4; BL), a writer of charters or religious documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मलिपि
dharma-lipi (EI 2, 33; CII 1), an edict on the subject of dharma (religion or moral precepts).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममहाधिराज
Dharma-mahādhirāja (EI 12, 28), royal title; cf. Mahādhi-rāja and Dharma-mahārāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममहामात्र|धर्ममहामात्रः
Dharma-mahāmātra (IE 8-3; EI 26; CII 1; HD), superintendent of morality; a Mahāmātra (high executive officer) of the department of religion; an executive officer superintending matters relating to religious affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममहाराज
Dharma-mahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 15, 28), royal title; supposed to mean ‘a Mahārāja who, at the particular time of issuing a record, was engaged in an act of religious merit.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्ममाहाराजाधिराज
Dharma-māhārājādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 5, 15, 28), imperial title; title assumed by certain rulers. Cf. Dharma-mahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=093" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मनिगम
dharma-nigama (LL), probably, a pious hamlet or its administrative council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मप्रधान|धर्म्मप्रधान
Dharma-pradhāna (EI 21; CII 4), head of the religious department; cf. Dharm-ādhyakṣa and Dharmakarm-ādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मपुत्र|धर्मपुत्रः|धर्म्मपुत्त्र|धर्म्मपुत्त्रः|धर्म्मपुत्र
dharma-putra (EI 32), ‘one theoretically accepted as a son’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मराज|धर्मराजः|धर्म्मराज|धर्म्मराजः
Dharmarāja (EI 28), royal title; title of a pious king; cf. Dharma-mahārāja, etc.; also dharmarājikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मराजगुरु
Dharma-rājaguru (EI 11), designation of the king's preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मराजिका
dharmarājikā (IA 14; ML), Buddhist; a stūpa built on the relics of the Buddha called Dharmarāja; a Buddhist stūpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशाला|धर्म्मशाला
dharma-śālā (IE 8-3; IA 9), a house for accommodating pilgrims free of cost; cf. śrī-Vāgmatī-jal-āvatāra-sopān-ārāma-ghaṇṭā-dharmaśālā-pratiṣṭhā-karma. See choultry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मासन|धर्म्मासन|धर्म्मासनं
dharm-āsana (EI 26; SII 3, 13; SITI), a court of justice; cf. Tamil dan̤m-āsanam (EI 22), the seat of justice; a law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मासनभट्ट
Dharmāsana-bhaṭṭa (SITI) a Brāhmaṇa versed in law assisting in a dharm-āsana or law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशासन|धर्म्मशासन
dharma-śāsana (EI 18, 22, 33; SII 1), an edict relating to dharma; a religious edict.<BR> (EI 22; SITI), same as tāmra-śāsana; a document recording a gift made for charitable purposes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशासनपट्ट
dharmaśāsana-paṭṭa (EI 3), a slab containing a religious edict.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मशास्त्र|धर्म्मशास्त्र|धर्म्मशास्त्रं
dharma-śāstra (BL), scriptures.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मस्थान
dharma-sthāna (EI 24, 26, 32), a temple; a holy place; a place of religious worship. Cf. a mijigiti or mosque referred to as a dharma-sthāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144); see also dharmasthāna-goṣṭhika.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 279, note 52), land or money assigned for a religious purpose.<BR> (EI 23), the office of justice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मस्थानगोष्ठिक
dharmasthāna-goṣṭhika (EI 33), member of a committee managing the affairs of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मस्थित
Dharma-sthita (IE 8-2), ‘steadfast in religion’; epithet of a Kuṣāṇa king who may have been a convert to Buddhism. See Satyadharma-sthita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मवारियम्
dharma-vāriyam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; committee looking after charitable endowments and institutions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=094" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मविजयशासन
dharmavijaya-śāsana (EI 33), same as dharma-śāsana; a royal record relating to one of the king's meritorious acts; cf. vijaya-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मविजयिन्
Dharma-vijayin (CII 4), a righteous conqueror; epithet of certain rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मवृत्तिइ
dharma-vṛtti-ir̤aiyili (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax-free land for the maintenance of some charity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मयात्रा
dharma-yātrā, cf. dhaṃma-yātā (EI 5; CII 1), pilgrimage; a tour of pilgrimage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मयुवमहाराज
Dharma-yuvamahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 24, 32), designation of a crown-prince engaged in a pious activity; cf. Dharma-mahārāja and Yuvamahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धार्मिक|धार्मिकः|धार्म्मिक|धार्म्मिकः
dhārmika (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, a cess collected in the name of a religious institution or festival.<BR> (IE 8-2), royal title; same as Prakrit Dhramika, translated from Greek Dikaios.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धर्मिन्|धर्म्मिन्
Dharmin, cf. dharmikal̤ (SITI), a body or commission managing endowments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धार्तराष्ट्र|धार्तराष्ट्रः|धार्त्तराष्ट्र|धार्त्तराष्ट्रः
Dhārtarāṣṭra (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धाटी
dhāṭī (LP), campaign; cf. para-rāṣtṛ-opari datta-dhāṭyām, ‘in the course of an expedition led against a foreign country’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धाटिवाह
dhāṭivāha (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 277, note 24), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धात्री
dhātrī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातु|धातुः
dhātu (ML), Buddhist; corporeal relics [of the Buddha].<BR> (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR> Cf. Dhātu-parigṛhīta, an epithet of the Buddha; probably, salvation (Select Inscriptions, p. 228).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातुगर्भ|धातुगर्भः
dhātu-garbha, ‘containing the corporeal relies of the Buddha’ (Journ. Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 136).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातुवर
dhātu-vara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 16, text line 13), a Buddhist stūpa containing the Buddha's relics.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धातुवरपरिगृहीत
Dhātuvara-parigṛhīta (EI 20), ‘one who has attained nirvāṇa’; epithet of the Buddha. Cf. dhātu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धौकणपत्र
dhaukaṇa-patra (LP), permission of divorce; cf. Gujarātī chuṭāchedā mel̤vavā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढौर
ḍhaura (LP), cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धावक|धावकः
Dhāvaka (EI 18), the fore-runner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धवलच्छत्र
dhavala-cchatra (SII 2), a white parasol which was one of the royal insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=095" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धवलागार
dhaval-āgāra, cf. dhavalāra (IA 14), ‘a mansion’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढेङ्कु
ḍheṅku (EI 30), a machine for extracting juice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढेङ्कुकड्ढक
ḍheṅku-kaḍḍhaka (IE 8-8), probably, one whose profession was to draw water from a well by means of a machinery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धी
dhī (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ढिंक
ḍhiṃka (EI 13), a well.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धीर्मर
dhīrmara (CII 4), probably, ‘a fish-basket’, according to some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धिष्णि
dhiṣṇi (EI 5), a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धृति|धृतिः
dhṛti (LP), consolation or encouragement.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘eighteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुव|ध्रुवं|ध्रुवः
Dhruva (EI 16, 32; HD), [a collector of] the fixed royal share of grains; contraction of Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika; cf. the Gujarātī family name Dhruva; same as dhruva-sthāna. See Bomb. Gaz., Vol. I, Part i, p. 477.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR> (CII 1), regular.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवा
dhruvā (CII 1), certainty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवाधिकरण
Dhruv-ādhikaraṇa (EI 30), office of [the collector of] the king's share of the produce of the fields from the farmers. Cf. Dhruva, Dhruvapati, Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवाधिकरणिक
Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika (IE 8-3; CII 3; HD; HRS), known from Maitraka records; according to some, the officer in charge of persons entrusted with the superintendence of the collection of the king's grain-share from the farmers; an official title of the Kathiawar region indicating an officer collecting the king's share of grains; sometimes called Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇika; the same as Dhruva or an employee of the dhruva-sthāna or Dhruva's office. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 339.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवपति
Dhruvapati (EI 32), cf. Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवस्थान
dhruva-sthāna (IE 8-3), a station for the collection of the king's fixed grain share; cf. Dhruva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्रुवस्थानाधिकरण
Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 30), the station for collecting the king's share or the office in its charge; cf. Dhruv-ādhikaraṇa and Dhruv-ādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वज|ध्वजः
dhvaja (CII 3), banner or standard as distinguished from lāñchana or crest. Cf. cihna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 135 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वजारोहण
dhvaj-ārohaṇa (EI 31), a ceremony; cf. dhvaj-āvarohaṇa<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वजस्तम्भ
dhvaja-stambha (CII 3, 4), a flag-staff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वजावरोहण
dhvaj-āvarohaṇa (SITI), function at the conclusion of a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=096" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वंशी
dhvaṃśī, same as vaṃśya; a theoretical unit of measurement (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दि
di (IE 8-1; CII 3), abbreviation of dina, dine, divasa or divase; used in connection with śu or su and ba in the case of lunar months and by itself in the case of solar months.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिबिर
Dibira, same as Divira (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिगम्बर|दिगंबर|दिगम्बरः
Digambara (IA 7), a Jain sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिग्गज|दिग्गजः
diggaja (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’. Eight poets patronised by Kṛṣṇadevarāya were called the aṣṭa-diggaja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिग्विजय|दिग्विजयः
dig-vijaya, used in Kannaḍa inscriptions in the sense of ‘going in state; going in a triumpal procession; making a state progress through one's dominions’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 223, note 5; Vol. VI, p. 51, note 5). See vijaya. It normally means ‘the conquest of the quarters’, conventional claim of a type of Indian rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Digvijayin, ‘the conqueror of the quarters’; title of some rulers conventionally claiming to have conquered the cakravarti- kṣetra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=557" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिकैओस्
Dikaios (IE 8-2) Greek; royal title; ‘pious’; translated in Prakrit as Dhramika (Sanskrit Dhārmika).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीकोला
dīkolā (LP), same as dāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिक्पाल|दिक्पालः
Dikpāla (HD), probably, officers in charge of the borders of a kingdom. See Nārada, Jolly's ed., Pariśiṣṭa, verse 17; Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 271; Kātyāyana (v. 813) quoted by Aparārka. (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीक्षा
dīkṣā (HA), initiation as a monk or recluse; initiation into any doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीक्षागुरु
dīkṣā-guru (EI 32, 33), preceptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीक्षित|दीक्षितः
Dīkṣita (EI 22; CII 3, 4), same as Yajña-dīkṣita; epithet of Brāhmaṇas; later stereotyped as a Brahmanical family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिन|दिनं|दिनः
dina (CII 3), a day; used to denote the solar, or more properly civil, day. See also di and divasa.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘fifteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनार
dināra (SITI), name of a coin; same as dīnāra; derived from the Roman coin name denarius; a cowrie-shell according to the Rājataraṅgiṇī (Stein's trans., Vol. II, pp. 308 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीनार|दीनारः
dīnāra (IE 8-8; EI 9, 23, 30; CII 3; SITI), a gold coin, the name being derived from the Roman denarius; gold coin equal to 16 silver rūpakas in the Gupta age (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 5); sometimes called kāśu in Tamil records; sometimes regarded as half of a satera or sateraka (Greek stater); mentioned as a silver coin (K. V. Rangaswami Aiyanger, Kṛtyakalpataru, Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, p. 125); also spelt dīnnāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारि
dināri (IE 8-8), name of a coin probably modified from the Roman denarius; cf. dīnāra and dināri-māṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=097" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारिमाषक
dināri-māṣaka (IE 8-8), name of a coin; cf. dināri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपमाला
dīpa-mālā, cf. tīpa-mālai (SITI), the string of lights hung in temples; same as śara-vil̤akku.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपना
dīpanā (CII 1), glorification.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपपूजा
dīpa-pūjā (EI 9), dīpa and pūjā wrongly taken as a compound word of special significance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपस्कम्भ
dīpa-skambha (LL), a lamp-post.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपावली
dīpāvalī (EI 5; CII 4), name of a festival; the festival of lights; cf. dīp-otsava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीपोत्सव|दीपोत्सवः
dīp-otsava (EI 11, 32), same as dīpāvalī, the festival^1 of lights.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिरमम्
diramam (IE 8-8), Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घमान्य
dīrgha-mānya (SITI), land set apart for the supply of water for the holy bath of idols.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घा
dīrghā (CII 1), distance or the distant future.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घनासिक्यार्चा
dīrghanāsiky-ārcā (EI 24), the image of a deity with long nose.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीर्घिका
dīrghikā (SITI), bath; a long or oval pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिश्
diś, diśā (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’; rarely used to indicate ‘four’ also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशा
diśā (IA 7), precepts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशः|दिश
diśaḥ (EI 2), the nymphs of the quarters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशाम्पति
Diśāmpati (EI 29), a provincial governor. A Cakravartin was sometimes conceived as a Dig-vijayin or a Diśāmpati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशापट
Diśāpaṭa (EI 16), Kannaḍa; ‘causing one's enemies to be scattered in all directions’; same as Diśāpaṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिशापट्ट
Diśāpaṭṭa (EI 5, 16), Kannaḍa; ‘causing one's enemies to be scattered in all directions’; same as Diśāpaṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिष्ट|दिष्टं|दिष्टः
diṣṭa (IA 18), same as kāla, time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दित्य|दित्यः
ditya (EI 9, 12, 28; CII 4; HRS), known from Maitraka records; name of a tax, according to some; probably, the same as datti, i. e. a gift or occasional present to be offered to the landlord; cf. sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna or ˚parihṛta (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 298, text line 20); also cf. sa-ditya-dāna-karaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 301, text line 14), an epithet of the gift land. Ditya is probably derived from Prakrit dijja = Sanskrit deya, ‘to be given’, ‘an object that has been given away’ in the sense of ‘customary presents’. For ditta, cf. Bhār. Vid., Vol. XVII, Nos. 3-4 pp. 125-26. See Dity-odgrāhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=098" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दित्योद्ग्राहक
Dity-odgrāhaka (CII 4), probably, ‘an officer in charge of collecting customary presents’; cf. ditya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव|दिवं
diva (CII 3, etc.), abbreviation of divasa or divase; used to denote the solar or, more properly, civil day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिवा
divā (CII 3), ‘by day’; an indeclinable used in some of the Nepal inscriptions in composition with words denoting tithis or lunar days.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिवाकर|दिवाकरः
divākara (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीवान्
Dīvān (BL), the chief administrator or finance minister; see Dīwān, Dīwānjī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिवस|दिवसः
divasa (CII 3, etc.), a day; sometimes used for the weekday, instead of the usual term vāra; generally used to denote the solar or, more properly, civil day; sometimes used in connection with words denoting tithis or lunar days. See also di, dina, diva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिविर
Divira (HD), same as Persian Dabīr, ‘a clerk’. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 131, mentioning Divira as distinct from Kāyastha; also CII, Vol. III, p. 122. Cf. Divirapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिविरपति
Divirapati, Divīrapati (IE 8-3; EI 5, 28; BL; HD), chief secretary or the chief of the clerks; cf. Divira. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 180 (Sandhivigrahādhikṛta-Divirapati); Vol. XXII, p. 117 (Divirapati also called Sandhivigrahika, Mahā-pratīhāra and Sāmanta).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव्य|दिव्यं|दिव्यः
divya (IA 10; LP), an ordeal; same as parīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव्यप्रबन्ध
divya-prabandha, see prabandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीटान्
Dīwān, Dīwānjī (BL), the chief administrator or finance minister. See Dīvān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोड्डि
doḍḍi (EI 4), a yard.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डोहलिका
ḍohalikā (EI 13), explained as ‘a piece of land granted to Brāhmaṇas, Svāmins, Sādhus and others’ (Prog. Rep. A. S. I., W. C., 1908-09, p. 53); cf. dohalikā dattā. See dohalikā-bhūmi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डोहलिकाभूमि
ḍohalikā-bhūmi (LP), explained as ‘land, of which the ownership is doubted and hence taken by government’; cf. Gujarātī ḍūlā, dulavuṃ, ḍohalavum; also lupta-ḍohalikā (LP), explained as ‘the ḍohalikā which is lost to the owner’. But see ḍohalikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोकारा
dokārā (LP), an old man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोलयात्रा
dola-yātrā (IA 9), the festival of the swinging of the image of Kṛṣṇa on Phālguna su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोण्
doṇ (IE 8-6), Bengali form of droṇavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=099" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोङ्गक
doṅgaka (EI 24), a variety of resin or aloe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोष|दोषः
doṣa (LP), doing anything wrongly.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR> (EI 9), black or red spots on the tongue supposed to be a foreboding of death.<BR> Cf. daṇḍa-doṣa; fines; see also pradhān-āpradhāna-doṣa-samanvita used as an epithet of the gift village (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 274). Here doṣa apparently means daṇḍa-doṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोस्य
dosya (IE 8-8; EI 30), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोयरक
doyaraka (EI 33), probably, ‘the singer who repeats part of a song after it has been once sung’; cf. Hindī dohrānā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्र
dra (EI 33; LP), abbreviation of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रछ्म
drachma (IE 8-8; CII 4), name of an old Greek coin; Indian dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रह्यितव्य
drahyitavya (CII 1), ‘should be firm’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षण|द्रक्षणं
drakṣaṇa, see draṃkṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षुण
drakṣuṇa, see draṃkṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम
drama (EI 23), same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रंक्षण|द्रङ्क्षण|द्रङ्क्षणं
draṃkṣaṇa, same as tolaka (q. v.); a weight of 8 māṣas, also spelt drakṣaṇa, drakṣuṇa, etc.; cf. maṃkṣūṇa, equal to 7 māṣas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्म|द्रम्मं
dramma (EI 25, 30; CII 4; SITI; BL), name of a coin; originally derived from Greek drachma.<BR> (IE 8-8), a silver coin, equal to one-sixteenth of a gold niṣka according to the Līlāvatī.<BR> Cf. pañciyaka-dramma (EI 30), Śrīmadādivarāha-dramma, Vigraha-dramma, Vigrahapāla-dramma, Vigrahapāla-satka-dramma, Vigrahapālīya-dramma, Vigrahatuṅgīya-dramma (IE 8-8; EI 1); Bhīmapriya-dramma (IE 8-8); poruttha-dramma (EI 23).--(IE 8-8), cf. gara-dramma, dāya-dramma, belliya-dramma (i. e. silver dramma), etc., of Kannaḍa inscriptions; the name dramma was also applied to the silver coin called purāṇa, dharaṇa or kārṣāpaṇa, though it was often used as the name of copper coins; money. For gold and ordinary (copper) dramma, cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 111.<BR> Cf. vāśal-tiramam (SITI), door tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मार्ध
dramm-ārdha (CII 4), ‘half of a dramma’; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मत्रिभाग
dramma-tribhāga (CII 4), ‘three-fourths of a dramma’; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रङ्ग|द्रङ्गः
draṅga (EI 32), used to indicate dramma; name of a coin.<BR> (EI 10), cf. Navagrāma-draṅga, ‘the draṅga of Navagrāma’; possibly ‘a station for the collection of revenue’. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-101" target="_blank">Page-101+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 8-3), a town or watch-station; possibly also a station for the collection of revenue (cf. Rājatar., VII. 2010); also called udraṅga which may thus indicate both revenue and the station for its collection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=100" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रङ्गपाल
Draṅgapāla (EI 28), same as Drāṅgika official designation. See draṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्राङ्गेश
Drāṅgeśa (EI 20; HD), supposed to be the designation of a guardian of the frontiers (cf. Stein, Rājataraṅgiṇī, Vol. II, pp. 291-92 for draṅga or draṅgā); cf. Draṅgapāla and Drāṅgika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्राङ्गिक
Drāṅgika (IE 8-3; EI 10, 30; CII 3, 4; HD), probably, an officer in charge of a city-station or watch-tower for collection of customs duties. Draṅga means either ‘a town’ (Bhandarkar's List, No. 810) or ‘a watch-station for the collection of tolls’ (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 2010). Drāṅgika was an officer in charge of a draṅga probably meaning a watch station or a station for revenue collection; similar to Audraṅgika in the latter sense; mentioned along with the Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇa or ‘the collector of the king's grain-share’. Cf. draṅga, Draṅgapāla, etc. See CII, Vol. III, p. 169.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रव|द्रवः
drava (EI 20), a kind of dancing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्राविडी
Drāviḍī, name applied to the South Indian variety of the Brāhmī alphabet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रव्यभाण्डारकरण
dravyabhāṇḍāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of stores.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोण|द्रोणः
droṇa (IE 8-6; Chamba), a grain measure; often regarded as equal to four āḍhakas; between one maund fourteen seers and two maunds, according to Bengali authors.<BR> (IE 8-1; EI 24, 29, 30), name of a land measure derived from that of a measure of capacity; shortened form of droṇavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणागीक
Droṇāgīka (EI 33), official disignation; possibly a mistake for Droṇāgraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणाग्रक
Droṇāgraka (EI 27), official disignation; probably an officer in charge of a droṇamukha or an important city, or one who collected the king's grain-share fixed per droṇa measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणमापक
Droṇamāpaka, measurer of the king's grain-share (Ghoshal, Ag. Syst. Anc. Ind., pp. 26-27).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणवाप
droṇavāpa (IE 8-6; EI 30), ‘an area of land requiring one droṇa measure of seed grains to be sown’; a land measure which was not the same in different ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणि|द्रोणिः
droṇi, droṇī (CII 4; IA 11), treasury; property (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144--‘the droṇī of Śrī-Somanāthadeva’ to [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-102" target="_blank">Page-102+ 40</a>] which a piece of land was attached); see devadroṇī probably meaning ‘rent-free property of a temple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=101" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रोणीकर
droṇī-kara, cf. Tamil toni-kkaḍamai (SITI), tax on boats.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृश्
dṛś, cf. peṭaṃ (Sanskrit udaraṃ) darśayitum (EI 11), literally, ‘to show one's belley’; but actually ‘to ask for the means of livelihood’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृशिधारिका
Dṛśidhārikā (EI 32), a female torch-bearer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृष्ट|दृष्टं
dṛṣṭa (EI 3, 23; CII 3; etc.), Prakrit diṭṭham, ‘has been seen’, i. e. ‘found correct and approved’, found on some copper-plate grants indicating the approval of the proper authorities endorsed on the original document later engraved on the plates. Cf. ni (an abbreviation of nibaddha or nirīkṣiṭa) in certain medieval copper-plate grants of Eastern India. In dṛṣṭa-pañcāśat-padāti (LP), dṛṣṭa-ghoṭaka (LP), etc., the word dṛṣṭa indicates that money should be paid after actually seeing the foot-soldiers and horses in question.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृष्टादृष्ट
dṛṣṭ-ādṛṣṭa (IA 20), dimly seen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दृष्टि|दृष्टिः
dṛṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra; also darśana, ‘six’.<BR> (IA 19), Buddhist; theory or doctrine; a peculiar or heretical doctrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दू
Dū (IE 8-1; LP), abbreviation of Dūtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुग्ध|दुग्धः
dugdha, cf. a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); milk which the villagers (probably, the milkmen) were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःखन
duḥkhana (CII 1), causing pain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाधसाधनिक
Duḥsādha-sādhanika (IE 8-3; HD), the leader of policemen engaged in apprehending robbers, etc., or of expeditionary^1 forces requisitioned on occasions of emergency; cf. Sādhanika, Duṣṭa-sādhaka, Dauḥsādhanika, Dussādhya-sādhaka, etc.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाध्य|दुःसाध्यः
Duḥsādhya (EI 2), abbreviation of Duḥsādhya-sādhanika, etc., or a criminal; cf. dussādhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाध्यादाय
duḥsādhy-ādāya (EI 21), a tax probably levied from habitually criminal people or for the maintenance of certain police or military officers called Duḥsādhya, etc. See duṣṭasādhy-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःसाध्यसाधनिक
Duḥsādhya-sādhanika (IE 8-3), same as Dauhsādha-sādhanika, etc. Cf. Dussādhya-sādhaka, Duṣṭa-sāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुःशम्य
duḥśamya (ML), unpreventable.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
dukra, (1/5) of a phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=557" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डुलित
ḍulita (LP), ‘[land, etc.,] that has become ḍohalikā (q. v.)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुम्फक
dumphaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably the same as Sanskrit dṛmphaka, ‘one who presses’; see nīla-ḍumphaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=102" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुन्दुभि|दुंदुभि|दुंदुभिः|दुन्दुभिः
dundubhi (ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्ग|दुर्गं|दुर्गः
durga (ASLV), a fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गदण्डनायक
Durga-daṇḍanāyaka (ASLV), the ruler of a fort; cf. Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गपाल
Durgapāla (HD), superintendent of a fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गपति
Durgapati (EI 27), governor of a fortress.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्गापुत्र
Durgā-putra (EI 33), epithet of one devoted to the goddess Durgā; used along with such similar epithets as Rudra-putra and Puruṣottama-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुरित|दुरितं
durita (SITI), famine; disturbance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्लभ|दुर्लभः|दुर्ल्लभ
Durlabha (EI 23), an official designation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुर्वाछक
dur-vāchaka, cf. tur-vāyakam (SITI), abusive language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्कृत|दुष्कृतं
duṣkṛta (CII 1), a bad deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुस्साध्य
dussādhya (CII 4), ‘a criminal’; abbreviation of Duḥsādhya-sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुस्साध्यसाधनिक
Dussādhya-sādhanika, same as Duṣṭa-sāhaṇi (EI 33), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाधक
Duṣṭa-sādhaka (EI 7; CII 4; HD), official designation; ‘the mentor of criminals’; same as Duḥsādhya-sādhanika, Dauḥsā-dhanika, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाध्य
Duṣṭa-sādhya (EI 21; CII 4), same as dus-sādhya or a criminal; abbreviation of the official designation Duṣṭa-sādhya-sādhanika; same as Duṣṭa-sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाध्यादाय
duṣṭasādhy-ādāya, probably, a tax levied for maintaining the police engaged in suppressing dacoits. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 254, note. See duḥsādhy-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाध्यसाधनिक
Duṣṭasādhya-sādhanika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 132), same as Duṣṭa-sādhaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुष्टसाहणि
Duṣṭa-sāhaṇi (EI 33), same as Duṣṭa-sādhaka, Duṣṭasā-dhya-sādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूष्य|दूष्यं|दूष्यः
dūṣya (CII 1), robe or clothes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूत|दूतः
Dūta (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30; CII 1; HD), a messenger or envoy. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 13-14, 28; CII, Vol. I, p. 67.<BR> (EI 23; CII 3, 4), an occasional substitute for Dūtaka, the executor of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूतक|दूतकः
Dūtaka (IE 8-3; HD), messenger; conveyor of a request or message; cf. the Khalimpur plate of Dharmapāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 250), according to which the king was requested to make a grant by a Mahāsāmantādhipati through prince [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-104" target="_blank">Page-104+ 40</a>] Tribhuvanapāla as the Dūtaka. His function is called dūtya in the Nalanda plate of Devapāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, 318 ff., text line 51).<BR> (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30; CII 3, 4), according to some, the technical title of an officer connected with royal charters, whose duty it was to carry the king's orders to the local officials by whom the charter was then drawn up and delivered. But the Dūtaka seems to have been responsible for putting the document and also perhaps the gift land in the donee's possession. There are instances of more Dūtakas than one (IA 19). See also Ājñā, Dūta, and sva-mukh-ājñā. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 143-44.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=103" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूतप्रैषणिक
Dūta-praiṣaṇika (HD), officer in charge of sending envoys; same as Dūta-preṣaṇika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321; Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306. Cf. Preṣaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूतप्रेषणिक
Dūta-preṣaṇika (CII 4), also called Duta-saṃpreṣaṇika and Dūta-praiṣaṇika; the officer who despatched Dūtas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूत्य|दूत्यं
dūtya, same as dautya; function of the Dūtaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दूयक
Dūyaka (LP), Sanskrit Dūtaka; a messenger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वादशभाग
dvādaśa-bhāga (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 203); name of an additional levy which was (1/12) of the fixed tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वादशक
dvādaśaka (SII 13), partnership in a land; cf. aṣṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वादशस्थानाधिपति
Dvādaśasthān-ādhipati, the head of twelve departments (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वन्द्व|द्वंद्व|द्वंद्वं|द्वन्द्वं|द्वन्द्वः
dvandva (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वार|द्वारं
dvāra (CII 1), a way or means.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR> (EI 4), the mouth of a river.<BR> (IE 8-3), cf. ‘the lord of the dvāra’ which was the designation of a commander of forces in Kashmir; possibly, a pass [leading into the Kashmir valley].<BR> Cf. Tamil vāśal-paṇam, ‘door-tax’; periodical payment due to the palace. Cf. dvār-ādeya.<BR> Cf. dvāra-koṣṭḥaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारादेय
dvār-ādeya (HRS), ‘gate-dues’; explained as a surcharge over and above the tolls on goods imported into a city. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 60, note. But cf. Tamil vāśal-paṇam explained as ‘door-tax’, i. e. the periodical payment due to the palace.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वाराधिप|द्वाराधिपः
Dvār-ādhipa (IE 8-3; HD), same as Dvāranātha, Dvāra-pati, etc.; ‘the lord of the pass’; cf. dvāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=104" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारकोष्ठक
dvāra-koṣṭhaka (Lüders, Mathurā Inscriptions, p. 135, text line 4), translated as ‘gateway’; gate-chamber.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारमण्डप
dvāra-maṇḍapa (HA), a hall or pavilion on the entrance or door of a shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारनाथ
Dvāranātha (IE 8-3; HD), superintendent of the passes leading into the kingdom, according to Stein (Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 214); same as Dvār-ādhipa, Dvārapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारपाल|द्वारपालः
Dvārapāla (EI 22), a door-keeper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारपरीक्षा
Dvāra-parīkṣā (IE 8-3; EI 28), Od̤iyā; Sanskrit Dvāra-parīkṣaka; same as Pratīhāra. Cf. Parīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारपति
Dvārapati (IE 8-3; HD), ‘lord of the gate’; a commander of forces under the Kampanāpati [in Kashmir]; the guardian of a pass [leading into the Kashmir valley]; same as Dvāranātha, Dvār-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वारोष्ठ
dvāroṣṭha (EI 1), meaning doubtful; probably a mistake for dvāra-koṣṭha, a gate-chamber.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वय|द्वयं
dvaya (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वेद
Dveda (EI 24, 29), contracted form of Dviveda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वेस
dvesa (CII 3), an epithet applied to land; a term of uncertain significance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वि|द्विः
Dvi (EI 11), abbreviation of Dviveda.<BR> (IE 8-1), abbreviation of dvitīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वीभूमिक
dvī-bhūmika (LP), two-storied.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विगर्भ
dvi-garbha (LL), a two-celled building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विजातिदाय
dvijāti-dāya (EI 22), same as brahma-dāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विका
dvikā, double measure (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 52, note 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विप|द्विपः
dvipa (EI (7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्वीप|द्वीपं|द्वीपः
dvīpa (IE 7-12), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विवल्लक्य
dvi-vallakya (LP), [coins] in which there is a mixture of two vāls (6 ratis) of a base metal. Cf. JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 197.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्विवेद
Dviveda (CII 4), also called Dvivedin; epithet of Brāhmaṇas; later stereotyped as a Brahmanical family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्व्यर्ध
dvyardha (CII 1), one and a half.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्यु|द्युः
dyu (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्युमणि|द्युमणिः
dyu-maṇi (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्यूत|द्यूतं|द्यूतः
dyūta (HRS), gambling; the king's dues collected by the superintendent of gambling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्यूतसभापति
Dyūtasabhāpati (BL), superintendent of the gambling hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=105" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडूक|एडूकं|एडूकः
eḍūka, cf. eḍuo (CII 2-1), supposed to be ‘a wall into which bones (meaning planks and other hard substances) have been inserted in order to strengthen the structure’, because it is explained in a commentary as asthy-aṅkita kuḍya; but asthy-aṅkita-kuḍya seems to mean a Buddhist stūpa raised on corporeal relics which were an object of worship. Although the word kuḍya is reckoned in the lexicons in the sense of a wall, it seems to mean ‘a mound’ in this case. The word aidūka derived from eḍūka is used in Buddhist Sanskrit in the sense of a Buddhist stūpa. See IHQ, Vol. XXIX, pp. 302-03.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकभोग
eka-bhoga (EI 16; SITI; ASLV), a tenure indicating exclusive ownership of a property invested in a single individual; sole possession and enjoyment of a village by a single person (without any joint owner); cf. ekabhoga-ir̤aiyili, tax-free land or village in the sole enjoyment of a single owner. Same as eka-bhogya. Cf. gaṇa-bhoga.<BR> (SITI), single crop; same as Tamil oru-pū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकभोग्य
eka-bhogya (EI 13, 14), a tenure; same as eka-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकदा
ekadā (CII 1), sometimes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशप्रसूति
ekādaśa-prasūti (LP), probably, eleven births.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशरुद्रभिक्षा
ekādaśa-Rudra-bhikṣā (EI 32), arrangement of free supply of food to Śaiva ascetics in the name of the eleven Rudras; land granted for such an arrangement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशशत
ekādaśa-śata (ML), same as ekādaś-ottara-śata, one hundred^1 and eleven.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकादशीव्रत
ekādaśī-vrata (EI 31; CII 4), name of a vrata rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकधन|एकधनः
eka-dhana (LP), joint family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकलमूर्ति
ekala-mūrti (HA), a single Jina image without any ornamental parikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकमुष्टि
eka-muṣṭi, cf. eka-muṣṭyā (LP), ‘collectively’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकाङ्ग|एकांग|एकाङ्गं|एकाङ्गः
Ekāṅga (HD), probably, an officer belonging to a body organized in military fashion for collecting revenue or performing police duties. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 249; VII. 1604.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकाङ्गिन्
Ekāṅgin (SITI), a single person; one who has no family, especially the Vaiṣṇava devotee in charge of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकपात्र
Ekapātra (EI 27), probably, Yāvadeka-pātra (q. v.); official designation^1; cf. Pātra and Mahāpātra.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=106" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकशाट
Eka-śāṭa (EI 29), same as Eka-cīvara; epithet of a monk who has taken a vow to wear only one piece of cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकतीर्थी
eka-tīrthī (HA), a sculpture showing only one Jina (Tīrthaṅkara) together with his parikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकत्य
ekatya (CII 1), ‘of one kind’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एकावली
ekāvalī, ekāvallī (SITI), necklace of a single string.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरदुबिल्कोदे
ěraḍu-bil̤koḍě (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एर्झुन
Erjhuna (ML), a title of foreign origin; ‘a prince’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एतत्क
etatka cf. etaka (CII 1); same as etat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एवंपरिणा
evaṃpariṇā (LP), ‘in this way’; cf. Gujarātī evī-pere.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअनम्
fanam, English spelling of Tamil paṇam; see paṇa. It was sometimes regarded as a gold coin equal to (1/10) of a partāb and (1/20) of a varāha (SII, Vol. I, p. 161).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअर्मान्
farmān, also spelt firmān; Persian; cf. phuramāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋईल्
fīl, Arabic-Persian; cf. pīlu, Pīlupati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋइर्मान्
firmān, cf. farmān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग|गं|गः
ga (IE 8-1), used for gā (in Kharoṣṭhī) as an abbreviation of gāthā; also abbreviation of gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गभारो
gabhāro (HA), Sanskrit garbha-gṛha; the sanctum of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गच्छ|गच्छः
gaccha (IA 11; BL), name of particular communities of Jain monks; cf. the eightyfour gacchas of the Jains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्दी
gaddī (EI 8), a throne; cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधैया
gadhaiyā, also called gadhaiyā paisā; same as gadhiyā; a copper coin modified from old Sasanian types.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधिया
gadhiyā, same as gadhaīyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदिआणक
gadiāṇaka, cf. Kumāra-gadiāṇaka (EI 8); same as gadyāṇaka.<BR> (EI 27), also called gadyāṇa; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदियाण
gadiyāṇa (EI 27; CII 4), same as gadyāṇa, gadyāṇaka; name of a coin called suvarṇa-gadiyāṇa, ‘gold gadiyāṇa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्या
gadyā, abbreviation of gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यान
gadyāna (EI 3), a gold coin or weight; also spelt gadyāṇa. generally regarded as 48 ratis in weight (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याण
gadyāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 27, 30), also called gadyāṇaka, often contracted as ga or gadyā; sometimes called pon-gadyāṇa or gadyāṇa-ponnu indicating that it was a gold coin; sometimes [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-108" target="_blank">Page-108+ 40</a>] called suvarṇa; cf. bhairava-gadyāṇa, lokki-gadyāṇa (SII 11-2), aṅka-gadyāṇa, gāva-gadyāṇa, komarina-gadyāṇa, priyaśrāha-gaja-malla-gadyāṇa, ambili-gadyāṇa, jagadalaṃ-gadyāṇa, etc. Cf. also ar̤u-gadyāṇa (IA 12) and kula-gadyāṇa (EI 17), names of coins. Cf. parameṣṭhi-gadyāṇa-ponna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 61).<BR> (SITI), name of a coin, probably equal to a varāha or pagoda; cf. bṛhad-bhairava-gadyāṇa (EI 30); also kaṭhāri-aṅkuśa-gadyāṇa (EI 8), name of a coin with the representation of a dagger and a goad; varāha-gadyāṇa (EI 8), name of the gold coin called both varāha and gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=107" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याण
gaḍyāṇa (CITD), same as gadyāṇa; a coin like a farthing equal to (1/4) or (1/5) of the paikamu; also a dināra or varāha; a weight used in weighing silver; equal in some places to 20 vals, 8 māṣas, or half a tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यानक|गद्यानकं|गद्यानकः
gaḍyānaka (EI 28), gaḍyāṇaka (IE 8-8; EI 27), same as gadyāna or gadyāṇa; name of a coin; a coin weighing 48 ratis according to the Līlāvatī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गगन|गगनं
gagana (IE 7-1-2; EI 52), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गाह्ण
gāhṇa (Chamba), threshing floor; from Sanskrit gāhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गैराट
gairāṭa, cf. gelāṭa (CII 1); probably, a hill bird.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गज|गजः
gaja (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजधर
Gajadhara (EI 4), same as Sūtradhara or Sūtradhāra, ‘mason’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजाधीश
Gajādhīśa (CII 4), ‘the lord of elephants’; official designation; title of certain rulers. Cf. Gajapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजलक्ष्मी
Gajalakṣmī (EI 32), representation of Lakṣmī receiving water on the head from a jar held in the trunk of an elephant on either side; found on the seals of certain rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजमाल
gajamāla (HA), row of elephants in the plinth of shrines; also called gajathara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजमृगयाविहार
Gaja-mṛgayā-vihāra (ASLV), ‘sportful hunting of elephants’; a title of the Vijayanagara kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजपति|गजपतिः
Gajapati (IE 8-2; EI 9, 30; CII 4; HD), ‘the lord of elephants’; officer in charge of the elephant arm in an army; title of certain rulers; dynastic name of the Sūryavaṃśīs of Orissa. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 7. See Mahāgajapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजसाहणी
Gaja-sāhaṇī (EI 32), a leader of the elephant force; same as Gaja-sāhiṇi, Gaja-sādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजसाहिणि
Gaja-sāhiṇi (IE 8-3; EI 27), same as Gaja-sāhaṇi, Gaja-sādhanika; leader of the elephant corps; cf. Sāhiṇi or Sāhaṇī, derived from Sādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=108" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजथर
gajathara (HA), same as gajamāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गजवाहराउत
Gajavāha-rāuta (EI 31), title of a subordinate chief.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गल्पुट्टि
gal-puṭṭi (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of land; a variation of puṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गाण्ठि
gāṇṭhi (LP), a package; cf. Gujarātī gāṇṭhd̤ī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गमागमिक
Gamāgamika (IE 8-3; EI 4, 23; CII 4; HD), same as Gamāgamin; official designation; probably, an officer in charge of regulating the people's entrance and departure into cities; explained by some as ‘a kind of messenger’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306). Utpala on the Bṛhatsaṃhitā, 85. 34, explains Dūta as Gamāgamika, though some Pāla inscriptions have dūta-khola-gamāgamik-ābhitvaramāṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, pp. 250, text line 45).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गमागमिन्
Gamāgamin (EI 31), same as Gamāgamika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गम्पण
gampaṇa (EI 27), same as kampaṇa; an administrative and territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गामुण्ड
Gāmuṇḍa (EI 15), Kannaḍa; same as Gāvuṇḍa; a village headman; probably derived from Grāmakūṭa, ‘headman of a village’, through Gāmaūḍa>Gāmuḍa under the influence of muṇḍa, ‘head’. Cf. Nāḍa-gāmuṇḍa Nār̤-gāmuṇḍa, ‘headman of a district (nāḍu)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण|गणः
gaṇa (LL), a section of the Jains.<BR> (SITI), a group of persons; a community or religious guild.<BR> (EI 26; CII 4), a guild or corporation.<BR> (EI 3), wrongly explained as a share.<BR> (SII 12), managing committee.<BR> (SII 2), the attendants of Śiva; also the fourteen divisions of learning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभोग
gaṇa-bhoga (SITI, ASLV), a tenure in which land is held in common by a group of persons; joint ownership of a village or villages by a number of persons; same as gaṇa-bhogya, gaṇa-bhojya. Cf. eka-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभोग्य
gaṇa-bhogya (EI 13, 15), see gaṇa-bhoga or gaṇa-bhojya. Cf. eka-bhoga or eka-bhojya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभोज्य
gaṇa-bhojya (EI 16), same as gaṇa-bhoga or gaṇa-bhogya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणभृत्
Gaṇabhṛt (EI 3; SII I), the head of a [Jain] school; same as Gaṇin, Gaṇa-dhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणाचार्य
Gaṇ-ācārya (LL), the teacher of a Buddhist community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणदण्ड
Gaṇadaṇḍa (EI 30), epithet of a hero; probably, an abbreviation of Gaṇa-daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=109" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणदण्डनायक
Gaṇa-daṇḍanāyaka, also called Gaṇa-daṇḍapāla (EI 18); official designation; probably, a Daṇḍanāyaka serving under a gaṇa or corporation or commanding several gaṇas or contingents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणदण्डपाल
Gaṇa-daṇḍapāla, same as Gaṇa-daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणधर|गणधरः
Gaṇadhara (HA), chief disciple of a Jina.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणक|गणकः
Gaṇaka (EI 18), official designation; cf. Tamil kaṇakan̤ (SITI), a village accountant; also vāśal-kaṇakkan̤ (SITI), accountant at the vāśal (palace or palace-gate); ūrkkaṇakkar-jīvitam (SITI), land assigned in lieu of salary to the village accountant or perquisites of the office of the village accountant (i. e. the Paṭvārī as he is called in many parts of India).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणना
gaṇanā (EI 20), accountancy.<BR> (CII 1), ‘taking into account’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणपक
Gaṇapaka (CII 4), official designation; probably the same as Sanskrit Gaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणपण
gaṇa-paṇa (EI 20), communal and professional guilds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणप्पेरुमक्कल्
Gaṇa-pperumakkal̤ (SII 12; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; the elders of a gaṇa managing its affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणश्रेष्ठ
Gaṇa-śreṣṭha (CII 3), probably, the head of a corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणस्थ
Gaṇastha (EI 15), probably, the member of a corporation; same as Tamil Gaṇattār; see Mahāgaṇastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणस्थिति
gaṇa-sthiti (IA 19), cf. Mālavānāṃ gaṇa-sthityā, Mālava-gaṇa-sthiti-vaśāt, explained as ‘by, or according to, the reckoning of the Mālavas’, gaṇa being taken to mean gaṇanā. But see sthiti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणत्तार्
Gaṇattār (SITI), Tamil; Sanskrit Gaṇastha; people belonging to a gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणवारियम्
gaṇa-vāriyam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; committee managing the affairs of a gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणवारियप्पेरुमक्कल्
Gaṇa-vāriya-pperumakkal̤ (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; elders of the committee called gaṇa-vāriyam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्ड|गंड|गंडः|गण्डः
Gaṇḍa (EI 12), cf. Tamil Gaṇḍan̤; a hero, probably from the meaning ‘rhinoceros’; cf. similar use of vyāghra, siṃha, etc.; also cf. Paragaṇḍabhairava (EI 29). See Gaṇḍan̤ and Gaṇḍa-peṇḍāra; also Calamartigaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डा
gaṇḍā (IE 8-6; EI 19; IA 27), in the monetary system of some areas of medieval and modern India, regarded as equal to four cowrie-shells and (1/20) of a paṇa; also a small area of land, twenty of which make one kānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डभेरुण्ड
gaṇḍabheruṇḍa (EI 3), a mythical double-headed eagle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=110" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डगोपाल
Gaṇḍagopāla (EI 30), title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डक|गंडक|गंडकः|गण्डकः
gaṇḍaka (EI 21), name of a coin; cf. gaṇḍā.<BR> (EI 27), an official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डकानायक
Gaṇḍakānāyaka (EI 33), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डमाड
gaṇḍa-māḍa (EI 5), name of a coin; sometimes specified as ‘small’; also called kārṣāpaṇa, niṣka or gaṇḍa-niṣka; cf. māḍa. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 43.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्ड|गंड|गंडः|गण्डः
Gaṇḍan̤ (SITI), Tamil; a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोण्डपेण्डार
gaṇḍa-peṇḍāra (ASLV), Tamil; ‘the anklet of a hero’ which was worn by men of distinction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डशैल|गंडशैल|गण्डशैलः
gaṇḍa-śaila (EI 12), a boulder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्धकुटी|गंधकुटी
gandhakuṭī (EI 9, 18; IA 14), originally, ‘a chamber for the Buddha's use’; later ‘the chamber enshrining the Buddha image in a monastery’; a shrine where the image of the Buddha is worshipped; a Buddhist temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गान्धर्व|गांधर्व|गान्धर्वः|गान्धर्व्वं|गान्धर्व्वः
gāndharva (EI 28), dance and music.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्धशालि|गन्धशालिः
gandha-śāli (EI 5), a kind of rice or paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गान्धिक|गांधिक|गांधिकः|गान्धिकः
Gāndhika (EI 28; LL), a perfumer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणेशचतुर्थी
Gaṇeśa-caturthī (EI 5; IA 17; CII 4), name of a tithi and festival; same as Bhādrapada su-di 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गनेशहोम
Ganeśa-homa (EI 26), a rite; same as Vināyaka-homa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गैकोण्ड
Gaṅgaikoṇḍa (IE 8-2), title of a Col̤̣a king meaning ‘the conqueror of the Gaṅgā’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गामार्ग
gaṅgā-mārga (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गापुपुटक
gaṅgāpupuṭaka (IA 18; CII 1), probably gaṅgā-puppuṭaka; a particular fish of the Ganges.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गायमुना
Gaṅgā-yamunā (EI 24, 29), royal insignia probably consisting of the representation of the Gaṅgā and Yamunā on the flags or at the gate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गाङ्गेय|गांगेय|गाङ्गेयं|गाङ्गेयः
gāṅgeya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 38), gold.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गास्नान
Gaṅgā-snāna (LP), ‘absence of sin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गङ्गिनिका
gaṅginikā (EI 18), a stream.<BR> (EI 12), a dried up river bed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गानी
gānī, cf. aṭha-gānī, a billon coin equal to 8 copper jitals and to (1/6) of a silver ṭaṅka (JNSI, Vol. XII, p. 198); cf. jītal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणिका
gaṇikā (EI 33), same as devadāsī.<BR> (EI 7), a female elephant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणिकाकरण
gaṇikā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the amusement department.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गणिन्
Gaṇin (SII 2), an astrologer. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-112" target="_blank">Page-112+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 3), head of a school.<BR> (IA 19; LL), Jain; a Jain ecclesiastic^1; an ācārya who has disciples but has not risen to be the head of his gaccha or śākhā.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=111" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्ज|गंज|गंजः|गञ्जः
gañja (EI 30), Persian ganj; a treasury or store-house. Utpala on the Bṛhatsaṃhitā, 52. 13, explains gañja as kośa-bhavana, i. e. treasury. See Gañjavara.<BR> (IE 8-8), a store-house of liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्जाधिकारिन्
Gañj-ādhikārin (HRS), a treasury-officer according to the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Gañjapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्जपति
Gañjapati (EI 13; HRS; HD), same as Persian Ganjwar, treasurer (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 115). See gañja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गञ्जवर|गञ्जवरः
Gañjavara (IE 8-3; EI 9; HD), Persian Ganjwar; a treasurer or store-keeper (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 247; Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 177). See Gañjapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्ज्टर्
Ganjwar, Persian; see Gañjavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भ|गर्भः
garbha (LL), a cell; cf. pañca-garbha (LL), ‘a five-celled building’; nava-garbha (LL), ‘a nine-celled building’; sapta-garbha (LL), ‘seven-celled building’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भद्वार
garbha-dvāra (LL), the hall-front.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भागार|गर्भागारं
garbh-āgāra (CII 1), the inner apartment of a temple or palace; same as garbha-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्भगृह
garbha-gṛha (SITI), the innermost sanctuary of a temple; inner part of palace; same as garbh-āgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्चा
garcā (Chamba), same as gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्गयवन
Garga-yavana (EI 33), name applied to the Turkish Muslim invaders of North India, Garga probably being Ghaznī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्जनकाधिराज
Garjanak-ādhirāja, Garjanik-ādhirāja (LP), ‘the emperor of Ghaznī’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गर्त|गर्तं|गर्तः|गर्त्त|गर्त्तः
garta, gartā (EI 3, 27; CII 3), a trench or pit; a boundary trench; a pit or valley; cf. sa-gart-oṣara (IE 8-5); also found as the termination of names of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गरुड|गरुडः
garuḍa (IA 20), the royal eagle; the white kite (in areas like Bihar and Madras).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गरुडध्वज|गरुडध्वजः
Garuḍadhvaja (CII 4), title of a ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गतराज्य
gata-rājya, same as vinaṣṭa-rājya or atīta-rājya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गति|गतिः
gati (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘four’; also explained as five in number (EI 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गात्र|गात्रं
gātra (IA 14), same as aṅga-bhoga.<BR> (EI 33), same as gotra or gotra-śailikā, i. e. a memorial pillar for the dead members of one's family. See yaṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=112" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गात्री
gātrī (LP), cf. Gujarātī gād̤a, a cart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौद
Gauḍa (EI 5; ASLV), Kannaḍa; same as Gāvuṇḍa; a village headman; the chief farmer of a village. See Gavuḍa.<BR> (EI 1), a temple priest.<BR> (IE 8-5; EI 28), Od̤iyā; same as gokuṭa; a cowherd or milkman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौडमहासान्धिविग्रहिक
Gauḍa-mahāsāndhivigrahika (IE 8-3), ‘the Mahāsāndhivi-grahika of the Gauḍa country’; cf. Mahāsāndhivigrahika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौडी
Gauḍī, name applied to the East Indian alphabet, language and style of composition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौडिक|गौडिकं|गौडिकः
Gauḍika (EI 28), maker and seller of sugar; see Guḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौग्गुलिक
Gauggulika (EI 13), a dealer in guggulu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौल्मिक|गौल्मिकः
Gaulmika (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HD), same as Gulma-pati (q. v.); ‘chief of a troop’; officer in charge of a gulma or outpost or group of guards, soldiers or policemen; ‘superintendent of woods and forests’ according to Fleet (CII, Vol. III, p. 50). See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 246.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौरी
gaurī, a virgin; cf. gaurī-varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौरीपट्ट|गौरीपट्टः
gaurī-paṭṭa, same as the yoni-paṭṭa of a Śiva-liṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौरीवराटिका
gaurī-varāṭikā, ‘virgin-money’. Gaurī means ‘a virgin’ and varāṭikā is used primarily in the sense of varāṭa or varāṭaka, ‘a cowrie-shell’, and secondarily in that of ‘money’. In the records of Mithilā, gaurī-varāṭikā means ‘money to be paid to the master of a slave girl of marriageable age by the master of her bridegroom’. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 264 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गौतमीपुत्र
Gautamī-putra (IE 2-8), metronymic meaning^1 ‘the son of a lady born in a family belonging to the Gautama gotra’. Such metronymics refer to the absence of gotr-āntara (i. e. the change of the bride's paternal gotra to that of her husband at the time of marriage) in a popular form of ancient Indian marriage.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गवुड
Gavuḍa (EI 5; ASLV), Kannaḍa; same as Grāmakūṭa, Gauḍa, Gāvuṇḍa; village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गावुण्ड
Gāvuṇḍa, Gavuṇḍu (HD), same as Grāmakūṭa, Gavuḍa, Gauḍa. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 74; JBBRAS, Vol. X, p. 208.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गव्य|गव्यं
gavya (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गव्यूत|गव्यूतं
gavyūta (EI 22), a distance of about 4 miles; same as gavyūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गव्यूति|गव्यूतिः
gavyūti (EI 27), a linear measure; same as gavyūta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गयाड
gayāḍa, cf. guyāḍa (EI 22), courtyard. Cf. the royal names Gayāḍa and Gayāḍatuṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=113" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गयामुक्त
Gayā-mukta (EI 33), one whose śrāddha ceremony has been performed at Gayā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गायत्री
gāyatrī (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyfour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गेलाट
gelāṭa (IA 18; CII 1), probably Sanskrit gairāṭa, ‘a hill bird’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गेणु
geṇu (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; ‘one span’; a unit of measurment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गेवक
gevaka (CII 1), inferior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घा
ghād̤ā (Chamba), a system by which the tiller receives one half of the produce. See ghād̤otā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घा
ghād̤aka, also called ghād̤ī (Chamba); land cultivated on the ghād̤ā system.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घदम
ghaḍa-mar̤uturu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of land; a variation of mar̤uturu (q. v.). Cf. kāl-mar̤uturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घडपुट्टि
ghaḍa-puṭṭi (CITD), Telugu; a variation of puṭṭi. Cf. gāl-puṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घा
ghād̤ī, cf. ghād̤aka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घडियारमु
ghaḍiyāramu (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a gong, a watch, a clock, an hour glass; a cup with a hole at the bottom placed on water for measuring time, an hour being counted when it sinks. Cf. ghaṭikā-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घा
ghād̤otā (Chamba), spoken of a land tilled on the condition that one half of the produce should go to the owner. See ghād̤ā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घले
ghalě (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; measuring rod; cf. Gaṅganaghale, ‘the rod [measured by the length of the forearm] of a person named Gaṅga’; cf. hasta in Śivacandra-hasta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाणक
ghāṇaka (EI 2, 32), an oil-mill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घरहण
gharahaṇa (Chamba), same as garaṭhā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोरक्षेत्र
ghora-kṣetra (SITI), gṛha-kṣetra; a building site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घरठा
gharaṭhā (Chamba), also called gharahana, gharaṭhāi, gharṭhāi; a house site; homestead; from Sanskrit gṛha-sthāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छाञ्चिक
Ghāñcika, maker of or dealer in oil (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 145-46); same as Gujarātī Ghāṃci.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घस्र|घस्रं|घस्रः
ghasra (IE 7-1-2), ‘fifteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घाट|घाटः
ghāṭa (EI 21), name of a tax. Cf. ghatṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटक|घटकः
ghaṭaka, a jar (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटशासुलु
Ghaṭaśāsulu (CITD), Telugu; logicians. See Ghaṭikāsāhasa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटि
ghaṭi, ghaṭī (CII 3), same as ghaṭikā, the sixtieth division of a day (i. e. day and night); equal to twentyfour English minutes. Cf. ghaḍīyāramu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=114" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटी
ghaṭī (CII 4), name of a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिक|घटिकं|घटिकः
ghaṭika (CII 2-1), used in the sense of ghaṭikā, an hour equal to twentyfour English minutes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिका
ghaṭikā (CII 3; ML), an hour; time equal to twentyfour English minutes; same as ghaṭi, ghaṭī.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 34, note 6), an establishment of holy and learned men. Cf. Tamil ghaṭikai (SII 12).<BR> Cf. ghaṭige (SII 3), an assembly.<BR> (SITI), an educational institution for advanced studies; a university; probably the same as śālā and mahāśālā. Cf. Prakrit ghaḍia-ghaḍā (EI 8), same as goṣṭhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकागृहकरण
ghaṭikāgṛha-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department^1 of time-keeping. Cf. ghaḍiyāramu.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकैयार्
Ghaṭikaiyār (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; members of a ghaṭikā managing its affairs; officials who declare to the public, by beat of tomtom, the orders of kings and other officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकालय
ghaṭik-ālaya (EI 1), a water-clock.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकामध्यस्थ
Ghaṭikā-madhyastha (SITI), an intermediary officer having the authority of the ghaṭikā or recognised by the ghaṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकासाहस
Ghaṭikāsāhasa (EI 8), same as the Brahmanical family name Ghaisāsa, also called Ghaṭaśāsin, etc. See Ghaṭaśāsulu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकाशाला
ghaṭikā-śālā (EI 25), same as ghaṭikā-sthāna; an establishment of holy and learned men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटिकास्थान
ghaṭikā-sthāna (EI 14, 16) ‘a religious centre’; the official meeting place of learned and godly men; cf. ghaṭikā-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटित
ghaṭita (CII 1), ‘put together’.<BR> (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 121, text line 55), engraved.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटितहीनद्रम्मा
ghaṭita-hīna-drammā (LP), ‘drammas that are wanting’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटियन्त्र
ghaṭi-yantra (EI 14), a clock. Cf. ghaḍiyāramu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घट्ट|घट्टः
ghaṭṭa (BL), bathing or landing place on the bank of a river.<BR> (IE 8-5), a harbour or a mountain pass.<BR> (ASLV), a contingent of elephants, the number being ten according to some authorities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घट्टपाल
Ghaṭṭapāla (IE 8-3); EI 31), the superintendent of landing places on the river banks or of passes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घट्टपति
Ghaṭṭapati (EI 7; CII 4; HD), same as Ghaṭṭapāla; generally explained as ‘an officer in charge of quays or landing places (ghāṭs)’; may also be an officer in charge of a pass (cf. the Orissan royal title Aṣṭādaśa-ghaṭṭa-gondram-ādhipati); [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-116" target="_blank">Page-116+ 40</a>] see Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91; JBORS, Vol. V, pp. 582, 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=115" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोष|घोषं|घोषः
ghoṣa (CII 4), a settlement of the milkmen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोटकविग्रह
ghoṭaka-vigraha (CII 4; BL), ‘a battle of horses’; probably, an encounter of horsemen; cf. caturdanta-samara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घोटिका
ghoṭikā (EI 31), a boundary post bearing the representation of a mare.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घृणि|घृणिः
ghṛṇi (EI 12), a ray.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घृष्टमूर्धक
ghṛṣṭa-mūrdhaka (LP), ‘with hairs of one's head fallen off.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घृतप्रदीप
ghṛta-pradīpa (LL), a lamp to be burnt with ghee instead of oil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घुमर
ghumara (EI 23), used in Bastar in the sense of ‘water-falls’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गि
gi (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Prakrit gimha = Sanskrit grīṣma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिद्द
gidda (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a gill, or a liquid ounce; a quarter especially of a sola weighing 16 dubbus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिम्ह
gimha (CII 4), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit grīṣma; name of a season consisting of eight fortnights or four months.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिरि|गिरिः
giri (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिरिदुर्ग
giri-durga (ASLV), hill fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गिरीन्द्र|गिरींद्र|गिरीन्द्रः
girīndra (SII 2), ‘a hill-chief’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गो
go (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; rarely used in the sense of ‘nine’ (cf. graha).<BR> Cf. a-paramparā-go-balivarda (IE 8-5); a cow. See balī-varda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोचर|गोचरः
gocara (EI 15; Chamba), pasture land.<BR> (LP), a tax for allowing cattle to graze in the pasture land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोचरक
gocaraka (Chamba), pasture land; same as gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोचर्मन्|गोचर्म्मन्
gocarman (IE 8-6; EI 28; CITD), an area of land often regarded as equal to ten nivartanas although the exact area varied in different ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोच्छकपति
Gocchakapati (EI 28), official designation of uncertain import. Cf. the Bengali family name Guchāita 〈 Gochāyati 〈 Gocchakapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोद्वादशी
go-dvādaśī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 161, 163-64), name of a tithi; Āśvina su-di 12; regarded doubtfully also as Mārgaśīrṣa su-di 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोगौड
go-gauḍa (EI 12, 28), name of a tax probably levied on the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-117" target="_blank">Page-117+ 40</a>] cowherds; gauḍa is the same as gokuṭa meaning a cowherd or milkman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=116" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोग्रास|गोग्रासः
go-grāsa, troughful of fodder for the cattle (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 108).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोहर|गोहरः
gohara, gohārā (Chamba), a path.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोहरि
gohari (EI 31), Od̤iyā; cattle track or pasture land; or probably, a road (cf. gohara, gohārā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोज
goja, the moon (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 58).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोझ
gojha (Chamba), pocket; pocket money; personal property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकर
gokara (IE 8-5; EI 4, 8, 13), probably, grazing tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकर्ण|गोकर्णः
gokarṇa (EI 9), gokarṇa-kuśa-kusuma-karatal-odaka-pūrṇa (EI 23), gokarṇa-kuśalatā-pūta-hast-odakena (Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 10, note 57), referring to an elaborate form of the ritual relating to donation generally indicated by the expression udak-ātisargeṇa; same as gaṇḍūṣa (in Bengali); palm hollowed to hold water and resembling a cow's ear.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुल|गोकुलं
gokula (EI 9), cf. ‘officer in charge of the gokulas’; cf. Gokul-ādhikārin, Gokulika, Gomaṇḍalika.<BR> (SITI), a temple of Kṛṣṇa; also called āyappāḍi in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुलाधिकारिन्
Gokul-ādhikārin (EI 24), superintendent of cattle; officer in charge of the royal cattle and cowpens (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 194). See Gokulika, Gomaṇḍalika. Cf. Vivīt-ādhyakṣa, Vrajabhūmika, Gomahiṣāj-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुलिक|गोकुलिकः
Gokulika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), same as Gokul-ādhi-kārin, Gomaṇḍalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोकुट
Gokuṭa (IE 8-5; EI 28), same as Od̤iyā Gauḍa; a milkman or cowherd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोला
golā (IA 21), a district.<BR> (EI 31), a granary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोलका
golakā (SITI), also called gulikā, gol̤akkai, kol̤akkai, kul̤igai; name of a coin, probably circular in shape.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोल्ल
Golla (EI 3), a cowherd.<BR> (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोल्लवारु
Golla-vāru (CITD), Telugu; a caste of watchmen [employed as treasure-guards], generally herdsmen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमहिषाजाविकावडवाध्यक्ष
Go-mahiṣ-āj-āvikā-vaḍav-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), cf. Kiśora-vaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमहिष्यजाध्यक्ष
Go-mahiṣy-aj-ādhyakṣa (EI 28), official designation; cf. Go-mahiṣ-āj-āvikā-vaḍav-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=117" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमण्डलिक
Gomaṇḍalika (EI 18), officer in charge of the royal cattle. See Gokulika, Gokul-ādhikarin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमठ
gomaṭha (EI 12), name of a sattra-like institution built by a Musalman chief together with a step-well and a garden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमिन्
Gomin (IA 13), epithet of a Buddhist priest hailing from Gauḍa-viṣaya; supposed to denote a learned lay brother who held some high office on the establishment of a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोमूत्रिकाबन्ध
gomūtrikā-bandha (CITD), the style of composition of a stanza, the second half of which repeats nearly all the syllables of the first.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोन्द्रम
gondrama (EI 30), Od̤iyā; probably, a hill fort or a state having its headquarters on a hill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोणी
goṇī (CII 4), name of a measure of capacity; cf. goṇī-prasṛti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोणीप्रसृति
goṇī-prasṛti (EI 1), a measure of uncertain weight; probably, a handful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोप|गोपः
Gopa (EI 24), a watchman.<BR> (HD), officer in charge of the royal cattle; officer over five or ten villages according to the Arthaśāstra, II. 35.<BR> (HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) officer in charge of five or ten villages with revenue and police functions; (2) officer in charge of ten, twenty or forty families in the city; similar to the Paṭel, or Paṭvārī (H. Rev. Syst., pp. 146-47).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपाल|गोपालः
Gopāla (IE 8-8), a milkman or cowherd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपथ|गोपथः
go-patha (EI 31), a cattle-track.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपथशर
gopathaśara (CII 3), perhaps ‘a cattle-path’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपीचन्दन
gopīcandana (IA 16), a kind of coloured earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोप्रचार|गोप्रचारः
gopracāra (EI 24, 31, 32; CII 4), pasture land.<BR> (EI 30), right of grazing cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोप्रचारभूमि
go-pracāra-bhūmi (SITI), grazing-ground; same as Tamil kaṇr̤u-meypāl̤.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपुर|गोपुरं
gopura (EI 3, 19, 24) a gateway; the gateway of a temple; a tower.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोपुरवाशल्
gopura-vāśal (SII 1), Sanskrit-Tamil; the gate of a gopura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोरचर
goracara (Chamba), same as Sanskrit gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोरचरका
goracarakā (Chamba), same as Sanskrit gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोरव
Gorava (EI 7), a Śaiva priest; same as Gurava, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोसहस्र
go-sahasra (EI 16, 24), name of a gift (mahādāna).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोस्तन|गोस्तनः
go-stana (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोष्ठी
goṣṭhī (EI 24; SII 3; BL), an assembly; a corporate body; cf. Tamil goṣṭhiśeydān̤, convener of a pariṣad. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-119" target="_blank">Page-119+ 40</a>]<BR> (LL), Buddhist; a committee; cf. Bauddha-goṣṭhī, Goṣthī-śramaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=118" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोष्ठिक
Goṣṭhika (EI 4, 24, 33; CII 4), member of a committee or assembly; member of a managing committee; member of a committee like that of the trustees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोत्र|गोत्रं|गोत्रः
gotra (CII 3; IA 19; CITD), a family or clan, a tribe or lineage; a caste. No Hindu can marry a girl of his own gotra or stock, though some forms of ancient Indian marriages did not involve the gotr-āntara, i. e. the change of the wife's gotra to that of the husband at the time of marriage (Proc. IHC, Annamalainagar, 1945, pp. 48 ff.). Cf. Gautamī-putra, etc.<BR> (EI 33), abbreviation of gotra-śailikā, a memorial pillar raised for the dead members of one's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोत्रान्तर
gotr-āntara (IE 8-2), the change of the wife's paternal gotra to that of her husband, which was absent in some popular forms of marriage in ancient India (Proc. IHC, Annamalainagar, 1945, pp. 48 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोत्रशैलिका
gotra-śailikā (EI 33), a pillar raised in memory of the dead members of one's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोउड्
Gouḍ (ASLV), Anglicised spelling of Gauḍa or Gavuḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोवल्लभ
Go-vallabha, cf. Prakrit Go-vallava (EI 24; II), a cowherd; keeper of the royal cattle; see Mahāgovallabha (EI 24).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोवल्लव
Go-vallava (IE 8-3), a cowherd; Sanskrit Go-vallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोयूथी
go-yūthī, cf. sva-sīmā-tṛṇagoyūthī-gocara-paryanta (EI 8-5); yuthī is the same as yūti (or pūti) used in the same context in many other records in the compound tṛṇa-yūti (or tṛṇa-pūti). Goyūthī-gocara may be ‘the enclosure for cattle and pasture ground’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोयूति
go-yūti, same as go-yuthī; cf. yūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रह|ग्रहः
graha (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR> (IA 21), seizure; cf. go-graha, cattle-lifting.<BR> Cf. sūrya-graha (EI 24), an eclipse of the sun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रहण|ग्रहणं
grahaṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रहणक
grahaṇaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, the custody or mortgage of an object.<BR> (LP), an ornament; cf. Gujarātī ghareṇuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राह्य|ग्राह्यः
grāhya (IE 8-8), ‘to be apprehended or recruited’.<BR> Cf. a-kiñcid-grāhya; ‘to be levied’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राम|ग्रामः
grāma (IE 8-4), ‘a village’; often suffixed to the names of localities. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-120" target="_blank">Page-120+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 24), a village assembly.<BR> (IE 8-4), sometimes used to indicate the number of villages in a territory or geographical unit; but the number was often either exaggerated or traditional without relation to reality; sometimes wrongly interpreted as ‘a unit of revenue assessment’. Cf. navanavati-sahasra-grāma-bhāj (IE 8-4), epithet of a territory. See Sircar, Stud. Geog. Anc. Med. Ind., pp. 200 ff.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 146-47), a villager; same as Grāmeyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=119" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामभर्तृ
Grāmabhartṛ (HD), same as Grāmapati (Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 271).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामभोगिक
Grāma-bhogika (EI 24, 29; CII 4), probably the Jāgīrdār of a village or one who enjoys a village as a free-holding. Cf. rāja-sāmanta-viṣayapati-grāmabhogika-purillaka-cāṭa-bhaṭa-sevak-ādīn (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, pp. 114-15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामदेव
grāma-deva (IA 14), a village god; cf. grāma-devatā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामदेवता
grāma-devatā (EI 3; SII 2), a village divinity; cf. grāma-deva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाधिपति|ग्रामाधिपतिः
grām-ādhipati (IE 8-4), ‘headquarters of a Parganā’ (cf. triṃśad-grām-ādhipati-śrī-Kukkunūru); also called modala-vāḍa or rājadhāni in Kannaḍa inscriptions.<BR> (HD), same as Grāmapati (Kāmasūtra, V. 5. 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामद्रोहिन्
Grāma-drohin (SITI), traitor to the village; cf. Grāmakaṇṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाग्रामभोजक
Grāmāgrāma-bhojaka (IE 8-3; LL), free-holders or Jāgīr-dārs of various villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामग्रास
grāma-grāsa (EI 5, 6, 31), a village granted for the maintenance of the donee; cf. grām-opahāra (EI 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाहार
grām-āhāra (IE 8-4; LL), ‘a village-district’; a group of villages; a small territorial unit; cf. mahāgrāma and āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामक|ग्रामकः
grāmaka (EI 8), a small village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकण्टक|ग्रामकंटक|ग्रामकण्टकः
Grāma-kaṇṭaka (EI 24; SII 13; SITI), a traitor to the village; enemy of the security of a village; annoyance to a village. Cf. Grāma-drohin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकार्य
grāma-kārya (IA 8), explained as ‘village rites’; probably, ‘the various functions of the village’; village business (SITI); administration; committee of administration (SII 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकायस्थ
Grāma-kāyastha (HD), a village scribe or Paṭvārī. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 175.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकूट|ग्रामकूटः
Grāmakūṭa (EI 8-3); EI 30; CII 4; HD), cf. Grāmamahattara; the headman of a village (or probably, a member of the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-121" target="_blank">Page-121+ 40</a>] village council). Paiṭhīnasi and Kauṭilya (IV 5) use the word, and the commentary on the Kāmasūtra (V. 55) explains Grāmakūṭa as halottha-vṛtti. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 285; Ind. Ant., Vol. XVI, p. 24. See Rāṣṭrakūṭa, Deśakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=120" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामकूटक
Grāmakūṭaka (EI 7, 12; HD), same as Grāmakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राममहत्तर
Grāma-mahattara (IE 8-3; EI 12, 28), same as Grāmakūṭa and Mahattara; the village headman and a member of the village council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राममहत्तराधिकारिन्
Grāmamahattar-ādhikārin (EI 25), official designation; probably, Grāma-mahattara and Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राममर्यादा
grāma-maryādā (EI 32), fixed local usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामनेतृ
Grāma-netṛ (HD), a village headman. See Śukra, II. 120.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामणी
Grāmaṇī (EI 27; LL; HD), a village headman; same as Grāmakūṭa. See Hist. Dharm., pp. 153-54; Pāṇini, V. 2. 78.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामपरिहार
grāma-parihāra (SITI), obligatory dues of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामपति
Grāmapati (EI 24, 26, 29; IA 9; HD), cf. Grāmakūṭa; the headman, owner or Jāgīrdār of a village (Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 281). See Grāma-svāmika, etc.<BR> Cf. Kuḍipati (EI 18), the headman of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामपत्र
grāma-patra (EI 9), a document indicating the revenue fixed for a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामप्रधान
Grāma-pradhāna (EI 2), a village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामसंस्था
grāma-saṃsthā (LP), a village institution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामाष्टकुलाधिकरण
grām-āṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa (EI 31), the administrative board (e. g. Pañcāyat) of a village; see aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामस्वामिक
Grāma-svāmika, cf. Gāma-sāmika (EI 24); same as Grāma-pati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामटक
Grāmaṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), official designation; probably a mistake for Grāmakūṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामतलार
Grāma-talāra (LP), probably, something like a Faujdār. See Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामटिका
grāmaṭikā (EI 9, 19; SII 1), a hamlet; a small village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामेयक|ग्रामेयकः
Grāmeyaka (EI 31; LL), a villager; inhabitant of a village; probably also the village headman, the same as Grāmika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 327); cf. Vaṭṭa-grāmeyaka (EI 27); also Grāmeyika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामेयिक
Grāmeyika (LL), a villager; same as Grāmeyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामिक|ग्रामिकः
Grāmika (IE 8-5; EI 15; CII 3; LL; HD), a village head-man (Manusmṛti, VII. 116; Arthaśāstra, III. 10; CII, Vol. III, p. 112); same as Grāmaṇī, etc. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-122" target="_blank">Page-122+ 40</a>]<BR> Cf. grāmika-jana-samūha (EI 24), ‘an assembly of the villagers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=121" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामीयकुल
grāmīya-kula (EI 24), an assembly of the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामोपहार
grām-opahāra (EI 5), same as grāma-grāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रन्थवारि
granthavāri (IA 24), household histories in Travancore.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रास|ग्रासः
grāsa (EI 11; LP), food; land granted for maintenance; cf. grāsa-lopana (LP), confiscation of the lands given for mainteanance; also cf. grāma-grāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रासग्रह
grāsagraha, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रासवासस्
grāsa-vāsas (CITD), food and raiment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृ
gṛ (IE 8-1), also spelt gri; wrong abbreviation of grīṣma in Prakrit records.<BR> Cf. gṛ-ṭī; abbreviation of gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृचटी
gṛ-ca-ṭī, abbreviation of an expression probably meaning ‘a mound on which houses can be (or, have been) built and fruit trees can be (or, have been) planted’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृह|गृहं|गृहः
gṛha, cf. ghara (EI 7), a caitya; a cave. Cf. gṛha-mukha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहकर
gṛha-kara, cf. ilvari, manai-ir̤ai, manai-ppaṇam (SITI), house-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहकृत्य
gṛha-kṛtya (HRS), an office concerned with domestic affairs of the kingdom as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 250.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहमुख
gṛha-mukha, cf. ghara-mugha (LL), the door of a cave.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहपति|गृहपतिः
Gṛhapati (EI 25; CII 3; LL), a householder; same as Gṛhastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहस्थ|गृहस्थः
Gṛhastha (LL), a householder; same as Gṛhapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहस्थान
gṛha-sthāna (EI 24), a house-site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहवार्ता
gṛha-vārtā (LP), household articles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहवेटक
Gṛha-veṭaka (EI 9), possibly a mistake for Gṛha-ceṭaka, ‘a servant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहीतसाहस्र
Gṛhīta-sāhasra (EI 33), probably, ‘one from whom one thousand coins have been realised’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रीष्म|ग्रीष्मः
grīṣma (EI 24; CII 4), one of the three seasons constituting the ancient Indian official year; the four months from Caitra ba-di 1 to Āṣāḍha su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृटी
gṛ-ṭī, abbreviation of gṛha-ṭikkara (ṭīkara) or gṛha-vāstu-ṭīkara, ‘a mound suitable for building houses’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुड|गुडः
guḍa, cf. a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (IE 8-5); sugar, the production of which was the monopoly of the king or landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=122" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुडान्तपत्र
guḍānta-patra (Journal of the Bihar Research Society, Vol. XL, Part 2, pp. 96-97), name of a type of document, the exact nature of which is doubtful; probably, a kind of lease deed. Cf. guṇa-patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुड्ड
guḍḍa, guḍḍa-dhvaja (IA 10), Kannaḍa; the meaning of guḍḍa is doubtful; probably, a disciple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गूढजालबन्ध
gūḍha-jāla-bandha (CITD), probably, the style of a verse with an artificial arrangement of the letters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गूढमण्डप
gūḍha-maṇḍapa (HA), an adjacent hall; hall in front of the sanctum, where devotees carry on worship, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गूढपुरुष|गूढपुरुषः
Gūḍha-puruṣa (HD), an officer of the secret service. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 156.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुडिक
Guḍika (EI 28, 31), maker or seller of sugar; see Gauḍika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुग्गुल|गुग्गुलः
guggula (CII 4), bdellium.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुहा
guhā (SITI), literally, ‘a cave’; a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुहाविहार
guhā-vihāra (CII 2-1), a cave-monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुजराती
Gujarātī, the people, language and alphabet of Gujarat. See Bod̤iyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुलिका
gulikā, cf. pudu-kkul̤igai (SITI), name of a coin; also śeṇapaka-kkul̤igai (SITI), name of a coin probably struck by the Śambuvārāyas; pul̤l̤i-gul̤ikai-varāhan̤ (SITI), name of a gold coin; vīracampan̤-kul̤igai (SITI), a coin struck and issued by the Śambuvarāya king Vīracampa; vāl̤āl-val̤itir̤antān̤ gul̤ikai (SITI), a Pāṇḍya coin supposed to have been issued by Jaṭāvarman Sundara-pāṇḍya I who had the title Vāl̤āl-val̤i-tir̤antān̤.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्म|गुल्मं|गुल्मः
gulma (EI 8, 12), a battalion, squadron or outpost. Cf. Gaulmika. (IE 8-5), a bush; cf. sa-gulma-latāka as an epithet of a gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्मदेय
gulma-deya (HRS), dues paid at the military or police station as indicated in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 78, 227.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्मपति
Gulmapati (HD), officer in charge of a gulma which means a group or outpost of guards, soldiers or policemen; same as Gaulmika. Cf. JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुल्फ|गुल्फः
gulpha (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुण|गुणः
guṇa (IE 7-1-2; EI 15, 17, 25), ‘three’; rarely in late records, ‘six’.<BR> (EI 8), six in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुणचरित
Guṇacarita (BL), supposed to be an epithet of a Pratīhāra king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=123" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुणाक्षर
guṇ-ākṣara (LP), a document for a lease of land by the proprietors to cultivators; see guṇa-patra.<BR> Cf. guṇ-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a concession letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुणपत्र
guṇa-patra (LP), a lease of land granted by proprietors^1 to tenants or cultivators for the purpose of cultivating or improving it; cf. Pañcāladeśīya-kulānāṃ guṇa-patra-vidhiḥ, ‘an order of royal favour concerning the farmers of the Pañcāla country’; also cf. Gujarātī gaṇotnāmuṃ. See guṇākṣara, guḍāntapatra.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुण्ड|गुंडः|गुण्डः
guṇḍa (EI 8), probably, a niche.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुञ्जा|गुंजा
guñjā (IE 8-8; IA 26), same as raktikā or rati.<BR> (EI 12), a kettle-drum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुण्ठ
guṇṭha (IE 8-6; EI 28, 31), a land measure of Orissa; equal to one-twentififth of a Māṇa.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 62), Telugu; a pond; cf. silā-guṇṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्त|गुप्तं|गुप्तः
gupta, cf. gupt-ākṣarāṇi (LP), same as gupta-patḷaka, a deed of permanent lease. See Tamil guttagai = Sanskrit guptakā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्तका
guptakā, see guttagai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्तपट्टक
gupta-paṭṭaka (LP), a deed of permanent lease; called gupta probably because it reserved the right of use to a particular man; cf. gupt-ākṣara (also gupta).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुप्ति|गुप्तिः
gupti (EI 4), three in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरचरका
guracarakā (Chamba), same as gocara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरव
Gurava, same as Gorava; epithet of a Śaiva priest (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 140, note 4); also supposed to be a Jain priest.<BR> (EI 4), a teacher; cf. Gorava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुराव
Gurāva (IA 11), same as Gorava; a Śaiva priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरु|गुरुः
guru (SII 1), a preceptor; also ‘the head’ as in Caṇḍik-āśrama-guru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरुदक्षिणा
guru-dakṣiṇā (EI 32), money paid to the preceptor for initiation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरुमुखी
Gurumukhī, also spelt Gurmukhī; alphabet in which the Punjabi language is written by the Sikhs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरुआयतन
gurv-āyatana (EI 21, 28) a temple where one's deceased guru (preceptor) is worshipped.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुत्तगै
guttagai (ASLV), Sanskrit guptakā; a contract or lease.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुत्तिगे
guttigě (ASLV), a contract; cf. guttagai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुवाक|गुवाकः
guvāka, cf. sa-guvāka-nārikela (IE 8-5); arecanut palms, the enjoyment of which was not allowed to the ordinary tenants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=124" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाद
hāda (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit pāda; a land measure equal to one-fourth of the standard measure which was the mattaru or nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हडपद
Haḍapada (EI 11), the bearer of the king's betel-bag (cf. Od̤iyā Vāguli, etc.); also explained as ‘a courtier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाग
hāga (IE 8-8, EI 5), Kannaḍa; same as pāga, or Sanskrit bhāga; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हैरण्यक|हैरण्यकः
Hairaṇyaka (LL), Hairaṇyika; a treasurer; also a goldsmith or mint-master. Cf. Hiraṇyakāra, Sauvarṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हल|हलं|हलः
hala (IE 8-6), literally ‘a plough’; a free-holding (cf. bhikṣu-hala); an area of land, which was not exactly the same in different ages and localities (EI 7, 24, 29, 30, 31; CII 4).<BR> (IA 18), a land measure equal to one-fourth of a sīrā (cf. halavāhā); half of a kula; one plough-measure.<BR> (EI 3), probably, ‘arable land’; cf. sītā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाल|हालः
hāla (EI 19), a land measure; same as hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलदगाङ्ग
haladagāṅga (IA 19), explained as ‘the portion having (ga) water (da) and arable land (hala)’; meaning doubtful; probably the name of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलदण्ड|हलदण्डः
hala-daṇḍa (EI 33), tax on ploughs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलकलित
hala-kalita, ‘cultivated [land]’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 297, text line 25).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हालकीय
Hālakīya (LL), a ploughman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
hala-nyāya, custom followed in granting rent-free holdings; same as brahmadeya-maryādā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलवाहा
halavāhā (IA 18), a land measure; cf. hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलि|हलिः
hali (EI 24), a land measure; same as hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हालिक|हालिकः
Hālika (LL), a ploughman (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 274 and note).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हालिका
Hālikā (EI 15), feminine form of Hālika, ‘an agriculturist or ploughman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलिकाकर
halikā-kara, cf. halirākara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हलिराकर
halirākara (CII 3), a fiscal term of uncertain implication; probably a mistake for halikā-kara, ‘plough-tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हम्मीर
Hammīra (EI 24, 33, 34), derived from Arabic Amīr, often adopted by Hindu princes as a personal name; sometimes written as Hambīra and Ahaṃvīra (EI 34). Cf. Suratrāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंस|हंसः
Haṃsa (EI 15), an ascetic; cf. Paramahaṃsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंसपद|हंसपदः
haṃsapada, same as suvarṇa (q. v.); same as kākapada (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=125" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंयमन
haṃyamana (EI 32, 35), same as hañjamana; regarded by some as derived from Persian anjumān; cf. haṃyamana-paura, explained as ‘the assembly of the Parsees’. But see añjuvaṇṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हण
haṇa (IE 8-8; EI 8), Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit paṇa; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हण्डिकापति
Haṇḍikāpati (EI 5), epithet of a Brāhmaṇa donee; meaning uncertain. Haṇḍikā means ‘an earthern pot [for cooking]’, and the expression may mean ‘the head of a joint family (i. e. one responsible for feeding the family)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हञ्जमण
hañjamaṇa, hañjamana (EI 25, 32), regarded by some as ‘a Parsee colony’, same as Persian anjumān (cf. haṃyamana), though really it is the same as Tamil añjuvaṇṇam = Sanskrit pañca-varṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हर|हरः
hara (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हारक|हारकः
hāraka, cf. ‘one hāraka of barley corn’ (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 30, text line 2); possibly bhāraka, a load or measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरनयन
hara-nayana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरणी
haraṇī, cf. Hastavapra-haraṇī (EI 17), a district; probably a mistake for āharaṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरिबाहु
haribāhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरिचन्दन|हरिचंदन|हरिचन्दनं|हरिचन्दनः
haricandana (CITD), a sort of yellow sandal-wood; one of the five trees of svarga; a title of nobility in medieval Orissa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 4); cf. Śrīcandana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरिदिन
hari-dina (SITI), ‘the day of Hari’; Saturday; the ekādaśī day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हारित|हारितः
hārita (CII 1), ‘caused to be imported’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हरीतक
harītaka, cf. a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); myrobalan [which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हारीतीपुत्र
Hārītī-putra (IE 8-2), originally a metronymic (cf. Gautamī-putra), but later sometimes adopted by members of a royal family like a dynastic usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हर्मिका
harmikā (EI 28), a pavilion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हर्म्य|हर्म्म्यं|हर्म्यं
harmya (LL), a temple or pavilion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हसन्तिका|हसंतिका
hasantikā (IA 15), a brazier or portable heater; also called kaṅgār in Kashmiri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त|हस्तं|हस्तः
hasta (IE 8-6), a cubit (24 aṅgulas); sometimes regarded as 36 aṅgulas (27 inches), 20(3/4) inches, 34 inches, etc., in length; cf. Śivacandra-hasta, ‘the cubit measured according to the length of the forearm of Śivacandra’ (cf. ghal̤e). [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-127" target="_blank">Page-127+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 23; SII 2), a square cubit; a land measure.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol XIV, p. 366 and note), probably the same as pakṣa, ‘a fortnight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=126" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तभां
hasta-bhāṃ (LP), abbreviation of hastaka-bhāṇḍārin; ‘by the hand of (i. e. through) the Bhāṇḍārin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तक|हस्तकः
hastaka (EI 31), same as hasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तप्रक्षेप
hasta-prakṣepa (EI 23), obstruction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिबन्ध
hasti-bandha (EI 32), name of a tax; cf. hasti-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिदण्ड
hasti-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 33), name of the tax for keeping elephants. Cf. hasti-bandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिदन्त|हस्तिदंत|हस्तिदन्तं|हस्तिदन्तः
hasti-danta (IE 8-5, EI 1), ‘ivory’, referring to the right to keep elephants’ tusks without surrendering them to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिकोश
Hastikośa, official designation (cf. The Successors of the Sātavāhanas, p. 110, note 2), mentioned along with Vīrakośa as an officer related to a district; probably, an officer in charge of elephants or the elephant corps.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिन्
hastin (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिपक|हस्तिपकः
Hastipaka, cf. Hāthivaka (EI 18), keeper of elephants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिसाधनिक
Hasti-sādhanika (EI 30), leader of the elephant corps; cf. Gajasāhanī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिशालाकरण
hastiśālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of elephants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिवैद्य
Hasti-vaidya (EI 38), the physician for elephants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तोदक
hast-odaka, cf. hatha-paṃni, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यध्यक्ष|हस्त्यध्यक्षः
Hasty-adhyakṣa (BL; EI 18), keeper of elephants; officer in charge of the elephant corps. Cf. Hasti-sādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यारोह|हस्त्यारोहः
Hasty-āroha (Sel. Ins., p. 54), elephant-rider or elephant-driver; cf. Hāthāroha (EI 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वगोमहिषाजाविकाध्यक्ष
Hasty-aśva-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), officer or officers in charge of elephants, etc.; Nauk-ādhyakṣa, Bal-ādhyakṣa, etc., are often mentioned separately in the same context.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वजनव्यापृत
Hasty-aśva-jana-vyāpṛta, Hasty-aśva-jana-vyāpṛtaka (EI 33), leader or leaders of the elephant corps, cavalry and infantry. Cf. Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛta, Kari-turagapaṭṭasāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वोष्ट्रबलव्यापृत
Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛta (EI 33), Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛtaka (EI 23, HD), military officer or officers in charge of the elephant, horse and camel corps.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वोष्ट्रगोमहिषाजाविकाध्यक्ष
Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), cf. Kiśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=127" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्त्यश्वोष्ट्रनौबलव्यापृतक
Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-nau-bala-vyāpṛtaka (IE 8-3; EI 24, 29; HD), military officer or officers in charge of the elephant force, cavalry, camel corps and navy. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 166; Ep. Ind. Vol. XVII, p. 321. Cf. Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa. It has to be noted that these two are never mentioned together while, on the other hand, one is used in place of the other. See Naubala-hasty-aśva-go-mahiṣ-ājāvik-ādi-vyāpṛtaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हथपंणि
hatha-paṃṇi, hatha-pāṇi, hatha-pāṇī (Chamba), libation of water; from Sanskrit hasta-pānīya. See hast-odaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्ट|हट्टः
haṭṭa (EI 1, 30, LP), a market or market-place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टदान
haṭṭa-dāna (EI 3), name of a tax; tolls collected at the market place. Cf. aṭṭapati-bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टमार्ग
haṭṭa-mārga (EI 19), the main bazar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टरथ्या
haṭṭa-rathyā (EI 30), passage between rows of stalls in the market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टव्यवहरमाण
haṭṭa-vyavahāramāṇa (LP), probably, ‘current in the market (haṭṭa)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हट्टिका
haṭṭikā (LP), a market.<BR> (EI 4) probably ‘market-dues’, mentioned along with talapāṭaka or talavāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हवन|हवनं|हवनः
havana (SII 3), a burnt oblation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हविर्बलि
havir-bali (SITI), same as śrī-bali; bali offered with cooked food; same as Tamil ti-yer̤iśor̤u; tax payable for meeting the expenses of the same in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हयपति|हयपतिः
Hayapati (EI 1, 24, 29; BL; CII 4), same as Aśvapati; ‘the lord of horses’; keeper of horses or a leader of horsemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हे
he (IE 8-1), abbreviation of hemanta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेड|हेडः
heḍa, cf. heḍāu, heḍavālā (LP), a man who wanders along with a herd of cattle (heḍa) for selling them.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेडाविक
heḍāvika (EI 12), also called heḍāvuka; a horse-dealer. See heḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेग्गडे
Hěggaḍě (IE 8-3; EI 28; ASLV) Kannaḍa; official designation indicating a chief, superintendent or director; same as Věrgaḍě, Pěrgaḍě, Adhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेज्जुङ्क
hějjuṅka (EI 21), Kannaḍa; name of a tax; also called pěrjuṅka; Sanskrit mahāśulka or bṛhac-chulka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेम|हेमं|हेमः
hema (IE 8-1), abbreviation of hemanta. See also hema-dhānyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=128" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमधान्यक|हेमधान्यकः
hemadhānyaka, same as māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 45); sometimes hema or dhānaka is used in the same sense (ibid., p. 44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमगर्भ
hema-garbha (EI 12, 16; SII 3), name of a mahādāna; same as hiraṇya-garbha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमाश्व
hem-āśva (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमाश्वरथ
hemāśva-ratha (EI 12), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमटङ्क
hema-ṭaṅka, ‘a gold ṭaṅka (q. v.)’. See JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 197.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमिद्रछ्म
hemidrachma (IE 8-8), name of a Greek coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिलालकन्नडसन्धिविग्रहिन्
Hěri-Lāl̤a-Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), same as Sanskrit Mahā-Lāṭa-Karṇāṭa-sandhivigrahin; the same officer is sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, Maně-věrgaḍě, etc., additionally. Cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिलालसन्धिविग्रहिन्
Hěri-Lāl̤a-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), ‘the great Sandhivigrahin of Lāṭa’; cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिलाटकर्णाटसन्धिविग्रहिन्
Hěri-Lāṭa-Karṇāṭa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), ‘the great Sandhivigrahin of Lāṭa and Karṇāṭa’; cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेरिसन्धिविग्रहिन्
Hěri-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; same as Mahāsandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेवक
hevaka (IA 18), love or desire; same as Arabic hawwa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हि
hi (IE 8-1), abbreviation of hiraṇya, ‘cash’ or ‘revenue income in cash’. Cf. sāṃ-hi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीनाक्षर
hīn-ākṣara (LP), ‘with some words wanting’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीनवादिन्
hīnavādin (LP), the defeated party.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिण्डिपक
Hiṇḍipaka (LP), explained as ‘a touring revenue officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीण्डोली
hīṇḍolī (LP), a swing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिन्दुराजसुरत्राण
Hindurāja-suratrāṇa (IE 8-2), title assumed by some of the Vijayanagara kings, adopted from the Muslim royal title Sult̤ān. See Suratrāṇa, Hindurāya-suratrāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिन्दुरायसुरत्राण
Hindurāya-suratrāṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 363), title of the Vijayanagara kings, Suratrāṇa being the same as Arabic Sult̤ān. See Hindurāja-suratrāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हीनि
hīni (CII 1), same as Sanskrit hāni; loss or diminution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्य|हिरण्यं
hiraṇya (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28, 29), same as hiraṇy-āya, hiraṇya-deya; tax payable to the king in cash; dues payable in coins; cash; sometimes abbreviated as hi as in sāṃ-hi=sāṃvatsarika-hiraṇya, annual revenue income in cash; cf. a-hiraṇya-dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya (IE 8-5); it may be in addition to the tax in grain or in lieu of the latter. Cf. Tamil kāś-āya, etc. Also cf. suvarṇ-ādāya, svarṇ-āya. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-130" target="_blank">Page-130+ 40</a>]<BR> (HRS), king's share of certain crops paid in cash.<BR> (CII 1), probably, ‘money’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=129" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यगर्भ|हिरण्यगर्भः
hiraṇyagarbha (EI 16; IA 10; SII 3), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यकार|हिरण्यकारः
Hiraṇyakāra (LL), a treasurer; also a goldsmith or mint-master. Cf. Hairaṇyika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यसामुदायिक
Hiraṇyasāmudāyika (IE 8-3), a collector of revenue in cash; sometimes mentioned along with the Audraṅgika or the collector of the udraṅga tax probably levied in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्याश्व|हिरण्याश्वः
hiraṇyāśva (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्याश्वरथ|हिरण्याश्वरथः
hiraṇyāśvaratha (EI 12), name of a mahādāna; same as hemāśvaratha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्याय
hiraṇy-āya (EI 7), tax in cash; cf. hiraṇya-deya, kāś-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरियभाण्डागारिन्
Hiriya-bhāṇḍāgārin (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; same as Mahābhāṇḍāgārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हिरण्यदेय
hiraṇya-deya (EI 17), tax in cash; cf. hiraṇy-āya, kāś-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होबलि
hobal̤i, also spelt hobl̤i (IE 8-4; ASLV), Kannaḍa; a small territorial unit like a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होब्लि
hobl̤i, cf. hobal̤i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होली
holī (EI 3, 5), the spring festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होम|होमः
homa (BL; SII 3), an oblation; name of a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होन्
hon, same as hūn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होर
hora, horaka (EI 9), probably, a foreign word meaning ‘a lady’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होरमुर्त
Horamurta (CII 2-1), a foreign word explained as ‘donation-master [of someone else]’; cf. Dānapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होतृ
hotṛ (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ह्रद|ह्रदः
hrada (LL), a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ह्रसित
hrasita (IE 8-3), cf. svayaṃ hrasite karṇe; partly cut off.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हृतप्रग्राहामात्य
Hṛtapragrāh-āmātya (EI 31), officer in charge of the recovery of stolen property. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 29.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हूहूकान्त
hūhūkānta (IA 18), the moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हून्
hūn (IE 8-8), same as varāha; name of a gold coin of about 50 grains, called pagoda or ‘star pagoda’ in English.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हुण्डिका
huṇḍikā (LP), a bill of exchange (Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 266).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हुताशन|हुताशनः
hutāśana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इभ|इभः
ibha (EI 25), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इभ्य|इभ्यः
Ibhya (CII 1), same as Rājanya or Kṣatriya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडङ्ग
iḍaṅgal̤̣i (EI 28), Tamil; a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईडरवारु
īḍara-vāru, īḍigě-vāḍu (CITD), Telugu; a toddy-man or arrack-drawer; from īḍa, ‘a date tree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=130" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इला
ilā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईलम्
Īl̤am (SII 1), Tamil name of Ceylon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इ|इः
Il̤̣aiya-nāyanār (SITI), the same as the god Subrahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ई
īl̤̣a-kkāśu, also called īl̤̣a-kkaruṅ-kāśu and karuṅ-kāśu (SITI); the Ceylonese coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इम्मडि
Immaḍi (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa; literally, ‘double’ or ‘twice’; prefixed to the names of certain kings in order to distinguish them from their predecessors bearing the same name; cf. Nūrmaḍi, Mummuḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्र|इंद्रः|इन्द्रः
indra (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR> (EI 7), a Jain priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रच्छन्द|इन्द्रच्छन्दः
indracchanda (SII 2), name of a jewel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रदण्ड
indra-daṇḍa (CII 4), a pole raised in honour of Indra; also called indra-dhvaja, śakra-dhvaja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रदृष्टि
indra-dṛṣṭi (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रासन
indr-āsana (IA 23), hemp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्द्रिय|इंद्रिय|इन्द्रियं|इन्द्रियः
indriya (IE 7-1-2; EI 5), five in number; ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इन्दु|इंदुः|इन्दुः
indu (IE 7-12), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईश|ईशं|ईशः
Īśa (EI 23), the god Śiva; the king.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईशदृश्
īśa-dṛś (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इष्टापूर्त्त|इष्टापूर्त|इष्टापूर्तं|इष्टापूर्त्तं
iṣṭāpūrtta (EI 4; SII 3), a charitable deed; performance of charitable deeds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इष्टि|इष्टिः
iṣṭi, used in the sense of viṣṭi; cf. sarv-eṣṭi-parihāra-parihṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इषु|इषुः
iṣu (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईश्वर|ईश्वरं|ईश्वरः
īśvara (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’; name-ending of Śiva-liṅgas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईश्वरालय
īśvar-ālaya (SII 11-1), a temple; a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इतिहास|इतिहासः
itihāsa (EI 13), legendary lore. Cf.Mahābhārata, XII, 103. 2: atr=āpy=udāharant=īmam=itihāsaṃ purātanam | Bṛhaspateś=ca saṃvādam=Indrasya ca Yudhiṣṭhira ||.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जदिआक्षेत्र
jadiākṣetra (IA 16), explained as ‘a kind of land’, but may be ‘land of a person named Jadiā’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगत्
jagat (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगति
jagati, jagatī (EI 11), explained variously as ‘ground’; (EI 3), ‘lower ground or compound’; (EI 1), ‘a kind of building’; also as ‘railed parapet’ (R. Narsimhachar, The Keśava Temple at Somanāthapura, p. 2). Cf. devagṛha-jagatī (IA 14); also jagati-ppaḍai (SII 2), the upper tier of the basement. See jagatī below.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगती
jagatī (HA), same as bhamatī; the corridor of a shrine [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-132" target="_blank">Page-132+ 40</a>] on the four sides of its open court, used for circumambulation of the main shrine.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’; sometimes also ‘fortyeight’; rarely used in the sense of ‘the earth’ to indicate ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=131" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगतीपुर
jagatīpura (EI 3), supposed to be the same as brahma-purī or Kannaḍa jagati-kaṭṭě which is ‘the raised square seat around a tree before a village’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जागीर्
jāgīr (EI 33; BL), Persian; a fief; a tenure under Muhammadan rule, in which the public revenues of a given tract of land were made over, either conditionally or unconditionally, to persons like a servant of the State together with the powers required to enable them to collect and appropriate such revenues and administer the general government of the tract. Cf. Wilson's Glossary. See Jāgīrdār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जागीर्दार्
Jāgīrdār (EI 33), Persian; a fief-holder. Cf. jāgīr.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जागृ
jāgṛ (CII 1), cf. [yūyaṃ] jāgṛta sampratipādayitum, ‘you would succeed in accomplishing [your duty]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाह्नवीवक्त्र
jāhnavī-vaktra (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जल|जलं|जलः
jala, cf. sa-jala-sthala (IE 8-5); the waters [in a village].<BR> (IE 7-1-2), used in the sense of jaladhi to indicate ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाल|जालं|जालः
jāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309), cf. Sanskrit jālaka, ‘a bunch of buds’; a load.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलधि|जलधिः
jaladhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलदुर्ग
jala-durga (ASLV), a fort surrounded by water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलजकरण्ड
jalajakaraṇḍa (CITD), probably, some sort of drum which was either made of conch or shell or was shaped like a lotus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलकर|जलकरः
jala-kara (IE 8-5; EI 4), ‘water-tax’ paid for fishing rights, etc., in tanks, lakes and rivers; sometimes wrongly read as jāta-kara (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 157, note 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलकरण
jala-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘navy’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलक्रीडा
jala-krīḍā (ASLV), water sports.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलनिधि|जलनिधिः
jalanidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलपवित्र
jala-pavitra (SII 3), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलाशय|जलाशयं|जलाशयः
jal-āśaya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; see sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलयन्त्र|जलयंत्र
jala-yantra (SII 2, 3), a water-lever.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जलयात्रा
jala-yātrā (IA 13), Jain; the festival of bathing a Tīrthaṅkara on the occasion of the consecration of an image or of the erection of a dhvaja-stambha or of the prevalence of a plague.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाली
jālī (EI 5), a trellis window.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जमलिकाम्बलि
jamalikāmbali (IA 18), also spelt yamalikāmbali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=132" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जमाथ
jamātha (IA 11), Indianised form of Arabic jamā'at; the congregation of a community. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जम्बुद्वीप|जंबुद्वीप|जम्बुद्वीपः
jambu-dvīpa, jambū-dvīpa (CII 1), used in the sense of ‘the earth’ or the dominions of the Maurya emperor Aśoka; cf. pṛthivī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जन|जनः
jana (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनपद|जनपदः
janapada, jānapada (IE 8-3; EI 23, 33), people of the countryside; regarded by some as an official designation (EI 26), and by others as a corporate body (EI 21).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनप्रधानिन्
Jana-pradhānin (SITI), probably, a minister governing a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनेन्द्र|जनेंद्र|जनेन्द्रः
Janendra (CII 3; IA 15), wrongly interpreted as ‘the lord of a people or tribe, a tribal ruler’; really, the same as Narendra, ‘a king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाङ्गल|जांगल|जाङ्गलं|जाङ्गलः
jāṅgala (IA 18), cf. s-ānūpa-jāṅgala, an epithet of the gift land; either ‘arid’ or ‘covered with jungle’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्गम|जंगम|जङ्गमः
jaṅgama, cf. sa-sthāvara jaṅgama (IE 8-5); the moveable belongings of a village.<BR> (SITI), a priest of the Liṅgāyat or Vīraśaiva sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्घा|जंघा
jaṅghā (HRS), forced service as messenger, as indicated by the Jātakas; also same as Jaṅghākarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्घाकरिक|जङ्घाकरिकः
Jaṅghākarika (HRS), ‘one who pays the royal dues by means of his legs’; ‘one who is liable to compulsory service as a messenger’, according to the Amarakośa. Same as Jaṅghā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जङ्घाल|जंघाल|जङ्घालः
jaṅghāla, an embankment (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाङ्घिक|जांघिक|जाङ्घिकः
Jāṅghika (HRS), same as Jaṅghā or Jaṅghākarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जानी
Jānī (EI 22), a corruption of Yājñika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनीनो
janīna (IA 17), ‘kind to people’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनिथ
janitha (EI 13), cf. sudhā-janitha-niḥsyandad-vapuḥ, ‘its body welling forth from nectarous sources’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जन्मभूमि|जन्मभूमिः
janma-bhūmi, called janma-kkāṇi in Tamil (SITI), gift of land, probably made for the lifetime of a person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जन्मपत्र
janma-patra (EI 1), a document recording the birth of a child prepared by an astrologer on payment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जानु
jānu (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जात|जातं|जातः
jāta (EI 2; CII 1), a living being.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातक|जातकं|जातकः
jātaka (LL), Buddhist; birth-story [of one who is to be a Buddha in a future life]; story of a previous birth of Gautama Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=133" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातकक्कुडि
jātaka-kkuḍi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; persons who have undertaken to serve for their lifetime in a temple, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातकर
jāta-kara (IA 15), explained as ‘a tax on things grown’; a mistake for or misreading of jala-kara (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातकर्मन्|जातकर्म्मन्
jāta-karman (EI 4), a ceremony performed at the birth of a child.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जाति|जातिः
jāti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातिसिद्धाय
jāti-siddh-āya (SITI), communal tax payable in coin; cf. inavari or inavari-kkāśu of Tamil inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जटिल|जटिलः
Jaṭila (LL), an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातिस्मरणज्ञान
jāti-smaraṇa-jñāna (HA), knowledge of previous births.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जातीय|जातीयः
jātīya, cf. jñātīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जतुक|जतुकं
jatuka (EI 2), a bat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जौहर्
jauhar (IA 29), javhar (IA 6), Rājasthānī; funeral pile; commitment of suicide en masse; same as sākā or śākā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जया
jayā (IA 23), hemp.<BR> (EI 12), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयधर
Jayadhara (IE 8-2), royal title; translated from Greek Nikephoros.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयघण्टा
jaya-ghaṇṭā (EI 15; IA 12), a gong.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जायाम्य
jāyāmya (IA 19), a kind of charm.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयनपति
Jayanapati (EI 13), probably, an officer in charge of armour or the armoury. Cf. jayanaśālā-karaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयनशालाकरण
jayanaśālā-karaṇa cf. karaṇa (LP), explained as ‘the armour department’. Cf. Jayanapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयन्तपुर
jayantapura (EI 4), probably, the same as brahmapurī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयन्ती|जयंती
jayantī (EI 9, IA 26), the twelfth tithi; the 12th tithi of a lunar month joined with the Punarvasu nakṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयन्तीव्रत
jayantī-vrata (IA 6), a festival in which maṇḍapanirmāṇa-jāgaraṇa-pratimādān-ādi (erection of a shed, watching through the night, distribution of images, etc.) take place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयपाल|जयपालः
Jayapāla (SITI), a class of merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जायापर
Jāyāpara (LL), probably, a householder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयपत्र|जयपत्रं
jaya-patra, jayarekha-patra (SITI), a certificate of victory in a dispute; a copy of the judgement. See jayarekha-patrikā.<BR> (EI 5), a certificate of success.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयरेखपत्रिका
jayarekha-patrikā (ASLV), a certificate of victory. See jayapatra, jayarekha-patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयस्कन्धावार
jaya-skandhāvāra (EI 30, 33; CII 3; BL) ‘camp of victory’; the royal camp or capital; epithet of royal camps or residences; same as skandhāvāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=134" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयस्तम्भ|जयस्तंभ|जयस्तम्भः
jaya-stambha (EI 23, 30, 33; CII 4; SII 1, 11-1), a pillar of victory; cf. dharma-jaya-stambha (IA 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जयिक
jayika (IE 8-8), the party that comes off victorious in a dispute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जेमक
jemaka (IE 8-5; EI 25, 28), melas or food which the villagers were obliged to provide to the royal officers on tour; the obligation of the villagers to provide food to such officers; wrongly explained by some as ‘a tax for the boarding of touring royal officers’ (CII 4). Cf. Marāṭhī jevā, ‘a feed, a meal; subsistence which the villagers were bound to provide for the subordinate servants or Peons when sent to receive the collections’ (Wilson's Glossary, s. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जेन
jena (CITD), Telugu; a span (about 7 inches).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जेना
Jenā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 304), Od̤iyā; ‘a prince’; a title of nobility; later stereotyped as a family name in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

झम्पिन्|झंपिन्
jhampin (EI 12), ‘excelling’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

झाट|झाटः
jhāṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 183), a shrub, wood or thicket; Bengali jhād̤; a bush; used in sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa (EI 27).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

झाटविटप
jhāṭa-viṭapa (EI 8-5), bushes and shrubs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिलो
jilo, jil̤o, jīlo (Chamba), a land measure. Cf. aḷu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिन|जिनः
Jina, same as Tīrthaṅkara.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyfour’.<BR> (LL), an epithet of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनभवन
jina-bhavana (EI 24), a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनकल्पिन्
Jina-kalpin (HA), a Jain monk practising rigorous austerities like those practised by the Jinas before their attainment of kevala-jñāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनमातृ
Jina-mātṛ (HA), the mother of a Jina.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिननगर
jina-nagara, cf. Tamil śinakaram (SITI), a Jaina temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिननिगम
jina-nigama (EI 24), a township in the possession of a Jain temple or, more probably, a Jain temple (cf. jina-nagara).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिनयुग्म
Jina-yugma (HA), an image showing two Tīrthaṅkaras; a pair of Jina images.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णश्रेष्ठिश्रीमल्लप्रिय
jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-śrīmalla-priya (LP), name of a coin struck by the old Śreṣṭhin named Śrīmalla. Cf. śreṣṭhijīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय
jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya (LP), literally, ‘the favourite (coin) of old Viśvamalla’; name of a coin. Cf. jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-śrīmalla-priya and śreṣṭhi-jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya; also cf. vīsalapriya-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=135" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णोद्धार|जीर्णोद्धारः
jīrṇ-oddhāra (EI 23, 26; HA), repairs or renovation and conservation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जित|जितः
jita, jīta (EI 28, 29), income or wages; revenue income; derived from Sanskrit jīvita in the same sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीतल्
jītal (SII 1), a copper coin; Indianised as jithala; (1/48)th of a silver ṭaṅka of the Delhi Sult̤āns (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44); sometimes regarded as a copper coin equal to (1/3) of a silver tār which was itself equal to (1/8) of a gold fanam (SII, Vol. I, p. 161); also called dehlīwāl (Num. Supl., No. 38, p. 33).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जितंभगवता
jitaṃ bhagavatā, also quoted as jitaṃ Viṣṇunā (CII 3, etc.); ‘victory has been achieved by the Divine One, i. e. Viṣṇu’; an invocation used at the commencement of certain inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीथल
jīthala, same as jītal. See JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 197.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवलोक|जीवलोकः
jīva-loka (EI 3), a village institution of uncertain meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवन|जीवनं|जीवनः
jīvana (SITI), maintenance; cf. jīvaṇa-śiṣa. See also bhṛtyebhyo jīvanam kartuṃ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 109-10).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवनशेष
jīvana-śeṣa (SITI), maintenance. Cf. jīvana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवपुत्रा
Jīva-putrā, Prakrit Jīva-putā (EI 24), a lady whose son is (or, sons are) still living.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीवित|जीवितं
jīvita (EI 28; SII 13; ASLV; SITI), maintenance; income or wages; also called jīvita-ppar̤r̤u, jita and jīta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जिवितक्कारर्
Jivita-kkārar (SITI), persons in enjoyment of lands in the jīvita (maintenance) tenure; a class of officials enjoying jīvita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीयर्
Jīyar (EI 25; SITI), an ascetic (sannyāsin) looking after the affairs of a temple; same as Maṭh-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्ञानदीक्षा
jñāna-dīkṣā (EI 32), a kind of initiation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्ञापक|ज्ञापकः
jñāpaka (SITI; ASLV), remembrancer; memorandum of events and happenings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्ञातिय
jñātiya (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, pp. 208, 229), used in the sense of jātīya; e. g. Prāgvāṭa-jñātīya=Prāgvāṭa-jātīya (i. e. ‘belonging to the Prāgvāṭa community).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जो
Jo (EI 30), an abbreviation of Joṣī, same as Jyotiṣin, an astrologer or astronomer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोड|जोडः
joḍa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 19), used in some East Indian records in the sense of ‘a canal’. Cf. joṭī, jolaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोलक
jolaka (EI 4), a canal; same as Bengali jolā; cf. joḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोषी
Joṣī (EI 30), modification of Sanskrit Jyotiṣin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोटी
joṭī, same as joṭikā (EI 28), a stream.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=136" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोटिका
joṭikā (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253, text line 37), a canal; same as joḍa and joṭī or joḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जूहक
jūhaka (EI 3), a village institution of uncertain meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्वलन|ज्वलनः
jvalana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठाधिकरणिक
Jyeṣṭh-ādhikaraṇika (EI 18, 31), explained as ‘the chief judge’; senior officer, chief officer of a class, or officer in charge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठदेवर
Jyeṣṭha-devara (LP), elder brother of the husband.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठकायस्थ
Jyeṣṭha-kāyastha (IE 8-3; EI 4, 24), the chief scribe, or the foreman of the Kāyastha class, or the scribe-member of the board of administration; explained as ‘the senior registrar’ (EI 31). Cf. Prathama-kāyastha, Paṭvārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठपिता
Jyeṣṭha-pitā, elder brother of one's father.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्येष्ठिकाग्राम
jyeṣṭhikā-grāma (CII 4), ‘the chief village’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्योतिस्कन्ध
jyoti-skandha (CII 1), masses of light; cf. agni-skandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ज्योतिष्टोम|ज्योतिष्टोमः
jyotiṣṭoma (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः
ka (IE 8-1), for kā (in Kharoṣṭhī), abbreviation of kāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

का
kā (PJS), abbreviation of kārita and kāritā (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions); also of Kāyastha; also of kāṇḍa, ‘a cluster’ (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कचकदा
kacakadā (LP), Gujarātī; tortoise-shell.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कच्छ|कच्छं|कच्छः
kaccha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), a field bordering on a stream; land near a well (Ep. Ind., Vol XXXIV, p. 175, line 15).<BR> (EI 22), a resolution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कच्छक
kacchaka (EI 19), a low hill.<BR> (IA 18), wrongly read also as kasthaka; cf. khalaka-kacchaka-bhūmī-sahitā as an epithet of the gift land; probably, ‘land around a well’. See kūpaṃ khalakaṃ kacchakaṃ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 114, text line 55, cf. line 43); also kūpa-kaccha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 175, text line 15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कच्छप|कच्छपः
kacchapa, cf. sa-matsya-kacchapa (IE 8-5); tortoise; see jala-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः
kad̤ā (IE 8-6; EI 19), Bengali; the cowrie-shell regarded as a coin; a small area of land; one-fourth of a gaṇḍā and one-eightieth of a paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कदरु
kadaru (CII 4), same as kṛdara; a granary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कड्ढक
kaḍḍhaka (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably the same as Sanskrit karṣaka; see ḍheṅku-kaḍḍhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कादि
kādi (EI 28), a grain measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=137" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडितामात्य
Kaḍit-āmātya (EI 23), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; official designation; same as Kaḍita-věrgaḍě (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडितवेर्गडे
Kaḍita-věrgaḍě (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; superintendent of accounts and records; same as Akṣapaṭalika; sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Hěrisandhivigrahin, Senādhipati, etc., additionally. See Kaḍit-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडीय
Kaḍīya (LP), a bricklayer or mason; cf. Gujarātī Kaḍīyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहल|काहलं|काहलः
kāhala, kāhalā (EI 24; IA 15), a musical instrument; a trumpet. See kākala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहण
kāhaṇa, kāhāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 29), Bengali-Od̤iyā; modified forms of kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कै
kai (IE 8-6), Dravidian; same as hasta, ‘cubit’; a unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कइसर
Kaïsara (EI 26), title of a Kuṣāna king; derived from Roman Caesar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कैटाल
kaiṭāla (IA 12), a castanet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कैवर्तभोग
kaivarta-bhoga (IE 8-5), fishermens’ preserve. Kaivarta-bhoga and Kaivarta-vṛtti really mean the land enjoyed by the fisher-men for their service, e. g., ferrying, supply of fish and boats, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काक|काकं|काकः
kāka (IE 8-6), same as kākinī.<BR> (EI 14), name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकबिन्दु
kāka-bindu (SII 2), name of a flaw in diamonds.<BR> (SITI), a black dot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकल|काकलं|काकलः
kākala (IA 12), a trumpet. See kāhala, kāhalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककलि
kakali (IE 3-4), paper; same as kakari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकणी
kākaṇī, kākaṇikā (EI 15), same as kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकपद|काकपदः
kākapada, kākapāda (SII 2), name of a flaw in diamonds; a mark indicating omission of letters written outside the line.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककरि
kakari (IE 3-4), paper; same as kakali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकवृन्त
kāka-vṛnta (SII 2), a variety of diamond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकिनी
kākinī (IE 8-6), also called kāka.<BR> (IE 8-6), a small land measure; cf. kānī.<BR> (IE 8-8; EI 1; CII 4), name of a small coin; equal to 20 cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī; (1/4) of a paṇa according to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K. V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, p. 125).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककुभ|ककुभः
kakubha (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कला
kalā (IE 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काल|कालं|कालः
kāla (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR> (CII 3, etc.), time, a period of time; used in the sense of ‘an era’; cf. kāl-ānuvartamāna-saṃvatsara (Select Inscriptions, p. 270, text lines 3-4), etc. See prakāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=138" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलभशालाकरण
kalabhaśālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the camel department’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालचक्र|कालचक्रं|कालचक्रः
kāla-cakra, a mechanical weapon placed at the gate of forts according to the Vasudevahiṇḍī (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 15). See śataghnī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालाक्षरित
kāl-ākṣarita (LP), probably, ‘a word of censure passed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलम्
kalam (EI 28), a grain measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलम्ब|कलंब|कलंबः|कलम्बः
kalamba (EI 12), an arrow; ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलन|कलनं|कलनः
kalana, a betelnut plantation (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 205).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः
kal̤̣añju (IE 8-8; EI 28, 30; SITI), Tamil; name of a gold coin; also of the equivalent weight; about 32 ratis (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 141).<BR> Cf. ūr-kal̤̣añju (EI 28), name of a coin.<BR> (SII 13), same as suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलापच्छन्द
kalāpacchanda (SII 2), name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलस|कलसः
kalaśa (CITD), a vase, flagon or water-pot; an ornamental piece of painted wood, stone, brass, etc., fixed on the spires of temples, carts, etc.; a rounded pinnacle or ball on the top of a temple; a dome.<BR> (EI 5), the pinnacle of a temple; same as kumbha.<BR> (EI 11, 33), a measure; cf. droṇa.<BR> (SII 3), a pot.<BR> (EI 33), also called kalasikā; probably, the same as droṇa; a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालसन्धि
kāla-sandhi (SII 1), same as trikāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलसी
kalasī (LP), a measure of capacity equal to sixteen maunds; cf. kalasikā, kalasikāvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलसिका
kalaśikā (EI 33), same as kalaśī or kalaśa; probably the same as droṇa; cf. kalaśikāvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलसिकावाप
kalaśikāvāpa (EI 33), a land measure; originally, a plot of land on which one kalasī measure of seed could be sown; cf. droṇavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलत्र|कलत्रं
kalatra (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलवाड
Kalavāḍa, Kalavāḍā, Kālavāḍa, Kālavāḍā (EI 24), same as Kālavāl̤a, Kālavāl̤ā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालवाल
Kālavāl̤a, Kālavāl̤ā (EI 24), designation of uncertain meaning if it is not the same as Sanskrit Kalyapāla, a vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालिगणत्तार्
kāl̤i-gaṇattār (SITI), Tamil; a committee for the temple of Kāl̤i (Kālī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=139" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलिका
kalikā (LP), quarrel; cf. Gujarātī kali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलिकावलिक
kalikāvalika (LP), a quarrel; cf. kalikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कलिङ्गवारियम्
kaliṅga-vāriyam (SITI), Tamil; committee looking after the sluice; derived from kaliṅgu, ‘a sluice’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काल्म
kāl-mar̤uturu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of land. Cf. mar̤uturu, ghaḍa-mar̤uturu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्नाडु
kal-nāḍu (SITI), Tamil; a hero-stone; setting up of a hero-stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्प|कल्पः
kalpa (CII 1), same as saṃvarta-kalpa, the aeon of destruction.<BR> (CII 3, etc.), name of a fabulous tree in Indra's paradise, supposed to grant all desires.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्पादि|कल्पादिः
kalpādi (EI 5; IA 18), name applied to certain tithis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्पाल
Kalpāla (EI 30), also called Kalvapāla, Kalyapāla, Kalyā-pāla; a distiller of liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कालु
kālu (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; ‘one foot’; a unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्वपाल
Kalvapāla (EI 30), same as Kalpāla, etc.; a vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्वपालवारिक
Kalvapāla-vārika (IE 8-8), official designation indicating a spirit-distiller.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याण|कल्याणं|कल्याणः
kalyāṇa (CII 1), a good deed which is beneficial to the people; a ceremony to bring health and prosperity to a person (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 147); cf. maṅgala in the same senses.<BR> (EI 19), a festival (especially, marriage); cf. kalyāṇa-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणागम
kalyāṇ-āgama (CII 1), ‘having pure knowledge’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणधन
kalyāṇa-dhana (HRS), tax levied for the expenses of festivals or for the performance of rites to avert evil. Cf. prathama-kalyāṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 147).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणक
kalyāṇaka (HA), a chief auspicious event in the life of a Tīrthaṅkara, there being five such events, viz. cyavana or descent from heaven, janma or birth, dīkṣā or initiation as monk, jñāna or attainment of kevala-jñāna, and mokṣa or nirvāṇa, i. e. death which means freedom from the last bondage in the life of a Jina. See kalyāṇikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणसुन्दर
Kalyāṇasundara, Śiva represented as marrying Umā Haimavatī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणी
kalyāṇī (EI 8), a square pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्याणिका
kalyāṇikā (EI 8), a festival. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-141" target="_blank">Page-141+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 11), certain auspicious days with the Jains. Cf. kalyāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=140" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्यपाल|कल्यपालः
Kalyapāla, Kalyāpāla (EI 30), same as Kalpāla, etc.; a vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्यश्रेष्ठिन्
Kalya-śreṣṭhin (IA 18), a dealer in liquors, Kalya being an abbreviation of Kalyapāla, or a word meaning ‘distillery’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काम|कामं|कामः
kāma (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामधेनु|कामधेनुः
kāma-dhenu (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामकोष्ठ
kāma-koṣṭha, cf. kāma-kkoṭṭam (SITI), a shrine of the goddess Pārvatī as an adjunct of the Śiva temple in the same compound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कमलपूजा
kamala-pūjā (BL), probably, worship of a deity with lotuses or flowers of gold or silver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामलि
kāmali (EI 24), often written as kambalin, which means ‘a bull’; a levy probably on prize bullocks (cf. vara-balīvarda). Cf. yamali-kambali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामत|कामतः
kāmata (EI 21; CII 4), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कामावचर
kām-āvacara (IA 10), Buddhist; belonging to the domain of sensual pleasure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्ब
kamba, kambha (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; name of a land measure; see kamma and stambha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्बल|कंबल|कम्बलं|कंबलः|कम्बलः
kambala (IA 23), an agricultural ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्बलिन्|कंबलिन्
kambalin (EI 24), ‘a bull’; a levy probably on prize bullocks (cf. vara-balīvarda); see kāmali and yamali-kambali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कंदासघूट
kaṃdāsaghūṭa (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काम्गार्
Kāmgār (BL), an official designation meaning a servant, a manager, a public officer; a person employed on public works. Cf. Wilson's Glossary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्म
kamma (IE 8-6; EI 12, 19), Kannaḍa; same as stambha=skambha; a land measure equal to one-hundredth of a mattaru or nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्मालर्
kammāl̤ar (SITI), Tamil; the five artisan classes; also called añju pañcālattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पल
kampala (ASLV), same as kampaṇa; name of an administrative division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पन|कंपन|कम्पनं|कम्पनः
kampana, kampanā (IE 8-3), the army [in ancient Kashmir]; cf. Kampanapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पण
kampaṇa (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit like a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनाधिपति
Kampan-ādhipati (HD), commander-in-chief [in ancient Kashmir]; same as Kampanapati, etc. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 447; VII. 1362, 1366.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=141" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनपति
Kampanapati (IE 8-3), same as Kampan-ādhipati, etc.; commander-in-chief [in ancient Kashmir].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनापति
Kampanāpati (HD), same as Kampan-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनेश
Kampaneśa (HD), same as Kampan-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कम्पनोद्ग्राहक
Kampan-odgrāhaka (HD), probably, collector of levies for the army. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 1430.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कंसकार|कंसकारः
Kaṃsakāra (EI 1, 19, 23), also called Kaṃsāra, Kāṃsāra; same as Kāṃsyakāra, ‘a brazier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कंसार|कंसारं
Kaṃsāra, Kāṃsāra (EI 23), same as Kāṃsyakāra. See Kāṃsāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कांसारक
Kāṃsāraka (BL), a worker in bell metal; a brazier. See Kaṃsāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कांस्यकार|कांस्यकारः
Kāṃsyakāra (EI 19, 32), a worker in bell-metal; a brazier. See Kaṃsāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्
kan (EI 12), to glitter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणभक्तक
kaṇa-bhaktaka (LP), undressed provisions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक
kaṇaka (LP), grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकहय
kanaka-haya (EI 24), same as hiraṇy-āśva; name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकमणितुलापुरुष
kanakamaṇi-tulāpuruṣa (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकसभापति
Kanakasabhāpati (EI 3), ‘the god worshipped in the Kanakasabhā’, i. e. Naṭarāja Śiva in the Chidambaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनकतुलापुरुष
kanaka-tulāpuruṣa (EI 16; BL), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक्कक्काणि
kaṇakka-kkāṇi (SITI), Tamil; cf. kaṇakka-pper̤u; land set apart for the village accountant, Kaṇakka being the same as Sanskrit Gaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक्कप्पे
kaṇakka-pper̤u (SITI), Tamil; cf. kaṇakka-kkāṇi; tax, payable in grains, for the maintenance of the village accountant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणम्
kāṇam (EI 21, 28; SII 3; SITI), Tamil; name of a coin; a gold coin; a weight; a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनरेसे
Kanarese, see Kannaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काञ्चनमेदिनी
kāñcana-medinī (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काञ्चनतुला
kāñcana-tulā (EI 23), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कञ्चोल
kañcola (IA 15), same as kañcūla; a bodice or waistcoat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कञ्चूल|कंचूलं
kañcūla, same as kañcola (IA 15), a bodice or waist-coat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्द|कंद|कंदं|कन्दं|कंदः|कन्दः
kanda (CITI), name of a metre common in Telugu and Kannaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्दाचार
kandācāra (ASLV), the military department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्दल|कंदल|कंदलं|कन्दलं|कंदलः|कन्दलः
kandala (LP), controversy; beating (from Sanskrit kand, to strike).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=142" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काण्डपति
Kāṇḍapati (IE 8-3); EI 31), an official designation of uncertain import; probably ‘the custodian of the arrows or the armoury’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काण्डपटिक
kāṇḍapaṭika (EI 9), probably, a quiver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्डार
kaṇḍāra, Prakrit; cf. utkṛ, ‘to engrave’. See kaṇḍāraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्डारण
kaṇḍāraṇa, Kannaḍa; carving or engraving; see Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 36.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कान्दिशीक|कांदिशीक|कान्दिशीकः
kāndiśīka (EI 13; LP), frightened; eager to flee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्दुक|कंदुक|कंदुकं|कंदुकः|कन्दुकः
kanduka (EI 1), probably, a sugar-boiler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्डूल|कंडूल|कण्डूलः
kaṇḍūla (EI 14), ‘itching’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानी
kānī (IE 8-6), Bengali; a land measure equal to one-sixteenth of a Doṇ; cf. kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणि
kāṇi (IE 8-6; EI 24, 28, 30; SII 3) Tamil; a land measure equal to one-eightieth of a veli.<BR> (SITI), Tamil; a weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानिक
kānika (IE 8-5), Tamil; also spelt kānuka; same as kāṇika. (EI 33), also called kānikě or kānikě-kappa in Kannaḍa; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिक
kāṇika (IE 8-5), same as Kannaḍa kāṇika-kāně, kāṇikě-kappa or kappa-kānikě, ‘presents from an inferior to a superior’, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानिके
kānikě, kānikě-kappa (EI 33), Kannaḍa; same as kānika; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिके
kāṇikě, kāṇiki (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a land measure of 57000 square feet; sixty-fourth part [especially of any coin]; also (1/8) or (1/34) part; a visit; a present or gift. See kānuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणिक्का
kaṇikkā (IE 8-8), same as Sanskrit kaṇikā, common^1 seed.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणिक्कै
kaṇikkai (EI 17), kāṇikkai (EI 21; SITI), a voluntary offering; a present offered like nazarāna; presents or customary payments to the king and other high officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्काणि
Kaṅkāṇi (EI 25; SII 2), Tamil; overseer; cf. Māhe-śvara-Kaṅkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कङ्कट|कंकट|कंकटः|कङ्कटः
kaṅkaṭa (EI 9; IA 18), boundary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्नड
Kannaḍa, written in English as Kanarese; language and alphabet of the Kannaḍigas, i. e. the people of Karṇāta (Sanskrit form of Kannaḍa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्नडसन्धिविग्रहिन्
Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3), ‘the Sandhivigrahin of the Kannaḍa (Karṇāṭa) country’; cf. Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=143" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्नदिग
Kannaḍiga, see Kannaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्टक|कंटक|कंटकं|कंटकः|कण्टकः
kaṇṭaka, cf. catuṣ-kaṇṭaka-viśuddha (EI 23), same as catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha; probably, ‘the boundary demarcated by planting thorny shrubs’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्टकशोधना
kaṇṭaka-śodhanā (SITI), criminal justice; cf. the Madras Museum plates of Jaṭilavarman Parāntaka-pāṇḍya and the Arthaśāstra of Kauṭilya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्ठिका|कंठिका
kaṇṭhikā (EI 4, 25, 31; SII 1), a necklace; the emblem of heir-apparency.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्ठिकापट्टबन्ध
kaṇṭhikā-paṭṭa-bandha (IA 11), the ceremony of anointing the Yuvarāja with a necklace which was his sign.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानुक
kānuka (CITD), Telugu; an offering or courtesy made in homage to a superior or a god. See kāṇikě, etc.<BR> (EI 33), same as kānika, tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्यादान|कन्यादानं
kanyā-dāna (SII 1), giving a daughter in marriage.<BR> (EI 29; ASLV), a form of marriage in which bride-price was not demanded or paid; offering one's daughter in marriage without demanding bride-price.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कन्याधर्म
kanyā-dharma (EI 25), same as kanyā-dāna-dharma, the gift of a girl in marriage without demanding bride-price.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपह
kapahad̤ī (Chamba), field meant for growing cotton only. Cf. kaphād̤ī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपालसन्धि|कपालसंधि|कपालसंधिः
kapāla-sandhi (CII 4), a peace treaty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कापालिका
kāpālikā (EI 3), a cloud [of dust].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्द|कपर्दः|कपर्द्द|कपर्द्दः
kaparda (CII 4), also called kapardī, kapardaka, etc.; cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दक|कपर्दकः|कपर्द्दक|कपर्द्दकः
kapardaka (EI 1), a cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकपुराण
kapardaka-purāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 14, 21), ‘a purāṇa [of silver] counted in cowrie-shells’. Cf. paṇa-purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकवोडि
kapardaka-voḍi (EI 23), a cowrie-shell used as coin. Note that boḍi or voḍi is also the same as Bengali bud̤i which is (1/4) of a paṇa and is equal to 20 cowrie-shells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दी|कपर्द्दी
kapardī, kapardikā (EI 9; CII 4), a cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कफा
kaphād̤ī (Chamba), same as kapahad̤ī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपिला
kapilā (BL), a kind of cow.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपिलषष्ठी
Kapila-ṣaṣṭhī (EI 25), cf. Kapila-caṭṭi (EI 5), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कप्प
kappa (EI 33), Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit śulka or kara.<BR> (SITI), Tamil-Telugu-Kannaḍa; periodical and customary payments by persons engaged in some professions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर|करः
kara (IE 8-5), explained by a commentator as ‘the dues [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-145" target="_blank">Page-145+ 40</a>] (bhāga) to be realised by the king for the enjoyment of royal land by using it for cultivation and for grazing cattle’; tax in general.<BR> (IE 8-5) rent or tax to be paid in grains when mentioned side by side with hiraṇya.<BR> (HRS), tax in general, according to the lexicons; according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) periodical tax over and above the king's customary grain-share; (2) emergency^1 tax levied upon the villagers over and above the normal grain-share; (3) tax upon merchants' profits.<BR> (EI 29; Chamba; CITD), a tax or impost; royal revenue; rent, dues; toll, tribute.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=144" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करघटिका
karaghaṭikā (EI 2), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करग्राम
kara-grāma (ASLV; SITI), a revenue-paying or ryotwari village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करैयीदु
karaiyīdu (ASLV), system of periodical redistribution of lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारक|कारकं|कारकः
kāraka (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR> Cf. Prakrit Karavaka (EI 12), same as Prakrit Kārāpaka; superintendent of the construction of a building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करकच|करकचः
karakaca (LP), ‘talk that may annoy the hearer’; cf. Gujarātī kackac.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कराकरकरण
karākara-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करण|करणं|करणः
Karaṇa (EI 4), an accountant.<BR> (EI 28; HD), a clerk; a scribe. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 155.<BR> (EI 19), same as Marāṭhī Kulkarṇī.<BR> (SITI), a type of law-court lower in rank than an adhikaraṇa.<BR> (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28, 30), same as or a shortened form of adhikaraṇa; a court of law.<BR> (IE 8-3), an office or department.<BR> (CII 4), a committee.<BR> (LP), a department, according to the editors of the Lekhapaddhati, the thirtytwo karaṇas or departments being the following; śrī-karaṇa, vyaya-karaṇa, dharm-ādhikaraṇa, maṇḍapikā-karaṇa, velākula-karaṇa, jala-karaṇa, [sthala] patha-karaṇa, ghaṭi-kāgṛha-karaṇa, ṭaṅkaśālā-karaṇa, dravya-bhāṇḍāra-karaṇa, aṃśuka-bhāṇḍāra-karaṇa, vārigṛha-karaṇa, devaveśma-karaṇa, gaṇikā-karaṇa, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-146" target="_blank">Page-146+ 40</a>] karaṇa, hastiśālā-karaṇa, aśvaśālā-karaṇa, kalabhaśālā-karaṇa, śreṇi-karaṇa, vyāpāra-karaṇa, tantra-karaṇa, koṣṭhāgāra-karaṇa, upakrama-karaṇa, karākara-karaṇa, sthāna-karaṇa, deva-karaṇa, sandhi [vigraha]-karaṇa, mahākṣapāla-karaṇa, mahārasa-karaṇa, jayanaśālā-karaṇa., sattrāgāra-karaṇa, antaḥpura-[karaṇa] and koṣṭhikā-[karaṇa].<BR> (CII 3, 4), a document.<BR> Cf. Karaṇam (SII 1; SITI), Tamil; also spelt Karṇam; a document; an accountant, also called Kaṇakkan̤ or Karaṇikka.<BR> (IA 17), name of the half of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=145" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारण|कारणं
kāraṇa, cf. ahaṃ kāraṇaṃ karomi (LP), ‘I shall prove’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणदण्ड
karaṇa-daṇḍa (SITI), fine imposed by the karaṇa (court).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणक
Kāraṇaka (EI 32), a scribe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणकर्मन्
karaṇa-karman (EI 30), the profession of the scribe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणकायस्थ
Karaṇa-kāyastha (EI 7; HD; BL), official designation of a scribe; a writer of legal documents. Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 133.<BR> (IE 8-3), mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणपूजा
kāraṇa-pūjā (IA 9), translated as ‘occasional worship’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणत्तार्
Karaṇattār (SII 12), same as Kāraṇavan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणवन्
Kāraṇavan (SITI), Tamil; an accountant; also called Kāraṇika and Karaṇattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिक
Karaṇika (CII 4; BL), official designation of a scribe; the writer of legal documents; explained by some as ‘an officer in charge of a State department or office’ (HD); but really, a scribe. Cf. karaṇika-ṭhakkura (i. e. a Karaṇika who enjoyed the dignity of a Ṭhakkura) in Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, p. 44; Vol. VIII, p. 158; and Karaṇika-Brāhmaṇa (i. e. a Karaṇika who belonged to the Brāhmaṇa community) in Bhandarkar's List, No. 350. See Mahākaraṇika.<BR> (EI 6; ASLV), same as Korṇam or Senabova; a village accountant.<BR> Cf. Vāśal-karaṇikam (SITI), same as Vāśal-kaṇakkam (˚gaṇaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारणिक|कारणिकः
Kāraṇika (EI 31), same as Karaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिक्कजोडि
Karaṇikka-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), the quit-rent of the Karaṇam or Karṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिकठक्कुर
Karaṇika-ṭhakkura (EI 33), see Karaṇika and Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिन्
Karaṇin (HD), same as Karaṇika. Cf. karaṇi-parikara (Harṣacarita, VII, para. 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करङ्क|करंक|करंकः|करङ्कः
karaṅka (EI 30), a cup made of coconut shell, used in [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-147" target="_blank">Page-147+ 40</a>] measuring liquids; a karaṅka measure; also the same as tāmbūla-karaṅka (the king's betel-box). Cf. Karaṅkika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=146" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करङ्किक
Karaṅkika (EI 13), officer in charge of the karaṅka (i. e. tāmbūla-karaṅka or the king's betel-box).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारापक|कारापकः
Kārāpaka (EI 19; IA 19), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit Kāraka; an agent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करशासन
kara-śāsana (EI 29, 33), charter recording a grant of land for which the donee had to pay rent; a grant for which revenue (either in full or at a concessional rate) was fixed; land granted in the said way.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करटिका
karaṭikā, cf. karaḍigai (SII 13), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करवृन्द
karavṛnda (SITI), a variety of diamond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिक
Karika (Ep. Ind., Vol XIII, p. 119, text line 8), official designation; probably a mistake for Tarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिणीभ्रमण
kariṇī-bhramaṇa (EI 24, 25), ‘taking the she-elephant around’; a ceremony in fixing the boundaries; cf. piḍi~śūl̤̣ndu (SITI), walking around by a female elephant to mark the boundary of the gift land, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिणीपरिभ्रमण
kariṇī-paribhramaṇa (EI 15), same as kariṇī-bhramaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करीष|करीषं|करीषः
karīṣa (IA 9), name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करितुरगपत्तनाकरस्थानगोकुलाधिकारिन्
Kari-turaga-pattan-ākarasthāna-gokul-ādhikārin (EI 18, 24, 33), designation of an officer (or designations of several officers) in charge of elephants, horses, townships, mines and cowpens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करितुरगपट्टसाहणि
Kari-turaga-paṭṭasāhaṇi (EI 5), military officer (or officers) in charge of the elephant force and cavalry. Sāhaṇi is the same as Sādhanika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करितुरगोष्ट्रनौसाधनिक
Kari-turag-oṣṭra-nau-sādhanika (EI 23), military officer (or officers) in charge of the elephant force, cavalry, navy and camel corps. See Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-bala-vyāpṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिवाहिनीश
Karivāhinīśa (EI 30), leader of the elephant force. Cf. Hasty-adhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करिवृन्दनाथ
Karivṛndanātha (EI 30), leader of the elephant corps. cf. Hasty-adhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्खाना
kārkhānā (HA), office of the managing body of a Jain shrine or of a group of Jain shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मन्|कर्म्मन्
karman (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR> (EI 3), eight in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मान्त|कर्मांत|कर्मान्तः|कर्म्मान्त|कर्म्मान्तः
karmānta (EI 13), cf. paśukul-āvadāra-karmānta-konakalika-gaṅgā-grāme. The reference seems to the karmānta, etc., at Gaṅgā-grāma. Cf. Karmāntika, Kārmāntika, etc. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-148" target="_blank">Page-148+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 31), also called karmānta-sthalikā, a barn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=147" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मान्तक
karmāntaka (EI 15), cf. Khaliṣa-karmāntaka-prabhu-Bhaṭṭa-Jayasomasvāmin in the description of a donee Brāhmaṇa who was the master of a karmānta at Khaliṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मान्तिक|कर्मांतिक|कर्मान्तिकः|कर्म्मान्तिक
Karmāntika (IA 14; LL), ‘the superintendent of a work’. Cf. Kārmāntika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्मान्तिक|कार्मान्तिकः
Kārmāntika (HD), superintendent of the mines and state manufactories. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (mentioned among the 18 tīrthas); II. 12 (section called ākara-karmānta-pravartanam, ‘the working of mining operations and manufactories’). Cf. Karmāntika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मार|कर्मारः|कर्म्मार|कर्म्मारः
Karmāra (LL), a blacksmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मसचिव|कर्मसचिवः|कर्म्मसचिव|कर्म्मसचिवः
Karma-saciva (IE 8-3; HD), an administrative officer; an executive minister; cf. Mati-saciva, a counsellor or minister. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 36.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मस्थान|कर्म्मस्थान
karma-sthāna (IA 18), a public building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मस्थाय
karma-sthāya (LP), building operation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मिक
Karmika (LL), a labourer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्मिन्|कर्म्मिन्
Karmin, cf. Tamil Kan̤mi (SITI), an official; ‘an officer’ as distinct from ‘a servant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्ण|कर्णः|कर्ण्ण
karṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णम्
Karṇam, also spelt Karaṇam. See Karaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णप्रावृत
Karṇaprāvṛta (SII 2), same as Karṇaprāvaraṇa, ‘a people whose ears are so large that they use them as a cloak’. Cf. Sircar, Stud. Geog. Anc. Med. Ind., pp. 36, 67.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णपूर|कर्णपूरः|कर्ण्णपूर
karṇapūra (EI 17), an ear-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णत्रोडनिका
karṇa-troḍanikā, see karṇa-troṭana (EI 30).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्णत्रोटन
karṇa-troṭana (IE 8-8), cutting off a bit from somebody's ears.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पट|कर्पटं|कर्पटः
karpaṭa, cf. karpaṭa-pade (LP), supposed to be something like nazarāna; literally, ‘[payment] on account of clothes’ (same as karpaṭa-bhāvena).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पटभाव
karpaṭa-bhāva (LP), explained as Pāghd̤ī, i. e. a present, bribe or inām; but cf. also aśana-karpaṭā(ṭa)-bhāvena (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 50, text lines 16-17 and note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्पटिक|कार्पटिकः
Kārpaṭika (BL), probably, a hermit or mendicant; cf. karpaṭi-vrata.<BR> (EI 11), explained as ‘a pilgrim’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पटीव्रत
karpaṭī(ṭi)-vrata (EI 31), observance of the life of a hermit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्पूरमूल्य
karpūra-mūlya, cf. kappūra-vilai (SITI), the sale-price [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-149" target="_blank">Page-149+ 40</a>] paid for temple lands; the price paid for cultivation rights of temple lands and in commutation of the taxes thereon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=148" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्ष|कर्षः
karṣa (IE 8-8; CII 4), name of a weight equal to 80 ratis; same as tolā; sometimes regarded as 100 or 120 ratis in weight (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 3).<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 309), a measure of capacity for liquids.<BR> (CII 4), name of a coin; cf. kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्षापण|कार्षापणं|कार्षापणः
kārṣāpaṇa (IE 8-8; EI 29; CII 4), name of a gold, silver or copper coin one karṣa (80 ratis) in weight; name of a silver coin of 32 ratis, same as purāṇa or dharaṇa; name applied to the gold gaṇḍa-māḍa also called niṣka or gaṇḍa-niṣka (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 43). The weight of a copper or gold kārṣāpaṇa was 80 or 100 ratis (JNSI, Vol XV, p. 143); copper kārṣāpaṇa was also called paṇa. Cf. kāhāpaṇa (EI 8), Prakrit for Sanskrit kārṣāpaṇa; see kāhāṇa, kāhaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्षार्ध
karṣ-ārdha, ‘half karṣa (q. v.)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्तव्य|कर्त्तव्य|कर्त्तव्यं|कर्त्तव्यः
kartavya (LP), derived from kṛt; ‘to be cut’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्ताकृतिक
Kārtākṛtika (IE 8-3), probably, an officer who reported to the king about the progress of important undertakings; cf. kṛt-ākṛta-jño bhṛtyānām (Matsya Purāṇa, CCXV, 17). See Mahākārtākṛtika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्तृ|कर्त्तृ
Kartṛ (CII 3, etc.), the maker; a technical term for the composer of a record, as opposed to the person who reduced it to writing.<BR> Cf. Karttār (EI 33), Tamil; an officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिक|कार्तिक|कार्तिकः|कार्त्तिकः
kārttika (CITD), crops reaped in the month of Kārttika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिकेयमुख
kārttikeya-mukha, cf. kumār-āsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिकोद्यापन
kārttik-odyāpana (IA 18), also called kārttik-odyāpana-parvan (BL), a festival in honour of Viṣṇu, connected with Kārttika su-di 11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुदेय
kāru-deya, cf. sarva-parihāra-kāru-deya (EI 24); tax realised from the artisans; same as kāruka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुक|कारुकः
Kāruka (LB), an artisan. The five classes of artisans may be the carpenter, the blacksmith, the potter, the barber and the washerman.<BR> (IE 8-5; EI 25, 32), tax on artisans and craftsmen; same as kāru-deya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुकर
kārukara (HRS), traced by some in the Prakrit passage sa-karukara in a Śātavāhana record and identified^1 with [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-150" target="_blank">Page-150+ 40</a>] udraṅga and uparikara; but may be Sanskrit kar-otkara, i. e. kara and utkara (probably the same as upakara or uparikara), or kāru-kara=kāru-deya (q. v.).<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=149" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुणा
karuṇā (CII 4), one of the bhāvanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारुशिल्पिगण|कारुशिल्पिगणः
kāru-śilpi-gaṇa, various types of artisans. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्वटक
karvaṭaka (EI 13), a market town; cf. Sanskrit kharvaṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्य|कार्य्य|कार्य्यं
kārya, cf. Tamil kāriyavārāycci (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR> Cf. Vāśal-kāriyam (SITI), the officer in charge of the palace gate; also known as Vāśal-mudali or Vāśal-nirvāham.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यचिन्तक|कार्यचिंतक|कार्यचिन्तकः|कार्य्यचिन्तक
Kārya-cintaka (CII 4), a member of the executive committee of a corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यदर्शिन्
Kārya-darśin (EI 22), a secretary or manager.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यकर्तृ
Kārya-kartṛ (SITI), an agent; also called Kāriyattukku-kkaḍavar, a designation sometimes enjoyed by the Pradhāni or the provincial governor (ASLV).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्यवाराय्च्चि
kārya-vārāycci (SITI), Tamil; also spelt ārāycci; cess paid for the superintendence of transactions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कासार|कासारं|कासारः
Kāsāra (EI 4), a brazier; same as Kāṃsyakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कषाय|कषायः
kaṣāya (CII 4), a spirituous liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशाय
kāś-āya (SITI), same as kāśu-āyam; taxes and dues payable in coin; also called kāś-āya-vargam, kāśu-vargam and kāśu-kaḍamai. Cf. hiraṇy-āya, dhānya-varga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठ|काष्ठं
kāṣṭha, cf. a-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-grahaṇa (IE 8-5), fuel or wood which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers. See also devakuṭī-kāṣṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठागार|काष्ठागारः
kāṣṭh-āgāra, cf. kaṭṭāgara (SII 3), a wooden house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठकार
Kāṣṭhakāra (SII 3), a carpenter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काष्ठयूति
kāṣṭha-yūti, cf. yūti; ‘a wood for preserving fuel’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशु
kāśu (SII 1), Tamil; money; a coin; ‘a tax’; cf. kāśu-kaḍamai, tax payable in cash; probably derived from Sanskrit karṣa.<BR> (IE 8-8), name of a coin; sometimes called dīnāra (q. v.); cf. ūr-kāśu (EI 28), vīrapañcālaṅ-kāśu (SITI), sambiraṇippalaṅ-gāśu; also īl̤̣a-kkāśu (EI 28), ‘the Ceylonese coin’; śol̤̣iya-kkāśu (SITI), name of a copper coin believed to have been introduced by the Col̤̣as; palaṅ-kāśu, nat-kāśa, nat-kāśu (SII 12); generally regarded as (1/100) of a paṇam; cf. triśūla-kāśu (SII 3).<BR> Cf. āśuva-kkāśu (SITI), or ājīvaka-kāśu, tax payable by the Ājīvakas.<BR> Cf. aḍimai-kkāśu (SITI), fees collected from the temple [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-151" target="_blank">Page-151+ 40</a>] servants; also adi-kkāśu, tax collected from stall-keepers in the markets.<BR> Cf. uppu-kkāśu (SITI), salt-tax.<BR> Cf. vagainda-kāśu (SITI), tax payable in cash for marking details of land, etc.; fees for the division of land; also the fee for settlement of a dispute, etc.<BR> Cf. veli-kkāśu, veli-ppayar̤u (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash, the exact nature of which is not clear. Cf. veli-kkul̤-ppaṇam.<BR> Cf. inavari-kkāśu (SITI), communal tax payable in coin; cf. jāti-siddh-āya of Telugu inscriptions.<BR> (SITI), Tamil; a measure of weight equal to (1/4) palam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=150" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटक|कटकं|कटकः
kaṭaka (EI 8, 17), the camp or capital.<BR> (SITI), a fortified place; a cantonment; a military camp.<BR> Cf. kaṭakaṃ kartavyam (LP), ‘an army should be sent [against one]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकाधिराज
Kaṭak-ādhirāja (EI 4), same as Kaṭakarāja, etc.; a military officer in charge of the royal camp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकाधीश
Kaṭakādhīśa (HD), same as Kaṭakarāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकनायक
Kaṭaka-nāyaka (EI 23), same as Kaṭakarāja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकराज
Kaṭakarāja (EI 9; HD), officer in charge of the royal camp; same as Kaṭakādhīśa, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 309, note 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकवारिक
Kaṭaka-vārika (EI 30), probably, officials serving under the superintendent of the royal camp (Kaṭakarāja, etc.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटकेश
Kaṭakeśa (EI 29; HD), superintendent of the royal camp; same as Kaṭakarāja, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 185.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटपयादि
ka-ṭa-pa-y-ādi (IE 7-1-3; EI 33; IA 19, 24), a system of recording numbers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कठारि
kaṭhāri (ASLV), same as Sanskrit kartarī, a sword.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कठ|कठः
kaṭha (LP), cf. Gujarātī kāṭmāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कथित|कथितः
kathita, drawn up or dictated (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 179). Cf. cintita, ‘composed’ (ibid., Vol. XXXV, p. 58).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटीसूत्र
kaṭī-sūtra (EI 16), an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टण
kaṭṭaṇa (SITI), periodical presents made to superiors by their subordinates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टुगुत्तगै
kaṭṭu-guttagai (ASLV), Tamil; a contract.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटुक|कटुकं|कटुकः
Kaṭuka (EI 13; HD), an official designation of uncertain import; explained as ‘a commander of the elephant force’ (Tripathi, History of Kanauj, p. 137); cf. Mahākaṭuka. See Ep. Ind., Vol XIII, p. 117.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कटुमुख
kaṭumukha (EI 5), name given to a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौबेरच्छन्द
kauberacchanda (CII 3), a particular kind of pearl-necklace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=151" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौलिकनिकाय
kaulika-nikāya (LL), the weaver's guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौमारसौध
kaumāra-saudha (EI 34), a prince's palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौपित्क
Kauptika (EI 1, 23), official designation of uncertain import; probably, a collector of tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काउसग्गिया
kā-usaggiyā (HA), Sanskrit kāyotsargikā; the image of a Tīrthaṅkara standing in the kāy-otsarga posture. See kā-ussagga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काउस्सग्ग
kā-ussagga (HA), Sanskrit kāy-otsarga (q. v.); a posture of meditation in which one stands erect with arms hanging and the soles of the feet kept four inches apart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौष्ठेयक
kauṣṭheyaka (HRS), occurring in the Arthaśāstra and understood by some in the sense of earnings from the king's store-houses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौस्तुभ|कौस्तुभः
kaustubha (CII 3, etc.), a jewel worn on the breast of Viṣṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कौटुम्बिक|कौटुंबिक|कौटुम्बिकः
Kauṭumbika, cf. Prakrit Koṭubika (EI 24), a householder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कवच|कवचं|कवचः
kavaca (SITI), same as Tamil tiru-kkōl̤̣gai, the metallic cover exactly fitting the image of a deity; same as kholī, kholikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कवले
kavalě, also called kavaleḍu, kavaligě (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a pack of written leaves; palm leaves prepared for writing accounts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कवेलुक
kaveluka, kāveluka (LP), tile; cf. kivelu, Marāṭhī kaul, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 144-45.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कविराज|कविराजः
Kavirāja (IA 26), title; sometimes found also among the Musalmans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काय|कायं|कायः
kāya (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कायस्थ|कायस्थः
Kāyastha (EI 24; ASLV; HD), a clerk; explained by some as ‘a registrar’ (EI 31); a scribe or writer in the king's revenue department according to some. See Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 322; Viṣṇu Dharma Sūtra, VII. 3; etc. Cf. Aśvaghāsa-kāyastha and Grāma-kāyastha (Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 175; IHQ, Vol. IX, p. 12). See also Hist. Dharm., Vol. II, pp. 75-77. For derivation, cf. Bhār. Vid., Vol. X, pp. 280 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कायव्रत
kāya-vrata (EI 11), self-immolation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कायोत्सर्ग|कायोत्सर्गः
kāy-otsarga (EI 3), a kind of obeisance.<BR> Cf. Prākrit kā-ussagga (HA), a posture of meditation in which one stands erect with arms hanging and the soles of feet kept four inches apart. Cf. kāusaggiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केदार|केदारः
kedāra (EI 28), a corn-field.<BR> (EI 32), low land.<BR> Cf. bhū-kedāra (EI 19); a land measure; cf. the land measure called keyār in the Sylhet region of East Pakistan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=152" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केदारिका
kedārikā (IA 15), a small field; cf. kedāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केला
kelā (IE 8-8; EI 30), meaning uncertain; probably, a doll or toy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केलि|केलिः
keli (EI 9), the earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केन्द्र|केंद्र|केंद्रं|केन्द्रं
kendra (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR> (CII 3), anomaly of the moon, taken to be her distance from apogee, from which point it is always reckoned by Hindu astronomers; the annual variation in the moon's kendra is 3 signs 2 degrees and 6.2 minutes, or 7 tithis 9 ghaṭīs and 42 palas. See also nīcocca-māsa, tithi-kendra, tithi-madhyama-kendra and tithi-spaṣṭa-kendra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केतु|केतुः
ketu (EI 24), the shape or form.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

केवलज्ञान
kevala-jñāna (HA), Jain; omniscience; a technical term for the highest knowledge; the Jain doctrine of unity (IA 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख|खं|खः
kha (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खद
khada (LP), grass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खद्गधर
Khaḍgadhara, cf. Mahākhaḍgadhara, Khaḍagrāhin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गग्राह
Khaḍgagrāha (IE 8-3; EI 30), probably the same as Khāḍgika; swordsman; sometimes distinguished from Khaṇḍapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गग्राहिमहापात्र
Khaḍgagrāhi-mahāpātra (EI 28, 31), official designation in which Khaḍgagrāhin seems to indicate an officer in charge of swordsmen (as opposed to the clubmen); see Mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गग्राहिन्
Khaḍga-grāhin (EI 28), same as the Khaṇḍāita (originally, swordsmen of the kings of Orissa); cf. Khaḍgagrāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खड्गरक्ष
Khaḍga-rakṣa (EI 30), same as Khaḍga-grāha; used in place of Aṅgarakṣa and Khaṇḍarakṣa of some records (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 11, text line 14); probably, the king's bodyguards.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाड्गिक
Khāḍgika (IE 8-3), ‘swordsman’; probably ‘a palace-guard’; mentioned separately from Khaṇḍarakṣa which is also spelt Khaḍgarakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाड्गिन्
Khāḍgin (EI 23), same as Khāḍgika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाडी
khāḍī (EI 31), a canal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाडूरिका
khāḍūrikā (EI 9), a military exercise ground.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाद्यकूटपाकिक
Khādyakūṭapākika, see Khādyaṭapākika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाद्यटपाकिक
Khādyaṭapākika (IE 8-3), probably^1 a mistake for Khādyakūṭa-pākika (cf. anna-kūṭa, ‘a heap of food’); same as Mahānas-ādhyakṣa; called Sandhivigrahika, Kumārāmātya, Mahā-daṇḍanāyaka, etc., additionally. See Bhānasa-věrgaḍě, Mahānas-ādhyakṣa, Sūpakārapati, Mahānasika.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=153" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाजण्
khājaṇ (IE 8-8), Marāṭhī, etc.; see khajjana, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खज्जन
khajjana, khajjaṇa, khajjāna, khajjaṇaka (IE 8-8; EI 33), same as Marāṭhī and Koṅkaṇī khājaṇ; an area near the sea shore, on which a thin layer of sand accumulates after the ebbtide coming through inlets; a rice field created out of such an area near a hillock by erecting embankments on the three other sides; a field created by reclaiming a river bed; cultivable land created from the bed of a river which carries the flood-water from the sea; a salty marsh or meadow; a rice field created near the bed of a nullah on the sea shore by putting embankments. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, pp. 53-54. It is sometimes called pukkoli-khajjana, pukkoli probably meaning a similar kind of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खल|खलं|खलः
khala (Chamba, etc.), threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलभिक्षा
khala-bhikṣā (EI 3, 25; HRS), a levy; cess payable at the threshing floor; portion of crop over and above the usual grainshare, collected from grains heaped upon the threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलक|खलकः
khalaka (IA 18), a threshing floor [probably situated near a well]; cf. khala.<BR> Cf. khalak-ānte (LP), ‘at the end of the threshing season’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलकीय
khalakīya (LP), tax payable at or for using the threshing floor; cf. khala-bhikṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खलरक्षक
Khala-rakṣaka, cf. Mahā-khalarakṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खल्ल|खल्लः
khalla (IE 8-5), same as Od̤iyā khāl; low land; cf. sa-khall-onnata (EI 12), ‘with low land and high land’.<BR> (IE 8-8), a hide.<BR> (EI 30), leather vessel for carrying wine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खल्लर
khallara (IA 13), probably, a pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खं|ख|खः
khaṃ, abbreviation of khaṇḍa, ‘a piece’ (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खम्पण
khampaṇa (EI 23), a territorial division; same as kampaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खम्पणक
khampaṇaka (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit; same as khampaṇa or kampaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खानक|खानकः
khānaka (EI 15), same as khātaka in the sense of khanana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्द
khaṇḍa (IE 8-4; EI 23), a territorial division; the sub-division of a deśa.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-155" target="_blank">Page-155+ 40</a>]<BR> Cf. nava-khaṇḍa (IE 8-4), ‘having nine divisions’; an epithet of Bhārata or Bhārata-varṣa.<BR> (EI 30), a habitation.<BR> (EI 3, 24), also called khaṇḍi; a land measure. See khaṇḍaka.<BR> Cf. Tamil kaṇḍam (SITI), a portion of the mukha-maṇḍapa of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=154" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्ड|खंड|खण्डं|खण्डः
khaṇḍa, khaṇḍā (IA 15), a sword.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डाइत्
Khaṇḍāit (IE 8-3), a community in Orissa; probably the swordsmen maintained by kings as opposed to their Pāiks or clubmen; cf. Khaṇḍarakṣa and Khaṇḍapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डक|खंडक|खण्डकः
khaṇḍaka (SITI), cf. Tamil kaṇḍakam, a land measure. See khaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डक्षेत्र
khaṇḍa-kṣetra (EI 3, 16, 23), a plot of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डल|खंडल|खंडलं|खंडलः|खण्डलः
khaṇḍala (IE 8-4; EI 12, 18), a territorial unit; a district or its subdivision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डल|खंडल|खंडलं|खंडलः|खण्डलः
khaṇḍala, khaṇḍalaka, same as khaṇḍa; cf. kṣetra-khaṇḍala or ˚khaṇḍalaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text time 22; p. 139, text line 22).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डपाल|खंडपाल|खण्डपालः
Khaṇḍapāla (IE 8-3; EI 28), official designation; same as Khaṇḍapati or Khaṇḍarakṣa (q. v.). See Khaṇḍavāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डपाल|खंडपाल|खण्डपालः
khaṇḍapāla, also called khaṇḍapālīya (IE 8-3; EI 24, 28), tax for the maintenance of swordsmen; tax for the maintenance of the Khaṇḍapāla or Khaṇḍapālas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डपति
Khaṇḍapati (EI 12, 28), official designation; same as Khaṇḍapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डरक्ष
Khaṇḍarakṣa (IE 8-3; HD), sometimes spelt as Khaḍga-rakṣa, ‘swordsman’; probably the king's bodyguard; mentioned separately from Khāḍgika; cf. Khaṇḍapāla; also Khaṇḍāit; sometimes regarded as the same as Khaṇḍapāla meaning the ruler of a small territorial unit. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321. Cf. Khaḍgarakṣa (Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 127-28).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डस्फुटितजीर्णोद्धार
khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-jīrṇ-oddhāra (EI 23), also called khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-navakarman, khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-prakaraṇa; repairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डवाल
Khaṇḍavāla (EI 7; HD), modification of Khaṇḍapāla. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91; JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डि
khaṇḍi (EI 3), also called khaṇḍa, a land measure. Cf. khaṇḍī spelt in English as candy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डी
khaṇḍī (CII 4), a measure of capacity; cf. khaṇḍīkā. See candy. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-156" target="_blank">Page-156+ 40</a>]<BR> (IA 15), a land-measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=155" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डिक|खंडिकः|खण्डिकः
khaṇḍika, khaṇḍikā (EI 22; CII 4; IA 20), measure of capacity; same as khaṇḍī or candy; often regarded as equal to between 800 and 1000 seers. See puṭṭi.<BR> Cf. Ṛgveda-khaṇḍikā, a school for teaching the Ṛgveda (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 37 and notes).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डुग
khaṇḍuga (IE 8-6; EI 4; CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a weight of 192,000 tolās for silk, sugar, drugs and cotton; a land measure; a land measure of 64,000 square yards of dry and 10,000 square yards of wet land [in Mysore]; a dry measure of 409,6000 or 134,400 or 128,000 tolās in different places. Cf. khaṇḍuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डुक
khaṇḍuka (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity; cf. khaṇḍukavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खण्डुकवाप
khaṇḍukavāpa (IE 8-6), an area of land requiring one khaṇḍuka measure of seed grains for sowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खनिक
khanika, cf. Prakrit khaniya (EI 20), a pillar. Cf. khāṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाणु
khāṇu (EI 24), a pillar; cf. khanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारि|खारिः
khāri (EI 17), a land measure; cf. khārī, khārīvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारी
khārī (IE 8-6; CII 4), a measure of capacity equal to sixteen droṇas.<BR> (IE 8-6), shortened form of khārīvāpa or khārikāvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारिका
khārikā (IE 8-6), shortened form of khārikāvāpa or khārī-vāpa; also same as khārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारिकावाप
khārikāvāpa (IE 8-6), same as khārīvāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खारीवाप|खारीवापः
khārīvāpa (IE 8-6), an area of land requiring a khārī measure of seed grains for sowing; a land measure equal to sixteen droṇavāpas or two kulyavāpas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खरोष्ठी
Kharoṣṭhī, an early Indian alphabet which was an Indian modification of the Aramaic alphabet; called Kharoṣṭrī by some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खर्वड
kharvaḍa (EI 5), Sanskrit kharvaṭa; a market town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खर्वट|खर्वटं|खर्वटः|खर्व्वट|खर्व्वटः
kharvaṭa (ASLV), an administrative unit. See also kharvaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खश्चा
khaścā (LP), also spelt ṣaścā; teasing; cf. khāṃc-khuṃc in Gujarātī. See khaśrā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खश्रा
khaśrā (EI 1), loss or injury. Cf. khaścā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खात|खातं
khāta (EI 19), a well.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खातक|खातकं|खातकः
khātaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253, text line 33, note 4), probably, a canal; same as Bengali khāt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खतिब
Khatiba, same as Arabic Khatīb, preacher (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 145).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=156" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खाटिका
khāṭikā (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253); the mouth of a river; same as Bengali khād̤ī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खत्तक
khattaka (EI 8), Kannaḍa; a pedestal or seat.<BR> (EI 11; HA), a niche; a term found in Jain inscriptions in the said sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खट्वा
khaṭvā, cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (IE 8-5); a cot which the villagers were obliged to provide for a touring officer of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खट्वाङ्ग|खट्वांग|खट्वाङ्गं|खट्वाङ्गः
khaṭvāṅga (EI 5; SII 2), a club with a skull fixed at the top; a Śaiva emblem.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खट्वापाद
khaṭvāpāda (EI 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खेडनीय
kheḍanīya (LP), same as pātanīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खेट|खेटं|खेटः
kheṭa (IE 8-5), a village or hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खिल|खिलं|खिलः
khila (EI 15; Chamba), uncultivated^1 land; fallow land; cf. sa-khila-nāla (IE 8-5).<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खिलक्षेत्र
khila-kṣetra (EI 23), fallow land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोज
Khoja (EI 6), a merchant. Cf. Khwāja, the Muslim title of distinction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोल|खोलः
Khola (IE 8-3); HD), an official designation of uncertain meaning (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, pp. 250, 253); probably a kind of messenger. Utpala on the Bṛhatsaṃhitā, 85. 34, explains Dūta as Gamāgamika while some Pāla inscriptions place Khola between the two; probably the same as Preṣaṇika or Dūta-preṣaṇika, a dispatcher of messengers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोली
Kholī, kholikā, same as kavaca (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोट
khoṭa (HRS), what is payable to the king in the shape of hiraṇya, etc., and of compulsory labour and the provision of food for the Cāṭas and Bhaṭas, according to the Abhidhāna-rājendra, s. v. parihāra. See khoṭa-bhaṅga, ukkoṭa-bhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोटभङ्ग
khoṭa-bhaṅga (HRS), applies to a person residing for one, two or three years, or as long as the king's favour extends, without contributing the hiraṇya, etc., and without providing food for the Gāṭas and Bhaṭas, according to the Abhidhānarā-jendra, s. v. parihāra; also called ukkoṭa-bhaṅga, akṣoṭa-bhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

खोवा
khovā (IE 8-8), cf. khovādāna; meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख्स्हथ्रपावन्
Khshathrapāvan (IE 8-2, 8-3), Old Persian; ‘a provincial governor.’ See Kṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख्स्हायथियख्स्हायथियानाम्
Khshāyathiya Khshāyathiyānām (IE 8-2), Old Persian; ‘king of kings’; same as Modern Persian Shāhān Shāh. See Basilěos Basilěon, Ṣāhānuṣāhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=157" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ख्स्हायथियवष्र्क
Khshāyathiya vazrka (IE 8-2), Old Persian; ‘the great king’; royal title. It was translated by the Indo-Greek kings in Greek and Prakrit in the legend of their coins and was the original of the Indian royal title Mahārāja. See Basilěos Měgalŏu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
kedāra, coin of the Kidāra-Kuṣāṇas (Bhandarkar, Carm. Lect., 1921, p. 205).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किल|किलः
kila, cf. Paṭṭakila, Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीलक|कीलकः
kīlaka (EI 23), a peg [for marking boundaries].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीलमुद्रा
kīla-mudrā, letter written on wedge-shaped wooden tablets (Select Inscriptions, pp. 236-37).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किंछन्दः
kiṃ-chandaḥ (CII 1), cf. kiṃ-chandaḥ svit rājā asmāsu, ‘of what attitude is the king towards ourselves?’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किण्वक्रेणि
kiṇva-kreṇi (EI 15), mistake for kliṇva-kreṇi meaning such articles as sugar, liquor, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तन|कीर्तनं|कीर्त्तन|कीर्त्तनं
kīrtana (EI 24, 28, 33; SII 1; CII 4), same as kīrti; a temple or any other thing that renders famous the name of the person responsible for it; often interpreted as ‘a building or temple’; but really, ‘any fame-producing work’; ‘a monument of fame’; a pious work like a temple. See kīrtanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तना|कीर्त्तना
kīrtanā (EI 33), same as kīrtana and kīrti; cf. kīrtita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्ति|कीर्तिः|कीर्त्ति|कीर्त्तिः
kīrti (EI 20, 24; CII 3, 4), literally, ‘the thing that speaks of or glorifies one’; used in the special meaning of ‘any work which renders the constructor of it famous’; a meritorious work; a pious deed; same as kīrtana, kīrtanā; often interpreted as ‘a building or temple’; but actually, ‘any fame-producing work’. See kīrti-sthāna.<BR> (CII 1), fame of a dead person; cf. yaśo vā kīrtir=vā. See yaśas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तिमुख
kīrti-mukha (CII 4), a decorative motif.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तिस्तम्भ|कीर्तिस्तम्भः
kīrti-stambha, cf. mahāmeru-śrī-kīrtistambha (BL); ‘the pillar of fame’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तिस्थान
kīrti-sthāna (EI 1), same as kīrti or kīrtana; a temple or some such object calculated to render famous the name of the person responsible for it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्तित|कीर्त्तित|कीर्त्तितः
kīrtita (EI 24), ‘built’; cf. prakīrtita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीशोरवडवागोमहिषाजाविकाध्यक्ष
Kīśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), cf. Go-mahiṣ-āj-āvikā-vaḍav-ādhyakṣa, Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, Kari-turaga-pattan-ākarasthāna-gokul-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किशोरवदवागोमहिष्यधिकृत
Kiśoravadavā-go-mahiṣy-adhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 17, 23), cf. Go-mahiṣy-aj-ādhyakṣa, Kiśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किशोरवडवागोमहिष्यजाविकाध्यक्ष
Kiśoravaḍavā-go-mahiṣy-aj-āvik-ādhyakṣa (EI 29), cf. Go-mahiṣy-aj-ādhyakṣa, Kiśora-vaḍavā-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādhyakṣa, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-159" target="_blank">Page-159+ 40</a>] etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=158" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किटिका
kiṭikā (EI 14), Sanskritised form of kiḍi or kiḍā, ‘a matting screen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किवेलु
kivelu (LP), ‘tile’; cf. Marāṭhī kaul. See kaveluka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्लिण्व
kliṇva, cf. a-lavaṇa-kliṇva-khātaka (IE 8-5); probably, such things as sugar and liquor; same as kliṇva-kreṇi; cf. also a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (IE 8-5), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्लिण्वक्रेणि
kliṇva-kreṇi, cf. a-lavaṇa-kliṇva-kreṇi-khanaka (IE 8-5); same as kliṇva meaning articles like sugar, liquor, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कॢप्त|कॢप्तः
kḷpta (CII 3, 4; HRS), cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta (IE 8-5); probably, the tax on permanent tenants or the fixed revenue; fixed tax which is one of the seven sources of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra; cf. upakḷpta, kḷpta-kara, udraṅga, kḷpta-śluka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कॢप्तकर
kḷpta-kara (IE 8-5), fixed tax; same as kḷpta-śulka; cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कॢप्तशुल्क
kḷpta-śulka (IE 8-5), fixed duty; same as kḷpta, kḷpta-kara; cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडे
koḍe (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of capacity. Cf. Kannaḍa koda-visa, an allowance of a visa of grain, etc., for every bullock-load that comes into a town, paid to a person employed to check the demands of the toll-collector.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडेवण
koḍevaṇa (EI 27), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोद्रव|कोद्रवः
kodrava (EI 5, 12), name of a grain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोह्ली
kohlī (Chamba), wet land, irrigable land; same as āli; opposed to otaḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्
kol (IE 8-6), Tamil; a measuring rod; cf. śrīpāda-kkol, ‘rod measured according to the length of the king's foot’; māliga-kkol, ‘the measuring rod of the palace’; etc.<BR> (EI 25), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल|कोलं|कोलः
kola, same as tolaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलग
kolaga (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलग
kol̤aga (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; measure of capacity equal to 4 bal̤as; a dry measure of 768 or 384 or 72 tolas in different places.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलभण्डालु
kola-bhaṇḍālu, also called kolla-baṇḍi (CITD), Telugu; a bullock-cart load. Cf. busi-baṇḍi or busi-bhaṇḍālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलिक
Kolika (IE 8-8; EI 30), same as Sanskrit Kaulika, a weaver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलिकनिकाय
kolika-nikāya (CII 4), a guild of the Kaulikas or weavers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्लबण्डि
kolla-baṇḍi, see kola-bhaṇḍālu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=159" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलु
kolu (IE 8-6), a measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोमटि
Komaṭi (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a Vaiśya shop-keeper; a member of the mercantile caste.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोम्मुमर्तुरु
kommu-mar̤turu (CITD), Telugu; see mar̤uturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोञ्जल्ल
koñjalla, cf. a-kara-viṣṭi-koñjalla (IE 8-5); a fiscal term of doubtful import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोरट
koraṭa (CII 3), a fiscal term of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष|कोषं|कोषः
koṣa, treasure, see Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 15-16.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोशाधिप
Koś-ādhipa (EI 32, 33), a treasurer; same as Koś-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोषगृह
koṣa-gṛha (HRS), treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोशजा
Kośajā (EI 9), a cocoon-producer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोषवाह
koṣavāha (EI 14), name of a land measure; as much land as can be irrigated by one koṣa or leather bucket.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठ|कोष्ठः
koṣṭha (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’. Cf. koṣṭhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठागार
koṣṭh-āgāra (HRS), the royal granary.<BR> (EI 29), cf. Tamil koṭṭagāram, koṭṭāram (EI 22; SITI), treasury or store-house.<BR> Cf. Tamil koṭṭagāram, etc. (SII 2), stables.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठागारकरण
koṣṭhāgāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), department of the collection of the king's share of grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठागारिन्
Koṣṭhāgārin, officer in charge of the treasury or store-house; cf. Mahākoṣṭhāgārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठक|कोष्ठकः
koṣṭhaka (BL; LP), a granary or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठकरण
Koṣṭha-karaṇa (EI 29), a treasury accountant; also the revenue department (cf. koṣṭha-vyāpāra).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठव्यापार
koṣṭha-vyāpāra (EI 29), the revenue department (cf. koṣṭha-karaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठी
koṣṭhī, cf. Prakrit koḍhi (LL), a hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठिका
koṣṭhikā (EI 15), same as koṣṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोष्ठिकाकरण
koṣṭhikā-karaṇa (LP), the royal treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट|कोटः
koṭa (LP), also called koṭaḍī; ‘wall of the compound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटाधिकरणिक
Koṭ-ādhikaraṇika (BL), officer in charge of or related to the government of a koṭa or koṭṭa (fort).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटडि
koṭaḍi, koṭaḍī cf. koṭaḍi-sahita (LP), ‘together with walls of the compound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटक|कोटकः
koṭaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 313), ‘a district’; same as koṭṭaka; cf. koṭṭa-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटपाल|कोटपालः
Koṭapāla (EI 17), same as Koṭṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=160" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोठव्यापार
koṭha-vyāpāra (EI 28), same as koṣṭha-vyāpāra; the revenue department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटिहोम|कोटिहोमः
koṭi-homa (EI 12, 33), name of a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोटिका
koṭikā, a load [of cloth] (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR> (EI 14), a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्ट|कोट्टं|कोट्टः
koṭṭa (EI 24), a fort. See koṭṭai and koṭṭam of the South Indian inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टै
koṭṭai (ASLV), a fort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टक
koṭṭaka, see koṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टम्
koṭṭam (IE 8-4; EI 27), Tamil; a district; a district within a maṇḍala or province.<BR> (ASLV), a division of the rājya; sometimes subdivided into nāḍus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टनिग्रह
Koṭṭa-nigraha (EI 8; IA 30; BL), commander of a fort; same as Koṭṭapāla. Cf. Koṭṭanigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टनिग्रहिन्
Koṭṭanigrahin (IA 30), probably, the commander of a fort; same as Koṭṭanigraha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टपाल
Koṭṭapāla (IE 8-3; EI 12, 18, 25, 30; BL), officer in charge of a fort; governor of a fort. Cf. the Bhagalpur plate of Nārāyaṇapāla (Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306); sometimes spelt Koṭapāla (cf. the Nalanda plate of Devapāla in Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321). Same as Koṭṭapati.<BR> (EI 25), the city prefect; same as Kotwāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टपति
Koṭṭapati (IE 8-3), same as Koṭṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टविषय
koṭṭa-viṣaya (IE 8-4; CII 1), a viṣaya or district around a fortress; a district with its headquarters in a fort. See koṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोत्टाल्
Kotwāl (IE 8-2, 8-3), same as Talāra or the prefect of the city police; the chief police officer of a city or town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोवै
kovai (SITI), Tamil; name of a gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोवेर
kovera (IE 8-5), cf. karaṇe koveram; probably, some levy at the court of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोयिल्नायकम्
Koyil-nāyakam (EI 25), Tamil; temple officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोयिल्श्रीकार्यम्
Koyil-śrīkāryam (EI 25), Tamil; a temple officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमादित्य
Kramāditya (IE 8-2), see āditya. The word krama here seems to mean vikrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमक|क्रमकः
Kramaka (EI 5), also called Kramavid, Kramayuta; epithet of Brāhmaṇas. Cf. Krama-vitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमविद्
Kramavid (EI 5), epithet of Brāhmanas; same as Kramaka, Kramayuta. Cf. Krama-vitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=161" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमवित्त
Krama-vitta (SITTI), a Brāhmaṇa well-versed in the method of reciting the Vedas according to the krama order. Cf. Kramaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रमयुत
Kramayuta (EI 5), epithet of Brāhmaṇas; same as Kramaka, Kramavid. Cf. Krama-vitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रयचीरिका
kraya-cīrikā (EI 26), a deed of purchase or sale-deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृदर|कृदरं|कृदरः
kṛdara (CII 4), a granary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रीडायित
krīḍāyita (EI 12), sporting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृशान्न
kṛś-ānna, ‘minor food’; cf. kṛśānna-mūlya which is the money to meet expenses of light food (Select Inscriptions, p. 159). See mukh-āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रिया
kriyā (CII 4), Śaiva ceremonies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रियणका
kriyaṇakā (LP), cf. Gujarātī kariyāṇuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रोड|क्रोडं|क्रोडः
kroḍa, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रोश|क्रोशः
krośa (CII 1), a distance of about two miles and a quarter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृपण|कृपणः
kṛpaṇa (CII 1), poor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृशानु|कृशानुः
kṛśānu (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णल|कृष्णलः
kṛṣṇala (IA 26), same as rati or guñjā. One kṛṣṇala is regarded by the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K. V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, p. 125) as equal to three guñjās or raktikās apparently through confusion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णराजरूपक
kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka (EI 30), name of a silver coin issues by the Kalacuri king Kṛṣṇarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृत|कृतं
kṛta (EI 12, 14, 23; BL; CII 3), literally ‘accomplished’. i. e. ‘completed’; used in earlier records in connection with the era later associated with Vikramāditya. Often spelt krita, possibly standing for krīta meaning ‘purschased’, which was a name sometimes applied to certain foreign rulers of North-Western Bhāratavarṣa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 152).<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR> (CII 1), ‘arranged for’, ‘made arrangements for’.<BR> (EI 23), fruit, booty, reward.<BR> (Sel. Ins., p. 202), ‘engraved’.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 41, verse 13), written, drafted or composed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतान्त|कृतांत|कृतान्तः
kṛtānta (EI 3), same as siddhānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतप्रान्त
kṛta-prānta, cf. sa-kṛta-prānta (IE 8-5), Prakrit sa-kuta-ppanta; probably, demarcated boundaries.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृति|कृतिः
kṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty’; cf. kṛtin, ‘twentytwo’.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 98), a composition or performance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=162" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतिन्
kṛtin (EI 7-1-2), ‘twentytwo’; cf. kṛti, ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृतोपसन्न
kṛt-opasanna (EI 30), an expression of doubtful import; epithet of a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृत्तिदार
kṛttidāra (IA 15), an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रूरदृश्
krūra-dṛś (EI 12), designation of Mars and Saturn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षान्ति|क्षांति|क्षांतिः|क्षान्तिः
kṣānti (CII 1), forgiveness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षपेश्वर
kṣapeśvara (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षार|क्षारं|क्षारः
kṣāra (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षत|क्षतं
kṣata (EI 23), engraved; cf. utkīrṇa, udghāṭita, etc.<BR> Cf. Prakrit chata (EI 7), ‘written’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षत्रप|क्षत्रपः
Kṣatrapa (IE 8-2, 8-3; ML; HD), feudatory title of foreign origin; Old Persian Khshathrapāvan, ‘a provincial governor’; a Satrap. See CII, Vol. II, pp. xxxiv, 23, 28; Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 166. See Mahākṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षत्तृ
Kṣattṛ (HD), a chamberlain. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 111. According to Manu (X. 16) and Yājñavalkya (I. 94), the offspring of a Kṣatriya woman from a Śūdra male was called Kṣattṛ. This apparently refers to a tribe or community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षौणी
kṣauṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेमराज
Kṣemarāja (LL), title of a pious king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्र|क्षेत्रं
kṣetra (EI 24), a department or committee.<BR> (SII 1), a sacred place. Cf. Varāha-kṣetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रकर|क्षेत्रकरः
Kṣetrakara (EI 12, 15), a cultivator.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रप|क्षेत्रपः
Kṣetrapa (IE 8-3; HD), same as Kṣetrapāla; superintendent^1 of the king's Khās Mahāl. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रपाल|क्षेत्रपालः
Kṣetrapāla (IE 8-3; EI 17; HD), same as Kṣetrapa. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षेत्रसीमन्
kṣetra-sīman (SII 1), explained as ‘a hamlet’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षीर|क्षीरः
kṣīra, cf. a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya (IE 8-5); milk which the villagers (probably, the milkmen) were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षिति|क्षितिः
kṣiti (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षितिदान
kṣiti-dāna (EI 23), same as bhūmi-dāna; name of a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्ष्मा
kṣmā (I 7-1-2; E 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षोभ|क्षोभः
kṣobha, cf. a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (IE 8-5; EI 1); obligation or trouble.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षोणी
kṣoṇī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्र|क्षुद्रः
kṣudra, cf. Prakrit cūla=culla ‘small’; prefixed to the names of persons, localities, etc., in order to distinguish them from [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-164" target="_blank">Page-164+ 40</a>] others; e. g., Kṣudra-Mūla, Mahā-Mūla; Kṣudra-Dharmagiri, Mahā-Dharmagiri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=163" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रक|क्षुद्रकः
Kṣudraka (CII 1), a person of a low position; a poor man.<BR> (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 44), same as tolaka or draṃkṣaṇa; also spelt kṣudrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रम
kṣudrama, see kṣudraka; same as tolaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुण|क्षुणः
kṣuṇa (CII 2-1), corruption of kṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षूण
kṣūṇa (EI 3), fault or defect.<BR> Cf. kṣūṇāni (LP), probably, ‘expenses’; kṣūṇ-ādika, ‘expenses, etc.’<BR> Cf. mānak-aikaṃ yāvat kṣūṇaṃ na hi (LP), ‘it matters not if there is a loss of one maund only’, i. e. such a case should not be considered a loss.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कु|कुः
ku (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR> (CITD), a contraction of Telugu kuṇṭalu or kuccelu, a certain measure of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुच|कुचः
kuca (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुचट
kucaṭa (LP), disturbance of the peace of mind; cf. Gujarātī kacvāṭ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुड्य|कुड्यं
kuḍya, probably, ‘a mound’; see eḍuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल|कुलं|कुलः
kula (LL), Jain; a particular section of the Jains.<BR> Cf. udhad̤īyā-jhumpad̤īya-kula (LP), ‘farmers on whom revenue is fixed in a lump sum and who live in huts’.<BR> Cf. kulam (EI 25), a land measure; equal to 2 halas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूल|कूलं
kūla (SITI), tax on grains and pulses; cf. Tamil kiru-kūlam.<BR> Cf. Tamil kūlam (SII 1), a market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलब्राह्मण
Kula-brāhmaṇa (SII 1), a family priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलचारिक
Kulacārika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 119, text line 8), wrong reading of Kulavārika=Kulavāra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलकरणि|कुलकरणिः
Kulakaraṇi (EI 15; SII 11-1), a hereditary clerk or officer; a clerk; cf. the modern family name Kulkarṇī. The word occurs in the Sūdi inscription of Śaka 981 (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 91). Same as Senabova (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलाख्या
kul-ākhyā (CII 3), a family appellation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलकुटुम्बिक
Kula-kuṭumbika (LP), farmers who are permanently settled.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपञ्जिका
kula-pañjikā, cf. vaṃśāvalī (IA 30).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपति|कुलपतिः
Kulapati (EI 9), probably, the head of a school or institution.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपुत्र|कुलपुत्रः
Kulaputra (EI 22; CII 8), literally, ‘high-born’; epithet of a nobleman. See Kulaputraka. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-165" target="_blank">Page-165+ 40</a>]<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 156); explained as ‘the chief architect’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=164" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलपुत्रक
Kulaputraka (EI 22, 23), a nobleman. See Kulaputra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलरिक
Kularika (CII 4), a potter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवार|कुलवारः
Kulavāra (EI 23), arbitrator; also called Kulavārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवारिक
Kulavārika, see Kulacārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवाय्
kulavāy (IE 8-6), Bengali form of kulyavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलि|कुलिः
kuli (IE 8-6; EI 28), Tamil; a small land measure equal to (1/240) of a pāḍagam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूलि
kūli (SII 1), Tamil; hire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलिक|कुलिकः
Kulika (EI 15, 35), ‘the head of a guild’; but cf. Prathama-kulika, ‘the foremost among the Kulikas’, who was the member of a board of administration like the Pañcāyat Board. Some inscriptions of the Gupta age mention a board of administration consisting of the Nagara-śreṣṭhin Sārthavāha, Prathama-Kulika and Prathama-Kāyastha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 130), where Kulika seems to mean ‘an artisan’. Kulika is also mentioned as a people probably meaning mercenary soldiers of the Kullu valley (ibid., Vol. XVII, p. 321); cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 126-27.<BR> (HD), an officer in charge of ten villages who was granted a kula of land for his salary (Manu, VII. 119, and Kullūka thereon); also ‘an arbitrator as a tribunal’ (IHQ, Vol. XIX, p. 14).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्लक
kullaka, cf. udak-āsīhāra-kullaka; probably, a kind of channel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्य|कुल्यं|कुल्यः
kulya (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity equal to 8 droṇas.<BR> (IE 8-6; EI 29), a land measure; shortened form of kulyavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्यवाप
kulyavāpa (IE 8-6; EI 28), ‘an area of land requiring one kulya measure of seed grains to be sown’; a land measure which was not the same in different ages and localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुल्या
kulyā (EI 13), a channel for irrigation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमार|कुमारं|कुमारः
Kumāra (IE 8-2; EI 28, 30; BL; HD), designation of a prince or the king's heir-apparent; usually a prince younger than the Yuvarāja (heir-apparent). See CII, Vol. I, pp. 93, 97; Vol. II, pp. 40, 48.<BR> Cf. Devī-kumāra (IA 18; CII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमाराधिराज
Kumārādhirāja (EI 12, 28), title of a ruler.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारदिवान
Kumāra-Divāna (BL), possibly, a Divāna or minister enjoying the status of a Kumāra or a Kumāra who was the Divāna. Cf. Kumār-āmātya, Kumāra-mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=165" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगदिआणक
kumāra-gadiāṇaka (CII 4), taken to be the name of a coin by some scholars; but probably, a tax. Same as kumāra-gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगद्याण
kumāra-gadyāṇa (IE 8-5; EI 4; HRS), probably, a tax of one gadyāṇa (i. e. the coin of that name) payable on the occasion of a prince's birth. See kumāra-gadiāṇaka, komarina-gadyāṇa, etc. Cf. Tamil kumara-kaccāṇam (EI 21), supposed to be a tax payable in coin for the maintenance of the temple of Kumāra or Subrahmaṇya (SITI). But kumāra-gadyāṇa is found in the records of the Gāhaḍavālas of Vārāṇasī, in whose dominions the god in question was not as popular as in the South.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगुरु
Kumāra-guru (BL), probably, the royal preceptor enjoying the status of a Kumāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमरकच्चाणम्
kumara-kaccāṇam (EI 21), a tax; cf. kumāra-gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारमहापात्र
Kumāra-mahāpātra (EI 8-3; EI 28), a Mahāpātra enjoying the status of a Kumāra or a Kumāra who was the Mahāpātra; cf. Kumār-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारामात्य
Kumār-āmātya (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), probably ‘an Amātya enjoying the status of a Kumāra’. Cf. Tamil pil̤l̤aigal̤-tanam (SITI), ‘the status of a Pil̤l̤ai (prince)’, an officers’ cadre mainly composed of the junior members of the royal family. See Proc. 6th AIOC, pp. 211 ff.; Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 123.<BR> (IE 8-3), in one case, a Kumār-āmātya was at first a Mantrin, but later became a Mahābalādhikṛta; in another case, a Kumārāmātya was also a Mantrin. Cf. Kumāra-mahāpātra, etc.<BR> Cf. Kumāra-varga=pil̤l̤aigal̤-tanam (SITI), literally, ‘the status of the Pil̤l̤ai or prince’; supposed to be an officers’ cadre composed mainly of the junior members of the royal family.<BR> (IE 8-3), also called Khādya(kū*)ṭapākika, Sāndhivigrahika, Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारामात्याधिकरण
Kumārāmāty-ādhikaraṇa (BL), office of the Kumār-āmātya<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारपादीयआमात्य
Kumārapādīy-āmātya (BL), an Amātya serving a Kumāra or enjoying the status of a Kumāra. Cf. Kumār-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारास्य
kumār-āsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारवर्ग
Kumāra-varga (SITI), subordinate chieftains who considered themselves as sons of the king or members of the royal family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारवृत्ति
kumāra-vṛtti, cf. Tamil pil̤l̤ai-vari (SITI), tax for the upkeep of the order of Pil̤l̤ais or Kumāras (princes). Kumāra-vṛtti occurs^1 in the inscriptions of the Western Cālukyas of Kalyāṇa.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=166" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारीसाहस
kumārī-sāhasa (IE 8-5; EI 3, 25; CII 4), ‘offence against an unmarried girl’; fine for abducting an unmarried girl; same as kumārīsāhasa-doṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हुमारीसाहसदोष
humārīsāhasa-doṣa (EI 32), fine for abducting an unmarried girl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुम्भ|कुंभ|कुम्भं|कुंभः|कुम्भः
kumbha (EI 5), the pinnacle of a temple; same as kalaśa. See also kumbhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुम्बाभिषेक
kumbh-ābhiṣeka (SII 3), same as Tamil tiru-kkalaśa-muḍittal (SITI), the consecration ceremony of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुम्भक|कुंभक|कुंभकः|कुम्भकः
kumbhaka (LL), the base of a pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमोस
kumosa (Chamba), forced labour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुंवर
Kuṃvara (BL), regional modification of Kumāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणम्
kāṇam (EI 16), name of a gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुञ्चि|कुंचि|कुंचिः|कुञ्चिः
kuñci (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity usually regarded as equal to eight handfuls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुण्ड|कुंड|कुंडं|कुण्डं|कुंडः|कुण्डः
kuṇḍa (EI 23), a spring.<BR> (EI 31), a pond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूण्डि
kūṇḍi (EI 23), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुण्डिका|कुंडिका
kuṇḍikā (LP), a reservoir of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुञ्जर|कुंजर|कुंजरः|कुञ्जरः
kuñjara (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुङ्कुमवस्त्र
kuṅkuma-vastra (ASLV), ‘saffron-coloured cloth’; sometimes the privilege to wear it was granted to particular persons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुन्नु
kunnu (Chamba), also called kunu; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुन्त|कुंत|कुंतः|कुन्तः
kunta (Chamba), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुण्ट
kuṇṭa (EI 21), a land measure; cf. guṇṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुन्तल|कुंतल|कुंतलः|कुन्तलः
kuntala (EI 24), ‘one who wields the spear’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुनु
kunu (Chamba), also called kunnu; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूप|कूपः
kūpa (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), an ordinary well; cf. vāpī which is a well with a flight of stairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूपदर्शक
Kūpadarśaka (EI 24), a water-diviner; an inspector of wells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुप्यगृह
kupya-gṛha (HRS), a store-house for forest produce as indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूर|कूरं|कूरः
kūra, cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-vāsa (IE 8-5); explained as ‘boiled rice’; but probably ‘unboiled rice’. The villagers were obliged to supply it to the touring officers of the king. See vodā, siddh-ānna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुरङ्गमद
kuraṅga-mada (IA 18), musk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूर्म|कूर्मः|कूर्म्म|कूर्म्मः
kūrma (EI 14), see madhya-kūrma, ‘a plot of land elevated in the middle.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=167" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कु|कुः
kur̤r̤am (IE 8-4), Tamil; a district or its subdivision; sometimes the same as nāḍu, but sometimes only the part of a nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुरुविन्द|कुरुविंद|कुरुविंदं|कुरुविन्दं|कुरुविंदः|कुरुविन्दः
kuruvinda, cf. kur̤uvindam (SII 2), an inferior ruby.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुश|कुशं|कुशः
kuśa, cf. kuśa-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil, tax on the potters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशल|कुशलं|कुशलः
kuśala (IA 17), used in the sense of puṇya, religious merit; cf. kuśala-mūla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशलमूल
kuśala-mūla (CII 2-1; ML), ‘the root of merit’; used to indicate ‘a pious deed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशलिन्
Kuśalin (CII 3; SII 3; IA 9), ‘being in good health’, used in the preamble of charters to indicate the genuineness and validity of the grant made by the donors when they were in a healthy state of body and mind; epithet of a donor of copper-plate grants to indicate that the charters were issued when the donor was not subject to any disease like madness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुसूत्र
kusūtra, (LP), wrong.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूट|कूटः
Kūṭa (IA 7), cf. Rāṣṭrakūṭa, Deśakūṭa, Grāmakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटक|कूटकं|कूटकः
Kūṭaka (EI 5), probably, headman of the cultivators; same as Grāmakūṭaka.<BR> (IE 8-5; EI 4, 26), tax for the maintenance of the Kūṭaka; see pravaṇikara-kūṭaka-prabhṛti-samast-ādāya (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 101).<BR> (CII 4), a measure of capacity.<BR> (EI 2), a load or measure of salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटकोलस
Kūṭakolasa (IE 8-3; EI 29), known from the Bhauma-Kara records of Orissa; official designation of uncertain import; cf. Kūṭa or Kūṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुताम्र
ku-tāmra (IA 30), a fraudulent charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटशासन
kūṭa-śāsana (EI 7; IA 30; BL), a forged charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूटायुक्त
Kūṭāyukta (EI 22), official designation; probably Kūṭa (Kūṭaka) and Āyukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटी
kuṭī (IE 8-8), a factory; cf. nīla-kuṭī.<BR> (LL), a Buddhist temple; an abbreviation of gandhakuṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटिल|कुटिलं
Kuṭila, cf. Siddhamātṛkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्
Kuṭum (EI 33; LP), abbreviation of Kuṭumbika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्ब|कुटुंब|कुटुंबं|कुटुम्बः
kuṭumba (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बक्षेत्र
kuṭumba-kṣetra (CII 4), an ancestral field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बवृत्ति
kuṭumba-vṛtti, cf. Kannaḍa kuttumbitti (EI 18), gift of land for the maintenance of the donee's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बयात्रा
kuṭumba-yātrā (EI 12; BL), name of a religious ceremony; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-169" target="_blank">Page-169+ 39</a>] a procession of the royal family to the temple of the family deity on the occasion of the king's coronation or a marriage in the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=168" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बिन्|कुटुंबिन्
Kuṭumbin (EI 12, 17, 23; SII 1), a cultivator; an agriculturist householder; a householder or ryot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुटुम्बिनी|कुटुंबिनी
kuṭumbinī (EI 19; CII 2-1; ML), originally, ‘the wife of a householder’; later, ‘wife’ in general (cf. Sel. Ins., p. 164).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुत्तुम्बित्ति
kuttumbitti, Kannaḍa; cf. grant of certain towns and kuttum-bittis as aṅuga-jīvita or fief (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, pp. 81-83); mentioned along with bhatta-grāma (Sanskrit bhakta-grāma), ‘provision village’ (ibid., Vol. XVIII, p. 193); probably, Sanskrit kuṭumba-vṛtti, grant made for the maintenance of the donee's family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुवर|कुवरः
Kuvara (BL), regional modification of Kumāra. Cf. Kuṃvar (Kuñar), Kunwar, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लब्धि|लब्धिः
labdhi, ‘nine’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 345).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाभ|लाभः
lābha (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाभारिका
lābhārikā, lābhālikā (Chamba), Sanskritised form of the land measure called lāhaḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्
lag, cf. lagitvā (EI 9), ‘commencing from, beginning with’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाग
lāga (EI 11), a cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लगडा
lagaḍā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309), a load; a bar of metal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लगण|लगणः
lagaṇa (Chamba), fines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लागसम्बन्ध
lāga-sambandha, lāga-bhāga (LP), ‘any connection.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्गावयित्वा
laggāvayitvā (IE 8-5), ‘having planted’; cf. Bengali lāgāiyā. See JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 202.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लागिद्रम्माः
lāgi-drammāḥ (LP), ‘expenses incurred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्न|लग्नं|लग्नः
lagna (IA 17; SII 1), an astronomical term; the rising of a sign of the zodiac or its passing the meridian. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, pp. 16 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लग्नदेवी
lagna-devī (IA 30), Jain; a stone-cow.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाहडि
lāhaḍi, lāhaḍī (Chamba), a land measure. See lābhā-rikā, lābhālikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लकार
lakāra (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लकटा
lakaṭā (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain. Cf. ārdraka-lakaṭā, probably, dried ginger stick or undried fire-wood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=169" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षदान
lakṣa-dāna (EI 12), name of a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षहोम|लक्षहोमः
lakṣa-homa (SII 11-1), name of a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षण|लक्षणं|लक्षणः
lakṣaṇa (IA 18), the sexual parts; the male organ; cf. nirlakṣitavya, to be castrated.<BR> (CII 1), branding.<BR> (SII 3; SITI), a document or deed; an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लक्षणाध्यक्ष
Lakṣaṇ-ādhyakṣa (HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, the superintendent of the mint, or royal dues received by the superintendent of the mint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाकुल
Lākula, also called Lākuleśvara (EI 15), a Śaiva sect following Lakulīśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लकुलेश्वरागम
Lakuleśvar-āgama (CITD), a form of Śaivism associated with Lakulīśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लालखण्डेयका
Lāl̤a-khaṇḍeya-kār̤ar-adhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; ‘superintendent of the revenue from Lāṭa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लम्बापटह
lambā-paṭaha (EI 12), a kind of drum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाञ्छन|लांछन|लांछनं|लाञ्छनं|लाञ्छनः
lāñchana (EI 28), an emblem. Cf. cihna.<BR> (EI 9), the [royal] emblem; cf. Tamil lāñjanai-pper̤u, lāñjinai-pper̤u, ilāñjai-pper̤u (SITI), the royal seal.<BR> (CII 3, etc.), a crest as distinguished from dhvaja or a banner. Cf. cihna.<BR> (HA), the distinguishing mark or symbol of a Jina image, which helps one to identify the different Jinas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाञ्छित|लांछित
lāñchita (EI 29), ‘registered with a seal (lāñchana)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लाङ्गडि
lāṅgaḍi (LP), a cart or carriage; cf. uchālaka-bhṛta-lāṅgaḍi, ‘a cartful of household furniture’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
laṅkā, islet in a river (Kākatīyasaṃcika, No. 31).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=558" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लङ्क
Laṅka (EI 19), a carpenter; cf. Leṅka, Leṅkā, Bud̤hāleṅkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लपित|लपितं
lapita (CII 1), used in the sense of ukta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लसं|लस
la-saṃ (IA 18), abbreviation of lakṣmaṇasena-saṃvatsara, ‘the era of Lakṣmaṇasena’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लष्टि
laṣṭi (CII 4), same as Sanskrit yaṣṭi; a memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लत्तलूरपुरपरमेश्वर
Lattalūrapura-parameśvara (IE 8-2), a typical title of the Rāṣṭrakūṭas claiming the city of Lattalūra to have been their original home. Similar titles are quite common in the early medieval records especially of the Kannaḍa-speaking area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लौकि
lauki˚, laukika˚ (IA 18), abbreviation of laukika-gaṇanayā. Laukika-saṃvatsara is a year of the Laukika era.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लवलिका
lavalikā (LP), loquacity; cf. Gujarātī lavlav or lavāro.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लवण|लवणं|लवणः
lavaṇa, cf. a-lavaṇa-khātaka (IE 8-5); salt [the production of which was the monopoly of the king or landlord]. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-171" target="_blank">Page-171+ 40</a>]<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’; also ‘cutting [of plants]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=170" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लवणाकर|लवणाकरः
lavaṇ-ākara (EI 24, EI 30), a salt pit or mine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लयन|लयनं
layana (LL, EI 22), Prakrit leṇa; an excavated cave; a cave; the residence of monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेख|लेखः
lekha (LP), official letter; cf. likhita, a private letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखाधिकारिन्
Lekh-ādhikārin (HD), secretary. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, III. 206.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखहार|लेखहारः
Lekhahāra, Lekhahāraka (EI 21; HD), the carrier of letters (see Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 319).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखक|लेखकः
Lekhaka (CII 3, etc.), a writer; a technical term for one who wrote a record [on copper plates, stone slabs, etc., in order to facilitate its correct engraving by an artisan], as opposed to the composer of the document (see also likhita).<BR> (IE 8-3; EI 28, 30; LL; HD), a writer, scribe or clerk (see Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XVI, pp. 582 and 605; Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 26-28; Śukranītisāra, II. 120).<BR> (LP), a record or document; mistake for lekhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखनाध्यक्ष
Lekhan-ādhyakṣa (CII 3), the superintendent of the writing of documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखयितृ
Lekhayitṛ (EI 12), one who is responsible for getting a grant recorded; mentioned together with Śāsayitṛ; cf. Ājñapti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेखित|लेखितं
Lekhita, Lekhitṛ (EI 24), same as Lekhaka; a writer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेण्क
Lěṅka (EI 3; SII 11-1), Leṅkā (EI 28), a servant; a Śūdra servant; a writer, according to some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लेप्यकार
Lepyakāra, model-maker (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिखित|लिखितं|लिखितः
likhita (CII 3, 4, etc.), ‘written’; a technical term indicating the manual drafting or writing of a record, as opposed to the composition and engraving of it; see also lekhaka.<BR> (LP), a private letter; cf. lekha, an official letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिङ्ग|लिंग|लिंगं|लिङ्गं
liṅga (BL; SII 1; CII 3, etc.), same as śiva-liṅga; the phallic emblem^1 of Śiva; the emblem connected with the worship of Śiva; generally named after the founder with the suffix īśvara.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिङ्गोरण
liṅgoraṇa (IA 11), conjecturally translated as ‘the festival of rams [to be sacrificed] to the liṅgas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिपि|लिपिः
lipi (SII 3), a letter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिपिकर|लिपिकरः
Lipikara (IE 8-3; EI 3; HD), a scribe or writer. See CII, Vol. I, p. 176; Pāṇini, III. 2. 21.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लिपिकृत्कुल
Lipikṛt-kula (EI 33), the community of scribes; the Kāyastha community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=171" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोभविजयिन्
Lobha-vijayin (CII 4), ‘an avaricious conqueror’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोचन|लोचनं
locana (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोह|लोहं|लोहः
loha, cf. so-loha-lavaṇ-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with mines of metals and salt pits [the right of which normally belonged to the king]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहचर्मकार
Loha-carma-kāra (EI 24), workers in metal and leather.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहडिया
lohaḍiyā, name of a coin equal to 20 pāvīsās and 100 cowrie-shells; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 238.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहार
Lohāra (EI 4; BL), modification of Lohakāra; a black-smith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहवाणिज
Loha-vāṇija (LL) an iron-monger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहिककारुक
Lohika-kāruka (LL), a worker in metal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहित|लोहितं|लोहितः
Lohita (ML), a blood relation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहितक|लोहितकं|लोहितकः
lohitaka, weight equal to 3 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोक|लोकः
loka (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’; sometimes also ‘three’; rarely used to indicate ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोकपाल|लोकपालः
Lokapāla (CII 3, etc.), a guardian of one of the quarters of the world, originally conceived as four in number and later as eight.<BR> (EI 15), cf. the king called ‘the fifth Lokapāla’, the four Lokapālas (guardians of the four quarters) being originally Yama of the south, Varuṇa of the west, Kubera of the north and Vāsava of the east. In the same sense, the king was also called madhyama-loka-pāla, though madhyama-loka may also mean ‘the earth’ standing midway between the heavens and the netherworld. See Suc. Sāt., pp. 196, 202; Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 93. Cf. Pañcama-lokapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः
Ma (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Maṅgala-vāra, Tuesday.<BR> (PJS), abbreviation of Mahattama, Mantrin, Mahetā (meaning ‘a clerk’ or ‘a teacher’ in Gujarātī), etc. (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मा
mā (IE 8-6; SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a land measure equal to one-twentieth of a veli; also the name of a weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माड|माडः
māḍa (IE 8-8; EI 7), Telugu; same as Od̤iyā mād̤ha or mād̤hā and Tamil māḍai; a coin of gold or silver; 40 ratis in weight; cf. biruda-māḍa, malla-māḍa, mallanandi-māḍa, surabhi-māḍa, gaṇḍa-māḍa, kulottuṅga-māḍa [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-173" target="_blank">Page-173+ 40</a>] (EI 29), gandhavāraṇamāḍa (or gandhahasti-māḍa), cāmara-māḍa, uttama-gaṇḍamāḍa, padmanidhi-malla-māḍa, rājarāja-māḍa, rājendracol̤̣a-māḍa, etc. The gaṇḍa-māḍa is sometimes called kārṣāpaṇa, niṣka and gaṇḍaniṣka and is also characterised in a few cases with the epithet ‘small’. See māḍai, māḍha. Note names like kulottuṅga-māḍa, a coin issued by the Col̤̣a king Kulottuṅga. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 43.<BR> (CITD), Telugu; half a pagoda; half of a dīnār or the tenth of a paṇa (cf. badi-māḍuvulu); half or 50 per cent of revenue, etc.; a weight of gold; money in general. Four māḍas are equal to one carṣam (karṣa ?).<BR> (IE 8-5), probably, payment of 50 per cent; see māḍalu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=172" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडबडिपातुक
māḍa-baḍi-pātuka (CITD), Telugu; an unknown coin with a fraction of the value of a māḍa. Baḍi means ‘petty’ and pātika ‘a quarter’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मदहस्तिपादरक्षापालक
Madahastipādarakṣā-pālaka (IA 30), explained as ‘the captain of the guards of elephants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडै
māḍai (IE 8-8; EI 7), Tamil; same as māḍha, māḍhā and māḍa; cf. rājarājan̤-māḍai, madhurāntakan̤-māḍai, bhujabala-māḍai (EI 7), etc.; often a gold coin (SII 12). Tamil māḍai is the same as māṣā derived from Sanskrit māṣaka.<BR> (SITI), name of a gold coin; a half pagoda; cf. nellūr-māḍai (SITI), a coin current in olden days and issued from Nellore; also known as nellūr-ppudu-māḍai; also cf. gaṇḍagopālan̤-māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडलु
māḍalu (IE 8-5; EI 33), same as māḍa, a levy; probably, ‘payment of 50 per cent’; cf. Kannaḍa pannasa or pannāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मडम्ब
maḍamba (EI 24), a territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मदनतिथि
Madana-tithi (IA 17), Caitra ba-di 13.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडास्यात
māḍāsyāta (CII 3), usually taken to be a word of uncertain import, but may really be the name of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मद्दल
maddala (SII 3), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माढ
māḍha, māḍhā (IE 8-8; EI 28, 29, 30, 33), Od̤iyā; a silver coin; also a gold coin; 40 ratis in weight; same as māḍa or māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्य|मध्यं|मध्यः
madhya (CII 1), middle course.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यदिवस
madhya-divasa (ML), mid-day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यकूर्म
madhya-kūrma (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV p. 98), probably, a plot of land elevated in the middle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यम|मध्यमं|मध्यमः
madhyama (CII 1), a class between the upper and the lower.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=173" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यमलोकपाल
Madhyamalokapāla, epithet of kings; cf. Lokapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मध्यस्थ|मध्यस्थः
madhyastha (EI 8, 25; SII 2; ASLV; SITI), a neutral person, generally the village headman; a mediator or arbitrator; secretary of the village assembly (SII 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मद्यपान
madya-pāna (SII 3), intoxicating drinks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मद्यवहनक
madya-vahanaka (IE 8-8), a carrier of wine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मग|मगः
Maga (EI 9; BL), the same as Śākadvīpīya; a community of Brāhmaṇas; name of the members of the Persian priestly community (Magi) settled in India and absorbed in the Brāhmaṇa class.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मागाणि
māgāṇi (ASLV), an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मागाणिस्थान
māgāṇi-sthāna (EI 13), epithet of a locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महा
Mahā (PJS), abbreviation of Mahājana (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR> Cf. Mahā-Mūla (i. e. the elder Mūla) distinguished from Kṣudra-Mūla (i. e. the younger Mūla); also Mahā-Dharmagiri and Kṣudra-Dharmagiri, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलाधिकरणिक
Mahābalādhikaraṇika (IE 8-3), superintendent of the office of the Mahābalādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलाधिकृत
Mahābalādhikṛta (HD), ‘the great commander’; designation of a military officer who was, in one case, originally a Mantrin (IE 8-3); see Balādhikṛta and Mahābalādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलाध्यक्ष
Mahābalādhyakṣa (CII 3), military title. See Balādhyakṣa and Mahābalādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाबलकोष्ठिक
Mahābalakoṣṭhika (IE 8-3), treasurer of the military department. Cf. raṇabhāṇḍāgār-ādhikaraṇa (Raychaudhuri, PHAI, 1950, p. 563).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभाण्डागार
mahābhāṇḍāgāra (EI 12), treasury; cf. bhāṇḍāgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभाण्डागारिक
Mahābhāṇḍāgārika (IE 8-2; HD) treasurer; one of the designations often included in the pañca-mahāśabda as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 39; Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142. Cf. Bhāṇḍāgārika.<BR> (CII 4), explained as ‘the Chancellor of the Exchequer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभाण्डागारिन्
Mahābhāṇḍāgārin (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa Hiriyabhaṇḍāgārin; sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभारतवृत्ति
Mahābhārata-vṛtti (SITI), land endowed to persons for expounding the Mahābhārata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोगपति
Mahābhogapati (EI 26), official designation; probably, the superintendent of rent-free holdings; cf. Mahābhogika, Bhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोगिक
Mahābhogika (EI 26; HD), a big Jāgīrdār; cf. Ep. Ind., [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-175" target="_blank">Page-175+ 40</a>] Vol. XII, p. 9; also cf. Bhogika and Mahābhogapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=174" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोज
Mahābhoja (IE 8-2; EI 7, 22, 28; LL), a big Jāgīrdār; title of a feudatory ruler; see Bhojaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभोजी
Mahābhojī (LL), wife of a Mahābhoja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभूत|महाभूतं|महाभूतः
mahābhūta (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभूतघटदान
mahābhūtaghaṭa-dāna (SITI), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाभूतक
mahābhūtaka (EI 14), name of a mahādāna; same as mahābhūtaghaṭa-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाचतुर्दशीपर्वन्
mahācaturdaśī-parvan (EI 9), 14th tithi of the bright half of a month.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाचैत्य
mahācaitya (LL), a great caitya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादाह
mahādāha (SITI), name of a hell which one is supposed to pass through after death on the way to the other world.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादान|महादानं
mahādāna (EI 7, 16; CII 4); a great gift, 16 of which are enumerated in the Purāṇas (see Hist. Dharm., Vol. II, pp. 869-70; Suc. Sāt. L. Dec., pp. 50f.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानाक्षपटलाधिकृत
Mahādān-ākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (EI 31), officer in charge of the accounts section of the gift department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानपति
Mahādānapati (EI 23; ML; HD), ‘the great gift-lord’, designation of one who gives a gift. Cf. CII, Vol. II, Pt. i., p. 28. Cf. Dānapati (EI 28), dedicator of an image of a god on the fulfilment of a desire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानपत्नी
Mahādānapatnī (EI 20), feminine form of Mahādānapati; a female bestower of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादण्डनायक
Mahādaṇḍanāyaka (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL.; HD); commander of forces; also called Khādya(kū*) ṭapākika, Sān-dhivigrahika, Kumārāmātya, etc., additionally; one of the designations sometimes included in the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case of Maitraka Dhruvasena I (Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, p. 7; Ind. Ant., Vol. IV, p. 105). The five mahāśabdas applied to Dhruvasena are Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahā-kārtākṛtika and Mahārāja. See Daṇḍanāyaka, Sarvadaṇḍa-nāyaka, Mahāsarvadaṇḍanāyaka, Daṇḍapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादानिक
Mahādānika (CII 4), head of the department of charity; officer in charge of donations; sometimes^1 explained as ‘the officer superintending the performance of the mahādāna ceremonies’ (HD). See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91. Cf. Dharmādhyakṣa.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादौःसाधसाधनिक
Mahādauḥsādhasādhanika (HD), cf. Dauḥsādhasādhanika. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादेव|महादेवः
mahādeva (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=175" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादेवी
Mahādevī (IE 8-2; EI 7; CII 3, 4; HD), a queen; often wrongly taken as the first wife of a king or his chief queen (SITI); a title of the wives originally of paramount sovereigns and later also of feudatory rulers; cf. Devī, Agra-mahādevī, Mahāmahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाधर्माधिकरणिक
Mahādharmādhikaraṇika (CII 4), explained as the chief justice (HD), Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309. See Dharmādhikara-ṇika and Mahādharmādhyakṣa, head of the department of religious; affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाधर्माध्यक्ष
Mahādharm-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3; EI 12, 21, 26, 33; HD), explained as ‘the chief judge’; but really ‘officer in charge of charities, etc.’; cf. Dharmādhyakṣa and Mahādharmādhikaraṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाधिराज
Mahādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 12), royal title; cf. Adhirāja; also cf. Dharmamahādhirāja (EI 12).<BR> (CII 3), a feudatory title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाध्यक्ष
Mahādhyakṣa (EI 12; CII 4), ‘the chief superintendent’; cf. Adhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादीक्षित
Mahādīkṣita (EI 4), cf. Dīkṣita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादोष
mahā-doṣa, cf. mahādoṣa-vivarjita (EI 23) as an epithet of the gift village; probably, fines for great crimes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाद्वादशक
mahā-dvādaśaka (IE 8-4), ‘the great twelve’; suffixed to the name of a district probably consisting of twelve Parganās or sub-districts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाद्वादशी
mahā-dvādaśī (EI 9; IA 26), also called pāpanāśinī; name of a tithi; eight kinds of the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाद्वाराधिपति
Mahādvār-ādhipati (BL), possibly the same as ‘the lord (i. e. the guard) of the Dvāra (a pass)’ of the Rājataraṅgiṇī; mentioned along with the Mahāsainyapati and Mahāpratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागजपति
Mahāgajapati (EI 30), ‘the great lord of elephants’; cf. Gajapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागणस्थ
Mahāgaṇastha (IE 8-3; EI 26; HD), probably, the chairman of a guild or superintendent of guilds; cf. Gaṇastha and Gaṇattār. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 160.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागन्धकूटी
mahā-gandhakūṭī (LL), a Buddhist temple; cf. gandhakuṭī and kūṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महागोवल्लभ
Mahāgovallabha (EI 24), the superintendent of cattle; see Govallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाग्रहार
mahāgrahāra (SII 11-1), see agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाग्राम|महाग्रामः
mahāgrāma (IE 8-4), a small territorial unit; a group of villages; cf. grām-āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=176" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाग्रामिक
Mahāgrāmika (IE 8-3), ruler of a mahāgrāma (subdivision of a district or a group of villages).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाजन|महाजनः
Mahājana (SITI; ASLV), Brāhmaṇa residents of the entire village; all the members of the village assembly; general body of the sabhā or village assembly.<BR> (IE 8-3), a member of village council.<BR> (EI 8), a merchant.<BR> (LP), generally, the merchants, magnates, grandees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाजनसभा
mahājana-sabhā (IE-3), village council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाजय
mahājaya, mahājayā (EI 7; IA 26), name of a tithi; same as su-di 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकरण
mahākaraṇa, cf. sa-mañca-mahākaraṇa (IE 8-5), an expression of doubtful import; probably, ‘official records’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकरणाध्यक्ष
Mahākaraṇādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), head of the department of records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकरणिक
Mahākaraṇika (CII 4; HD), the chief secretary; the chief scribe. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309. Cf. Karaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकर्तक
Mahākartaka (LL), epithet of an artisan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकार्ताकृतिक
Mahākārtākṛtika (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3; HD), official designation of uncertain import; probably, a reporter who informed the king about the progress of big undertakings; sometimes explained as ‘the royal agent or judge’; one of the designations sometimes included in the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case of Maitraka Dhruvasena I. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306. See Kārtākṛtika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकार्त्तिकी|महाकार्तिकी
Mahākārttikī (EI 11; CII 4), full-moon day of the month of Kārttika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकटुक
Mahākaṭuka (IE 8-3), official designation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकवि|महाकविः
Mahākavi (CII 4), ‘great poet’; title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकविचक्रवर्तिन्
Mahākavicakravartin (EI 30; BL), title of a poet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाखड्गधर
Mahākhaḍgadhara (EI 30), official designation. See Khaḍgadhara, Khaḍgagrāha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाखलरक्षक
Mahākhalarakṣaka (LP), superintendent of the king's threshing floors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाखेट
mah-ākheṭa (EI 5), a great hunting expedition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकोष्ठागारिन्
Mahākoṣṭhāgārin (SII 2), ‘great treasurer’; cf. Koṣṭhāgārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकोट्टपाल
Mahākoṭṭapāla (CII 4), chief guardian of a fort or^1 the forts; cf. Koṭṭapāla.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=177" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्ष|महाक्षः
Mahākṣa (EI 33), abbreviation of Mahākṣpaṭalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षनि
mahākṣa-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of mahākṣapaṭalika-nirīkṣita, ‘examined by the Mahākṣapaṭalika’; ni may not be an abbreviation of nibaddha (registered) in this case since mahākṣa-ni is often used along with several^1 other expressions of the kind. See ni.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपालकरण
mahākṣapāla-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the depository of legal documents’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलाधिकरणाधिकृत
Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta (BL) superintendent of the office of the akṣapaṭala or mahākṣpaṭala department; sometimes regarded as the same as Mahākṣpaṭalika (HD). Cf. Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलाधिकृत
Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (BL), same as Mahākṣapaṭalādhi-karaṇ-ādhikṛta or Mahākṣapaṭalādhyakṣa; also called Mahā-kṣapāla (cf. karaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलाध्यक्ष
Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa (BL), see Akṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलिक
Mahākṣapaṭalika (IE 8-3; CII 3; EI 30; BL; HD), record-keeper and accountant; same as Mahākṣapaṭal-ādhyakṣa; see Akṣapaṭalika, sometimes explained as ‘the chief keeper of records’ (CII 4), Cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 120.<BR> (IE 8-3), mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षपटलिन्
Mahākṣapaṭalin (EI 33), same as Mahākṣapaṭalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाक्षत्रप|महाक्षत्रपः
Mahākṣatrapa (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 16, 27; CII 4; BL; ML; HD), the great Satrap or provincial governor; feudatory title of foreign origin; originally, title of a provincial governor; later the Śakas of Western India continued to use it even when they were practically independent. Cf. CII, Vol. II, p. 48. See Kṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकुलपति
Mahākulapati (EI 29), epithet of a priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकुमार|महाकुमारः
Mahākumāra (CII 4), title of a prince or the crown-prince.<BR> (IE 8-2; EI 28; BL), title of certain rulers; title of some semi-independent Paramāra rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाकुमारामात्य
Mahākumārāmātya (EI 29; CII 3; HD), see Kumārāmātya. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महालया
mahālayā (EI 33), name of a tithi; pūrṇimānta Āśvina-badi 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महले
Mahale, Mahaleka (IA 9), Ceylonese; official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महल्लक|महल्लकः
Mahallaka (IE 8-5; EI 25), probably, a member of the Pañcāyat; explained as ‘city elders’; cf. yat … nagara-mahallakāvicārya vadante, etc. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-179" target="_blank">Page-179+ 40</a>]<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20); also called Mahallāka, Mahallika.<BR> (CII 4), same as Mahattara.<BR> (EI 2; CII 1), an old man. In Od̤iyā, it means a guard of the royal harem.<BR> (CII 1), big, vast.<BR> (EI 23), a landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=178" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महं|मह|महः
Mahaṃ (BL), abbreviation of Mahattama.<BR> (LP), abbreviation of Mahantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मह|महं|महः
Maha, Mahaṃ (IA 18), abbreviations of Mahattara or Mahattama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहादेवी
Mahāmahādevī (BL), designation of a queen or the chief queen; cf. Mahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहन्तक
Mahāmahantaka (EI 7; CII 4; HD), same as Mahā-mahattaka. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहत्तक
Mahāmahattaka (EI 25, 33; CII 4; HD; BL), head of a group of villages or of the village council; chief among the village headmen; same as Mahāmahattara, Mahāmahattama. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 362. See Mahattaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहत्तम
Mahāmahattama (BL), same as Mahāmahattaka, Mahā-mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहत्तर
Mahāmahattara (IE 8-3; EI 26, 29; BL), mentioned along with the Mahattara; probably, the chairman of the council of Mahattaras; same as Mahāmahattaka, Mahāmahattama; see Mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहावारुणी
mahāmahāvāruṇī (EI 4), name of a tithi; same as vāruṇī and mahā-vāruṇī; amānta Caitra-badi 13 with Śatabhiṣā-nakṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहिषी
Mahāmahiṣī (IE 8-2), cf. Piriya-arasi (IE 8-2), Kannaḍa; title of a chief queen; see Mahiṣī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामहोपाध्याय|महामहोपाध्यायः
Mahāmahopādhyāya, title of certain scholars like Jīvadeva of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महमै
mahamai (EI 17), Tamil magamai; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामख
mahāmakha (EI 25), a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलचक्रवर्तिन्
Mahāmaṇḍala-cakravartin (EI 9), royal title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलाचार्य
Mahāmaṇḍal-ācārya (EI 26), title of a Buddhist teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलाधिपति
Mahāmaṇḍal-ādhipati (EI 29), same as Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलनाथ
Mahāmaṇḍala-nātha (HD), same as Mahāmaṇḍleśvara. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 227.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलेश्वर
Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 4; HD; BL; SITI; CITD), according to the lexicons, a sovereign ruler [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-180" target="_blank">Page-180+ 40</a>] who is the lord of 40 yojanas of land and a lakh of villages; but, in inscriptions^1, generally, the governor of a district or province; title of a feudatory ruler or governor (see Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354); see Maṇḍaleśvara essentially meaning ‘the ruler of a maṇḍala or district’; also called Mahāmaṇḍalika, etc., cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvar-ādhipati. The status of a Mahāmaṇḍal-eśvara seems to have been superior to that of a Maṇḍaleśvara, while Mahāmaṇḍaleśvarādhipati apparently enjoyed a still higher rank.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=179" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलेश्वराधिपति
Mahāmaṇḍaleśvar-ādhipati (IE 8-2; EI 23), title of a feudatory higher in rank than a Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara (cf. Mahā-sāmantādhipati); a feudatory who had some subordinate chiefs under him; cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara, Maṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलिक
Mahāmaṇḍalika (IE 8-3), feudatory title; see Mahā-maṇḍalīka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डलीक
Mahāmaṇḍalīka (HD), same as Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 35. See Mahāmaṇḍalika, Mahāmaṇḍale-śvar-ādhipati, Māṇḍalika etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामण्डप
mahāmaṇḍapa (SITI), a large pillared hall next to the ardha-maṇḍapa in a temple; also called mukha-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामन्त्रिन्|महामंत्रिन्
Mahāmantrin (EI 12, 30; CII 4; IA 19; BL; HD), ‘the chief minister or counsellor’. See Mantrin. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामनुष्य
Mahāmanuṣya (IE 8-3), probably, a landlord; mentioned in the list of a king's subordinates. cf. Mahājana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्र|महामात्रः
Mahāmātra (IE 8-3), cf. Prakrit Mahāmāta (EI 3); a high executive officer employed in various capacities; cf. Nagara-vyavahārika-mahāmātra, Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra, Dharma-mahāmātra, etc.; adopted in Greek as Mamātrai. See CII, Vol. I, p. 92, etc.; Arthaśāstra, I. 12, V. 1; etc.; Kāmasūtra, V. 5. 17. 33 and 35. The word Mahāmātra in Manu, IX. 259, is explained by Medhātithi as ‘the Mantrin, Purohita and others’ and by Kullūka as meaning ‘the professional tamers of elephants’. (SITI) explained as ‘a senior minister.’ See Mātra in a similar sense.<BR> Cf. Antaḥpura-mahāmātra in the Masulipatnam plates of Amma II (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR> (EI 28; CII 4), ‘an elephant-driver’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्रगण
Mahāmātra-gaṇa (CII 4), corporation of elephant-drivers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्रनगरव्यवहारिक
Mahāmātra-nagaravyavahārika (CII 1), an executive officer who is the judge or administrator of a city.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=180" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामातृका
mahāmātṛkā, ‘mother's mother’; used side by side with āryikā, ‘father's mother’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 225).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्य|महामात्यः
Mahāmātya (IE 8-3; EI 25; CII 4; BL), the chief minister or executive officer; the prime minister or a viceroy (HD); see Amātya; sometimes also called a Mahāpradhāna additionally. Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 122; Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 242.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामात्यवर
Mahāmātya-vara (EI 30), chief minister; cf. Amātya and Mahāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामेरुश्रीकीर्तिस्तम्भ
mahāmeru-śrī-kīrtistambha (BL), name of Mahārāṇā Kumbhā's tower at Chitor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामुद्राधिकृत
Mahāmudr-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 12, 14, 15; HD), the keeper of the royal seal; officer in charge of the royal seal; cf. Mahāmudr-āmātya. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामुद्रामात्य
Mahāmudr-āmātya (IA 11), same as Mahāmudr-ādhikṛta; cf. Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महामुरज
mahā-muraja (ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महान
Mahāna (Chamba), a writer; possibly from Sanskrit Mahantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानाड्प्रभु
Mahānāḍ-prabhu (ASLV), the Paṭṭanasvāmin (q. v.) of the rural areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानाडु
mahā-nāḍu (SITI), general assembly of the mercantile community of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानगर
mahā-nagara (SITI), merchants' guild of a city; cf. nagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महणलोक
mahaṇaloka, possibly the same as Sanskrit mahalloka=mahājana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानसाध्यक्ष
Mahānas-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa Bhānasa-věrgaḍě (EI 5); superintendent of the royal kitchen; sometimes also called Mahāsāmantādhipati, Mahāpradhāna, Accupannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka, etc., additionally; cf. Mahānasika, Sūpakārapati, Khādya-(kū*)ṭapākika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानसिक
Mahānasika, ‘the kitchen-officer’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 156); cf. Mahanas-ādhyakaṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानवमीअमावास्या
mahānavamī-amāvāsyā (EI 5; IA 18), Kannaḍa name for the new-moon of Bhādrapada; new-moon preceding the mahānavamī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानाविक
Mahānāvika (EI 27), the captain of a ship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानायक|महानायकः
Mahānāyaka (EI 4; BL), official designation probably indicating a class of feudatories; a subordinate title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानि
mahā-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of some such expression [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-182" target="_blank">Page-182+ 40</a>] as Mahāsāndhivigrahika-nirīkṣita, ‘approved by the Mahāsāndhivi-grahika’. See ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=181" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महानियोग
mahā-niyoga (SITI), king's order; royal command; an officer bearing the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महन्त्|महत्
Mahant (EI 4), variant spelling of Mahanta; the same as Mahantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महन्त|महंतः|महन्तः
Mahanta (EI 8; BL), head of a monastery; title of a pontiff.<BR> (ML), Prakrit form of Sanskrit mahat; ‘the great’; a title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महन्तक
Mahantaka (LP), an accountant; a clerk. It is a term of respect among the Baniyās of Gujarat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापादमूलिक
Mahāpādamūlika (IE 8-3), the king's chief personal attendant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापलुपति
Mahāpalupati (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 22), same as Mahā-pīlupati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापण
mahāpaṇa, cf. māppaṇam (SITI), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापञ्चकुलिक
Mahāpañcakulika (CII 4; HD), ‘head of the department of Pañcāyats’ or ‘the chairman of a Pañcāyat board’; see pañca-kula. Cf. JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापान्धाकुलिक
Mahāpāndhākulika (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 87), a mistake for or wrong reading of Mahāpāñcakulika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापाप|महापापं
mahā-pāpa (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापण्डित
Mahāpaṇḍita (EI 9; BL), title of a learned man, generally a learned Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापरमविश्वासिन्
Mahāparamaviśvāsin (IE 8-3; EI 5), probably, a private secretary or privy councillor; same as Rahasyādhikṛta, etc.; sometimes called Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally. See Paramaviśvāsin, Vaiśvāsika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापरिनिर्वाण
mahāparinirvāṇa (CII 4), the passing away of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापर्षद्
mahāparṣad (EI 32), an assembly or committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापार्षिक
mahāpārṣika (EI 32), used in the sense of ‘a member of the mahāparṣad’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापर्वन्
mahā-parvan (EI 12), auspicious time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापात्र|महापात्रः
Mahāpātra (IE 8-3; EI 19, 30), a minister; a minister higher in rank than the Pātra; cf. Pātra and Ekapātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापसायित
Mahāpasāyita (IE 8-3; EI 5, 27), probably from Sanskrit Prasādita, ‘favoured’, meaning a Jāgīrdār of a particular type; sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Antaḥpuravěrgaḍě, Daṇḍa-nāyaka, Sarvādhikārin, Mahāsāmanta, Senādibāhatta raniyogādhiṣṭhā-yaka, etc., additionally; cf. Pasāita, Pasāyita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=182" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापेरियप्रधान
Mahāpěriyapradhāna (EI 24), Sanskrit Mahābṛhatpradhāna; see Mahāpradhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापीलुपति
Mahāpīlupati (IE 8-3; EI 28), ‘the great superintendent of elephants’; chief of the elephant corps; the master of elephants; sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta, Pañcā-dhikaraṇ-oparika, Mahāpratīhāra, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 298. The word pīlu is the same as Perso-Arabic fīl. See Mahāpalupati and Pīlupati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रभु|महाप्रभुः
Mahāprabhu (EI 21, 32), sometimes used in respect of subordinate rulers; (HD), a governor; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 335. (SITI) ‘the great banker’; the senior merchant; the title by which the leader of the nānādeśi merchant community was designated.<BR> (IA 30), a village official; see Prabhu.<BR> (EI 19), explained as ‘the high sheriff’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रचण्ड
Mahāpracaṇḍa (EI 12), either a separate official designation or an epithet prefixed to the designation Nāyaka or Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रचण्डदण्डनायक
Mahāpracaṇḍa-daṇḍanāyaka (EI 20), official designation; cf. Mahāpracaṇḍa and Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रचण्डनायक
Mahāpracaṇḍa-nāyaka (EI 29), official designation; cf. Mahāpracaṇḍa-daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रधान
Mahāpradhāna (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 4; BL; HD), ‘the great minister’; ‘the chief minister or administrator’; sometimes also called Mahāsāmant-ādhipati, Antaḥpura-věrgaḍě (˚ādhyakṣa), Mahāpasāyita, Senāpati, Hěri (Mahā) sandhivigrahika, Maně-věrgaḍě, Kaḍitavěrgaḍě, Senādhipati, Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, Hěri-Lāl̤a-Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin, Bhānasa-věrgaḍě, Accupanāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka, Sarvādhikārin, Hěri (Mahā) bhāṇḍāgārin, Bāhattaraniyogādhipati, Paṭṭasāhaṇ-ādhiṣṭhāyaka, Senāpati, Daṇḍanāyaka, Mahāsāmanta, Senādibhāhattaraniyog-ādhiṣṭhāyaka, Mahāmātya, Paramaviśvāsin, Mahāparamaviśvāsin, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 28.<BR> (SITI), senior councillor of the king, usually a military officer; same as Mahāpradhāni. See Pradhāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रधाननायक
Mahāpradhāna-nāyaka (IA 12), regarded as a single official designation; but probably Mahāpradhāna and Nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रधानि
Mahāpradhāni (CITD; ASLV), often, the chief minister or administrator; same as Mahāradhāna; a high executive officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमातार
Mahāpramātāra (BL; MD), same as Mahāpramātṛ, Mahā-pramātra or Mahāpramattavāra. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 280.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=183" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमातृ
Mahāpramātṛ (CII 4), explained as ‘the chief surveyor’; same as Mahāpramātāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमात्र
Mahāpramātra (EI 12), same as Mahāpramātṛ, Mahā-pramātāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रमत्तवार
Mahāpramattavāra (HD), probably, the same as Mahā-pramātāra, etc.; explained wrongly as ‘the chief of the elephant corps’ (CII 4); cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 141.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रति
Mahā-prati (IA 18), abbreviation of Mahāmātya-Pratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रतिहार
Mahāpratihāra, Mahāpratīhāra (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3; BL), head of the door-keepers of the palace or the king's chamber, or of the capital; city; sometimes explained as ‘the chief usher’ (CII 4). See Pratihāra.<BR> (HD), the superior officer above all door-keepers, the great chamberlain. See Kādambarī, para. 97; Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142; Ep. Ind., Vol. X, p. 75; etc.<BR> (IE 8-2), one of the designations often included in the pañca-mahāśabda, as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī.<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpīlupati, Pañcakaraṇ-oparika, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रतिहारपीडा
mahāpratihāra-pīḍā (EI 12), occurs in the Rājataraṅgiṇī; explained as ‘the office of the high chamberlain’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाप्रतोली
mahā-pratolī (BL), main gateway; cf. pratolī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापुरोहित
Mahāpurohita (IE 8-3; CII 4), chief priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापुरोहितठक्कुर
Mahāpurohita-ṭhakkura (IE 8-3), ‘the head of the chief priests’; mentioned as a Pātra along with Mahāpurohita, Dharmādhikaraṇika, Daivāgārika, Śaṅkhadhārin, Paṇḍita, Upā-dhyāya, Daivajña, Mahārthaśāsanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापुरुष|महापुरुषः
Mahāpuruṣa (BL), same as the god Viṣṇu.<BR> (EI 7), official designation; probably, the same as Mahā-manuṣya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महर
Mahara (EI 1), probably a mistake for Mahattara, ‘a village-headman’ or ‘a member of the village Pañcāyat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराज|महाराजः
Mahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HD), royal title first assumed by the foreign rulers of India and later adopted by indigenous rulers; originally, an imperial title; later (when the emperors assumed more dignified titles), a title of feudatories and smaller rulers; cf. Greek Basileos Megalou and Old Persian Kshāyathiya vazrka. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-185" target="_blank">Page-185+ 40</a>]<BR> (IE 8-2), one of the designations sometimes included in the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case of Maitraka Dhruvasena I.<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes also called Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pañcādhikaraṇ-oparika, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika, etc., additionally.<BR> (IE 8-2), often used in the South even when Mahārājā-dhirāja became the popular imperial title in the North.<BR> (ASLV), designation of a priest of the members of the Vallabhācārya sect. Cf. Mahanta-mahārāja, title of pontiffs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=184" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजबप्पस्वामिन्
Mahārāja-bappa-svāmin (IE 8-2), designation by which the father and predecessor of a ruling king is sometimes referred to.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधि
Mahārājādhi (CII 3), abbreviation of Mahārājādhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधिराज
Mahārājādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 3; CII 3, 4), one of the technical titles of paramount sovereignty closely connected with Paramabhaṭṭāraka and Parameśvara; later sometimes also assumed by subordinate rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधिराजपरमेश्वरी
Mahārājādhirāja-parameśvarī (IE 8-2), title of certain ruling queens of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजाधिराजपति
Mahārājādhirāja-pati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 242), title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजकुल
Mahārājakula (IE 4; BL), official^1 designation^2 of a feudatory; same as Mahārāval of the Rajasthan region; cf. Rājakula.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR>[2] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजकुमार
Mahārājakumāra, cf. Bālaka-mahārājakumāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजमाता
Mahārāja-mātā (IE 8-2), epithet of the mother of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजनक
Mahārājanaka (EI 21), feudatory title; cf. Rājanaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजपण्डित
Mahārājapaṇḍita (EI 9), official designation; see Rājapaṇḍita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजपितामही
Mahārāja-pitāmahī (IE 8-2), epithet of the grandmother of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजप्रयोजन
Mahārāja-prayojana (SITI), probably, fees collected for the performance of police duties; same as Tamil araśu-pper̤u (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजपुत्र
Mahārājaputra (EI 26; CII 4; HD), ‘son of the Mahārāja’; designation of a prince. See Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजासाहेब्
Mahārājā-sāheb (BL), the same as Mahārāja with the Arabic honorific expression sāhib suffixed to it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराजातिराज
Mahārājātirāja (LL), imperial title; cf. Rājātirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराज्ञी
Mahārājñī (IE 8-2; EI 4, 21; CII 4; BL; HD), designation of queens; see Rājñī. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराज्य
mahārājya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 313), ‘a province’; cf. rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराणा
Mahārāṇā (EI 21, 24; BL), derived from Mahārāṇaka; feudatory title; later, also a royal title. See Rāṇā and Rāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=185" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराणक
Mahārāṇaka (EI 27; CII 4; BL; HD), title of feudatory rulers; see Rāṇaka. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 214.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारसकरण
mahārasa-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the liquor department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराष्ट्रिन्
Mahārāṣṭrin (IE 8-3; LL), Prakrit Mahāraṭhi; ‘ruler of a rāṣṭra (a district or subdivision or a group of villages)’; see Rāṣṭrin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराष्ट्रिणी
Mahārāṣṭriṇī (LL), cf. Prakrit Mahāraṭhiṇī (EI 7), wife of a Mahārāṣṭrin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारथ|महारथः
Mahāratha (EI 7), explained as ‘a race’ (EI 17); official designation; cf. Mahārathin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारथिन्
Mahārathin (IE 8-3; EI 7), wrong Sanskritization of Prakrit Mahāraṭhi (sometimes read as Mahārathi) which really stands for Mahārāṣṭrin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराउल
Mahārāula (EI 24; BL), same as Mahārāvala; derived from Mahārājakula; designation of a feudatory; title of nobility.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराउत
Mahārāuta (BL), designation of a feudatory; from Sanskrit Mahārājaputra. See Rāuta, Rāvata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराव
Mahārāva (BL), designation of a feudatory; from Sanskrit Mahārāja,<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारावल्
Mahārāval, Mahārāvala (BL), same as Mahārāula; designation of a fendatory; from Sanskrit Mahārājakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाराय
Mahārāya (EI 4, 24; BL), from Sanskrit Mahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महरी
Maharī, Mahārī, Māhārī (EI 33), same as Mehari, a dancing girl or Devadāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महारुण्डा
Mahāruṇḍā, a name of the Mother-goddess (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 36).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महार्थमहामहत्तक
Mahārtha-mahāmahattaka (CII 4), official designation; see Mahāmahattaka, Mahārtha may also be a separate official designation or an abbreviation of Mahārthaśāsanika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महार्थशासनिक
Mahārthaśāsanika (EI 8-3; EI 7), probably, an officer in charge of gifts; sometimes mentioned as a Pātra. Cf. Mahā-rtha-mahāmahattaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महार्यक
mah-āryaka (EI 8), probably, the great-grandfather; tentatively explained as ‘mother's grandfather’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाशब्द
mahā-śabda (IE 8-2), cf. aśeṣa-mahāśabda (EI 22), same as pañca-mahāśabda (q. v.). Cf. paṭaha-ḍhakkā-mahāśabda (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVI, p. 325).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासभा
mahā-sabhā (SII 1; ASLV; SITI), ‘the great assembly’; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-187" target="_blank">Page-187+ 40</a>] meeting of the general body of the sabhā; meeting of the Mahā-janas in session; body of the Mahājanas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=186" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाधनभाग|महासाधनभागः
mahāsādhanabhāga (IE 12; IA 14; HD), occurring in the Rājataraṅgīṇī; explained as ‘the office of the chief executive minister’; but cf. Mahāsādhanika; one of the five offices instituted by Lalitāditya of Kashmir (Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142-43).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाधनिक
Mahāsādhanika (IE 8-2, 8-3; CII 4; BL; HD), official designation indicating a commander of forces; the chief military officer; one of the designations often included in the pañca-mahāśabda as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Sādhanika derived from sādhana or army. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाहनी
Mahāsāhanī (BL), cf. Masāhaṇī (EI 5), a military officer; the same as Sanskrit Mahāsādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासाहसिक|महासाहसिकः
Mahāsāhasika (IE 25), official designation; cf. Duḥ-sādhya-sādhanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासैन्यपति
Mahāsainyapati (EI 29; HL), commander of forces; cf. Sainyapati and Mahāsenāpati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाशाइत्
mahāśāli (EI 5), a kind of rice or paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासांकरणनि
mahāsāṃ-karaṇa-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of mahāsāndhi-vigrahika-karaṇa-nirīkṣita, ‘examined by the clerk of the Mahāsāndhivigrahika’. Karaṇa here may also be an abbreviation of Adhikaraṇa or office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासामन्त|महासामन्तः
Mahāsāmanta (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL), ‘the great chieftain’; title of a feudatory of a higher rank than the Sāmanta; sometimes called Mahārāja, Mahāpratīhāra, Pañca-karaṇ-oparika, Pāṭy-uparika, Purapāl-oparika, Senādibāhattara-niyogādhiṣṭhāyaka, Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, Mahāpasāyita, Daṇḍanāyaka, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 217; Vol. IX, p. 107.<BR> (SITI), a vassal chief, sometimes holding the position of a minister or governor.<BR> (IE 8-2), one of the designations sometimes included in the pañca-mahāśabda; cf. the case of Maitraka Dhruvasena I.<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes a feudatory of a lower grade than Rājan and Rājanaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासामन्ताधिपति
Mahāsāmantādhipati (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 29, 30; CII 4; BL; HD), a feudatory title; cf. Sāmantādhipati (EI 16); title of feudatories who had some subordinate chiefs under them; title of a feudatory of a higher rank than the Mahāsāmanta; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-188" target="_blank">Page-188+ 40</a>] cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara, Samasta-mahāsāmant-ādhipati; sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Bhānasavěrgaḍě, Accupannāyadadhiṣṭhā-yaka, etc., additionally. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 259. See Mahāsāmanta, Mahāmaṇḍaleśvarādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=187" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासामन्तराज
Mahāsāmantarāja (EI 33), feudatory title; cf. Mahāsāmant-ādhipati. It may also indicate one enjoying the titles Mahā-sāmanta and Rājan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासानि
mahāsā-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of mahāsāndhivigrahikaṇirī-kṣita, ‘examined by the Mahāsāndhivigrahika’. See ni, mahākṣa-ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिकरण
mahāsandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa (EI 12; CII 4), the office or department of the Mahāsandhivigrahika; the department of peace and war.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिकरणआधिकृत
Mahāsandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta (BL), superintendent of the office of war and peace or foreign affairs. See Sandhi-vigrah-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिकृत
Mahāsandhivigrah-ādhikṛta (CII 4; HD), same as Mahā-sāndhivigrahika; minister of peace and war. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 80; Harṣacarita, Parab's ed., p. 194.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाधिपति
Mahāsandhivigrah-ādhipati (EI 21; CII 4), same as Mahā-sāndhivigrahika; cf. Sandhivigrah-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहाक्षपटलाधिकृत
Mahāsandhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta (EI 31), officer in charge of the accounts section of the foreign affairs department; same as Mahāsandhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासान्धिविग्रहाक्षपटलाधिपति
Mahāsāndhivigrah-ākṣapaṭal-ādhipati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 274), same as Mahāsandhivigrah-akṣapaṭal-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहिक
Mahāsandhivigrahika (BL; HD), same as Mahāsāndhivigra-hika; designation of the minister for war and peace or of foreign affairs. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309. See Sandhivigrahika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासान्धिविग्रहिक|महासांधिविग्रहिकः
Mahāsāndhivigrahika (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), same as Mahāsandhivigrahika; minister for peace and war or of foreign affairs; a civil or military title; one of the designations often included in the pañca-mahāśabda as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. See Sāndhivigrahika.<BR> (IE 8-3), cf. Gauḍa-mahāsāndhivigrahika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासन्धिविग्रहिन्
Mahāsandhivigrahin (BL), designation of the minister for war and peace or of foreign affairs. See Sandhivigrahin, Mahā-sāndhivigrahika, etc.<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Maně-věrgaḍě, Senādhipati, Kaḍita-věrgaḍě, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासप्तमी
mahāsaptamī (EI 4), a tithi; Māgha-sudi 7; Āśvina-sudi 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=188" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासर्वदण्डनायक
Mahāsarvadaṇḍanāyaka (CII 3), the commander-in-chief. See Sarvadaṇḍnāyaka and Daṇḍanāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासर्वाधिकृत
Mahāsarvādhikṛta (EI 12, 28), the chief minister or administrator. Cf. Sarvādhikṛta and Sarvādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासती
mahā-satī (EI 31), spelt mā-sati in Tamil, etc.; a lady who has committed^1 satī; cf. satī.<BR> Cf. mā-sati-kal, a stone raised in memory of a satī (Journ. Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 136).<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासत्त्रपति
Mahāsattrapati (EI 13), superintendent of the sattras (houses for free distribution of food).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनाधिपति
Mahāsenādhipati (EI 19), commander of forces. Cf. Mahāsenāpati, Senādhipati, Samastasenādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनानी
Mahāsenānī, commander of forces (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 156).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनापति
Mahāsenāpati (EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), ‘the great commander of armies’. See Senāpati, Mahāsenādhipati. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महासेनापत्नी
Mahāsenāpatnī (IE 8-2; EI 20; LL), wife of a Mahāsenā-pati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाशिरःप्रधानि
Mahāśiraḥ-Pradhāni (ASLV), a high officer who had a seat in the Imperial Council of the Vijayanagara kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्रमण|महाश्रमणः
Mahāśramaṇa (EI 32), the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्रेष्ठिन्
Mahāśreṣṭhin (EI 7; CII 4; HD), ‘the great banker’; the chief banker; see Śreṣṭhin. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महास्थान
mahāsthāna (EI 7), a holy place.<BR> (EI 24), a great temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महास्थविर
Mahāsthavira (LL), Buddhist; cf. Sthavira, an Elder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महास्वामिक
Mahāsvāmika (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), probably, ‘the king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वपति
Mahāśvapati (BL), designation of the leader of horsemen. See Aśvapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वसाधनिक
Mahāśvasādhanika (EI 12; HD), commander of a cavalry force. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 309.<BR> (CII 4), the great equerry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वशाला
mahāśvaśālā (EI 12; HD), explained as ‘the office of the chief master of the horses’; one of the five high offices instituted by Lalitādiya of Kashmir (Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाश्वशालाधिकृत
Mahāśvaśāl-ādhikṛta (IE 8-2), superintendent of the stables; one of the designations often included in the pañca-mahāśabda (cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 142).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=189" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महता
Mahatā (EI 32), the same as Mahattaka, Mahattara or Mahattama. Cf. Mahato.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातलवर
Mahātalavara (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 25; HD), explained by some authorities as a subordinate ruler and by others as the police magistrate of a city or the prefect of the city police. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, pp. 6, 16. See Talavara, Talāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातलवरी
Mahātalavarī (IE 8-2; EI 20, 25), wife of a Mahātalavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातन्त्र
mahātantra (SITI; ASLV), often mentioned in South Indian records in the sense of ‘the army’; the army council; the great assembly of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातन्त्राधिकृत
Mahātantrādhikṛta (IE 8-3), explained by some authorities as ‘an officer in charge of judicial and charitable affairs’; but the word tantra also means ‘administration’ or ‘the army’; probably ‘the chief administrator’. The designation may have also indicated different functions in different localities and ages. See Tantrapāla, Tantrapati and Mahātantrādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातन्त्राध्यक्ष
Mahātantrādhyakṣa (EI 28), official designation; same as Mahātantrādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाठक्कुर
Mahāṭhakkura (IE 8-2; IA 17), a title indicating office or rank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातीर्थ
Mahātīrtha (BL), epithet of a holy place or shrine. Cf. tīrtha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातिथि|महातिथिः
mahātithi (EI 13), an auspicious tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महात्मन्
Mahātman (CII 1), a person of high rank; a rich man; explained in some cases as ‘a magistrate’ (cf. Select Inscriptions, p. 248, note 6).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माहात्म्य|माहात्म्यं
māhātmya (IA 30), a culogistic work on deities or holy places, rivers, etc.; cf. sthala-purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महतो
Mahato (EI 8-3), same as Mahattaka, Mahattara or Maha-ttama. Cf. Mahatā; also Mahto in Wilson's Glossary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महातोरण
mahātoraṇa (SITI), a variety of temple lamps; probably the same as makaratoraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तक
Mahattaka (EI 8; BL; HD), probably, a village head-man or a member of the Pañcāyat board; same as Mahattara. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 30 (Mahāmahattaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तम
Mahattama (IE 8-3; EI 29; CII 4; BL; HD), probably the village headman or a member of the Pañcāyat board; cf. Mahattara. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 306; Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 266 (Mahattara and Mahattama occur one after another, Mahattama being senior or superior to Mahattara); Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 438. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-191" target="_blank">Page-191+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 26), same as Gujarātī Mahetā or Mehtā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=190" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तर|महत्तरः
Mahattara (IE 8-3; EI 23, 29, 30; CII 4; BL; HD), literally, ‘an elder [of a town or village]’; according to Stein (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 659); a chamberlain, a village headman or head of a family or community and a member of the village council; cf. Hindī Mahato; Gujaratī Mahetā. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, p. 114 (rāṣṭra-grāma-mahattara); Daśakumāracarita, III, p. 77 (janapada-mahattara).<BR> Cf. mahattar-ādy-aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa (EI 31), ‘office of the administrative board of the aṣṭakula headed by the Mahattara’; see Mahattara and aṣṭakul-ādhikaraṇa.<BR> (IE 3-3), official guide. (Beal, Life of Hiuen Tsiang, p. 190).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महत्तरक|महत्तरकः
Mahattaraka (EI 23; LL), explained as ‘a chamberlain’; same as Mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महात्राण
mahātrāṇa (IE 8-5), Bengali; a rent-free holding in the possession of non-Brahmanical communities, e. g. the Vaiṣṇavas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावड्डव्यवहारिन्
Mahāvaḍḍavyavahārin (EI 13; SII 11-2), see Vaḍḍavya-vahārin and Mahāvaṇḍavyavahārin; Sanskrit Mahāvṛddhavyavahārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावलाकोष्ठिक
Mahāvalākoṣṭhika (IE 8-3), probably a mistake for Mahā-balakoṣṭhika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावण्डव्यवहारिन्
Mahāvaṇḍavyavahārin (EI 19; SITI), the great banker or chief merchant; head of a mercantile guild; same as Mahāvaḍḍavyavahārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावारुणी
mahāvāruṇī (EI 4), name of a tithi. See mahāmahāvāruṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविहार
mahāvihāra (BL), Buddhist convent or monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविहारस्वामिन्
Mahāvihāra-svāmin (EI 8; CII 3; BL), designation of the builder of a Buddhist monastery and his heirs who were responsible for its maintenance; the builder or owner of a big monastery; cf. Vihāra-svāmin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविहारायतन
mahāvihār-āyatana (EI 22), a monastic establishment. Cf. āyatana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाविनयधर
Mahāvinayadhara (LL), Buddhist; cf. Vinayadhara, ‘one who has committed the Vinaya texts to memory’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महावरतिन्
Mahāvaratin (EI 27; SITI), name of a Śaiva sect; followers of the said sect of Śaivism; an ascetic of the Kālāmukha sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाव्यवस्था
mahā-vyavasthā (SITI), probably, the regulations framed by the mahā-sabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महाव्यूहपति
Mahāvyūhapati (EI 19, 28, 30; HD), the chief master of battle arrays. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 40.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=191" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महायज्ञ|महायज्ञः
mahāyajña (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’. See pañca-mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महायुवराज
Mahāyuvarāja (EI 32), title of a crown prince; see Yuva-rāja and Yuvamahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेन्द्रादित्य
Mahendrāditya (IE 8-2), see āditya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेश्वर|महेश्वरः
Maheśvara (SITI), Māheśvara, followers of the Śaiva religion; a congregation of Śaiva devotees having a voice in the management of the affairs of a Śiva temple.<BR> (ASLV), trustee of a Śaiva temple.<BR> (IE 8-2), ‘devotee of Maheśvara (Śiva),’ epithet of a Kuṣāṇa king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेश्वर|महेश्वरः
maheśvara (EI 28), the Pāśupta faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महेश्वरपुत्र
Maheśvara-putra (EI 33), sometimes used as an epithet of one devoted to the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मही
mahī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महीधर|महीधरः
mahīdhara (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महिमद
Mahimada (EI 32), Indianised form of the Muhammadan name Muḥammad or Mahmūd.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महीमण्डलेश्वर
Mahīmaṇḍaleśvara (BL), rare modification of the feudatory title Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महिषकर
mahiṣa-kara, cf. Tamil erumai-ppon (SITI), tax on buffaloes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महिषी
Mahiṣī, cf. Agaramahiṣī Agramahāmahiṣī, Mahāmahiṣī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महोदय|महोदयं|महोदयः
Mahodaya (IA 18), used in the sense of Svāmin or possessor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महोद्रङ्ग
mah-odraṅga, cf. udraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महोपाध्याय|महोपाध्यायः
Mahopādhyāya (EI 6, 15), a title of teachers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माहुत्
Māhut (CII 4), derived from Mahāmātra, an elephant-driver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मह्य
mahya (EI 28), same as namasya. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, pp. 77 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैरा
mairā (CII 4), boundary of a field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैथिली
Maithilī, language and alphabet of Mithilā or the Tirhut region of North Bihar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैथुन|मैथुनं
maithuna (SITI), wife's brother; elder sister's husband.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मैत्री
maitrī (CII 4), benevolence; one of the bhāvanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरसङ्क्रमण
makara-saṅkramaṇa (SITI), entrance of the sun into Capricorn; commencement of the Tamil month Tai; same as Makara-saṅkrānti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरसङ्क्रान्ति
makara-saṅkrānti (SITI), same as makara-saṅkramaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरतोरण
makara-toraṇa (EI 29), one of the royal insignia.<BR> (EI 3; SII 1, 3), an ornamental arch; an arch in the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-193" target="_blank">Page-193+ 40</a>] shape of a makara (crocodile); gateway with figures of crocodiles. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol XXXV p. 107.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=192" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरिका
makarikā (CITD), figures of crocodiles drawn in gold dust on the cheeks and breasts of women; same as makarikā-patra.<BR> (EI 14), cf. mukuṭa-makarikā-marakata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकरिकापत्र
makarikā-patra (CITD), same as makarikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मकुति|मकुतिः
makuti (CII 4), an edict addressed to the Śūdras. Cf. Mākutika, official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माल|मालं|मालः
māla (EI 22), an elevated ground.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलधारि
Maladhāri (BL), epithet of a Jain religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालाकार|मालाकारः
Mālākāra (LL), a florist. See Mālin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलमार्गण
malamārgaṇa (LL), cf. Gujarātī mal̤avero; a tax to be utilised when the whole village wants to honour a particular man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालवगणाम्नात
Mālava-gaṇ-āmnāta, Mālava-gaṇa-sthiti, Mālava-pūrvā (EI 23), expressions used in early records in connection with the Vikrama-saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालवी
Mālavī, dialect of Hindī prevalent in Mālava (Malwa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालवीय
Mālavīya (EI 22), ‘the king of Mālava’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलय|मलयः
malaya (IA 14), derived from Dravidian malai, ‘a hill’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलयालम्
Malayāl̤am, name of a language and alphabet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलेयसाहणि
Maleya-sāhaṇi (Naik's List, No. 264); mentioned alongwith Peyiya-sāhaṇi; official designation. See Sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालिम
Mālima, same as Arabic Mualim, ‘an instructor’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्ल|मल्लः
Malla (CII 4), a wrestler, a match.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लक|मल्लकः
mallaka (EI 21) a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लकर
malla-kara (HRS), found in Nepal inscriptions; tax levied as tribute to the Mallas or for defence against their attack. Cf. turuṣka-daṇḍa, etc. It may also be a professional tax on wrestlers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लकवुन्धक
mallaka-vundhaka, cf. talabhedyā-ghāṇaka-mallaka-vundhaka (IA 18); probably, a professional tax on wrestlers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मलिक्
Malik, Malika (EI 4; BL), Muslim title of nobility; same as Arabic Malik; also spelt in Indian languages as Mallika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मालिन्
Mālin (EI 9), a florist. See Mālākāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ममत्रै
Mamátrai (IE 8-3), Greek modification of Mahāmātra; explained as ‘commanders or rulers among Indians’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मंक्षूण
maṃkṣūṇa, see draṃkṣaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मामूलादाय
māmūl-ādāya (SITI), customary payment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=193" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्
man, cf. mānayitvā (LP) ‘having accepted’; cf. Gujarātī mānine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान|मानं|मानः
māna (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; (1/16)th part of the measure called tūmu; that which can hold rice of the weight of 4 ṭaṅkalamulu (varying in different localities); a particular measure or weight often regarded as half of a seru; a measuring rod.<BR> (EI 16), also called mānaka; name of a measure; a liquid measure (SII 11-1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान|मानं|मानः
māna, māṇa (IE 8-6; EI 30, 31), used in medieval Orissan records in the sense of a land measure; a land measure regarded as equal to an English acre in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानभोग
māna-bhoga (SITI), enjoyment of tax-free lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानदण्ड|मानदंड|मानदण्डः
māna-daṇḍa (SITI), measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानक|मानकं
mānaka (EI 14, 16), name of a measure; also called māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानपौतव
māna-pautava (EI 30), probably, a store-house where grains were measured and stored. Cf. mānya (al̤l̤āya-mānya).<BR> (IE 8-8), scales and measures.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानस्तम्भ
māna-stambha (EI 5, 8), a pillar; an elegant tall pillar with a small pinnacled maṇṭapa at the top erected in front of Jain temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनवर्ति
manavarti, manavartika (EI 32), grant for maintenance; also spelt as manovarti, manuvṛtti, etc., probably derived from Sanskrit mānya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानव्य|मानव्यं
Mānavya (EI 16), name of a gotra that was claimed by royal families which had originally no real Brāhmanical gotra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्च|मंच|मंचः|मञ्चः
mañca, cf. sa-mañca-mahākaraṇa (IE 8-5); probably, elevated platforms for official use.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्ड|मंडं|मण्डं|मंडः|मण्डः
maṇḍa, weight equal to 5 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46); cf. māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डई
maṇḍaī (EI 23), derived from maṇḍapikā; same as maṇḍī, ‘market’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डक|मंडकः|मण्डकः
maṇḍaka (SITI), same as maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डल|मंडल|मण्डलं|मण्डलः
maṇḍala (IE 8-4; EI 29, 30; CII 4), an administrative unit; a district or province.<BR> (SITI), a province consisting of several koṭṭams or valanāḍus.<BR> (IE 8-4), sometimes mentioned as bigger than a viṣaya and sometimes smaller than it; sometimes a viṣaya was included in a maṇḍala, but sometimes a maṇḍala was included in a viṣaya; sometimes [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-195" target="_blank">Page-195+ 40</a>] maṇḍala and viṣaya are identical; sometimes a maṇḍala was smaller than the vīthī or subdivision.<BR> (IE 8-4; SII 3; ASLV), sometimes used in a wider sense to indicate a country.<BR> Cf. Kona-maṇḍala (EI 22), also called an avani-maṇḍala or deśa. Here maṇḍala means a kingdom or territory.<BR> (ASLV), an assembled body. Cf. mātṛ-maṇḍala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=194" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलाचार्य
Maṇḍal-ācārya (EI 33, IA 14), same as Paṭṭ-ācārya; designation of a high priest.<BR> (BL), epithet of a [Jain] religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलाधिपति
Maṇḍal-ādhipati (EI 25), the ruler of a maṇḍala; cf. Maṇḍaleśvara Maṇḍalapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलगणिन्
Maṇḍala-gaṇin (EI 33), title; cf. Gaṇin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलकरण
maṇḍala-karaṇa (LP), department dealing with the administration of districts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलमुदलियार्
Maṇḍala-mudaliyār, official designation; cf. maṇḍala-mudan-mai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलमुदन्मै
maṇḍala-mudanmai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; leadership or governorship of a province, its governor or chief being known as Maṇḍala-mudaliyār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलपति
Maṇḍalapati (IE 8-3; EI 26, 33), ruler or officer-in-charge of a maṇḍala; the governor of a district or a feudatory ruler (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 78, text line 9); same as Maṇḍaleśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलेश|मण्डलेशः
Maṇḍaleśa (BL; HD), ‘lord of a maṇḍala’; a provincial governor; same as Maṇḍaleśvara. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 73; VII. 996; VIII. 1228, 1814, 2029.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलेश्वर|मण्डलेश्वरः
Maṇḍaleśvara (IE 8-2; BL; HD), title of a feudatory or governor lower in rank than a Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara; same as Maṇḍaleśa. Cf. Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354. Cf. Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara, ‘governor of the provinces’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 110).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलिक
Maṇḍalika (EI 26), ruler of a maṇḍala or district; same as Māṇḍalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माण्डलिक|मांडलिक|माण्डलिकः
Māṇḍalika (IE 8-2; BL; CII 4), ruler of a maṇḍala or district; title of a feudatory chief; cf. Maṇḍalika, Maṇḍalīka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलीक|मंडलीकः|मण्डलीकः
Maṇḍalīka (IE 8-2; SII 1; SITI; BL), feudatory title; ruler of a maṇḍala; same as Maṇḍalika and Māṇḍalika, also called Maṇḍaleśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डप|मंडपः|मण्डपः
maṇḍapa (IE 8-3), customs house; Marāṭhī māṇḍavī, from Sanskrit maṇḍapikā; explained by some as ‘a market place’ [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-196" target="_blank">Page-196+ 40</a>] (Hindī maṇḍī); but Hindī maṇḍī seems to be derived from the same word because the toll-stations were often situated in market-places.<BR> (BL), name of a structure in front of a temple.<BR> (LL), a porch or hall.<BR> (CII 4), the hall in a temple.<BR> (CII 4), a temple.<BR> (EI 31), a temple or public building.<BR> Cf. vaiccamudu-maṇḍapa (SITI), kitchen; same as maḍaip-pal̤l̤i.<BR> Cf. vakkāṇikku-maṇḍapa (SITI), hall where disputations in the śāstras are held. Cf. śanivāra-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=195" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिका|मंडपिका
maṇḍapikā (EI 1, 3, 33), customs house; same as śulka-maṇḍapikā (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 339 and note 31). See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 238-39.<BR> (EI 3; CII 4); market; a market pavilion.<BR> (CII 4), a small temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माण्डपिक
Māṇḍapika (IE 8-2), cf. Prakrit Maṃḍavika (EI I), officer in charge of a maṇḍapikā or customs house; a collector of tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिकादाय
maṇḍapik-ādāya (EI 23), explained as ‘the market tax’; customs duties.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिकाकरण
maṇḍapikā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), the customs department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डपिकापट्टक
maṇḍapikā-paṭṭaka (LP), a contract for market-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माण्डवी
Māṇḍavī (LP), one who gets the market-tax; same as Māṇḍapika.<BR> (LP), a tax levied on articles that are to be sold in a market-place.<BR> (IE 8-3), Marāṭhī; same as maṇḍapikā, ‘customs house’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डवो
maṇḍavo (EI 22), market place; regarded as the same as maṇḍapikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनेवेर्गडे
Maně-věrgaḍě (IE 8-3; EI 16; SII 11-2), Kannaḍa; superintendent or steward of the royal household (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 77); sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Hěri-sandhivigrahin, Antaḥpurādhyakṣa, Hěri-Lāl̤a-Kannaḍa-sandhivi-grahin, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनेयसमस्तसैन्याधिपति
̎Maněyasamastasainyādhipati (IE 8-3), leader of all the troops in the royal household. Cf. Samastasenādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गल|मंगल|मङ्गलं|मङ्गलः
maṅgala (CII 1), a ceremony for one's good or for averting evil; cf. kalyāṇa. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-197" target="_blank">Page-197+ 40</a>]<BR> (SITI), a Brāhmaṇa village; shortened form of caturvedi-maṅgala.<BR> (ASLV), a small administrative unit.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=196" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गलकलस
maṅgala-kalaśa (CII 4), an auspicious vase. Cf. nidrā-kalasa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गालिहा
maṅgālikā (IA 15), probably, an upper garment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माङ्गलिक्य
māṅgalikya (LP), some present (made in lieu of the benefit one is going to get).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माङ्गलीयक
māṅgalīyaka (LP), probably, a tax collected on the occasion of auspicious events in the royal family, such as the birth of a son to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माङ्गल्य|मांगल्य|माङ्गल्यं
māṅgalya (SITI), Tamil maṅgiliyam; the ornament called tāli worn round the neck as the marriage badge by a married woman with her husband living.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मङ्गणि
maṅgaṇi, maṅgaṇī, maṅaṇī (Chamba), a tax in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणि|मणिः
maṇi (IA 20), a burning glass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानि
māni (LP), a measure of capacity equal to about 6 maunds.<BR> (SII 11-1), Kannaḍa; also spelt Māṇi; a bachelor; Brahmacārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माणि
māṇi (EI 14; Chamba), name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणिभण्डलु
maṇi-bhaṇḍalu (CITD), Sanskrit-Telugu; probably, from Sanskrit maṇi-bhāṇḍa or the receptacle of jewels.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणिग्राम
maṇi-grāma (SITI), a mercantile guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माणिक|माणिकः
māṇika (CITD), Telugu; a measure; (1/4) of a kuñcamu and (1/15) of a tūmu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मणिकार|मणिकारः
Maṇikāra (LP), a jeweller.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माणिक्यभाण्डार
māṇikya-bhāṇḍāra, cf. maṇikka-paṇḍāram-kāppār (SITI), ‘keeper of the treasury [of precious stones] in the temple or palace.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानिन्
Mānin, cf. Māṇi (IA 18), an Elder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मानित
mānita (LP), accepted.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जाडि
mañjāḍi (IE 8-8; EI 21, 33; SII 2, 12; SITI), Tamil; name of a weight for measuring gold and silver; about 2 or 3 ratīs or 4 or 5 grains; a weight equal to two kun̤r̤i-maṇi used in weighing gold; (1/10) of a kal̤̣añju and (1/100) of a śatamāna (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 141).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जूर
Mañjūra (LP), day-labourer; cf. Majūr.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जूषा|मंजूषा
mañjūṣā (LL), casket.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्नेय
Manněya (CITD), Telugu; same as Sanskrit Mānya; a respectable man; a chieftain; a commander; a chief. Cf. Mannīḍu, Manniya. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-198" target="_blank">Page-198+ 40</a>]<BR> (SII 11-1), ruler of a group of villages; cf. manneya-svāmya, tenure held by a Manneya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=197" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्नीडु
Mannīḍu (CITD), same as Manneya (Sanskrit Mānya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्निय
Manniya (CITD), same as Manneya (Sanskrit Mānya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनोहारी
manohārī (LP), cf. nija-manohāryā, ‘at one's own will’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनोतिरेक
mano-'tireka (CII 1), eagerness; cf. atireka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनोवर्ति
manovarti (EI 32), same as manavarti or manuvṛtti in the sense of namasya-vṛtti or mānya; probably derived from Sanskrit mānya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्थनयन्त्रक
manthana-yantraka (IA 20), a fire-producing instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रदेवमनुजभूतपितृगण
mantra-deva-manuja-bhūta-pitṛgaṇa (IA 15), refers to the pañca-mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रपाल
Mantrapāla (EI 22), official designation; probably, a private secretary or privy councillor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रपुष्प
Mantrapuṣpa (IA 12), designation of a priest who repeats the mantra when the chief priest asks forgiveness at the conclusion of each pūjā at the Rāmeśvaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रशक्ति|मन्त्रशक्तिः
mantra-śakti (CII 4), the power of good counsel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रस्नान
mantra-snāna (EI 4), repetition of prayers used at ablution without the actual bath.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रिन्|मंत्रिन्
Mantrin (EI 12, 25; CII 4; BL; HD), a minister or councillor; a counsellor; an executive officer. See Arthaśāstra, I. 80; Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 312; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR> (IE 8-3), explained as vyavahāra-draṣṭṛ. Cf. Mahāmantrin.<BR> (IE 8-3), in one case, the Mantrin later became a Mahā-balādhikṛta; in another case, also a Kumārāmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्त्रिपरिषद्
mantri-pariṣad (CII 4; ASLV), the council of ministers; same as pariṣad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनु|मनुः
Manu (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनुष्य|मनुष्यः
Manuṣya, cf. Mānisi (EI 24), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनुष्ययज्ञ|मनुष्ययज्ञः
manuṣya-yajña (CII 4), reception of guests; one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनुवृत्ति
manuvṛtti (EI 32), a grant made for the maintenance of the donee; same as manavarti, etc.; probably derived from Sanskrit mānya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्वादि
manvādi (IA 18), name applied to certain tithis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्य|मान्यः
mānya (IE 8-5; EI 20, 23; ASLV), a rent-free holding, tax-free land; same as sarva-mānya; cf. mānya-sthiti, manuvṛtti, etc.<BR> Cf. sthāna-mānya (CITD), an honour or glebe-land [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-199" target="_blank">Page-199+ 40</a>] granted by the ruler on quit-rent or on various favourable tenures.<BR> (EI 13), land either liable to a trifling quit-rent or altogether exempt from tax.<BR> Cf. al̤l̤āya-mānyam (SITI), right to receive a handful of grain or the prescribed quantity of an article brought for sale in the market as charges for measuring; cf. māna-pautava.<BR> Cf. guḍḍe-mānya (IA 19), a particular kind of rent-free holding.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=198" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यकणिके
mānya-kaṇikě (EI 25), a small amount of tax levied from land declared rent-free. Cf. nikara, tṛṇodaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यकपट्ट
mānyaka-paṭṭa, a rent-free village (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यस्थिति
mānya-sthiti, cf. mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्यवान्तरराष्ट्र
manyavāntara-rāṣṭra (SII 1), same as nāḍu or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मान्यवृत्ति
mānya-vṛtti, cf. manuvṛtti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पणम्
māppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; same as Sanskrit mahā-paṇa; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्
mār (IA 15), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर|मरः
mara (EI 14), name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरमक्कतयम्
maramakkatayam (EI 9), system of inheritance prevalent in the Malayāl̤am-speaking area, according to which property is owned by females and passes from female to female.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मराठी
Marāṭhī, language and people of Maharashtra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरवडै
maravaḍai (EI 17), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्ग|मार्गः
Mārga (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Mārgaśīrṣa, Mārgaśira, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गादाय
mārg-ādāya (EI 23; SITI), same as vartma-daṇḍa; levy for passage of articles of merchandise through the gift village by the village road; tolls; tolls on the articles on transit. See mārgaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गक|मार्गकः
mārgaka (EI 26), name of a levy; same as mārg-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गण|मार्गणं|मार्गणः
mārgaṇa (EI 24), a beggar^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गणक|मार्गणकः
mārgaṇaka (EI 3; IA 18; CII 4; HRS), known from records like those of the Caulukyas; a levy; a kind of cess or tax; explained as ‘benevolences of a general character, as distinguished from the special types called prasthaka and skandhaka’. See mārgaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गणिक
mārgaṇika (IE 8-5), same as mārgaṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गप
Mārgapa (EI 20), same as Mārgapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गपाल
Mārgapāla (HD), same as Mārgapati, etc. See Nārada quoted in the Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 71. Cf. Dikpāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=199" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गपति|मार्गपतिः
Mārgapati (BL; HE), explained as ‘the guardian of the frontiers or passes’ (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XX, pp. 37, 41); probably, a collector of customs duties on the roads. See mārg-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गेश
Mārgeśa (EI 20), same as Mārgapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरीछि
marīci, a theoretical unit of measurement (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्झक
Marjhaka (ML), title of foreign origin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्तण्ड|मार्तंड|मार्तंडः|मार्तण्डः|मार्त्तण्ड|मार्त्तण्डः
mārtaṇḍa (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः
mar̤utu (CITD), same is mar̤uturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः
mar̤uturu (IE 8-6; CITD); also called mar̤utu, mattaru, etc.; Telugu; Kannaḍa mattar or mattaru; a certain land measure of uncertain area generally used as an equivalent^1 of nivartana, different kinds being mentioned as kāl-mar̤uturu, ghaḍa-mar̤uturu, kommu-mar̤utu, etc.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्वा
Marvād̤ī, spelt Marwari in English; name of the Rājasthānī dialect prevalent in Marwar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्यादा|मर्य्यादा
maryādā (SITI), Tamil mariyādi; customary dues; manners; ways; extent; limit; also spelt in Tamil as marjādi, mariśādi, maruśādi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्यादाधुर्य
Maryādā-dhurya (BL), explained as ‘the Warden of Marches.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मर्यादापरिहार
maryādā-parihāra (EI 22), customary exemptions of taxes. See parihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मास|मासं|मासः
māsa (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माष|माषः
māṣa (EI 21, 25, 30, 33; CII 4), according to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K. V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, p. 125), a gold coin as opposed to silver māṣaka; name of a weight; name of a coin; 5 ratis in weight; sometimes regarded as 10 ratis in weight and as equal to (1/4) of a śāna. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 41. It was sometimes regarded as (1/20) of a paṇa of 100 ratis (ibid., Vol. XV, p. 143). Cf. māṣaka, ādya-māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माषक|माषकः
māṣaka (IE 8-8), name of a coin; cf. māṣa and dināri-māṣaka; mentioned as a silver coin (K. V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, Kṛtyakalpataru, Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, p. 125).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मासार्ध
māsārdha (IE 7-1-2), used to indicate ‘six’; cf. māsa, ‘twelve’; also pakṣa, ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माशु
Māśu (Chamba), one enjoying land, who does not pay rent or tax but renders service; e. g., a carpenter, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मसूर|मसूरः
masūra (ML), small-pox.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत|मतं|मतः
mata, cf. guru-mata (CII 1), ‘a matter considered to be serious’. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-201" target="_blank">Page-201+ 40</a>]<BR> (LP), a signature; cf. the use of the word with the signature as in mataṃ mama amukasya found copied in many copper-plate grants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=200" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातङ्ग|मातंग|मातंगः|मातङ्गः
mātaṅga (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातापितृपादानुध्यात
mātā-pitṛ-pād-ānudhyāta (IE 8-2), ‘meditating on or favoured by the feet of one's parents’; epithet of rulers; cf. mātā-pitṛ-pād-ānudhyāna-rata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातरः|मातर
Mātaraḥ (CII 3), the Divine Mothers, sometimes indicated as seven in number; cf. Mātṛ and Mātṛ-gaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठ|मठं|मठः
maṭha (EI 17, 19, 23, 31, 32; CII 3, 4; SII 1; BL; ASLV; CITD), a school or religious college; a temple; a monastery; hermitage or convent; a monastery which was a religious and educational institution. See maṭhikā. In Telugu records, it also means ‘a bullock cart’ and ‘a cart load’ (cf. Kannaḍa maṭṭī, ‘a load’).<BR> (SITI), place where pilgrims and religious mendicants (tapasvins) are fed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठाधिपति|मठाधिपतिः
Maṭhādhipati (EI 25), same as Jīyar and Mudaliyār; cf. Maṭhapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठपति
Maṭhapati (EI 33), superintendent of a monastery; the chief priest of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माठापत्य
māṭhāpatya (SITI), the office or position of a Maṭhapati; management of the affairs of a maṭha or temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठस्थान
maṭha-sthāna (EI 26), a monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मठिका
maṭhikā (EI 31), a hut, cottage or cell.<BR> (EI 26, 32), a shrine or temple; cf. maṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मतिसचिव
Matisaciva (IE 8-3; HD), counsellor or minister; cf. Karma-saciva, administrative officer. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 44.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातृ
Mātṛ (EI 9), the Divine Mothers, often described as seven in number; cf. mātṛ-maṇḍala, various forms of the Mother-goddess installed around a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मात्र|मात्रं|मात्रः
Mātra, designation of a class of officers; cf. Mahāmātra in a similar sense. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 117 (mentioned along with Mūlaprakṛti; cf. Prakṛti).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मातृगण|मातृगणः
Mātṛ-gaṇa (IA 7), the Divine Mothers, often described as seven in number. Cf. mātṛ-maṇḍala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्स्याकर
matsy-ākara, cf. sa-matsy-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with the sources of fish’, the fishing right belonging to the king or landlord; cf. jala-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मात्स्यन्याय|मात्स्यन्यायः
mātsya-nyāya (EI 4), ‘the law of the fish’; anarchy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=201" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्त|मत्तः
matta (LP), a signature; corrupt form of mata, ‘approved’, written along with the signature as in mataṃ mama amukasya. See mata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्तल्
mattal (EI 16; IA 11), land measure; same as mattar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्तर्
mattar (EI 16, 20), Kannaḍa; land measure; same as mar̤uturu or nivartana; cf. gaṇṭi-mattar (IA 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मत्तरु
mattaru (IE 8-6; CITD), same as mattar or nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मट्टस्कन्ध
maṭṭa-skandha (LP), a layer of mud; cf. maṭṭa-skandha-rahita (LP), free from the layers of mud.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मट्टिवा
Maṭṭivā (IA 10), Hindī; an exorcist.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मट्टु
maṭṭu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown measure of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मौख|मौखं
maukha (EI 13), same as mukhya; ‘chief disciple’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मौलिक|मौलिकः
maulika (IE 8-5; EI 32), a tax; the principal or main tax or the perquisites of hereditary officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मवाड
mavāḍa (CII 4), name of a tax; cf. māvaḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मावडै
māvaḍai (EI 17), name of a tax. cf. mavāḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मयूर|मयूरः
mayūra (CII 1), a peacock; a bird in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मयूट
mayūṭa (HRS), probably, the contributions of fruits, firewood, etc., paid by villagers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मे
Me (Chamba), abbreviation for Mehtā (Mahattaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेढि
meḍhi (LP), a barn-yard, a threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेढिहारक
meḍhi-hāraka (LP), a special tax on the threshing-floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेध्य|मेध्यं|मेध्यः
medhya, cf. a-paśu-medhya (IE 8-5), ‘free from the obligation of supplying animals for sacrifices’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेडि
meḍi (EI 9), also called meli, a kidnapper of victims for sacrifices.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेघाडम्बर|मेघाडंबर|मेघाडम्बरः
meghāḍambara (SII 3), Hindusthānī; a covered howdā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेह|मेहः
Meha (IA 18), abbreviation of Mehara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेहर
Mehara (EI 33), village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेहरी
Meharī (EI 33), same as Devādāsī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेलापक|मेलापकः
melāpaka (LP), a group.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेलि
meli (EI 9), same as meḍi. (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्शान्ति
Mel-śānti (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; chief priest in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्विट्टियवड्डारवुल
melviṭṭiya-vaḍḍāravul̤a (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax; see vaḍḍāravul̤a.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेर
mera (EI 6), Telugu; a fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरिदर्ख
Meridarkha (IE 8-3; ML), an official designation of foreign origin; same as Greek Meridarkhes, ‘a district officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरिदर्खेस्
Meridarkhes (IE 8-3), Greek; see Meridarkha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरु|मेरुः
meru (SII 3), name of a gift. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-203" target="_blank">Page-203+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 2; CII 4), a kind of temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=202" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेषसङ्क्रान्ति
meṣa-saṅkrānti (CII 3, etc.), the entrance of the sun into the sign Aries, regarded as the starting point of the Śaka year; see also abdapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेय
meya (IE 8-5; EI 31; HRS), the share of grains to be paid to the king or landlord; revenue from agricultural land paid in kind; same as bhāga. Cf. tulya-meya, tax on commodities brought to market for sale.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेय्कावल्
Meykāval (ASLV), watchman in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मजिगिति
majigiti (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 242), also spelt mijigiti; Indianised form of Arabic masjid, a mosque.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिजिगिति
mijigiti (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12); see majigiti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिलिवलित
milivalita, same as Sanskrit sammilita, ‘taken collectively’ (JAS, Latters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिश्र|मिश्रं|मिश्रः
miśra (IA 18), an honorific title; cf. Mahāmiśrapaṇḍita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मीठिक
Mīṭhika (LL), a polisher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिति|मितिः
miti (IA 20), cf. Saṃvat 1384 miti Bhādra-vadi 3 Guru-dine; probably a corruption of Sanskrit mita, ‘counted’, ‘calculated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म्लेच्छ|म्लेच्छं|म्लेच्छः|म्लेछ
Mleccha (EI 22), name applied to the Muhammadans and other foreigners; cf. Mleccheśvara (EI 32).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोचि
moci, mocī (EI 2; CII 4), a shoe-maker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोदलवाड
modala-vāḍa (IE 8-4), Kannaḍa; the chief village in a Pargana consisting of a number of villages, i. e. headquarters; sometimes called rājadhānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोदति
modati, cf. svarge modati bhūmidaḥ; parasmaipada in place of the expected ātmanepada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोदिन
Modina, same as Arabic Muazzin, ‘a public crier to prayers’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोहिनी
Mohinī (IA 19), female devils who possess men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोकीरक
mokīraka (LP), a den in a mountain forest; Gujarātī bhokaruṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृड|मृडः
mṛḍa, also called pṛḍa or pruḍa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 40); unit of metal weight like the mañjāḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृग|मृगः
mṛga (CII 1), a deer; an animal in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृगाङ्क|मृगांक|मृगाङ्कः
mṛgāṅka (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृत्युकवृत्ति
mṛtyuka-vṛtti (BL; HRS), land granted by the king as military pension to the heir of a person killed in a battle against the king's enemies; compensatory grant made in favour of the heir of a person who died fighting on behalf of his master. See rakta-mānya, etc. Cf. vīra-śeṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=203" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूडा
mūḍā (LP), same as mūḍaka or mūṭaka; a measure of capacity equal to a hundred maunds or to 24 maunds in the Surat District.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूडक|मूडकः
mūḍaka (LP), same as mūṭaka or mūḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल्
Mudal, cf. Evi-mudal (EI 25), an official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल्
mudal (SII 3), Tamil; cost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल
mudala (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 18), used in some Orissan inscriptions in the sense of a royal order [regarding the grant of land or its execution]. Cf. ibid., Vol. XXVIII, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदलि
Mudali, Mudaliyār (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a chief.<BR> (EI 25), same as Maṭhādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदिरथ
Mudiratha (EI 33), Od̤iyā; same as Mudrāhasta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदिता
muditā (CII 4), cheerfulness; one of the Buddhist bhāvanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्रा
mudrā (CII 4), the position of fingers in worship.<BR> (LP), the government seal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूर्धाधिकार
mūrdh-ādhikāra, cf. Tamil mūtt-ādikāram (SITI), supreme authority.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राधिकारिन्
Mudrādhikārin (EI 30), officer in charge of the royal seal; also called Mudr-ādhyakṣa, etc. Mudrādhikāri-saciva, may be Mudrādhikārin and Saciva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राधिकृत
Mudr-ādhikṛta (EI 14, 15), same as Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राध्यक्ष|मुद्राध्यक्षः
Mudr-ādhyakṣa, same as Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.; cf. Rājamudrādhikārin. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 96.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राहस्त
Mudrāhasta (EI 33), official designation; same as Oḍiyā Mudiratha, designation of a class of servants in the temple of Jagannātha at Purī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्रापवार
mudr-āpavāra (IE 8-8; EI 30), the crime of using counterfeit coins or the misuse of official seals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राशङ्ख
mudrā-śaṅkha, cf. Tamil muttirai-ccaṅgu (SITI), a variety of conch-shell; conch-shell marked with a seal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्रावतार
mudr-āvatāra, cf. Tamil muttir-āvatāram (SITI), an ear-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुद्राव्यापार
mudrā-vyāpāra (IE 8-2); 8-3; BL), ‘the affairs associated with the royal seal’; often used in connection with the function of the viceroy described as conducting the said business; cf. samasta-mudrā-vyāpārān paripanthayati, śrī-śrīkaraṇ-ādi-samasta-mudrāvyāpārān paripanthyati. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 154. See also vyāpāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदुड
Muduḍa (EI 27), same as Mutuḍa; probably, a village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=204" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुहपत्ति
muha-patti (HA), a piece of cloth held in front of the mouth by Jain monks and nuns, while they are talking, in order to avoid small living beings being destroyed by breath.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुहूर्त|मुहूर्तं|मुहूर्तः|मुहूर्त्त|मुहूर्त्तः
muhūrta (CII 3; IA 17), the thirtieth part of a mean day and night; equal to fortyeight minutes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुख|मुखं|मुखः
mukha (EI 22; LL), the face, the gate; a door.<BR> Cf. dāna-mukha (ML), the principal gift.<BR> (EI 16), used at the end of compounds in the sense of mukhya; ‘head’ ‘heading’ or ‘sum’. Cf. pañca-mukha-nagara.<BR> Cf. muha-patti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखकट्टण
mukha-kaṭṭaṇa (SITI), porch; also called darśana-kāṇikkai; front side of a building (SII 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखमण्डप
mukha-maṇḍapa, Tamil muga-maṇḍaka (SITI), the front hall in a temple; cf. mahāmaṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखमुद्रा
mukha-mudrā (EI 5), same as mauna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुक्ता
muktā (BL), epithet of a grant; a grant; possibly Arabic mukhta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुक्तिभूमि
mukti-bhūmi (EI 27, 30), a holy place where salvation is attainable on death.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुखाहार
mukh-āhāra, ‘principal food or meals’; same as mukhy-āhāra. See Sel. Ins., p. 162, text line 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुख्य|मुख्यः
Mukhya (EI 32), city elder; member of the city council. Cf. Hindī Mukhiyā, a village elder.<BR> (CII 1), chief officer.<BR> (EI 16), see mukha meaning ‘head’, ‘heading’ or ‘sum’. mukhy-āhāra, cf. mukh-āhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूक्कुत्ति
mūkkutti (ASLV), an ornament; the nose-screw.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूल|मूलं|मूलः
mūla (SITI), original; a document regarding a title to the property or right.<BR> (HRS), investment of capital which is one of the seven sources of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 26.<BR> (Sel. Ins., p. 163), seedling. Cf. sa-mūla (EI 13), a tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलभृत्य|मूलभृत्यः
Mūla-bhṛtya (SITI), the chief servant; also called Caṇḍeśvara who was the chief servant of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलगभारो
mūla-gabhāro (HA), Jain; same as garbha-gṛha; the sanctum where the Mūla-nāyaka is installed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलाइटन
mūlāiṭana (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलनायक
Mūla-nāyaka (BL), epithet of a Jain Tīrthaṅkara; Mahāvīra called ‘the Mūla-nāyaka of the Saṇḍeraka-gaccha’. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-206" target="_blank">Page-206+ 40</a>]<BR> (HA), the main deity in the sanctum of a shrine or in a devakulikā; also the central Jina in a sculpture representing a group of Jinas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=205" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलपरिषद्
mūla-pariṣad, cf. Tamil mūla-pariṣai (SITI), chief assembly [of a Śiva temple]; variously written in Tamil as mūla-paraḍai, mūla-paruḍai, mūla-pariḍai, mūla-paruṣai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलप्रकृति|मूलप्रकृतिः
Mūlaprakṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR> (EI 18), probably ‘the prominent subjects’ or ‘landlords’ or the six important officers styled Prakṛti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलरत्नभण्डरत्तार्
Mūlaratnabhaṇḍarattār (SII 2), Sanskrit Mūlaratnabhāṇḍārastha; treasures of the chief jewels.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलसङ्घ|मूलसंघ|मूलसंघः
Mūla-saṅgha (EI 16, 25), name of a Jain sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलस्थान
mūla-sthāna, cf. Tamil mūla-ttānam (SII 3; SITI; CITD), a place; the origin, base or foundation; the supreme spirit; the central shrine in a temple (SII 13); the place where the main image stands.<BR> (EI 18), an important seat of monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलवीस
mūla-vīsa (EI 6; ASLV), cf. Telugu-Kannaḍa vīsa, (1/16) of a haṇa (paṇa); name of a tax or levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलिआ
Mūliā (EI 31), Od̤iyā; a day-labourer; from Sanskrit Mūlika, possibly an abbreviation of Pādamūlika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूलुड
Mūl̤uḍa (LL), same as Mutuḍa or Muduḍa; probably, a village headman. Cf. Śīrṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूल्य|मूल्यं
mūlya (CII 3), an endowment; equivalent to akṣaya-nīvī, a perpetual endowment.<BR> (HRS), proceeds of sale of metal-ware manufactured in the government workshops, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुम्मुडि
Mummuḍi, cf. Mummuḍi-col̤̣a, ‘three times a Col̤a king’; cf. Nūrmaḍi and Immaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुम्मुरिदण्ड
mummuri-daṇḍa (ASLV), name of an organisation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुमोद
mumoda (EI 13), parasmaipada form instead of the expected ātmanepada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूना
Mū˚-nā˚ (PJS), contraction of Mūla-nāyaka, ‘the principal deity in a Jain temple’; often found in medieval Jain inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुण्डमोल
muṇḍamola (IE 8-5), cf. khaṇḍapāla-muṇḍamola (EI 24); name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुन्दिरि
mundiri (EI), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुनि|मुनिः
muni (SII 1; IA 30; LL), a Jain monk.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=206" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुरा
murā (EI 33), a measure of capacity; cf. muraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुरक
muraka (EI 9), a measure; cf. murā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूर्ति|मूर्तिः|मूर्त्ति|मूर्त्तिः
mūrti (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’; rarely used to indicate ‘eight’; but cf. rūpa used in the sense of ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुरुण्ड
Muruṇḍa (EI 14, 19), Śaka title of a chief; a title or tribal name; supposed to be derived from a Scythian word meaning ‘a king’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूसरवारु
Mūsara-vāru (CITD), Telugu; probably, goldsmiths or manufacturers of metallic objects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुष्टि|मुष्टिः
muṣṭi (IE 8-6), a handful.<BR> Cf. eka-muṣṭyā (LP), ‘at the same time’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुटक
muṭaka, mūṭaka (IE 8-5; EI 25), a measure or head-load; cf. caṇā-satka-mūṭaka, ‘one mūṭaka of peas’ (LP). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 303, text line 50; cf. moṭ (a load) in Hindī and other dialects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूटक|मूटकः
mūṭaka (LP), same as mūḍā, a measure of capacity equal to a hundred or twentyfour maunds; a bullock's load (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309; cf. Marāṭhī mūṭh, ‘a bullock's pack-saddle’).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुटी
mu-ṭī, abbreviation of an expression probably meaning ‘a mound covered with jungle’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुतिरिगै
mutirigai (IE 8-6), Tamil; a small land measure equal to (1/320) of a veli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुत्कलनीय
mutkalanīya (LP), ‘may be sent’; cf. Gujarātī mokalavuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुत्तावरण
muttāvaraṇa (EI 21), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुतुड
Mutuḍa (EI 27), also spelt as Muduḍa, Mul̤uḍa; probably, the headman of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नभस्
nabhas (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ना
nā, cf. nā-bhū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाभू
nā-bhū (IE 1), abbreviation of nāla-bhūmi, ‘cultivated land’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाड्
nāḍ (ASLV), same as nāḍu; a district; the assembly of a district; the professional association and guild of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नड|नडं|नडः
naḍa (IE 8-6), same as nala, a measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडगौड
Nāḍa-gauḍa, same as Nāḍu-gauḍa, Nār-gāvuṇḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडक
nāḍaka, same as nāḍuka (IE 8-4); same as nāḍ, nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडसेनबोव
Nāḍa-senabova (ASLV), officer in charge of the accounts of a nāḍu or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडी
nāḍī (IA 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=207" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नदीकूल
nadī-kūla (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नदीपाल
nadīpāla (HRS), fixed tax on villages situated upon the banks of rivers and lakes as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नदीतरस्थान|नदीतरस्थानं
nadītara-sthāna (IE 8-5), ferry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडीयक
nāḍīyaka (LP), same as aṇāḍīyaka; a place where the carts stand to dispose of goods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडु
nāḍu (IE 8-4; SII 1; SITI), a country; a territorial division; a district or a subdivision; the local assembly to govern the civic affairs of the division called nāḍu.<BR> (EI 31), a chamber.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुगौद
Nāḍu-gauḍa (ASLV), the head of an organisation relating to a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुक
nāḍuka (EI 12; ASLV), same as nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नग|नगः
naga (IE 8-1-2), ‘seven’; rarely used to indicate ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाग|नागं|नागः
nāga (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागदल
nāgadala (BL), meaning uncertain; cf. ‘a race subsisting on nāgadala’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागामावास्या
nāg-āmāvāsyā, cf. nāgara-amāvāsyā (EI 5), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगकार
Nagakāra (BL), wrong reading for Taṭṭhakāra, ‘a brazier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगर|नगरं
nagara (IE 8-4), city; palace; cf. navara.<BR> (EI 21; SITI), a commercial guild; guild of merchants; a mercantile town; often spelt in Kannaḍa inscriptions as nakara or nakhara; cf. pañca-nagara.<BR> (CITD), in Telugu inscriptions, a territorial assembly like the sabhā and ūr; the merchant community in general or the organization of the merchant community of a town. In some places, the nagara and ūr carried on their functions side by side. The word is sometimes used to indicate occupational groups like śāleyanagarattom. Cf. K. A. Nilakanta Sastri, The Col̤̣as, Vol. II, 1st ed., p. 294.<BR> (EI 4), same as Kaliṅga-nagara. Cf. śrī-Nagara-bhukti = Pāṭaliputra-bhukti (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 311).<BR> (IA 17), represented in Prakrit by nera further corrupted to ner or nar. See nagarī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगराधिकृत|नगराधिकृतः
Nagar-ādhikṛta (HD), the city prefect. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, IV. 81; VI. 70; VIII. 3334.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगराधिप|नगराधिपः
Nagar-ādhipa (HD), same as Nagar-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागरक|नागरकः
Nāgaraka (HD), same as Nāgarika; chief officer of the city; the city prefect of police. See Arthaśāstra, II. 36; Kāmasūtra, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-209" target="_blank">Page-209+ 40</a>] V. 5. 9 (the commentator explaining Nāgaraka as Daṇḍapāśika). Cf. Talavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=208" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगराक्षदर्श
Nagar-ākṣadarśa (LL), the city-judge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरमहल्लक
Nagara-mahallaka (EI 25), the City Elder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरपरिवार
nagara-parivāra (ASLV), an organisation relating to a town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरपति
Nagarapati (EI 12, 32; HD), the city prefect; ruler of a city. See Ind. Ant., Vol. IV, p. 35.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगररक्षक
Nagara-rakṣaka (IE 8-2), same as Talāra, Nagararakṣin, Nāgarika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगररक्षिन्
Nagara-rakṣin, same as Nagara-rakṣaka, etc; prefect of the city police (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 156-57).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरश्रेष्ठिन्
Nagara-śreṣṭhin (IE 8-3; EI 15, 21; BL; HD), according to some, the city banker or guild president of the town; but actually, the chairman of a board of administration like the Pañcāyat; same as the Nagarseṭh who was the chairman of the board called Cauthiyā in late medieval Rajasthan. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 115; Proc. IHC, Ahmadabad, 1954, pp. 52 ff. See Pura-śreṣṭhin, Pura-pradhāna, Śeṭṭi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरस्वामिन्
Nagara-svāmin (SITI), headman of the merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरत्तार्
Nagarattār (EI 30), Sanskrit Nagarastha; leading men of the city.<BR> (ASLV; SITI), members of a guild of a town; members of a mercantile guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरव्यवहारिक
Nagara-vyavahārika (IE 8-3; CII 1; HD), Prakrit Nagala-viyohālaka; judicial officer of a city; superintendent of the judicial affairs of a city; the city magistrate; also styled a Mahā-mātra. See Paura-vyavahārika (Arthaśāstra, I. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगरी
nagarī (IA 17), represented in Prakrit by nerī; further corrupted into nar. See nagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागरिक
Nāgarika (HD), chief of the police. See Vikramorvaśīya, V (after verse 4); Daśakumāracarita, II, pp. 58-59. The Vaijayantī explains the word as Kārāpati, the superintendent of jails.<BR> (ASLV), the chief bailiff or prefect at Vijayanagara. See also Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 95-96. Cf. Nagara-rakṣin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नगर्सेठ्
Nagar-seṭh (IE 8-3), Sanskrit Nagara-śreṣṭhin (q. v.); designation of the chairman of an administrative board called Cauthiyā in Western India. See Śeṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नागवन
nāga-vana (IE 8-4), an elephant-forest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=209" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नहरण
naharaṇa, a thief's weapon to dig a hole in the walls (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैधानीशिला
naidhānī-śilā (EI 32), a boundary pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैगम|नैगमः
Naigama, cf. Negama (EI 24; LL), the inhabitant of a nigama (township); a merchant. See Nigama-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैजायमान
naijāyamāna (LP), from nija; ‘when they are going to get themselves separated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैमित्तिक|नैमित्तिकं|नैमित्तिकः
Naimittika (EI 19, 26; HD), a soothsayer or astrologer. See Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैर्गमिक
nairgamika (IE 8-8; EI 30), exit tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैवेद्य|नैवेद्यं
naivedya (EI 30), daily offerings to gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैयामिक
Naiyāmika, Naiyamika (EI 24), also called Naiyāvika; a law officer or judge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैयोगिक
Naiyogika (IE 8-3; EI 12, 24), cf. Niyogika (EI 8), ‘an officer’; officer-in-charge of an administrative unit; same as Niyogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नैय्योक
Naiyyoka (EI 2), a mistake for Naiyogika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नकर
nakara, Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit nagara (q. v.); also spelt nakhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नख|नखं|नखः
nakha (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नखर|नखरं|नखरः
nakhara, Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit nagara (q. v.); also spelt nakara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाखुदा
Nākhudā Arabic; captain or commander of a ship (Ep. Ind. Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नक्षत्र|नक्षत्रं
nakṣatra (CII 3), a lunar mansion.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyseven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल|नलं|नलः
nala (IE 8-6), measuring rod; same as daṇḍa; sometimes regarded as 12 cubits, 22 cubits, 56 cubits, etc., in length; cf. Samataṭīya-nala, ‘the rod as used in the Samataṭa country’; Vṛṣabhaśaṅkara-nala, ‘the rod introduced by king Vṛṣabhaśaṅkara’, ‘the rod of the village of Pattiyamattavura’, etc. See kol, kolu, ghal̤e, etc.<BR> (IE 8-6), cf. aṣṭaka-navaka-nala, ṣaṭka-nala, etc., the first probably referring to the custom of measuring the length and breadth of a plot of land by rods of different length.<BR> (EI 28), used in some Orissan inscriptions in the sense of measurement of the area [of the gift land] (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20).<BR> (EI 21), a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नला
nalā, same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=210" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाल|नालं|नालः
nāla, cf. sa-khila-nāla (IE 8-5; EI 14); cultivated land; same as nāla-bhūmi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालभूमि
nāla-bhūmi (IE 8-1), cultivated land; see nāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालि|नालिः
nāl̤i, nāl̤̣i (EI 9, 28), a grain measure; same as nālikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालिका
nālikā (IE 8-6), same as Pali nālī or nāl̤i; regarded as the same as prastha, i. e. one-sixteenth of a droṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नालिकावाप
nālikāvāpa (IE 8-6; EI 31), a land measure; an area of land requiring one nālikā measure of seed grains for sowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नलु
nalu, nāluka (EI 7; CII 4), a measure of land; same as nalva; 400 (or 100 or 120) square cubits.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नामगृह
nāma-gṛha, cf. nāmghar (IA 25), Assamese; a place of worship of the Vaiṣṇavas, where plays, etc., are performed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमक
namaka (IA 18), name applied to the first section of the Rudrajapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नामकरण|नामकरणं
nāmakaraṇa (BL), naming ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नामलिङ्ग
nāma-liṅga (EI 15), a deity bearing the name of a person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमस्
namas (CII 3), ‘reverence’; an invocation, generally connected with the names of gods, at the commencement of inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमस्य|नमस्यः
namasya (IE 8-5; EI 5, 13, 28), same as mānya, sarva-namasya, namasya-vṛtti, etc.; a rent-free tenure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नमस्यवृत्ति
namasya-vṛtti (IE 8-5; EI 32), same as sarva-namasya, etc.; a tax-free holding.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणा
nāṇā (EI 30), name of a coin; same as nāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नानादेशि
nānādeśi (EI 31; SITI; ASLV), guild of merchants coming from outside.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणै
nāṇai (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 197, text line 18), same as Sanskrit nāṇaka; ‘a coin.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणक|नाणकं
nāṇaka, see nāṇai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नङ्ग|नंग|नंगः|नङ्गः
naṅga (IE 8-5; EI 25), cf. naṅge gṛhītasya yac=c=āṣṭau ṣoḍaśa vā nagara-mahallakā vicārya vadante tad=eva pranāṇam; a word of uncertain meaning; but a fine is prescribed for a merchant's son described as naṅge gṛhīta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणी
Nāṇī (CII 4), an engraver; probably a corruption^1 of Vijñānin.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्द|नंद|नंदः|नन्दः
nanda (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दादीप
nandā-dīpa, also called nandā-dīvigě (CITD); used in Telugu and Kannaḍa inscriptions in the sense of a lamp that is always kept burning before a deity in a temple; same as akhaṇḍa-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=211" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दवन
nandavana, nandāvana, cf. tiru-nandavanam, etc. (SII 1); a sacred flower-garden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दाविलक्कु
nandā-vil̤akku (SII 1, 2), also spelt as nondā˚, nundā˚; a perpetual lamp; same as nandā-dīpa, akhaṇḍa-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दीमुख
nandīmukha (CII 1), a species of water-birds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नान्दीसमारोहण
nāndī-samārohaṇa (EI 32), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नन्दीश्वराष्टमी
nandīśvar-āṣṭamī (SII 11-1), same as Phālguna-sudi 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नप्तृ
naptṛ (CII 1), a grandson.<BR> (EI 4, 9), a great-grandson.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नप्तृक
naptṛka, cf. natika (EI 22), a grandson.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नराधिपति|नराधिपतिः
Narādhipati (IA 15), royal title; same as Narapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नरपति|नरपतिः
Narapati (IE 8-2; EI 12, 19; HD; SITI), ‘lord of men’, ‘leader of the infantry’; title borne by the Col̤̣a monarchs; Vijayanagara rulers, etc., in view of the large infantry they possessed; cf. the titles Aśvapati and Gajapati, and also Aśvapati-gajapati-narapati-rāja-tray-ādhipati which was the title of some kings. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 7; JBORS, Vol. V, p. 588.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नरस्वामिन्
Narasvāmin, probably ‘a Jāgīrdār’; cf. ˚grāme mahattama-narasvāminaḥ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 51).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नार्गावुण्ड
Nār-gāvuṇḍa (EI 23, 27), village headman; also called Nāḍa-gauḍa; cf. Nār-gāvuṇḍa-svāmya-bhūta, ‘being in the possession of the Nār-gāvuṇḍas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नारिकेल|नारिकेलः
nārikela, cf. sa-guvāka-nārikela (EI 8-5); coconut palms [which the ordinary tenants had no right to enjoy].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नर्मसचिव|नर्मसचिवः|नर्म्मसचिव
Narma-saciva (EI 13), minister of amusement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नासत्य
Nāsatya (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्ट|नष्टः
naṣṭa (LP), disappeared.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्टभरट
naṣṭabharaṭa (HRS), name of a levy; same as naṣṭibharaṭa; (see Ep. Ind., Vol. III, note 4); may be ‘compensation for losses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्टराज्य
naṣṭa-rājya (IA 22), former rule of a dead king. Cf. also vinaṣṭa-rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्टिभरट
naṣṭibharaṭa (HRS), same as naṣṭabharaṭa; name of a levy (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 264, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नट|नटः
Naṭa (EI 31), a dancer; sometimes mentioned in the list of officials probably indicating ‘the chief dancer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाटकशाला
nāṭaka-śālā (SII 3; 11-1), a theatre hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाथ|नाथः
Nātha (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 313), same as Nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नट्टकार
Naṭṭakāra (BL), mistake for Taṭṭhakāra, a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टवर्
Nāṭṭavar (ASLV), Tamil; members of an organisation relating to a nāḍu or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=212" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्यशाला
nāṭya-śālā (EI 4), dance hall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौबलहस्त्यश्वगोमहिषाजाविकादिव्यापृत
Naubala-hasty-aśva-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādi-vyāpṛta (IE 8-3; EI 12), an officer in charge of the royal navy and cattle; looks like a combination of Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-naubala-vyāpṛtaka and Hasty-aśv-oṣṭra-go-mahiṣ-āj-āvik-ādi-vyāpṛtaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौदण्ड|नौदंड|नौदण्डः
naudaṇḍa, same as naupatha (IHQ, Vol. XXIII, pp. 255-56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौकाबन्ध
naukā-bandha (EI 32), a levy from the boatmen at landing places.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौकाध्यक्ष
Nauk-ādhyakṣa (IE 8-3), officer in charge of the navy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौकाभाटक
naukā-bhāṭaka (EI 14), charges for hiring a boat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौक्रम|नौक्रमः
nau-krama (EI 19), a bridge of boats or a ferry station.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौवाह|नौवाहः
Nauvāha (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 244), a ship-owner, mariner or captain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौवाटक
Nauvāṭaka (EI 24), a naval officer. Cf. Ardha-nauvāṭaka.<BR> (EI 15), probably, a wall (so to say) made of a large number of boats.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नौवित्तक
Nauvittaka, leader or owner of ships (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवचतुष्किका
nava-catuṣkikā, cf. nava-cokī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवचोकी
nava-cokī (HA), Sanskrit nava-catuṣkikā; a hall (open on three sides) adjacent to and in front of the gūḍha-maṇḍapa, so called because it is divided into nine sections by means of the pillars supporting its ceiling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नावः|नाव
nāvaḥ (HRS), charges for hiring royal boats; same as nau-bhāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकार
navakāra (HA), Sanskrit namaskāra; the chief Jain formula for worship or an obeissance to the arhats, siddhas, ācāryas, upā-dhyāyas and sādhus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मन्
nava-karman, cf. Tamil nava-karumam (SITI); renovation; repairs. Cf. Prakrit nava-kama (EI 20), foundation, extension or repairs to buildings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मपति
Navakarmapati (EI 22), an architect or the supervisor of building operations; same as Navakarmika and Navakarmin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मिक
Navakarmika (EI 16, 23; LL), superintendent of a work (possibly of repairs); cf. Navakamika (EI 4, 20), an overseer of work (building or repairing operations); superintendent of building operations. Cf. Navakarmapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवकर्मिन्
Navakarmin (ML), same as Navakarmika, the superintendent of a work. Cf. Navakarmapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=213" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवखण्ड
nava-khaṇḍa (IE 8-4), epithet of Bhārata or Bhāratavarṣa; see khaṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवमिका
navamikā (EI 9), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवाङ्ग|नवाङ्गः
navāṅga, cf. Pali navaṃga (EI 33); cf. navāṅga-Śāstṛ-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवनिधान
nava-nidhāna, cf. nava-nidhāna-sahita (IA 11), epithet of gift land; see Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, pp. 180 ff. (Inscriptions Nos. 4-11); explained as ‘new taxes imposed for the first time’; probably ‘a fresh assessment of tax’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवर
navara, Od̤iyā; same as Sanskrit nagara; capital city, palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवरत्न|नवरत्नं
nava-ratna (BL), the nine gems at Vikramāditya's court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवरात्र|नवरात्रं
navarātra, navarātri (EI 11, 25; CII 4), the festival of Durgā; Āśvina-sudi 1 to 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवरात्रिअमावास्या
navarātri-amāvāsyā (EI 5), new-moon preceding the nava-rātri; also called mahālayā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवतरभूमी
navatara-bhūmī (LP), land as yet uncultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवीनपञ्जिकाकरण
navīna-pañjikā-karaṇa (LP), probably, ‘to have new fences’, i. e. ‘to have additional land in one's possession.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नय|नयः
naya (EI 3), argumentation.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, pp. 318 ff, text lines 26-27), a territorial division like a Pargana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायक|नायकः
Nāyaka (EI 33; CII 4), a royal officer or ruling chief. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 142, text line 35.<BR> (HD), explained as ‘the head of ten villages.’ See Arthaśāstra, I. 12; Śukra, I. 192.<BR> (EI 32; BL), title of a subordinate ruler.<BR> (ASLV), one who held lands from the Vijayanagara kings on the condition of offering military service (cf. Amara-nāyaka).<BR> (EI 7), a general.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 313), head of a nāḍu or district.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायकनरक
nāyaka-naraka (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; the principal hell.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायकवाडि
Nāyakavāḍi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; watchmen stationed by the State or landlord to keep watch over the crops before or during harvest time; the inām granted to such persons was known as kākku-nāyaka-vil̤āgam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नयन|नयनं
nayana (IE 8-1-2), ‘two’; cf. netra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नायङ्कर
nāyaṅkara, nāyaṅkāra (EI 16; ASLV), the feudal system prevalent in the Vijayanagara kingdom, in which the Nāyakas [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-215" target="_blank">Page-215+ 40</a>] enjoyed royal land on condition of offering military service; see Nāyaka, Amara-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=214" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नयिनार्
Nayinār (IA 12), Tamil; the chief temple-servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नष्रान
nazrāna (EI 26), Persian; customary presents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेल्लायम्
nell-āyam (SII 1), Tamil, revenue in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेमक
nemaka (EI 1), probably, salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेत्र|नेत्रं
netra (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; in some areas of Eastern India, it was used in the sense of Hara-netra, ‘three’. The word dṛk seems to bear the sense of three in the Pamulavaka plates of Eastern Cālukya Vijayāditya VII (JAHRS, Vol. II, p. 287, text line 67).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेत्तरगोडग
nettara-goḍaga (ASLV), a kind of compensation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नि|निः
ni (IE 8-1; EI 33), abbreviation of nibaddha or nirīkṣita, i. e. registered or approved.<BR> (Select Inscriptions, pp. 238-39, 247-48), explained as an abbreviation of nija and as a sort of genitive suffix often with a word indicating relationship understood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नी
nī (LP), used for the verb ānī.<BR> (LP), to make.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबद्ध
nibaddha (IE 8-1; EI 29), explained as ‘registered’.<BR> (IA 13), used in respect of a copper-plate grant and translated as ‘prepared’.<BR> (IA 15), interpreted as ‘assigned’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबन्ध्|निबंध्
nibandh (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), to register.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबन्ध|निबंध|निबन्धं|निबंधः|निबन्धः
nibandha (EI 7), an endowment.<BR> (Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 49), a register.<BR> (SII 2), also spelt nivanda or nimanda in Tamil; the fixed requirements of a temple; cf. Nivandakkārar, temple servants who attend to the nibandha.<BR> (SII 3; SITI), expenses or arrangements; arrangement for the conduct of affairs in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निबरव
nibarava (CITD), Telugu; an unknown weight used in the case of salt and paddy (unhusked rice).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीच|नीचः
nīca (CII 1), mean or low.<BR> (CII 1), southern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीचोच्चमास
nīcocca-māsa (CII 3), the anomalistic month, the period in which the moon comes from perigee or apogee to the same point again; its duration is 27 days, 33 ghaṭīs and 16. 65 palas, or 27 tithis 59 ghaṭīs and 33. 36 palas; see also kendra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=215" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निदान|निदानं
nidāna (CITD), Telugu; same as Sanskrit nidhāna; a treasure; a hoard or fund; store, wealth or property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधान|निधानं
nidhāna (HRS), explained as ‘cess imposed upon agricultural land’; but ‘freshly assessed tax’; cf. nava-nidhāna. cf. sa-nidhi-nidhāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139, text line 20), in which it is the same as nikṣepa; also sa-vana-śvabhra-nidhāna; probably, a mine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधानालिपक
nidhān-ālipaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 274, text line 61), probably the same as nidhi-nikṣepa or nidhy-upanidhi. But ālipaka, also read as āliyaka and often spelt as ālīpaka, may refer to the right on beehives and honey (see alīpaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधि|निधिः
nidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR> Cf. nidhi-nikṣepa (IE 8-5; HRS; SITI); treasure trove; a treasure-hoard; hidden treasure under the ground; one of the eight kinds of enjoyments allowed to the donees of rent-free land. Cf. nidhāna.<BR> (CITD), a treasure; a repository^1; store; a place where anything is placed.<BR> Cf. nidhi-nikṣepa-jala-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣ-prakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247; text lines 101-02), privilege mentioned along with aṣṭabhoga-tejassvāmya-daṇḍaśulka-yukta.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निध्याप्ति
nidhyāpti, cf. Prakrit nijhati (EI 2; CII 1), explanation, exhortation or argumentation; to cause understanding; cf. anu-nidhyāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निध्यायन
nidhyāyana, cf. nijhati (CII 1); the act of explaining; argumentation [in favour of a particular view]; consolation. See nidhyāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निद्राकलस
nidrā-kalaśa, a pūrṇa-ghaṭa kept near the head of the bed (Matsya Purāṇa, 265. 14; Harṣacarita, IV).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निगमपुत्र
Nigama-putra (LL), inhabitant of a nigama (township); a merchant; cf. Naigama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निगमसभा
nigama-sabhā (EI 7, 8), a public hall or the assembly of the town Pañcāyat; the city council.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निग्रह|निग्रहः
nigraha (EI 27), ‘reducer’. Cf. also koṭṭa-nigraha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Nigrāhaka, tax-collector (Ghoshal, Ag. Syst., p. 25). cf. Koṭṭa-nigraha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=558" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निहेलपति
Nihelapati (IE 8-3; HD), official designation of uncertain import; probably, the governor of a territorial unit; also spelt Nihilapati. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 124; CII, Vol. III, p. 289.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निहिलपति
Nihilapati (IE 8-3; CII 3; HD), an official title of uncertain import. See Nihelapati. Cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 289.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निःसार|निःसारः
niḥsāra, cf. nissāreṇa (LP), ‘in an excellent manner.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=216" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निकर|निकरः
nikara (EI 12, 33), cf. yathādīyamāna-bhoga-bhāga-kara-nikara-ādikam; a small tax or cess; small amount of rent fixed for a gift land; practically the same as kara or tax (IHQ, Vol. XXXIV, p. 279). Cf. upakara, tṛṇodaka, mānya-kaṇikě, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निकाय|निकायः
nikāya (EI 7), a religious corporation.<BR> (EI 18; LL), a Buddhist school or community; a fraternity of Buddhist monks.<BR> Cf. Kaulika-nikāya (LL), a guild of the Kaulikas or weavers.<BR> (CII 1), a class or group.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निकेफोरोस्
Nikephoros (IE 8-2), Greek; royal title; ‘victorious’; translated into Prakrit-Sanskrit as Jayadhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निक्षेप|निक्षेपः
nikṣepa, cf. nidhi-nikṣepa (IE 8-5; HRS), deposits and finds on the soil (probably including beehives, cf. alīpaka, nidhāna); deposits; same as upanidhi; one of the eight kinds of enjoyment of the property allowed to the donees of rent-free land; sometimes wrongly explained as a treasure-trove (SITI). See nidhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीलडुम्फक
nīla-ḍumphaka (IE 8-8), probably, one whose profession was to press indigo plants for getting blue dye; ḍumphaka may be Sanskrit dṛmphaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीलकूटी
nīla-kūṭī (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, an indigo manufactory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निलय|निलयः
nilaya (EI 9), cf. grāma-nilaya-nāḍa-sarva-bādhā-parihāreṇa; probably a territorial unit like a Parganā; the inhabited area of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निमन्त्रण|निमंत्रण|निमंत्रणं|निमन्त्रणं
nimantraṇa (IA 20), explained as ‘an invitation which admits of no refusal’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निमित्त|निमित्तं
nimitta (SII 1), a sign.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निम्नोन्नत
nimn-onnata (IA 16), explained as ‘what is above and below’; but really, ‘low and high lands’; cf. khalla-unnata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निन्दन|निंदन|निंदनं|निन्दनं
nindana (LP), weeding out grass growing along with the crops; cf. Gujarātī nindavuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नि|निः
nin̤rair̤ai (EI 30), Tamil; permanent tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निपान|निपानं
nipāna, same as pāna, cf. grāma-nipāna-kūpaka (EI 4); ‘the drinking well of a village’; may also be the same as āpāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निप्रतिष्ठापित
nipratiṣṭhāpita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248), same as pratiṣṭhāpita; established, installed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीरगृह
nīra-gṛha (EI 31), ‘a water-house’; same as Persian abdār-khāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीराजन|नीराजनं
nīrājana (SII 1), the waving of a lamp before an idol; same as ārātrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=217" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरस्त|निरस्तः
nirasta, nirasti, cf. sarvajāta-bhoga-nirastyā (IE 8-5), ‘with all kinds of the [king's] rights renunciated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरवकर
niravakara (EI 31), used in some Orissan inscriptions in the sense of ‘the nett total after deductions’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरयण
nirayaṇa (CII 3), destitute of precession of the equinoxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्ग्रन्थ|निर्ग्रंथ|निर्ग्रन्थः
Nirgrantha (CII 1), a follower of the Jain religion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्ग्रन्थनाथ
Nirgranthanātha (BL), epithet of a Jain poet of the Digambara sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरीक्षित|निरीक्षितं
nirīkṣita (IE 8-1), same as ḍṛṣṭa, ‘examined [and approved]’. See ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्लक्षण|निर्लक्षणः
nirlakṣaṇa (CII 1), castration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीरोग
nīroga, the science of medicine (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 146).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूध्य
nirūdhya (LP), ‘up to’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीरुनेल
nīru-nela, nīr-nela (CITD), Telugu; low lying land irrigated by water from a tank, canal, well, etc.; usually called ‘wet land’ and considered the most valuable. Cf. veli-volamu or veli-cenu, i. e. land on a comparatively higher level, which depends solely on rain and is called ‘dry land’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूप
nirūpa (SITI), written order; communication from the king or other superiors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूप
Nirūpa (ASLV), the carrier of a royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूपण|निरूपणं
nirūpaṇa (LP), order for transfer of service; appointment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूपित|निरूपितः
nirūpita (LP), appointed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरूपितदण्ड
nirūpita-daṇḍa (IA 18), wrongly regarded as a doubtful technical expression; actually, ‘appointed as Daṇḍa (i. e. Daṇḍa-nāyaka)’. Cf. niyukta-Daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वचनीय
nirvacanīya, cf. bhoga-sambandha-nirvacanīya (EI 12), ‘the relations [of the gift land] with the district [to which it belonged] should not be reckoned’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वह्
nirvah, cf. nirvahanīya (LP), ‘should be observed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाह|निर्वाहः|निर्व्वाह|निर्व्वाहः
nirvāha, cf. vāśal-nirvāham (SITI), same as vāśal-kāriyam (kārya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाह|निर्वाहः|निर्व्वाह|निर्व्वाहः
Nirvāha (ASLV), probably, a manager.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाहसभा
nirvāha-sabhā (SITI), a managing or executive committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाण|निर्व्वाण|निर्व्वाणं|निर्व्वाणः
nirvāṇa (CII 3), annihilation of human passion; a stage in the Buddhist practices, anterior to parinirvāṇa or complete annihilation of personal existence by absorption into the all-pervading spirit.<BR> (HA), same as mokṣa; liberation from all bondage including [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-219" target="_blank">Page-219+ 40</a>] that of this earthly body; the death of the Jinas or monks who have obtained kevala-jñāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=218" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाणचैत्य
nirvāṇa-caitya (BL), name of the Buddhist memorial built at Kasia (ancient Kuśīnagara) in the Deoria District, where the Buddha obtained mahāparinirvāṇa (death).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वाप|निर्वापः|निर्व्वाप|निर्व्वापः
nirvāpa (EI 11), dole.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्वृत्ति|निर्वृत्तिः
nirvṛtti (ASLV), same as viṣaya or koṭṭam; an administrative division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्यामक|निर्यामकः
Niryāmaka (LP), probably, an officer who allowed licensed^1 articles to pass.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्यातित|निर्य्यातित
niryātita (CII 2-1; ML), given.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निर्योगक्षेम|निर्य्योगक्षेम
niryoga-kṣema (LP), ‘renouncing all claims’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशदम्
niśadam, also called niśadi (SII 1), supposed to be the same as nityam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशधि
niśadhi (EI 28), also spelt nisidhi, niṣidhi, niṣedhikā, etc.; the tomb of Jain monks. Cf. niśīdikā, etc. (Sanskrit niṣadyā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशदि
niśadi, cf. niśadam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषद्या
niṣadyā, cf. Prakrit nisidiyā (LL), a dwelling. Cf. niśliṣṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषेध|निषेधः
niṣedha (LP), same as vyāṣedha (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषेधिका
niṣedhikā (BL), memorial on the burial ground of Jain religious teachers; cf. nisidhi, etc.; also niśīdikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषिधि
niṣidhi, niśidhi, niśīdhi (IA 12), Jain; the tomb of Jain monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषीदी
niṣīdī (EI 20), a Jain tomb; cf. niṣīdhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निशीदिका
niśīdikā, also spelt niśīdigai (SITI), the death of a Jain by fasting; the memorial set up for such a person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निसिम
nisima (ML), Prakrit; supposed to be the same as stūpa; cf. nissīma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्क|निष्कं|निष्कः
niṣka (IE 8-8; EI 15, 27, 30), name of a gold coin; name sometimes applied to śatamāna, śāna, ṭaṅka, gaṇḍa-māḍa, etc.; cf. gaṇḍa-niṣka, also called gaṇḍa-māḍa. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 41 ff.<BR> (IE 8-8), a gold coin equal to sixteen silver drammas.<BR> (EI 5), a coin equal to a half-pagoda.<BR> (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 139), a silver coin equal to one śata-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्कावल
niṣkāvala (LP), a thing on which no one has any right; cf. Sanskrit kavala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निश्लिष्टक
niśliṣṭaka, Prakrit nisiḍhayā (CII 1), explained as ‘a rest-house’. But the correct reading is nisidiyā = Sanskrit niṣadyā (q. v.). See Nach. Akad. Wissen. Goetting., 1959, No. 4, pp. 47ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=219" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निश्रानिक्षेपहट्ट
niśrā-nikṣepa-haṭṭa (EI 11), probably, a place in the market for storing goods to be exported.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निस्सीम
nissīma (CII 2-1), explained as ‘a piece of land outside a monastery’. See nisima.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्ठापित
niṣṭhāpita, ‘caused to be completed’ (Sel. Ins., p. 224). Cf. nipratiṣthāpita, niṣṭhita.<BR> (LP), finished.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्ठित|निष्ठितं
niṣṭhita (Select Inscriptions, p. 203), completed. Cf. anuṣṭhita, niṣṭhāpita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नित्य|नित्यं|नित्यः
nitya (EI 19), compulsory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवन्द
nivanda (SITI), allocated duties of servants in temples; temple expenses; same as Sanskrit nibandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीवपात
nīva-pāta (LP), the falling of rain-water from the eaves; cf. Gujarātī nev or nevāṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवर्तन|निवर्त्तन
nivartana (IE 8-6; EI 21, 26, 28; CII 4), an area of land, which was not the same in different ages and localities^1. See Ind. Ep., pp. 409-10; also Matsya Purāṇa, 283. 14-15, representing a gocarman as (2/3) of a nivartana (210×210 sq. cubits).<BR> (CITD), same as mar̤uturu, the identification of the two being established by bilingual Sanskrit-Telugu inscriptions.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवर्तनिन्
nivartanin (CII 4), name of a land measure, same as nivartana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
nivāta see s-oṣar-āvaskara-sthāna-nivāta-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 22); same as āvāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=558" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेदनक
nivedanaka (EI 13), cf. Vāmanasvāmi-pādānāṃ nivedanaka-nimittam, ‘in order to be presented at the feet of Vāmanasvāmin.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेद्य|निवेद्यं
nivedya (EI 15), same as naivedya; the food offering to a god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेश|निवेशः
niveśa (EI 28), a house-site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेशन|निवेशनं
niveśana (LL), a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवेशित
niveśita (CII 1), written [on stone].<BR> Cf. prāsādo = yaṃ niveśitaḥ (Select Inscriptions, p. 295, text line 19); erected.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीवी
nīvī (EI 17), a permanent endowment; same as akṣaya-nīvī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीवीधर्म
nīvī-dharma (EI 15, 17; HRS), the custom regarding permanent endowments; the condition that the donee should not destroy the principal but should only enjoy the income arising from it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवीत|निवीतं|निवीतः
nivīta, cf. s-oṣar-āvaṣkara-sthāna-nivīta-lavaṇākara (EI 22).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निवृत्
nivṛt (EI 8), a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियतभोग
niyata-bhoga (EI 30), regular offerings to gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=220" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियतानियत
niyat-āniyata (IE 8-5), regular and fixed taxes and those which were occasional.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियायत्तार्
Niyāyattār (ASLV), Tamil; Sanskrit Nyāyastha; a judge. Cf. Nyāyattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोग|नियोगः
niyoga (EI 24; SITI), an appointment; authority; the officer bearing the same. Cf. Niyogin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगनियुक्त
Niyoga-niyukta (EI 23), cf. Niyogin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगस्थ
Niyogastha (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 11, text line 13), ‘an officer’; same as Niyog-niyukta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगि
Niyogi (ASLV), a class of Brāhmaṇas in the Telugu-speaking land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगिक
Niyogika (IE 8-3; EI 8, 25, 32), same as Niyogin or Naiyogika, ‘an officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियोगिन्
Niyogin (EI 5, 24, 30), same as Niyogika; ‘one having a niyoga’. Cf. Parameśvara-niyogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्त|नियुक्तः
Niyukta (IE 8-3; EI 12, 21, 24), official designation; same as Niyuktaka, Tanniyukta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्तदण्ड
niyukta-daṇḍa (IA 18), wrongly regarded as a doubtful technical expression; actually, ‘appointed as Daṇḍa (i. e. Daṇḍa-nāyaka’). Cf. nirūpita-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्तक
Niyuktaka (HD), probably, a subordinate officer under the Āyuktaka; same as Niyukta. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 84.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नियुक्तकाधिकारिक
Niyuktak-ādhikārika (EI 33), better Niyuktaka and Adhikārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नृत्यभोग
nṛtya-bhoga (SITI), same as Tamil śākkai-kkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नृप|नृपः
nṛpa (IE 7-1-2), ‘sixteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नूर्मडि
Nūrmaḍi (IE 8-2; SII 3), Kannaḍa, ‘hundred times’; word prefixed to the names of certain kings in order to distinguish them from their predecessors bearing the same name; e. g. Nūrmaḍi Taila, ‘one who is a hundredfold Taila’; cf. Savāi Jayasiṃha, ‘one and one-fourth of Jayasiṃha’. See Immaḍi and Mummuḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्याय|न्यायः
nyāya, cf. niyāyam (SII 2), an appointment or pledge.<BR> (SITI), body or association of persons having the same duties or interests.<BR> Cf. gardabha-cāṇḍāla-nyāyena (LP), ‘like a donkey or a Caṇḍāla’.<BR> Cf. khaṇḍa-badarīphala-nyāyena (LP), ‘like sugar and the badarī fruit’.<BR> Cf. śāka-phalaka-nyāyena (LP), ‘like vegetables and fruits’. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-222" target="_blank">Page-222+ 39</a>]<BR> Cf. vṛddhi-phala-bhoga-nyāya (LP), principle of enjoying the interest of a deposit; also cf. gṛhasya bhāḍakaṃ na hi; drammāṇāṃ vyājaṃ na hi; eṣa vṛddhi-phala-bhoga-nyāyaḥ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=221" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्यायकरणिक
Nyāya-karaṇika (EI 12), one responsible for settling disputes regarding the gift land.<BR> (BL), official designation of the writer of complaints or the scribe of the law-court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्यायत्तार्
Nyāyattār (SII 12; SITI), Sanskrit Nyāyastha; judges; members of the court of justice; a committee of judges. Cf. Niyāyattār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

न्यायवाद
nyāya-vāda (LP), a judgment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओडय
Oḍaya (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a king, ruler, master or leader.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओदयन्त्रिक
Odayantrika (CII 4), correctly Audayantrika; a manufacturer of hydraulic machines or, more probably, a person in charge of such a machine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओ
Od̤iyā, spelt as Oriya in English; people, language and alphabet of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओघो
ogho (HA), same as rajo-haraṇa; usually made of twisted woollen threads tied to a wooden handle, used by Jain monks and nuns, for removing dust particles and insects and for protecting the latter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओहोरु
ohoru (IE 8-5), Od̤iyā; cf. daṇḍoāsi-ohoru, ‘tax for the maintenance of watchmen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओज|ओजः
Oja (SII 11-1), same as Ojhā; designation derived from Sanskrit Upādhyāya; cf. Bengali Ojhā, Maithilī Jhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओकपिण्ड
okapiṇḍa (IA 18; CII 1), explained as ‘a fox’; probably, ‘household vermin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओलीपात
olīpāta (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओम्
om, the praṇava sometimes found at the commencement of inscriptions; often represented by a sign which should not be confused with the symbol standing for the auspicious word siddham.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओणी
oṇī (EI 27), a territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओण्टुदारु
Ŏṇṭudāru (EI 27), Telugu; a revenue officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओरिय
Oriya, same as Od̤iyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओष्ठ|ओष्ठः
oṣṭha (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओत
otad̤a, otad̤ā, otad̤ī (Chamba), dry land, unirrigable land; opposed to kohlī or āli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=222" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः
Pa (CITD), abbreviation of the Telugu name of a certain measure of grain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पा
Pā (EI 32), contraction of the surname Pāṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पा
pā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of pāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पबासण
pabāsaṇa (HA), the seat (āsana) on which the figure of a Jina is placed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पचन|पचनं|पचनः
pacana (LL), a cooking place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद|पदं|पदः
pada (EI 33), share; quarter of the standard land measure.<BR> (EI 4, 9; IA 17), a share.<BR> (EI 21), a land-measure; cf. paḍa (paṭa) in Sel. Ins. p. 408.<BR> Cf. sv-āṅgabhoga-pada (LP), ‘under the head of personal expenditure’.<BR> (LL; ML), foot-print.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाद|पादः
pāda (IE 8-6), same as Kannaḍa hāda; ‘one-fourth’; a measure equal to one-fourth of the standard land measure.<BR> Cf. poā (EI 19), literally, ‘one-fourth’; name of a land measure.<BR> Cf. sa-pādika (LP), ‘with one-fourth in addition’.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248), foot-print, foot-mark.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडा
paḍā, pāḍā (IE 8-4), corrupt forms of pāṭaka, ‘part of a village’; often suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादभक्त
Pāda-bhakta (IE 8-2), ‘devoted to the feet of’; cf. Pād-ānu-dhyāta and Pād-ānudhyāna-rata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादचारिन्
Pādacārin (CII 3), ‘moving on feet’; ‘personified’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडग
paḍaga (SITI), Tamil; name of a measure of land; cf. pāḍaga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडग
pāḍaga (IE 8-6), Tamil; same as Sanskrit pāṭaka; a land measure which was equal to 240 kul̤̣is, and 6(1/4) of which made one veli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादघट
pāda-ghaṭa (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडैक्काण्वर्
Paḍaikkāṇvar (ASLV), a military class.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडैपर्रु
paḍaipar̤r̤u (ASLV), a military station or cantonment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदका
padakā (Chamba), same as paduka; foot-print.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदकार|पदकारः
padakāra (IE 8-8), probably, a shoe-maker or a hawker (Hindī pāukār).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदक्क
padakka (ASLV), Tamil; a chest ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादकुल
pāda-kula (EI 12; IA 15), probably, ‘a tribe of attendants’, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-224" target="_blank">Page-224+ 40</a>] Pāda being the same as Pāḍamūla or Pādamūlika, ‘an attendant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=223" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदलेख्यक
pada-lekhyaka (LP), the ledger in which items of income are written.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडलिकै
paḍalikai (SITI), Sanskrit paṭalikā; name of a measure of quantity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादमूल|पादमूलं
Pādamūla (EI 12), an attendant.<BR> (EI 25), foot-prints.<BR> (EI 21), a sanctuary (p. 156; Sel. Ins., 2nd ed., p. 512).<BR> (SII 13), cf. pādamūlattār, temple servants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादमूलिक
Pādamūlika (EI 4; LL), a servant.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 156), a temple attendant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादानुध्यानरत
Pād-ānudhyāna-rata (IE 8-2), ‘engaged in meditating on the feet of … ’; cf. Pād-ānudhyāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादानुध्यात
Pād-ānudhyāta (IE 8-2; EI 2; CII 3), ‘meditating on the feet or favoured by the feet of … ’, a technical expression for the relations of a feudatory to his paramount sovereign, of a subordinate to a chief, of a successor to his predecessor, of a son to his parents, of a nephew to his uncle, of a grandson to his grandfather, and of a younger to his elder brother; used also in respect of gods. In rare cases, the word pāda is omitted. Cf. Pāda-bhakta and Pād-ānudhyāna-rata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपद्मोपजीविन्
Pāda-padm-opajīvin (CII 3; IA 18), ‘subsisting [like a bee] on the lotuses that are the feet of … ’; a technical expression (often occurring in medieval South Indian inscriptions) for the relations of a feudatory or officer to his master; cf. Pāda-piṇḍ-opajīvin, Pād-opajīvin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपाश|पादपाशः
pāda-pāśa (SITI), name of a foot-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपिण्डोपजीविन्
Pāda-piṇḍ-opajīvin (CII 3, etc.), ‘subsisting on the food supplied by the feet of … ’; a technical expression to denote the relationship of officials or subordinates to their master; same as Pād-opajīvin and Pāda-padm-opajīvin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपीठ|पादपीठं|पादपीठः
pāda-pīṭha (SII 2), a foot-stool.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादपुष्प
pāda-puṣpa (SITI), same as Sanskrit-Tamil pāda-kāṇaikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादरक्षा
pāda-rakṣā, cf. Tamil pāda-raṭcai (SITI), shoes; sandals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादशैव
Pādaśaiva (IA 12), designation of a conch-blower at the Rāmeśvaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादसङ्घाट
pāda-saṅghāṭa, a pair of feet (i. e. foot-prints). Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदातिजीव्य
padāti-jīvya (IE 8-5; EI 12, 29), also spelt padāti-jīva; tax for the maintenance of Pāiks; same as Od̤iyā pāikāli; cf. khaṇḍapāla [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-225" target="_blank">Page-225+ 40</a>] or khaṇḍapālīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=224" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदातिक|पदातिकः
Padātika (IE 8-3), modern Pāik (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादवक्काणि
pādava-kkāṇi (SITI), Tamil; land given as wage for temple service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदवार
padavāra (SITI), also called paduvāra; fee payable for exchanging landed property; transfer fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादावर्त|पादावर्तः|पादावर्त्त|पादावर्त्तः
pādāvarta (IE 8-6; EI 4, 21, 24; CII 3), a land measure, an area of 100 pādāvartas being 100 feet each way, i. e. 10,000 square feet; also spelt padāvarta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदवी
padavī (EI 24), ‘an office’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादविंशोपक
pāda-viṃśopaka (viṃśaka), see pāvīsā, paisā, viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडि
paḍi (EI 21), a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडिहार
Paḍihāra (BL), same as Sanskrit Pratīhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादिक
pādika, cf. Telugu-Kannaḍa pātika (CITD); one-fourth of anything; (1/64)th part of the coin termed pagoda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडिकावल्
pāḍikāval (ASLV), the right of policing, which was sometimes leased to people.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः
Pad̤irā, cf. Od̤iyā Sāmanta-pad̤irā (EI 32); Sanskrit Prati-rāja; title of a fendatory or governor; cf. Pratirājya = Pratirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादिशाह्
Pādiśāh^1 (IA 20), Persian; spelt Pādisāha, Pātisāha, etc., in Indian records; a [Muhammadan] emperor.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dhaval Patel on 20160121. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/CORRECTIONS/issues/243. note: sh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडियारि
Paḍiyāri (EI 27), Sanskrit Pratīhārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मबन्ध|पद्मबंध|पद्मबन्धः
padma-bandha (CITD), a kind of artificial composition of verses, in which the syllables are arranged in the form of a lotus. Cf. padma-vṛtta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मनिधि|पद्मनिधिः
padma-nidhi (IE 8-8), a sacred deposit made in the temple treasury. Cf. the coin called padmanidhi-malla-māḍa which was probably issued by the temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मपीठ
padma-pīṭha (SII 2), a lotus-pedestal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मासन|पद्मासनं|पद्मासनः
padm-āsana (IA 18), used to indicate ‘the sun’; cf. padma-sadman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मसद्मन्
padma-sadman (IA 18), used to indicate ‘the sun’; cf. padm-āsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मवृत्त
padma-vṛtta (CITD), probably, the same as padma-bandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादोनलक्ष
Pādonalakṣa (IE 8-4), name of a territory with reference to the number of villages in it; cf. Sapādalakṣa, Caurāśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादोपजीविन्
Pād-opajīvin (IA 18), same as Pāda-padm-opajīvin and Pāda-piṇḍ-opajīvin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्र|पद्रः
padra (IE 8-4; EI 24; CII 4), ‘a village’; often suffixed to the names of villages; see padraka. Cf. pādrīyaka (LP), those [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-226" target="_blank">Page-226+ 40</a>] living in the confines of a village.<BR> (IE 8-5), probably, ‘inhabited area’; may also be ‘common land’ (cf. padraka); cf. sa-padr-āraṇyaka as an epithet of a gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=225" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्रक
padraka (IE 8-4; CII 3; etc.); ‘a village’; generally used as the termination of the name of a village; interpreted as ‘common-land’ in expressions like Bhumbhusa-padraka and Śivaka-padraka. Wilson's Glossary explains pādar (i. e. padra) as ‘common-land, land adjacent to a village left uncultivated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुक
paduka (Chamba, etc.), sacred foot-prints; from Sanskrit pādukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुक|पादुकः
pāduka (EI 22; LL; HA), foot-prints. See pādukā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुका
pādukā (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 11), foot-prints.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुकपट्ट
pāduka-paṭṭa, pādukā-paṭṭa (LL), cf. Prakrit paduka-paṭa (EI 20), a foot-print slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादुकापट्टी
pādukā-paṭṭī, cf. Prakrit pājugā-paṭī (EI 24), a slab with foot-marks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुवार
paduvāra (SITI), same as padavāra (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाग
pāga (bhāga ?), cf. Kannaḍa hāga (EI 9), name of a coin.<BR> (IA 11), same as Kannaḍa hāga; one-fourth [of the revenue collected]; may be Sanskrit bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाघ्डी
pāghd̤ī, cf. talār-ābhāvya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पगोद्
pagod, pagoda (EI 8-8), also called ‘star pagoda’; English name of the gold coin called hūn (hon) or varāha; probably so called because the coins often bore the representation of a temple called pagod or pagoda by the early European travellers. The word seems to have been derived from Sanskrit bhagavat or bhagavatī meaning the deities worshipped in the temples and also often figuring on the coins. Cf. ‘ṭaṅkakas stamped with the figure of the Bhagavat’ (Bhandarkar's List, No. 2033).<BR> Cf. Cīna-pagoda (SII 12), ‘the Chinese temple’; name of a Buddhist shrine at Nāgapaṭṭanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाहुड
pāhuḍa, Sanskrit prābhṛta; cf. pāhuḍa-pramāṇena (LP), ‘in proportion to the gift given by him’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइक्
Pāik (IE 7-3; EI 33), Sanskrit Padātika; same as Bhaṭa or Bhaṭa-manuṣya; a footman; cf. Piāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइका
pāikā (IE 8-5; EI 29), Od̤iyā; also called pāikāli; same as padāti-jīvya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइकालि
pāikāli, see pāikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैकमु
paikamu (EI 6), Telugu; name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=226" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाइला
pāilā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 42), a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैण्डपातिक
Paiṇḍapātika (LL), a Buddhist mendicant; cf. piṇḍapāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैसा
paisā, used in Hindi, Bengali, etc., for pāvīsā or pāda-viṃśaka- (vimśopaka); ‘a copper coin’; ‘money’; also a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैटकिन्
Paiṭakin (LL), Buddhist; a teacher of the piṭakas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाकदण्ड
pāka-daṇḍa (EI 14), cf. Kannaḍa kir̤u-kula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाखी
pākhī (IE 8-6), Bengali; a land measure in parts of Bengal, which is smaller than the bīghā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पखिल
pakhila (IA 17), apparently a mistake for upakhila (q. v.); cf. sa-khilaṃ pakhilam wrongly read or written for sa-khil-opakhilam; semi-waste land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पक्ष|पक्षः
pakṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’; sometimes also ‘fifteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पक्षपात|पक्षपातः
pakṣa-pāta, ‘one who works on behalf of someone else’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 250).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पक्व|पक्वं
pakva, cf. pakva-pura, ‘a brick-built house’, same as Bengali pākā-bād̤i. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 184.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल|पलं|पलः
pala (EI 9, 21, 30; CII 3), name of a weight.<BR> (IA 26), a weight equal to 320 ratīs; sometimes spelt phala in Pāli.<BR> (CITD), in Telugu-Kannaḍa records, a weight equal to that of 10 pagodas; four karṣas or (1/100) of a tula; the 8th part of a ser, or 3 tolas or rupees; 4 tolas or 320 guñjās.<BR> (CII 3), the sixtieth division of a ghaṭī; equal to twenty-four English seconds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाला
pālā (LP), sheds.<BR> (LP), a foot-soldier; cf. Gujarātī pāl̤o.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालक|पालकः
pālaka (EI 3), cf. grāmasya pālakaḥ, ‘the headman of a village’.<BR> (Select Inscriptions, p. 236), escort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलकाय
pala-kāya (SITI), sundry spices as pepper, etc., used in preparing curry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलम्पुल्लिमाडै
pal̤ampul̤l̤i-māḍai (SITI), Tamil; name of an ancient coin; see māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलनियायम्
Palaniyāyam (EI 21), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालापन
pālāpana (LP), cf. Gujarātī pal̤āvavuṃ, ‘to compel to obey’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलार्ध
palārdha, weight equal to half of a pala (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालि|पालिः
Pāli, name of a language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाली
pālī (EI 3), embankment.<BR> (CII 3), a bridge.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=227" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिध्वज
pāli-dhvaja (EI 30, 32; CII 4), name of the banner of certain kings or dynasties, which was their royal insignia; same as pāli-ketana; sometimes explained as ‘flags in rows’ (SII 1). The expression pāli-ddhaya in Apabhraṃśa is explained as ‘small flags’ (Bhār. Vid., Vol. XXV, p. 34).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलिका
palikā, pālikā (EI 1, 11), same as pālī; a measure of capacity; measure of capacity for liquids (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिकेतन
pāli-ketana (EI 29; IA 7), name of the banner of certain kings or dynasties, which was their royal insignia; also called pāli-dhvaja, explained as ‘flags in rows’ (SII 1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिया
pāliyā (CII 4), Gujarātī; a memorial stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लडिका
pallaḍikā (IA 11, 18), cf. gṛhāṇāṃ pallaḍikā-sametā, an epithet of the gift land; probably, a cluster; sometimes referred to as property belonging to a deity (Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, pp. 180 ff., Inscriptions Nos. 5-11). Cf. ‘the entire pallaḍikā belonging to the god Vakuleśvaradeva and consisting of houses facing different directions’ and ‘another [pallaḍikā] which lay close to a two-storied temple’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 144-45).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लव|पल्लवं|पल्लवः
pallava (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्ली
pallī (IE 8-4; EI 23), ‘a hamlet’; ‘a village or its part’; often suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लि|पल्लिः
pal̤l̤i (SII 1, 2; SITI), Tamil; often, a Jain temple; the shrine of non-Hindu communities like the Jains, Buddhists, Christians, Muhammadans, etc.; cf. pal̤l̤i-ccandam, temple land; pal̤l̤i-grāma, a village belonging to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लीच्छन्द
pallī-cchanda, cf. pal̤l̤i-ccanda (EI 23, 24), ‘temple land’; ‘land granted to a Jain or Buddhist temple’; mentioned along with devadāna and brahmadeya; see pal̤l̤i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लिदेव
palli-deva (EI 29), a village deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्लिका
pallikā (EI 4), a village.<BR> (EI 31), a habitation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलोल
palola (IA 22), marshes or swamps.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पं|प|पः
Paṃ (IE 8-1; PJS), abbreviation of Paṇḍita.<BR> (PJS), abbreviation of Paṃnyāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण|पणः
paṇa (IE 8-8; EI 23, 24, 30; SII 11-1), same as Tamil paṇam, spelt in English as fanam; cf. Yādavarāyan-paṇam (SITI), name of a coin issued by the Yādavarāyas; name of a coin 80 ratis in weight; same as the copper kārsāpaṇa; equal to 80 cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī; copper coin (1/16) of a silver kārṣāpaṇa according to the Kṛtyakalpataru (Vyavahāra-kāṇḍa, ed. K.V. Rangaswami Aiyangar, p. 125), and (1/48) of a [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-229" target="_blank">Page-229+ 40</a>] suvarṇa (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 7); also used to indicate ‘money’. In Tamil, paṇam means a particular coin (usually, a small gold coin), or money in general, or taxes; cf. paṇa-vargam (SITI), a class of taxes payable in cash, same as kāśāya-vargam; also paṇa-vāśi, ‘discount payable for the exchange of coins; amount payable to make up the wear in the coin’. Cf. vil-paṇam (SITI), sale-tax; also understood as a tax on bows or archery; vāśal-paṇam (SITI), door-tax or periodical payment due to the palace.<BR> (ASLV), a sect or caste, eighteen in number theoretically.<BR> (EI 19), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=228" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणक
pāṇaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309), small quantity of a liquid; name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणपुराण
paṇa-purāṇa (IE 8-8), a purāṇa [of silver] counted in paṇas [of copper]. Cf. kapardaka-purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणव|पणवः
paṇava (EI 24), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणविक
Pāṇavika, one who plays on the paṇava (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 241).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्च|पंच
pañca (EI 22, 23), abbreviation of pañcakula; same as Mahājana; a Pañcāyat Board.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाचार्य
Pañc-ācārya (SITI), a temple priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चधार
pañcadhāra (CITD), the five paces of a horse called dhorita, valgita, pluta, uttejita and utterita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाधिकरणोपरिक
Pañc-ādhikaraṇ-oparika (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 29; BL), official designation; cf. Pañca-karaṇ-oparika and Pañca-karaṇ-ādhikṛta; the head of five departments; sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pāṭy-uparika and Purapāl-oparika, additionally. See Sapt-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चद्रव्य
pañca-dravya (SITI), five articles used in bathing an idol.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चगव्य|पंचगव्य|पञ्चगव्यं
pañca-gavya (SITI), same as Tamil ān-āñju; the five products of the cow, viz., milk, butter, curds, urine and dung.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाञ्चाहण
Pāñcāhaṇa, Pāñcāhaṇaṃvāru (ASLV), same as Pāñcāl̤a.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाञ्चक
pāñcaka (CII 3), a committee. See pañca-maṇḍalī and pañcakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चक|पंचक|पञ्चकं|पञ्चकः
pañcaka (CII 4), same as Pañcāyat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकल्पिन्
Pañcakalpin (EI 9), same as Pañcolī; title and family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकरणाधिकृत
Pañcakaraṇ-ādhikṛta (EI 30), head of five departments; cf. Pañcakaraṇ-oparika, etc. See Saptā-mātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकरणोपरिक
Pañcakaraṇ-oparika (EI 29), same as Pañcādhikaraṇ-oparika, etc.; head of five departments. See Sapt-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=229" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकर्मार
pañca-karmāra, also called pañca-kammāl̤ar (SITI), the five castes of artisans, viz., goldsmith, blacksmith, brassmith, carpenter and stone-mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकशालाप्रत्या
pañcaka-śālā-pratyā (LP), ‘at five per cent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चकुल
pañcakula (IE 8-3; EI 5, 25; CII 4; LP; HRS), the Pañcāyat Board; an assembly of administrators and arbitrators, usually consisting of five members; a board of administration charged with control of the customs house, with the deposit of property of persons dying without heirs into the royal treasury, etc.; also called pañcapa (EI 4); members of such a board; according to some, an officer over a certain number of villages (HD). Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 242. Cf. Pañcavīra, Pāñca-kulika, añjaṣṭa-sabhā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाञ्चकुलिक
Pāñcakulika (CII 4), the head or a member of a pañcakula or Pañcāyat board; cf. Caturjātakīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाल|पंचाल|पञ्चालः
Pañcāla (EI 3; ASLV), an artisan; members of the artisan classes also called Pāñcāl̤aṃvāru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चलगुडिक
Pañca-laguḍika (BL), title of a warrior who could probably fight with five clubs at a time.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चलाङ्गल
pañcalāṅgala (IA 18), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चालत्तार्
Pañcāl̤attār (ASLV), an organisation of the artisans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाली
Pañcālī (IA 10), same as Pañcālikā; a Pañcāyat board or its members. Bengali pāñcālī is a kind of versified composition so called probably because it was originally sung either before the members of the Pañcāyat board or at puppet shows.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाली
pañcālī (EI 27; IA 16), territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चालिका
Pañcālikā (IA 9), same as Pañcālī; a Pañcāyat board or its members.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहापातक|पंचमहापातक
pañca-mahāpātaka (EI 26; CII 3; CITD), the five great sins or heinous crimes, viz., killing a Brāhmaṇa, drinking intoxicating liquors, stealing gold, committing adultery with the wife of a guru and associating with any one guilty of these crimes. Cf. daś-āparādha, pañc-ānantarya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहाशब्द
pañca-mahāśabda (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4; SITI; CITD; BL), refers to the privilege of enjoying the sounds of five musical instruments, or five titles beginning with mahat; five official designations or musical instruments mentioned in connection with feudatories; five official designations beginning with the word mahā in the North and five kinds of musical instruments in the South; in South India, it was the same as pañca-mahānināda, i. e. the sounds of the five great musical instruments called the pañca-mahāvādya enumerated by some as a [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-231" target="_blank">Page-231+ 40</a>] horn, a tabor, a conch-shell, a kettle-drum and a gong; in some parts of North India, the expression indicated five official designations with the prefix mahā.<BR> (CII 3), sounds of five musical instruments, the use of which was allowed to persons of high rank and authority; usually a title of feudatories; cf. tat-pradatta-pañcamahāśabda (IE 8-2), used in respect of feudatory rulers who received the right of enjoying the pañca-mahāśabda from their overlords; rarely used in the South by independent monarchs. Cf. pañca-vādya (EI 4) and pañca-mahāvādya. See Samadhigata-pañcamahāśabda, etc.<BR> Cf. pañca-māśattam (SITI), the five musical instruments, to the use of which a nobleman was entitled; sometimes enumerated as ceṇḍai, timilai, śegaṇḍi, cymbals and kāhal̤am or as tattal̤i, maddal̤i, karal̤ikai, cymbals and kāhal̤am.<BR> (SII 11-1), cf. grant of 40 mattars of land to a piper for arranging to play the five musical instruments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=230" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहावाद्य
pañca-mahāvādya (EI 12), enumerated as the horn, conch-shell, tambourine, trumpet and gong. See pañca-mahāśabda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमहायज्ञ|पंचमहायज्ञ
pañca-mahāyajña (EI 29; CII 3, 4), ‘the five great sacrifices’; the five daily duties of a Brāhmaṇa enumerated as bali, caru, vaiśvadeva, agnihotra and atithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमलोकपाल
Pañcama-lokapāla (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 93), epithet of certain kings; cf. Lokapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमण्डली
pañca-maṇḍalī (CII 3, 4; HD), an assembly of five persons; equivalent to the modern Pañcāit, Pañcāyat or Pañc, i. e., a village jury. See pāñcaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमातृका
pañca-mātṛkā, cf. Prakrit paṃca-mātuka (EI 20), five principal texts of the Buddhists, also called pañca-nikāya, viz., the Dīgha-nikāya, Majjhima-nikāya, Aṅguttara-nikāya, Khuddaka-nikāya and Saṃyutta-nikāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमौष्टिकलोच
pañca-mauṣṭika-loca (HA), plucking out five handfuls of hair by a would-be Jina at the time of dīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमीबलि
pañcamī-bali (EI 11), a particular tithi of the year.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चामृत|पंचामृत|पञ्चामृतं
pañc-āmṛta (SITI), mixture of five objects for anointing idols, viz. banana, honey, sugar, ghee and grape.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चमुखनगर
pañca-mukha-nagara (LP), explained as ‘a city in which there are five leading men’; cf. pañca-mukha-nagara-viditam (LP), ‘having informed the five leading men of the city’; explained as ‘the five-fold people of the town’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XLI, p. 20); really ‘the citizens headed by the members of the Pañcāyat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=231" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चनगर
pañca-nagara, a mercantile guild (cf. nagara, also pañca); see A. R. Ep., 1956-57, No. B 190.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चनैकायिक
Pañcanaikāyika (LL), Buddhist; a teacher of the five nikāyas (e. g. Dīgha-nikāya, Majjhima-nikāya, Khuddaka-nikāya, Saṃyutta-nikaya and Aṅguttara-nikāya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चानन्तर्य
pañc-ānantarya (CII 3), the five sins that entail immediate retribution. See pañca-mahāpātaka, daś-āparādha, pañc-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाङ्ग|पंचांग|पञ्चाङ्गं|पञ्चाङ्गः
pañcāṅga (CII 3), the Hindu almanac; in the Deccan and in some other parts, the pañcāṅgas are now prepared from the Grahalāghava and the Tithicintāmaṇi of Gaṇeśa-daivajña. The right of reading the pañcāṅga was sometimes granted by the rulers to individuals (ASLV).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाङ्गनमस्कार
pañcāṅga-namaskāra (HA), bowing down in such a way that five limbs of the body (viz., two hands, two knees and the head) touch the ground. Cf. aṣṭ-āṅga-namaskāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाङ्गप्रसाद
pañcāṅga-prasāda, cf. pañcāṅga-pasāya (Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 95), translated as ‘five manners of gifts’; cf. pañcāṅga-pasāya chatra sukhāsana bbala gaddi aṅka-daṇḍa-khaṇḍane, translated as ‘gave [to that Māro-śěṭṭi] five manners of gifts--an umbrella, a palanquin, an escort, a throne and with the faults, fines and divisions (really ‘with fines and the grain share’).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
pañcāṅgula, impression the plam with outstretched fingers dipped in sandal paste or any such thing; also called Pañcāṅgulika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चप
pañcapa (EI 4), same as pañcakula (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चापराध
pañc-āparādha (HRS), known from the Gupta and other records; donee's privilege relating to the enjoyment of fines payable by persons committing five offences. Cf. daś-āparādha, pañc-ānantarya, pañca-mahāpātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चपरमेष्ठिपद
pañcaparameṣṭhi-pada (EI 2), also called ˚paṭṭa; a slab for worship containing the oṅkāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चपाठिन्
Pañcapāṭhin (EI 32), epithet or family name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चपात्र|पंचपात्र|पञ्चपात्रं
pañca-pātra (SITI), literally, ‘a vessel made of five [metals]’; offerings of food made to a deity along with cooked rice; probably the same as pañca-bhakṣya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चार्थ
Pañcārtha (CII 4), the Pāśupata sect of the Śaivas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चार्थिक
Pañcārthika, Pāñcārthika (CII 4; IA 18), same as Pañcārtha, the Pāśupata sect of the Śaivas; a follower of the Pāśupata sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चरत्न|पंचरत्न|पञ्चरत्नं
pañca-ratna (EI 19), a group of five stanzas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चशब्द
pañca-śabda (CII 4; BL), five [musical] sounds or five official designations [beginning with the word mahā]; same as pañca-mahāśabda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाशत्|पंचाशत्
pañcāśat, see pannasa, pannāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=232" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चाष्टकुल
pañc-āṣṭa-kula, see añjaṣṭa-sabhai (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चस्तूपनिकायिक
Pañcastūpanikāyika (BL), epithet of a Jain religious teacher. See Pañcanaikāyika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवाद्य
pañca-vādya (EI 4), cf. pañca-mahāśabda, pañca-mahāvādya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवार
pañca-vāra (EI 23), a tax; cf. pañcavāri, pañcupīli, etc.; also pañca-vāram (SITI), one-fifth of the produce due to the government as land-revenue.<BR> (SITI), five branches in the administration of big villages, each looked after by a committee called pañcavāra-vāriyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चविंशति|पंचविंशति|पञ्चविंशतिः
pañcaviṃśati, see pannavīsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवीर
pañca-vīra (EI 24), also called pañcavīra-goṣṭhī; an administrative board of five members; cf. pañcakula. Also 5 deified heroes of the Vṛṣṇi clan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चायत्
pañcāyat (EI 26), a board of administration usually consisting of five members; cf. pañcakula, pañcavīra, pañcāyati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चायति
pañcāyati (IE 8-3), an administrative board consisting of five members; same as pañcāyat, pañcakula, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चायतन
pañc-āyatana (EI 28; CII 4), a type of temple ‘consisting of five rooms’; a five-shrine temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चिक
Pañcika (EI 1), a member of the pañcakula or Pañcāyat board.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चीयकद्रम्म
pañcīyaka-dramma (EI 1; CII 4), name of a coin. It is uncertain whether it was so called owing to its issue by some Pañcāyat board or because it was equal to five copper coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चोली
pañcolī (HD), same as pañcakula. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 89.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चुपीलि
pañcupīli (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डा
Pāṇḍā (EI 32), a temple superintendent; same as Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्डारवाडै
paṇḍāravāḍai (ASLV), crown lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डव|पांडव|पांडवः|पाण्डवः
pāṇḍava (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्डित|पंडित|पण्डितः
Paṇḍita (HD), same as Dharmatattvavit according to Śukra, II. 85; head of the ecclesiastical department (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 115).<BR> (CII 4), epithet of Brāhmaṇas.<BR> (IE 8-3), the court Pandit, mentioned as Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डुलेख|पांडुलेख|पाण्डुलेखः
pāṇḍu-lekha, pāṇḍu-lekhya (IE 3-5), chalk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डुसुत
pāṇḍu-suta, cf. pāṇḍava (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्ग
paṅga, pāṅga (IE 8-5; EI 30, 33), Telugu-Kannaḍa; one-fourth of the produce sometimes collected from rent-free holdings in the possession of gods and Brāhmaṇas; a kind of tax; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-234" target="_blank">Page-234+ 40</a>] sometimes used to indicate ‘taxes in general’; cf. paṅga-śulka, paṅga-tappu, paṅga-tappu-śulka, paṅga-parihṛta, paṅga-parihṛta-parihāra, sarva-paṅga-parihṛta, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, pp. 54 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=233" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्गतप्पु
paṅga-tappu (IE 8-5), probably, interest or fine on arrears of paṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्गोत्कोट
paṅg-otkoṭa (EI 33), see paṅga and utkoṭa, names of levies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्गु|पंगु|पङ्गुः
paṅgu (EI 33), a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणि|पाणिः
pāṇi, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणिग्राहिन्
Pāṇigrāhin (EI 26), Od̤iyā; Sanskrit Pānīya-grāhin, ‘one who receives water’; the principal donee who received the water on behalf of all the other donees of a gift village; stereotyped as a family name in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयभाजन
pānīya-bhājana (LL), a water-cistern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयछायामण्डप
pānīya-chāyā-maṇḍapa (EI 28), probably, a shaded hall cooled by water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयागारिक
Pānīyāgārika (IE 8-3), superintendent of the water-chamber. See Pānīyagṛhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयग्राहिन्
Pānīya-grāhin (EI 31), ‘one who receives ceremonial water as the donee of a gift’; recipient of a grant. See Pāṇigrāhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयगृहिक
Pānīyagṛhika (LL), superintendent of a water-house. Cf. Pānīyāgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पानीयक
pānīyaka (LL), a cistern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्जाबी
Pañjābī, name of the language of the Pañjāb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्क|पंक|पंकं|पंकः|पङ्कः
paṅka (EI 33), a share; cf. paṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पङ्क्ति|पंक्ति|पंक्तिः|पङ्क्तिः
paṅkti (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नस
pannasa, also spelt pannāsa, pannāsu (IE 8-6; EI 5, 12; Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 336, note 3), Kannaḍa; probably derived from Sanskrit pañchāśat in the sense of a tenure in which the donee enjoyed fifty per cent of the revenue of the donated land. Cf. pannavīsa. (EI 20), explained as ‘a gift’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नास
pannāsa (EI 30; IA 11), Kannaḍa; same as pannasa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नासु
pannāsu (IA 10), Kannaḍa; same as pannasa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नवीस
pannavīsa (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, No. B. 17), Kannaḍa; Sanskrit pañcaviṃśati; probably a tenure in which the donee enjoyed twentyfive per cent of the revenue of the donated land. Cf. pannāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नाय
pannāya (IE 8-5; EI 27), Kannaḍa, name of a tax; cf. pannāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नायदसुङ्कवेर्गडे
Pannāyadasuṅkavěrgaḍě (SII 11-2), Kannaḍa; official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=234" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पान्थशाला
pāntha-śālā (CII 4), a sarāi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्यसंस्था
paṇya-saṃsthā (HRS), various dues collected for the king by the superintendent of the market and the superintendent of merchandise, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 76.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पापनाशिनी
pāpanāśinī (IA 26), the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर|परं|परः
Para, abbreviation of a modified form of Purohita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर|परं|परः
para (LL), possibly, the chief.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार|पारं|पारः
pāra, cf. a-pār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE 8-5); probably, [free] ferrying of rivers [by the royal officers], which the villagers were obliged to provide.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परब्रह्मन्
parabrahman (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परदत्ति
paradatti (SII 2), Tamil; an assembly; cf. Tamil paraḍai= Sanskrit pariṣad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परदेशिन्
Para-deśin (SITI; CITD), an outsider; an emigrant; used along with Sva-deśin (i. e. native), while mentioning two classes of merchants or their respective guilds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परगना
paraganā (Chamba, etc.), parganā; a territorial division; subdivision of a district, same as pratijāgaraṇaka of the Paramāra charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिकाल्
Parakesari-kāl (EI 30), Tamil; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिक्कल्
Parakesari-kkal (EI 30), Tamil; name of a weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिना
Parakesari-nāl̤i (EI 30), Tamil; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकेसरिउळक्कु
Parakesari-ul̤̣akku (EI 30), Tamil; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पराख्य
parākhya (CII 3), a correction in time, to be applied to the mean tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परकोणा
parakoṇā (EI 31), probably, the same as parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पराक्रम्
parākram (CII 1), ‘to make an effort’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पराक्रम|पराक्रमः
parākrama (CII 1), an effort; zealous activity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभागवत
Parama-bhāgavata (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3), ‘highly devoted to the Bhagavat (Viṣṇu)’, epithet of the followers of the Bhāgavata form of Vaiṣṇavism; cf. Paramavaiṣṇava (highly devoted to Viṣṇu), etc. See Atyanta-bhagavad-bhaktā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभगवतीभक्त
Parama-bhagavatī-bhakta (IE 8-2), ‘a devout worshipper of the goddess Bhagavatī (Śiva's consort)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभट्टारक
Paramabhaṭṭāraka (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4), one of the technical titles of paramount sovereignty, closely connected with Mahārājādhirāja and Parameśvara; sometimes applied to a priest (generally of the Śaiva order); cf. Paramabhaṭṭārak-ety-ādi-rājāvalī [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-236" target="_blank">Page-236+ 40</a>] (IA 19); also Paramabhaṭṭārak-etyādi-rājāvalī-tray-opeta (IE 8-2), ‘endowed with the three royal titles beginning with Paramabhaṭṭāraka.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=235" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमभट्टारिका
Paramabhaṭṭārikā (IE 8-2; EI 6, 7; CII 3), a title of the wives of paramount sovereigns and of ruling queens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमब्रह्मण्य
Parama-brahmaṇya (IE 8-2; EI 29), probably not ‘highly devoted to the god Brahman’, but ‘highly devoted to the Brāhmaṇas’; epithet of certain Brāhmanical rulers. See Atibrahmaṇya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदैवत
Parama-daivata (IE 8-2; EI 28, 30; BL), ‘highly devoted to the god (i. e. Viṣṇu)’; epithet of Vaiṣṇava rulers; epithet of a devotee of the Brahmanical gods. Cf. Parama-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata, Parama-guru-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata-viśeṣa (EI 28), epithets of pious rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदैवताधिदैवत
Parama-daivat-ādhidaivata (EI 23), same as Parama-de(dai)-vatādhidaivata (q. v.); epithet of pious kings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदेवताधिदैवत
Parama-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata (IE 8-2; EI 23), ‘one who is a great devotee of the various gods and of the supreme god’; see Paramadaivata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदेवी
Paramadevī (IE 8-2; CII 3), designation of the chief queen; cf. Devī, Mahādevī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमदीक्षीत
Paramadīkṣīta (EI 26), see Dīkṣita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमादित्यभक्त
Param-āditya-bhakta (IE 8-2; CII 3), ‘a devout worshipper of the Sun-god’; cf. Parama-saura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमगुरु
Parama-guru (EI 31, 33), ‘the supreme teacher [of the subjects]’; royal title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमगुरुदेवताधिदैवतविशेष
Parama-guru-de(dai)vat-ādhidaivata-viśeṣa (IE 8-2), ‘one who is a great teacher to his subjects and is devoted to the various gods and of the supreme deity’; see Parama-daivata and Paramade(dai)vat-ādhidaivata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमहंस|परमहंसः
Paramahaṃsa (EI 5; BL), an ascetic; epithet of an ascetic. See Haṃsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परममाहेश्वर
Parama-māheśvara (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3, 4), a devout worshipper of Maheśvara (Śiva)’; epithet of Śaiva rulers; see Māheśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमनारसिंह
Parama-nārasiṃha (IE 8-2; EI 26), ‘highly devoted to the man-lion incarnation of Viṣṇu’; epithet of a devotee of the man-lion form of Viṣṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमपाशुपताचार्य
Parama-pāśupat-ācārya (BL), epithet of a Śaiva religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमराज|परमराजः
Paramarāja (EI 31, 33), royal title. See Paramarājādhirāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=236" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमराजाधिराज
Paramarājādhirāja, royal title. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 219; cf. Paramarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमसौगत
Parama-saugata (IE 8-2; EI 29; CII 3; BL), ‘a devout worshipper of the Sugata (Buddha)’; cf. Parama-tāthāgata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमसौर
Parama-saura (IE 8-2), ‘a devout worshipper of the Sun-god’; cf. Param-āditya-bhakta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमस्वामिन्
Parama-svāmin (EI 28; SII 3), epithet of deities.<BR> (EI 3), title of an imperial ruler; an overlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमलाथागत
Parama-tāthāgata (IE 8-2; EI 29; BL), ‘a devout worshipper of the Tathāgata (Buddha)’; usually spelt Parama-tathāgata; cf. Parama-saugata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमवैष्णव
Parama-vaiṣṇava (IE 8-2; EI 30; CII 3, 4), ‘highly devoted to Viṣṇu’; epithet of Vaiṣṇava rulers; cf. Parama-bhāgavata, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमविश्वासिन्
Parama-viśvāsin (IE 8-3), probably, a private secretary; same as Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.; sometimes called Mahāpradhāna, Sarvādhikārin, etc., additionally. See Vaiśvāsika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेष्ठिगद्याण
parameṣṭhi-gadyāṇa (SII, Vol. IX, Part i, No. 68), cf. gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वर|परमेश्वरः
Parameśvara (IE 8-2; EI 29, 30; CII 3, 4), an imperial title; one of the technical titles of paramount sovereignty closely connected with Māhārājādhirāja and Paramabhaṭṭāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरहस्त
parameśvara-hasta (SII 2), the royal cubit; cubit measured according to the length of the king's forearm. Cf. śrīpāda-kol.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरमहाकोष्ठकारिन्
Parameśvara-mahākoṣṭhakārin (EI 27), officer in charge of the royal treasury or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरनियोगिन्
Parameśvara-niyogin (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 9), a special officer attached to the king. Cf. Niyogin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरेत्यादि
Parameśvar-ety-ādi (IE 8-2), shortened form of Parameśvar-ety-ādi-raj-āvalī-tray-opeta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेश्वरी
Parameśvarī (EI 6), title of a queen, especially a ruling queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमोपासक
Param-opāsaka (BL; LL), epithet of a male member of the Buddhist laity; cf. upāsaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमोपासिका
Param-opāsikā (EI 22, 32; LL; BL), epithet of a female member of the Buddhist laity; cf. upāsikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारम्पर
pārampara (EI 15), same as paramparā-balīvarda-grahaṇa; refers to the obligation of the villagers to supply bullocks in succession for the cart of a royal agent on tour in their villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परम्परा|परंपरा
paramparā, cf. a-paramparā-balīvarda (IE 8-5); ‘succession’; refers to the obligation of the villagers to supply bullocks for the cart of the touring officers visiting different villages in succession.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=237" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारशव|पारशवः
Pāraśava (BL), name of a community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारसीक|पारसीकः
Pārasīka (EI 12), originally, a Persian; but used to indicate any foreigner; a Dutch in the present case.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारसि
Pārasi, Pārasī, Pārasika (EI 5; SII 1), a Persian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारशिव
Pāraśiva (SITI), probably Pāraśava; explained as ‘one who wields a weapon; a soldier’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परस्वत्|परस्वन्त्
parasvat (CII 1), a rhinoceros.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परत
parata (Chamba), return, exchange, substitute, compensation; derived from Sanskrit parivarta; same as badalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारत्रिक|पारत्रिकं
pāratrika (CII 1), ‘benefit in the other world’; merit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परसमय
para-samaya (EI 24), explained as a particular Jain doctrine; doctrines other than one's own.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्गना
parganā (EI 9, 32), a group of villages; same as pratijā-garaṇaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारि
Pāri (EI 31; LP; PJS), abbreviation of Gujarāti Pārikha, Pārekha (Sanskrit Pārīkṣaka), originally meaning ‘an examiner of coins’; a surname among the Baniās of Gujarat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिभूतनामन्
paribhūta-nāman (CII 3), a nickname.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिबोध|परिबोधः
paribodha (CII 1), obstacle, fetters; being in fetters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिचक्र
paricakra (LL), a circular panel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिचारक|परिचारकः
Paricāraka (EI 31), a servant; sometimes mentioned in the list of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिच्छन्द|परिच्छंद|परिच्छंदः|परिच्छन्दः
paricchanda (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 16), a vessel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिच्छेद|परिच्छेदः|परिछेद
pariccheda (CII 3), a territorial term meaning a group of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिछा
Parichā (IE 8-3; EI 31), Od̤iyā; same as Sanskrit Parīkṣaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिदर्शना
paridarśanā (IE 8-5; EI 29), a supervision tax probably related to division of property; may also be the same as Persian nazrāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिघ|परिघः
parigha (HRS), ‘door-bolt’; one of the seven sources of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिग्रह|परिग्रहः
parigraha (ML), acceptance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिगृहीत
parigṛhīta (IE 8-2; EI 31), ‘accepted’, sometimes used in place of anudhyāta (‘meditating’ or ‘favoured’) in passages like tatpāda-parighṛhīta; cf. bappa-bhaṭṭāraka-pāda-parigṛhīta, bhaṭṭāraka-Mahāsena-parigṛhīta, etc.; refers to selection or acceptance of a succession or appointment or receipt in one's favour.<BR> Cf. catuḥśāla-parigṛhītaṃ śaila-maṇḍapam and Samyaksam-buddhasya dhātu-parigṛhītasya (Select Inscriptions, p. 228).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिहार|परिहारः
parihāra (IE 8-5; EI 6; SITI), same as maryādā-parihāra; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-239" target="_blank">Page-239+ 40</a>] exemptions from taxes and obligations granted to the donees of rent-free land; privileges of the donee of rent-free holdings; for many such privileges, see Appendix I. Cf. certain privileges in respect of a number of taxes and obligations enumerated in Tamil records as follows: vaṭṭi-nāl̤i (payment of one nāl̤i per vaṭṭi), pudā-nāl̤i (or pidā˚, cess on each door or tax for the maintenance of sluices), maṇr̤upādu (fine imposed by a court of law), ūrāṭci (tax for running the village administration), taragu (tax on brokers), kūlam (tax on grains), īl̤̣am-puṭi (tax on toddy-drawers), nāḍu-kāval (tax for the policing of a district), ūḍupokku (meaning uncertain), uppu-kocceygai (tax for the manufacture of salt), nall-ā (tax for maintaining specimen cows), nallerudu (tax for maintaining specimen buffaloes), nerv-āypuvum (meaning uncertain) and others. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 124.<BR> (IA 17), a ring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=238" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिहारिक|पारिहारिकः
pārihārika (HRS), land exempted from revenue, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra; privileges enjoyed by the donee of a rent-free holding.<BR> Cf. sarva-jāta-pārihārika; same as parihāra or the parihāras collectively. See Select Inscriptions, pp. 192, 194.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिहीनिक
pārihīnika (HRS), damage-fee which was a branch of accidental revenue, according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 28.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिकर|परिकरः
parikara (IE 8-5; CII 4), same as uparikara, occasional or minor taxes; cf. sa-parikara (EI 23) which is the same as s-opari-kara.<BR> (SITI), requisites of a village.<BR> (HA), accessory decoration round the figure of a Jina, the motifs being taken from the Jain conception of the eight chief objects attendant upon a Jina (aṣṭa-mahāprātihāryāṇi, viz. the wheel of law, the caitya-tree, the lion-seat, the aureole behind the head, two attendant flywhisk-bearers, drum-beaters and pipe-players, and garland-bearers).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिकार
Parikāra (SITI), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिख्
Pārikh (EI 31), Gujaratī; Sanskrit Pārīkṣa; an examiner of coins; a family name amongst the Baniās. See Rūpa-darśaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिखाय
pārikh-āya (IA 19), a levy; cf. Pārikh, pārīkṣika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिक्रय|परिक्रयः
parikraya (SII 1), an exchange.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिक्रेय
parikreya (Sel. Ins., p. 236), remuneration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षा
Parīkṣā (IE 8-3; EI 28, 31), same as Sanskrit Parīkṣaka; Sanskritised [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-240" target="_blank">Page-240+ 40</a>] from Od̤iyā Parichā; superintendent of a department or a governor; cf. Dvāra-parīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=239" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षा
parīkṣā (IA 10), same as divya, an ordeal.<BR> (CII 1), self-examination.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षक|परीक्षकः
Parīkṣaka (IE 8-3), see Parīkṣā = Od̤iyā Parichā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारीक्षिक
pārīkṣika (HRS), testing-charge for private minting of coins, according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 43. Cf. pārikhāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परीक्षिपट्ट
parīkṣi-paṭṭa (IE I), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिमोटन
parimoṭana (EI 12), cracking.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिनिर्वाण
parinirvāṇa (EI 8), the death of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपन्थ्
paripanth, cf. paripanthayati (IE 8-2), same as vyavaharati; cf. samasta-mudrā-vyāpārān paripanthayati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपन्थना
paripanthanā, ‘creation of obstacles’; same as vidhāraṇā (EI). See vādhā or bādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपर|परिपरः
paripara (EI 3), a fight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारिपार्श्विक|पारिपार्श्विकः
Pāripārśvika (IA 11), a servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपृच्छा
paripṛcchā (CII 1), questioning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिपूर्ण
paripūrṇa (LP), probably, ‘in full youth’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिषद्
pariṣad (LL), four classes of the Buddhist order.<BR> (EI 32), used in the sense of pāriṣada, ‘a councillor’.<BR> Cf. Tamil paraḍai, etc. (SII 3), an assembly.<BR> (CII 1), cf. Prakrit parisā (EI 8), a council; the council [of ministers]; cf. mantri-pariṣad, ‘council of ministers.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिसर|परिसरः
parisara (EI 11), an area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिषदा
pariṣadā (HD), same as sabhā; an assembly or audience.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिश्रव
pariśrava (CII 1), sin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिशु
pariśu (SII 1), probably, a contract.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिसूत्र
parisūtra (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34), explained as ‘an establishment.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परित्याग|परित्यागः
parityāga (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 10, text line 2), donation; cf. deyadharma-parityāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवार|परिवारः
Parivāra (SII 3), a servant.<BR> Cf. horaka-parivāra (ML), explained as ‘the following of horakas.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवारालय
parivār-ālaya (SII 3), surrounding verandah of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवस्त्र
parivastra, cf. Tamil parivaṭṭam, pariśaṭṭam, pariyaṭṭam (SITI), literally, garment; honour done to a nobleman in a temple by tying a piece of cloth (generally, silk cloth) round his head.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिवृद्ध
Parivṛddha (EI 12), same as Prabhu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=240" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्णाकर
parṇ-ākara, cf. sa-parṇ-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with the fields producing leaves (i. e. betel-leaves).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्णशशन्
parṇa-śaśan (CII 1), an animal; probably, a rabbit living on leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परोक्षम्
parokṣam (IA 18), ‘in the absence of’; ‘behind the back of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः
par̤r̤u (IE 8-4), Tamil; a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्षद्
parṣad (LL), a congregation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार्षद|पार्षदः
pārṣada, cf. Prakrit pāṣaṃḍa (CII 1), a religious community; one belonging to a parṣad or religious group.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार्श्व|पार्श्वं|पार्श्वः
pārśva (HRS), extra charge upon land over and above the king's grain-share, which was a branch of ‘accidental revenue’ according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 28, 38.<BR> (IE 8-4), explained by some as a small territorial unit; but may be ‘side’; cf. prāveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पार्श्विक|पार्श्विकं|पार्श्विकः
Pārśvika (EI 9; CII 4), an aide-de-camp; also used to indicate a neighbour or one having land in the neighbourhood of the gift land (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 197, text line 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्ताब्
partāb (SII 1), Sanskrit pratāpa; a half pagoda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्वमासोत्सव
parva-mās-otsava (EI 15), a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारुत्थ
pāruttha, a silver coin equal to 8 drammas of copper or billon (JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 196).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्वन्|पर्व्वन्
parvan (IA 18), used in relation to eclipses.<BR> Cf. Koṅkaṇa-vijaya-parvan (EI 33), festival celebrating the conquest of the Koṅkaṇ; an anniversary of the said conquest.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्वत|पर्वतः|पर्व्वत|पर्व्वतः
parvata (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्याय|पर्यायः|पर्य्याय|पर्य्यायः
paryāya (IA 18), used in relation to an allotment.<BR> (CII 1), cf. dharma-paryāya, ‘exposition of the doctrine’; a religious text.<BR> Cf. Pallānakāra (EI 23), Sanskrit Paryāyakāra, a saddler, a saddle-maker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्युषित|पर्य्युषित|पर्य्युषितं
paryuṣita (HRS), ‘outstanding revenue’ which was one of the three kinds of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाश|पाशः
pāśa (CII 4), fetters of worldly existence.<BR> (IA 18), a land measure.<BR> (EI 26), a girdle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसाइत
Pasāita (EI 29, 33), also spelt Pasāyita; official designation; probably Sanskrit Prasādita in the sense of ‘a fief-holder’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाषाण|पाषाणः
pāṣāṇa (IE 8-5; SITI), one of the eight kinds of enjoyment [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-242" target="_blank">Page-242+ 40</a>] of landed property; rocky soil and its products; mineral products; probably, stony and hilly land referring to the right of quarrying, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=241" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशानम्
paśānam (EI 23), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसापालक
Pasāpālaka (EI 33), official designation; cf. Pasāyita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसायति
Pasāyati (EI 33), same as Pasāyita (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पसायित
Pasāyita (IE 8-3; EI 33), probably Sanskrit Prasādita used to indicate a Jāgīrdār. See Pasāita pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाश्चात्यलिखित
pāścātya-likhita (LP), written on the back of the bond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशु|पशुः
paśu (EI 8), animal sacrifice.<BR> Cf. a-paśu-medhya (IE 8-5), ‘free from the obligation of supplying animals for sacrifices.’<BR> (CII 4), the individual soul.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशुपाल|पशुपालः
Paśupāla (IA 22), nomads.<BR> (EI 1), also called Paśupālaka; a person in charge of cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपत|पाशुपतः
pāśupata (SII 2), same as pāśupat-āstra; name of a weapon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपत|पाशुपतः
Pāśupata (EI 32), name of a Śaiva sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपताचार्य
Pāśupat-ācārya (BL), epithet of a Śaiva religious teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशुपतराज्ञी
Pāśupata-rājñī (BL), epithet of a Śaiva queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट|पटं|पटः
paṭa, paṭā, pāṭa (EI 28; Chamba), charter, deed; same as Sanskrit paṭṭa or paṭṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट|पाटः
pāṭa, cf. daṇḍapāṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातक|पातकं|पातकः
pātaka (IE 8-1-2), ‘five’. Cf. pañca-mahāpātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटक|पाटकः
pāṭaka (IE 8-4; EI 4, 24; IA 18), ‘part of a village’, a quarter; the outlying part of a village; a hamlet; often prefixed to the name of localities; often modified to vāṭaka.<BR> (EI 15, 17, 28), a land measure.<BR> (IE 8-6), a land measure equal to forty droṇavāpas or to five kulyavāpas; part of a village.<BR> (EI 23, 24), a territorial division.<BR> (SITI), portion of a field.<BR> (SITI), anklet worn by women.<BR> (LP), same as Gujarātī pāḍo, a street or the division of a town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटकार|पटकारः
Paṭakāra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 186), a weaver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटकार
Pāṭakāra (EI 28), a splitter of wood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटकील
Paṭakīla (EI 23), village headman; same as Paṭṭakila, modern Paṭel or Pāṭīl; cf. Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाताल|पातालं|पातालः
pātāla (IE 7-1-2), sometimes used to indicate^1 ‘seven’.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=242" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातलकरणिन्
Pātala-karaṇin (IA 12), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटलिका
paṭalikā, cf. Tamil paḍaligai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतङ्ग|पतंग|पतङ्गं|पतंगः|पतङ्गः
pataṅga (IA 11), a paper kite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातनीय
pātanīya (LP), ‘should be left aside’, i. e. ‘should not be taken into account’.<BR> (LP), to be kept uncultivated; see kheḍanīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातसाह
Pātasāha (EI 11, 30; BL), Muslim imperial title; same as Persian Pādshāh. Cf. Pātasāhi, Pātisāha, Pātusāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातसाहि
Pātasāhi (BI), Indian modification of an imperial title of the Muhammadans; same as Persian Pādshāh; cf. Pātasāha, Pātisāhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातयिष्यामि
pātayiṣyāmi (LP), ‘I shall deduct and thus take less.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटेल्
Paṭel, Pāṭel (IE 8-3; EI 7), also called Pāṭīl; village headman; a member of the administrative board called Cauthiyā in Western India; cf. Paṭṭakila, Paṭakīla, Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाथ|पाथं|पाथः
pātha (IE 8-6; IA 11), a land measure regarded as equal to 240 square feet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पथक|पथकः
pathaka (IE 8-4; EI 4, 23, 27; CII 3, 4; LP), a group of villages; a territorial division like a Parganā of later days.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पथकीयक
Pathakīyaka (LP), explained as one who collects the road-tax [for the maintenance of the road] or the transit tax. But cf. pathaka also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाथि|पाथिः
pāthi (IA 15), a territorial unit; same as pathaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाठिन्
Pāṭhin (EI 31), epithet or family name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटी
pāṭī (IE 8-3); ‘arithmetic’; cf. the designation Pāṭy-uparika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पति|पतिः
pati (LL), a king; cf. adhipati.<BR> (EI 18), same as Kuḍipati = Sanskrit Grāmapati.<BR> Cf. grāma-patyā (probably the same as grāma-jana-patitvāt) and nānā-patyā (probably nānā-grāma-jana-patitvāt). See JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, pp. 203-04.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पटि|पटिः
paṭi (IA 18), same as Sanskrit prati, but sometimes substituted for Sanskrit pari in Prakrit; cf. paṭibhoga, ‘consumption [of food].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतिभाग
pati-bhāga (CII 4), a share of the produce payable to the landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतिहारि
Patihāri (EI 27), Sanskrit Pratihārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटिका
pāṭikā (CII 4), a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातिका
pātikā, cf. rāja-pātikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=243" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाटील्
Pāṭīl, see Paṭel, Pāṭel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Pāṭīpati (Tripathi, History of Kanauj, p. 137); cf. Pāṭyuparika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातिसाह
Pātisāha, also spelt Pādisāha (EI 30; BL); same as Persian Pādshāh; ‘Muslim imperial ruler’. See Pādishāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातिसाहि
Pātisāhi (BL), Indian modification of an imperial title of the Muslim rulers; same as Persian Pādshāh. See Pātisāha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पतित|पतितः
patita (LP), uncultivated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातित
pātita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 14), ‘killed in a battle’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्र|पत्त्रं|पत्रं
patra (CITD), a letter or document; a note; a written paper or deed.<BR> (LP), a bond.<BR> Cf. tāmra-patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पात्र|पात्त्रं|पात्रं|पात्रः
Pātra (IE 8-3; EI 28, 29; BL), a minister; cf. Mahāpurohita-ṭhakkura, Paṇḍita, Upādhyāya, Karaṇa-kāyastha, etc., mentioned as Pātra probably meaning ‘a courtier.’ See Ekapātra and Mahāpātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पात्र|पात्त्रं|पात्रं|पात्रः
pātra, probably, a document (patra). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169.<BR> (EI 9), a donee.<BR> Cf. Pātrapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पात्रपति
Pātrapati, probably, the driver or owner of a horse-cart (ṭaṅgā). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 145.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्रसमय
patra-samaya (LP), the conditions laid down in a bond.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्ट|पट्टं|पट्टः
Paṭṭa, abbreviation of Paṭṭakila (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, No. B 296).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्ट|पट्टं|पट्टः
paṭṭa (IE 8-4; CII 3, 4), a territorial term meaning a group of villages; cf. apara-paṭṭa (EI 22) ‘the western district’.<BR> (EI 7, 9, 11; SII 1; BL), a school or spiritual line; a pontificate; a pontifical seat; the dignity of the head of a Jain school; cf. reference to a Jain religious teacher as belonging to the paṭṭa of another teacher and the santāna of a third teacher; cf., e. g., ‘in the paṭṭa of Dharma-sūri’; also cf. ‘paṭṭ-āvalī of the Kharatara gaccha’.<BR> Cf. rāja-paṭṭa, paṭṭa-bandha, paṭṭ-ābhiṣeka, etc.<BR> (EI 18), a piece of land.<BR> (LL), a slab; cf. Prakrit paṭa (EI 20), a stone slab. Cf. yoni-paṭṭa; Gaurī-paṭṭa.<BR> (Chamba), also called paṭha; a grain measure, derived from Sanskrit prastha.<BR> Same as paṭṭaka (q. v.); cf. Paṭṭa-lekhin, etc.<BR> (ASLV), an account book. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-245" target="_blank">Page-245+ 40</a>]<BR> (LP), abbreviation of Paṭṭadhara; probably one who has the charter for collecting government revenues; cf. Paṭṭakila.<BR> Cf. Paṭṭarājñī, Paṭṭanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्ट
pāṭṭa, same as or a mistake for paṭṭa, a district. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 235.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टबन्ध|पट्टबन्धः
paṭṭa-bandha (EI 5, 22, 26), coronation; crowning ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टाचार्य
Paṭṭ-ācārya (IA 14), a religious title; same as Maṇḍal-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टक|पट्टकः
paṭṭaka (EI 30; IA 17), a passport; a charter; a copper-plate grant. Cf. paṭṭak-ārtha-samasta-karaṇāya (LP), ‘for fulfilling all the conditions in the charter’; also Tamil paṭṭayam (SITI), grant inscribed on copper-plates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकधार्मिक
paṭṭaka-dhārmika (IE 8-8; EI 30); probably, an authorised cess to be collected for performing a religious function; cf. dhārmika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकापचारिक
Paṭṭak-āpacārika (IE 8-3; EI 31), officer in charge of dealing with paṭṭak-āpacāra (crime relating to the misuse or fraud concerning grants).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकार
Paṭṭakāra (EI 24), also called Paṭṭalekhin; writer of documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकिल|पट्टकिलः
Paṭṭakila (EI 25; CII 4; HD), village headman; same as modern Paṭel, Pāṭel or Pāṭīl. See Ind. Ant., Vol. VI, pp. 51, 53. Cf. Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकिलादाय
paṭṭakil-ādāya (EI 21; CII 4), tax for the maintenance of the Paṭṭakila or village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टक्कारै
paṭṭakkārai (ASLV), neck-ring; an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टकूल
paṭṭa-kūla (LP), silk cloth; cf. pāṭoluṃ in Gujarātī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तला
pattalā (EI 8-3; EI 19, 24; 26; CII 4), a territorial division; a district.<BR> (IA 18; LP), same as paṭṭa, a royal charter; cf. prasāda-pattalā (LP), a deed recording the grant of rent-free land; (IA 18), cf. prabhoḥ prasād-āvāpta-pattalayā, explained as ‘[area enjoyed] under a patent obtained through the favour of the lord’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तलक
Pattalaka (IE 8-3; EI 3, 9, 23), official designation; probably, not an officer in charge of a territorial unit called pattalā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टलेखिन्
Paṭṭa-lekhin, cf. Paṭṭakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तलिका
Pattalikā (EI 9), official designation; feminine form of Pattalaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टम्
pāṭṭam (EI 21), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=245" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टमहादेवी
Paṭṭamahādevī (IE 8-2; EI 4, 20, 22; BL), designation of the chief queen; cf. Mahādevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टमहिषी
Paṭṭamahiṣī (EI 28), a crowned queen; chief queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टन|पट्टनं
paṭṭana (HRS), duties levied upon merchants at the ports, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR> (EI 19), same as pattana, a township.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तन|पत्तनं
pattana (IE 8-4; IP), a township; suffixed to the names of cities like Aṇahillapura-pattana (modern Pāṭan in the Kadi District of the former Baroda State).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तनाकरस्थानगोकुलाधिकारिपुरुष
Pattan-ākarasthāna-gokul-ādhikāri-puruṣa (IA 15), official designation or designations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टनस्वामिन्
Paṭṭana-svāmin (ASLV), head of an organisation or a guild in a city; sometimes regarded as the same as Mahānāḍ-prabhu. See Seṭṭi-Paṭṭanasvāmi.<BR> (SITI), chief or leader of the mercantile community of a town.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टनायक
Paṭṭanāyaka (IE 8-3; EI 29), the chief officer or a ruling chief; same as Puronāyaka (cf. Tamil Por̤r̤u). It is a family name in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टराज्ञी
Paṭṭarājñī (IE 8-2; EI 23, 30; BL), designation of the chief queen; cf. Rājñī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टराणी
Paṭṭarāṇī (BL), title of a chief queen; cf. Rāṇī. Same as Paṭṭarājñī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टसाहनाधिपति
Paṭṭasāhanādhipati (IE 8-3; EI 15), same as Mahāsādha-nika, etc.; see Paṭṭasāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टसाहणि
Paṭṭasāhaṇi (EI 15), same as Paṭṭasāhanādhipati; see Sāhaṇi = Sanskrit Sādhanika; cf. Kari-turaga-paṭṭasāhaṇi (EI 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टशाल
paṭṭa-śāla (CITD), Sanskrit ˚śālā; a reading hall; probably, ‘the main hall’; in Kannaḍa, ‘a silk-shop’.<BR> (EI 3), name applied to the abode of certain Brāhmaṇas.<BR> (LP), cf. Gujaratī Paḍaśāla; the first room in a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टावली
paṭṭ-āvalī (IA 19; SITI; BL), a list of Jain pontiffs; succession list of spiritual heads among the Jains; cf. ‘paṭṭ-āvalī of the Bṛhat-Kharatara gaccha [of the Jains].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टवारिक
Paṭṭavārika, same as modern Paṭvāri; cf. Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टेल
Paṭṭela (EI 7), same as Paṭṭakila, Paṭel or Pāṭīl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टि
paṭṭi (IE 8-6; EI 8), a measure of land; same as nivart-tana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टी
paṭṭī (EI 9), a plot of land.<BR>Same as paṭṭa; cf. rāja-paṭṭī (EI 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्ति|पत्तिः
patti (SII 2), same as nivartana.<BR> (SII 1), a sheep-fold; a square measure.<BR> (CII 4), share of the produce.<BR> (IE 8-3), the smallest division of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्ती
pattī (IA 15), an extra land cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तिभाग
patti-bhāga (CII 4), same as pati-bhāga, a share of produce payable to the landlord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तिक
Pattika (IE 8-3), leader of the patti, the smallest division of the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तिका
pattikā (CII 4), a share; same as patti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिका
paṭṭikā (EI 8, 17), same as tāmra-paṭṭa or tāmra-paṭṭikā; a copper plate or copper-plate grant.<BR> (EI 3), a document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिकापालक
Paṭṭikā-pālaka, same as Pustapāla (Select Inscriptions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टीपद
paṭṭī-pada (EI 24), footprints on a slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पत्तियाणक
Pattiyāṇaka (IA 132), official designation of doubtful import; probably, an administrator or document-writer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोला
paṭṭolā, cf. Tamil paṭṭolai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोलै
paṭṭolai (SII 1), Tamil = Sanskrit paṭṭolā; a document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टोलै
Pāṭṭolai (EI 21, 22), Tamil; official designation; cf. paṭ-ṭolai, ‘a document’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोली
paṭṭolī, ‘a deed of purchase’ also ‘land purchased by means of a paṭṭolī’ (Jour. As. Soc., Letters, Vol. XX, p. 205). See Tamil paṭṭolai = paṭṭolā, ‘a document’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टोपाध्याय|पट्टोपाध्यायः
Paṭṭ-opādhyāya (HD), a writer or keeper of official documents. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पातुसाह
Pātusāha (BL), Indian modification of a Muslim imperial title; same as Persian Pādshāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्वारि
Paṭvāri (IE 8-3), probably Sanskrit Paṭṭavārika; the accountant-clerk; a member of the administrative board called Cauthiyā in Western India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्युपरिक|पाट्युपरिकः
Pāṭy-uparika (IE 8-2; 8-3; BL), official designation of uncertain implication; possibly indicating ‘the head of the department of accounts’; sometimes also called Mahārāja, Mahā-sāmanta, Mahāpratīhāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pañc-ādhikaraṇ-oparika and Purapāl-oparika, additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाउका
pāukā (IE 8-5; EI 29), same as Od̤iyā pāuseri; tax on the money realised by creditors from debtors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पऊक
paūka (EI 31), misprint for Pāli pattha = Sanskrit prastha; a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=247" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौण्डरीक|पौंडरीक|पौण्डरीकं|पौण्डरीकः
pauṇḍarīka (EI 4; IA 19), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौराणिक|पौराणिकः
Paurāṇika (EI 30; BL), a reciter of the Purāṇas; also probably, an astrologer. Cf. Vyāsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौर|पौरं|पौरः
paura (CII 4), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौरवीथिल्लक
Paura-vīthillaka, probably officers in charge of a city and a subdivision; cf. Paura-vi(vī)thillaka-grāmakūṭa-niyuktāniyukta-pradhān-āpradhāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 169, where the reading is given as visvillaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौरव्यवहारिक
Paura-vyavahārika, cf. Nagara-vyavahārika. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, pp. 112, 147.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौषध|पौषधः
pauṣadha (HA), Sanskrit uposatha; living like a Jain monk for 12 or 24 hours; the observance of fast on the eighth and fourteenth of the fortnight, the full-moon day and the day before the new moon and abstention from wicked acts, chastity, abandonment^1 of bathing, etc., i. e. living temporarily like a monk. See poṣadha.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाउसेरि
pāuseri, cf. pāukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौतव|पौतवं
pautava (HRS), various dues collected by the superintendent of weights and measures, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR> (EI 30), measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौटि
pauṭi (EI 29, 32), same as Sanskrit pravarti; a measure of capacity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावाडै
pāvāḍai (SITI), Tamil; cloth spread on the ground for persons of distinction to walk on; also food-offering on a large scale spread over a cloth in front of the deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावै
pāvai (IE 8-5), same as darśana or nazrāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावक|पावकः
pāvaka (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवन|पवनं|पवनः
pavana (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावीसा
pāvīsā (EI 33), probably, Sanskrit pāda-viṃśaka (viṃśopaka); name of a coin; regarded as equal to five cowrie-shells; same as modern paisā. See lohaḍiyā and dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवित्र|पवित्रं|पवित्रः
pavitra (EI 9), the argha vessel.<BR> (Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 187), thread, 360 of which are tied round the neck of the image of Kṛṣṇa on Śrāvaṇa su-di 12.<BR> Cf. Caitra-pavitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवित्रक|पवित्रकं|पवित्रकः
pavitraka (EI 1), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पायला
pāyalā (EI 11), also called pāyalī; name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेडा
peḍā (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piṭha, piḍā, pyoḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=248" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेडार्पात
Peḍārpāla (BL), mistake for Peḍāpāla, ‘keeper of the record-boxes’. See Peṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेद्दगड्यमु
pědda-gaḍyamu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेज्जुङ्क
pějjuṅka (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax; same as pěrjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्गडे
Pěrgaḍě (IE 8-3; EI 4), Kannaḍa; a chamberlain; a superintendent or director (Sanskrit Adhyakṣa); see Věrgaḍě, Hěggaḍě, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्ग्गावुण्ड
Pěrggāvuṇḍa (EI 26), Kannaḍa, official designation. Cf. Gāvuṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्जुङ्क
pěrjuṅka (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; same as pějjuṅka; name of a tax or toll.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्जुङ्कदपेर्गडे
Pěrjuṅkadapěrgaḍě (EI 16), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुजुङ्क
pěrujuṅka (EI 28), same as pěrjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुमानडिगल्
Pěrumān-aḍigal̤ (SITI), Tamil; a term of reverence used to indicate a god or a king. Cf. personal names like Pramāḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुम्बडैयोम्
perumbaḍaiyom (ASLV), military classes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटकपाल
Peṭakapāla (EI 28, 29), keeper of the boxes containing records; record-keeper; same as Peṭāpāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटपाल
Peṭapāla (EI 30; BL), keeper of boxes containing official records; the record-keeper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटापाल
Peṭāpāla (EI 29), also called Peṭakapāla; record-keeper; same as Peṭapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेटविक
Peṭavika (EI 30), a class of officials; Peṭavika-vārika (IE 8-8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेठ
peṭha (IE 8-4; CII 3), a small territorial unit; a group of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेट्टपाल
Peṭṭapāla (EI 15, 28), keeper of the record-boxes; same as Peṭāpāla, Peṭakapāla, Peḍāpāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेयियसाहणि
Peyiya-sāhaṇi (Naik's List, No. 264), mentioned along with Maleya-sāhaṇi; official designation. Cf. Sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फा
Phā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Phālguna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फदिया
phadiyā, see phadyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फद्यक
phadyaka (EI 23), same as phadiyā; name of a coin; (1/20) of a rupee and equal to 5 dukrās and 2 dukānīs (JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 295).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फैण्डिआयायि
phaiṇḍi-āyāyi (CITD), Telugu; same as phaiṇḍivāya-mar̤uturu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फैण्डिवायम
phaiṇḍivāya-mar̤uturu (CITD), Telugu; a mar̤uturu measure of land which brought an income in coin and not kind; in Telugu, paiḍi means gold and āyam income.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=249" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फल|फलं|फलः
phala (IA 27), a Pāli form of Sanskrit pala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फालदिव्य
phāla-divya (IA 17), the ordeal of taking a heated plough-share in hand.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलहिक
phalahika, cf. sa-phalahikaṃ (LP), with an open space round about the house; same as Gujarātī phaliyuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलक|फलकं|फलकः
phalaka (IE 3-5), a wooden slab used as a slate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलसंस्कार
phala-saṃskāra (CII 3), equation of the centre.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलित|फलितं|फलितः
phalita, cf. phalita-pade (LP), also Gujarātī huṃḍī pāke tyāre, ‘when the bill of exchange becomes due’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फिक
phika (LP), a bull which is not castrated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फुरमाण
phuramāṇa (EI 2), Persian farmān; a royal order or grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फुट्ट
phuṭṭa (CII 3), a Prakrit word meaning a break or damage in a construction, sometimes Sanskritised as sphuṭita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 144, note 3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिआद
Piāda (IE 8-3), same as Bhaṭa or Bhaṭa-manuṣya; cf. Pāik.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचु|पिचुः
picu, same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचुल|पिचुलः
picula, weight equal to 6 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिडा
piḍā (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piṭha, peḍā, pyoḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिडागै
piḍāgai (ASLV), a hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिदानालि
Pidā-nāl̤i (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिढ
piḍha (LL), probably, a chair; cf. Sanskrit pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिल्लैगल्तनम्
pil̤l̤aigal̤-tanam (SITI), Tamil; status of the prince, supposed to be an officers' cadre composed of the junior members of the royal family. Cf. Kumār-āmātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीलु|पीलुः
pīlu (IE 8-3), Indian form of Arabic-Persian fīl, an elephant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीलुपति
Pīlupati (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 13, 28; CII 4), leader of the elephant force or keeper of the elephants; cf. Mahāpīlupati, pīlu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिञ्छ
piñcha (IA 18), bunch of feathers carried by a Jain ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डादान
piṇḍ-ādāna (EI 12), quit rent. Cf. also piṇḍa-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डक|पिंडक|पिंडकं|पिण्डकं|पिंडकः|पिण्डकः
piṇḍaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 254, text line 55), same as piṇḍ-ādāna or bhāga-bhoga; cf. samucita-kara-piṇḍak-ādi-samasta-pratyāya; taxes assessed in a lump; cf. piṇḍa-kara.<BR> (IA 2), same as grāsā; probably, a part of the produce of the fields for the maintenance of certain persons.<BR> (HRS), known from Pāla records; same as hiraṇya, according to some.<BR> (LL), probably, a slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डकर
piṇḍa-kara (HRS), lump assessment upon villages, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra. Cf. also piṇḍ-ādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=250" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिण्डपात|पिंडपात|पिण्डपातः
piṇḍa-pāta (EI 25), food [for the Buddhist monks].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिशाचचतुर्दशी
piśāca-caturdaśī (EI 1), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिषारडि
Piṣāraḍi (IA 24), Malayāl̤am; the manager of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिशुनवेत्रिक
Piśunavetrika (EI 33; HD), probably, an officer who drives away undesirable persons with a cane; or, one engaged in a court for caning culprits. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 94. See Vetrika, Yāṣṭika, Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिटक|पिटकं|पिटकः
piṭaka (CII 4), a measure of capacity.<BR> Cf. Traipiṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितलहार
Pitalahāra (EI 20, 32), a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितामह|पितामहः
Pitāmaha (EI 24, 33), epithet of the Buddha.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; but cf. Brahman used to indicate ‘nine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिठ|पिठः
piṭha (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piḍā, peḍā, pyoḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठ|पीठं
pīṭha (CII 4; IA 12), receptacle of a Śiva-liṅga; the ablution trough of a Śiva-liṅga; also called Yoni-paṭṭa.<BR> (SITI), pedestal for the image of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठी
pīṭhī (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 16), a pedestal or seat; same as pīṭha and pīṭhikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठिक
pīṭhika (ASLV), Sanskrit pīṭhikā; a throne; same as rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठिका
pīṭhikā (EI 2), a platform.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठिकावित्त
Pīṭhikāvitta (IE 8-3; EI 12; HD), probably, ‘those who have acquired [special] seats’; same as Utthitāsanika. The word occurs in such records as the Belava plate of Bhojavarmadeva (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 40). Cf. Velāvitta. Pīṭhikāvitta is sometimes explained as the collector of state dues from pilgrims or religious institutions (Sen, Hist. Asp. Ins. Beng., p. 552).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पीठीपति
Pīṭhīpati (BL), explained as ‘the lord of Magadha’ in the commentary of Sandhyākaranandin's Rāmacarita; title of the head of the Buddhist religious institution at Bodhgayā, who was the precursor of the later Mahant Mahārājas of Bodhgayā. The word pīṭhī in this title is the same as pīṭha or pīṭhikā meaning the vajrāsana at Bodhgayā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितृपर्वन्
pitṛ-parvan (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 37), probably, śrāddha or dāna on each amāvāsyā day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पितृयज्ञ|पितृयज्ञः
pitṛ-yajña (CII 4), offerings to the manes; one of the pañca-mahāyajña.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्ल
pla (IE 8-1), contraction of pala; often found in the records of the Orissa region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोचिलभूमि
pocila-bhūmi (LP), soft land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=251" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोढी
poḍhī (LL), a cistern; cf. Sanskrit prahi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोदुवा
Poduvāl̤̣ (EI 18), Tamil-Malayalam; an officer supervising charitable endowments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोलाच्य
polācya, cf. sa-khila-polācya (IE 8-5); cultivated land; same as nāla; Hindī polach, ‘land constantly under cultivation.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोंद
poṃda (Chamba), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोंदी
poṃdī (Chamba), bottom; foot of a hill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्
pon (SITI), also spelt pon̤; name of a gold coin also called māḍai. Cf. pon-bhaṇḍāram, ‘gold-treasury’; pon-paṇḍāra-vāśal, ‘the gate of the gold-treasury; royal gold-treasury’; pon-vargam (SITI), ‘a class of taxes payable in gold or coin; ponvari, ‘tax payable in gold (cash)’; also ‘the fee for minting gold into coins’; probably, the same as ponvari-māḍai.<BR> Cf. turai-min̤n̤ar̤-pon (SITI), name of a coin.<BR> (IE 8-8; EI 16), name of a coin; same as gadyāṇa, hūn or varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्
pon̤ (EI 24), a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो
Pon̤-bhaṇḍāram (ASLV), a treasurer; treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोरपाञ्जिधरपरीक्षा
Pora-Pāñjīdhara-parīkṣā (EI 28), chief astrologer; cf. puro prefixed to certain official designations in Orissa. See Paṭṭanāyaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोरश्रीकरण
Pora-Śrīkaraṇa (EI 28), chief secretary; cf. puro prefixed to certain official designations in Orissa. See Por̤r̤u.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो
Por̤-Bhaṇḍāri (EI 25), Tamil; temple officer mentioned along with Śāsana-bhaṇḍāri (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 132); cf. pora prefixed to Od̤iyā official designations like Pora-Śrīkaraṇa; also Tamil Por̤r̤u.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोर्रु
Por̤r̤u (EI 25), Tamil; official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोषध|पोषधः
poṣadha, derived from Sanskrit uposatha; also called poṣa-dha-vrata; cf. pauṣadha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत|पोतः
pota (EI 9), a sacrificial victim.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोतक|पोतकः
potaka (LP), the government's money-bag.<BR> (LP), cf. Gujarātī poluṃ; the amount of revenue of a village sent to the Government treasury. Cf. pottaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत्र|पोत्रं
potra (EI 26), name of a tax. Cf. potta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत्त
potta, cf. milita-potta-drammā (LP), collected government money. Cf. potra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोत्तक
pottaka (LP), same as Gujarātī potuṃ; the amount of the revenue of a village sent to the government treasury. Cf. potaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोट्टलिका
poṭṭalikā (IE 8-8), a bundle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=252" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्र
pra (PJS), abbreviation of pratimā (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR> (IE 8-1), abbreviation of prathama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रबन्ध|प्रबंध|प्रबंधः|प्रबन्धः
prabandha, name of hymnal^1 compositions in Tamil by ancient Vaiṣṇava devotees. The contributions of hymns and prayers by the twelve āl̤̣vārs in praise of Viṣṇu make up the Nālāyiradivyaprabandham. Nālāyira (four thousand) indicates the rough total number of items and prabandham is regarded as meaning a compilation. The first thousand is known as Tirumol̤̣i and comprises hymns of Periyāl̤̣vār, Āṇḍāl, Kulaśekhara, etc.; the second thousand contains the hymns of Tirumaṅgai; the third comprises the compositions of the first three āl̤̣vārs called Iyar̤pā, viz. Tirumal̤̣iśai, Nammāl̤̣var and Tirumaṅgai, and the fourth called Tiruvāymol̤̣i is entirely the work of Nammāl̤̣vār. Nāthamunigal̤̣ is stated to be the compiler of this anthology. See M. S. Purnalingam Pillai, Tamil Literature, pp. 181 ff.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रबर्ह
prabarha (EI 13), a worthy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राब्द
prābda (EI 16), same as abda, ‘the year.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभा
prabhā (SII 2), an aureole or nimbus. Cf. prabhā-valaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभाटक
prabhāṭaka (EI 24), same as bhāṭaka; rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभावलय
prabhā-valaya (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 16), aureole or nimbus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राभृतीकृत
prābhṛtīkṛta (EI 14), ‘presented’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभु|प्रभुः
Prabhu (IA 30; BL), a village official; cf. Mahāprabhu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभुज्यमान
prabhujyamāna (IA 18), cf. bhujyamāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभुशक्ति
prabhu-śakti (CII 4), power derived from the royal position.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रभुस्वाम्य
prabhu-svāmya (SII 11. 1), a tenure held by a Prabhu (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रबोधनी
prabodhanī (EI 8), prabodh-otsava (EI 32), same as utthāna-dvādasī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदक्षिण|प्रदक्षिणं|प्रदक्षिणः
pradakṣiṇa (CITD), circumambulation from left to right; paying homage to a temple, etc., by solemnly walking round it with the right hand towards it, so that the right side is always turned towards the person or object circumambulated; a reverential salutation made by walking in this manner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदेश|प्रदेशः
pradeśa (IE 8-4), a province or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रादेशिक|प्रादेशिकः
Prādeśika (IE 8-3; HD), cf. Prakrit Pādesika (EI 3), provincial governor; governor of a pradeśa or province. Cf. CII, Vol. I, pp. 4-5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदेष्टृ
Pradeṣṭṛ (HD), a class of magistrates; the police magistrate. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 147; Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 156; Arthaśāstra, I. 12; IV. 1 and 10 (last verse).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=253" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रदेय|प्रदेयः
pradeya (EI 12), same as deya; dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधान|प्रधानं|प्रधानः
Pradhāna (SII 1; HD; BL), an official designation sometimes indicating the chief minister or administrator also called Pradhāna-saciva (EI 23); cf. pañca-Pradhānāḥ (EI 5) ‘the five ministers’. See Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 35 where Mantrin, Amātya and Pradhāna are separately mentioned.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानमण्डप
pradhāna-maṇḍapa (LL), Buddhist; the hall for practising religious exercises.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानिन्
Pradhānin (CITD), according to lexicons, a governor, minister or president; noble or courtier; etc.<BR> (EI 31; ASLV), a high executive officer; same as Pradhāna.<BR> (EI 30), a village headman.<BR> Cf. Mahāpradhāni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानिजोडि
pradhāni-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; an inām held on a fixed quit-rent by a minister; the chief minister's quitrent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राधिराज्य
prādhirājya (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रद्वार|प्रद्वारं
pradvāra (IA 7), a place in front of the gate; explained as ‘a suburb’ (EI 21); same as Gujarātī parā. Cf. Valabhī-prad-vāra-Homba-vāsakāt (IA 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राड्विवाक|प्राड्विवाकः
Prāḍvivāka (HD), the chief justice; a judge. See Manusmṛti, IX. 234.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रघट्टक|प्रघट्टकः
praghaṭṭaka (EI 15), probably, a conflict.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राघूर्णक|प्राघूर्णकः
prāghūrṇaka (LP), a present or gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रग्राह्य
pragrāhya (EI 12), cf. a-kiñcit-pragrāhya; same as grāhya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रहणीक
prahaṇīka (LL), a class of Buddhist monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रहर|प्रहरः
prahara (SII 2; SITI), flaw in rubies.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राहरिक्य
prāharikya (LP), cf. Gujarātī pahero; a guard or custodian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रहितक
prahitaka (IA 6), doubtfully explained as ‘a messenger’ or ‘a committee man.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रैषणिक
Praiṣaṇika (IE 8-3), same as Preṣaṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकाल
prakāla (Select Inscriptions, p. 305, text line 15); an era; cf. Gupta-prakāle gaṇanāṃ vidhāya. See kāla in kāl-ānuvartta-māna-saṃvatsare (ibid., p. 270, text lines 3-4), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकरण|प्रकरणं
prakaraṇa (CII 1), proper occasion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकीर्तित|प्रकीर्त्तित|प्रकीर्त्तितं
prakīrtita (EI 24), built; same as kīrtita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रम|प्रक्रमः
prakrama (CII 1), an effort; zealous activity; same as parākrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रान्त|प्रक्रांत|प्रक्रान्तः
prakrānta (CII 1), active or zealous.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=254" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रय
prakraya (HRS), income from mines and salt-works, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकृत|प्रकृतः
prakṛta, cf. saṅgha-prakṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रित्
Prakrit, Anglicised spelling of Prākṛta, the name of a language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राकृत|प्राकृतः
Prākṛta, see Prakrit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रकृति|प्रकृतिः
prakṛti (HD); cf. Mahābhārata, II. v. 23, speaking of the seven prakṛtis which Nīlakaṇṭha explains as referring to Durg-ādhyakṣa (commandant of the citadel), Bal-ādhyakṣa (controller general of the army), Dharm-ādhyakṣa (chief of the departments of charity and justice), Camūpati (commander of the army in the field), chaplain, physician and astrologer. The Milindapañha (IV. i. 36) mentions six officers, e. g., the commander-in-chief, prime minister, chief judge, chief treasurer, bearer of the sun-shade and bearer of the sword of state (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 77, note 6). Cf. Mātra.<BR> (EI 16), a temple official.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyone.’<BR> (EI 9), the Kṣatriya community.<BR> Cf. sa-tantuvāya-gokuṭa-śauṇḍik-ādi-prakṛtika (IE 8-5); subjects of a king.<BR> (CII 1), usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्रिया
prakriyā (IA 18), cf. samasta-rāja-prakriy-opeta; prerogative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रक्षेप|प्रक्षेपः
prakṣepa (EI 13), cf. amīṣāṃ prakṣepa-pratiṣedhau na karaṇ-īyau, ‘they should not be ousted [from the possession] or hindered [from their enjoyment of the gift land].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमदाकुल
pramadā-kula (EI 11), a host of courtesans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमाण|प्रमाणं|प्रमाणः
pramāṇa (EI 6; SII 1; SITI), a document; a title deed.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 109), authority; witness.<BR> (SII 12), cf. mūla-pramāṇa, original order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमाणयष्टि
pramāṇa-yaṣṭi (LL), measuring rod.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमातार
Pramātāra (HD), an officer concerned with the administration of justice, according to some (Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 122-23). See Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 211. Cf. Pramātṛ, Pramattavāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमत्तवार
Pramattavāra (EI 21), official designation; same as Pramātṛ or Pramātāra (q. v.); the commander of the elephant corps according to some (CII 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमातृ
Pramātṛ (BL), same as Pramātāra, Pramattavāra (q. v.); a civil judge, according to some (HD); cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321; literally, ‘measurer [of the king's grain share]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=255" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रमुख|प्रमुखं|प्रमुखः
Pramukha (CII 4), a member of the executive committee of a corporation.<BR> (EI 28), probably the same as Pradhānin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राण|प्राणः
prāṇa (CII 1), living being; same as prāṇin.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणाचार्य|प्राणाचार्यः
Prāṇ-ācārya (EI 8), title of a physician; explained as the medical adviser of the king (HD). Cf. Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 33-34 (for his qualifications).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणदाक्षिण्य
prāṇa-dākṣiṇya (CII 1), gift of life.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणाली
praṇālī (CII 3), a conduit, a channel, an irrigation canal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणान्तिक|प्राणांतिक
prāṇāntika (SITI), ‘till the close of one's life’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रनप्त्रिक
Pranaptṛka (CII 1), cf. panatika (EI 22), the great-grandson; but cf. naptṛ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राणसमेत
prāṇa-sameta, cf. Prakrit praṇa-sameda (EI 24), ‘endowed with life’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणश्य
praṇaśya (LP), ‘going out of sight’; cf. Gujarātī nāśīne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणय|प्रणयः
praṇaya (IE 8-5; HRS), known from the Arthaśāstra, the Junagadh inscription of Rudradāman, etc.; emergency tax or benevolence; also called praṇaya-kriyā (IE 8-5); cf. a-hiraṇya-dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya, an epithet of rent-free land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रणयक्रिया
praṇaya-kriyā (EI 8), benevolence or emergency impost; same as praṇaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रान्तपाल
Prāntapāla (IE 8-3; EI 18, 29, 31), warden of the marches; also explained as the governor of a province or guardian of the frontiers (HD). Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 124.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपा
prapā (EI 3; IA 18; LL), watering trough; a cistern or reservoir.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), a place of distributing water gratis to travellers; a cistern.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राप
prāpa (EI 17), ‘sub-division of a district’; but see prāpīya, prāveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपापूरक
Prapā-pūraka (IE 8-8; EI 30), a person responsible for filling the cisterns with water in a place for watering cattle or supplying water to travellers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपर्णक
praparṇaka, royal order; same as Persian parwāna (Select Inscriptions, p. 248).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रपौत्र|प्रपौत्रः
prapautra, cf. pautra-prāpautrika (CII 1); the great-grandson.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रापीय
prāpīya (EI 17), same as prāveśya; cf. Akṣasaraka-prāveśya and Akṣasaraka-prāpīya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 109); cf. prāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राप्तपञ्चमहाशब्द
Prāpta-pañcamahāśabda (IE 8-2), same as Samadhigata-pañcamahāśabda; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-257" target="_blank">Page-257+ 40</a>] subordinate title or epithet; sometimes applied to a crown prince. See pañca-mahāśabda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=256" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्राप्ति|प्राप्तिः
prāpti (SII 2), benefit.<BR> (EI 7), revenue.<BR> (SITI), enjoyment; what is obtained from someone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रारब्धि|प्रारब्धिः
prārabdhi (EI 2), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रार्य
prārya (EI 15), father's father or father-in-law's father. Cf. āryaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसाद|प्रसादः
prasāda (EI 3), gift (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 162, note 2).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रासाद|प्रासादः
prāsāda (CII 4; LL), a palace or temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसादक
prasādaka, cf. Pali and Prakrit pasādaka (EI 20), one who converts some one to the Buddhist faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसादमुक्त
prasāda-mukta (LP), cf. Gujarātī prasād choḍvā khāt, ‘for allowing this favour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसन्न|प्रसन्नः
prasanna (CII 1), devoted or attached.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रशस्ति|प्रशस्तिः
praśasti (EI 15, 23, 24; CII 3, 4), a culogy; a culogistic inscription generally on stone; a copper-plate charter (with reference to the introductory section of medieval charters); rarely praśastā (Ep. Ind., Vol. 36, p. 52), śubhā (Vol. 35, p. 59).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रास्तरिकश्रेणी
prāstarika-śreṇī (EI 23), a guild of stone-masons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रशास्तृ
Praśāstṛ (EI 31), probably, a judge; the chief magistrate, according to some (HD); cf. Arthaśāstra, I. 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रशिष्य|प्रशिष्यः
Praśiṣya (ML; SITI), the disciple's disciple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसृमर
prasṛmara (EI 13), explained as ‘spreading out in some corner’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसृति|प्रसृतिः
prasṛti (EI 30), a measure; a handful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रस्थ|प्रस्थः
prastha (IE 8-6; CII 4; Chamba), a measure of capacity, often regarded as one-sixteenth of a droṇa; cf. Pāli pattha, a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रष्ठ|प्रष्ठः
praṣṭha, cf. praṣṭham (Sel. Ins., p. 236), ‘immediately’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रस्थक
prasthaka (HRS), known from the Gurjara-Pratihāra records; cess at the rate of a prastha of grain over and above the usual grain-share. Cf. akṣapatala-prastha, pratihāra-prastha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
prasūti-śālā, maternity home (Kākatīyasaṃcika, No. 31).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रताप|प्रतापः
pratāpa, see partāb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्
Pratāpa-cakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथम|प्रथमः
Prathama (EI 21), prefixed to Kāyastha and Kulika to indicate representatives of certain classes as members of an administrative board of the Pañcāyat type.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमद्वादाशी
prathama-dvādāśī (EI 12; SII 2), Āṣāḍha su-di 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमकायस्थ
Prathama-kāyastha (IE 8-3; EI 27; BL), representative [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-258" target="_blank">Page-258+ 39</a>] of the scribal class on the local council of administrators; the clerk-member of the Pañcāyat board (see Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 130); the chief scribe, according to some (HD).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=257" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमकुलिक
Prathama-kulika (IE 8-3; BL), literally, ‘the chief artisan’; designation of a member of the artisan class represented on an administrative board like the Pañcāyat (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 130).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमपुस्तपाल
Prathama-pustapāla (EI 15), wrongly regarded as occurring in some epigraphs; see Pustapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमस्कन्ध
prathama-skandha (LP), the first instalment. See skandha, skandhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमतरम्
prathamataram, ‘at first’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 240).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रथमतृतीया
prathama-tṛtīyā (EI 7), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रति
Prati (LP), abbreviation of Pratihārī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रति
prati, cf. śata-pratyā (LP), ‘per hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिबद्ध|प्रतिबद्धः
pratibaddha (IA 15), generally used in the sense of ‘attached to’ or ‘belonging to’ in respect of a village pertaining to a territorial unit; sometimes used in the sense of ‘hailing from’ or ‘one whose family hails from’ (cf. vinirgata generally used in the same sense).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिभाग|प्रतिभागः
pratibhāga (HRS), offerings of fruits, firewood, roots and the like payable by villagers to the king as indicated in the Manusmṛti.<BR> Cf. pati-bhāga.<BR> (CII 1), one's lot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिभेदिका
prātibhedikā (IE 8-5; EI 9, 12), an obligation or impost of uncertain meaning; may be the same as prātivedhanika.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 298, text line 20), explained by some as ‘a special right’ (CII 4); but cf. viṣṭi-prātibhedikā (EI 14); supposed to be related to umbara-bheda (q. v.) and meaning a special levy on defaulters in the payment of taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिभोग|प्रतिभोगः
pratibhoga, prātibhoga (HRS), same as pratibhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिबोध|प्रतिबोधः
pratibodha (HA), teaching in the Jain doctrine; conversion to the Jain faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिबोधित
pratibodhita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVI, p. 132, note 3), same as vijñāpita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिभू
pratibhū (EI 30), a security.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिच्छन्द|प्रतिच्छंद|प्रतिच्छंदः|प्रतिच्छन्दः|प्रतिछन्द
praticchanda, a model for artists (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 12). See lepyakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिदिश्
pratidiś, cf. bhuñjato bhojayatah kṛṣataḥ karṣayataḥ pratidiśato vā na ken = āpi paripanthanā kāryā [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-259" target="_blank">Page-259+ 40</a>] (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 280, text lines 65-66); probably, ‘to dispose of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=258" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिढक्का
pratiḍhakkā (EI 4, 29), a kind of drum; one of the royal insignia of certain kings of South India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिगणक
pratigaṇaka (EI 26), subdivision of a district; same as pratijāgaraṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिग्रह|प्रतिग्रहः
pratigraha (SITI), acceptance of gifts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहार|प्रतिहारः
Pratihāra, Pratīhāra (EI 23; BL), also called Pratihārin (EI 3, 23), ‘a door-keeper’; but cf. Mahāpratihāra who was a high officer; officer in charge of the defence of the royal palace or bed-chamber or the head of the guards of the city gate; a chamberlain or inditer of grants, according to some (HD); personal attendant of a king, according to others (CII; 4). See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 73; Vol. IX, p. 192; Bṛhaspati quoted by Viśvarūpa on the Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 307 (for his qualifications); Mahābhārata, Ādiparvan, 85. 28-29; Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 12; Śukra, I. 121. Cf. Antaḥ-pratīhāra (IE 8-3), Rajju-pratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहार|प्रतिहारः
pratihāra (IE 8-5), levy for the maintenance of the door-keepers of the city gates; cf. pratihāra-prastha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहारप्रस्थ
pratihāra-prastha (HRS), tax paid by the villagers at the rate of one prastha of grain for payment to the Pratihāra; see pratihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहाररक्षी
Pratihāra-rakṣī (IE 8-3; LL), ‘a female door-keeper’; a female officer in charge of the gates of the royal harem or the personal attendant of a queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहारिन्
Pratihārin (EI 23, 30), official designation; same as Prati-hāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिहस्त|प्रतिहस्तः
Pratihasta, cf. Od̤iyā Paḍihasta (EI 28), a representative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिजागरणक
pratijāgaraṇaka (IE 8-4; EI 9, 32; CII 4), a territorial unit often found in Paramāra inscriptions; same as parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिक|प्रतिकः
pratika, cf. Prakrit paḍika (EI 8), see pratikaṃ śatam, ‘one coin per cent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिकर|प्रतिकरः
pratikara, cf. kara; also a-kiñchit-pratikara (EI 23), ‘land without any yield of revenue’.<BR> (HRS), compensatory allowance paid by the government to dispossessed owners of rent-fee land, as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिकरण
pratikaraṇa, repairs; cf. khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-pratikaraṇa, same as khaṇḍa-sphuṭita-jīrṇoddhāra (q. v.).<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 114, note 2), meeting the expenses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=259" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिक्रमण|प्रतिक्रमणं
pratikramaṇa (LP), morning and evening prayers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिमा
pratimā, cf. pratimam (SII 2), image of a human being; usually, the image of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिनर्तक
Pratinartaka (CII 3; BL; HD), an official title; perhaps meaning ‘a herald’; cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 190 (a person described as tanniyukta-pratinartaka-kulaputr-āmātya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिनिधि|प्रतिनिधिः
Pratinidhi, a representative (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 150).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिनिवासिन्
Pratinivāsin (EI 20), same as Nivāsin, a resident.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपद्
pratipad (CII 1), ‘to follow’; same as anuvṛt, anupratipad.<BR> (Select Inscriptions, p. 281, text line 10); cf. pratipādya, ‘having decided’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपदा
pratipadā (EI 24), a slab with foot-prints. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 247.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपादितक
pratipāditaka (EI 13), given or granted.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपन्न|प्रतिपन्नं
pratipanna, ‘decided’; cf. pratipad.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिपत्ति|प्रतिपत्तिः
pratipatti, cf. pratipattau (LP), explained as ‘convincing’; but actually ‘during the administration of … ’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिराज्य
Prātirājya (EI 3, 6), same as Pratirāja, ‘a hostile king.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिराज्यिक
Prātirājyika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 71), probably, an envoy at the court of a hostile king; but cf. Paḍirā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसमासन|प्रतिसमासनं
pratisamāsana (IE 8-8), refutation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसांवत्सरिकश्राद्ध
pratisāṃvatsarika-śrāddha (CII 4), the annual śrāddha ceremony; same as sāṃvatsarika-śrāddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसरक
Pratisaraka (IA 7), cf. Vartmapāla-Pratisaraka-Rājasthānīya; official designation; same as Pratisāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसारक
Pratisāraka (EI 31; HD), explained as an officer who collects tax and allows carts to go out of the nālī or a strip of low ground (LP); see Pratisārin; same as Pratīsāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतीसारक
Pratīsāraka (LP), explained as ‘a gate-keeper’. See Prati-sāraka, Pratisārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिसारक
Prātisāraka (HD), same as Pratisāraka. See Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 187.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिसारिन्
Pratisārin (LP) explained as ‘one who allows the merchants to go through strips of low ground’. See Pratisāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशरीर
Pratiśarīra (BI), a representative.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशासन|प्रतिशासनं
pratiśāsana (SII 11-1), a renewed charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषेध|प्रतिषेधः
pratiṣedha, cf. prakṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषिद्धाय
pratiṣiddh-āya (IA 19), same as siddh-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिश्रय|प्रतिश्रयः
pratiśraya (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), a shelter-house for travellers. See ucchraya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=260" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिष्ठा
pratiṣṭhā (EI 11; SII 1; BL; HA), installation, consecration; ceremony of installation or consecration (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 20).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिष्ठान|प्रतिष्ठानं
pratiṣṭhāna, cf. yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāna (CII 2-1), used in the sense of pratiṣṭhāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिष्ठापित
pratiṣṭhāpita, cf. a-pratiṣṭhāpita (ML); interred.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशूरक
Pratiśūraka (EI 31), probably, the superintendent of wrestling; cf. Pratiśūrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिशूरिक
Pratiśūrika (IE 8-3), probably, the superintendent of gladiatorial^1 combats; cf. Pratiśūraka.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिटिप्पनक
pratiṭippanaka (LP), a receipt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवासुदेव
Prati-vāsudeva (HA), an enemy of Vāsudeva in Jain mythology.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवेदक
Prativedaka (IE 8-3; CII 1), a reporter or spy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवेदना
prativedanā (CII 1), reporting of news.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रातिवेधनिक
prātivedhanika (HRS), punching-fee collected from merchants at the time of the inspection of weights and measures, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिवेश्य|प्रतिवेश्यः
prativeśya, prātiveśika (CII 1), a neighbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिविधान|प्रतिविधानं
pratividhāna (CII 1), supporting [with money]; gift [of money].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिव्यञ्जन
prativyañjana, Tamil paḍi-viñjanam (SITI), articles other than rice for the preparation of food-offerings in a temple, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतोली
pratolī (EI 9; CII 3; BL), a gate-way; a gate-way with a flight of steps; a gate-way strongly built and considerably high.<BR> (EI 31), probably, a street.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतोलिका
pratolikā (EI 1), same as pratolī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यब्दकाल
pratyabda-kāla (EI 3), an anniversary [of death].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यादाय
pratyādāya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 21; Vol. XIV, p. 196; Vol. XXXV, p. 127), income or tax; cf. pratyāya in the same sense.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यंश
pratyaṃśa, see agra-pratyaṃśa (ML); a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यन्धारुवा
pratyandhāruvā (IE 8-5; EI 12, 33), Od̤iyā; probably pratyarthāruvā (Sanskrit pratyartha-rūpyaka), name of a tax or levy of uncertain import; probably, a levy on the money realised by money-lenders from debtors. See arthāruvā, pāukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यन्त|प्रत्यंत|प्रत्यन्तः
pratyanta (IE 8-4; CII 1), a state beyond the borders of one's territories; a land outside one's dominions; also its people; cf. anta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यन्तनृपति
Pratyanta-nṛpati (EI 15), ruler of a bordering state.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यर्थारुवा
pratyarthāruvā (IE 8-5), a tax of uncertain import; probably [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-262" target="_blank">Page-262+ 40</a>] Sanskrit pratyartha-rūpyaka in the sense of a levy on amounts realised by the money lenders from debtors; also read as pratyandhāruvā; see arthāruvā and pāukā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=261" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यय|प्रत्ययः
Pratyaya, probably, a lessee (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 143-44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यय|प्रत्ययः
pratyaya (EI 11, 15), a holding; sometimes also written as pratyāya (cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 170, note 5).<BR> Cf. Prakrit avija-pracaga saṃkara (CII 2-1) = Sanskrit avidyā-pratyayāḥ saṃskārāḥ, ‘in inter-connection with delusion are the saṃkāras’, i. e. the saṃkāras spring from avidyā.<BR> Cf. etat-pratyaye, in this matter (Select Inscriptions, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्याय|प्रत्यायः
pratyāya (IE 8-5; EI 29; HRS), revenue; income or tax; dues payable to the king including bhāga-bhoga-kara and hiraṇya; cf. bhūla-vāta-pratyāya (EI 10). See pratyaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्यय|प्रत्ययः
pratyaya, pratyāya (CII 3), primarily ‘income’ and secondarily ‘a holding, the income of which is enjoyed.’ Cf. amuka-pratyaya-amuka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्येकबुद्ध
Pratyeka-Buddha, cf. Prakrit Pracega-Budha (CII 2-1), Buddhist; name of certain Buddhas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रत्युपगमन
pratyupagamana (CII 1), meeting personally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रौढप्रताप
Prauḍha-pratāpa (IE 8-2), cf. Pratāpa and Vīrapratāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रौढप्रतापचक्रवर्तिन्
Prauḍha-pratāpa-cakravartin (IE 8-2), see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवचन|प्रवचनं|प्रवचनः
pravacana, exposition of texts (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 150).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवहण|प्रवहणं
pravahaṇa (LP), same as vāhana; a boat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवहणघोटक
pravahaṇa-ghoṭaka, (LP), a carriage horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवण|प्रवणः
pravaṇa (EI 1), ‘excellent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवणि
Pravaṇi (CII 4), a banker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवणिकर
pravaṇikara (EI 18, 24, 26; HRS), cf. yathādīyamāna-bhāga-bhoga-kara-pravaṇikara-kūṭaka-prabhṛti-samast-ādaya (IE 8-5), known from the Gāhaḍavāla records; a minor tax other than what was bhāga-bhoga-kara, according to some; explained by some as a tax levied from a class of merchants. See pravaṇivāda.<BR> (IA 15), explained as hiraṇya or tax in cash.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवणिवाद
pravaṇivāda (EI 21), name of a tax; cf. pravaṇikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर|प्रवरं|प्रवरः
pravara (IA 19), an invocation of ancestors at the performance of certain rites.<BR> (CII 4), a member of the executive committee of a corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रावारञ्चर
Prāvārañcara (EI 24), supposed to be ‘a licensed spy’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=262" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्ह|प्रवर्हः
pravarha (EI 13), see prabarha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्तवाप
pravartavāpa (EI 32), also called pravarta; a land measure; cf. pravarti and pravartikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्तमान|प्रवर्त्तमान
pravartamāna (IA 18, 19), current [year]; cf. atīta or expired.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्तन|प्रवर्तनं|प्रवर्त्तन|प्रवर्त्तनं
pravartana (CII 1), establishment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवर्ति
pravarti, pravartikā (EI 32), a measure of capacity; cf. pauṭi, pravarta and pravartavāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवेश|प्रवेशः
praveśa, prāveśa (EI 17), explained as ‘a small territorial unit’; but probably refers to the assessment of the rent of a locality along with another; cf. Siviḍi-praveśa-Kandalivāḍa-grāma interpreted as ‘Kandalivāḍa-grāma having its rent assessed along with Siviḍi’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 59, note 1). See prāveśya, prāpīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवेशभागिक
Praveśa-bhāgika (HD), a subordinate officer of the treasury who received cash payments, according to Stein (Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII, 278).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रवेशक|प्रवेशकः
praveśaka (SITI), admission, entry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रावेश्य
prāveśya (EI 31), also spelt praveśya; explained by some as a small territorial unit; sometimes translated as ‘situated in’ (CII 4); but may refer to the revenue^1 assessment of a village along with another; cf. Ardhaṭi-prāveśya-Lavaṅgasikāyām (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 143); same as praveśa. Cf. Hastiśīrṣa-prāveśya-Tāpasapottake with Siviḍi-praveśa-Kandalivāḍa-grāma interpreted as ‘Kandalivāḍa-grāma having its rent assessed along with Siviḍi.’ Same as prāpīya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 109); cf. Akṣa-saraka-prāveśya used in the sense as Akṣasaraka-prāpīya.<BR> Cf. praveśa, prāveśa, prāpīya (LP), also patra-pṛṣṭhato praveśyo dātavyaḥ, ‘should get [the sum] entered at the back of the document’ (dātavya from dā ‘to cut’).<BR> Cf. a-prāveśya, etc. (IE 8-5); entrance.<BR> (IE 8-8; EI 30), an entry tax or levies relating to the entry of royal agents.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रव्रजित|प्रव्रजितः
pravrajita (CII 1; LL), a Buddhist monk; an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रव्रजिता
pravrajitā (LL), a Buddhist nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रयाणदण्ड
prayāṇa-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 25, 26), cf. rājasevakānāṃ vasati-daṇḍa-prayāṇa-daṇḍau na staḥ; refers to the obligation of the villagers to provide free conveyance and carriage of loads, etc., when royal officers passed through their village. Prayāṇa thus seems to mean ‘passage, transit’, and daṇḍa ‘levy’; cf. rūḍhabhāroḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रयोजन|प्रयोजनं
prayojana (LP), need; cf. drammaiḥ hasta-prāptaiḥ prayojanaṃ jāyate [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-264" target="_blank">Page-264+ 40</a>] (LP), ‘when there is a necessity of having the money back [before the stated time].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=263" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रायोपवेशाधिकृत
Prāyopaveś-ādhikṛta (HD), officer who watched those that had resolved to fast unto death at the palace gate. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रयुक्त|प्रयुक्तं
prayukta (IA 15), ‘drawn up’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेगडा
Prěgaḍā (EI 9), Kannaḍa; a minister. Cf. Pěrgaḍě, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेषण|प्रेषणं
preṣaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 9, text lines 13-14), service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेक्षणक|प्रेक्षणकं
prekṣaṇaka (EI 22), a show.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेषणिक
Preṣaṇika (IE 8-3), officer in charge of the despatch of messengers; the dispatcher of messengers; cf. Praiṣaṇika, Vaik-ṣepika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेष्यकुल
Preṣya-kula (EI 33), a batch of workers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रेतदक्षिणा
preta-dakṣiṇā, cf. peta-dakkhinā (EI 24), a gift to one's dead ancestors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रियदर्शिन्
Priyadarśin (CII 1), cf. Priyadasi (EI 5), secondary name of the Maurya king Aśoka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रो
Pro, abbreviation of Prohita = Sanskrit Purohita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 192).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रोहत
Prohata, Prohita (Chamba, etc.) a priest; from Sanskrit Purohita.<BR> Cf. Para.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृड
pṛḍa, see mṛḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृष्ठ|पृष्ठं
pṛṣṭha, cf. pṛṣṭhe hastaḥ (LP), ‘hand on someone's back’; a sign of warning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृथिवी
pṛthivī, cf. Prakrit sava-puṭhaviyaṃ (CII, Vol. I, p. 87, text line 7); used to indicate the dominions of the Maurya emperor Aśoka, versions other than Dhauli (Rock Edict V) having sarvatra vijite (i. e. ‘everywhere within the dominions’) in its place. Cf. Jambudvīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृथ्वी
pṛthvī (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृथ्वीलिङ्ग
pṛthvī-liṅga (SII 2), a Śivaliṅga made of earth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रुड्
pruḍ, see mṛḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पु
pu (PJS), abbreviation of putra, ‘a son’ (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजा
pūjā (CII 1; ML), an honour; the act of honouring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजाहारि
Pūjāhāri (EI 33), same as Pūjāri (Sanskrit pūjādhārin); priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजक|पूजकः
Pūjaka (SITI), one who performs worship; a temple priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजामात्य
Pūj-āmātya (IA 11), official designation; cf. ‘the Pūj-āmātya of the province of Timbāṇaka’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=264" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुजारि
Pūjāri (EI 5, 15), a priest; a temple priest; called Pūjārī or Pūjāhārī (Sanskrit Pūjādhārin) in the early medieval records of Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजाशिला
pūjā-śilā (EI 16, 22), same as śālagrāma-śilā (the stone emblem of Viṣṇu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूजावृत्ति
pūjā-vṛtti (SITI), tax-free land endowed to a temple for conducting worship. Cf. tala-vṛtti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुक्कोलि
pukkoli, pukkolli, pukkūli (IE 8-8), cf. pukkoli-kṣetra, explained as ‘an arecanut palm plantation’. An inscription of Kadamba Mṛgeśvarman seems to suggest that it really means ‘land inundated by floods’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 152). See khajjana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुक्कोलिखज्जन
pukkoli-khajjana (EI 33), a type of land; see khajjana and pukkoli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुक्कोलिक्षेत्र
pukkoli-kṣetra (EI 33), a type of land like khajjana; see pukkoli or pukkoli-khajjana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूलक|पूलकः
pūlaka (CII 4), a small bundle (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुनर्जन्मन्
Punarjanman (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 290, text line 3), used in the sense of Dvijanman (i. e. a Brāhmaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्डरीक|पुंडरीक|पुंडरीकं|पुण्डरीकं|पुण्डरीकः
puṇḍarīka (CII 3; BL), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्याहवाचक
puṇyāha-vācaka (EI 11), a priest who officiates in a ceremony and proclaims by means of mantras a happy day to the ceremony and its performer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्याहवाचन|पुण्याहवाचनं
puṇyāha-vācana (IA 14), a ceremony; cf. puṇyāha-vācaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुण्यवाचन
puṇya-vācana (IA 21), a purificatory rite [in Madras]; cf. puṇyāha-vācana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुर|पुरं|पुरः
pura, a temple (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 184). See bhavana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूरक|पूरकः
pūraka (CII 3; etc.), used as a termination of the names of villages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुराण|पुराणं|पुराणः
purāṇa (IE 8-8; EI 12, 21, 29), name of a coin; a silver coin also called dharaṇa and kārṣāpaṇa (32 or 24 ratis); cf. kapar-daka-purāṇa (EI 26), meaning purāṇa calculated in cowrie-shells; also paṇa-purāṇa (i. e. purāṇa counted in copper paṇas).<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 246), the Purāṇa texts, e. g. the Āditya Purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुराणलक्षण
purāṇa-lakṣaṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरपालोपरिक
Purapāl-oparika (IE 8-2, 8-3; BL), official designation probably indicating the governor of a city or chief amongst the governors of cities; called Mahārāja, Mahāsāmanta, Mahāprati-hāra, Mahāpīlupati, Pañcakaraṇoparika and Pāṭyuparika additionally (IE 8-3). The expression may also mean two different [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-266" target="_blank">Page-266+ 40</a>] designations, viz. Purapāla and Uparika. With Purapāla, cf. Pura-pati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=265" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरपति
Purapati (EI 25), mayor of a town; cf. Pura-pradhāna, Puraśreṣṭhin, Nagara-śreṣṭhin, Purillaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरप्रधान
Pura-pradhāna (CII 4), mayor of a city; cf. Purapati, Puraśreṣṭhin, Nagara-śreṣṭhin, Purillaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरश्रेष्ठिन्
Pura-śreṣṭhin (EI 25), official designation; same as Nagara-śreṣṭhin, Pura-pradhāna, Purapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरतोभद्र
puratobhadra (EI 9), probably, a building with only one gate in the front side.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरिल्लक
Purillaka (EI 29; CII 4), explained as ‘the mayor of a town.’ Cf. rāja-sāmanta-viṣayapati-grāmabhogika-purillaka-cāṭa-bhaṭa-sevak-ādin (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIX, pp. 114-15); also Deśillaka and Pura-pati, Pura-pradhāna, Pura-śreṣṭhin, Vīthillaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्ण|पूर्णः
pūrṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्णघटकपट्ट
pūrṇaghaṭaka-paṭṭa (LL), slab bearing the representation of a flower-vase.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्णिमान्त
pūrṇimānta (CII 3, etc.), the technical name for the scheme of the lunar months in Northern India, according to which the months end with the full-moon day, and the dark fortnights precede the bright; Fleet states that in astronomical works, it is always the amānta arrangement that is actually taken for calculations though, even in Southern India, the pūrṇimānta arrangement was used with the Śaka years, for the civil reckoning, up to between 804 and 866 A. D.; on the other hand, according to him, even in Northern India, it was not used with the Newar era in Nepal, though it was adopted there when the Newar era was followed by the Vikrama era in its northern variety.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोग|पुरोगः
Puroga (EI 23), prominent among a particular class of people; sometimes wrongly taken to be the same as Purohita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोहित|पुरोहितः
Purohita (CII 4; SII 1; BL; ASLV; HD), a priest; a family priest; the royal priest; occurs in the list of functionaries in records like those of the Gāhaḍavālas (Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305) and Senas (ibid., Vol. XII, p. 9). See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, pp. 111-12, 117.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोनायक
Puro-nāyaka (IE 8-3; EI 28), the chief Nāyaka; probably the same as Paṭṭa-nāyaka or Puro-Parīkṣaka; cf. Nāyaka. Puro may really be the modification of a Dravidian word (cf. Tamil Por̤r̤u).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोपरीक्ष
Puro-parīkṣa (EI 28, 31), probably, the same as Paṭṭa-parīkṣaka, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-267" target="_blank">Page-267+ 40</a>] ‘the chief superintendent’; the chief superintendent of a department. Puro may really be the modification of a Dravidian word (cf. Tamil Por̤r̤u).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=266" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोप्रतिहस्त
Puro-pratihasta (EI 31), probably, ‘the chief representative’. Puro may really be the modification of a Dravidian word (cf. Tamil Por̤r̤u).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरोश्रीकरण
Puro-śrīkaraṇa (EI 31), probably, ‘the chief secretary’. Puro may really be the modification of a Dravidian word (cf. Tamil Por̤r̤u).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुष|पुरुषः
Puruṣa (IE 8-3), same as Rāja-puruṣa, ‘royal officer or agent.’<BR> (HD) an inferior servant (Arthaśāstra, II. 5) or a bailiff attached to a court of justice (as in Bṛhaspati). See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 278.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषच्छाय
puruṣa-cchāya (EI 14), name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषाकार
puruṣ-ākāra (SITI), human form.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषारिक
puruṣārika, cf. ardha-puruṣārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषार्थ|पुरुषार्थः
puruṣ-ārtha (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषोत्तमपुत्र
Puruṣottama-putra (EI 33), epithet of one devoted to the god Puruṣottama-Jagannātha of Purī. See Rudra-putra, Durgā putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषयुग
puruṣa-yuga, cf. Prakrit purisa-yuga (EI 20); a generation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरुषायुस्
puruṣ-āyus (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्व|पूर्वः|पूर्व्व|पूर्व्वः
pūrva (IE 7-1-2), sometimes used to indicate ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वा|पूर्व्वा
pūrvā (IE 8-8; CII 4; ML), ‘the above’; ‘the aforesaid (tithi or praśasti)’; used with reference to a tithi and a praśasti; sometimes wrongly used as a synonym of a tithi or praśasti.<BR> Cf. anupūrvī used with reference to a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वाचार
pūrv-ācāra (SII 3; SITI), an old usage or ancient custom. Cf. pūrva-rīti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वाग्रहारिक
Pūrv-āgrahārika (EI 23), the former holder of an agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वमर्यादा
pūrva-maryādā (ASLV), ancient constitutional usage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वराज
pūrva-rāja (EI 17), a king of eastern countries or of early times.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वरीति
pūrva-rīti (LP), old custom. Cf. pūrv-ācāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वसिद्धायतन
pūrva-siddh-āyatana (EI 33), epithet of a Buddhist temple; see siddh-āyatana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्कल|पुष्कलं|पुष्कलः
puṣkala (IE 8-6), a measure of capacity usually regarded as equal to sixtyfour handfuls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्कर|पुष्करं|पुष्करः
puṣkara (ML), a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्प|पुष्पं
puṣpa (IE 8-8), a coin having the shape or sign of flower.<BR> Cf. a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa (IE 8-5), flowers which [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-268" target="_blank">Page-268+ 40</a>] the villagers (probably, the florists) were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=267" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्पक|पुष्पकं
puṣpaka (CII 4), a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्त|पुस्तं
pusta (CII 4), painting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तक|पुस्तकं|पुस्तकः
pustaka, cf. Tamil pottagam (SITI); register, as of land and revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तकभाण्डार
Pustaka-bhāṇḍāra (EI 25), a library.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तकपाल
Pustakapāla (IE 8-3; EI 6, 29), record-keeper; same as Pustapāla; cf. Peṭapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुस्तपाल|पुस्तपालः
Pustapāla (IE 8-3; EI 28; CII 4; HD), record-keeper; occurs in epigraphs like the Damodarpur plates of the Gupta age (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 13; cf. Vol. XX, p. 61).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्यराग|पुष्यरागः
puṣya-rāga (SITI), same as puṣpa-rāga; a kind of gem.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुष्यरथ|पुष्यरथः
puṣya-ratha (EI 3), a car. Cf. puṣpa-ratha or puṣpaka-ratha, the celestial car.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुटि
puṭi (EI 33), same as puṭṭi or puṭṭidosillu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूति|पूतिः
pūti (EI 12, 14), also read as yūti; cf. tṛṇa-pūti (or yūti)-go-cara-paryanta, epithet of a gift village. The expression tṛṇa-pūti or tṛṇa-yūti may mean ‘grass-land’. The word is sometimes written as yutī and yuthī also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
putra, cf. Kerala-putra, king of the Keralas; Guhila-putra, descendant of Guhila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्र|पुत्त्रः|पुत्रः
putra, cf. Nigama-putra (LL), ‘the inhabitant of a nigama (township).’<BR> Cf. Durgā-putra, Puruṣottama-putra, etc.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), probably confused with pāṇḍu-putra and used to indicate ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रसूनु
putra-sūnu (SII 2), used in the sense of pautra, ‘son's son’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुट्टि
puṭṭi (CITD), Telugu; a measure equal to twenty tūmus; also called khaṇḍi (spelt candy in English and found as khaṇḍikā in Sanskrit inscriptions) and regarded as equal to between 800 and 1000 seers. Khaṇḍi at Masulipatam has 3 weights, viz. 488 pounds for tobacco, 500 pounds for metals, hardware, etc., and 560 pounds for sugar, dates and other soft articles. The puṭṭi and its fractions also denote the area of the land that is supposed by some to produce the particular quantities of grain. According to some, it is a land measure equal to 8 acres being presumably the area which can be sown with a puṭṭi of grain. There were different kinds of puṭṭis, e. g. gāl-puṭṭi. Cf. also pelle-puṭṭi regarded as equal to 80 kuñcas and Malaca-puṭṭi or Malacca ton as equal to 300 to 240 kuñcas.<BR> (EI 4, 27), a land and grain measure. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-269" target="_blank">Page-269+ 38</a>]<BR> (IE 8-5), same as Telugu puṭṭi-dosillu, ‘a fee of two handfuls from each puṭṭi of grain paid to the village-servants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=268" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुट्टिदोसिल्लु
puṭṭi-dosillu (EI 33), a levy; see puṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्योडा
pyoḍā (Chamba), a grain measure; also spelt piṭha, piḍā, peḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रा
Rā (LP), abbreviation of Rājaputra, Rāuta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राभस्य|राभस्यं
rābhasya (CII 1), a crime.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राच्छपोच्छ
rāccha-poccha (LP), Gujarātī; household furniture.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रचित|रचितः
racita (CII 3; etc.), composed; a technical term used in connection with the composition of a record, as opposed to the writing on the plate or slab for facilitating the work of engraving and also to engraving. Cf. cintita in Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 59.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रद|रदः
rada (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtytwo’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राधा
rādhā (EI 8), a posture of standing with the feet a span apart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राधान्त
rādhānta (EI 3), same as siddhānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राग|रागः
rāga (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहापयति
rahāpayati (LP), ‘he keeps’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राहसिक
Rāhasika (IE 8-3; EI 27, 30), same as Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.; a privy councillor; a private secretary or adviser.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहसिनियुक्त
Rahasi-niyukta (IE 8-3), a private secretary; same as Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहस्य|रहस्यं
Rahasya (IE 8-3; EI 3-6, 23, 27, 30), a private secretary; same as Rāhasika, Rahasy-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रहस्याधिकृत
Rahasy-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 6, 27, 30; SITI; HD), a privy councillor or private secretary; same as Rahasya, Rāhasika, Rahasi-niyuka, etc.; cf. also Vaiśvāsika, Paramaviśvāsin Mahāpara-maviśvāsin, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 7; Vol. VI, p. 13; Vol. XXII, p. 298.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राहुत
Rāhuta, Rāhutta (IE 8-2), same as Rāvata = Sanskrit Rāja-putra; a title of nobility.<BR> (IA 20), also called Rāuta; explained as ‘a horseman.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राहुत्तरायन्
Rāhutta-rāyan (SITI), Sanskrit Rājaputra-rājan; title of nobility; explained as ‘a cavalry officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रैक्वाल
Raikvāla (Chamba), the king's personal servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज|राजः
Rāja (LP), abbreviation of Rājaputra (Rājpūt); explained as a cavalry-soldier or a Rājpūt. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-270" target="_blank">Page-270+ 40</a>] 143-44, where it is probably an abbreviation of Rājakula (Rāval).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=269" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभाग
rāja-bhāga (LP), government revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभण्डार
rāja-bhaṇḍāra (SITI, ASLV), Sanskrit rāja-bhāṇḍāra; royal treasury or store-house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभोग|राजभोगः
rāja-bhoga (EI 12), also rāja-sambhoga; dues enjoyed by the king or land belonging to the king's Khās Mahāls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजदण्ड|राजदण्डः
rāja-daṇḍa (SII 1), punishment imposed by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजदत्ति
rāja-datti (EI 23), a royal gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजदौवारिक|राजदौवारिकः
Rāja-dauvārika (EI 2; BL), door-keeper of the royal palace (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 115). See Dauvārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजधानी
rājadhānī (EI 23), the capital; sometimes used to indicate the headquarters of a chief or governor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाधिराज|राजाधिराजः
Rājādhirāja (IE 8-2; EI 21, 22, 30; CII 3, 4), title of paramount sovereignty; an imperial title meaning ‘the king of kings’; used in the Gupta period in some metrical passages, both alone and along with Rājarājādhirāja. Cf. Adhirājarāja (EI 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाध्यक्ष
Rājādhyakṣa (IA 12; SII 11-2), official designation; probably the same as Rājasthānīya, literally, ‘an officer acting for the king.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजद्रोह|राजद्रोहः
rāja-droha (SITI), treason against the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजद्वार
rāja-dvāra (EI 32), king's court.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजग्रह
rāja-graha (IE 8-8); apprehension or recruitment in the king's name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजगृह
rāja-gṛha, cf. Tamil rāja-karam (SITI); palace (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107) or government; officers or authorities; also the taxes due to the same. Cf. rājakaraṅ-kāṇikkai, ‘customary presents to be made to the palace’; rājakara-upādi, ‘tax payable to the palace or to the government officers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजगुरु|राजगुरुः
Rājaguru (EI 21, 27, 30; CII 4; BL; ASLV; HD), king's preceptor. Cf. Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354; Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 120.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजहुण्डिका
rāja-huṇḍikā (LP), the royal bill of exchange.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाज्ञाप्रद
Rājājñāprada (EI 27), probably, the same as Ājñapti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकदैवक
rājaka-daivaka (LP), calamities owing to the king or the gods; cf. rājaka-daivaka-vaśāt (LP).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकर|राजकरः
rāja-kara, cf. rāja-garam (ASLV), taxes in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकार्य|राजकार्य्य
rāja-kārya (SITI), duties of the state; official work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकार्यभाण्डार
rājakārya-bhāṇḍāra (SITI; ASLV), a treasury related to state business; an official committee of management.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=270" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकीय|राजकीयः
rājakīya (LP), government tax.<BR> Cf. samasta-rājakīyānām = apraveśya (IE 8-5); same as Rāja-puruṣa or Rāja-sevaka; also Rāja-satka; an officer of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकीयमान
rājakīya-māna (EI 23), same as rāja-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकुल
Rājakula (IE 8-5; CII 3; IA 20; BL; HD), royal household; the king, royal officers and members of the royal family. Originally, ‘the royal family’; then ‘a member of the royal family’; and then ‘a royal officer’; later, a title of nobility, same as modern Rāval or Rāul. See Bhandarkar's List, No. 324.<BR> Cf. rājakulaṅ-kāṇi-ppar̤r̤u (SITI), ‘land or village in the enjoyment of the members of the royal family’. The expression occurs along with devadāna, brahmadeya, pal̤l̤iccandam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजकुमार|राजकुमारः
Rājakumāra (IE 8-3; LL; HD), same as Rājaputra; designation of a prince. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजलिपिकर
Rāja-lipikara (IE 8-3; EI 2; LL), king's scribe.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजमान
rāja-māna (IE 8-6; EI 12, 23, 28; SII 11-1), royal measure; the standard measure fixed or accepted by the king or government; same as rājakīya-māna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजमाङ्गलीयक
rāja-māṅgalīyaka (LP), auspicious occasions for the royal family.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजामात्य
Rāj-āmātya (EI 26; CII 3; HD), Prakrit Rāy-āmaca; the king's minister. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 91; CII, Vol. III, pp. 213, 216.<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes used to indicate the ministers of the feudatory rulers; see Amātya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजमुद्राधिकारिन्
Rājamudr-ādhikārin (BL), official designation indicating the keeper of the royal seal or a governor. Cf. Mudr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजन्
Rājan (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; HD), royal title; originally used by imperial rulers; later, when emperors assumed more dignified titles, a title of feudatories and smaller rulers. Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 121; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 297.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजनक
Rājanaka (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 23, 29), same as Rājānaka, Rājanyaka, Rājānika; a feudatory; in some cases, smaller than the feudatory called Rājan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजानक|राजानकः
Rājānaka (IE 8-2, 8-3; EI 30; BL; HD), same as Rājanaka, Rājanyaka, Rājānika or Rāṇaka; title of feudatory rulers or of the nobility; often a feudatory smaller than a Rājan. Cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 117, 261 (title given for services to the king and surviving in the form Rāzdān as a family name of Kashmir Brāhmaṇas); Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, pp. 394, 306.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=271" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजानिक
Rājānika (EI 1), same as Rājanaka, Rājānaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाङ्क
rāj-āṅka (EI 22), brand of royal animals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजन्य|राजन्यः
Rājanya (ASLV; SITI), officers of the king.<BR> (IA 22), same as Kṣatriya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजन्यक|राजन्यकं
Rājanyaka (IE 8-2; EI 15, 23, 29; HD), same as Rājanaka, Rājānaka, Rājānika or Rāṇaka, title of subordinate rulers. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपं
Rāja-paṃ (BL), abbreviation of Rāja-paṇḍita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपण्डित
Rāja-paṇḍita (EI 32), a court Pandit; a scholar patronised by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपरमेश्वर
Rāja-parameśvara (EI 4, 20), imperial title. Cf. Rāja-rājaparameśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपातिका
rāja-pātikā (EI 1), royal procession.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपट्ट|राजपट्टः
rāja-paṭṭa, cf. rāja-paṭṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपट्टी
rāja-paṭṭī (EI 4; BL), royal fillet or tiara; status of a ruler or a feudatory indicated by turban. Same as rāja-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपुरुष|राजपुरुषः
Rājapuruṣa (IE 8-5), a royal agent or officer; same as Rāja-sevaka or Rājakīya; cf. also Rāja-satka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपुत्र|राजपुत्त्रः|राजपुत्रः
Rāja-putra (EI 30; CII 3; 4; HD), originally ‘a prince’; title of princes and subordinate rulers; but later a title of nobility especially in the modified forms Rāvata, Rāuta, etc.; sometimes also used in the sense of ‘a Rājpūt’ often explained as ‘a horse-man’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321. See Rāja-putraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजपुत्रक
Rāja-putraka (EI 17), same as Rāja-putra; mentioned in the list of subordinates and officials addressed by the king in respect of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजप्रदेय
rāja-pradeya (SII 3), taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजप्रासादचैत्यक
rājaprāsāda-caityaka (LL), a small caitya in the royal palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराज|राजराजः
Rājarāja (IE 8-2; LL), imperial title; cf. Greek Basileos Besileon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजपरमेश्वर
Rājarāja-parameśvara (EI 4), imperial title. Cf. Rājaparameśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजार्घिका
rāj-ārghikā (IE 8-8; EI 30), name of a levy; probably, periodical offerings to the king or the king's share of articles sold in the markets.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजर्षि|राजर्षिः
Rājarṣi (EI 22), a sage-like king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसामन्त
Rājasāmanta (EI 25), a Rājan and a Sāmanta, or one feudatory enjoying both the designations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसम्भोग
rāja-sambhoga (EI 12), same as rāja-bhoga (q. v.); land [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-273" target="_blank">Page-273+ 40</a>] belonging to the king's Khās Mahāls (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 46). Cf. ratnatraya-sambhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=272" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसत्क
Rāja-satka (IE 8-3; EI 29), literally, ‘one belonging to the king’, i. e. ‘a servant of the king’; same as Rāja-puruṣa or Rāja-sevaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसेवक
Rāja-sevaka (IE 8-5), same as Rāja-puruṣa, Rājakīya or Rāja-satka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसिद्धान्त
rāja-siddhānta (EI 24), science of polity; same as rājanīti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजश्रावित
rāja-śrāvita (EI 6; IA 19), a royal decree or proclamation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजाश्रय
rāj-āśraya (IA 8), the capital; same as rājadhānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजश्रेष्ठिन्
Rāja-śreṣṭhin (HD), king's banker or the chief of the bankers. See Commentary on the Yaśastilaka, I, p. 91.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थान
Rājasthāna, same as Rājasthānīya and Rājasthān-ādhikāra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 292).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानाधिकार|राजस्थानाधिकारः
Rājasthān-ādhikāra (IE 8-3), probably, the chief justice; cf. Rājasthānīya (a viceroy), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानी
Rājasthānī, dialect of Hindī prevalent in Rajasthan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानीय|राजस्थानीयः
Rājasthānīya (IE 8-3; EI 24, 26, 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), ‘an officer acting for the king’; generally a viceroy; probably also a subordinate ruler; but cf. Rājasthān-ādhikāra who was also a judge; an official title indicating a viceroy in some areas and a judge in others; an officer who carried out the object of protecting subjects, according to some (Ind. Ant., Vol. V, p. 207). Cf. CII, Vol. III, p. 157; Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 112; Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 176 (probably, a chief justice), explained wrongly as ‘an officer connected with other kings, i. e. a foreign secretary’ (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 122, note 76).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्थानोपरिक
Rājasthān-oparika (EI 29), probably a viceroy; cf. Rājasthānīya and Uparika. See Rājasthān-ādhikāra and Rājasthānīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसूय|राजसूयः
rājasūya (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजस्व|राजस्वं
rājasva (SITI), property belonging to the king or state [by confiscation, etc.].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजातिराज
Rājātirāja (IE 8-2; EI 21, 26, 30; ML), imperial title of certain foreign rulers; cf. Basileos Basileon Megalou.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवैद्य
Rāja-vaidya (IE 8-3; LL), physician to the king; the royal physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजावली
rāj-āvalī (EI 9; IA 30), genealogy of rulers; a list of lineal succession of kings.<BR> (EI 10), royal titles; cf. rājāvalī pūrvavat (IE 8-2), ‘the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-274" target="_blank">Page-274+ 40</a>] royal titles as above’, often used when a repetition of the string of royal titles was avoided. Cf. Paramabhaṭṭārak-ety-ādi-rāj-āvalī-tray-opeta referring to the imperial titles Paramabhaṭṭāraka, Mahārājādhirāja and Parameśvara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=273" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवल्लभ|राजवल्लभः
Rāja-vallabha (EI 6, 9, 24; CII 4), explained as ‘a court-favourite’; a courtier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजावर्त|राजावर्तः|राजावर्त्त|राजावर्त्तः
rājāvarta (SII 2; SITI), a kind of gem; lapis lazuli; same as vaiḍūrya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवर्त्मन्
rāja-vartman (EI 22), a public road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजवेश्याभुजङ्ग
Rāja-veśyā-bhujaṅga (SITI), ‘the lover of the courtesans of the [enemy] kings’; a title assumed by some kings after capturing the enemies’ countries, probably describing rājya-śrī as a prostitute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजविलासिनी
rāja-vilāsinī, king's courtesan (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजविषय
rāja-viṣaya (CII 1), a king's dominions. Cf. Rājaviṣayādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजविषयाध्यक्ष
Rājaviṣay-ādhyakṣa, explained as ‘the royal superintendent of a district’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 234); but rāja-viṣaya in this case may be the king's Khās Mahāls so that the designation means ‘the superintendent of the king's Khās Mahāls.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजयोग|राजयोगः
rāja-yoga (EI 12), a particular auspicious moment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जू
rajjū (HRS), used in the Arthaśāstra probably in the sense of the cost realised by the government in connection with the expenses of land-measurement or survey.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जुग्राहकामात्य
Rajjugrāhak-āmātya (IE 8-3), same as Rajjuka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जुक|रज्जुकः
Rajjuka (IE 8-3; HD), Prakrit Rajuka or Lajūka (EI 2); an officer of the land survey and revenue department, according to some; but seems to be the governor of a district, one of whose functions was probably the survey of land with a measuring rope for the fixation of the amount of the king's share of the produce; probably the same as Greek Agronomoi mentioned by Megasthenes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रज्जुप्रतिहार
Rajju-pratihāra (EI 24), ‘rope-jugglers or dancers’; cf. rajju-pratihār-āpaṇa, ‘booths of rope-jugglers and dancers’; but rajju-pratihār-āpaṇājīvika may be a tax for maintaining surveyors and gate-keepers (toll-collectors) and from shop-keepers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्ञी
Rājñī (IE 8-2; EI 26; CII 3; HD), a queen; a title of the wives of paramount sovereigns and subordinate rulers; cf. Mahā-rājñī, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 305.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रजोहरण
rajo-haraṇa (HA), same as ogho (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्य|राज्यं
rājya (IE 8-4; EI 19), district or province of a kingdom; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-275" target="_blank">Page-275+ 40</a>] (SITI; ASLV), the biggest administrative unit of the Vijayanagara empire; same as pīṭhika; also means ‘sovereignty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=274" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्याभिषेक|राज्याभिषेकः
rājy-ābhiṣeka (IA 10), coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्यचिन्तक
Rājya-cintaka (EI 11; BL), a minister or the chief administrator; same as Rājyacintākārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्यचिन्ताकारिन्
Rājyacintākārin (EI 1), a minister or the chief administrator; same as Rājya-cintaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्याधिकृत
Rājy-ādhikṛta (EI 22, 23), chief minister; cf. Rājyādhikārin; also cf. rājya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राकाशशाङ्क
rākā-śaśāṅka (SII 1), same as rākā-viṭa; the full-moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रकतपटा
rakata-paṭā (JBORS, Vol. XVIII, pp. 219-20), Od̤iyā; Sanskrit rakta-paṭṭaka, same as rakta-mānya; also called sira-kaṭā tambā-paṭā in Od̤iyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राकाविट
rākā-viṭa (SII 1), same as rākā-śaśāṅka; the full moon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षा
rakṣā (EI 17), confirmation of a former grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षाभोग
rakṣā-bhoga (EI 9), same as rāja-bhoga, the king's share.<BR> (SITI), a fee or a share in the produce given to the village watchman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षामणि|रक्षामणिः
rakṣā-maṇi (EI 15), protecting jewel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षण|रक्षणं|रक्षणः
rakṣaṇa, cf. doṣa-vināś-āvaṣṭabdhi-rakṣaṇāya (LP), ‘for keeping it safe from the three faults, viz. doṣa, vināśa and avaṣṭabdhi’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्षणीय
rakṣaṇīya (LP), ‘to be [prepared and] maintained.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तबिन्दु|रक्तबिन्दुः
rakta-bindu (SII 2), a flaw in diamonds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तमान्य
rakta-mānya, cf. Tamil iratta-mānya, iratta-kkāṇikkai (SITI); ‘blood-present’; endowment of rent-free land for the support of the descendants of warriors killed in battle; same as mṛtyuka-vṛtti. See rudhira, rakatapaṭā, vīra-śeṣā, etc. See Ind. Arch. Rev., 1960-61, Section III, No. 42.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तपट्टक
rakta-paṭṭaka, see rakata-paṭā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तिका
raktikā (IA 27), same as ratī or guñjā (q. v.); a unit of measurment; about 1-825 grains or 119 grammes in weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राम|रामं|रामः
rāma (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रामनन्दन
rāma-nandana (EI 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रामानुजकूट
rāmānuja-kūṭa (SITI), a rest house for Vaiṣṇava travellers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्घ्|रंघ्
raṅgh (CII 1), ‘to be eager’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राण|राणं
Rāṇa (EI 16, 23), same as Rāṇaka; see Rāṇa-putra, rāṇa-kula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणा
Rāṇā (IE 8-2; EI 23, 30), derived from Rāṇaka; title of ruling chiefs; same as Rāṇa, Rāṇaka.<BR> Cf. Rannā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=275" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणक
Rāṇaka (IE 8-2; EI 23, 30; CII 4; BL; HD), derived from Rājanaka, Rājānaka or Rājanyaka; a feudatory title; title of feudatory rulers and, later, of the nobility. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR> (EI 9), explained as ‘the chief counsellor’.<BR> (EI 1), title of the great artist Śūlapāṇi described as Vārendraka-śilpi-goṣṭhī-cūḍāmaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणकचक्रवर्तिन्
Rāṇaka-cakravartin (EI 33), feudatory title; cf. Mahā-sāmantādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणकुल
rāṇa-kula (LP), same as rāja-kula (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रणरणक|रणरणकः
raṇaraṇaka (LP), anxiety.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रणस्तम्भ|रणस्तंभ|रणस्तम्भः
raṇa-stambha (CII 3, 4), a victory-pillar; a column in memory of the victory in a battle; same as jaya-stambha.<BR> (BL), a memorial pillar raised for a person who died fighting for his master on the battle-field; same as vīra-kkal (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणपुत्र
Rāṇa-putra (BL), also called Rāṇa-utra; literally, ‘the son of a subordinate king’; a title of nobility. See Rāja-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणौत्र
Rāṇa-utra (BL), see Rāṇa-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ध्र|रंध्र|रंध्रं
randhra (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘nine’; used in the sense of ‘cypher’ in a few late works.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ध्रपूरक
Randhrapūraka (CITD), probably, a musician who played on some kind of wind instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्ग|रंग|रङ्गं|रंगः|रङ्गः
raṅga (E I 15), abbreviation of raṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गभोग
raṅga-bhoga (EI 17), amusement to be arranged for a deity and land granted for it; also called śṛṅgāra-bhoga (EI 5).<BR> (CITD), enjoyment of splendour other than aṅga-bhoga or personal decoration; gift land received for raṅga-bhoga. See aṅga-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गलेख
raṅga-lekha (LP), ‘coloured letter’; probably refers to the custom of sprinkling saffron water on the letters addressed to a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गमण्डप|रंगमंडप|रङ्गमण्डपः
raṅga-maṇḍapa (SITI), inner hall of a temple; same as Tamil tiruv-araṅgu.<BR> (HA), same as sabhā-maṇḍapa; main hall in a shrine.<BR> (EI 9), hall in front of a shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गाङ्गभोग
raṅg-āṅga-bhoga (EI 3), same as aṅga-raṅga-bhoga (i. e. raṅga-bhoga and aṅga-bhoga), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रङ्गत्
raṅgat (EI 12), ‘rolling’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राणी
Rāṇī (EI 23, 33), feminine from of Rāṇa or Rāṇā (i. e. Rāṇaka); designation of a queen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=276" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ना
Rannā, name of the Sun-god's wife in West Indian mythology; probably a modification of Rājñī. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 343. The name is also spelt Raṇṇā or Rāṇā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्नेश
Ranneśa, a name of the Sun-god; cf. Rannā. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 343. The name of the Sun-god worshipped at Thanwala near Pushkar was Rannāditya (also spelt Raṇṇāditya and Rāṇāditya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशि|राशिः
rāśi (IA 17), a sign of the zodiac.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR> Cf. rāśi-ppon (SITI), also called rāśi-paṇam; explained as ‘pure gold’; probably, ‘current good coin.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिमित्र
Rāśi-mitra (EI 32), a friend of one, because of the birth of both under the same rāśi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिपण
rāśi-paṇa, also called rāśi-ppon (SITI); probably ‘current good coins’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रश्मि|रश्मिः
raśmi (IE 7-1-2), probably confused with śīta-raśmi and used to indicate ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्र|राष्ट्रं|राष्ट्रः
rāṣṭra (IE 8-3, 8-4; EI 9, 23; CII 4; LL), a district or its subdivision; often the subdivision of a district; cf. Śātavāha-nīya-rāṣṭra; also Kona-rāṣṭra (EI 32), variously called deśa, maṇḍala, sīma, sthala, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रग्रामकूट
Rāṣṭra-grāma-kūṭa (EI 28), i. e. Rāṣṭrakūḷa and Grāmakūṭa; cf. Rāṣṭra-grāma-mahattara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रग्राममहत्तर
Rāṣṭra-grāma-mahattara (IE 8-3; EI 6, 28), i. e. Rāṣṭra-mahattara and Grāma-mahattara; cf. Rāṣṭra-grāma-kūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रकूट
Rāṣṭrakūṭa (EI 8-3), same as Rāṣṭra-mahattara; either the officer in charge of a territorial unit called rāṣṭra or, more probably, a member of the administrative council of a rāṣṭra; cf. Grāma-kūṭa; also Deśakūṭa (IA 7).<BR> (EI 9), interpreted as ‘the headman of a village’.<BR> (EI 24), according to some, a land-holder.<BR> (CII 4; HD), interpreted as ‘the head of a district or subdivision’; cf. JBBRAS, Vol. XVI, p. 117.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रमहत्तर
Rāṣṭra-mahattara (IE 8-3), same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa; either the head of a territorial unit called rāṣṭra or, more probably, a member of the administrative council of a rāṣṭra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रमहत्तराधिकारिन्
Rāṣṭramahattar-ādhikārin (EI 25), official designation; probably, Rāṣṭramahattara and Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रपाल|राष्ट्रपालः
Rāṣṭrapāla (HD), head of a district, province or subdivision; same as Rāṣṭrapati. See Arthaśāstra, V. 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=277" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रपालक
Rāṣṭrapālaka (EI 28), ruler of an administrative unit called rāṣṭra; same as Rāṣṭrapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रपति|राष्ट्रपतिः
Rāṣṭrapati (EI 12, 25; HD), ruler of a province, district or subdivision called rāṣṭra; same as Rāṣṭrapāla. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, pp. 278, 285; Vol. VII, p. 39.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रविषय
rāṣṭra-viṣaya (IE 8-4), originally, a rāṣṭra, but later a viṣaya; cf. Karma-rāṣṭra-viṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रिक|राष्ट्रिकः
Rāṣṭrika (IE 8-3; CII 1; HD; LL), Prakrit Raṭhika (EI 2), Raṭṭhika (EI 7); same as Rāṣṭrin; ruler of a rāṣṭra, i. e. a district or its subdivision; also the name of a people called ‘hereditary Rāṣṭrikas’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5; Bhandarkar, Aśoka, p. 30.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 78), mentioned in the list of officials addressed by the king in respect of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रिन्
Rāṣṭrin (EI 7), ruler of a rāṣṭra; same as Rāṣṭrika. Cf. Rāṣṭrapati, Mahārāṣṭrin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रिय|राष्ट्रियः
Rāṣṭriya (IE 8-3; LL; HD), same as Rāṣṭrika, ruler of a district or province; a provincial governor. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 43; Pāṇini, IV. 2. 93; Mahābhārata, Śānti-parvan, 85. 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राष्ट्रीय|राष्ट्रीयः
Rāṣṭrīya (IE 8-3), same as Rāṣṭriya; a provincial governor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रात
Rāta (BL), modification of or mistake for Rāvata or Rāuta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथ|रथः
ratha, rock-cut temples at Mahābalipuram (Journ. Mad. Univ., Vol. XXXII, p. 140).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथाध्यक्ष
Rath-ādhyakṣa (EI 18), superintendent of chariots.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथकार|रथकारः
Rathakāra (SITI), artisan classes; also their association.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथसप्तमी
ratha-saptamī (EI 22; CII 4; IA 17), an auspicious tithi; same as Māgha śu-di 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथाष्टमी
rath-āṣṭamī EI 29; CII 4; IA 17), same as Māgha śu-di 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथयात्रा
ratha-yātrā (EI 11), a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथिक|रथिकः
Rathika, superintendent of chariots (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 156).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथोत्सव
rath-otsava (EI 16), car-festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथ्या
rathyā (EI 19), a street.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रति|रतिः
rati, ratī (IE 8-8; IA 19), also spelt rattī; a small weight; see Sanskrit raktikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राटि|राटिः
rāṭi (LP), ‘a cry’; cf. Gujarātī rād̤.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्न|रत्नं
ratna (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’; sometimes also used to indicate ‘nine’, and rarely even ‘fourteen’.<BR> (EI 22; CII 4), same as the Buddhist tri-ratna, i. e. the Buddha, Dharma and Saṅgha.<BR> (ML), a relic [of the Buddha].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=278" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नधेनु|रत्नधेनुः
ratna-dhenu (EI 13, 16, 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नगृह
ratna-gṛha (CII 3), ‘the jewel-house’; the house enshrining the three ratṅas, regarded by some as denoting a great Buddhist stūpa.<BR> (EI 19; LL), Buddhist; a sanctuary; the sanctuary of a Buddha image.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नाश्व
ratn-āśva (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नत्रय
ratna-traya (EI 8), Jain; samyag-darśana, samyag-jñāna and samyak-cāritra.<BR> (EI 27, 30, 31), Buddhist; the tri-ratna or trinity; a Buddhist religious establishment enshrining the three ratnas; rent-free land in its possession (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 46). Cf. ratnatraya-sambhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्नत्रयसम्भोग
ratnatraya-sambhoga (HRS), traced in Bengal records; rent-free holding in the possession of Buddhist religious establishments where the Buddha, Dharma and Saṅgha were worshipped; same as ratna-traya. Cf. rāja-sambhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रट्टगुडि
Raṭṭaguḍi (EI 30), same as Raṭṭoḍī; official designation; probably the same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रट्टगुल्लु
Raṭṭagul̤l̤u (EI 27), probably, the same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रत्ती
rattī, see rati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रट्टोडि
Raṭṭoḍi (EI 30), official designation; same as Raṭṭaguḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउ
Rāu (IA 18), same as Rāva (Sanskrit Rājan) or abbreviation of Rāuta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रौक्यद्र
raukya-dra (LP), abbreviation of raukya-dramma; ‘drammas in cash’; cf. raukya with Gujarātī rokad̤ā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउल
Rāula (EI 24, 28), derived from Sanskrit Rājakula; title of nobility; same as Rāvata, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रौप्यटङ्क
raupya-ṭaṅka, ‘silver ṭaṅka (q. v.)’. See JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 197. According to Nārada, a silver kārṣāpaṇa was called raupya in South India.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउत
Rāuta (IE 8-2; EI 4, 28, 30, 31; CII 4; BL), same as Rāvata = Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatory rulers and noblemen.<BR> (IA 20), also called Rāhutta; explained as ‘a horseman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राउत्त
Rāutta (IE 8-2; EI 5, 30, 32), same as Rāuta or Rāvata = Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatories and noblemen. See Rāuta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राव|रावः
Rāva (IE 8-2; BL), spelt in English as Rao; title of subordinate rulers and noblemen; derived from Sanskrit Rājan; cf. Rāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=279" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राव|रावः
rāva (LP), a complaint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावल्
Rāval (BL), title of subordinate rulers and noblemen; derived from Sanskrit Rājakula.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावल
Rāvala (EI 24; BL), same as Rāval; derived from Sanskrit Rājakula; title of subordinate rulers and noblemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावणभुज
rāvaṇa-bhuja (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावणहस्त
rāvaṇa-hasta (ASLV), a musical instrument; may also indicate ‘twenty’ (cf. rāvaṇa-bhuja).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावणशिरस्
rāvaṇa-śiras (IE 7-1-2), ‘ten’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावत्
Rāvat (EI 32), a title of subordinate rulers and noblemen; same as Rājaputra, Rāuta, etc. See Rāvata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावत
Rāvata (IE 8-2; BL), same as Rāvat; derived from Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatories and noblemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रवि|रविः
ravi (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रविबाण
ravi-bāṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रविचन्द्र
ravi-candra (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रावुतु
Rāvutu (EI 21), same as Rāuta, Rāvata, etc.; derived from Sanskrit Rājaputra; a title of feudatories and noblemen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राट
Rāwa (EI 30), variant spelling of Rāva; derived from Sanskrit Rājan; title of nobility.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राय|रायः
Rāya (IE 8-2; BL), title of nobility; derived from Sanskrit Rājan; cf. Rāva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायराउत
Rāya-rāuta (EI 31), title of nobility; derived from Sanskrit Rāja-rājaputra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायराय
Rāyarāya (EI 21), title of nobility; derived from Sanskrit Rājarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायरेख
rāya-rekha (IA 15), a system of land measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायस
Rāyasa (EI 3, 17; ASLV), Kannaḍa; a secretary; an officer in the Vijayanagara administration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायस
rāyasa (ASLV), royal order.<BR> (SITI), office of a writer; clerkship; order of the king; written orders. Cf. Rāyasa-svāmin, head of the rāyasa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रायसस्वामिन्
Rāyasa-svāmin (ASLV), ‘the head of the rāyasa’ (SITI); the chief secretary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋद्धि|ऋद्धिः
ṛddhi (EI 3), supernatural power.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋद्धिपाद
ṛddhi-pāda, cf. iddhi-pāda (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेड्डि
Reḍḍi (ASLV), a village official.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेखा
rekhā (EI 19), a land measure.<BR> Cf. rekai, rekai-ppon (SITI), irekai; regarded as the name [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-281" target="_blank">Page-281+ 40</a>] of a gold coin (probably bearing signs in straight lines); used in Vijayanagara inscriptions; probably, revenue income in cash.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=280" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेखादण्ड
rekhā-daṇḍa (EI 14), name of a linear measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेष
reṣa (IE 8-8), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रिन्तकावड्डि
rintakāvaḍḍi (EI 33), name of a levy; cf. antarābaḍḍi or āturā-baḍḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रिपु|रिपुः
ripu (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋषिपञ्चमी|ऋषिपंचमी
ṛṣi-pañcamī (EI 23), same as Bhādrapada su-di 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रीतिकार
Rītikāra (EI 32), a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोचयितव्य
rocayitavya (CII 1), ‘should be liked’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोचीक
rocīka (IE 8-5), a tax or obligation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोहण|रोहणं|रोहणः
rohaṇa (SITI), function performed at the commencement of a festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोही
rohī (IA 11), Pañjābī; uplands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रोक|रोकं|रोकः
roka (Chamba), cash. See rūka under rū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋषि|ऋषिः
ṛṣi (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋतु|ऋतुः
ṛtu (EI 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रू
rū (IE 8-1), abbreviation of rūpaka or rūpyaka.<BR> (CITD), abbreviation of Telugu rūka meaning ‘cash’ and probably derived from Sanskrit rūpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूढभारोडि
rūḍhabhāroḍi (HRS), system of forced carriage of loads as indicated by the Rājataraṅgiṇī. Cf. prayāṇa-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुधिर|रुधिरं|रुधिरः
rudhira, cf. Tamil udira-paṭṭi (SITI), literally, ‘blood-land;’ land given to the descendants of a person who fell fighting on the king's behalf; see also rakta-mānya, mṛtyuka-vṛtti, rakta-paṭṭaka and vīra-śeṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्र|रुद्रः
Rudra (SITI), a Śaiva devotee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्र|रुद्रः
rudra (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रदामक
rudradāmaka, ‘silver coin (kārṣāpaṇa) issued by Rudradāman’; name of the silver coins issued by the Śaka rulers of Western India (JNSI, Vol. XIII, pp. 1 7 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रगण|रुद्रगणः
Rudra-gaṇa (SITI), devotees of Śiva, their managing committee looking after the affairs of a Śiva temple and being known as Rudragaṇa-pperumakkal̤.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रगणिका
Rudra-gaṇikā (SITI), a dancing woman attached to a Śiva temple; a devadāsī serving in a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रमाहेश्वर
Rudra-māheśvara (SITI; ASLV), the two classes of Śaiva devotees, known as the Rudras and Māheśvaras; designation of the authorities of a Śaiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=281" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रपुत्र
Rudra-putra (EI 33), epithet of one devoted to the god Śiva. See Durgā-putra, Puruṣottama-putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रास्य
rudr-āsya (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुण्डा
Ruṇḍā, cf. Mahāruṇḍā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुन्द्र
rundra (IA 6, 10), cf. guṇa-rundra, an epithet of Jinendra; also cf. Himavad-girīndra-rundra-śikhara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप|रूपं
rūpa (HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) a subsidiary charge in excess of the prescribed fines; (2) a charge upon mines and upon imported salt. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 94, 106.<BR> (IE 8-8; EI 20, 21), currency or coins; name of a silver coin; same as rūpya or rūpaka.<BR> (EI 1), an animal.<BR> (CII 1), a representation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपदक्ष
Rūpa-dakṣa, cf. Prakrit lupa-dakha (EI 22), a painter or sculptor. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 30.<BR> (LL), explained by some as ‘a copyist’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपदर्शक
Rūpa-darśaka (EI 20, 21; HD), an examiner of coins. See Arthaśāstra, II. 5. Cf. Pārikh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपक|रूपकं|रूपकः
rūpaka (IE 8-8; EI 30; CII 4), name of a coin of silver; cf. kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka (EI 25; CII 4), a silver coin issued by the Kalacuri king Kṛṣṇarāja; silver coin (1/16) of the value of a gold dīnāra in the Gupta age (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 5); same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकार|रूपकारः
Rūpakāra (EI 8; BL), a sculptor; epithet of a sculptor. See Rūpakāraka, Rūpakārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकारक
Rūpakāraka (LL), a sculptor; same as Rūpakāra, Rūpakārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकारिन्
Rūpakārin (EI 5), a sculptor; same as Rūpakāra, Rūpakāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपकर्मन्
rūpa-karman (LL), carving.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुपेए
rupee, Anglicised form of rūpīa (q. v.); derived from Sanskrit rūpyaka. See JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 142.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपीअ
rūpīa (IE 8-8), same as rūpya or rūpyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपिक|रूपिकः
rūpika (HRS), tax on the sale of salt; one of the sources of revenue specified in the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 25, 92, 106.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप्यक
rūpyaka (IE 8-8), same as rūpaka, rūpīa, rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स|सं|सः
sa (IE 8-1), also written as saṃ; abbreviation of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सा
Sā (EI 32), abbreviation of Sādhanika (q. v.). [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-283" target="_blank">Page-283+ 40</a>]<BR> (PJS), abbreviation of Sāhu or Sādhu, designation of a member of the mercantile community often used in medieval inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=282" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शब्द|शब्दः
śabda, same as mahā-śabda; cf. pañca-śabda (BL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाब्दिक|शाब्दिकः
śābdika (BL), a grammarian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभा
sabhā (SII 2; SITI; ASLV), same as mahāsabhā; the body of the Mahājanas; the assembly of a Brāhmaṇa village of the Tamil-speaking area, such an assembly of a non-Brāhmaṇa village being called ūr; local assembly of a Brāhmaṇa village; same as Tamil kur̤i.<BR> (EI 22), the Buddhist saṅgha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभामध्यम
sabhā-madhyama (SITI), the village common or waste land in the village belonging to the sabhā; also called sabhai-ppodu, ūr-ppodu, ūr-mañjikkam, sabhā-mañjikkam, etc., in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभामण्डप|सभामण्डपः
sabhā-maṇḍapa (HA), same as raṅga-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभाविनियोग
sabhā-viniyoga (SITI), individual share payable to make up the expenses of the sabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सब्रह्मचारिन्
Sabrahmacārin (CII 3), a religious student of a group that follows the same śākhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साचित्त
sācitta (LP), probably, ‘land attached to government servants as long as they serve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सचिव|सचिवः
Saciva (EI 33; BL; HD), minister or counsellor. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 105, note 150.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साद|सादः
sāda (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदक
sadaka, cf. upari-sadaka, explained as ‘the upper region’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI. p. 234).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदासेवा
sadā-sevā, cf. Tamil sadā-servai, sadā-sevai (SII 1; SITI); constant service; permanent service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षडशीति|षडशीतिः
ṣaḍaśīti (IA 19), same as mithuna-rāśi (Gemini).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षडायतन
ṣaḍ-āyatana, cf. Prakrit ṣaḍ-ayadana (CII 2-1), the six organs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षड्भाग|षड्भागः
ṣaḍ-bhāga, cf. dharma-ṣaḍ-bhāga (Sel. Ins., p. 348, text line 16), one-sixth of the merit for a pious work done by the subjects, which goes to the king. See ibid., p. 344, text line 3.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधाचार्य
Sādhācārya (IA 12), assistant to the officiating priest at the Rāmeśvaram temple; also called Adhyayana-bhaṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधन|साधनं
sādhana (IE 8-3; EI 24; LP), an army, cf. sādhana-sahasra-aikam, an army consisting of one thousand men.<BR> (EI 15), an army, or money.<BR> (SII 12), cf. mūla-sādhana, the original deed; also called mūla-olai in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=283" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधनिक
Sādhanika (CII 4), a general; same as Sāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधनिन्
Sādhanin (EI 23), explained as a ‘a councillor’; but really, the same as Sādhanika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधार
sādhāra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), either a mistake for sādhāraṇa, ‘common’, or means ‘together with the adjacent grounds’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधारण|साधारणः
sādhāraṇa (IA 20), used in the sense of laukika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सधर्मिवात्सल्य
sadharmi-vātsalya (HA), attachment to or service of the followers of one's own faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सध्र्यग्विहारिन्
sadhryagvihārin (LL), doubtful Sanskritisation of Pāli saddhi-vihārin (Sanskrit sārdhaṃvihārin under the influence of sādhya), companion of a Buddhist monk. Cf. Jain Sārdhaṃcara, Sārdhaṃcarī (LL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधु|साधुः
Sādhu (EI 9), a priest.<BR> (HA), a Jain monk.<BR> (LP; HA), same as Sāhu, a merchant.<BR> (CII 1), an adjective meaning ‘good’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साध्वी
Sādhvī (JHA), a Jain nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साध्य|साध्यः
sādhya (IE 8-5; EI 15; SITI), a type of income; income from land that may be brought under cultivation in future; one of the eight kinds of enjoyment of property. See aṣṭa-bhoga, siddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साध्यपाल
Sādhyapāla (HD), a bailiff who summoned parties and witnesses. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 278.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साद्यस्क्र|साद्यस्क्रः
sādyaskra (EI 22; CII 3; etc.), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगर|सगरः
sagara (IE 7-1-2), confused with sāgara and rarely used to indicate ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सागर|सागरः
sāgara (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; used in the sense of ‘seven’ by some late writers (IA 19).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगोत्र|सगोत्रं|सगोत्रः
Sagotra (CII 3, etc.), belonging to the lineage of the person from whom the gotra name is derived.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहदेश
Sahadeśa (IA 17), also called Sahadeśin, ‘belonging to the same country’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहगमन
sahagamana (ASLV), self-immolation of a widow on the funeral pyre of her husband; same as satī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहजकवि
Sahaja-kavi (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 231, note 1), epithet of a poet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणि
Sāhaṇi (IE 8-3), also called Sāhiṇi, etc.; derived from Sanskrit Sādhanika; cf. Gaja-sāhiṇi, etc.<BR> (EI 15), see Paṭṭa-sāhaṇi, Peyiya-sāhaṇi, Maleya-sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहानी
Sāhānī (EI 33), same as Sādhanika, Sāhaṇi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=284" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणिअ
Sāhaṇia (IE 8-3), Prakrit form of Sādhanika from sādhana or army; cf. the modern family name Sāhnī. Same as Sāhaṇiya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणिकाटि
sāhaṇikāṭi (SII 11-1), supposed to be the name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहणिय
Sāhaṇiya (EI 11), Prakrit form of Sādhanika; same as Sāhaṇia, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहानुषाहि
Sāhānuṣāhi (IE 8-2; EI 19, 22, 30), title of the Kuṣāṇa kings, derived from Old Persian Kshāyathiyānām Kshāyathiya; same as modern Persian Shāhān Shāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शहर्
śahar, Persian shahr, a town (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 145-46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहस|साहसं|साहसः
sāhasa (CII 4), a violent crime.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहसाधिपति|साहसाधिपतिः
Sāhasādhipati (HD), a judicial or police officer. See Śukra, I. 120.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहसमल्लाङ्क
sāhasamallāṅka (BL), epithet of a year of the Kalacuri era probably through confusion, as normally the expression would mean the Vikrama era.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहस्रांशु|सहस्रांशुः
sahasr-āṃśu (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहस्रायतन
sahasr-āyatana (EI 29), epithet of a temple; literally, ‘having one thousand rooms or shrines’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहि
Sāhi, Śāhī (IE 8-2; EI 30; LL), same as Persian Shāh, Old Persian Kshāyathiya; royal title used by some Indian rulers of foreign origin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहिजादा
Sāhijādā (BL), title of a prince; same as Persian Shāhzādah. See Sāhiyādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहीकरी
sahī-karī (Chamba), ‘having approved; having got approved; having put the signature on’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहिल्य
sāhilya (IA 23), same as bhāṇḍāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहिणि
Sāhiṇi (IE 8-3; EI 32), same as Sanskrit Sādhanika (q. v.), interpreted as ‘the master of the royal stables’ (BL).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहितीविद्या
sāhitī-vidyā (EI 13), same as sāhitya, literature.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहित्य|साहित्यं
sāhitya, cf. sāhitī-vidyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहियादा
Sāhiyādā (BL), title of a prince; same as Persian Shāhzādah. See Sāhijādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साह्नी
Sāhnī (IE 8-3), modern family name derived from Sanskrit Sādhanika = Prakrit Sāhaṇia, Sāhaṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहोदर|सहोदरः
sahodara (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’ possibly referring to Kuntī's sons.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साहु
Sāhu (LP), same as Sanskrit Sādhu; a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैबर
śaibara, cf. sa-śaibaram (EI 17); a levy in kind according to some; but see saivara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=285" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सइका
saïkā (EI 28), Sanskrit śatikā; a levy per one hundred articles; one payable in a hundred articles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैल|शैलं|शैलः
śaila (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलदेवगृह
śaila-devagṛha (EI 24), a stone temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलगृह
śaila-gṛha (LL), a cave.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलकर्मन्
śaila-karman (LL), stone-work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलालक
Śailālaka (EI 1; LL), same as Śilālin, an actor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलरूपकर्मन्
śaila-rūpakarman (LL), stone-carving.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैलवर्धकिन्
Śaila-vardhakin (LL), cf. Prakrit Sela-vaḍhākī (EI 20); a stone mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैनिकसङ्घमुख्य
Sainika-saṅgha-mukhya (EI 22), official designation; probably, a general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैन्य|सैन्यं|सैन्यः
sainya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 71), probably, an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैन्याधिकारिन्
Sainy-ādhikārin (IE 8-3), same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सैन्यपति
Sainyapati (IE 8-3), same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवाचार्य
Śaiv-ācārya (CII 4), an ascetic of the Śaiva sect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवाचार्यक्षेत्र
śaivācārya-kṣetra (SITI), tax-free land endowed to a Śaiv-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवदीक्षा
śaiva-dīkṣā (EI 32), initiation into the Śaiva faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शैवर
śaivara, a revenue term; cf. śaibara; a levy in kind according to Ghoshal (H. Rev. Syst., p. 220); but probably the same as Marāṭhī śerī, ‘arable land originally excluded from the village assessment’ (Wilson's Glossary); may also be a tax on farm-houses (cf. śibara).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक|शकः
Śaka (EI 24), originally, the Scythians; later any foreigners including Muhammadans; used to indicate the Musalmans (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 44; Bhandatkar's List, No. 926).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक|शकः
śaka, śāka (IA 9, 19), used in the sense of ‘a year’ or ‘an era’; cf. Vikrama-śaka (IA 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक|शाकं|शाकः
śāka, cf. a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa (EI 8-5); vegetables which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers. Cf. śāka-śaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साका
sākā (IA 29), Rājasthānī; same as jauhar or javhar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाकम्भरीविद्या
śākambharī-vidyā (EI 29; CII 4), name of a science, the nature of which is uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शकानिका
Śakānikā (CII 4), a Śaka woman. Cf. anikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाकपणिका
śāka-paṇikā, cf. śāka-paṇikā-nyāyena (LP), ‘like vegetables in a market’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकरुकर
sakarukara, occurs in a Śātavāhana inscription probably for [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-287" target="_blank">Page-287+ 40</a>] Sanskrit sa-kar-otkara meaning the same thing as s-odraṅga-s-oparikara, ‘with the udraṅga (kara) and uparikara (utkara) taxes’; may also be sa-kārukara. See kāru-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=286" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाखा
śākhā (CII 3, 4; IA 18, 19), literally, ‘a branch’; a Vedic school following any particular recension of the Vedas.<BR> (LL), a section of the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्र|शक्रः
śakra (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्रध्वज|शक्रध्वजः
śakra-dhvaja, cf. indra-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्रयज्ञ
śakra-yajña (IE 7-1-2), ‘one hundred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्रोत्थान|शक्रोत्थानं
śakr-otthāna (EI 32), a festival, same as śakradhvaj-otthāna. Cf. śakra-dhvaja, indra-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साक्षिन्
Sākṣin (EI 3, 23; SITI), a witness; an eye-witness.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सक्षीणारम्भ
sa-kṣīṇ-ārambha (CII 1), gentle in action.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सक्त|सक्तः
sakta (LP), written for satka, ‘belonging to’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्ति|शक्तिः
Śakti (EI 17), name of the wife of Kāmadeva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्ति|शक्तिः
śakti (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘three’; three in number (EI 6).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्तिमुख
śakti-mukha, (SITI), cf. śatti-mugam; king's order; probably the same as śrīmukha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्तित्रय
śakti-traya (SII 1), the three [regal] powers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक्य|शाक्यः
Śākya (CII 1), a Buddhist; see Śākya-bhikṣu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक्यभिक्षु|शाक्यभिक्षुः
Śākya-bhikṣu (BL; LL), epithet of a Buddhist monk; same as Śākya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाक्योपासिका
Śāky-opāsikā (LL), a female member of the Buddhist laity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाला
śālā (EI 4; SII 1), a hall.<BR> (EI 4; SITI), a school; same as pāṭha-śālā.<BR> (SII 3), cf. śālai (EI 7; SITI), an alms-house; a feeding house; cf. śālā-bhoga.<BR> Cf. śālai (EI 24), a hospital; cf. ārogya-śālā, ātura-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शालाभोग
śālā-bhoga (SII 2; SII), same as Tamil arac-cālā-bhogam; land granted in favour of a feeding house (sattra-śālā). (EI 23), mentioned along with devadāna and brahmadeya; a rent-free holding in the possession of a śālā meaning an almshouse or a school.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शलाका
śalākā, cf. śalāgai (SITI), name of a coin also called palañ-śalāgai (accu) and śrīyakki-palañśalāgai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शालास्थानमुख्य
Śālāsthāna-mukhya (EI 32), probably, officer in charge of the stables.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलाट
Salāṭa (PJS), Gujarātī; also called Salāvaṭa; a stone-cutter or mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सालवी
Sālavī (LP), Gujarātī; a weaver.<BR> (PJS), Gujarātī; a carpenter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=287" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शालीन|शालीनः
Śālīna (CII 4), a kind of householder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलिलपूर्वक
salila-pūrvaka (IA 9), same as udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सल्लेखना
sallekhanā (EI 3, 6; SITI), Jain; a religious practice of the Jains; starving oneself to death; starving oneself to death in fulfilment of a vow; same as samādhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलोहित
Sa-lohita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 295), ‘one having the same blood’; a relation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शल्यत्रय
śalya-traya (SII 1), the three thorns.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सं|स|सः
saṃ (IE 8-1), abbreviation of saṃbaddha, ‘attached to’, ‘belonging to,’ etc.; possibly also saṃsakta, ‘relating to’ (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 204).<BR> (CII 3, 4), abbreviation of the word saṃvatsara, a year, or of its declensional cases that can be used in expressing a date.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सं|स|सः
Saṃ (PJS), also written Saṃgha; contraction of Saṃghavī or Saṃghapati in medieval Jain inscriptions; same as the modern Jain family name Siṅghī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सां
sāṃ (IE 8-1; LP), abbreviation of sāṃvatsarika, annual. See sāṃ-hi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शम्
śam (ML) ‘to prevent’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम|समः
sama, cf. sam-ālindakam (LP), ‘with a terrace in front of the door.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाचर्य
samācarya (CII 1), impartiality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाधि|समाधिः
samādhi (CII 4), poetic quality of a composition.<BR> (EI 33), explained as a ‘granary’; probably ‘an agreement’.<BR> Cf. sallekhanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समधिगतपञ्चमहाशब्द
Samadhigata-pañca-mahāśabda (IE 8-2; CII 3), a customary epithet of feudatory rulers, indicating that they were entitled to the privilege of the pañca-mahāśabda (five kinds of musical instruments), or of using five official titles beginning with the word mahā. There are a few instances in which the epithet is applied to paramount sovereigns in South India. The title is sometimes stated to have been conferred on a feudatory by his overlord. See mahāśabda, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाहर्तृ
Samāhartṛ (EI 27; HD; HRS), official designation; explained as ‘the collector-general’; officer in charge of the collection of various branches of revenue; compared by Ghoshal with the Qānungo of Mughal times (H. Rev. Syst., p. 52). See Arthaśāstra, I. 12; II. 6; Śabara on Jaimini, XII. 1. 28; Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 141; Vol. XI, p. 94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाज|समाजः
samāja (EI 20; CII 1), a fair; a festival; a festive gathering [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-289" target="_blank">Page-289+ 40</a>] on a particular occasion or for the celebration of an event.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=288" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाज्ञप्ति
Samājñapti (EI 27), same as Ājñapti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामक|सामकं|सामकः
sāmaka (LP), ‘collectively’; cf. Gujarātī sāṃṭuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समकरग्राम
samakara-grāma (LP), a village for which a permanent revenue is fixed at a particular rate, not to be increased in future.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समकरकुल
samakara-kula (LP), family on which rent is fixed once for all; farmers that have to pay revenue at a particular rate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समाक्रान्त
samākrānta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20), used in some Orissan records probably in the sense of ‘endowed with boundaries’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समम्
samam (LP), ‘in the same way as’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समञ्जस|समंजस|समञ्जसं|समञ्जसः
samañjasa (SITI), conformity; resemblance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समञ्जित
Samañjita (SITI), accountant of a village or a village assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्त|समंत|समन्तः
samanta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्त|सामंत|सामन्तः
Sāmanta (IE 8-2; 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), title of feudatory rulers; a feudatory smaller than the Rājan; a sub-ordinate chief; also explained as ‘a minister’ (SITI). See Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354; Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 297. Cf. Mahāsāmanta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्त|सामंत|सामन्तः
Sāmanta (CII 1), a neighbour; ‘one who is in possession of a piece of land in the neighbourhood of the gift land’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 220).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्तभद्र|समंतभद्र|समन्तभद्रः
samantabhadra (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 199), prosperous on all sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्ताधिकारिन्
Sāmant-ādhikārin (ASLV), see Sāmanta and Adhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्ताधिपति
Sāmant-ādhipati (EI 16), cf. Mahāsāmant-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्तपडिरा
Sāmanta-paḍirā (EI 32), Od̤iyā; Sanskrit Sāmanta-pratirāja; title of a feudatory or nobleman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्तिक
sāmantika, derived from Sāmanta; chiefship (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्थु
samanthu (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामान्य|सामान्यं
sāmānya, cf. traividya-sāmānya (EI 23), cāturvedya-sāmānya; ‘belonging to’; Valabhī-cāturvidya-sāmānya, ‘one of the Catur-vedins of Valabhī’; used also in the sense of vāstavya, ‘resident of … ’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 172, 176).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समारचन
samāracana, repairs (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समारण
samāraṇa Prakrit used in Sanskrit for samāracaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 59).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समरापणीय
samarāpaṇīya (LP), to be got repaired; cf. Gujarātī samrā-vavuṃ; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-290" target="_blank">Page-290+ 40</a>] see samarcāpanīya, samāracana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=289" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समराप्य
samarāpya (LP), ‘should be repaired’; cf. Gujarātī samrā-vatruṃ; also samāracana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समर्चापन
samarcāpana (LP), repairing; cf. samarcāpanīya (LP), ‘to be got repaired’; cf. samarāpaṇīya; also samāracana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्त|समस्तं
samasta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat especially in medieval Orissan records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तमहासामन्ताधिपति
Samasta-mahāsāmant-ādhipati (BL), title of a feudatory ruler of the highest rank. See Mahāsāmant-ādhipati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तसेनाधिपति
Samasta-sen-ādhipati (EI 29, 30), ‘leader of all the forces’; commander-in-chief. See Sen-ādhipati, Senāpati, Maněya-samasta-sainy-ādhipati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तसुप्रशस्त्युपेत
samasta-supraśasty-upeta (IE 8-2), a royal epithet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्त्येत्यादि
samasty-ety-ādi (IE 8-2), shortened form of samasta-supra-śasty-upeta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्यापूरण
samasyā-pūraṇa (CII 4), completion of incomplete verses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्
samat (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत
samata (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समता
samatā (CII 1), impartiality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्त
samatta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवाद|सामवादः
sāma-vāda, cf. Prakrit sama-vāyo (CII 1), found in a rock edict of Aśoka; ‘restrained speech’; same as saṃyama (i. e. vāk-saṃyama) found in one version; generally sama-vāyo is taken as samavāya or concord.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवाजिक
Sāmavājika (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 135, note 6), probably, an officer; cf. Sāmavāyika, Sāmavājin, Sāṃmavājin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवाजीन्
Sāmavājin (EI 6), probably, an officer; cf. Sāṃmavājin, Sāmavājika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समवसरण
samavasaraṇa (HA), congregation-hall believed to be built by celestials when a Tīrthaṅkara delivered his sermon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामवायिक|सामवायिकः
Sāmavāyika (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 135, note 6), probably, an officer; cf. Sāmavājika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समवेत|समवेतः
samaveta (IE 8-3), ‘associated’; generally explained as ‘assembled’; but see samupāgata, upeta, upayāta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समय|समयः
samaya (EI 10), a religious system.<BR> (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a sect; an assemblage, a company or congregation; established moral or ceremonial custom; cf. samaiyam (EI 24), a creed.<BR> Cf. samaye (EI 19), used instead of varṣe in the dates after saṃvat.<BR> (SITI), a religious mendicant; cf. Samay-mudali, religious head.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=290" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयाचार|समयाचारः
samay-ācāra (SITI), religious usage; established custom; supervision of the religious and social life of the people; censoring of public morals; also a class of officials called Samayācārya or Dāsari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयाचार्य
Samayācārya (ASLV), also called Samayācāra; same as Dāśari; a censor of morals; a class of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयधर्म|समयधर्मः
samaya-dharma (SITI), law of the samaya or agreement. The expression is generally used in relation to the organisation of merchants and agriculturists known respectively as Nānādeśīn and Citramel̤̣i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समयपत्र
samaya-patra (SII 1; SITI; LP), an agreement; a document containing an agreement; a deed of agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामायिक
sāmāyika (HA), remaining steadfast in worship or meditation (at least for 48 minutes), with the mind drawn away from attachments or ill will and abstaining from committing sins, which is the daily duty of a Jain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बद्ध|संबद्ध|सम्बद्धः
sambaddha (IA 15), ‘belonging to’ or ‘connected with’.<BR> Cf. Devadroṇī-sambaddha (IE 8-3), probably, superintendent of a temple property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बधना
sambadhanā (LP), strong opposition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शम्बल|शंबल|शंबलं|शंबलः|शम्बलः
śambala (LP), provisions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संभाल
saṃbhāla (LP), care, protection; cf. Gujarātī saṃbal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्भार|संभार|संभारः|सम्भारः
sambhāra (ML), provision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्भोग|संभोग|संभोगः|सम्भोगः
sambhoga, cf. rāja-sambhoga, ratnatraya-sambhoga; same as bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्भोग|संभोग|संभोगः|सम्भोगः
Sambhoga (LL), a section of the Jain community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बोधित
sambodhita (LP), advised.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बुद्ध|संबुद्ध|संबुद्धः|सम्बुद्धः
sambuddha (LP), one who is no longer a minor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संग्रहण|सङ्ग्रहण|संग्रहणं
saṃgrahaṇa, adultery (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्हलातमक
samhalātamaka, cf. samhalātamaka-samanvita (EI 9), meaning uncertain; may be a name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांहि
sāṃ-hi, abbreviation of sāṃvatsarika-hiranya, ‘annual revenue income in cash’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 55).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामीप
sāmīpa (CII 1), a neighbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समिति|समितिः
samiti (EI 4), five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संकाचितक
saṃkācitaka (EI 30), cf. poṭṭalikā-saṃkācitak-ādāna, ‘tax on bundles suspended from loops at both ends of a pole’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संमत्
saṃmat (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्मत्
sammat (ASLV), same as samuta; an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांमवाजिन्
Sāṃmavājin (EI 33), same as Sāmavājin, Sāmavājika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्मुखवार
sammukha-vāra, probably, Sunday (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 115).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=291" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संम्वत्
saṃmvat (EI 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्प्राप्ति|संप्राप्ति|संप्राप्तिः|सम्प्राप्तिः
samprāpti, cf. sampirātti (SITI) ‘that which has been obtained’; ‘an acquisition’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्प्रति|संप्रति|सम्प्रतिः
Samprati (SITI), senior accountant; the manager of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्प्रतिपत्ति|संप्रतिपत्ति|संप्रतिपत्तिः|सम्प्रतिपत्तिः
sampratipatti (CII 1), proper behaviour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्राट्
Samrāṭ (EI 19, 22; CII 3, 4), imperial title; a paramount sovereign.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संसरण|संसरणं
saṃsaraṇa (CII 1), a house or road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांशयिक|सांशयिकः
sāṃśayika (CII 1), ‘of doubtful value’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्कृत|संस्कृतं|संस्कृतः
Saṃskṛta, see Sanskrit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्तव|संस्तवः
saṃstava (CII 1), cf. dharma-saṃstava, ‘acquaintance through Dharma’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्था
saṃsthā (HRS), king's dues derived from the market-place, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संस्तुत|संस्तुतः
saṃstuta (CII 1), cf. mitra-saṃstuta-jñāti, ‘friends, acquintances and relatives’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्त
samta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat. Mta = mat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदाय|समुदायः
Samudāya (EI 25), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदाय|समुदायः
samudāya (ASLV), same as gaṇa-bhoga; a tenure in which land is enjoyed by a group of people.<BR> (SITI), a village under the gaṇa-bhoga tenure.<BR> (SITI), village common; managing committee of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदयबाह्य
samudaya-bāhya (HRS), occurs in the Damodarpur inscriptions; ‘revenue-free’ or ‘yielding no income’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदायप्राप्ति
samudāya-prāpti, cf. samudāya-ppirātti (SITI), any acquisition from the village to be enjoyed in common by the villagers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुद्र|समुद्रः
Samudra (EI 10), an epithet of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुद्र|समुद्रः
samudra (EI 16), same as sapt-āmbhodhi; name of a mahā-dāna; also means 4 (rarely 7).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुद्रघोष
samudra-ghoṣa (EI 5), name given to a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समूह|समूहः
samūha (EI 28; CII 4), an assembly; the assembly of a corporation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुपगत
samupagata (EI 12), explained as ‘assembled at’; really, ‘having connection with’, ‘associated with’; cf. samupagama, ‘contact’; also samaveta, upeta, upayāta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुपागत
samupāgata (IE 8-3), ‘associated’; often explained as ‘assembled’; but cf. samaveta, samupagata, upayāta, upeta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुत
samuta (ASLV), same as sammat; an administrative unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=292" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुत्क्रीडा
samutkrīḍā (EI 15), same as krīḍā or sport.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्व
samva (IE 8-1), mistake for saṃva which is an abbreviation of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संव
saṃva (IE 8-1) same as saṃvat; contraction of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवदन|संवदनं
saṃvadana (IE 8-8), submission of information.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवर्तकल्प
saṃvarta-kalpa (CII 1), the aeon of destruction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवास|संवासः
saṃvāsa, cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-saṃvāsa (IE 8-5); same as āvāsa; shelter or accommodation [which the villagers were obliged to supply to the touring officers of the king].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्|संवन्त्
saṃvat (IE 8-1), originally an abbreviation of saṃvatsara (a year) or any of its declensional cases that can be used in expressing a date; later stereotyped in the sense of ‘a year’ or ‘an era’. It was generally regarded as indeclinable; but we have some cases of the use of forms with case-endings, e. g., saṃvataḥ, saṃvatā, saṃvati and saṃvatām. See also saṃvate (IE 8-1), the seventh case-ending of saṃvata, a corrupt form of saṃvat. Since the late medieval age, the word specially indicates the Vikrama era, although originally it was used with the name of any reckoning in quoting the dates of records, especially the regnal reckoning. The word is used in inscriptions in a large number of corrupt forms, e. g., samvata, samvatta, samata, samanta, samatta, saṃmat, samasta, smat, samvatu, samvatū, etc., etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्वत्
samvat (IE 8-1), mistake for saṃvat, originally an abbreviation of saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सर|संवत्सरः
saṃvatsara (CII 3; 4; IA 17), ‘a year’; ‘an cra’, the earlier years of the Indian eras being quoted by this term (or by its abbreviations saṃ, saṃvat, etc.), without any dynastic or other appellation just as in the case of the year of a regnal reckoning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांवत्सर|सांवत्सरः
Sāṃvatsara (HD), an astrologer. See Viṣṇu Dh. S., III. 75; Bṛhatasaṃhitā, 2. 9; cf. Sāṃvatsarika (EI 5).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरप्रतिपदा
saṃvatsara-pratipadā, name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरश्राद्ध
saṃvatsara-śrāddha (CII 4), śrāddha performed on the first anniversary of a person's death.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरवारिय
saṃvatsara-vāriya (SITI), annual committee appointed by the sabhā; annual committee for supervising the management of village affairs; also called āṭṭi-vāriyam (SITI) in Tamil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवत्सरविमोक्षश्राद्ध
saṃvatsara-vimokṣa-śrāddha (CII 4), same as saṃvatsara-śrāddha performed on the first anniversary of a person's death.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांवत्सरिक|सांवत्सरिकः
Sāṃvatsarika (HD), an astrologer. See Paiṭhīnasi quoted [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-294" target="_blank">Page-294+ 40</a>] in Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 193.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=293" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांवत्सरिकहिरण्य
sāṃvatsarika-hiraṇya (IE 8-1), annual revenue in cash; often abbreviated as sāṃ-hi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्वत्त
samvatta (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्वतु
samvatu, samvatū (IE 8-1), corrupt forms of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संवतुं
saṃvatuṃ (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संविभाग|संविभागः
saṃvibhāga (CII 1), separation of one thing from another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संविद्
saṃvid (EI 32), an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सांविनयिक
sāṃvinayika, cf. a-raṭṭha-sāṃvinayika (EI 1), a-rāṣṭra-sāṃ-vinayika (IE 8-5); administration or control, i. e. administrative control.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

संव्यवहारिन्
Saṃvyavahārin (EI 23), an administrator; same as Vyava-hārin; cf. Saṃvyavahāry-ādi-kuṭumbinaḥ (EI 24), the agriculturist householders led by the village-headman or the collector of royal dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्य|साम्यं
sāmya (EI 23), often written for svāmya; cf. leja-sāmya standing for tejaḥ-svāmya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्यक्प्रधान
samyak-pradhāna, cf. sammappadhāna (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्
san (IA 18), Arabic; a year; an era; sometimes used in Sanskrit records; in some cases, corrupted to sna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शण|शणं|शणः
śaṇa (LP), linen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाण|शाणं|शाणः
śāṇa, name of a weight or coin; a silver coin which was (1/8) of a śatamāna in weight and value; generally regarded as 40 ratis in weight, but sometimes also as 32 or 24 or 20 ratis; also called niṣka, ṭaṅka or dharaṇa or śānaka. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 42, 44-45. See śāna-pāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानभोग
Śānabhoga (IE 8-3), village-accountant; same as Senabova, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानक
śānaka, see śāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानपाद|शानपादः
śāna-pāda, same as māṣa (JNSI, Vol. p. 47).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनाथ
Sanātha (IA 7), wrongly supposed to mean ‘one whose father is alive’ or ‘a worthy’; actually, a personal name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चकार
sañcakāra (IA 19), same as satyakāra; an agreement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चरन्तक
Sañcarantaka (HD), Prakrit; ‘a spy’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. I, p. 5. Kauṭilya (Arthaśāstra, I. 12) speaks of Sañcāra (wandering spies like Tīkṣṇa, Rasada, etc.). Cf. Sañcārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चरत्क
Sañcaratka (IE 8-3), a spy; cf. Sañcarantaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चारिन्|संचारिन्
Sañcārin (EI 24), cf. Śāsana-sañcārin and Ājñā-sañcārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्चरित
sañcarita, cf. ājñāta (IA 18).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=294" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षण्ड|षंड|षंडः|षण्डः
ṣaṇḍa (IA 18), a bull living or wandering at liberty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षण्डगुल
ṣaṇḍa-gula (LP), same as Gujarātī khāṃḍ-gol, i. e. sugar and molasses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धि|संधि|संधिः|सन्धिः
sandhi (EI 4; SITI), literally, ‘twilight’; but actually, ‘service in the temple in the morning and evening’; daily worship in temples; special worship offered in the names of persons who arrange for it by creating endowments, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिपात
sandhi-pāta, emergency (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 213).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकरण
Sandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa (CII 4), department of peace and war.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकरणाधिकृत
Sandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇ-ādhikṛta (EI 30; BL), official designation indicating a person in charge of the office of war and peace (i. e. foreign affairs); an officer of the ministry or the minister of foreign affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकरणकायस्थ
Sandhivigrah-ādhikaraṇa-kāyastha, official designation of a scribe of the office of war and peace (i. e. foreign affairs).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहाधिकृत
Sandhivigrah-ādhikṛta (CII 4; BL), an officer in charge of the department or the minister of war and peace; same as Sandhivigrahin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिकरण
sandhi-[vigraha]-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); department of foreign affairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहकारिन्
Sandhivigrahakārin (EI 21), same as Sandhivigrahika. See Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 320.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहप्पेरु
sandhivigraha-pper̤u (EI 24; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; a fee payable to the village Madhyastha; also a fee payable to document-writers; cf. sandhivigrahi-paṇṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहिक
Sandhivigrahika (HD), minister for peace and war. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 17; Mahābhārata, Śānti-parvan, 85. 30. See Sāndhivigrahika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सान्धिविग्रहिक|सांधिविग्रहिक|सांधिविग्रहिकः
Sāndhivigrahika (IE 8-3; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; HD; LP), minister for peace and war, i. e. of foreign affairs; sometimes also called Khādya[kū]ṭapākika, Kumārāmātya, Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, etc., additionally; same as Sandhivigrahika, etc. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 17; Mitākṣarā on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 320; CII, Vol. III, p. 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहिन्
Sandhivigrahin (IE 8-3, SITI), minister in charge of peace and war; officer in charge of the foreign relations department, who was often the writer of important documents; same as Sandhivigrahika, etc. Cf. Kannaḍa-sandhivigrahin (EI 16), Hěri-Lāl̤a-sandhivigrahin (EI 12), Hěri-sandhivigrahin (EI 12), Lāl̤a-sandhivigrahin [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-296" target="_blank">Page-296+ 40</a>] (EI 12), Hěri-Lāṭa-Karṇāta-sandhivigrahin, Hěri-Lāṭa-sandhivigrahin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=295" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहिपण्णु
Sandhivigrahi-paṇṇu (EI 30), name of a levy; same as sandhivigraha-pper̤u.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविलक्कु
sandhi-vil̤akku (SII 1), a sacred lamp; cf. nandā-vil̤akku, sandhi-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्ध्या|संध्या
sandhyā (CITD), the morning, noon and evening prayers of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR> (CII 3; IA 17), a period at the commencement of each of the four Hindu ages; the sandhyā of the Kali-yuga lasts for 36,000 years of men, and is still running; cf. sandhyāṃśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिदीप
sandhi-dīpa, cf. sandi-vil̤akku (SITI), a twilight lamp; generally lighted in the temples in the evening, but sometimes in the morning; same as sandhyā-dīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्ध्यांश|संध्यांश|संध्यांशः|सन्ध्यांशः
sandhy-āṃśa (AI 17), a period at the end of each of the four yugas, the sandhy-āṃśa of the Kali-yuga to last for 36,000 human years.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्दोह|संदोह|संदोहः|सन्दोहः
sandoha, cf. a-puṣpa-kṣīra-sandoha (IE 8-5), realisation or levy (cf. a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्गडिरक्षापालक
Saṅgaḍi-rakṣā-pālaka (EI 6), an officer; the meaning of saṅgaḍi is uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्गम्|संगम्
saṅgam, Tamil; same as Sanskrit saṅgha; an assembly of ancient Tamil poets; the name given to an assembly of poets reported in tradition to have functioned in three different periods. The poets are believed to have been both literary critics and composers. Literary compositions of the age were later collected and compiled into anthologies known as Eṭṭuttokai, Pattuppāṭṭu and Padineṅkīl̤kaṇakku according to their contents and size. The saṅgam is stated to have flourished at Kūḍal (also called Madurai in later literature) in the first and last period and at Kavāṭapuram in the middle period. The latest limit for the first two anthologies may be placed round about 700 A. D. See M. S. Purnalingam Pillai, Tamil Literature, pp. 14-18; S. Vaiyapuri Pillai, History of Tamil Language and Literature, p. 38.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घ|संघ|संघः|सङ्घः
saṅgha (ASLV), a social organisation.<BR> (BL), a community of Buddhist monks; the Buddhist Church.<BR> (HA), a Jain congregation; the Jain Church (made up of four constituents, viz. sādhu, sādhvī, śrāvaka and śrāvikā) also called Jaina-saṅgha; a group of pilgrims going together on [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-297" target="_blank">Page-297+ 40</a>] pilgrimage under the leadership of a Saṅghapati (q. v.).<BR> (EI 22), a tribe.<BR> Cf. Tamil saṅgam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=296" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घपति
Saṅgha-pati (EI 8; BL), title of the leader of a group of Jain pilgrims to a holy place, who bears all the expenses of the whole group; same as Saṅghaprabhu, Saṅghavī, etc. Cf. the modern Jain family name Siṅghī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घप्रभु
Saṅgha-prabhu (EI 8), Jain; same as Saṅghapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घप्रकृत
Saṅgha-prakṛta (LL), Buddhist; probably, a supporter of the saṅgha; translated as ‘commissioners of the community’ (Lüders, Mathurā Inscriptions, pp. 84 ff.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घराज
Saṅgharāja (EI 8), Buddhist; title of the principal ecclesiastical functionary in Burma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घाराम|संघारामः
saṅghārāma (EI 4; ML; LL), a Buddhist monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घस्थविर
Saṅgha-sthavira (LL), an Elder of the Buddhist congregation. Cf. Sthavira.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घाट|संघाटः
saṅghāṭa, saṅghāṭā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 248), cf. pāda-saṅghāṭa or pāda-saṅghāṭā, ‘a pair of feet (i. e. foot-marks)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घाटी
saṅghāṭī (EI 25), robe of a Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्घवी
Saṅghavī (BL; HA; PJS), derived from Sanskrit Saṅgha-pati (q. v.); designation of the leader of a saṅgha or group of Jains; the leader of a group of Jain pilgrims, who bears expenses of all the pilgrims going with him (cf. the Jain family name Siṅghī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्ग्रहण|संग्रहण|संग्रहणं
saṅgrahaṇa (IE 8-5), adultery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्ग्रहीतृ|संग्रहीतृ
Saṅgrahītṛ (HD), explained by some as ‘a treasurer or charioteer’ (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 111); probably, collector of the king's grain share. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानि
śāni (SITI), Dravidian; wife; a term by which a Brāhmaṇa woman was referred to.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शनिवारमण्डप
śanivāra-maṇḍapa (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 13), name of a building attached to a temple apparently meant for some function held there on Saturdays; cf. vaikkāṇikku-maṇḍapa under maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्जाति
sañjāti (LP), cf. rāja-sañjātyāṃ kartavyaḥ, ‘may be made a government property.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सञ्जीवराज
Sañjīva-rāja, cf. Sañjīvarāyar (SITI), name of Hanumān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्काचितक
saṅkācitaka (IE 8-8), a loop; same as Sanskrit kāca.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्कल्प|संकल्प|संकल्पः|सङ्कल्पः
saṅkalpa (Chamba), also called saṅkalpa-hast-odaka; libation of water; donation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्कर|संकर|संकरः|सङ्करः
saṅkara (EI 9), also called saṅkuru; a double sack.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=297" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्कराक्षि
śaṅkar-ākṣi (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्केत|संकेत|संकेतः|सङ्केतः
saṅketa, cf. sva-saṅketa (LP), ‘one's own special arrangement’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्ख|शंख|शंखं|शंखः|शङ्खः
śaṅkha (CII 3, etc.), conch-shell as an emblem^1 on seals; cf. śaṅghu (ASLV), the use of which was sometimes granted by kings to their favourites as a privilege.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खधारा
śaṅkhadhārā, cf. śaṃkudhāra (CITD); Telugu; continuous blowing of the conch-shell. See Śaṅkhadhārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खधारिन्
Śaṅkhadhārin (IE 8-3), blower of the conch-shell; sometimes mentioned as a Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खकार|शंखकार|शङ्खकारः
Śaṅkhakāra (EI 28), also called Śāṅkhika (q. v.); maker of conch-shell bangles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शङ्खिक
Śaṅkhika, Śāṅkhika (EI 24, 28), same as Śaṅkhakāra (q. v.), worker on conch-shells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्क्रमण|संक्रमण|संक्रमणं|सङ्क्रमणं
saṅkramaṇa (CII 3; IA 17), also called saṅkrānti; the entrance of the sun into a sign of the zodiac; regarded as an auspicious time for performing religious duties^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सङ्क्रान्ति|संक्रान्ति|संक्रांति|संक्रांतिः|संक्रान्तिः|सङ्क्रान्तिः
saṅkrānti (CII 3; IA 17), same as saṅkramaṇa (q. v.).<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षण्मुखबाहु
ṣaṇmukha-bāhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्नाह|संनाह|संनाहः|सन्नाहः
sannāha (LP), armour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्निधातृ|संनिधातृ
Sannidhātṛ (EI 27), official in charge of the receipt of various articles into the king's treasury, according to some (HRS); superintendent of the construction of the royal treasury, store houses, etc., according to others. See Arthaśāstra, II. 5; cf. I. 10 and 12; Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, pp. 138, 141; Vol. XI, pp. 93-94.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्निधि|संनिधि|संनिधिः|सन्निधिः
sannidhi, cf. sannadi (SII 1), presence of a deity; the front of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्नियुक्तक
Sanniyuktaka (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVII, p. 11, text line 14), same as Tanniyuktaka or a mistake for it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्स्क्रित्
Sanskrit, Anglicised form of Saṃskṛta, the name of the sacred language of the Indians.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्त|संत|संतः|सन्तः
santa (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a fair or market day.<BR> (EI 14), name of a measure or a coin; probably, a small coin (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तै
santai (ASLV), a weekly fair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तक
santaka (EI 27; CII 3), Prakrit; ‘belonging to’; sometimes Sanskritised as satka. Sometimes santaka (also santika apparently used in the same sense) has been regarded as [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-299" target="_blank">Page-299+ 40</a>] meaning ‘a territorial unit’; supposed similarly to mean ‘a servant’ (EI 23) or ‘an officer’ (EI 24).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=298" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सान्तकिक
Sāntakika (IE 8-3), official designation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तान|संतान|संतानं|संतानः|सन्तानः
santāna (SITI), lineage.<BR> (BL), cf. a Jain religious teacher described as belonging to the paṭṭa of another teacher and the santāna of a third teacher.<BR> (IA 20), used in the sense of āmnāya or kula-krama.<BR> (EI 6), same as santānaka, santati; seven in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तानशाप
santāna-śāpa (SITI), curse that prevents progeny.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तानिकशैव
Santānika-śaiva (SITI), Śaivas who belong to the line of ācāryas of the santāna-kuravar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तति|संतति|संततिः|सन्ततिः
santati (SITI), lineage. Cf. also sapta-santati (EI 14) and santānaka (under santāna).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्ततिप्रवेशम्
santati-praveśam (SITI), ‘from generation to generation’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्ति|शांति|शांतिः|शान्तिः
Śānti, a priest in a temple; cf. Tamil-Sanskrit Mel-śānti; also cf. Śāntikāra, of which Śānti seems to be an abbreviation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्ति|शांति|शांतिः|शान्तिः
śānti (EI 33), a propitiatory rite; cf. śānty-āgāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तिक
santika (EI 25), proximity, presence.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्तिकार
Śāntikāra (SITI), a temple priest; also known as Śāntiy-aḍigal and Śānti-śeyyān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्तीरणा
santīraṇā, cf. artha-santīraṇā (CII 1), despatch of business.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्तिवारिक
Śānti-vārika (EI 12, 30, 33), priest in charge of the performance of propitiatory rites or the priest who provides for śānti-vāri, ‘propitiatory water’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्त्यागार
śānty-āgāra (EI 12, 30), room wherein a bath is taken with the propitiatory water after a sacrifice; the room for performing propitiatory rites. See Śāntyāgārika, Śāntyāgār-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्त्यागाराधिकृत
Śāntyāgār-ādhikṛta (EI 30), priest in charge of the room for the performance of propitiatory rites. Cf. śānty-āgāra, Śānty-āgārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शान्त्यागारिक
Śāntyāgārika (EI 30), same as Śāntyāgār-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्हओननोस्हओ
Shaonano Shao (EI 30), known from the legend of Kuṣāṇa coins; same as Sāhānuṣāhī (q. v.), Persian Shāhān Shāh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपादलक्ष
Sapādalakṣa (IE 8-4), name of two territories so called with reference to the theoretical number of villages in each of them. Cf. Pādonalakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपिण्डीकरणश्राद्ध
sapiṇḍīkaraṇa-śrāddha (CII 4), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तक्षेत्र
sapta-kṣetra (IA 19), Jain; seven spheres of action.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तमचक्रवर्तिन्
Saptama-cakravartin (LP), ‘the seventh emperor’, i. e. the ruling monarch; according to the Abhidhānacintāmaṇi, the six [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-300" target="_blank">Page-300+ 40</a>] older Cakravartins are: Māndhātā Dhundhumāraś = ca Hariścan-draḥ Purūravāḥ | Bharataḥ Kārtavīryaś = ca ṣaḍ = ete cakravartinaḥ ||<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=299" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तमातृ
Sapta-mātṛ (EI 23), the seven Divine Mothers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तामात्य
Sapt-āmātya (EI 27), an officer in charge of seven departments. Cf. Pañca-karaṇ-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्ताम्भोधि
sapt-āmbhodhi (EI 16), name of a mahādāna; same as sapta-sāgara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्ताङ्ग
sapt-āṅga (CII CITD), the seven constituent^1 parts of a kingdom, viz., king, ministers, allies, treasury, territory, forts and forces.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तसागर|सप्तसागरः
sapta-sāgara (EI 24), name of a mahādāna; same as sapt-āmbhodhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तसन्तान
sapta-santāna (SITI), also called sapta-santati; merit equal to that obtainable through progeny from their performance of seven kinds of great deeds, viz. digging of tanks, hoarding of treasure, founding of agrahāras, erection of temples, creation of flower gardens, getting literary works written by poets, and the establishment of Choultries. An inscription (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, pp. 88 ff.) mentions the following seven meritorious acts a man ought to perform during his lifetime; viz. procreation of sons, accumulation of wealth, planting of groves, helping people (Brāhmaṇas) to marry, getting poems composed, erection of temples and excavation of tanks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तसन्तति
sapta-santati (SITI), same as sapta-santāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्तविधि
sapta-vidhi (LP), probably, seven kinds of defects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शर|शरं|शरः
śara (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारा
sārā (EI 9; LP), care; cf. etair = aṣṭabhir = goṣṭhikaiḥ … sārā karaṇīyā, ‘[this place of worship] has to be taken care of by the following eight trustees’. Cf. also Gujarātī sāravār.<BR> (EI 8, 11), supervision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरभङ्ग|शरभङ्गः
Śarabhaṅga (IE 8-3; 8-8; EI 23), a leader of forces; an officer of the military department; possibly, a military governor; same as Persian Sarhang and Hindī Serāṅg; also spelt Sarabhaṅga and Sarobhaṅga; Wilson's Glossary explains Sarhang as ‘a commander’ and says, “but [it is] generally applied in India to the headman of a native crew, whether on board a ship or a boat; also to the headman of a gang of natives attached to artillery, dragging guns, or to the army in general, as tent-pitchers, and the like, or to the head of gangs of a superior order of labourers employed in public or private works, in docks, buildings, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-301" target="_blank">Page-301+ 40</a>] etc.’ Cf. Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., pp. 123, 166 (spelt Sarobhaṅga), Ind. Cult., Vol. VII, p. 309. Kane (Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 1005) is certainly wrong when he thinks that it may be connected with śarayantra and Śarayantrin (a title bestowed in Mithilā upon a very learned man who faced the ordeal of answering satisfactorily all questions on any śāstra put to him by learned Ācāryas and also the questions put by common people). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, pp. 95. ff. See Sarāṅgha, Sarāhang, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=300" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारदा
Sāradā, name of the alphabet which developed out of late Brāhmī and was prevalent in the Kashmir region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सराहन्ग्
Sarāhang (IA 20), also called Sarang, Sarhang, etc. See Sarāṅgha, Śarabhaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरणागतवज्रपञ्जर
Śaraṇāgata-vajrapañjara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 317), ‘the impregnable shelter for one who seeks for it’; a subordinate title of the Kannaḍa-speaking area; used by the Sena kings of Bengal because they hailed from the same region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरन्ग्
Sarang (IA 20), also called Sarhang, Sarāhang, etc.; see Sarāṅgha, Śarabhaṅga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सराङ्घ
Sarāṅgha (IE 8-3), Persian Sarhang and Indian Śarabhaṅga, Serāṅg, etc. cf. Giligittā-sarāṅgha, ‘the chief of the army at Gilgit’, in the Hatun inscription of Paṭoladeva (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 228).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरस्वतीभाण्डार
Sarasvatī-bhāṇḍāra (EI 25; SITI), a library. Cf. Saras-vatī-bhāṇḍārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरस्वतीभाण्डारिक
Sarasvatī-bhāṇḍārika (EI 25), librarian. Cf. Sarasvatī-bhāṇḍāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरयन्त्र
śarayantra, Maithilī; test [prevalent in Mithilā] of the scholarship of one who is prepared to answer any question on any śāstra put to him by any other scholar or by the common people. See Proc. AIOC, Benares, 1943; Kane, Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 1005.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरयन्त्रक
śarayantraka (IE 3-1), same as sūtra; the string passing through the hole in the leaves of manuscripts for holding them together (Vāsavadatta, Hall's ed., p. 250).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरयन्त्रिन्
Śarayantrin (EI 35), one who has been successful in the śarayantra test of Mithilā. See śarayantra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारयित्वा
sārayitvā (LP), ‘having finished’; cf. Gujarātī sārvuṃ, ‘to accomplish’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्धञ्चर
Sārdhañcara, Sārdhañcarī (LL), companion of a Jain monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्धंविहारिन्
Sārdhaṃvihārin, cf. Sādhyavihāri (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-302" target="_blank">Page-302+ 40</a>] p. 10), Pāli saddhivihāri; one's fellow-priest living at the same monastery; a fellow-student. Cf. F. Edgerton, Bud. Hyb. Sans. Gram. Dict., Vol. II, p. 593. See Sadhryagvihārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=301" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्हन्ग्
Sarhang (IE 8-3; IA 20), Persian; see Śarabhaṅga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरीर|शरीरं
śarīra (SITI), person; individual.<BR> (EI 24; ML), corporeal relies of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सरोभङ्ग
Sarobhaṅga (IE 8-3), same as Śarabhaṅga or Sarabhaṅga (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्प|सर्पः
sarpa (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्पबलि
sarpa-bali (IA 19), an offering in snake-worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्षप|सर्षपः
sarṣapa, a small unit of measurement; sometimes specified as ‘red’ (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्थवाह|सार्थवाहः
Sārthavāha (IE 8-3; EI 24, 31; BL; LL), a trader, a merchant; designation of a member of the mercantile community represented on an administrative board like the Pañcāyat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्थवाहिनी
Sārthavāhinī (EI 1, 24), wife of a merchant (Sārthavāha) or a female merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्थवहित्र
sārtha-vahitra (IE 8-3), probably, a cart-load of articles for sale.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सारूप्य|सारूप्यं
sārūpya (CITD), assimilation in the deity, one of the four states of mukti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सार्वभौम|सार्वभौमः|सार्व्वभौम|सार्व्वभौमः
Sārvabhauma (EI 7, 27, 30, 32), title of imperial rulers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाभ्यन्तरसिद्धि
sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi (IA 19; SII 11-1), a fiscal term denoting full and complete right of enjoyment of agricultural income or internal revenue or taxes to be paid to the village authorities; cf. sarv-ābhyantara-siddhyā (IA 18), also abhyantara-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदण्डनायक
Sarva-daṇḍa-nāyaka (CII 3; IA 9; IA BL), official designation; ‘lord of all the forces’; cf. Samasta-sainy-ādhipati. See Daṇḍa-nāyaka, Mahādaṇḍanāyaka, Sarva-mahā-daṇḍanāyaka. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. VIII, p. 19; Vol. IX, p. 167.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदेशाधिकारिन्
Sarva-deś-ādhikārin (AI 7), chief minister; see Deśādhikṛta, Sarv-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकाराधिकृत
Sarv-ādhikār-ādhikṛta (EI 31), chief minister or administrator; same as Sarv-ādhikārin, Sarv-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकारकरण
Sarv-ādhikāra-karaṇa (EI 30), probably, the office of the chief secretary, administrator or minister.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकारनियुक्त
Sarv-ādhikāra-niyukta (EI 32), official designation; same as Sarv-ādhikārin, Sarv-ādhyakṣa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकारिन्|सर्व्वाधिकारिन्
Sarv-ādhikārin (IE 8-3; EI 19; CII 4; HD), prime minister (cf. Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 568); minister plenipotentiary [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-303" target="_blank">Page-303+ 39</a>] or viceroy; sometimes also called Senāpati, Mahāpradhāna, Hiriya-bhaṇḍāgārin, Mahāsāmanta, Sen-ādi-bāhattara-niyog-ādhipati, Daṇḍanāyaka, Mahāpasāyita, Amātya, Paramaviśvāsin or Mahāpramaviśvāsin, etc., additionally.<BR> (IE 8-3), a governor or chief administrator (cf. ‘the Sarv-ādhikārin of Hagaraṭage-300’).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=302" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाध्यक्ष
Sarv-ādhyakṣa (EI 24, 27; CII 3), literally, a general superintendent; probably, the chief minister or administrator; same as Sarv-ādhikārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाधिकृत
Sarv-ādhikṛta (HD), same as Sarv-ādhikārin, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, pp. 360, 362. See Mahāsarvādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाग्रहार
sarv-āgrahāra (EI 21), same as sarva-mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजात
sarva-jāta, cf. sarva-jātaa-bhoga-nirastyā (EI 8-5), ‘with all kinds of the [king’s] rights renounced’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वमान्य
sarva-mānya (IE 8-5, SITI; CITD), a free tenure; a rent-free holding; land exempted from taxes; lands and villages fully exempt from all taxes. This corresponds to the ir̤aiyili class of land mentioned in the Col̤̣a inscriptions. Often this is associated with aṣṭa-bhoga, i. e. the eight forms of enjoying the land. For a discussion of this form of land tenure, see JAHRS, Vol. X, pp. 123-32. It is noteworthy that even the so-called tax-free (ir̤aiyili) lands paid to the king certain dues of the nature of taxes. See K. A. Nilakanta Sastri, The Col̤̣as, 2nd ed., pp. 534-35. See sarva-namasya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वमेध|सर्वमेधः
sarva-medha (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वनमस्कृत
sarva-namaskṛta (IA 8), same as sarva-namasya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वनमस्य
sarva-namasya (IE 8-5; EI 23; CITD), a rent-free holding; same as sarva-mānya, sarva-namaskṛta, namasya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वनियोग
sarva-niyoga (EI 7), exclusive property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वसैन्याधिकारिन्
Sarva-sainy-ādhikārin (IE 8-3), commander-in-chief; cf. Maneya-samasta-sainy-ādhipati, commander of all the soldiers in the royal household; also cf. Sarva-daṇḍa-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वस्वहरण|सर्व्वस्वहरण
sarvasva-haraṇa (SITI), forfeiture of one's entire property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वतन्त्राधिकृत
Sarva-tantr-ādhikṛta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV pp. 144-45), a superintendent of all departments; but tantra is used in South Indian records in the sense of ‘the army’. See tantra, Tantr-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वतोभद्र|सर्वतोभद्रः|सर्व्वतोभद्र|सर्व्वतोभद्रं|सर्व्वतोभद्रः
sarvatobhadra (EI 9), a building having doors on all the four sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=303" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वतोभद्रिका
sarvatobhadrikā (LL; HA), quadruple image showing a Jina (or several Jinas) on each of the four faces; same as caumukha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्ववादिनायक
Sarvavādināyaka (EI 10), explained as ‘superintendent of the intelligence department’; probably, ‘the chief court Pandit.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाय
sarv-āya (EI 15), all the usual dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वीय|सर्व्वीय|सर्व्वीयः
sarvīya (EI 13), ‘good to all’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासन|शासनं
śāsana (EI 19; IA 20), order, a royal edict; any royal record (cf. vijaya-śāsana).<BR> (IE 8-4; EI 13, 23; CII 3; BL), a charter; land or village granted by a charter; rent-free land or village; sometimes suffixed to the names of localities which were once rent-free holdings. See also tāmra-śāsana, a technical term for a deed of conveyance on copper-plates.<BR> (EI 9, 10), a doctrine; religion or religious faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनबद्ध
Śāsana-baddha (SITI), people bound by a royal charter; original grantees of a charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनभाण्डारिन्
Śāsana-bhāṇḍārin (EI 25), official designation; cf. Śāsan-ādhikārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनदेवी
Śāsanadevī (IA 18), divine female messenger of a Jain Arhat; same as Śāsana-sundarī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनाधिकारिक
Śāsan-ādhikārika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 155, text line 85), same as Śāsan-ādhikārin, etc.; officer in charge of grants (or their writing or issue), mentioned along with Dān-ādhikārin, ‘officer in charge of gifts’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनाधिकारिन्
Śāsan-ādhikārin (EI 28, 31), officer in charge of royal grants or their issue, who was often the writer of documents; same as Śāsan-ādhikārika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनपटा
śāsana-paṭā (Chamba, etc.), charter; same as Sanskrit śāsana-paṭṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनमर्यादा
śāsana-maryādā (EI 15), specification of privileges by a charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनार्धिक
śāsan-ārdhika (IE 8-5; 12, 28), name of a levy; probably, the half of the cultivator's share of the produce of the land in the gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासयितृ
Śāsayitṛ (EI 12; BL), one who is responsible for getting a royal grant executed; cf. Dūtaka, Lekhayitṛ, Ājñāpti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनसञ्चारिन्
Śāsana-sañcārin (EI 8, 24), same as Ājñā-sañcārin; an official messenger.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनसुन्दरी
Śāsana-sundarī (IA 30), Jain; same as Śāsandevī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=304" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शासनिककायस्थ
Śāsanika-kāyastha (EI 11), writer of a grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शशाङ्क|शशांक|शशाङ्कः
śaśāṅka (IE 7-71-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सष्घानी
s̤as̤ghānī, billon coin of the Tughluq Sult̤āns, equal to six copper jitals and to (1/8) of a silver ṭaṅka; same as cha-gānī and śāśukāni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शशिन्
śaśin (EI 25), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षष्ठाधिकृत
Ṣaṣṭh-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; HD), a collector of the king's grain share which was originally one-sixth of the produce according to many authorities; cf. Dhruvasthān-ādhikaraṇika. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 246.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षष्ठतप
ṣaṣṭhatapa (IA 19), Jain; a kind of penance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षष्ठीअमावास्या
ṣaṣṭhī-amāvāsyā, cf. caṭṭī-amavāse (EI 5), new-moon following the campā-ṣaṣṭhī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सष्टिरात्र
Saṣṭirātra (BL), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शास्त्र|शास्त्रं
śāstra (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाशुकानि
śāśukāni, Indianised form of s̤as̤ghānī; also called śāśukāni-ṭaṅka. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, ‘The Śāṇa’, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाश्वतीय
śāśvatīya (SITI), perpetuity, eternity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शत|शतं
śata, cf. ekādaśa-śata (ML), ‘one hundred and eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सात|सातं
Sāta (EI 32), abbreviation of the name Śātavāhana or Śātakarṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतघ्नी
śataghnī (IA 7, 12), a gun or canon according to late works; a mechanical weapon placed at the gate of forts according to the Vasudevahiṇḍī (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, No. 1, p. 15). Seekālacakra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतमान|शतमानः
śatamāna, name of a coin; a silver coin weighing 320 ratis (rarely also 160 ratis); also called pala, niṣka, śukti, aṣṭamikā and nalā; wrongly regarded as 100 ratis in weight. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 41, 46-47. For śatamāna as a gold coin, see ibid., Vol. XV, p. 140.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शताङ्ग|शतांग|शताङ्गः
śatāṅga (EI 3), a car.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्चतुष्किका
ṣaṭ-catuṣkikā, cf. cha-cokī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतेर|सतेरः
satera, sateraka, same as Greek stater; regarded as equal to two dīnāras (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 153).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सती
satī (EI 6, 30; CII 3, 4; BL; CITD), literally, ‘a chaste woman’; really ‘a woman burning herself with her husband’.<BR> (EI 6, 30), self-immolation of a widow usually on the funeral pyre of her husband; usually spelt suttee in English.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतिका
śatikā (EI 28), cf. saikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतिलोदक
sa-til-odaka (IA 19), cf. sa-til-odakena vidhinā; same as udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=305" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्क
satka (EI, 1, 13; IA 17), Sanskritised from Prakrit santaka; ‘the holding of … ’, ‘belonging to … ’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्कर्मन्|षट्कर्म्मन्
ṣaṭ-karman (SII 1), the six duties of a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्पञ्चाशत्|षट्पंचाशत्
ṣaṭpañcāśat, ‘all’; cf. ṣaṭpañcāśad-deśa = chappanna-deśa (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 217, note 7), literally, ‘fiftysix countries’; but really, ‘all the world’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्पण
ṣaṭ-paṇa, cf. ar̤uvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्पुरुष|सत्पुरुषः
Satpuruṣa (LL), a Buddhist saint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्र|सत्त्रं|सत्रं
satra (EI 10, 19, 23, 26), same as sattra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्त्र
sattra (SII 1; CII 3, 4), ‘a charitable feeding house’; an alms-house; sometimes used to indicate one of the five mahā-yajñas, usually called atithi. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8.<BR> (EI 10, 19, 23), also spelt satra; hospitality to guests; one of the five mahāyajñas.<BR> (IA 15), a hall for the charitable distribution of food, etc. Cf. satra-śālā (SII 11-1), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्रागार
satr-āgāra (LP), a house where alms are distributed. Cf. satra-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्रागारकरण
satr-āgāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); department of Dharmaśālās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्रप्
Satrap (IA 20), Greek; same as Khshathrapāvan, Kṣatrapa, Sertīp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्त्रपति
Sattrapati (BL), priest in charge of a sacrificial session.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्त्रिंशत्
ṣaṭtriṃśat, literally, ‘thirtysix’, but actually ‘all’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 115). See aṣṭādaśa, ṣaṭapañcāśat, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षट्त्रिंशद्दण्डायुध
ṣaṭtriṃśad-daṇḍ-āyudha (LP), thirtysix (really, all), kinds of weapons; sometimes enumerated as: Cakra pāsa mogaru gadā ghana tomara tīraha | sakati sūla trisūla vajra kātara karaḍaṃḍha || Paṭukaṭārī kaṃta sarasī ghaḍu avājī | kaṇīu churī khaḍga nāli golā nārājī || ṣaṃḍuṃ ṣapnu muṃsala hala sīṃgani pharasī gupati gaṇi | niṣaṃga śāṃgi aṃkuśa guruja kuhaka bāṇa batrīsa bhaṇi || Cf. Prācīnagurjarakāvyasaṃgraha, G. O. S., pp. 106-07.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शात्त्विकदान
śāttvika-dāna (SITI), gift without the pouring of water and therefore not expecting any merit in return for the donation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्यधर्मस्थित
Satyadharma-sthita (IE 8-2), ‘adherent of the true religion’; same as Dharma-sthita; epithet of a Kuṣāṇa king probably pointing to his Buddhist faith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सत्यज्ञानदरिशनिगल्
Satya-jñāna-dariśanigal̤ (SITI), followers of a sect of Śaivism; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-307" target="_blank">Page-307+ 40</a>] evidently those belonging to the lineage of Měykaṇḍār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=306" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौ
Śau, abbreviation of Śaulkika or Śauṇḍika (A. R. Ep., 1953-54, No. B 117).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौध|सौधः
saudha (IA 15), used in the sense of brahmapurī, ‘a Brāhmaṇa settlement’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौगन्धिक|सौगंधिक|सौगन्धिकं|सौगन्धिकः
Saugandhika, cf. Prakrit Sagandhaka (EI 18); a dealer in scents or superintendent of the perfumery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौगतपरिव्राजक
Saugata-parivrājaka (BL), a Buddhist mendicant^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौल्किक|शौल्किकः
Śaulkika (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; EI 30; HD), toll-collector or customs officer; officer in charge of collecting customs duties; superintendent of tolls or customs duties. See Yājñavalkyasmṛti, II. 173; CII, Vol. III, pp. 50, 52; Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 246.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौम्य|सौम्यः
saumya (EI 27), lunar or auspicious.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौनिक|शौनिकः
Śaunika (IE 8-3), superintendent of slaughter-houses and the sale of meat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शौण्डिक|शौंडिक|शौंडिकः|शौण्डिकः
Śauṇḍika (IE 8-5), vintner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौत्रिक|सौत्रिकः
Sautrika (LL), weaver.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्ण|सौवर्णं|सौवर्णः
sauvarṇa (EI 19), name of a coin; cf. suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्णिक|सौवर्णिकः
Sauvarṇika (HD), cf. Prakrit Sovaṇika (EI 10), a goldsmith; the State goldsmith. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, pp. 144-45. See Hairaṇyika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्णिक|सौवर्णिकः
sauvarṇika (HRS), profits of the royal monopoly of manufacture of gold and silver articles, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सव|सवं|सवः
sava (IE 8-1), contraction of Prakrit savachara = Sanskrit saṃvatsara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शावडि
śāvaḍi (IE 8-4), a subdivision; same as uśāvaḍi or cāvaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवर्णवृत्ति
savarṇa-vṛtti (SITI), profession of writing documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सावु
Sāvu (EI 9; CII 4), a title; same as Sāhu (Sanskrit Sādhu).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शय|शयः
śaya (IE 3-4), derived from a Chinese word; paper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सायक|सायकः
sāyaka (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सायन|सायनं
sāyana (CII 3), ‘inclusive of precession^1 of the equinoxes’.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शयनपूजा
śayana-pūjā (IE 8-8), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शयनीय|शयनीयं
śayanīya, a cot; cf. śayanīy-āsana-siddānnaṃ na dāpayet (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 171).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सायर
sāyara (PJS), Arabic shāher; a tax on palm-tree juice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शय्याग्राहक
Śayyāgrāhaka (HD), explained as ‘the guardian of the bed-chamber.’ See A. S. Gadre, Imp. Ins. Bar. St., p. 72. Cf. Śayyāpāla, Vāsāgārika, Vitān-ādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शय्यापाल|शय्यापालः
Śayyāpāla (EI 25; HD), officer in charge of the king's bed [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-308" target="_blank">Page-308+ 40</a>] (i. e. bed-chamber); guardian of the bed-chamber. See Śayyāgrāhaka, Vāsāgārika, Vitān-ādhipa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=307" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेइआ
seiā (IE 8-8), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit selikā (q. v.); cf. seigā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेइगा
seigā (IE 8-8), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit setikā (q. v.); cf. seiā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेगाण
Segāṇa (BL), official designation of uncertain import, found in the Chamba inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक
śeka (EI 11), same as Sanskrit śikya, a loop or swing made of rope and suspended from the ends of a pole placed on one's shoulder for carrying loads, or the load itself. Cf. saṃkācitaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेक्यकार
Sekyakāra (EI 12; BL), a brazier; secondarily, an engraver; cf. Bengali seṅkrā, a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेलहस्त
Selahasta (EI 11), probably, the collector of the king's grain share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाभक्त
senā-bhakta (HRS), contribution of oil, rice, etc., which the villagers had to pay to the royal army on march, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनभोग
Sena-bhoga, cf. Śeṇai-bhogam (SITI), an accountant. See Śāṇa-bhoga, Senabova.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनभोगिक
Senabhogika (EI 18; HD), same as Senabova, etc.; a clerk or an accountant-clerk. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 285.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनबोव
Senabova (EI 5, 10; IA 18; SII 11-1), a clerk; an accountant; a village accountant; modern Śānabhoga or Kul̤karṇī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाधिकारिक
Sen-ādhikārika (EI 23), same as Senāpati, Sen-ādhipati, etc.; a general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाधिप
Sen-ādhipa (BL), ‘leader of forces’. See Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाधिपति
Sen-ādhipati (IE 8-3; EI 23; SII 11-1), same as Sen-ādhikārika, etc.; sometimes also called Mahāpradhāna, Hěri-sandhivigrahin, Kaḍita-věrgaḍě, etc., additionally. Cf. Mahā-senādhipati, Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनादिबाहत्तरनियोगाधिष्ठायक
Sen-ādi-bāhattara-niyog-ādhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-2; EI 5), superintendent of all appointments including those in the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनगण
Sena-gaṇa (SITI), a division of the Jain community; also known as Sen-ānvaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनागोप|सेनागोपः
Senāgopa (LL), a general; same as Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनाङ्ग|सेनांग|सेनाङ्गं
sen-āṅga (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनैमुदलियार्
Senai-mudaliyār (SITI), Tamil; same as Sanskrit-Tamil Senāpatiy-āl̤̣vār; name of the god Viṣvaksenai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनैयळ्ङ्गाडिक
Senaiy-aṅgāḍikal̤̣ (SITI), a class of merchants who follow [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-309" target="_blank">Page-309+ 40</a>] the army with their merchandise; a class of cloth merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=308" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनानीनेत्र
senānī-netra (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनापति|सेनापतिः
Senāpati (IE 8-3), leader of forces; mentioned separately along with Bal-ādhyakṣa; probably, a subordinate of the latter; the military governor of a district, according to some (HD); commander-in-chief (ASLV), also called Sarva-sainy-ādhikārin and Dalavāya, i. e. the chief officer in charge of the military department. See Bṛhaspati quoted by Viśvarūpa on Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 307; Ind. Ant., Vol. XV, p. 187. Puṣyamitra, the founder of the Śuṅga dynasty, was called Senāpati even after his accession to the Maurya throne. See Sen-ādhipa, etc.; cf. also Anusenāpati (EI 18).<BR> (IE 8-3), sometimes called Mahāpradhāna, Bāhattara-niyogādhiṣṭhāyaka, Paṭṭa-sāhan-ādhipati, etc., additionally.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनापतिप्पेरुविलै
senāpati-ppěruvilai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; the sale of lands of a Viṣṇu temple executed in the name of Senai-mudaliyār, i. e. the god Viṣvaksenai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेनापतिया
Senāpatiy-āl̤̣vār (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; same as Senai-mudaliyār, i. e. the god Viṣvaksenai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेर्
ser (Chamba), also called seri; crown land; state demesne.<BR> (Chamba, etc.), a weight equal to 80 tolās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेराङ्ग्
Serāṅg (IE), see Śarabhaṅga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेरि
seri (Chamba), same as ser; crown-land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेर्तीप्
Sertīp (IA 20), Persian; same as Old Persian Khshthrapā-van and Indian Kṣatrapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेर्वै
śervai (ASLV), Tamil; derived from Sanskrit sevā (q. v.); a service inām.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेषशीर्ष
śeṣa-śīrṣa (IE 7-1-2), ‘one thousand’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेसिबिय्यमु
sesi-biyyamu (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; sesi means the remains of flowers, raw rice and other offerings made to an idol or used in a śubha-kārya and afterwards distributed among the worshippers and attendants. The expression probably means raw rice over which incantations have been pronounced and which is thrown on the heads of the bride and bridegroom during the marriage ceremony and in connection with similar other rites.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेतिका
setikā (IE 8-5; EI 25), Prakrit seiā, seigā; a measure of weight equal to two handfuls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टि
Śěṭṭi (ASLV), Sanskrit Śreṣṭhin; the leading member of a guild. Cf. Nagar-seṭh, Nagara-śreṣṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=309" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टिपत्तणस्वामिन्
Śěṭṭi-Pattaṇasvāmin (ASLV), designation of the president of a merchants' guild. Cf. Nagar-seṭh, Nagara-śreṣṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेतु|सेतुः
setu, embankment; income or taxes resulting from it (Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 108-09).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेवा
sevā, cf. Tamil sevai, śervai (SITI); service; inām for services; tax-free land given to servants for enjoyment in lieu of salary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेवक|सेवकः
Sevaka (SITI), a soldier; cf. sevaka-ttevai (SITI), expenses in connection with the supply and maintenance of retainers of chiefs and officers during their visit to a place.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेविडु
śeviḍu (SITI), Tamil; a small grain measure; (1/5) of an āl̤̣ākku.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाह्
Śāh^1 (IE 8-2; EI 30), Persian; royal title; same as Old Persian Khshāyathiya. See Sāhī.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dhaval Patel on 20160121. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/CORRECTIONS/issues/243. note: sh-Persian.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिबर
śibara, sibara (CII 4), a farm-house. But cf. śaibara, śaivara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्ध|सिद्धं|सिद्धः
Siddha (CII 4), a person possessing miraculous powers; an emancipated person.<BR> (CII 3), ‘a perfect one’; the epithet of a class of Jain saints who are invoked in the plural.<BR> (LL), a Jain saint.<BR> (CII 4), cf. siddham (q. v.), used at the beginning of inscriptions to ensure the success of the undertaking and meaning siddhir = astu, ‘let there be success’. Cf. siddhi.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twenty-four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्ध|सिद्धं|सिद्धः
siddha, (IE 8-5), income from land under cultivation. See siddh-āya, etc.<BR> (SITI), also called siddhi; the right of cultivating land; one of the eight kinds of enjoying landed property; may be the same as abhyantara-siddhi. See siddha, siddh-āya, ūrdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धचक्र
siddha-cakra (EI 2), a yantra for worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धम्
siddham (EI 30; CII 3), literally, ‘success has been attained’; an invocation found in early inscriptions at the commencement of the text; used in the sense of siddhir = astu, ‘let there be success’; sometimes confused with the praṇava; generally indicated in later records by a symbol having several varieties; sometimes indicated by the letter cha. Cf. siddhi<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धमातृका
Siddhamātṛkā, name of the Indian alphabet which is derived from Late Brāhmī and from which are derived North Indian alphabets like Nāgarī; wrongly called Kuṭila, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धान्न
siddh-ānna (IE 8-8), cooked rice or uncooked food (cf. Hindī sīdhā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=310" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धान्त|सिद्धांत|सिद्धान्तः
siddhānta (CII 4), ‘an established doctrine’; sometimes used to indicate the Śaiva doctrine or religion (SITI).<BR> Cf. Lākula-siddhānta (EI 32), doctrine of the Śaiva teacher Lakula (Lakulīśa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धान्तदर्शन
siddhānta-darśana (EI 32), philosophy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धपीठ|सिद्धपीठः
siddha-pīṭha, see yoga-pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धसाध्य|सिद्धसाध्यः
siddha-sādhya (EI 13), present income and the income that may accrue in future.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धस्थान
siddha-sthāna (EI 22), the place sanctified by a holy man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धाय
siddh-āya (EI 23; SII 11-2; ASLV), fixed income; regular income; same as Tamil sidd-āyam, sometimes explained as ‘a tax’ (EI 27); probably, agricultural income.<BR> (SITI), a fixed assessment; minor taxes; minor taxes payable in cash in the days of the Vijayanagara kings; also written in Tamil as sidd-āyam, sitt-āyam. See pratiṣiddh-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धायतन
siddh-āyatana (EI 33), cf. pūrva-siddh-āyatana (Buddhist); temple associated with a Siddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिद्धि|सिद्धिः
siddhi (CII 4), emancipation; sometimes used at the beginning of documents to ensure the success of the undertaking, as siddham in early inscriptions, and meaning siddhir = astu.<BR> (SITI), same as siddham, the right of cultivating land.<BR> Cf. ūrdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi-yutā (IA 18), together with income from horticulture and agriculture; cf. sa-bāhy-ābhyantara-siddhi, siddhi meaning ‘income’. (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीघ्रलिखित
śīghra-likhita, a document written in a quick hand or cursive characters (SII, Vol. XI, Part i, p. 29, No. 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिग्लोस्
siglos (IE 8-8), name of the old silver coin of the Persians (86.45 grains or 5.6 grammes).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिकावण
sikāvaṇa (EI 27), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिखर|शिखरं|शिखरः
śikhara (SITI; CITD), top portion of the turret built over the main shrine and the gateway of a temple; the top of the gopura or vimāna of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिखिन्
śikhin (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिला
śilā (IA 23), [an inscription on] stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलागृह
śilā-gṛha (EI 22), a stone mansion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलागुण्ठ
śilā-guṇṭha (EI 12), Sanskrit-Telugu; a pond with a demarcation stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाकर्मान्त
śilā-karmānta (LL), stone-work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाकूट
Śilā-kūṭa (EI 1), a stone-cutter; cf. Śilā-kuṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाकुट्ट
Śilā-kuṭṭa (IA 15), a stone-cutter; cf. Śilā-kūṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=311" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलालष्टि
śilā-laṣṭi (CII 4), Sanskrit śilā-yaṣṭi; memorial pillar of stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलालेख
śilā-lekha (IA 30; SITI), writing on a stone; an inscription on stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीलन|शीलनं
śīlana (CII 1), same as anuśīlana; practice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीलपत्र
śīla-patra (LP), certificate of good character.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाप्रावेश
śilā-prāveśa (IA 9), laying the corner-stone of a building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलाशासन
śilā-śāsana (IA 30), a stone-charter; a document engraved on stone.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्पिन्
Śilpin (EI 4, 8; BL), epithet of an artist or artisan; generally, applied to engravers of inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्पकार|शिल्पकारः
Śilpakāra (EI 32), same as Śilpin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोतर
śilotara (EI 32), also called śilotarī, śilotra, śilotrī, śilot-tara; name of a tax or income; cf. śrotaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोतरी
śilotarī (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोत्र
śilotra (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोत्री
śilotrī (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलोत्तर
śilottara (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्वरि
śilvari (EI 23), Tamil; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीम
sīma (IA 18), used for ‘country’ in the areas on the banks of the Kṛṣṇā and the Godāvarī.<BR> Cf. Kona-sīma (EI 32), also called a deśa, maṇḍala, sthala, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमा
sīmā (EI 11), five types enumerated by Nārada: Dhvajinī matsyinī c = aiva naidhānī bhaya-varjitā | rājaśāsana-nītā ca sīmā pañca-vidhā smṛtā (i. e. big trees or hills, rivers or tanks, underground signs and artificial marks made by men and by the king's order).<BR> Cf. Tamil śīrmai, śīmai (SITI), a territorial division; also called sīman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमकर्मकर
Sīmakarmakara (HD), officer in charge of boundaries or of boundary disputes. See CII, Vol. III, pp. 213, 216.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमन्
sīman (IE 8-4; ASLV), Kannaḍa sīmě; a small territorial unit like a Parganā; the sub-division of a district; sometimes used to indicate ‘a province’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमाविवाद|सीमाविवादः
sīmā-vivāda, cf. Tamil śīmai-vivādam (SITI), a boundary dispute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीमेहब्बरुव
Śīměhabbaruva (ASLV), an officer associated with the administrative unit called sīmai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
siṃhakara, ‘lion-tax’ (Ghoshal, HRS, p. 232).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहनिका
siṃhanikā, service rendered in lieu of taxes (Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 28).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=312" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहपाद
siṃha-pāda, cf. Tamil śiṅga-pādam (SITI), legs of a vessel or vessel-stand in the shape of lion's feet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहासन|सिंहासनं|सिंहासनः
siṃh-āsana (EI 29), literally, ‘the lion-seat’; the throne which was one of the royal insignia. Cf. siṃha-sthāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहासनाधिपति
Siṃhāsan-ādhipati (EI 25), officer in charge of the king's throne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहस्तम्भ
siṃha-stambha (LL), lion-pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिंहस्थान
siṃha-sthāna (LL), a lion-seat; same as siṃh-āsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिन्धु|सिंधु|सिंधुः|सिन्धुः
sindhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिन्दूर|सिंदूर|सिन्दूरं|सिंदूरः|सिन्दूरः
sindūra (IA 19), corruption of sindhura, an elephant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीरा
sīrā (IA 18), a land measure equal to four halas. See hala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरःप्रधानिन्
Śiraḥ-pradhānin (ASLV), cf. Tamil Śirappradāni (SITI), a senior minister; cf. Pradhāni, Mahāpradhāni, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरःस्थायिन्
śiraḥ-sthāyin (IA 17), used in the description of a trial by ordeal with reference to the bearing of some sacred symbol or image on the head of the accused while undergoing it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिरकटा
sira-kaṭā, cf. sira-kaṭā tambā-paṭā (JBORS, Vol. XVIII, pp. 219-20), Od̤iyā; same as rakata-paṭā, Sanskrit rakta-paṭṭaka. See also rakta-mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिरिडिक
siriḍika, siriḍikā (EI 32), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरोरक्षिक
Śiro-rakṣika (IE 8-3), body-guard of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरोवर्त्तना
śiro-varttanā (SII 2), top part of a Śiva-liṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीर्षक|शीर्षकं|शीर्षकः
Śīrṣaka (EI 28), village headman; same as Mutuḍa or Mul̤uḍa of South Indian inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरुपाडु
śirupāḍu (EI 30), Tamil; an endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिष्षिन्ति
śiṣṣinti (IA 18), modification of śiṣya-paṅkti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिष्य|शिष्यः
Śiṣya (SII 1), a pupil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीता
sītā (EI 31), cultivated land. Cf. hala.<BR> (HRS), produce of the royal farms, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सितचामर
sita-cāmara (EI 29), ‘white chowrie’; one of the royal insignia.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीताधयक्ष
Sīt-ādhayakṣa (CII 4), officer in charge of the king's Khās Mahāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीतालेख्य
sītālekhya (IA 12), chilly-powder.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीतांशु|शीतांशुः
śītāṃśu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सितपिञ्छ
sitapiñcha (SII 2), a swan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीतरश्मि|शीतरश्मिः
śītaraśmi (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शीतारि
śītāri (SITI), Tamil; burning of incenses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=313" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिथिलाचार्य
Śithil-ācārya (IA 19), Jain; an Ācārya permitting laxity of observances.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीत्क
sītka (EI 11), a well.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिव|शिवं|शिवः
śiva (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR> (SITI), title applied to a Śaiva devotee; often śiva, śambhu etc., are used as the ending of the names of Śaiva ascetics.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिव|शिवं|शिवः
śiva, cf. śrīvijaya-śiva-Mṛgeśavarman; used as an honorific. Cf. śrī, vijaya, vijayaśiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवभाण्डारिन्
Śiva-bhāṇḍārin (SITI), treasury officer of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवब्राह्मण
Śiva-Brāhmaṇa (EI 25; SITI), a Śaiva Brāhmaṇa; the priest of a Śiva temple; also called Ādi-śaiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवदीक्षा
śiva-dīkṣā (EI 32), same as śaiva-dīkṣā, śiva-maṇḍala-dīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवद्रोहिन्
Śiva-drohin (ASLV), a sinner against the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवमान
śiva-māna (EI 33), a measure approved by a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवमण्डलदीक्षा
śivamaṇḍala-dīkṣā (EI 32), same as śaiva-dīkṣā, śiva-dīkṣā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवपञ्चायतन
Śiva-pañcāyatana (EI 27), a Śiva temple consisting of five shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवस्थल
śiva-sthala (CII 2-1), probably, the same as dharma-sthāna, or a Śiva shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवतिथि
Śiva-tithi (EI 5), same as Śiva-rātri or Śiva-caturdaśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिवयोगिन्
Śiva-yogin (SITI), a Śaiva ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कम्भ|स्कंभ|स्कंभः|स्कम्भः
skambha (LL), a post or pillar; cf. dīpa-skambha (LL), a lamp post. Same as Kannaḍa kamba, kamma. Cf. stambha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्दक|स्कंदक|स्कंदकः|स्कन्दकः
Skandaka (HD), a petty officer; probably the head of the village administration. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 175.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्दक|स्कंदक|स्कंदकः|स्कन्दकः
skandaka (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIII, p. 69), an instalment; cf. skandha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्ध|स्कंध|स्कंधः|स्कन्धः
skandha (LP), an instalment; cf. skandaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्धक
skandhaka (EI 3; HRS), known from Gujara-Pratīhāra records; name of a tax; probably, a cess at a certain rate per shoulder-load.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्कन्धावार|स्कंधावार|स्कन्धावारः
skandhāvāra (EI 29; CII 3; BL), camp; usually called jaya-skandhāvāra (i. e. the victorious camp) which indicates the capital of a king in some cases. Cf. Kannaḍa neleviḍu = Sanskrit sthira-śibira.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्लो
ślo (IE 8-1), abbreviation of śloka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्लोत्र
ślotra (EI 32), same as śilotara, etc.; cf. śrotaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्मत्
smat (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṃvat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्मृत्युपस्थान
smṛty-upasthāna, cf. satipaṭṭhāna (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=314" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्नानयात्रा
snāna-yātrā (IA 9), festival of bathing the image of Kṛṣṇa on Jyaiṣṭha su-di 15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्नानमहोत्सव
snāna-mahotsava (HA), bathing ceremony (i. e. birth-bath) of a Jina performed by Indra and other gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सो
So (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Soma-vāra, Monday.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोडशी
śoḍaśī, śoḍaśikā (SII 4), name of a coin which may have been (1/16) of the standard coin in weight or value; cf. paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षोडशिन्
ṣoḍaśin (EI 4, 22; CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोद्रङ्गीकृत्य
sodraṅgīkṛtya (IE 8-3), same as udraṅgīkṛtya; used in respect of a gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोलग
śol̤aga (IE 8-6), Kannaḍa; name of a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोम|सोमं|सोमः
soma (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमग्रहण
soma-grahaṇa (SII 1), lunar eclipse; same as soma-parvan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमपर्वन्
soma-parvan (LP), lunar eclipse; same as soma-grahaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमस्कन्द
Somaskanda, South Indian representation of Śiva along with Umā and Skanda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमवती
somavatī (IA 26), same as ba-di 15 falling on a Monday.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमयाग|सोमयागः
soma-yāga (CII 4), name of a Vedic sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोमयाजिन्
Somayājin (SITI), one who has performed the soma-yāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपान|सोपानं
sopāna (SITI), steps; stairs; a sloping roof; the base of the garbha-gṛha of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोतेर्
Soter (IE 8-2), Greek; ‘saviour’; royal title; translated into Prakrit as Tratara = Trātara (Sanskrit Trātṛ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोटी
śoṭī (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, pot for measuring liquids like wine; a ladleful; name of a measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्पार्हविहारता
spārha-vihāratā, cf. Prakrit phāsu-vihālatā (CII 1), comfort.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्पष्ट|स्पष्टं
spaṣṭa (CII 3), an astronomical term meaning ‘apparent’; cf. spaṣṭa-tithi, ‘an apparent tithi’, from which the mean tithi has to be determined.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्फोटन|स्फोटनं|स्फोटनः
sphoṭana (IE 8-5), cf. śira-sphoṭana, ‘breaking somebody's head.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्फुरम्
sphuram, quickly (Select Inscriptions, p. 240).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रा
Śrā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Śrāvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्ध|श्राद्धं
śrāddha (CII 4), funeral rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रद्धादान
śraddhā-dāna (ML), a pious gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्धाङ्ग
śrāddh-āṅga (EI 28), gift for the merit of a deceased person.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्धकर
śrāddha-kara, tax for performing śrāddha at Gayā (Rājatar., VI. 254; VII. 1008).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राद्धतिथि
śrāddha-tithi (CII 4), date on which the śrāddha is to be performed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राहे
śrāhe, also spelt śrāhi, srāhi, śrāhī, srāhī, ‘the year’ (probably [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-316" target="_blank">Page-316+ 40</a>] derived from Prakrit sarahi, Sanskrit śaradi, ‘in the year’); the period of 12 months. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 80, note 2; Vol. XXIX, p. 106; Vol. XXX, p. 161, note 12; XXXII, p. 233 and note 8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=315" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राहि
śrāhi, śrāhī (IE 8-1; EI 6, 23), probably, derived from Sanskrit śaradi = Prakrit sarahi; ‘in the year’; ‘the year’; used sometimes in place of saṃvat, but sometimes side by side with it. See srāhe, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्राहि
srāhi, srāhī, same as srāhe, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमण|श्रमणः
Śramaṇa (EI 8; CII 3; LL; BL), a Buddhist or Jain monk; an ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणश्राविका
Śramaṇa-śrāvikā (LL), female disciple of Jain ascetics. Cf. Śramaṇ-opāsaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रामणेर|श्रामणेरः
Śrāmaṇera (EI 25), cf. Sāmanera (EI 2); Buddhist; a novice monk; cf. the feminine form Śrāmaṇerī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणिका
Śramaṇikā (LL), cf. Samaṇikā (EI 25), a Buddhist nun.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणोद्देश
Śramaṇoddeśa (LL), Buddhist; a novice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रमणोपासक
Śramaṇ-opāsaka (LL), lay follower of Buddhist Śramaṇas. Cf. Śramaṇa-śrāvikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावक|श्रावकः
Śrāvaka (EI 7, 8, 24; ML; LL; HA), a lay follower of Jainism or Buddhism; cf. the feminine form Śrāvikā, sometimes called Śrāvikā bhaginī in Jain records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावक|श्रावकः
śrāvaka (CII 1), ‘a matter relating to a declaration’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावण|श्रावणः
śrāvaṇa (SITI), also called śrāvaṇa-patra (q. v.), sale deed; a document; cf. śālāvaṇam (SITI), a sale deed (āvaṇa-śālāvaṇam).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावणपत्र
śrāvaṇa-patra (EI 30), a deed of declaration; a sale-deed. Cf. śrāvaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्राविका
Śrāvikā (HA), cf. Sāvikā (EI 7), Jain; a female lay worshipper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रावित
śrāvita, cf. rāja-śrāvita (EI 6; IA 19), decree; a proclamation.<BR> (EI 28), religious instruction.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रे
śre (PJS; LP), contraction of Śreṣṭhin, ‘a banker’ or śreyase, ‘for the merit of … ’ (especially in medieval Jain inscriptions).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेणि|श्रेणिः
śreṇi, śreṇī (CII 3, 4; LL), Prakrit seni (EI 25); a corporation or guild; cf. śreṇī-bala, the army maintained by a guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेणिकरण
śreṇi-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of guilds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेष्ठिजीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय
śreṣṭhi-jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya, wrongly read as śreṣṭha (LP), [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-317" target="_blank">Page-317+ 40</a>] probably a mistake for jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya; name of a coin struck by Śreṣṭhin Viśvamalla. See jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla (or śrīmalla)-priya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=316" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेष्ठिन्
Śreṣṭhin (IE 8-3; CII 4; LL), a banker or merchant or the foreman of a guild; sometimes mentioned in the list of the king's officials and subordinates addressed by him while making a grant (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR> (BL), representative of the banker class in the council of the local administrators of a town. Cf. Śeṭṭi, Nagara-śreṣṭhin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्री
śrī (CII 3, etc.), honorific prefix to names often rendered variously in English; e. g., in the case of paramount sovereigns and their wives by ‘glorious’; of feudatories and other ordinary persons by ‘illustrious’; of priests, teachers, etc., by ‘saintly’; of gods by ‘holy’; sometimes śrī is used before consonants and śrīmat before vowels. The honorific śrī is sometimes used in South Indian records along with the words vijaya or vijaya-śiva (q. v.). Cf. śrī-ni, Śrīcaraṇa, etc.<BR> (IA 17), cf. śrī-pūrva used for śrī-yuta; śrī is sometimes repeated for emphasis, e. g., ‘śrī 108’ is written to indicate the repetition of the word for 108 times.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीबलि
śrī-bali (SITI), daily offering of the bali service in temples; also havir-bali. Cf. Tamil śrī-bali-koṭṭuvār, a musical troupe playing on the instruments at the time of the śrī-bali in temples.<BR> (SITI), image of the deity taken round the temple when the bali is offered; the procession circumambulating the temple at the time of the bali service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीबलिभोग
śrī-bali-bhoga (SITI), land set apart to meet the expenses of the śrī-bali service in a temple; also called śrī-bali-ppaṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीभाण्डार
śrī-bhāṇḍāra (EI 33; SITI), the treasury of a temple.<BR> (ASLV), collective name for the trustees of a temple; same as śrībhaṇḍāra-vāriyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीभण्डारवारियम्
śrībhaṇḍāra-vāriyam (EI 33), executive body in charge of the administration of a temple. Cf. śrī-bhāṇḍāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीचन्दन
Śrīcandana, a title of nobility in medieval Orissa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 310, text lines 8-9). Cf. Haricandana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीचरण
Śrī-caraṇa (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28), literally, ‘the honourable feet [of the king]’; the king; cf. Śrī-hasta, Śrī-pāda, śrī-ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीद्वार
śrī-dvāra (EI 6), a special type of gateway like the makara-toraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीघन|श्रीघनं|श्रीघनः
śrīghana (SII 1), glorious.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=317" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीगोशाला
śrī-gośālā, cf. Tamil tiru-kkośālai (SITI), cow-stall of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीहस्त
Śrī-hasta (IE 8-1, 8-8; EI 28), literally, ‘the honourable hands [of the king]’; the king; see Śrī-caraṇa, Śrī-pāda, śrī-ni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीज्ञान
śrī-jñāna, cf. Tamil tiru-ñānam (SITI), sacred hymns sung to the deity in a temple during worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकण्ठमणि
śrī-kaṇṭhamaṇi, cf. tiru-kkaṇṭamaṇi (SITI), a kind of necklace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकार|श्रीकारः
śrīkāra (LP), recognition by writing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरण|श्रीकरणं
śrīkaraṇa (IE 8-3; EI 11, 21, 31; HD), the drafting of documents; a scribe or scribe-accountant or secretary; the minister Hemādri was styled Sarva-śrīkaraṇa-prabhu (Hist. Dharm., Vol. I, p. 356, note 849). Cf. Karaṇa, Śrī-karaṇ-ādhipa, śrīsrīkaraṇa.<BR> (EI 23, 29, 30), record office; the record department; the department responsible for drawing up documents.<BR> (EI 30; CII 4), record officer; the officer in charge of drawing documents.<BR> Cf. Puravuvari-śrīkaraṇa-nāyaka (EI 21), official designation.<BR> Cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the income department.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणाधिप
Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa (IE 8-3; HD), superintendent of the department of records; head of all the scribes or of all the departments. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 17. Hemādri was styled Samasta-karaṇ-ādhīśvara or Samasta-karaṇ-ādhipati (Hist. Dharm., Vol. I, pp. 356-57, notes 850-51). See śrīkaraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणाग्रणी
Śrīkaraṇ-āgraṇī (HD), same as Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकारमुद्राङ्कित
śrīkāra-mudr-āṅkita (LP), sealed with the syllable śrī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणप्रभु
Śrīkaraṇa-prabhu (IE 8-3), same as Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणविदितम्
śrīkaraṇa-viditam (LP), ‘having informed the records office or officer’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकरणिन्
Śrīkaraṇin (EI 26), same as Śrīkaraṇ-ādhipa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकार्य
śrī-kārya (SII 2), management of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीकटक
śrī-kaṭaka (LP), royal camp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीखण्ड|श्रीखंड|श्रीखण्डः
śrīkhaṇḍa (LP), also spelt śrīṣaṇḍa; sandal wood.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीखण्डघोडु
śrīkhaṇḍa-ghoḍu (LP), a kind of horse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमाड
śrīmāḍa (EI 10), palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमदादिवराहद्रम्म
śrīmad-ādivarāha-dramma (EI 1), name of a coin, issued by king Ādivarāha (Bhoja I Pratīhāra, c. 835-85 A. D.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमाहेश्वर
Śrī-māheśvara (ASLV), a Śaiva ascetic who is one among the authorities of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमलय
śrī-malaya, cf. Tamil tiru-malai (SITI), literally, ‘the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-319" target="_blank">Page-319+ 40</a>] sacred hill;’ but really, the central shrine, generally of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=318" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमालिका
śrī-mālikā, cf. Tamil tiru-māl̤igai-ppatti (SITI), small shrines or niches in the prākāra of a temple on the inner side of the compound wall. Cf. tiru-māl̤igai-ppil̤ḷai, the temple executive.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमन्दिर
śrī-mandira, cf. Tamil tiru-mandiram (SITI), a temple; also tiru-mandira-kkoḍi, cloth threaded round the flag-staff of a temple during festivals. See also Tiru-mandirav-olai, a secretary of the government; an officer entrusted with the duty of communicating the decisions of the king in writing; also Tiru-mandirav-olai-nāyakam, the chief secretary to the government; chief of the tiru-mandirav-olai department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमल्
śrīmat (CII 3; IA 13), prefixed, like śrī, to names of persons and also of places; often used before names beginning with a vowel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमुख|श्रीमुखः
śrī-mukha (SII 12; SITI), royal order or charter; a letter from the king or a chief. Cf. Tamil tiru-muga-kkāṇam, expenses as wages, etc., paid to the person who brings the tiru-mugam (royal order) to the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनक्षत्र
śrī-nakṣatra, cf. Tamil tiru-nakṣatra (SITI), natal star; annual birthday; a year.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनामन्
śrī-nāman, cf. Tamil tiru-nāma-kkāṇi, tiru-nāmattu-kkāṇi (SITI), literally, ‘the hereditary right of enjoyment in the sacred name’; actually, land or village, generally tax-free, endowed to a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनयन
śrī-nayana, cf. Tamil tiru-nayanam (SITI), an ornament made of gold or silver resembling the eye and put on the eyes of the idol; same as Tamil kaṇ-malar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीनि
śrī-ni (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Śrīhasta-nirīkṣita, ‘examined by the king’. See ni and Śrī-hasta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपाद
Śrīpāda (IE 8-8), used to indicate ‘the king’; cf. Śrī-caraṇa, etc.; also Tamil Śrīpādaṅgal (SITI), an exalted personage; used as an expression of respect.<BR> Cf. Tamil śrīpadatāṅgikal̤ (SITI), vehicle-bearers attached to a temple, as supporting the feet of the god.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपश्चिममन्दिर
śrī-paścima-mandira, cf. Tamil tiru-mer̤-koyil (SITI), sacred temple in the west; a Viṣṇu temple which is situated to the west of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपट्ट
śrī-paṭṭa (EI 15), royal charter or seal.<BR> (EI 2), diadem bestowed [upon a favourite] by the king. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-320" target="_blank">Page-320+ 39</a>]<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 344), same as rāja-paṭṭa or paṭṭī (EI 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=319" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपट्टिका
śrī-paṭṭikā, cf. Tamil tiru-ppaṭṭigai (SITI), girdle worn by the image of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीफल|श्रीफलः
śrīphala (EI 9), the bilva fruit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीपृथिवीवल्लभ
Śrī-pṛthivī-vallabha (IE 8-2), literally, ‘the husband of [the goddesses] Śrī and Pṛthivī (i. e. the god Viṣṇu)’; title assumed by some kings of the Deccan probably claiming to be incarnations of the god Viṣṇu; often abbreviated as Śrīvallabha or Vallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीराम|श्रीरामः
Śrī-Rāma (ASLV), sign manual of some kings of Vijayanagara who often wrote Śrī-Virūpākṣa for the purpose.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीरङ्ग|श्रीरंग|श्रीरङ्गः
śrī-raṅga, cf. Tamil tiru-araṅgu (SITI), same as raṅga-maṇḍapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीरुद्र
Śrī-rudra (SITI; ASLV), also called^1 Śrī-rudra-māheśvara; a Śaiva devotee; same as Śrī-māheśvara.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीसामन्त
Śrīsāmanta (EI 21, 26), sometimes a personal name (e. g. Sandhivigrahin Śrīsāmanta who was the writer of a royal charter) and sometimes a designation (as in Kaṃsāra-kulapu-traka-śreṣṭhin Śrīsāmanta-Svayambhū who was the engraver of the same charter). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 240.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीश्रीकरणादिसमस्तमुद्राव्यापार
śrīśrīkaraṇ-ādi-samasta-mudrā-vyāpāra, cf. mudrā-vyāpāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवल्लभ|श्रीवल्लभः
Śrīvallabha (IE 8-2), cf. Śrī-pṛthivī-vallabha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवत्स|श्रीवत्सः
śrīvatsa (SII 2), mole on Viṣṇu's chest; sometimes represented in the shape of a crown as found in the Hathingumpha inscription of Khāravela.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीविजय
śrī-vijaya, cf. śrī-vijaya-Nandivarman, śrī-vijaya-Veṅgīpura, etc. See The Successors of the Sātavāhanas, p. 63. Cf. śrī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीविजयशिव
śrī-vijaya-śiva, honorific prefixed to the names of a few South Indian kings; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 152, text line 4; The Successors of the Sātavāhanas, p. 63. Cf. śrī, vijaya-śiva, śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीविमान
śrī-vimāna (SII 2, 13), same as vimāna; central shrine in the temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवीरूपाक्ष
Śrī-Vīrūpākṣa (ASLV), sign manual of the Vijayanagara kings, Virūpākṣa being their tutelary deity. Cf. Śrī-Rāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीवीथिनायक
Śrī-vīthi-nāyaka, cf. Tamil Tiru-vidi-nāyakar (SITI), a metallic image of the deity for being taken in procession along the streets round the temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शृङ्ग|शृंग|शृंगं|शृङ्गं|शृङ्गः
śṛṅga (EI 14), mentioned in relation to a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=320" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शृङ्गारभोग
śṛṅgāra-bhoga (EI 5), same as raṅga-bhoga (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रोतक
śrotaka (IE 8-5; EI 32), a kind of rent; cf. śrotra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रोत्र|श्रोत्रं
śrotra (IE 8-5; EI 32), probably, a tax in kind collected from farmers by a lessee of State lands; same as Marāṭhī śilotara, śilotarī or śilotrī; cf. śrotaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रोत्रिय|श्रोत्रियः
śrotriya (SITI), land or a village granted to a Śrotriya or Brāhmaṇa learned in the Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रुतदेवता
śruta-devatā (EI 2), the goddess of eloquence.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रुति|श्रुतिः
śruti (SII 1), a Vedic text.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रुतिमान्
Śrutimān (SITI), elders of a community looking after its affairs; perhaps adapted from Tamil Kel̤vi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्र्याज्ञा
śry-ājñā, cf. Tamil śrīy-ājñai (SITI), royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्र्यमृत
śry-amṛta, cf. Tamil tiruv-amudu (SITI), food offering (mainly, rice) to a deity in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्तम्भ|स्तंभ|स्तंभः|स्तम्भः
stambha (BL), a tower.<BR> (LL), a pillar. Cf. skambha.<BR> (IE 8-6; EI 3), same as Kannaḍa kamma, kamba, kambha; a land measure equal to one-hundredth of a mattaru or nivartana.<BR> (SITI), lamp-stand or lamp-post.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्था
sthā, cf. paratra sthāpayitvā (LP), ‘by laying it out at interest’; yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāpanaṃ sthāpayitvā, ‘besides raising the pillar’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 136). See sthāpayitvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थल्
sthal̤ (IA 15), a standard for measuring gardens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थल|स्थलं
sthala (IE 8-4), shortened form of deva-sthala; sometimes suffixed to names of localities; also the subdivision of a district.<BR> (IE 8-4; EI 12, 18, 24; ASLV), a small territorial unit like a Parganā; a district or its subdivision. Cf. Kona-sthala (EI 32), also called a deśa, maṇḍala, rāṣṭra, sīma, etc.<BR> (CITD), a place, habitation; a holy place; a district.<BR> Cf. sa-jala-sthala (IE 8-5); the land [of a village].<BR> Cf. Tamil sthala-kkāval (SITI), village watch.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलदुर्ग
sthala-durga (ASLV), fort built on the plains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलगौड
Sthala-gauḍa (ASLV), officer associated with the administration of the unit called sthala; cf. Sthala-karṇam, Gauḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थालक|स्थालकः
sthālaka (EI 19), explained as ‘a back-bone.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलकरण
Sthala-karaṇa, cf. Sthala-karṇam (q. v.)., a village official (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 261).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलकर्णम्
Sthala-karṇam (ASLV), an accountant-clerk associated with the administration of the unit called sthala. Cf. Sthala-karaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=321" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलपथकरण
[sthala]-patha-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of roadways.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलपुराण
sthala-purāṇa (IA 30), a eulogistic work on a holy place, river, etc. Cf. māhātmya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थलवृत्ति
sthala-vṛtti (EI 13), explained as ‘a tenure in which payment of tax was made in kind from the produce’; cf. tala-vṛtti (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 273).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थली
sthalī (IE 8-4), shortened form of deva-sthalī; sometimes suffixed to names of localities; also the subdivision of a district (EI 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थाम्य
Sthāmya (EI 24), wrong reading of Sthāyin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थान|स्थानं
sthāna (EI 8), residence.<BR> (IE 8-4; SITI), literally, ‘a place’; abbreviation of deva-sthāna or a temple; sometimes suffixed to names of localities. Cf. bhagavato … sthāne (Lüders, Mathurā Ins., p. 62, text lines 2-3).<BR> (LL), also sthānaka, a temple; cf. Sthānika, Sthānattār.<BR> (SII 1), a shrine; cf. mahāsthāna, a great temple.<BR> (IA 3), a Bhūta temple.<BR> Cf. tāna-mānam (SITI), dignity or honour attached to a status or office.<BR> Cf. siṃha-sthāna (LL), same as siṃh-āsana.<BR> (SII 11-1), cf. Kannaḍa thāna; name of a geographical unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थान|स्थानं
Sthāna (CII 4), a superintendent cf. Sthānapāla, etc.<BR> (EI 9), cf. ‘officer in charge of the sthānas.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानभूमि
sthāna-bhūmi (EI 24), land belonging to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाचार्य
Sthān-ācārya (EI 5, 6, 16, 28), priest of a temple; the chief priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानदान
sthāna-dāna (LP), allowing one to stand somewhere, i. e. allotting some land to one.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिकार|स्थानाधिकारः
sthān-ādhikāra (IA 18), office of the superintendent of a shrine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिकरणिक
Sthān-ādhikaraṇika (EI 3, 6, 24), officer in the administration of an outpost; see Sthān-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिकृत
Sthān-ādhikṛta (IE 8-3; EI 24), modern Thānādār; officer in charge of a police or military outpost; cf. Gaulmika. See Sthān-ādhipati, Sthānapāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानाधिपति
Sthān-ādhipati (CITD), same as Sthān-ādhyakṣa, Sthānapati, etc.; a local governor; superintendent of a place; a watchman; [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-323" target="_blank">Page-323+ 39</a>] a police officer; often also called Sthānika-dharma-kartṛ. (EI 24), officer in charge of an outpost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=322" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानक|स्थानकं
sthānaka (LL), same as sthāna, a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानकरण
sthāna-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the public works department’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानलक
Sthānalaka (CII 4), a local officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानमहाजन
Sthāna-mahājana (EI 31), same as Tamil Sthānattār (Sanskrit Sthānastha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानमान्य
sthāna-mānya (CITD), probably, land granted by the ruler to his officers for their maintenance in lieu of salary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानान्तरिक
Sthānāntarika (IE 8-3; EI 23, 28, 29), probably, superintendent of encampment or transfer of the king's residence from one camp to another.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानपाल|स्थानपालः
Sthānapāla (EI 15; HD), officer in charge of a police outpost. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 149.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानपति
Sthānapati (IE 18), a civil agent kept by the Nāyakas at the imperial court at Vijayanagara.<BR> (EI 18, 28), officer in charge of an outpost.<BR> (IA 18), designation associated with a religious office; cf. Sthān-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानत्तार्
Sthānattār (SITI; ASLV), Sanskrit Sthānastha; managers of a temple; the temple executive.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थानिक|स्थानिकः
Sthānika (IA 12; ASLV), superintendent or manager of a temple; cf. Tamil Tānigar (SITI), temple executive; also Tānika-rāyar, director of the temple ceremonies.<BR> (EI 8), title of priests in Jain temples.<BR> (EI 28), an officer belonging to an outpost probably serving under the Sthānapati, or the same as the Sthānapati.<BR> (HD), an officer in charge of a ward of a city or a district. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, pp. 143 and 149.<BR> (HRS), according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) officer in charge of one-fourth of the kingdom; (2) officer in charge of one-fourth of a city.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थापनाचार्य
Sthāpan-ācārya (HA), same as Thavaṇī (q. v.). Cf. Sthān-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थपति|स्थपतिः
Sthapati (EI 4; BL; HD), a mason or architect. See Viṣṇudharmottara, II. 24. 39.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थपतिसम्राज्
Sthapati-samrāj (CII 3; HD), ‘the chief of architects’; the chief architect. See CII, Vol. III, p. 119.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=323" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थापयित्वा
sthāpayitvā, cf. Prakrit ṭhapaīchaṃ (CII 2-1), literally, ‘having kept’; relly, ‘besides’, ‘in addition to … ’; cf. yaṣṭi-pratiṭhanaṃ ṭhapaīchaṃ (Sanskrit yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāpanaṃ sthāpayit-vā), ‘in addition to the erection of the memorial pillar’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थावर|स्थावरं|स्थावरः
sthāvara, cf. sa-sthāvara-jaṅgama (IE 8-5); the immovable belongings of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविर|स्थविरं|स्थविरः
Sthavira (CII 3, etc.), a Buddhist priestly title; same as Pāli Thera; an Elder in the community of Buddhist monks; a senior monk. Cf. Thaira (EI 3), an Elder among Buddhist monks; also Saṅgha-sthavira (Lüders, Mathurā Ins., p. 190), ‘the senior of the order’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविरकल्पिन्
Sthavira-kalpin (HA), a Jain Sādhu whose practices are not so rigorous as that of a Jina-kalpin and are easier to practise.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविरी
Sthavirī (LL), Buddhist; a senior nun; Pāli Therī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थविरीय
Sthavirīya, cf. Prakrit Therīya (EI 33), community of the Buddhist monks called Sthaviravādin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थायिन्
Sthāyin (wrongly read as Sthāmin in Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 145, text line 2), possibly, the permanent tenants of a village. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 234. Cf. Āsthāyika-puruṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थिरा
sthirā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 181), a permanent endowment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थिरशिबिर
sthira-śibira (IA 12), same as Kannaḍa nele-vīḍu; ‘a standing camp’; capital; cf. jaya-skandhāvāra of the Pāla inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थित|स्थितः
sthita (CII 1), same as upasthita, present.<BR> (BEFEO, Vol. XLIII, p. 6, text lien 15), same as pratiṣṭhita, installed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितक
sthitaka (EI 11), perpetual grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थिति|स्थितिः
sthiti (EI 32), decree.<BR> (IE 8-5), regulation; see ācāra-sthiti.<BR> (EI 12), usage; practice [in respect of calculation of dates]; Mālava-gaṇa-sthiti-vāśāt=kāla-jñānāya likhiteṣu, ‘[in the years … ] written for the knowledge of time (i. e. the date of some event) according to the practice [of calculation] of the Mālava republic’; Mālavānāṃ gaṇa-sthityā yāte śata-catuṣ-ṭaye, ‘four hundred years … having elapsed according to the practice [of calculation] of the Mālavas.”<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिपात्र
sthiti-pātra (IE 8-5), same as ācāra-sthiti-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169); a document containing regulations; see sthiti-vyavasthā, etc. Pātra seems to be used for patra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिपत्रक
sthiti-patraka (EI 32), a record of decision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=324" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिपात्रव्यवस्था
sthitipātra-vyavasthā (IE 8-5), same as sthiti-pātra or ācāra-sthithi-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थितिव्यवस्था
sthiti-vyavasthā (IE 8-5), same as sthiti-pātra or ācāra-sthiti-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 169).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्थूणा
sthūṇā (ML), a pilaster.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्रतेग
Stratega (IE 8-2, 8-3), Greek Strategos (q. v.), commander of forces.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्रतेगोस्
Strategos (IE 8-2, 8-3), Greek; commander of forces, transliterated as Stratega (q. v.) in Indian records; a feudatory or gubernatorial title.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्रीधन|स्त्रीधनं
strī-dhana (SITI; ASLV), dowry.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्र्यध्यक्ष|स्त्र्यध्यक्षः
Stry-adhyakṣa (IE 8-3; CII 1), superintendent of matters concerning the ladies of the royal household; cf. Antaḥpur-ādhyakṣa, Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्त्र्यध्यक्षमहामात्र
Stryadhyakṣa-mahāmātra (HD), Prakrit Ithijhakha-mahā-māta, etc.; superintendent of the harem. See CII, Vol. I, p. 20.<BR> Cf. Antaḥpura-mahāmātra in the Masulipatam plates of Amma II (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIV, p. 276).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्तूप|स्तूपः
stūpa (CII 3; BL; LL), technical name of a type of Buddhist monument; a Buddhist structure enshrining relics. Sometimes the term ratna-gṛha (i. e. the house enshrining the three ratnas or the best amongst the three) seems to be used to denote a stūpa.<BR> (EI 2), a Jain religious establishment.<BR> (SITI), pinnacle of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्तुपी
stupī, same as vimāna (IA 9), q. v.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शु
śu (IE 8-1; CII 3; LP), abbreviation of śukla-pakṣa or śuddha-pakṣa or the bright fortnight; a day of the bright half of the month; used in connection with di (e. g. śu-di), but sometimes by itself; often written as su. Cf. ba-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सु
su, cf. śu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुभाषित|सुभाषितः
subhāṣita (CII 4), a pithy saying in a stanza.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुभ्र|शुभ्रं|शुभ्रः
śubhra (IA 17), used to indicate the bright fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूचि|सूचिः
sūci (LL), sūcī (EI 15), a rail bar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुदि
śu-di (IE 8-1), abbreviation of śukla (or śuddha)-pakṣa-dina (or divasa), often written as su-di. See śu-ti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुदि
su-di (IE 8-1), mistake for śu-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुद्धावास
śuddh-āvāsa (IA 10), Buddhist; ‘pure abode’ being five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुधाकर्मन्
sudhā-karman (EI 23), white-washing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=325" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुधांशु|सुधांशुः
sudhāṃśu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुदिवसा
su-divasā (IA 18; CII 1), an auspicious day.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुकनास|शुकनासः
śuka-nāsa, cf. śukanāsi (Arch. Rev., 1960-61, Section III) literally, ‘a parrot's nose’ explained as ‘a gargoyle or the water spout in a building’ (Acharya, Ind. Arch., p. 169) and ‘a vestibule’ (R. Narasiṃhachar, The Keśava Temple of Somanāthapur, p. 3); but also as ‘the projection of the main body of the śikhara of a temple originally at the frontside’ (Kramrisch, Hindu Temple, p. 241); also called śuk-āṅghri. The Dīpārṇava (ed. Prabhāśaṅkar O. Sompurā, p. 116) has the following stanzas on the subject: agre kolī kapolas = tu śuka-nāsas = tu nāsikā | sāndhāre stambha-rekhā ca kartavyā madhya-koṣṭhake || prāsādasya puro-bhāge nirvāṇa-mūla-śṛṅgakam | tad-agre śuka-nāśaṃ ca ek-ādi saptam = udgamam || tasy = opari siṃhaḥ sthāpyo maṇḍapa-kalaśa-samaḥ | dvi-stambhaḥ śuka-nās-āgre vijñeyaḥ pāda-maṇḍapaḥ ||<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकरकवि
Sukara-kavi (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 231, note 1), epithet of a poet; cf. Āśu-kavi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखा
sukhā (IA 26), same as su-di 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखडि
sukhaḍi, sukhaḍī (LP), Gujarātī; also spelt suṣaḍī; a kind of sweetmeat; a reward.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखन
sukhana, sukhanā (CII 1), ‘causing happiness’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखासन
sukh-āsana (Ind. Ant., Vol. IX, p. 95), translated as ‘a palanquin’; enumerated as one of the five prasādas granted by a king to a subordinate. Cf. pañcāṅga-prasāda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुखसङ्कथाविनोद
sukha-saṅkathā-vinoda (IA 8), ‘the delight of pleasing conversation’; cf. ‘while he was ruling, with the delight of pleasing conversation, at the capital of Kalyāṇa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुक्रनेत्र
śukra-netra (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकृत|सुकृतं
sukṛta (CII 1), a good deed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुक्ति|शुक्तिः
śukti, same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूल|शूलं|शूलः
śūla (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’; cf. triśūla, a trident.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुलपाल
Śulapāla (EI 11), probably, an associate of the courtesans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुलतान
Sulatāna (BL), Indian modification of a title of the Muhammadan kings; same as Arabic Sult̤ān. Cf. Sulitāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूलवरि
śūlavari (EI 25), Tamil; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूलिन्
śūlin (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुलितान
Sulitāna (BL), Indian modification of a title of the Muhammadan kings; same as Arabic Sult̤ān. Cf. Sulatāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=326" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्क|शुल्कं|शुल्कः
śulka (IE 8-5; EI 12, 23, 25, 30; CII 4; CITD), tolls; customs duties; octroi duties; taxes particularly levied at ferries and passes and on roads, etc.; cf. krīḍara-śulka (EI 5), name of a tax; also śuṅgam, śuṅkam (SITI), customs, tolls.<BR> (HRS), tax, probably identical with bali according to early authorities; ferry dues, tolls and transit duties according to the Smṛtis and lexicons; according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) duties levied upon articles imported into a city, (2) port-dues, (3) duty upon the sale of liquors, (4) customs collected by the ferrymen and boundary-officers, (5) duty upon mining products, (6) duty upon imported salt, and (7) duty upon animals intended for slaughter; according to Śukra, tolls and duties upon building-sites, etc. The Amarakoṣa explains śulka as ghaṭṭ-ādi-deya and Kṣīrasvāmin enumerates the dues as ferry duties, tolls paid at military stations or police outposts and transit duties paid by merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्काधिकार
śulk-ādhikāra, cf. suṅk-ādhikāra (EI 5), ‘office for the collection of tolls [of the Banavāsi District]’. Same as Śulk-ā-dhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कग्राह
Śulkagrāha (HD), an official who collected tolls or customs duties. See Śukra, II. 128.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कमण्डपिका
śulka-maṇḍapikā (EI 3, 9), customs house. See śulka-śālā.<BR> (CII 4), explained by some as ‘a market-pavilion’.<BR> (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI, p. 329 and note 31), translated as ‘the rent office’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कशाला
śulka-śālā, cf. śuṅga-śālai (SITI), place where tolls are collected; a customs house. See śulka-maṇḍapikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कातियात्रिक
śulk-ātiyātrika (IE 8-8; EI 30), boundary-crossing fee; exit tax; cf. atiyātrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुमन्त्र|सुमन्त्रः
Sumantra (HD), king's counsellor on matters relating to income and expenditure. See Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 114, note 150.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूना
sūnā (HRS), royal dues collected by the superintendent of the slaughter-house, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुण्डक
suṇḍaka (IA 19), meaning doubtful; probably, a bundle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्क
suṅka (EI 12), a corrupt form of śulka often found in South Indian inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्कपन्नायदधिष्ठायक
Suṅkapannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa-Sanskrit; superintendent of the income from tolls. See Suṅka-věrgaḍě.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्कवेर्गडे
Suṅka-věrgaḍě (EI 19), Kannaḍa; official designation; Sanskrit Śulk-ādhyakṣa. See Suṅkapannāyadadhiṣṭhāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=327" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शून्य|शून्यं|शून्यः
śūnya (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शून्यग्राम
śūnya-grāma, cf. ‘she made a further grant of five śūnya-grāmas’ (Arch. Rev.,) 1960-61, Section III, No. 44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुण्यारा
Suṇyārā, Sunyārā (Chamba), a goldsmith; from Sanskrit Suvarṇakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूपकारपति
Sūpakārapati (EI 13; HD), the chief cook. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, pp. 109, 115. Cf. Bhānasa-věrgaḍě, Mahānas-ādhyakṣa, Ma(Mā)hānasika, Khādya(kū*)ḷapākika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुपर्ण|सुपर्णः
Suparṇa (EI 2), a class of demi-gods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुप्रभात|सुप्रभातं
suprabhāta (IA 12), name of the morning worship at the Rāmeśvara temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुप्रदार्य
supradārya (CII 1), ‘easy to enter’, ‘easy to do’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुर|सुरः
sura (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरभि|सुरभिः
surabhi, see surahī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरही
surahī (HA), Sanskrit surabhi; inscribed stone with the representation of a cow with her calf and the sun and the moon in the upper part, the inscriptions usually recording gifts or donations or exemptions from obligations or taxes declared by kings. This indicated permanence and inviolability^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुराकरण
surā-karaṇa (EI 30), distillation of liquor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरताण
Suratāṇa (IE 8-2; EI 12), same as Arabic Sult̤ān; see Suratrāṇa, Sulatāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरत्राण
Suratrāṇa (IE 8-2; EI 4, 1, 13, 32; BL), variously spelt as Suritrāṇa, Suratāṇa, etc.; Hindu adaptation of the Muslim royal title Sult̤ān; often adopted as a personal name. Cf. Hammīra. See Sulatāna, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरवाल
Suravāla (EI 33), one who sets songs or musical instruments to tune.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूरि|सूरिः
Sūri (EI 9), title of Jain religious teachers; often used as their name-ending.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरित्राण
Suritrāṇa (BL), same as Suratrāṇa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्य|सूर्यः|सूर्य्य|सूर्य्यः
sūrya (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्यभ
sūrya-bha (JAHRS, Vol. II, p. 287, text line 64), literally, ‘the sun's asterism’, the Hastā-nakṣatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्यग्रह|सूर्यग्रहः|सूर्य्यग्रह|सूर्य्यग्रहः
sūrya-graha (EI 24), solar eclipse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूर्यपर्वन्|सूर्य्यपर्वन्
sūrya-parvan (IA 19; LP), solar eclipse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुश्रूषा
śuśrūṣā (CII 1), obedience; cf. dharma-śuśrūṣāṃ śuśrūṣatu, ‘one should practise obedience to morality.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुत|सुतः
suta (IE 7-1-2), confused with Pāṇḍu-suta and used to indicate ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=328" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत|सूतः
Sūta, one of the king's high functionaries (ratna or ratnin); cf. Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 111.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुतचेला
Suta-celā (BL), a pupil or disciple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुति
śu-ti (IE 8-1), contraction of śukla (or śuddha)-pakṣa-tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्र|सूत्रं
sūtra (IA 20), a manual of religious rituals, etc.<BR> (HRS), royal receipts collected by the superintendent of weaving, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR> (IE 3-1), same as śarayantraka; the string holding the leaves of a manuscript together (Vāsavadatta, Hall's ed., p. 250).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्र|सूत्रं
Sūtra (PJS), abbreviation of Sūtradhāra, a mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रभृत्
Sūtrabhṛt (EI 33), same as Sūtradhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधार|सूत्रधारः
Sūtradhāra (EI 24; CII 4; BL), a mason; an artisan; an epithet generally applied to the engravers of stone inscriptions of the medieval period. See Sūtrabhṛt, Sūtradhṛt, Sūtradhārin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधारपितामह
Sūtradhāra-pitāmaha, cf. pitāmaha (IA 19); ‘the very Brahman among the masons’; title of a mason.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधारिन्
Sūtradhārin (EI 15), same as Sūtradhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रधृत्
Sūtradhṛt (EI 31), same as Sūtradhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रान्तिक
Sūtrāntika (LL), a Buddhist monk versed in the sūtra works. See Sūtrāntikinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सूत्रान्तिकिनी
Sūtrāntikinī (LL), a Buddhist nun versed in the sūtra works. See Sūtrāntika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुत्तेए
suttee (CII 3, etc.), see satī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्ण|सुवर्णं|सुवर्णः|सुवर्ण्ण
suvarṇa (IE 8-8; EI 28; CII 3), name of a gold coin and also of a weight of gold; equal to 16 māṣas or 80 ratis; also called akṣa, picu, pāṇi, kroḍa, binduka, viḍālapadaka, haṃsapada, grāsagraha and tola. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46.<BR> (SII 13), same as Tamil kal̤añju.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णदण्ड
suvarṇa-daṇḍa (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28), tax on goldsmiths; same as Tamil taṭṭar pāṭṭam, etc., noticed in Appendix II.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णादाय
suvarṇ-ādāya (CITD), same as suvarṇ-āya. Cf. hiraṇya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णाध्यक्ष
Suvarṇ-ādhyakṣa (EI 24), official designation; probably the same as Suvarṇavthy-adhikṛta (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णकार|सुवर्णकारः
Suvarṇakāra (EI 24, BL), a goldsmith; often the epithet of the engravers of copper-plate grants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णवीथ्यधिक्त
Suvarṇavīthy-adhikṛta (EI 18), superintendent of the goldsmith's business. Suvaṇa-vīthī literally means ‘the quarters of the goldsmiths’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=329" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णाय
suvarṇ-āya (also called suvarṇ-ādāya); land revenue paid in cash. Cf. hiraṇya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुवास्तियम्
śuvāstiyam (SITI), Tamil; right of hereditary enjoyment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वभ्र|श्वभ्रं
śvabhra, cf. sa-vana-śvabhra-nidhāna; a pit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वदेशिन्
Svadeśin (CITD), often used with the word Para-deśin or Nānādeśin with reference to the two main communities of traders and merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वहस्त|स्वहस्तः
sva-hasta (EI 23; CII 3; IA 8), signature or sign-manual.<BR> Cf. sva-hast-ākṣarāṇi (LP), a receipt.<BR> (Ind. Ep., p. 187, verse 77), used to indicate a grant of land because the donor's signature was required to be put on a deed of grant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वःश्वः|श्वःश्व
śvaḥ-śvaḥ (CII 1), daily; same as ahar-ahaḥ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वल्प|स्वल्पः
svalpa (EI 24), small; sometimes prefixed to the name of a locality (e. g. Svalpa-Vallūra), etc., to distinguish it from others of the same name but styled ‘big’ or ‘medium’. Cf. Kṣudra-Dharmagiri and Mahā-Dharmagiri; Vaḍa-Hosa and Maṃjhi-Hosa (EI 35).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वामिन्
Svāmin (IE 8-3; EI 24; CII 3; LL), royal title probably of foreign origin, assumed by the kings of Śaka-Kuṣāṇa extraction; adopted by indigenous rulers like the Śātavāhanas.<BR> Cf. Śāmi (SITI), the king.<BR> Cf. Vihāra-svāmin (founder or master of a monastery), etc.<BR> (EI 7), same as Svāmi-Mahāsena, i. e. Kārttikeya.<BR> (EI 23), designation of the member of a guild.<BR> (EI 5), cf. ‘the 500 Svāmins of Aiholě’; probably meaning the Māheśvaras.<BR> Cf. svāmi-vāram (SITI), land-lord's share; same as Tamil mel-vāram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वामिभोग
svāmi-bhoga (EI 8; SII 3), ‘the master's share’; the landlord's share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वामिनी
Svāminī (CII 3), a noble lady or mistress. Cf. also Vihāra-svāminī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वमुखाज्ञा
sva-mukh-ājñā (CII 3), ‘the order or command from one's own mouth’; used with reference to the king's verbal order for the preparation and issue of charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वाम्य|स्वाम्यं
svāmya (SITI), ownership; right to property; cf. ubhaya-svāmya (EI 5), tejaḥ-svāmya; also mameya-svāmya (SII 11-1), tenure held by a Manneya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर|स्वरः
svara (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=330" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वरत्राण
Svaratrāṇa (BL), same as Suratrāṇa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्ग|स्वर्गः
svarga (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyone’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्ण|स्वर्णं
svarṇa, cf. śoṇa-vari (SITI), svarṇa-vari, explained as ‘tax payable in gold'; same as Tamil pŏn-vari; but cf. also suvarṇa-daṇḍa, profession-tax payable by the goldsmiths.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णभाण्डारिन्
Svarṇa-bhāṇḍārin, cf. Pon̤-paṇḍārigal (EI 33), members of the administrative council of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णादाय
svarṇ-ādāya (SII 1; SITI), ‘revenue in gold’; taxes payable in coin. Cf. hiraṇya, suvarṇ-ādāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णदण्ड
svarṇa-daṇḍa, see suvarṇa-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णकार|स्वर्णकारः
Svarṇakāra (EI 24), a goldsmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णक्ष्मा
svarṇa-kṣmā (EI 16), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णमेरु
svarṇa-meru (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वरूप|स्वरूपं|स्वरूपः
svarūpa (SITI), an estate of the Nambūdris, royal personages, etc., of Malai-nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसमय
sva-samaya (EI 24), explained as a Jain doctrine; the doctrines of one's own religion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्ति
svasti (CII 3, 4), welfare; auspicious word used at the beginning of some inscriptions to ensure success of the undertaking; an exclamation used at the commencement of inscriptions. Sometimes used as a neuter noun, with astu in the maṅgala at the end of documents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्तिकपट्ट
svastika-paṭṭa (LL), slab with the representation of a svastika symbol.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्त्ययन
svastyayana (EI 31), rite for averting evil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वतल
sva-tala (EI 11), surface of the ground [of the gift land].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वतन्त्र|स्वतंत्र|स्वतन्त्रः
svatantra (SITI), a share; a customary fee; emoluments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वयंवर|स्वयंवरः
svayaṃvara (EI 8), the bride's selection of her husband.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतच्छत्र
śveta-cchatra (EI 29), ‘the white umbrella’; one of the royal insignia; same as śvet-ātapatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतगरुत्
śveta-garut (SII 2), swan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेताम्बर|श्वेतांबर|श्वेताम्बरः
śvetāmbara (IA 7), a Jain sect; same as Śvetapaṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतपट
Śvetapaṭa (IA 7), same as Śvetāmbara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्वेतातपत्र
śvet-ātapatra (EI 29), ‘the white umbrella’, one of the royal insignia; same as śveta-cchatra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वोलिकापात
svolikā-pāta, svolī-pāta (EI 1), meaning doubtful. Svo = kho ?<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्याद्वाद|स्याद्वादः
syādvāda (EI 3; SII 1), Jain; also called syādvāda-mata, syādvāda-vidyā; scepticism.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्यारमल्लिक
Syāramallika (EI 33), probably Persian Sair Malik (i. e. Malik-us-Sair), collector or taxes, Sair meaning ‘tax’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=331" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तबु
tabu (IA 20, 29), a taboo.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तदानियुक्तक
Tad-āniyuktaka (IE 8-3; EI 23), official designation; same as Tad-āyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तदात्व|तदात्वं
tadātva (CII 1), the present time; the time being.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तदायुक्तक
Tad-āyuktaka (IE 8-3; EI 6, 23), an officer who was a subordinate to the Āyuktaka; mentioned along with Viniyuktaka; cf. Tad-āniyuktaka, Tan-niyuktaka, Tad-viniyuktaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तादायुक्तक
Tādāyuktaka (EI 15), same as Tad-āyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तद्भव
tad-bhava (IA 7), a word in Prakrit or the regional languages, which is modified from a Sanskrit word.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तद्विनियुक्तक
Tad-viniyuktaka (IE 8-3), same as Tad-āyuktaka or Tan-niyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तगरपति
Tagarapati (EI 13), mistake for Nagarapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैल|तैलं
taila, oils; a branch of revenue according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 90.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलाभ्यङ्ग|तैलाभ्यंग|तैलाभ्यङ्गः
tail-ābhyaṅga (IA 22), cf. abhyaṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलघाणक
taila-ghāṇaka (EI 19), oil mill.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलपर्णिका
taila-parṇikā (EI 24), explained as ‘leaves producing oil’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैलिकराज
Tailika-rāja (EI 23), ‘chief of a guild of oilmen’; designation of the chairman of the oilmen's guild.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तैर्थिक|तैर्थिकः
Tairthika (EI 32), same as Tīrthika, a priest [of the non-Buddhists].<BR> (IE 8-3), cf. Tūthika (EI 1; LL), ferry-officer or officer in charge of the places of pilgrimage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताजिक|ताजिकः
Tājika, Tajjika (EI 23, 32), Tājiya, Tāyika; an Arab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाका
ṭākā, Bengali form of ṭaṅka, meaning a silver coin (rupee) and also money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठाकोर्खाना
ṭhākorkhānā (HA), same as balānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तक्षाचार्य
takṣ-ācārya, cf. Tamil tacc-ācāriyam (SITI), the status of the master carpenter; chief of the carpenters. Cf. tacc-ācāriya-kkāṇi, the right of officiating as the chief carpenter, as also the stone-mason of a temple; the land set apart for the enjoyment of the holder of that office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तक्षन्
takṣan (IE 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तल|तलं|तलः
tala, cf. sa-tala (IE 8-5); surface of the ground.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताल|तालं|तालः
tāla (IE 8-5), a palmyra palm; cf. sa-tālaka as an epithet of a gift village referring to the right of enjoying the trees by privileged tenants in some areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=332" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताल|तालं|तालः
tāla (SII 2), Tamil; a dish.<BR> (EI 21; SITI), Tamil; the treasury<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभेद्या
tala-bhedyā (IA 18), word of uncertain implication; mentioned with ghāṇaka, mallaka, vundhaka etc. (IA 18); cf. talabhedyā-ghāṇaka-mallaka-vundhaka-daṇḍadoṣa-prāpt-ādāya (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 83, text lines 19-20), epithet of gift village. See tala-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभोग
tala-bhoga (IA 7; SII 11-1), explained as ‘the enjoyment of sites of land’; really, ‘land granted for the maintenance of a temple at the time of its consecration’; same as tala-vāṭaka, tala-vṛtti, and probably also tala-bhedyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालध्वज|तालध्वजः
Tāladhvaja (BL), official designation of the governor of a territory; same as Gujarātī Tāl̤ājā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैवन्
Talaivan̤ (SII 1), Tamil; a chief.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैयारि
Talaiyāri (SII 1), Tamil; same as Kannaḍa Talāri; a watchman. See Talavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलक|तलकं|तलकः
talaka (LP), ‘on the spot’.<BR> (EI 23), a territorial division.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलाक
tal̤āka (EI 14), same as taṭāka, taḍāga; a tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलपद
tala-pada (HRS), known from Caulukya records; lands fully assessed for revenue, as distinguished from estates which were held on condition of service or for a reduced lump assessment; explained as Gujarātī talpat, ‘land paying rent to the government’ (IA 11).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलपाट
tala-pāṭa (SITI), Tamil; an army; armaments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालपत्र|तालपत्रं
tāla-patra, Tamil olai (SITI); literally, ‘palmyra-leaf’; an order from the king or a person in authority. Cf. olai-ccāda-nam, ‘a document written on palm-leaf’; olai-ccampaḍam, ‘wages paid to the messenger who brings the olai to meet his expenses on the way’; also written as olai-ccambal̤am, olai-ccammāḍam, etc.; same as nirūpa-ccambaḍam; cf. olai-nāyaka, ‘the chief secretary or the senior officer looking after correspondence.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालपट्ट
tāla-paṭṭa (IA 15), probably the same as tāla-patra, meaning ‘an ear-ornament’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलप्रहारिन्
Talaprahārin (EI 6), official designation; probably the same as Talārī or Kotwāl.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलार
Talāra (IE 8-2; EI 22; LP; BL; HD), administrator of a city or prefect of the city police; same as Talavara, Talārī or Kotwāl. Talavara of early South Indian inscriptions means a Rājasthānīya (a Duke or a viceroy) according to some [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-334" target="_blank">Page-334+ 40</a>] commentators and the Kotwāl or a city magistrate according to others. A subdivision of high class Khatris of the Punjab is called Tālwār. Cf. Tala-rakṣa or Tal-ārakṣa; also called Ārakṣika and Daṇḍapāśika. See Bhandarkar's List, No. 579; IHQ, 1960, p. 266.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=333" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलाराभाव्य
talār-ābhāvya (EI 11), tax for payment to the Talāra; according to some, Talāra is the Kotwāl and bhāvya or ābhāvya is what is called saṃbhāvanā, i. e. pāghḍī, and talār-ābhāvya is the pāghḍī money given to the Kotwāl (LP).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलारी
Talārī (IE 8-2), Telugu-Kannaḍa; ‘a village watchman’; same as Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलारिक
talārika (ASLV), the office of the Talāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलारक्ष
Tal-ārakṣa (EI 22), same as Talavara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलाटी
Talāṭī (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 165, noted 38), a stipendiary (i. e. not hereditary) village accountant in the Kannaḍa-and Marāṭhī-speaking areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवर
Talavara (IE 8-2; EI 20, 28), a title of the nobility or of subordinate rulers in some cases (a Rājasthānīya according to Vinayavijaya's Subodhikā commentary on the Jain Kalpa-sūtra); but the designation of the administrator of a city or of the police officer in charge of a city, according to some sources (Hemacandra explaining Talāra as Nagara-rakṣaka); cf. Talāra, Talārī, etc.; also Mahātalavara.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 78), cf. Talavara mentioned in the list of royal officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवर्गिक
Talavargika (EI 3), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवारिका
talavārikā, cf. Kannaḍa tal̤avārikā (EI 1), the village-watchman's quit-rent; cf. Tal̤avāra or Talāri (Tamil Talaiyāri), ‘a village-watchman’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालावारिक
Tālāvārika (IA 12), official designation; same as either Talārī or Talāṭī (a stipendiary village-accountant in the Marāṭhī-and Kannaḍa-speaking areas).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवाटक
tala-vāṭaka (EI 31), same as tala-pāṭaka or tala-vṛtti. But cf. tala-vāṭaka in tala-vāṭaka-vāstunā saha kṣetram, ‘a piece of land together with suburbs, gardens and homestead land’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 349, text line 18). The meaning here may also be ‘adjoining land’ which was probably the original implication of the expression.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलावाटक
Talāvāṭaka (CII, Vol. III, p. 216; also p. 217 and note), possibly the superintendent of temple property (cf. tala-vāṭaka); [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-335" target="_blank">Page-335+ 40</a>] same as Gujarātī Talāṭī (a petty revenue officer), according to some (HD).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=334" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलवृत्ति
tala-vṛtti (EI 13, 15, 21, 33; IA 7; SII 11-1; SITI), ‘endowment of the adjoining land’; land granted for the maintenance of a temple or deity at the time of its consecration; same as tala-bhoga, tala-vāṭaka, tala-pāṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तालि|तालिः
tāli, tālī (EI 1), a measure of liquor.<BR> (SII 3), the marriage badge; cf. māṅgalya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तल्लज|तल्लजः
tallaja (SII 1), excellent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टं|ट|टः
ṭaṃ (Chamba, etc.), abbreviation of ṭaṃkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्बूलदानाधिकृत
Tāmbūladān-ādhikṛta (EI 19), officer supplying betel bīḍās to the king. Cf. Vārgulika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्बूलकवाहक
Tāmbūlaka-vāhaka (EI 28), bearer of the king's betel-box; same as Od̤iyā Vāguli. See Tāmbūladān-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्बुलिक
Tāmbūlika (EI 28), producer and seller of betel leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तम्बूरु
tambūru (ASLV), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तमिल्
Tamil, name of an alphabet and language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तम्मडि
Tammaḍi (CITD), Telugu; also called Tammal̤a, Tāṃbal̤i, Taṃbala-vāḍu and Taṃbiga; a Śaiva priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्र|ताम्रं|ताम्रः
tāmra (IE; EI 8, 23), same as tāmra-śāsana; a copper-plate grant; also land granted by means of such charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रहार
Tāmrahāra, cf. Tāmerā (EI 16), a coppersmith.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रक|ताम्रकं
tāmraka (IE; EI 1, 4), same as tāmra-paṭṭa; a copper-plate grant; also gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रपत्र|ताम्रपत्रः
tāmra-patra (EI 23), also called tāmra-paṭṭa, tāmra-paṭṭaka; same as tāmra-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रपट्ट|ताम्रपट्टं|ताम्रपट्टः
tāmra-paṭṭa (EI 19, 23, 24; CII 4; Chamba), a copper-plate charter; gift land. Cf. tāmra-patra, tāmra-paṭṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रपट्टक
tāmra-paṭṭaka (EI 4, 23), same as tāmra-paṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रफली
tāmra-phalī (EI 22), a copper plate. Cf. triphalī-tāmra-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रप्रशस्ति
tāmra-praśasti (CII 4), culogy written on copper plates; a copper-plate charter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताम्रशासन
tāmra-śāsana (IE; EI 23; CII 3), a copper-charter; a technical term for a deed of conveyance written on copper plates; also gift land. See śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तान|तानं|तानः
tāna (IE 7-1-2), ‘fortynine’; but sometimes used to indicate ‘thirtyfour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तनयप्राप्त
tanaya-prāpta (CII 3), ‘an adopted son’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताण्डव|तांडव|तांडवं|ताण्डवं|तांडवः|ताण्डवः
tāṇḍava (CII 4), name of the dance of Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=335" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डुल|तंडुल|तंडुलः|तण्डुलः
taṇḍula, unit of measurement; half of a dhānya-māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 48).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डुलपर्वत
taṇḍula-parvata (IA 9), name of a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाङ्क्
ṭāṅk (IA 26), also called tāṅkī, etc.; same as ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्क|टंक|टंकं|टंकः|टङ्कः
ṭaṅka (EI 9, 20; CII 4; ML), name of a coin; cf. Vijayarāja-ṭaṅka, ṭaṅka issued by Vijayarāja; spelt often as ṭaṅkā and in old Bengali as taṅkā; same as śāna also called dharaṇa; a coin in general; regarded as equal to 4 silver fanams; name applied to both gold and silver issues 80 ratis in weight (JNSI, Vol. XXII, pp. 197-98); silver coins of the Delhi Sult̤āns--96 or 100 ratis in weight. See JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 42-49. Cf. śāśukāni-ṭaṅka, hema-ṭaṅka, raupya-ṭṅka; also ṭaṅka (LP), a copper coin equal to half of a pice.<BR> (Chamba), a copper coin equal to (1/20) of a Rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कक|टंकक|टंककः|टङ्ककः
ṭaṅkaka (EI 19; CII 4; BL), name of a coin; a silver coin. Cf. ‘ṭaṅkakas stamped with the figure of the Bhagavat’ (Bhandarkar's List, No. 2033).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कशाला
ṭaṅka-śālā, cf. Tamil iṭaṅka-śālai (SITI), a mint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कशालाकरण
ṭaṅka-śālā-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of minting coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्मात्र|तन्मात्रं
tanmātra (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्नियुक्तक
Tan-niyuktaka (IE 8-3); an officer probably under the Āyukta; same as Tad-āyuktaka or Tad-viniyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्तलि
tantali (IE 8-5), a tamarind tree; cf. sa-tantalika, epithet of a gift village referring to the right to enjoy such trees by privileged tenants in some areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्र|तंत्र|तंत्रं|तन्त्रं
tantra (ASLV), army, government; cf. Tantrin in South Indian inscriptions.<BR> (SITI), army, mainly the infantry; cf. Tantrin in South Indian inscriptions.<BR> (CII 4), explained as ‘Home Affairs’.<BR> (LP), cf. tantre nirūpita, ‘officially sent’.<BR> (HIQ, Vol. XXXIV, p. 277), cf. Tantr-ādhikārin, ‘officer in charge of administration’, in the Bhāturiyā inscription of Rājyapāla. In this case, a person was at first a Mantrin, then a Saciva and finally a Tantr-ādhikārin.<BR> Cf. Sarva-tantr-ādhikṛta (EI 24), superintendent of all departments.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्राधिकारिन्
Tantr-ādhikārin (EI 33), also called Tantr-ādhyakṣa, Tan-trapāla, etc.; probably, officer in charge of administration. See [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-337" target="_blank">Page-337+ 40</a>] Sarvatantr-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=336" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्राधिप
Tantr-ādhipa (EI 25, 29; CII 4), same as Tantr-ādhikārin, etc.; minister for home affairs, according to some. See Sarvatantr-ādhikṛta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्राध्यक्ष
Tantr-ādhyakṣa (EI 33), same as Tantr-ādhikārin, etc. See Sarvatantr-ādhikṛta, Tantrapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रकरण
tantra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the political department’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रनायक
Tantra-nāyaka (ASLV), official designation associated with tantra meaning the army or government. See Tantr-ādhi-kārin, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रपाल
Tantrapāla (SITI), chief of the army.<BR> (IE 8-3; EI 33), probably, officer in charge of administration; cf. Mahātantr-ādhyakṣa, Sarva-tantr-ādhikṛta, Tantra-pati and Mahātantr-ādhikṛta, etc.<BR> (HD), an officer like the Chargé-d' Affaires, according to some; cf. Tantrapāla-Mahāsāmanta-Mahādaṇḍanāyaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 185; cf. Vol. V, p. 77).<BR> (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, p. 34), explained as ‘an officer of the king's bodyguard or royal retinue.’<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 77), explained as ‘a councillor.’<BR> (SII 11-2), cf. Tantrapālaradhiṣṭhāyaka; also Tantra-pāladadhiṣṭhāyaka (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रपति
Tantrapati (IE 8-3); HD), occurs in the Rājataraṅgiṇī, VIII. 2322; explained as Dharm-ādhikārin, ‘officer in charge of the department of justice and charity’; see Bṛhattantrapati. Cf. the Muslim official designations Sadrus-Sudūr, etc., explained as ‘the chief judge and officer in charge of the king's charities’ (Journ. As. Soc. Pak., Vol. IV, pp. 53-54).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रवाय|तंत्रवाय|तन्त्रवायः
Tantravāya (EI 24), a weaver. Cf. lunnavāya = a tailor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तन्त्रिन्|तंत्रिन्
Tantrin (SITI; ASLV), a soldier; a trooper; a leader of the army; a temple priest; a weaver. It has been supposed that the Tamil words Kaikkol̤ar and Aṭavi came to signify both a soldier and a weaver on the analogy of the word Tantrin used in both the senses. Cf. Tantrimār, members of the army corps; a class of persons who perform worship in temples; a priest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तनु|तनुः
tanu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’; rarely used to indicate ‘eight’.<BR> (Select Inscriptions, pp. 241, 245); one's own; see tanuvaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तनुवक
tanuvaka (CII 2-1), Prakrit; used in the sense of svakiya; see tanu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तपन|तपनः
tapana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’ with reference to Agni; but [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-338" target="_blank">Page-338+ 40</a>] ‘twelve’ with reference to ‘the sun’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=337" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तपस्विन्
tapasvin (SITI), an ascetic; a recluse; a religious mendicant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तापत्रय
tāpa-traya (SII 1), the three kinds of pain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तापित
tāpita (EI 23, 24), ‘heated’ [for affixing the seal to a copper-plate grant].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तपोधन|तपोधनः
Tapodhana (CITD), in Telugu-Kannaḍa records, often used to indicate Jain monks; in Orissan records, a Śaiva ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तार्
tār (SII 1), name of a silver coin, equal to (1/6) of a gold fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तर|तरः
tara (EI 9), same as nilaya; the family aggregate of dwellings with some of them meant for servants and artisans; also a street or a hamlet.<BR> (HRS), same as tara-deya, ferry dues, as indicated by the Arthaśāstra. See tārya.<BR> Cf. taram (EI 7), revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरदेय
tara-deya, ferry dues. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 78, 227.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरपणी
tarapaṇī (HA), a wooden water-vessel used by Jain monks.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरपति|तरपतिः
Tarapati (IE 8-3; CII 4; HD), officer in charge of the ferries; superintendent of the ferries; cf. Tarika and Tairthika; but see Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321, where Tarika and Tara-patika are separately mentioned, and Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, p. 306, text line 35 where Tarapati is likewise mentioned separately from Tarika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवर
Taravara (EI 20, 25), same as Talavara (q. v.); official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवुशात्तु
Taravu-śāttu (SITI), an officer of the Col̤̣a kings, possibly associated with taravu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक|तरिकः
Tarika (IE 8-3; HD), a ferry officer or one in charge of a ferry service. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVII, p. 321.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक|तरिकः
tarika (HRS), same as tara; ferry dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तर्क|तर्कः
tarka (IE 7-1-2; EI 25), ‘six’.<BR> (CII 4), logic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तर्कुक|तर्कुकः
Tarkuka (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 34, note 7), a supplicant; a beggar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तार्य|तार्य्य
tārya (HRS), same as tara; ferry dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत|ततं|ततः
tata (IE 7-1-2), probably confused with tattva and used to indicate ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तटाकमातृक
taṭāka-mātṛka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 98), ‘tank-nourished [land].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=338" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताताम्बा
tāt-āmbā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 261), the mother, step-mother or aunt of one's father.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताटङ्क|ताटंक|ताटंकः|ताटङ्कः
tāṭaṅka (EI 16), an ear-ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तथाज्ञातीय
tathā-jñātīya (EI 8), used for taj-jñātīya (taj-jātīya; cf. jñātīya).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत्पादपरिगृहीत
tat-pāda-parigṛhīta (IE 8-2), see parigṛhīta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत्सम
tatsama (IA 7), a Sanskrit word used in the regional languages without change or with slight change.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टार्
Taṭṭār (SII 1), goldsmith; cf. Taṭṭhakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्ठकार
Taṭṭhakāra (EI 15, 28; BL), a brazier, cf. Ṭhaṭhara, Ṭhaṭherā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तत्त्व|तत्त्वं
tattva (IE 7-1-2; EI 8), ‘twentyfive’; rarely also used to indicate ‘five.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तौण्डिक
tauṇḍika (IE 8-8), ‘biting of crops with the mouth’; cf. gavāṃ tauṇḍike.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजः|तेज
tejaḥ (EI 12), abbreviation of tejaḥ-svāmya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजःस्वाम्य
tejaḥ-svāmya (IE 8-5; EI 16), cf. aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya; tejaḥsvāmya is tejo-yukta-svāmya, ‘ownership endowed with full authority’, which resulted from the eight (i. e. all or various) kinds of enjoyment. See tejo-mānya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजस्कर|तेजस्करं
tejaskara (EI 24), polisher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजि
tejī (LP), fine.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजोलिङ्ग
tejo-liṅga (SII 2), the Śivaliṅga of light.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेजोमान्य
tejo-mānya, cf. teja-mānyam (SITI), the ownership of landed property with the aṣṭa-bhoga or eight (various or all) kinds of enjoyment; also called tejaḥ-svāmyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेलुगु
Tělugu, also spelt Těnugu, name of a language and alphabet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेलुगुकन्नड
Tělugu-Kannaḍa, also called Kannaḍa-Tělugu; name of the medieval alphabet prevalent in the Telugu-and Kannaḍa-speaking areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठ|ठः
Ṭha (IE 8-1; LP; PJS), abbreviation of Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठा
Ṭhā (PJS), contraction of Ṭhākura, a modification of Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थड
thaḍa (LP), stem or trunk of a tree; a tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठक
ṭhaka, cf. ṭhakka (IA 6); ṭhaka-purisa is explained as ‘a trader’, and associated with ṭhag, ‘a cheat’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थाकमान
thākamāna (LP), remainder; what remains to be paid up; cf. thakalelī bākī in Marāṭhī. See also apūryamāṇa-thākamāna-drammāḥ, i. e. drammas (coins) which are not completely paid off and are still to be paid.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=339" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठक्कुर|ठक्कुरः
Ṭhakkura (IE 8-3; EI 23, 30; CII 4; HD), supposed to be a title derived from a Turkish word (Tegin); occurs as a title in the Rājataraṅgiṇī, VII. 290, 706, 738; probably, a fief-holder; sometimes mentioned in the list of subordinates; generally used as a title of particular persons indicating their rank or office. The significance of the word possibly varied in different localities and ages. Its foreign origin is supported by its unpopularity in the South. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 297; Vol. XIX, p. 243.<BR> (IE 8-3), probably a fief-holder; mentioned as Pātra.<BR> (EI 9), explained as ‘the lord-in-waiting’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठक्कुराज्ञी
Ṭhakkurājñī (EI 8; CII 4; IA 16), title of the wife of a Ṭhakkura; same as Ṭhākurāṇī in some dialects.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठाक्रि
Ṭhākri (CII 4), same as Ṭhākur.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठकुर
Ṭhakura, Ṭhākura (EI 23, 33; CII 4), same as Ṭhakkura.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठाकुर
Ṭhākura (LP), Gujarātī; often a member of the Koli caste of Gujarat, who generally tries to detect thieves, etc.<BR> (LP), Gujarātī Ṭhākor, the chief among certain tribes of Rajputs; a small chieftain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठामि
ṭhāmi (LP), a kind of earthern pot.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थानापति
Thānāpati (EI 30), same as Sthānapati; officer in charge of an outpost.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थठर
Thaṭhara, Thaṭhāra (Chamba), a brazier or copper-smith; same as Taṭṭhakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

थवणी
thavaṇī (HA), a wooden stand used as a symbol for the teacher or the Tīrthaṅkara, a religious text or certain prescribed small objects being placed on it and worshipped by Jain monks; same as sthāpan-ācārya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ठेक
ṭheka (LP), special restraint.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ति|तिः
ti (IE 8-1), abbreviation of tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टि
ṭī (IE 8-1), abbreviation of ṭīkar or ṭikkara, ‘a mound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिगुलदण्ड
tigul̤a-daṇḍa (IE 8-5), name of a tax; see turuṣka-daṇḍa and āndhra-daṇḍa. Tigul̤a is the same as Tamil̤̣. Tigul̤a-daṇḍa may also be ‘the Tamilian measuring rod’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टीकर
ṭīkara (IE 8-1), same as ṭikkara; a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिखरा
tikharā (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टिक्कर
ṭikkara (EI 28), same as ṭīkara; a mound.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिलमक
tilamaka (CII 3; IA 9), a water-course; probably, a channel leading the waters from the hillside over the terraced fields.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=340" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिलपिषक
Tila-piṣaka (CII 4; LL), an oil-miller.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीम्मिर
timmīra (EI 11), a land measure; cf. timpira, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिम्पीर
timpīra (IE 8-6; EI 23, 24, 29), also spelt timpira, ṭim-pira, etc.; a land measure mentioned in Orissan records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टिप्पनक
ṭippanaka (LP), a certificate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरम
tirama (EI 24), Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्णदण्ड
Tīrṇa-daṇḍa (CII 1), ‘one who has been convicted’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थ|तीर्थं|तीर्थः
tīrtha (IE 8-3, 8-4; EI 3; SII 1; CII 4; LL), a place of pilgrimage; a holy place or holy waters; a bathing place; a flight of steps for descent into a river; a ferry; sometimes suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थकर|तीर्थकरः
Tīrthakara (BL), epithet of the Jinas; same as Tīrthaṅ-kara (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थङ्कर|तीर्थङ्करः
Tīrthaṅkara (CII 3; EI 9); epithet of the 24 great leaders of the Jain faith; propagator of the Jain faith or tīrtha; creator of the four sections, viz. monk, nun, layman and laywoman (sādhu, sādhvī, śrāvaka and śrāvikā); same as Jina; sometimes spelt Tīrthakara; also called Ādikartṛ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थिक|तीर्थिकः
Tīrthika (EI 9), Buddhist; teacher of a religion other than one's own; a non-Buddhist (especially, Śaiva) teacher.<BR> (EI 32), same as Tairthika, ‘a priest’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीर्थोपाध्याय
Tīrth-opādhyāya (BL), title of a family priest at Jagannātha-kṣetra (Purī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरुमेनिकावल्
Tiruměni-kāval (ASLV), watchman in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरुविडैयाट्टम्
tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam (EI 30), Tamil; a gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथि|तिथिः
tithi (CII 3; IA 17), a lunar day; one mean tithi is equal to 0.9843529572 of a mean solar day and night; the mean tithis in a solar year are 371, and 3 ghaṭīs and 53.4 palas; generally the term tithi means the end of a tithi, not its beginning or duration, and the week-day of a tithi is the week-day on which that tithi ends; the tithis given in the Pañcāṅga are apparent, not mean, and they are intended to be given from apparent sunrise.<BR> Cf. Tamil tiyadi, tedi (SITI), a date.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘fifteen’.<BR> (EI 16), same as mahā-tithi, an auspicious tithi; cf. saptamī called the tithi of the sun-god and aṣṭamī that of the god Śiva (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 168, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिभोग
tithi-bhoga (CII 3; IA 16), duration of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिध्रुव
tithi-dhruva (CII 3; IA 16), constant of a tithi; a term [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-342" target="_blank">Page-342+ 40</a>] denoting the number of complete tithis that elapse from the commencement of Caitra upto the tithi during which the Meṣa-saṃkrānti occurs. See tithi-śuddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=341" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिकेन्द्र
tithi-kendra (CII 3), anomaly of a tithi, expressed in tithis; an annual variation in the tithi-kendra is 7 tithis, 9 ghaṭīs and 42 palas. See kendra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिस्पष्टकेन्द्र
tithi-spaṣṭa-kendra (IA 16), the apparent anomaly of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिथिशुद्धि
tithi-śuddhi (CII 3), the subtraction of tithis; a term denoting the number of tithis that elapse from the commencement of Caitra up to the time of the Meṣa-saṃkrānti. See tithi-dhruva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोल|तोलं|तोलः
tola, tolā, cf. Telugu-Kannaḍa tulā (CITD), weight of a rupee, taken as the unit of the system of weights; fixed at 180 grains troy by the British; also called suvarṇa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 46).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोलक|तोलकं
tolaka, same as tola; equal to 2 śānas or 80 ratis; also called kola, draṅkṣaṇa, badara, kṣudraka, vaṭaka, etc. (JNSI, Vol. XVI, pp. 41, 44).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोरै
torai (SITI), Tamil; a standard linear measure of four fingers' breadth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोरण|तोरणं|तोरणः
toraṇa (CII 4; LL; CITD), an arch; a gateway; an arched doorway; a portal; a temporary ornamental arch; also a garland in Telugu-Kannaḍa.<BR> Cf. toraṇa-kkāṇikkai (SITI), tax on gates or presents for decorating the village with arches.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैपिटक
Traipiṭaka, cf. Trepiṭaka (EI 9), one versed in the three piṭakas, i. e. the three classes of Buddhist religious literature.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैपिटकोपाध्याय
Traipiṭak-opādhyāya (LL), Buddhist; teacher of the three piṭakas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैपुरुष
Traipuruṣa (Hyderabad Archaeological Series, No. 18, pp. 34-35), same as the composite god Tripuruṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैराज्य
trairājya (EI 19), a group of three realms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैराज्यस्थिति
trairājya-sthiti (EI 27), cf. trairājya-sthitim = ātmasāt = kṛtavataḥ, ‘of one who has obtained steadiness in the three realms.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैविद्य|त्रैविद्यं|त्रैविद्यः
Traividya (LL), Buddhist; teacher of the three piṭakas.<BR> (EI 16), cf. Trivedin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रैविद्यसामान्य
Traividya-sāmānya (EI 23), same as Trivedin; cf. Cāturvidya-sāmānya = Caturvedin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रास|त्रासः
trāsa (SII 2), flaw in a ruby.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=342" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रातृ
Trātṛ (IE 8-2; LL), same as Prakrit Trātara, ‘the saviour’; royal title of foreign origin; Greek Soter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रयी
trayī (SII 1), the three Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रयोदशम
trayodaśama (EI 15), same as trayodaśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रि|त्रिः
Tri (EI 32), abbreviation of Trivedin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रि|त्रिः
tri (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभागाभ्यन्तरसिद्धि
tribhāg-ābhyantara-siddhi (IE 8-5), generally spelt tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi; the right to enjoy one-third of the revenue, the other two parts going in equal shares to gods and Brāhmaṇas. Cf. abhyantara-siddhi, bāhy-ābhyantara-siddhi, tribhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभङ्ग
tri-bhaṅga (EI 17), pose in standing images with bends in three limbs, viz. the neck, the wrists and the knees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभङ्गि
tri-bhaṅgi, cf. tri-bhaṅga; see Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 65.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभोग
tri-bhoga (EI 16; IA 19), a joint tenure enjoyed by a private person, a god (or gods) and the Brāhmaṇas (cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 271). See tribhāg-ābhyantara-siddhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभोगाभ्यन्तर
tribhog-ābhyantara (EI 15), same as tribhog-ābhyantara-siddhi, tribhāg-ābhyantara-siddhi, tribhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभोग्य
tribhogya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 313), cf. gaṇa-bhogya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिभुवनविजयस्तम्भ
tribhuvana-vijaya-stambha (SII 1), a pillar commemorating the conquest of ‘the three worlds’, the conventional claim of a hero.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिचीवर
tri-cīvara (EI 25), complete robe of a Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिदण्ड|त्रिदंड|त्रिदण्डः
tri-daṇḍa, cf. Tridaṇḍin (IA 10); tree staves tied together as borne by Brāhmaṇa mendicants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिदश|त्रिदशः
tridaśa (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirtythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिदीनारिक्य
tridīnārikya (EI 15), same as traidīnārikya, ‘priced at three dīnāras.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिगत
tri-gata (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिगुण|त्रिगुणं
tri-guṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिजगत्
tri-jagat (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’; but jagat sometimes also means ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिक|त्रिकं
trika (HA), a group of three figures of the Tīrthaṅkaras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिकाल
tri-kāla (SII 1; SITI), the three parts of the day, viz. morning, noon and evening [when worship is offered in temples].<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिकूट|त्रिकूटं|त्रिकूटः
trikūṭa (EI 3), a junction of three villages (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 34, note 3); same as trikuṭa or trikuṭṭa. Cf. tri-sandhi; also Telugu muggaḍa, ‘a junction of three or more villages’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=343" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिलक्षण
tri-lakṣaṇa (EI 3), three qualities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृण|तृणं
tṛṇa, cf. a-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-grahaṇa (IE 8-5); grass which the villagers were obliged to supply to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणयूति
tṛṇa-yūti, cf. yūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणयूति
tṛṇa-yūti(or puti)-gocara (EI 17), grass-fields and pasturelands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणोदक
tṛṇ-odaka (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28), name of a tax or cess; the grazing tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिनेत्र|त्रिनेत्रः
trinetra (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपद
tripada (LP), the three chief account books, viz. rojmol, khātā-vahī and pāvtī-vahī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपदलेख्यक
tripada-lekhyaka (LP), accounts book and receipt book.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपाठिन्
Tripāṭhin (EI 4, 31), same as Trivedin; epithet or family-name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिफलीताम्रशासन
triphalī-tāmraśāsana (EI 3), a grant engraved on three copper plates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपीडिदान
tri-pīḍi-dāna (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 271), a grant to be enjoyed by three generations.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिपुरुष
Tripuruṣa (EI 33), a composite deity (tri-mūrti); a combined image of Brahman, Viṣṇu (represented as Sūryanārāyaṇa in Gujarat) and Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिसहस्र
trisahasra (EI 31), also called trisahasra-vidyā; certain sciences.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिसन्धि|त्रिसन्धिः
tri-sandhi (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 34, note 3), a junction of three villages; cf. trikūṭa or trikuṭṭa; also Telugu muggaḍa, ‘the junction of three or more villages’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिशर
triśara (SII 2), name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिस्पर्शा
trisparśā (IA 26), the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिस्थली
tri-sthalī (EI 21), the three holy places, viz. Gayā, Prayāga and Kāśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिष्टुभ्
triṣṭubh (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिशूल|त्रिशूलं
triśūla, cf. tiriśūlam (SITI), trident; same as śūla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रितीर्थी
tri-tīrthī (HA), an image showing figures of three Jinas, usually one Jina standing or sitting in the centre as the main deity of the group and two others sitting or standing on the two sides.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिवर्ग|त्रिवर्गः
tri-varga (SII 1), the three objects of human life.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिवेदिन्
Trivedin (EI 4), same as Tripāṭhin; epithet of Brāhmaṇas later stereotyped as family name.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिविधक्षितीशचूडामणि
Trividha-kṣitīśa-cūḍāmaṇi (IE 8-2), epithet of a king probably [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-345" target="_blank">Page-345+ 40</a>] referring to the Aśvapati, Gajapati and Narapati types of rulers, i. e. those who were strong in elephants, cavalry and infantry respectively.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=344" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रोडनिका
troḍanikā (IE 8-5), same as troṭana; cf. karṇa-troḍanikā, ‘cutting somebody's ears.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रोटन
troṭana (IE 8-5), cf. karṇa-troṭana, same as karṇa-troḍanikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्र्यक्षमुख
tryakṣa-mukha (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुडवु
tuḍavu (SITI), Tamil; a liquid measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुक्खार|तुक्खारः
tukkhāra (CII 4), a Tokharian horse; cf. Tuḥkhāra people of the Purāṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुला
tulā (IA 26), a weight [of silver].<BR> (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit tola or tolaka; the weight of one rupee or 30 canteroy fanams; (1/3) of a navaṭāku; a measure or weight of gold and silver, being 100 palas or about 145 ounces troy. The tulā varied a great deal according to the age and locality.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलाभार|तुलाभारः
tulā-bhāra (EI 4, 17, 26; SITI), name of a mahādāna; same as tulāpuruṣa; weighing a king or an exalted personage against gold or other precious metals and stones and distributing the same to temples, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलाधिरोह
tul-ādhiroha (EI 3), same as tulā-puruṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलापुरुष|तुलापुरुषः
tulā-puruṣa (EI 29; CII 4), name of a mahādāna; same as tulā-bhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलसीविवाह|तुलसीविवाहः
tulasī-vivāha (EI 32), name of a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलु
Tulu, name of a language which is written in Malayāl̤am characters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुल्य|तुल्यः
tulya (SITI), literally, ‘equal’; a true copy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुल्यमेय
tulya-meya (EI 7, 10; HRS), ‘what is to be weighed and measured’; same as meya in deya-meya; known from records like those of Harṣavardhana, in which it may be epithet of bhāga-bhoga or a separate item (Ind. Ep., p. 394).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूम्बु
tūmbu (SITI), Tamil, a measure of capacity; cf. tūmu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूमु
tūmu (EI 27), a grain measure; cf. tūmbu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तून्क्
tūnk (HA), Jain; top of a mountain or hill on which there is a shrine or several shrines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरग|तुरगः
turaga (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरगसाधनिक
Turaga-sādhanika (EI 25), the leader of cavalry. Cf. Sādhanika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरक
Turaka (EI 32), same as Turuka and Turuṣka; a Turk or Turkish Muhammadan; a Muhammadan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=345" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरङ्गम|तुरंगम|तुरंगमः|तुरङ्गमः
turaṅgama (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरीयजन्मन्
Turīya-janman (EI 24; CII 4), same as Śūdra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरुक
Turuka (EI 32), cf. Turaka and Turuṣka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरुष्क|तुरुष्कः
Turuṣka (EI 5, 17, 32), originally, a Turk or a Turkish Muhammadan; later, Muhammadans in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरुष्कदण्ड
turuṣka-daṇḍa (HRS; Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 196, Vol. XI, p. 21), name of a tax collected by the Gāhaḍavāla kings from their Muhammadan subjects or for defending their kingdom from Muhammadan attacks; cf. the danegeld in early English history. See andhra-daṇḍa, tigul̤a-daṇḍa, bhoṭṭa-viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुर्य|तुर्य्य|तुर्य्यः
turya (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्यागीआचार्य
Tyāgī-ācārya (IA 19), Jain; an Ācārya who does not permit laxity of observances.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उ|उः
u (IE 8-1), abbreviation of the land measure called udāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभय|उभयं|उभयः
ubhaya, cf. ubhaiyam (SII 1), an offering.<BR> Cf. ubhaya-paliśai (SITI), interest in two ways, i. e. in money and in kind.<BR> (SITI), a tax payable in gold; probably the same as ubhaya-mārga or the tolls collected on the highways in both the directions, i. e. inward and outward.<BR> (SII, Vol. III, p. 209), a gift to a temple or monastery in Tamil records.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयमुखी
ubhaya-mukhī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 15, note 4), a cow in the act of giving birth to a calf; sometimes explained as ‘a pregnant cow’ (EI 6).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयमुखीदक्षिणा
ubhayamukhī-dakṣiṇā (CITD), some special kind of religious present or fee; the gift of a cow at the point of giving birth to a calf (cf. ubhayamukhī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयनानादेशि
Ubhaya-nānā-deśi (SITI), the two divisions of the Nānā-deśi organisation, e. g., the Nānādeśi and the Citramel̤̣i.<BR> (CITD), explained as the entire merchant community, i. e. including both the Sva-deśi and Para-deśi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उभयस्वाम्य
ubhaya-svāmya, cf. ubhaya-sāmya (EI 5), probably, two kinds of ownership.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उचट
ucaṭa (LP), impatience, anxiety; cf. Gujarātī uchāṭ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्चावच|उच्चावचः
ucc-āvaca (CII 1), ‘more or less’, ‘of various kinds’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=346" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छन्न|उच्छन्नं
ucchanna (CII 3), corruption of utsanna; found in Sanskrit inscriptions. See JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, 1954, p. 204.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छीर्ण
ucchīrṇa (IA 19), a loan.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छ्रय|उच्छ्रयः
ucchraya (Ep. Ind., Vol. VIII, p. 46, note 3), a shelter; same as pratiśraya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उच्छृङ्खल|उच्छृंखल|उच्छृङ्खलं
ucchṛṅkhala (LP), free from a burden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उछालकभृत
uchālaka-bhṛta (LP), loaded with uchālaka (Gujarātī ucāl̤o), i. e. household furniture that can be easily moved about.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उड
uḍa (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentyseven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदगयन|उदगयनं
udag-ayana (EI 23), the winter solstice; same as uttarāyaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदगयनपर्वन्
udagayana-parvan (EI 20), cf. udag-ayana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उडैयार्
Uḍaiyār (SITI), Tamil; literally, a possessor; a king or lord; the chief deity of a temple. Cf. uḍaiyār-śālai, the feeding house attached to a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकबन्ध
udaka-bandha (EI 3), a sluice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकधारा
udaka-dhārā, cf. udaka-dārai (SITI), [a gift given] with the libation of water; also referred to in Tamil as udakañśeydu and udakaṃ paṇṇi. See udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकपूर्वम्
udaka-pūrvam (IA 7), also expressed as udak-ātisargeṇa, ‘with libations of water’; refers to the custom of pouring water in the hand of the donee while making the ceremonial gift of an object which cannot be placed in the latter's hands. Cf. Dra-vyasya nāma gṛhnīyād=dadān=īti tathā vadet | toyaṃ dadyāt=tato haste dāne vidhir=ayaṃ smṛtaḥ || (Agni Purāṇa, Ch. 209, verses 49-50).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकसर्ग
udaka-sarga (IA 8), same as udak-ātisarga (cf. udaka-pūrvam).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकासीहारकुल्लक
udak-āsīhāra-kullaka, cf. sa-vanaspaty-udak-āsīhāra-kullaka-pānīya-sametā (IE 8-5), translated as ‘together with the fruit-trees and with the water-courses and channels’ (with the omission of the doubtful words).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदमान|उदमानः
udamāna (IE 8-6; EI 29), a small land measure; probably the same as unmāna and udāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदान|उदानः
udāna, see udamāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदपान|उदपानं|उदपानः
udapāna (CII 1; LL), a well or reservoir.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदार|उदारः
udāra (CII 1), a person of high rank; a rich man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदरबन्धन
udara-bandhana (SII) 2), a waist-band; name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदरम्भरीण
udaram-bharīṇa (IA 17), same as udaram-bharin, ‘filling the belly.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=347" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदर्चिस्|उदर्च्चिस्
udarcis (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदासीन|उदासीनः
udāsīna, cf. udāsina-vāriyam (SITI), a committee which is neutral to both the parties; same as madhyastha or the arbitration committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदय|उदयः
udaya (EI 24), ‘the produce’ [of a field]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदयगिरि|उदयगिरिः
Udaya-giri (IA 22), the mythical Sun-rise mountain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्बलि
udbali, cf. umbal̤i (EI 13), umbal̤am, umbal̤ikkai, umbal̤ika (SITI), rent-free gift of land; land granted rent-free for the performance of service; same as mānya. See udbalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्बलिक
udbalika (IE 8-5; CII 1), free from taxes; free from the obligation of paying bali probably meaning land tax payable in addition to the king's share of grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्दामन्
uddāman (EI 9), same as uddāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्दातव्य
uddātavya, ‘to be repaid’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 239); ‘to be handed over’ (ibid., p. 246).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्देश|उद्देशः
uddeśa (CII 4), a territorial division.<BR> (EI 14), cf. s-oddeśa (IE 8-5); space above the ground; same as ūrdhva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्ध
uddha (IA 19), explained as ‘deserted’. Cf. uddha-grāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धग्राम
uddha-grāma (LP), the village of which the revenue is fixed in a lump sum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धखिलभूमि
uddha-khila-bhūmi (LP), table land which is uncultivated (khila). But cf. uddha-grāma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धार|उद्धारं|उद्धारः
uddhāra (LP), borrowed on trust or credit; cf. udhār.<BR> (IE 8-5), same as udraṅga; cf. Tamil uttāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धारप्रोद्धार
uddhāra-proddhāra (LP), taking on credit; cf. Marāṭhī udhār-pādhār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धार्य
uddhārya (LP), ‘may be debited’; cf. Gujarātī udhāra-vuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्धार्यव्यवहार
uddhārya-vyavahāra (LP), the business of lending money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्द्योतित
uddyotita (EI 13), literally, ‘caused to shine’; actually ‘with repairs effected.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्गणक
udgaṇaka (LP), a revenue chart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्गणनीय
udgaṇanīya (LP), cf. Gujarātī gaṇī āpavuṃ, ‘the charge should be handed over.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्घाटित|उद्घाटितः
udghāṭita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20), same as utkīrṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्ग्राह्
udgrāh, cf. udgrāhayiṣyāmi (LP), ‘I shall get the revenue collected [from the country in this way]’; also udgrāhita (LP), ‘taxed’; udgrāhyamāṇa (LP), cf. Gujarātī ughrāvayuṃ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=348" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्ग्रन्थ|उद्ग्रंथ|उद्ग्रन्थः
udgrantha (IE 8-5), same as udraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उधरित
udharita (IA 18), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदीचीपति
Udīcīpati (BL), literally, ‘the ruler of the north (i. e. the northern province of an empire)’; title of a viceroy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्रङ्ग|उद्रंगः|उद्रङ्गः
udraṅga (IE 8-3; 8-5; EI 22; CII 3, 4; HRS), explained as ‘the fixed tax’, ‘the land tax’, ‘the principal tax’ or ‘the tax on the permanent tenants’; generally mentioned along with uparikara, i. e. minor taxes or the tax on temporary tenants; same as kl̤pta. Udraṅga may have been paid in grains at least in soem regions since the Audraṅgika (collector of ud-raṅga) is sometimes separately mentioned together with the Hiraṇyasāmudāyika (collector of revenue in cash). In one case, the land is said to have been granted after making it udraṅga, i. e. s-odraṅga. See s-odraṅga (IA 10), draṅga, uttāra. Cf. mah-odraṅga in pravartita-mahodraṅg-ādi-dāna-vyasan-ānupajāta-santoṣa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXII, p. 118, text line 40).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्रङ्गीकृत्य
udraṅgīkṛtya (IE 8-3), same as s-odraṅgīkṛtya; used in respect of a gift land. Cf. udraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्रव
udrava (EI 27), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदुम्बर|उदुंबर|उदुम्बरं|उदुंबरः|उदुम्बरः
udumbara (LP), ‘threshold’; cf. gṛh-odumbara-madhye, ‘into the house’; cf. umbara-bheda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्वस
udvasa, cf. udvasa-kuṭumbika (LP), cultivators who have come from outside and settled.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्वात
udvāta (EI 13), tempest; cf. bhūta-vāla-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्याम|उद्यामः
udyāma (CII 1), used in the sense of udyama or exertion.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्यान|उद्यानं|उद्यानः
udyāna (CII 1), march; a garden.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्क
ukka, ukkā (Chamba), the total sum; a lump sum.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्कोड
ukkoḍa, a kind of levy; probably, periodical presents; same as utkoṭa. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्कोटभङ्ग
ukkoṭa-bhaṅga, same as khoṭa-bhaṅga (q. v.) according to the Abhidhānarājendra, s. v. parihāra; cf. utkoṭa and ukkoḍa, periodical presents (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्कुट्ठी
ukkuṭṭhī (IE 8-8), Prakrit; see utkṛṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्तनियोग
ukta-niyoga (EI 33), doubtful expression probably indicating an official designation. Cf. uttara-niyoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उक्थ्य|उक्थ्यः
ukthya, (EI 22; CII 3), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लन्बन
ullanbana (IE 8-8), a crime, the real nature of which is uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लेख|उल्लेखः
ullekha, ‘high-flashing’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, p. 36).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=349" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लेखक
Ullekhaka, engraver (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 203 and note 11). See Vilekhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लुञ्चन|उल्लुंचन|उल्लुंचनं
ulluñcana (LP), cleaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उमराव
Umarāva (EI 26; BL), title of a feudatory ruler; same as the Muhammadan title Umrah.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बलि
umbal̤i (ASLV), Tamil; same as Sanskrit udbali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बर|उंबर|उंबरः|उम्बरः
umbara (IE 8-8), same as Prakrit ummara; threshold or door; cf. umbara-bheda, also udumbara and unmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बरभेद|उम्बरभेदः
umbara-bheda (IE 8-5; EI 25), ‘violation of the closed door’; the right of royal officers to enter into a house with doors closed for realising taxes. This probably related to the houses of merchants who were away from their home-towns in the course of their business; cf. unmara or umbara; also prātibhedikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उमुरभेद
umura-bheda (CII 4), mistake for umbara-bheda (q. v.); forcible entry into a house. Cf. unmara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊनाब्दिकश्राद्ध
ūnābdika-śrāddha (CII 4), a rite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छ|उञ्छं|उंछः|उञ्छः
uñcha, cf. uñcha-kara-bhar-ādi-vivarjita; tolls (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 89); may be collection of small quantities of crops (cf. prastha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उण्बलि
uṇbal̤i (SII 11-1), same as Sanskrit udbali.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छमन्न
uñchamanna (EI 26), used along with mar̤umanna; a privilege of the donee of rent-free land; see uñcha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छवृत्ति
uñcha-vṛtti (EI 24), a gleaner of corn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्मान|उन्मानं|उन्मानः
unmāna (IE 8-6; EI 15, 21, 29), name of a small land measure; same as udāna or udamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्मर
unmara (EI 30), Sanskritised form of Prakrit ummara (cf. umbara); threshold. Merchants, who were often absent from home for a long time, were sometimes made free from unmara-bheda (entry into their house) by royal officers probably because they paid their dues on their return from business tours. Cf. prātibhedikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्नत|उन्नतः
unnata (IE 8-5), high land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उन्नीति
unnīti, ‘adopted daughter’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 237).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपधा
upa-dhā (CII 1), cf. hīta-sukham=upadadhyuḥ; to bring [welfare and happiness to the people].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाधि|उपाधिः
upādhi (SII 1), probably, a condition.<BR> Cf. opādi (SII 2), dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाध्याय|उपाध्यायः
Upādhyāya (CII 4), a teacher; epithet of Brāhmaṇas.<BR> (IA 19), Jain; an Ācārya who has the right of reading the sacred text, but not of explaining it. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-351" target="_blank">Page-351+ 40</a>]<BR> (IE 8-3; EI 7), epithet of teachers; mentioned as a Pātra.<BR> (CII 3), a sub-teacher who is the instructor in only a part of the Veda, or in grammar and the other Vedāṅgas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=350" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाध्यायिनी
Upādhyāyinī (LL), a female teacher; the wife of an Upādhyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपग
upaga (CII 1), suitable; cf. manuṣy-opaga, ‘beneficial to men’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपगत|उपगतः
upagata (CII 1), same as saṅgata, intimately associated; see upeta, etc. See Ind. Ep., pp. 161 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपगता
upagatā (LP), a receipt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपहन्
upa-han (CII 1), to harm; cf. upaghāta, injury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपकर
upakara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 106, note 5), cf. nikara and upaskara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपकारिका
upakārikā, probably, a territorial unit around the headquarters of an administrative unit (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 286).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपखिल
upakhila, cf. sa-khil-opakhila (Chamba), ‘together with fallow (khila) and partially fallow (upakhila) land’. See pakhila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपकॢप्त
upakḷpta (EI 15; CII 3, 4), a levy; probably, the tax on temporary tenants or the unfixed taxes or minor income; cf. sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta (IE 8-5), also kḷpta, kḷpta-kara, udraṅga and uparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपक्रमकरण
upakrama-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the department of new undertakings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपक्षय|उपक्षयः
upakṣaya (LP), expense; ‘other expenses’; cf. s-opak-ṣaya, sañjāt-opakṣaya, ‘expenses incurred’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपक्षिति
upakṣiti (IE 8-5; EI 33), probably, tax on inferior land; may also be the same as upakṣaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपलक्षित
upalakṣita (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), ‘examined’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपान
upāna (SITI), the first moulding above the plinth, in the construction of temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपनिधि|उपनिधिः
upanidhi (IE 8-5; EI 12), same as nikṣepa; cf. nidhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपनिपातक
upanipātaka (CII 3), same as upapātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपपातक|उपपातकं
upapātaka (CII 3), sins of the second degree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपपीठ
upapīṭha (SII 2), a lower pedestal; cf. pīṭha; also upa-pīṭhattukaṇḍappaḍai, the lower tier of the basement of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपप्रधानिन्
Upapradhānin (ASLV), an executive officer lower in rank than the Pradhānīn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरहिण्डीय
Uparahiṇḍīya (LP), a tax-inspector.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=351" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरक्षित
uparakṣita (LL), explained as ‘kept in custody’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिक
Uparika (IE 8-3; CII 3; BL; HD), a viceroy; the governor of a province. An Uparika was appointed by the emperor and he himself appointed the governor of the district (cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 130). He is sometimes styled Mahārāja and Rājaputra. Viśvarūpa on the Yājñavalkyasmṛti, I. 307, quotes a prose passage from Bṛhaspati where the requisite qualities of an Uparika are set out. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 123. The word literally means ‘one placed at the top’.<BR> (IE 8-3), cf. Auparika, a viceroy.<BR> Cf. Bṛhad-uparika (IE 8-3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिकमहाराज
Uparika-mahārāja (IE 8-3), an Uparika enjoying the title Mahārāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिकर|उपरिकरः
uparikara (IE 8-5; CII 3, 4; HRS), explained as ‘additional taxes’, ‘unfixed taxes’, ‘minor taxes’, or ‘tax paid by the temporary tenants’; cf. s-oparikara (IA 10), sometimes called parikara (cf. sa-parikara in place of s-opakriara). See upri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपरिङ्ख्
upa-riṅkh (EI 12), to spread.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपासक|उपासकः
Upāsaka (EI 3, 8, 27; CII 3), a Buddhist lay worshipper; a lay follower of the Buddha; cf. Upāsikā.<BR> (SII 13), a temple servant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपसम्पदा
upasampadā (EI 9; IA 22), the initiation of a Buddhist monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपसन्धि
upasandhi (SITI), intermediary service of worship in a temple, between the morning and the midday service.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपासनिन्
Upāsanin (EI 32), title or family name of Brāhmaṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपसन्न|उपसन्नः
upasanna, cf. kṛt-opasannā (EI 30); word of doubtful import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपासिका
Upāsikā (CII 3, 4), feminine form of Upāsaka (q. v.); a female lay-follower of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपस्कर|उपस्करः
upaskara (HRS), known from the Kamauli plate of Vaidyadeva; probably meaning upakara (q. v.) or the appurtenance to a tax (kara).<BR> Cf. nikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाश्रय|उपाश्रयः
upāśraya (LL), a shelter.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपस्थान|उपस्थानं
upasthāna (LL), reception room.<BR> (HRS), a group of royal receipts arising from underhand methods of collection of the contributions in kind, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=352" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपस्थानशाला
upasthāna-śālā (LL), hall of reception.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपतल्प|उपतल्पः
upatalpa (EI 8), the upper story [of a house].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाति
upāti (SITI), Tamil; also spelt opādi; Sanskrit upādhi; literally, obstruction; dues; anything payable as a debt or obligation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपात्त|उपात्तं|उपात्तः
upātta, cf. sa-bhūt-opātta-pratyāya (EI 23), ‘together with the income derived on account of changes in the natural phenomena.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपाय|उपायः
upāya (EI 6, 25), four in number; ‘four’. Cf. catur-upāya (SII 1).<BR> (SITI), probably, minor taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयात
upayāta (EI 33), same as opeta, upagata, ‘closely associated’. See samupagata, samaveta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयुक्त|उपयुक्तः
Upayukta (HD), same as Upayuktaka, ‘a subordinate officer’. See Arthaśāstra, II. 5; Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 285.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयुक्तक
Upayuktaka (IE 8-3; HD), probably the same as Niyuk-taka, Viniyuktaka, Tad-viniyuktaka, etc. See Upayukta; cf. Yuktak-Opayukta (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 40).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपयुक्तिक
Upayuktika (EI 23), official designation; probably the same as Upayuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपेक्षा
upekṣā (CII 4), Buddhist; indifference; one of the bhā-vanās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपेत
upeta (CII 1), same as saṅgata; ‘intimately associated’; cf. upagata, upayāta, samupagata, samaveta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपोद
upoda (Chamba), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उपोसथागार
uposath-āgāra (EI 23), ‘the uposatha hall’. See poṣadha, pauṣadha<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उप्रि
upri (IE 8-5), Marāṭhī; same as uparikara (q. v.), tax on temporary tenants, according to some.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्
ūr (ASLV), the assembly of a non-Brāhmaṇa village, that of a Brāhmaṇa village being called sabhā or mahāsabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरन्दर
urandara (LP), delay.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्व|ऊर्द्ध्वः
ūrdhva, cf. s-ādha-ūrdhva (IE 8-5), ‘[what is] above the surface of the ground’; same as uddeśa.<BR> Cf. ūrdhva-dina-pāṭikāyām (LP), ‘for the series of days afterwards.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वाधः
ūrdhv-ādhaḥ (IA 16), explained as ‘what is above and below [in the gift land]’; cf. ūrdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi-yutā (IA 18), ‘with income from the produce above and below the surface of the ground’; same as s-ādha-ūrdhva, epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=353" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वपट्ट
ūrdhva-paṭṭa (LL), an upright slab.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वयित
ūrdhvayita, cf. Prakrit ubhayita (EI 20), raised. See ūrdhvita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ध्वित
ūrdhvita, Prakrit ubhayita (Sel. Ins., p. 222), raised, contributed. See ūrdhvayita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उर्गामुण्ड
Ur-gāmuṇḍa (IA 12), Kannaḍa; official designation; cf. Gāmuṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्ण|ऊर्णं|ऊर्ण्ण
ūrṇa (EI 8), a mark between the brows of the Buddha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्णस्थान
ūrṇa-sthāna (IE 8-3), a wool factory. Cf. Aurṇasthānika, officer in charge of the ūrṇā-sthānas (Select Inscriptions, p. 360, text line 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरोडे
Uroḍě (IA 8), Kannaḍa; the village headman; cf. Uroḍěya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरोडेय
Uroḍěya (IA 12), Kannaḍa; official designation; cf. Uroḍě.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्पद्दिन्काडि
ūr-paddin̤kāḍi (EI 28), name of a rural tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उर्वरा|उर्व्वरा
urvarā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उषर
uṣara, cf. sa-gartt-oṣara (IE 8-5); a saline spot or barren land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उशावडि
uśāvaḍi (IE 8-4; SITI), a subdivision of the district; same as śāvaḍi or cāvaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊष्मल
ūṣmala (EI 12), glowing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उष्णिष
uṣṇiṣa, cf. Prakrit uṃnisa (EI 20; LL), a coping stone.<BR> (EI 8), protuberance of the Buddha's skull.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कलित|उत्कलितः
utkalita, cf. kaṭakam=utkalitam (IA 14, 30), ‘the camp was pitched’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कर|उत्करः
utkara (IE 8-5), probably, minor taxes; but see kāru-kara. Cf. upakara, nikara, etc. But see also Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 47.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कर्णित
utkarṇita (LP), frightened.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कर्ष|उत्कर्षः
utkarṣa (CII 1), used in the sense of utkṛṣṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्खातकार्मण
Utkhātakārmaṇa (EI 15), epithet of a donee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्खेटन
utkheṭana (EI 32; HRS), known from certain records from Assam; explained as an impost levied upon the villagers on specified occasions; probably, the trouble of free labour. Cf. Utkheṭayitā, Autkheṭika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्खेटयिता
Utkheṭayitā (EI 12; BL; HRS), known from certain Assam records; explained as a tax-collector; officer in charge of utkheṭana (q. v.); same as Autkheṭika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कीर्ण|उत्कीर्ण्ण
utkīrṇa (CII 3), ‘engraved’; a technical expression for the actual engraving of an inscription on copper or stone; sometimes indicated by the word udghāṭita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20) and ghaṭita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 121). See Ullekhaka, likhita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=354" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कोट
utkoṭa (IE 8-5, 8-8; EI 33), Prakrit ukkoḍa; a levy; customary presents to be made on occasions to the king or landlord and others. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कॄ
ut-kṝ, ‘to engrave’; cf. Prakrit kaṇḍāra, used in some Kannaḍa inscriptions (Bul. Dec. Col. Res. Inst., Vol. XI, 1950, pp. 170-71). Cf. utkīrṇa, udghāṭita, Ullekhaka, Vilekhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कृष्टि
utkṛṣṭi (IE 8-8; EI 30), same as Prakrit ukkuṭṭhī (q. v.), Sanskrit utkrośa; wailing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्क्रोश|उत्क्रोशः
utkrośa (IE 8-8), see utkṛṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्कृति|उत्कृतिः
utkṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentysix’; rarely ‘twentyone’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पद्यमानविष्टिक
utpadyamāna-viṣṭika (CII 4), ‘with the right to unpaid labour as occasion may arise’; a privilege attached to gift lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पन्न|उत्पन्नः
utpanna, decided or ascertained^1 (Select Inscriptions, pp. 284, 286); same as pratipanna; cf. pratipad.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पाट्
ut-pāṭ (LP), Gujarātī upāḍavuṃ; cf. Vaidyanātha-patram= utpāṭayati, ‘takes a bilva-patra of the god Vaidyanātha (Śiva)’, i. e. swears.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पात|उत्पातः
utpāta (EI 33), unusual phenomenon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पट्ट
utpaṭṭa, cf. upaṭṭa (EI 13), abundance; exuberance or overflowing [especially^1 of rich dishes at a feast].<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्पत्ति|उत्पत्तिः
utpatti (EI 12), cf. samast-otpatti-sahita, ‘together with all the produce (or income)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
utpratikara, same as apratikara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIX, p. 54, line 10).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्साह|उत्साहः
utsāha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 189), generous gift, bounty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्साहशक्ति|उत्साहशक्तिः
utsāha-śakti (CII 4), personal energy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सङ्ग|उत्संग|उत्संगः|उत्सङ्गः
utsaṅga (HRS), extra cess levied upon villagers and citizens on occasions of festival events, such as the birth of a prince, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सर्पण|उत्सर्पणं|उत्सर्प्पण
utsarpaṇa, cf. pañca-mahāyajña-kriy-otsarpaṇ-ārtham (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 279, text lines 64-65).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सर्पित|उत्सर्प्पित
utsarpita (CII 1), erected.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्सृत
utsṛta (CII 1) = ucchrita, man of a high position; a rich man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्त|उत्तं
utta (LP), modification of Sanskrit putra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमदानि
uttama-dāni (SITI), a gift made without expecting any merit for the same; a superior kind of gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमगोसास
uttama-gosāsa (IA 11), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमोत्तम
uttam-ottama (EI 25), a type of temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तानद्वादशि
uttāna-dvādaśī (SITI), twelfth day of the bright fortnight in the month of Kārttigai when the god Viṣṇu is believed to wake up from his sleep; see utthāna-dvādaśī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=355" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
utthāpita, dedicated (E. I., 16, p. 15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तर|उत्तरं|उत्तरः
uttara, cf. uttarāṇi (LP), same as uttar-ākṣarāṇi. See akṣara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तार|उत्तारः
uttāra (SITI), a regular fixed payment; same as uddhāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरकुलिक
Uttarakulika (EI 30), a class of officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरकुलिकवारिक
Uttarakulika-vārika (IE 8-8), an official designation of uncertain import. See Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरमन्त्रिन्
Uttara-mantrin (EI 8; SITI), the chief minister.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरनियोग
uttara-niyoga (EI 32), ‘subsequent assignment’; cf. ukta-niyoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरसभा
uttara-sabhā (EI 19), the supreme assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरवाद
uttara-vāda (SITI), a guarantee; responsibility.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तरायण|उत्तरायणं
uttar-āyaṇa (IA 17; SII 1), the winter solstice; the period during which the sun gradually moves from south to north; cf. dakṣiṇ-āyana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थान|उत्थानं
utthāna (CII 1), exerting oneself.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थानद्वादशी
utthāna-dvādaśī (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 163, 167, 169), name of a tithi (EI 9); twelfth day of the bright fortnight in the month of Kārttigai when the god Viṣṇu is believed to wake up from his sleep (SITI).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थाय
utthāya, ‘of one's own accord’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 248).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्थितासनिन्
Utthit-āsanin (IE 8-3); see Autthilāsanika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तिरम्
uttiram (SII 2), the projecting part of a wall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उवटक
uvaṭaka (EI 1), probably, a verandah, porch or vestibule; cf. Marāṭhī oṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
va (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vaḍḍavāra (Saturday or Thursday).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
va (CII 3; IA 8-1), an abbreviation of vadya or ‘the dark fortnight’ or else a substitute for ba (abbreviation of bahula) used in connection with di; see ba-di, va-di.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
va, vā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Prakrit vassa or vāsa- Sanskrit varṣā, the rainy season.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वा
vā (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vāra.<BR> Cf. vā-bhū, vā-ṭī.<BR> (LP), abbreviation of Vāṇija, a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाभू
vā-bhū (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vāstu-bhūmi, ‘homestead land.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाचक|वाचकः
Vācaka (LL), a Jain preacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वचन|वचनं
vacana (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=356" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वचनकार
Vacanakāra (EI 23), an author of vacanas or sayings; cf. subhāṣita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाचनिक
vācanika, cf. rāja-vāchanika (CII 1), a royal order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वचोगुप्ति
vaco-gupti (CII 1), restraint in the matter of speech.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाड|वाडः
vāḍa (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa; a street, a range of houses.<BR> (EI 11), a ward.<BR> (IA 7), also vāḍi; often suffixed to geographical names.<BR> (CII 4), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाड|वाडः
vāḍa, vāḍā (IE 8-4), corrupt forms of pāṭaka, ‘part of a village’; in soem dialects, also ‘a village’; often suffixed to the names of localities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वडहरक
Vaḍaharaka (EI 11), same as Marvād̤ī (Marwari) Baḍero; an old man.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डाचार्य
Vaḍḍ-ācārya (SII 11-1), Sanskrit Vṛddh-ācārya or Bṛhad-ācārya; designation of a Jain teacher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डवार
vaḍḍa-vāra (EI 13; CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa;' Saturday or Thursday (A. Venkatasubbiah, Some Śaka Dates in Inscriptions, pp. 57. ff.); same as bṛha-vāra. The word in the Telugu part of an inscription is explained as śanaiścara-vāra in the Sanskrit portion of the said record; sometimes wrongly supposed to stand for some other day, e. g. Friday (IA 23) or Sunday (Venkatasubbiah, op. cit., p. 58). Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 147; XIII, p. 16; Vol. XXXI, p. 100, note 1; Vol. XXXIII, p. 1, note 2; Ind. Ant., Vol. XXII, pp. 111, 251-52; XXIII, p. 168. Vaḍḍa=vṛddha or bṛhat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डव्यवहारि
Vaḍḍa-vyavahāri (SITI; ASLV), the leader of a merchant guild; a banker; the principal money-changer; chief of the Nānādeśi (non-local) merchants. Cf. Mahāvaḍḍavyavahāri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वडवा
Vaḍavā (EI 22, 27), Marāṭhil; record-keeper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाध|वाधः
vādha (EI 16), land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाधा
vādhā, cf. bādhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाढढा
vāḍhaḍhā (IA 15), a doubtful word probably meaning ‘a drum’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वध्रिकुक्कुट
vadhri-kukkuṭa (IA 18, CII 1), Prakrit vadhi-kukuṭa; a capon; also Sanskritised as vṛddhi-kukkuṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वधू
vadhū, one's own wife; one's son's wife. (putra-vadhū)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वदि
va-di (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vadya-pakṣa-dina or a mistake for ba-di (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाडि
vāḍi (IA 7), same as vāḍa; often suffixed to geographical names.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=357" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाद्य|वाद्यं|वाद्यः
vādya (SITI), a musical instrument.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाद्यमहाराज
Vādya-mahārāja, cf. Tamil Vācciya-mārāyan̤ (SITI), the head musician or the chief Mel̤akāran̤ of a temple or palace; title conferred by the king on an expert in instrumental music.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वगैर
vagaira (IA 20), Persian; ‘and so forth’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वागुली
Vāgulī (EI 28), Od̤iyā; also written Bāgulī; the king's betel-bearer; same as Vārgulika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वागुलिक
Vāgulika, Vāgūlika (CII 4; BL), explained by some as ‘a seller of betel-leaves’; the bearer of the betel-box of an Orissan ruler; same as Vārgulika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वागुणि
Vāguṇi (EI 24), mistake for Vāguli.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वह|वहः
vaha, cf. a-vaha (IE 8-5); [free] carrying of loads [which the villagers had to provide for the touring officers of the king or land-lord]; may also be a horse for the use of the officers.<BR> (EI 31; IA 18; CII 4), a streamlet; a water-channel.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), a common highway.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाह|वाहः
vāha, cf. Vāha-nāyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहक|वाहकः
Vāhaka (EI 3), probably, a driver or attendant of cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहला
vāhalā (EI 3), a water course.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहलि
Vāhali (BL), official designation explained as ‘the lord of horses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहमान
vahamāna (LP), cf. vahamāna-hala-balīvarda, ‘bullocks used in ploughing land’; vahamāna-samakara-bhūmi in which vahamāna means ‘[the land that is] being ploughed’.<BR> (LP), travelling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहन|वाहनं
vāhana (LP), a load-carrier; a cart, ship, etc. See vahitra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहनायक
Vāha-nāyaka (EI 23), official designation; probably, ‘the officer in charge of the king's Khās Mahāls’ (from vāha, a plough); may also be the superintendent of transport. See vāhoṭaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहिका
vahikā (LP), an account book.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहिनीपति|वाहिनीपतिः
Vāhinīpati (EI 28; IA 10), leader of forces; a general; cf. Senāpati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहणि
vahaṇi (IA 18), meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वहित्र|वहित्रं
vahitra (IE 8-5, 8-8; EI 30), boat or any large carrier like a cart; see vāhana. Cf. sārtha-vahitreṣu praveśe nirgame ca pratyekaṃ rūpakaḥ devasya yātr-otsave dātavyaḥ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 232).<BR> (IE 8-8), cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra, ‘a wagon full of pots or jars’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=358" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वह्नि|वह्निः
vahni (IE 7-1-2, EI 33), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाहोटक
vāhoṭaka (LP), either Gujarātī vighoṭi, an assessment of land collected per vighā (bīghā), or the plough tax (i. e. land tax) from vāha, a plough.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाह्यालि
vāhyāli (BL), explained as ‘stables’; cf. bāhy-āli.<BR> (EI 6), explained as ‘a camp’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैभोग
vaibhoga, cf. aṅga-raṅga-vaibhoga (EI 3; SII 1; SITI); same as bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैदर्वेयक
vaidarveyaka, cf. vedaveyaka (IA 18; CII 1), an eel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैधरण
vaidharaṇa (HRS), a compensation fee levied upon the sale of liquors, royal merchandise, mining products and imported salt, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैदिल
vaidila (CII 3), a word of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्य|वैद्यः
Vaidya (EI 9, 30; BL), a physician; member of the physician community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यभाग
vaidya-bhāga (SII 2), same as vaidya-bhoga, vaidya-vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यभोग
vaidya-bhoga (SITI), also called vaidya-bhāga, vaidya-vṛtti; land set apart for the maintenance of the physician.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यपरिचारक
Vaidya-paricāraka, cf. Tamil Vaijya-paricārakar (EI 24), medical attendants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैद्यवृत्ति
vaidya-vṛtti (SII 1), land enjoyed by the Vaidyas for their maintenance; cf. vaidya-bhāga, vaidya-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैजक
Vaijaka (EI 26), official designation; probably Vaidyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैजयिक|वैजयिकं
vaijayika, carrying victory; cf. Ep. Ind., XXXII, p. 88. See vijaya-vaijayika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैजयिकधर्मस्थान
vaijayika-dharmasthāna (EI 22), ‘the victorious office of justice’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैक्षेपिक
Vaikṣepika (EI 8-3; EI 26), probably, the dispatcher of messengers; same as Preṣaṇika. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVI, p. 206. See also vikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैलब्धिक
Vailabdhika (EI 8-3; EI 30), officer in charge of vilabdhi (q. v.); probably, the custodian of recovered stolen property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैदान्तिक
Vaidāntika (BL), an exponent of the Vedānta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैर|वैरं
vaira (IA 18), blood-money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैरागि
Vairāgi (SITI), an ascetic serving in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैशारद्य|वैशारद्यं
vaiśāradya cf. vesārajja (EI 5), Buddhist; four in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैषयिक|वैषयिकः
Vaiṣayika (EI 7), probably, the ruler of a viṣaya or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्वदेव|वैश्वदेवः
vaiśvadeva (EI 10, 14, 23; CII 3, 4), offerings to gods; one of the five mahāyajñas; sometimes called vaiśvānara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=359" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्वानर|वैश्वानरः
vaiśvānara (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR> Cf. vaiśvadeva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्वासिक
Vaiśvāsika (IE 8-3; EI 9, 28, 29), probably the same as Rahasyādhikṛta, etc.; cf. Paramaviśvāsin, Viśvāsa, Viśvāsika; the privy councillor or private secretary.<BR> (EI 3), mentioned along with Antaraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्याग्रहार
vaiśy-āgrahāra (IE 8-5; EI 30, 33), a privileged holding created in favour of members of the mercantile community; see agrahāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वैश्यवाणियनगरत्तार्
vaiśya-vāṇiya-nagarattār (SITI), ASLV), Sanskrit vaiśya-vāṇija-nagarastha; a corporation of the merchants; the guild of a class of merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाजपेय|वाजपेयं|वाजपेयः
vājapeya (EI 22; CII 4; BL), name of a Vedic sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाजिन्
vājin (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाजिवैद्य
Vāji-vaidya (BL), explained as ‘a veterinary physician’; literally, ‘a physician for horses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वज्र|वज्रं|वज्रः
vajra (HA), thunderbolt.<BR> Cf. vaccira-ppaḍai (SITI), the lower or foundation tier of the wall of a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वज्रासन
vajrāsana (LL), name of the seat on which the Buddha sat for meditation for the attainment of supreme knowledge (bodhi).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाक्पारुष्य|वाक्पारुष्यं
vāk-pāruṣya (EI 30), use of abusive language.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाक्ष
vākṣa (Chamba), tax in cash; same as bācha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलदी
valadī (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 17, text line 21), correctly baladī derived from balīvarda; same as vara-balīvarda, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालगिरि
vāl̤a-giri (SITI), abbreviation of the name of the mythical mountain called cakravāla-giri.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलनाडु
val̤anāḍu (IE 8-4; EI 25), Tamil; a province; a district consisting of sub-divisions called kur̤r̤am or nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलक्ष|वलक्षः
valakṣa (IA 17), used to indicate the bright fortnight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालनीय
vālanīya (LP), see valiṣyati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलत्कौषन्
Valatkauṣan (CII 3), official designation of uncertain import; probably, a mistake for Bala-kauṣṭhika, officer-in-charge of the treasury of the military department. Cf. Mahavalākoṣṭhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलाकोष्ठिक
Valākoṣṭhika, probably, a mistake for Balakoṣṭhika; cf. Valat-kauṣan, Mahāvalākoṣṭhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलय|वलयं|वलयः
valaya (CITD), a ring; a bracelet; in Telugu-Kannaḍa, also an enclosure, a boundary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलयष्टि
vala-yaṣṭi (CII 4), mistake for bala-yaṣṭi, memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=360" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलययष्टि
valaya-yaṣṭi (EI 33; CII 3), wrong emendation of bala-yaṣṭi and supposed to mean ‘a boundary-pillar’. See bala-yaṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालयित्वा
vālayitvā (LP), Gujarātī vāl̤īne.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्होडीय
valhoḍīya (LP), rams.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालि|वालिः
vāl̤i (SII 2), ear-ring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलिस्यति
valiṣyati (LP), cf. Gujarātī vāḷi levāmāṃ āvaśe; see vālanīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलित|वलितः
valita, val̤ita (E 12; SITI), same as vaṇita; a small territorial unit; a district or its subdivision.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलितपत्रविधि
valita-patra-vidhi (LP), cf. Gujarātī val̤at-dān-khat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलीवर्द|वलीवर्दः|वलीवर्द्द|वलीवर्द्दः
valīvarda, variant spelling of balīvarda (q. v.); cf. a-param-parā-valivarda, etc. (IE 8-5); a pair of bullocks [which the villagers were obliged to provide for the cart of the royal officers when they were camping or touring in the village].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्ल|वल्लः
valla (IE 8-8), name of a weight equal to 3 ratis; see dvi-vallakya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्लभ|वल्लभः
Vallabha (IE 8-3; EI 12, 26), the king's favourite or a courtier; same as Rājavallabha.<BR> (IE 8-2), same as Vallabharāja; a shortened form of the title Śrī-pṛthivī-vallabha assumed by certain imperial rulers of the Kannaḍa-speaking area.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्लक्य
vallakya, cf. dvi-vallakya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्लव|वल्लवः
Vallava (IE 8-3; 27; LL), official designation; officer in charge of the king's cattle; same as Sanskrit Vallabha, a herdsman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वामनमुद्रा
vāmana-mudrā (SITI), figures of śaṅkha and cakra marked on the boundary stones set up to demarcate the lands of a Viṣṇu temple. Cf. Vāmana-kkal, boundary stone of land granted for religious purposes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वांफय
vāṃphaya, cf. niddhi-vāṃphaya-sahita (EI 12), wrong reading of nidhi-nikṣepa-sahita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंशधर|वंशधरः
vaṃśadhara (EI 24), a palanquin-bearer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंशकर|वंशकरः
Vaṃśakara (LL), a bamboo-worker.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंशावली
Vaṃś-āvalī (IA 30), a genealogical list; called kula-pañjī or kula-pañjikā in Bengal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वांशिक|वांशिकः
Vāṃśika (EI 33), a flute-player.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वंश्य|वंश्यः
vaṃśya, same as dhvaṃśī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वन|वनं
vana, a source of income. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 109-10. Cf. nāga-vana (IE 8-4), an elephant-forest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनचर|वनचरः
vanacara (EI 12), an animal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनधि
vanadhi (IE 7-1-2), used in the sense of vāridhi to indicate ‘four.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=361" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनदुर्ग
vana-durga (ASLV), fort built in the midst of forests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणजारक
Vaṇajāraka, also spelt Vaṇijāraka (EI 11), same as the Vanjārī of Rājasthān, whose hereditary calling is to carry grains on pack-bullocks; cf. Vaṇijjāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वन्दापना
vandāpanā (IE 8-5; EI 12, 33), Od̤iyā; presents to be made on meeting the king or landlord; same as Persian nazrāna; cf. vijaya-vandāpanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वङ्गाली
Vaṅgālī, see Bengali which is its Anglicised spelling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाणिज|वाणिजः
Vāṇija, Vāṇijaka (EI 15; LL), a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिज्जारक
Vaṇijjāraka (BL), probably, merchants or traders of caravans; cf. Vaṇajāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्
Vaṇik (IE 8-3; BL), merchant or a member of the merchantile community.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्पथ|वणिक्पथः
vaṇik-patha, ‘trade-route’; a revenue term. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 79-80.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्स्थान
vaṇik-sthāna (EI 23), an association of merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिक्सुवर्णकार
Vaṇik-suvarṇakāra (BL), probably, ‘one who is a banker and a goldsmith’; cf. the Suvarṇa-vaṇik community of Bengal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिङ्कोट्ट
vaṇiṅ-koṭṭa (CII 4), ‘the traders’ fortress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणिङ्नगर
Vaṇiṅ-nagara (CII 4), ‘a town of merchants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वणित
vaṇita (IE 8-4; SITI), Kannaḍa; same as val̤ita; a small territorial unit like a Parganā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वञ्जुली
vañjulī (IA 26), the twelfth tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वन्निआ
vanniā (IE 8-8), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit varṇikā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वण्टक|वंटक|वंटकः|वण्टकः
vaṇṭaka (EI 9, 13), a share.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वण्ट्य
vaṇṭya (EI 12), a district; cf. věṇṭhě, věṇṭhěya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाप|वापः
vāpa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 310, note 4), explained as a handcast or handful; but really, the same as vapa, sowing [seed grains appa ently by handcast].<BR> (EI 15), cf. kulyavāpa (area requiring one kulya measure of seeds to be sown by handcast); see vāpa-gatyā, etc.<BR> (EI 3), a land measure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वापगत्या
vāpa-gatyā, cf. vauge (EI 10), grain sown broadcast.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वापी
vāpī (EI 13), step-well; an irrigation well; same as vāpikā.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, p. 46, note 8), a well with a flight of stairs; cf. kūpa which is an ordinary well.<BR> (EI 22), a reservoir of water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वापिका
vāpikā (CII 3), a step-well, an irrigation well; same as vāpī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वप्पक
vappaka (EI 23), a land measure. Same as vapyaka, vāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वप्यक
vapyaka (EI 3), a land measure; same as vappaka, vāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=362" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार|वारं|वारः
vāra (BL), a board of administrators [formed by the śreṣṭhins, sārthavāhas and others].<BR> (IA 16), the solar day.<BR> (SITI), method of reciting the Vedas.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 17, note 1), probably, a week.<BR> (EI 30; SITI), a share of the produce.<BR> (EI 24), a multitude. Cf. also vāra-Nāka-Lokta-Gāñīk-ādīnāṃ, ‘belonging to Nāka, Lokta and Gāñīka collectively’ (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, pp. 202, 204).<BR> (CII 1) cf. vārataḥ, ‘in consequence of an occasion.’<BR> (EI 23), same as vāra-goṣṭhī; a committee; cf. vāra-pra-mukha. Vāra is the same as Tamil vāriyam.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘seven’.<BR> Cf. bāre (Chamba), ‘during or in the time of’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरबलीवर्द
vara-balīvarda (EI 12, 33), tax on choice bullocks for bull-fights; cf. valadī, yamalikambali, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरदमुद्रा
varada-mudrā (HA), the gift-bestowing attitude of the right hand with palm outwards and fingers pointing downwards.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारगोष्ठी
vāra-goṣṭhī (EI 5, 23), a committee's assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरग्राम
vara-grāma (SITI), village given as a gift to a temple or maṭha or a Brāhmaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारगृह
vāra-gṛha (EI 19), outside houses; cf. Sanskrit bahir-gṛha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराह|वराहः
varāha (IE 8-8; EI 25; SITI; SII 1), also called hūn or hon; name of a gold coin called pagoda or ‘star pagoda’ in English; Cf. doḍḍa-varāha (EI 20), varāha-paṇam (SITI), varāhanpul̤l̤i-kul̤igai (SITI), parumul̤ai-varāhan (SITI); etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहगद्याण
varāha-gadyāṇa (EI 8, 27), same as varāha or gadyāṇa; i. e. a pagoda.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहकीयविंशोपक
varāhakīya-viṃśopaka (EI 1), name of a coin which was one-twentieth of a varāha in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहमुद्रा
varāha-mudrā, cf. varāha-muddirai (SITI), the seal or emblem bearing the figure of a boar, being the crest of certain kings like those of Vijayanagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराक|वराकः
varāka (CII 1), distressed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारकृत
Vārakṛta (EI 23), official designation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरण|वरणं|वरणः
varaṇa (SITI), the selection or election of a person to a committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरण्डिकावृत
varaṇḍikā-vṛta (LP), ‘surrounded by a verandah’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारप्रमुख
Vāra-pramukha (EI 5), the head of a committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=363" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारसिद्धि
vāra-siddhi, cf. a-vāra-siddhika (EI 8-5); probably refers to the supply of unpaid labour by the villagers in turn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरटका
varaṭakā (EI 1), ‘cowrie-shell used as a coin’; same as varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराटिका
varāṭikā, ‘a cowrie-shell used as a coin’; money. See Gaurī-varāṭikā, varaṭakā, barāḍ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरवझे
varavajhe (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIV, p. 103, text line 12), doubtful name of a tax; same as vara-balīvarda, baladī, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरयात्रा
vara-yātrā (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, the procession of a bride-groom to the bride's place for marriage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्धकि|वर्द्धकिः|वर्धकिः
Vardhaki (LL), a carpenter; cf. Śaila-vardhaki, a mason or sculptor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्धमान|वर्द्धमानः|वर्धमानः
vardhamāna (LP), ‘when cut down.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्धि|वार्द्धिः|वार्धिः
vārdhi (EI 25), ‘seven’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्ग|वर्गः|वर्ग्ग
varga (CII 1), a group or cadre of officers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्गुलिक
Vārgulika (IE 8-3; EI 28; BL), same as Od̤iyā Bāguli, Vāguli; the bearer of the king's betel-box. Cf. Veṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरि
vari (SITI), Tamil; tax; revenue register; order of the king and his officers fixing the revenue. Cf. vari-ppotta-gam, tax register; an officer maintaining the same; also Vari-ppottaga-nāyakam, the head office of the revenue accounts; the chief officer of the same office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिधि|वारिधिः
vāridhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिग
Vāriga (EI 33), corruption of Vārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिगृहकरण
vāri-gṛha-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); explained as ‘the department of water works’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिक
Vārika (IE 8-8; EI 30, 32), a class of officials; the priest or superintendent of a temple like a Pāṇḍā of modern times; cf. Deva-vārika (EI 27), superintendent of a temple; also cf. Tamil Vāriyan (SITI), a supervisor.<BR> Cf. Mahāgandhakuṭī-vārika (LL), ‘superintendent of the great gandhakūṭī (q. v.).’ The official designation Pāṭvāri seems to be derived from Paṭṭavārika.<BR> Cf. Tamil vāriyaṃ (SITI), an executive committee; appointment as a member of that body; an office of supervision^1; cf. śrībhaṇḍāra-vāriyam (EI 33). See SII, Vol. III, p. 151, note.<BR> Cf. bārika (EI 5, 19), a village official; one entrusted with putting an official seal or stamp to a document; cf. bārika-jana-hasta.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारिनिधि|वारिनिधिः
vārinidhi (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=364" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्कर|वर्करः
varkara (IA 19), a goat; cf. botkaṭa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्ण|वर्णं|वर्णः|वर्ण्ण
varṇa (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR> (Select Inscriptions, p. 187, text line 6), same as varṇanā, a description or list.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्णन|वर्णनं
varṇana (Select Inscriptions, p. 202), a written order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्णिका
varṇikā (IE 8-8; EI 30), same a Prakrit vanniā, a sample; sometimes, a small measure of capacity (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 302, verse 69).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्ष|वर्षं|वर्षः
varṣa (CII 3, 4; IA 17), a year; used for saṃvatsara or its abbreviations.<BR> (EI 23), the rainy season.<BR> Cf. varṣe (IA 19), used in the dates after the quotation of saṃvat; sometimes abbreviated to va. Cf. samaye used in the same sense.<BR> Cf. Tamil varuṣa-kāṇikkai (SITI), annual presents.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘nine’; cf. the nine divisions of Jambu-dvīpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षग्रन्थि
varṣa-granthi (EI 8), an anniversary.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षपर्युषित
varṣa-paryuṣita (IE 8-8; EI 30), probably, ‘camping for the rainy season only’; used in connection with merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षवर्तमानी
varṣa-vartamānī, the annual Durbar (Journ. Or. Inst., Vol. X, p. 15).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्षवृद्धि|वर्षवृद्धिः
varṣa-vṛddhi, probably ‘birthday anniversary’ (JAS, Letters, Vol. XX, p. 206).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्त|वार्त्त|वार्त्तं|वार्त्तः
Vārta, Vārtta (CII 4; IA 14), same as Vṛtti-bhuj, ‘one who enjoys a grant or the share of a grant’; a person in possession of a vṛtti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तमान|वर्तमानः|वर्त्तमान|वर्त्तमानः
vartamāna (HRS), ‘running revenue’, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तमानभविष्यत्
vartamāna-bhaviṣyat (IE 8-3), ‘of the present and future’; used with reference to the officers associated with a gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तना
vartanā (SITI), perquisites due to an office; periodical presents to be offered to an officer of rank by his subordinates and the people. Cf. vartanī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्तनी|वर्त्तनी
vartanī (HRS), transit duties collected by the ferrymen, the superintendent of tolls and the boundary officer, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra. Cf. vartanā.<BR> (IA 18), a district; often found suffixed to the names of districts in the Kaliṅga region.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 174), a road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=365" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वार्तानुकर्षक|वार्त्तानुकर्षक|वार्त्तानुकर्षकः
Vārt-ānukarṣaka (IA 6), official designation of doubtful meaning; probably, a spy; mentioned in the Mahābhārata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्त्मदण्ड
vartma-daṇḍa (IE 8-5), tolls collected on the roads for the passage of articles of merchandise through a village. Cf. Tamil val̤iy-āyam (SITI), ‘tolls on the roadway’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वर्त्मपाल
Vartmapāla (IE 8-3), superintendent of roads or the collector of the vartma-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारुघोटक
vāru-ghoṭaka (LP), a riding horse; cf. Marāṭhī vāru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वारुणी
vāruṇī, cf. mahāmahāvāruṇī, mahāvāruṇī (EI 25); name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसा
Va-sā (PJS), probably, an abbreviation of Vaṇik-sādhu, ‘a merchant’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसद्भोगमर्यादा
vasad-bhoga-maryādā (IA 5), explained as ‘the condition that the gift villages should be enjoyed only by those residing therein’; the custom relating to the enjoyment of the gift land by the donee^1 by residing therein; but see vasad-bhogya-maryādā.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसद्भोग्यमर्यादा
vasad-bhogya-maryādā (EI 24), interpreted as ‘with the tenants’ occupancy rights assured’; same as vasad-bhoga-maryādā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसदि
vasadi (EI 10), Sanskrit vasati; a Jain temple; cf. vasahī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासागारिक
Vāsāgārika (IE 8-3; EI 30), officer in charge of the king's bed-chamber. See Vitān-ādhipa, Śayyāpāla, Śayyāgrāhaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसही
vasahī (HA), Sanskrit vasati; a Jain temple; cf. vasadi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासक|वासकः
vāsaka (EI 3, 14, 23, 30; IA 13), royal residence whence the copper-plate grants were often issued; the camp or capital of a king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासक्षेप
vāsa-kṣepa (HA), scattering of powder; also the powder itself.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्
Vāśal (ASLV), same as Vāśal-kāriyam; chief guard of the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्कारियम्
Vāśal-kāriyam (ASLV), also called Vāśal; chief guard of the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्पणम्
vāśal-paṇam (SII 1), the door-money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासनिका
vāsanikā (EI 23), a dwelling.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसन्तगरुवु
vasantagaruvu (ASLV), a rest house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसन्तमण्डप
vasanta-maṇḍapa (SITI), maṇḍapa in the midst of a pleasure garden where the spring-festival of a deity is celebrated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसन्तोत्सव|वसंतोत्सव|वसन्तोत्सवः
vasant-otsava (BL), spring festival.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासापक
Vāsāpaka (EI 6, 12; CII 4; IA 12, 13), explained as ‘officials whose duty was to assign places of residence to strangers’; also spelt Vāsāvaka; cf. also the tax called vāsāvakī (EI 33). Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. XIII, p. 69, note 11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=366" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासावक
Vāsāvaka (CII 4), same as Vāsāpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसावकी
vasāvakī (EI 33), name of a tax; cf. the official designation Vāsāpaka or Vāsāvaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसति|वसतिः
vasati, modified to basadi (EI 10), basahi (HA), pasti, basti (SITI), etc.; a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसतिदण्ड
vasati-daṇḍa (EI 25), obligation of the villagers to supply food to the royal officers camping in their village; explained by some as ‘the tax for the lodging of touring royal officers’ (CII 4); but probably refers to an obligation and not a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासेलकुटुंबिक
Vāsela-kuṭuṃbika (LP), resident farmers; cf. Gujarātī Vasṇārā-kaṇbī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तव्य|वास्तव्यः
Vāstavya (EI 16), a community of the Kāyasthas.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 172, note 3), rarely also called sāmānya; ‘resident’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तु
vāstu (EI 15, 32), homestead land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुभूमि
vāstu-bhūmi (IE 8-1), homestead land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुक|वास्तुकं
vāstuka, a building site. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., pp. 97-98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुकृत्य
vāstu-kṛtya (SITI), building work.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुपरिवार
vāstu-parivāra (SITI), vacant site attached to a house.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वस्तुप्राभृतक
vastu-prābhṛtaka, cf. vastu-prābhṛtakena (LP), ‘in exchange for a present’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसु|वसुः
vasu (IE 7-1-2; EI 15), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वासु|वासुः
vāsu (EI 11), a ward.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसुधा
vasudhā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसुन्धरा|वसुंधरा
vasundharā (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वसुपत्रपद्म
vasu-patra-padma (IA 9), eight-petalled lotus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाल|वालः
vāta (IE 8-5; EI 15; CII 3), cf. sa-bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc.; probably, storms (cf. udvāta; also called āvāta.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातादेय
vāt-ādeya (EI 32), ‘income resulting from storms’; same as vāta-pratyāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटक|वाटकः
vāṭaka (LL), a garden.<BR> (IE 8-4; EI 15; IA 7), corrupt form of pāṭaka; ‘part of a village’; often suffixed to names of localities.<BR> Cf. the second component in Talla-vāṭaka, meaning modern vāḍa, spelt in English as wara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वटक|वटकः
vaṭaka, same as tolaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातप्रत्याय
vāta-pratyāya (EI 32; CII 4), explained by some as ‘octroi duty’, but actually, ‘income resulting from storms’; same as vāt-ādeya. See bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=367" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वति|वतिः
va-ti (IE 8-1), contraction of vadya-pakṣa-tithi, though va may be a mistake for ba (bahula).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटि
vāṭi, vāṭī (IE 8-6; EI 28, 30), also called vāṭikā (q. v.); land measure equal to twenty māṇas in Orissa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटी
vā-ṭī, abbreviation of vāstu-ṭīkara, ‘a mound containing land suitable for building houses.’ See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 56.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाटिका
vāṭikā (EI 15; SITI), same as nilam or vel̤i, defined in the Mayamata as 5120 square daṇḍas, the length of the daṇḍa being 4 cubits; 4. 48 acres.<BR> (EI 30), a land measure equal to twenty māṇas in Orissa; same as vāṭi, vāṭī; equal to 20 acres.<BR> (EI 27), a hamlet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातोत्तर
vāt-ottara (IE 8-5), ‘resulting from storms’; cf. vāt-ādeya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टग्राम
vaṭṭa-grāma (EI 24), subsidiary village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टम्
vaṭṭam (SITI), money-changer's commission; trade discount.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टे
Vaṭṭel̤̣uttu, name of a alphabet prevalent in medieval times in the southern part of the Tamil-speaking area and the land to its west.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाव
vāva (IE 8-2), one's uncle or a relation of one's father's generation; cf. vāva-pād-ānudhyāta, ‘meditating on (or, favoured by) the feet of the uncle (or a relation of one's father's generation).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाय्क्केल्वि
Vāy-kkel̤vi, Vāy-kkel̤viyār (SITI), an officer who received the king's oral orders; an officer in attendance on the king, acting as the intermediary between the king and his subjects; the king's order. Cf. Ājñapti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वायु|वायुः
vāyu (IE 7-1-2), ‘fortynine’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेद|वेदः
veda (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’ (the four Vedas being Ṛk, Yajus, Sāman and Atharvan); rarely used to indicate ‘three’ (cf. trayī) in late records (IE 7-1-2; IA 9).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदमठ
veda-maṭha (ASLV), school for teaching the Vedas. There was such a school at Kāñcīpuram. Cf. śālā, khaṇḍikā, Ṛgveda-khaṇḍikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदपारायण
Veda-pārāyaṇa (IA 12), priest who repeats the Veda at the Rāmeśvaram temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदवेयक
vedaveyaka (CII 1), Prakrit; see vaidarveyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदवृत्ति
veda-vṛtti (SITI), tax-free land set apart for meeting the expenses of reciting, the Vedas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदि|वेदिः
vedi (EI 32), a seat; also a raised platform (cf. vedikā). [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-369" target="_blank">Page-369+ 40</a>] See JBRS, Vol. XXXIX, Parts 1-2, pp. 43-44, 47; Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 192.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=368" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेदिका
vedikā (LL), a rail; also, a raised platform (cf. vedi). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 192.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेग्गडे
Věggaḍě (IE 8-3), same as Věrgaḍě, Pěggaḍě, Pěrgaḍě, Hěggaḍě, etc. (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलादुर्गपाल
Velā-durga-pāla (SITI), a port officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलैक्कारर्
Vel̤ai-kkārar (SITI), Tamil; trusted warriors even prepared to lay down their lives in the service of their master.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलाकुल
velākula, velākūla (IE 8-4; EI 31; LP), a harbour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलाकुलकरण
velākula-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP); the harbour department.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलापुर
velāpura, cf. velāura (IA 10, 14), a harbour; same as velākūla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलावित्त|वेलावित्तः
Velāvitta (HD), meaning uncertain. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, V. 226; VI. 73, 106, 126. Cf. Pīṭhikāvitta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलि
věl̤i (IE 8-6; EI 25), Tamil; a big land measure. See vāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिचेनु
věli-cenu (CITD), Telugu; usually, a field on a high level depending on rain water.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिपोलमु
věli-pŏlamu (CITD), Telugu; see veli-volamu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिवोलमु
věli-vŏlamu (CITD), Telugu; also called veli-polamu; similar to veli-cenu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेल्लि|वेल्लिः
vel̤l̤i (EI 15), name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेना
venā (EI 31), a kind of grass.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेणी
veṇī (IA 17), a stream or river.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेङ्कटविलासमण्टप
veṅkaṭa-vilāsa-maṇṭapa (ASLV), hall in which the royal council met at Vijayanagara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेण्ठे
věṇṭhě (EI 16; ASLV), same as viṣaya, nirvṛtti, koṭṭam, etc.; an administrative division; also called věṇṭhěya, vaṇṭya, věṭha, věṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेण्ठेय
věṇṭhěya (EI 16), a sub-division or district; same as věṇṭhě.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेर्गडे
Věrgaḍě (IE 8-3), Kannaḍa; same as Věggaḍě, Pěrgaḍě, Hěggaḍě, etc.; also Sanskrit Adhyakṣa, Adhikārin (a superintendent or governor).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेश्य|वेश्यं
veśya (CII 4), explained as ‘situated in … ’ Cf. prāveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेट
věṭa (IE 8-4), same as věṇṭhě, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेटकिल
Veṭakila (IE 8-3); HD), probably ‘the bearer of vīṭikā (betel bīd̤ā)’. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 128. Cf. Vārgulika; also Paṭṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेतन|वेतनं
vetana, vetanā (SITI), wages (used along with veṭṭi, i. e. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-370" target="_blank">Page-370+ 40</a>] Sanskrit viṣṭi or unpaid labour); probably wages for the labourers in the public works of the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=369" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेठ
věṭha (IE 8-4), Kannaḍa; same as věṇṭhě, věṭa, etc.; a small territorial unit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेत्रिक
Vetrika (EI 9; CII 4), explained by some as ‘the chamberlain’; cf. Yāṣṭika, Piśuna-vetrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वि|विः
vi (CITD), abbreviation of Telugu vinnapamulu, representation or saying. It may stand for visālu (visā or vīsa) also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभाग|विभागः
vibhāga (HRS), king's share of the output of mines; as suggested by the Arthaśāstra, rent from mines and from the private manufacturers of salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभव|विभवः
vibhava (IA 14), used in the sense of nirvāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभेद|विभेदः
vibheda (IE 8-4), subdivision of a khaṇḍa of Bhārata or Bhārata-varsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभोग
vibhoga (EI 16), holy ashes; same as vibhūti (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभूति|विभूतिः
vibhūti (IA 12), holy ashes; same as vibhoga.<BR> (SITI), also called vibhūti-kāṇikkai in Tamil inscriptions; originally, voluntary contribution to a temple by the devotees while receiving the sacred ashes; later, it was collected as a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विचारकर्तृ|विचारकर्त्तृ
Vicārakartṛ, (EI 8), a supervisor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विचित्रकवित्व
vicitra-kavitva (CITD), probably, a class of poetry like citra-kavitva, abounding in all kinds of highly artificial verses displaying the pedantry and verbal jugglery of the composer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडालपदक|विडालपदकं
viḍālapadaka, same as vivarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विध|विधः
vidha (SITI), variety, kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विधारणा
vidhāraṇā (EI 1), same as paripanthanā, ‘creating obstacles’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विधिपत्र
vidhi-patra (LP), a judgement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विधु|विधुः
vidhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडूरसार
viḍūra-sāra (EI 3), same as vaiḍūrya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्वज्जन
vidvaj-jana (SITI), a body of learned men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्या
vidyā (CII 4), the right knowledge.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘fourteen’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याभोग
vidyā-bhoga (EI 18), same as vidy-ānubhoga and vidyā-dhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याचारण
vidyā-cāraṇa, see cāraṇa (EI 3).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याधन|विद्याधनं
vidyā-dhana (HRS), explained as land assigned as a reward for learning; same as vidyā-bhoga and vidy-ānubhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याधरतोरण
vidyādhara-toraṇa (SII 2), an ornamental arch probably depicting Vidyādharas; cf. makara-toraṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=370" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्याधिकारिन्
Vidy-ādhikārin (EI 11, 25; HD), officer in charge of a school or of schools; the director of education. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 314; explained as ‘the chief court Pandit’ (Sarma, Reḍḍi Kingdoms, pp. 466-67).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्यानुभोग
vidy-ānubhoga (SITI), an endowment of land to a school for the encouragement of learning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्यार्थिन्
Vidyārthin (SITI), a student.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विद्यास्थान
vidyā-sthāna (EI 2; SII 2; SITI), an educational institution for higher studies; a college.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहद्रम्मविसोवक
vigrahadramma-visovaka (EI 1), name of a coin; the latter part of the name (i. e. visovaka = viṃśopaka) suggests that it was one-twentieth of the vigraha-dramma in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालद्रम्म
vigrahapāla-dramma (EI 1), name of a coin; same as vigrahapāla-satka-dramma, vigrahapālīya-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालसत्कद्रम्म
vigrahapāla-satka-dramma (EI 1), see vigrahapālīya-dramma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालीयद्रम्म
vigrahapālīya-dramma (EI 1; CII 4), name of a coin apparently so called after a king named Vigrahapāla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहतुङ्गीयद्रम्म
vigrahatuṅgīya-dramma (EI 1; CII 4), name of a coin apparently so called after a king named Vigrahatuṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहार|विहारः
vihāra (EI 22, 25; CII 3, 4; BL), a Buddhist or Jain monastery or temple or convent (EI 35).<BR> (HA), wandering of a Jain monk; also a Jain temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारकारक
Vihārakāraka, cf. Prakrit Viharakarahvaa (CII 2-1), ‘one who builds a monastery’; same as Vihārasvāmin; explained by some as ‘the superintendent of monastery’ (ML).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहरमाणजिन
Viharamāṇa-Jina (HA), a Jina at present living in other kṣetras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारपाल
Vihārapāla, ‘the manager of a monastery’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 345).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारस्वामिन्
Vihārasvāmin (EI 8, 33; CII 3; BL; LL), ‘the master of a monastery’; the builder or owner of a monastery. Cf. Vihāra-kāraka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारस्वामिनी
Vihārasvāminī (CII 3; IA 11), the feminine form of Vihārasvāmin; wife of a Vihārasvāmin or the female owner of a vihāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारयात्रा
vihāra-yātrā (CII 1), a pleasure-tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहारिका
vihārikā (EI 23, 27), derived from vihāra, vihāraka; a small vihāra or monastery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहिंसा
vihiṃsā (CII 1), hurting, injuring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहित|विहितः
vihita (CII 1), established; settled.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=371" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विहृतयति
vihṛtayati, ‘[he] wastes’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 245).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजालयितव्य
vijālayitavya, to be untied (Select Inscriptions, p. 238).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजाटिन्
Vijāṭin (IA 11), cf. Vijāṭi-vidyādhara, ‘a Vidyādhara unwinding his head-dress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजय|विजयः
vijaya, used in Kannaḍa inscriptions in the sense of ‘going in state, going in a triumpal procession, making a state procession, making a state progress through one's dominions’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 223, note 6; Vol. VI, p. 51, note 5).<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 18), Od̤iyā, etc.; used in Od̤iyā inscriptions in the sense of ‘stay’.<BR> (IA 7), cf. vijaya-rājya-saṃvalsara, vijaya-saṃvatsara, vijaya-kaṭaka, vijaya-skandhāvāra, etc. Cf. śrī-vijaya and śrī-vijaya-śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजया
vijayā (IA 26), same as su-di 11 or the eleventh tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयाभिषेक
vijay-ābhiṣeka (SITI), being crowned as a victor; same as vīr-ābhiṣeka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयचन्द्र
vijaya-candra (SII 2), name of an ornament.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयादशमी
vijayā-daśamī (EI 31), Āśvina-sudi 10.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयक
vijayaka (LP), same as vijaya, victory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयकटक
vijaya-kaṭaka (EI 2; LP), ‘the victorious camp’; the royal camp or capital.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयलेख
vijaya-lekha (EI 9), a royal record.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयराजटङ्क
vijayarāja-ṭaṅka (CII 4), name of a coin apparently so called after a ruler named Vijayarāja who was its issuer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयसप्तमी
vijaya-saptamī (EI 3), name of a tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयशासन
vijaya-śāsana (EI 33), any royal record (cf. śāsana); sometimes the same as dharma-vijaya-śāsana (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयशिव
vijaya-śiva, cf. śrī-vijaya-śiva-Mṛgeśavarman, etc. (The Successors of the Sātavāhanas, pp. 261 ff.); an honorific prefixed to royal names. See śrī, vijaya, śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयस्तम्भ
vijaya-stambha (SITI), pillar of victory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयवैजयिक
vijaya-vaijayika, victory; sometimes used as an adjective qualifying the regnal date (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 152, text line 5; cf. ibid., Vol. XXXII, p. 88).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयवन्दापना
vijaya-vandāpanā (IE 8-5; EI 12), Od̤iyā; a levy; presents to be offered to the king or landlord on the occasion of his victorious return from a campaign or for the preparation of a campaign; cf. vandāpanā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयविक्षेप
vijaya-vikṣepa (IA 13), epithet of a place where a king was staying. See vikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=372" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजित|विजितः
vijita (CII 1), dominions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञानिन्
Vijñānin (EI 20, 32), an artisan; same as Śilpin; epithet of an artisan who is usually the engraver of an inscription.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञापना
vijñāpanā (IA 10), also called vijñapti; an application; a request; cf. Kannaḍa binna-vattaḷě = Sanskrit vijñāpana-patra (SII 11-1).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञप्ति|विज्ञप्तिः
Vijñapti (EI 29), official designation. Cf. Ājñapti, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञप्ति|विज्ञप्तिः
vijñapti (SITI), sometimes also spelt vijñāpti; petitioning to the king (cf. vijñāpanā); an officer who brings the petition of the subjects to the king's notice.<BR> (EI 23; SII 2), also called vijñāpya, an application or petition.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञापि
vi-jñāpi (CII 3, etc.), verb used in connection with the making of a grant by the king at the request, or on the advice, of someone who was the real donor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विज्ञाप्य|विज्ञाप्यं
vijñāpya (EI 23), cf. Tamil viṇṇappam (SII 1), a petition; also called vijñapti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विकर|विकरः
vikara, cf. vikara-padāni (LP), a small present, a bonus; cf. Gujarātī pān-sopārī.<BR> (LP), cf. vikara-pada explained as ‘miscellancous expenses’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विकरणपट्टक
vikaraṇa-paṭṭaka (LP), a merket-tax contract.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विक्रमादित्य|विक्रमादित्यः
Vikramāditya (IE 8-2), see āditya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विकृति|विकृतिः
vikṛti (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentythree’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विक्षेप|विक्षेपः
vikṣepa (IA 7, 13), cf. vijaya-vikṣepa used as an epithet of the place whence a royal charter was issued; cf. vijaya-vikṣepāt Bha-rukaccha-vāsakāt; wrongly interpreted as ‘a camp or cantonment’ (IA 17). See also Vaikṣepika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलब्धि
vilabdhi (IE 8-3; EI 30), used in the Rājataraṅgiṇī, probably in the sense of presents offered to the king or the stolen property recovered; explained as ‘an assignment’. See Vailabdhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलहणा
vilahaṇā (LP), probably, an escort; suite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलासिनी
Vilāsinī (EI 33), same as Devadāsī; also called Gaṇikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलेखक
Vilekhaka (EI 22), an engraver. Cf. Ullekhaka, utkṛ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विलोक्
vi-lok, cf. vilokyante (LP), ‘are being searched for’, used in respect of one who is in search of money in times of difficulty.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विमान|विमानं|विमानः
vimāna (SITI), the pinnacle or upper structure over the sanctum of a temple; the central shrine of a temple (SII 3); also called śrī-vimāna (SII 13); same as garbha-gṛha.<BR> (EI 3, 23), a shrine. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-374" target="_blank">Page-374+ 40</a>]<BR> (IA 9), the steeple tower over a shrine; also called stupī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=373" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशतिक|विंशतिकः
viṃśatika, regarded as equal to 20 māṣas (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 52); cf. viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंसतिम
viṃsatima (CII 3), used for viṃśatitama, twentieth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंसोपक
viṃsopaka (EI 1), corrupt form of viṃśopaka, a copper coin which was (1/20) of the standard silver coin in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशोपक
viṃśopaka (IE 8-6, 8-8; EI 29, 30; CII 4), a copper coin which was one-twentieth of the standard silver coin in value; cf. Viśālapriya-viṃśopaka (IE 8-8); Varāhakīya-viṃśopaka (EI 1); Vṛṣa-viṃśopaka (q. v.); a land measure equal to one twentieth of the standard land measure. See vīsa, viṃsopaka, vīsovā, visovaka.<BR> Cf. viśopaka (LP), supposed to be the same as vighā, a measure of land equal to 20 vasas [in Gujarat].<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीणा
vīṇā (ASLV), a musical instrument. Cf. vīṇai-kkāṇi (SITI), right of playing on the vīṇā before the god in a temple during worship.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनमु
vinamu (CITD), Telugu; an unknown weight greater than a cinna or cinnamu, otherwise called sinna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनाश|विनाशः
vināśa (LP), ‘not doing anything at all’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनाशिन्
vināśin, cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-vāsa (IE 8-5), an attendant, or fuel. The villagers were obliged to supply it to the touring officers of the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनष्टराज्य
vinaṣṭa-rājya (IE), same as gata-rājya or atīta-rājya, someone's sovereignty that was a thing of the past.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनय|विनयः
vinaya (IE 8-8; EI 30), fines.<BR> (EI 13), same as indriya-jaya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनयधर
Vinayadhara (LL), Buddhist; one who has learnt the Vinaya texts by heart.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनायक|विनायकः
Vināyaka (LL), a teacher of the vinaya texts; a name of the god Gaṇeśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनायकहोम
Vināyaka-homa (EI 26), a rite; same as Gaṇeśa-homa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विन्दु|विंदु|विन्दुः
vindu (EI 7-1-2), also spelt bindu; ‘cypher’.<BR> (SII 2), a flaw in diamonds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनिबद्धकार
Vinibaddhakāra, see Vinibandhakāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनिबन्धकार
Vinibandhakāra (EI 8), same as Vinibaddhakāra; explained as ‘one who registers [a document]’; really, ‘one who cancels the registration [of a document]’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 202).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनिर्गत
vinirgata (EI 7), cf. Pāṭaliputra-bhaṭṭāgrahāra-vinirgata (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 122, text line 16); ‘hailing from’, or more suitably ‘one whose family hails from’. When a [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-375" target="_blank">Page-375+ 39</a>] locality called Aṭṭamūla is described as vinirgata from Bṛhaddhaṭṭa, it seems to mean that the former was originally a part of the latter (ibid., Vol. XXXIII, p. 151).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=374" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनियोग|विनियोगः
viniyoga (SITI), an employment; use; expenditure.<BR> (EI 24), a tax; cf. Tamil vāśal-viniyogam (SITI), same as vāśal-paṇam; also sabhā-viniyoga (SII 13).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनियुक्त
Viniyukta (HD), an officer probably under the Āyuktaka; same as Viniyuktaka (q. v.), etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 256.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विनियुक्तक
Viniyuktaka (CII 3, 4), an official title meaning a smaller administrative officer serving under a higher officer; an official probably under the Āyuktaka; same as Viniyukta. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, pp. 80, 83.<BR> (IE 8-3), mentioned along with Tadāyuktaka. Cf. Tad-viniyuktaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विप्रविनोदिन्
Vipra-vinodin (SITI), a class of Brāhmaṇas who were adepts in jugglery and magical practices.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीर|वीरं|वीरः
vīra (IE 8-2), sometimes prefixed to the names of kings and even treated as almost an integral part of the name; cf. pratāpa, vīra-pratāpa, etc.<BR> (EI 3), Jain; same as Mahāvīra.<BR> Cf. vīra-kal̤ (SITI), also written vīra-kkal̤, vīra-gal̤; a hero-stone; an inscribed or uninscribed stone pillar raised in honour of a person who died in fighting for a good cause.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरभद्र|वीरभद्रः
Vīrabhadra (SITI), also called Vīramuṣṭi; member of a militant class of temple servants who diligently protected the properties and rights of the temples. Cf. Vīrakośa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीराभिषेक
vīr-ābhiṣeka (EI 18; SITI), ‘anointment as a hero’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरभोग
vīra-bhoga (SITI), land assigned for the maintenance of a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरगल्
vīra-gal̤ (CII 4), also written vīra-kkal̤. See vīra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरक्कल्
vīra-kkal̤ (CII 4), also written vīra-gal̤, a stone pillar raised in memory of heroes. See vīra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरकोश
Vīrakośa, official designation (The Successor of the Sātavāhanas, p. 110, note 2); mentioned along with Hastikośa as an officer related to a district; probably, an officer in charge of the local soldiers or infantry men. Cf. Vīrabhadra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरक्त|विरक्तः
Virakta (SITI), an ascetic; a man free from worldly attachment; a recluse of the Śaiva order.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=375" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरलरिशि
viral-ariśi (ASLV), rice provided for goldsmiths for amputating the last two fingers of the wives of farmers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरमाला
vīra-mālā, cf. vīra-mālai (SITI), a poem in praise of a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरमुष्टि
Vīramuṣṭi (SITI), same as Vīrabhadra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरपट्ट|वीरपट्टः
vīra-paṭṭa (SII 2; SITI), an ornament; a front plate, probably a plate worn on the forehead by distinguished warriors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरपट्टण
vīra-paṭṭaṇa (SITI), also called er̤i-vīra-paṭṭaṇam; a mercantile town inhabited by the er̤i-vīrar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरप्रताप
Vīra-pratāpa (IE 8-2), cf. Vīra and Pratāpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरशासन
vīra-śāsana (SITI), CITD) explained by some as the same as vīrakal̤, ‘a hero stone’, established for commemorating the death of soldiers on the battle-field; a grant made by the king in recognition of the heroic activity of a person; a charter recording the grant of land or other property to a warrior.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरशेष
vīra-śeṣa, cf. vīra-śeṣai (SITI); probably, the provision made for the descendants of dead warriors; sometimes explained as a tax (EI 22). Cf. mṛtyuka-vṛtti, rakta-mānya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरसिंहासन
vīra-siṃhāsana (SII 1), the throne of heroes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरयात्रिक
Vīra-yātrika (IA 17; HD), an official designation; probably, the leader of an expedition; a person taking part in a military expedition. See Vogel, Ant. Ch. St., p. 129.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरूपाक्षपति
Virūpākṣa-pati, cf. Prakrit Virūpakha-pati (EI 20), epithet of the god Mahāsena or Kārttikeya, Virūpākṣa probably being the name of a host of which the god was conceived as the leader.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीस
vīsa (IE 8-8; EI 5), name of a coin (JNSI, Vol. XXVI, pp. 127ff.); cf. lokkiya-vīsa, probably meaning ‘a vīsa minted at Lokkiguṇḍi’; Sanskrit viṃśa, viṃśaka, viṃśatika, or viṃśopaka.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 232, note 6), Telugu-Kannaḍa; (1/16) of a haṇa (paṇa); but (1/20) of the standard coin in value essentially.<BR> (CITD), also called visā, visya, visāmu; Telugu-Kannaḍa; the fraction (1/10); gold equal in weight to one grain of rice; (1/256) of a Hun or Pagoda; 40 palas; a measure of land equal nearly to 2 acres.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसा
visā, also spelt visāmu (CITD), see vīsa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषहरभोग
viṣahara-bhoga (SITI), also called viṣa-vṛtti; land set apart for the support of a poison-doctor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसलप्रियद्रम्म
vīsala-priya-dramma, also called vīsala-prī-dramma; cf. jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya, etc. (A. R. Ep., 1957-58, Nos. B 490-92).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=376" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसंस्थुल
visaṃsthula (LP), agitated, unsteady.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसतिअठूप्रस्थ
visatiaṭhū-prastha (IA 18), a levy; probably viṃśatisatka-prastha, ‘one out of 20 prasthas.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषवृत्ति
viṣa-vṛtti (SITI), same as viṣahara-bhoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषय|विषयः
viṣaya (EI 8-4), a district; often a kingdom or territory; sometimes a viṣaya was included in a maṇḍala; but, in some cases, a maṇḍala was included in a viṣaya; at times maṇḍala and viṣaya were synonymous.<BR> (IE 8-5; EI 30; CII 3, 4; BL; SITI), a district; cf. viṣaya-suṅka (EI 24), the tax of a district; Viṣaya-vyavahārin, officer in the service of a district.<BR> (ASLV), same as nirvṛtti or koṭṭam; an administrative division.<BR> (IE 8-4; CII 4), sometimes used in a wider sense to indicate ‘a country’.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसय
visaya (CITD), same as Telugu visā, visāmu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयभोगिक
Viṣaya-bhogika (EI 28), probably, the ināmdār or ināmdārs of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयभूभुज्
Viṣaya-bhūbhuj (IA 15), explained as ‘a native ruler’ as opposed to a ‘foreign conqueror.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयदान
viṣaya-dāna (HRS), name of a tax (Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 21; Vol. XIV, p. 196), probably, a regional tax or taxes realisable from a particular district; known from Gāhaḍavāla records; cf. viṣayālī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयदानिक
Viṣaya-dānika (EI 7; CII 4), collector of the levy called viṣaya-dāna; or a district officer in charge of gifts or an officer in charge of gift lands in a district; or the collector of the revenue of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयाधिकरण
Viṣay-ādhikaraṇa (EI 23, 31), administrative officer of a district; the district administrator's office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयाधिपति|विषयाधिपतिः
Viṣay-ādhipati, same as Viṣayapati (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 219).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयकरण
Viṣaya-karaṇa (EI 32), probably, the chief scribe at the office of the administrators of a district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयाली
viṣayālī (EI 33), name of a tax; probably the same as viṣaya-dāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयामात्य
Viṣay-āmātya (EI 27, 30), governor of a district; an Amātya in charge of a viṣaya or an Amātya under the Viṣayapati. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 64.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=377" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयण
viṣayaṇa (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयपाल
Viṣayapāla (EI 28), same as Viṣayapati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयपति|विषयपतिः
Viṣayapati (IE 8-3; CII 3, 4; BL; HD), governor of a district called viṣaya; distinguished from Viṣaya-vyāpṛtaka; same as Viṣay-ādhipati. Cf. Ind. Ant., Vol. V, p. 114. See Viṣa-yeśa, Viṣayeśvara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयव्यापृतक
Viṣaya-vyāpṛtaka (IE 8-3), sometimes distinguished from the Viṣayapati; an officer associated with the administration of a district (cf. Viṣaya-vyavahārin).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयव्यवहारिन्
Viṣaya-vyavahārin (IE 8-3), an administrative officer in a district or a member of the district council. Cf. Viṣaya-vya-vahārin, Viṣayika, Viṣayin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयेश
Viṣayeśa (HD), same as Viṣayapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयेश्वर
Viṣayeśvara (EI 26), same as Viṣayapati, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयिक
Viṣayika (EI 24), same as Viṣaya-vyavahārin; cf. Viṣayin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयिकाधिकारिक
Viṣayik-ādhikārika (EI 32), taken to be a single official designation; probably Viṣayika and Ādhikārika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषयिन्
Viṣayin (EI 24, 32), possibly, the same as Viṣaya-vyava-hārin; cf. Viṣayika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसेणिम
viseṇima, viseṇimā (CII 4), a tax, also called viseṇim-ādāya (EI 21).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशेषादाय
viśeṣ-ādāya (SITI), also called viśeṣ-āya; a special group of taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशेषाय
viśeṣ-āya (SITI), same as viśeṣ-ādāya (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशिख|विशिखः
viśikha (BL), name of a kind of building.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशीर्ण|विशीर्णः
viśīrṇa, wearing out, worn out part of a building; cf. bhagna-viśīrṇa-samāracana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशिष
Viśiṣa (IE 8-3; EI 1, 30), probably, the governor or commander of a fort; a word of uncertain derivation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुबाहु
viṣṇu-bāhu, see hari-bāhu (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुगृह|विष्णुगृहं
viṣṇu-gṛha (SITI), a Viṣṇu temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुपद|विष्णुपदं
viṣṇu-pada (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुतिथि|विष्णुतिथिः
viṣṇu-tithi (IA 19), same as Jyaiṣṭha-sudi 11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्णुश्राध
viṣṇu-śrādha (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 37), an expression of doubtful meaning.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसोवा
vīsovā (CII 4), name of a coin; a land measure; same as viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसोवक
visovaka (EI 1), corrupt form of viṃśopaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्टप|विष्टपं|विष्टपः
viṣṭapa (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विस्तरण
vistaraṇa (EI 1), meaning doubtful.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=378" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्टि|विष्टिः
viṣṭi (IE 8-5; CII 4; HRS), labour which the villagers were obliged to provide to the king or landlord on occasions; unpaid labour; forced labour.<BR> Cf. veṭṭi (SITI), unpaid labour for public works in the village without time or other limits; usually mentioned along with vetana as veṭṭi-vetanai. Cf. veṭṭi-ccor̤u, the obligation of feeding veṭṭi labourers free of cost; also cf. Tamil veṭṭi-pāṭṭam (EI 24), explained as ‘a kind of tax’; tax in lieu of viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशुद्धि|विशुद्धिः
viśuddhi, cf. viśuddhiṃ yāvat (LP), ‘till the account is clear’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषुव|विषुवं
viṣuva (CII 4; SII 1), the autumnal or vernal equinox; also called viṣuvat (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विषुवत्|विषुवन्त्
viṣuvat (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR> Cf. viṣuva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्व|विश्वं|विश्वः
viśva (IE 7-1-2), same as viśvedevāḥ, ‘thirteen.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वचक्र|विश्वचक्रं
viśvacakra (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वेदेवाः
viśvedevāḥ (IE 7-1-2), ‘thirteen’; same as viśva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विष्वग्देवा
viṣvag-devā (LL), Jain; a quadruple^1 image.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वकर्मन्|विश्वकर्म्मन्
Viśvakarman (LL), an architect.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वाल
Viśvāla (EI 31), Od̤iyā; a village watchman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वास|विश्वासः
Viśvāsa (EI 24), official designation; same as Vaiśvāsika; cf. the titles Viśvāsa-Khāna, Viśvāsa-rāya, etc., conferred by the Muslim rulers especially in the Bengal region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वासन|विश्वासनं
viśvāsana (CII 1), ‘being inspired with faith’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वसत्ता
viśva-sattā (IA 14), wrong Sanskritisation of Prakrit vasa-sata (Sanskrit varṣa-śata); translated as ‘universal rule’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 241, note 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वासिक
Viśvāsika (EI 24), same as Vaiśvāsika (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विश्वविश्वोपक
Viśvaviśvopaka (IA 19), Jain; explained as ‘one whose body and soul exhibit marks of an ācārya’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वितान|वितानं|वितानः
vitāna (SII 13), probably, a canopy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वितानाधिप
Vitān-ādhipa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 325, note 3), supposed to be ‘an officer in charge of the king's bed-chamber’. Cf. Vāsāgārika, Śayyāpāla, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विटप|विटपः
viṭapa (IE 8-5), a bush; used in sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa; a branch. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 183.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विठविगार
viṭha-vigāra (Chamba), unpaid labour; from Sanskrit viṣṭi and Persian begār.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीथि|वीथिः
vīthi, vīthī (SII 1), a street.<BR> (EI 24, 30; CII 4), a shop; a stall or shop in a market. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-380" target="_blank">Page-380+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 21, 23, 29, 30), a territorial unit; the subdivision of a district.<BR> (IE 8-4), sometimes a subdivision forming part of a maṇḍala, but sometimes a district forming part of a bhukti or province.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=379" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीथीमहत्तर
Vīthī-mahattara (HD), headman of the territorial unit called vīthī. Cf. IHQ, Vol. XIX, pp. 16, 21.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीथ्यधिकरण
vīthy-adhikaraṇa (EI 31), administrative office of a subdivision called vīthī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वित्तबन्ध
vitta-bandha (CII 4), mortgage^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विट्टोल्लकर
viṭṭolla-kara (HRS), known from Maitraka records; explained as the contribution in forced labour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाह|विवाहः
Vivāha (EI 12), ‘one whose vehicle is the bird’; i. e. Viṣṇu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाह|विवाहः
vivāha (CII 1), marriage of a daughter; cf. āvāha which means the marriage of a son.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाहकर
vivāha-kara, cf. Tamil kaṇṇāla-kkāṇan (EI 28), the marriage fee; cf. vivāha-ppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाहपण
vivāha-paṇa, cf. vivāha-ppaṇam (SITI), same as kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam; a tax on marriage.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवीत|विवीतः
vivīta (HRS), royal dues collected by the superintendent of pastures, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवीताध्यक्ष|विवीताध्यक्षः
Vivīt-ādhyakṣa (EI 28), known from the Arthaśāstra; officer in charge of the pasture land. Cf. Vrajabhūmika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वियत्|वियन्त्
viyat (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोदा
vodā (IE 8-5; EI 29), a kind of levy in Od̤iyā records; same as Od̤iyā vadāi, ‘the obligation of offering uncooked food.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोडी
voḍī, voḍrī (EI 23), (1/4) paṇa; 20 cowrie-shells; cf. kapardaka-voḍī, ‘voḍī counted in cowrie-shells’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोलापन
volāpana, see volāpika, vulāvi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोलापिक
Volāpika (LP), an officer in charge of collecting the tax called volāpana or vulāvī. It is supposed that a Volāpaka or the men under him accompanied the merchants in their journey for the safety of their goods and the volāpana tax was collected from the merchants for safeguarding their goods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोट
voṭa, cf. boṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रज|व्रजं|व्रजः
vraja, see Vraja-bhūmika. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 110.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रजभूमि
vraja-bhūmi (IE 8-4), grazing land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रजभूमिक
Vrajabhūmika (CII 1; EI 2; HD), Prakrit Vacabhūmika; superintendent of cowpens; officer in charge of the royal cattle and pasture lands. Cf. Vivīt-ādhyakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=380" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रत|व्रतं|व्रतः
vrata (CITD), religious vow; a self-imposed task; a religious act of devotion or austerity; vowed observance; a vow in general. There are many vratas mentioned in the different Purāṇas. But new vratas crop up in different parts of the country.<BR> (EI 4), five in number.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्रीहिकर
vrīhi-kara, cf. Tamil arisi-kkāṇam (SITI), a levy for husking paddy into rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्ध|वृद्धं|वृद्धः
vṛddha (LP), participle of vṛdh, ‘to cut’.<BR> Cf. Vṛddha-Gaṇeśa (IA 19), ‘the senior Gaṇeśa’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धधानुष्क
Vṛddha-dhānuṣka (IE 8-3), senior archer; the chief archer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धराज|वृद्धराजः
Vṛddharāja (EI 3; LL), ‘prosperous king’; title of a pious king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धि|वृद्धिः
vṛddhi (EI 28), a super tax or the interest on arrears of taxes; also interest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृद्धिकुक्कुट
vṛddhi-kukkuṭa (CII 1), Prakrit vadhi-kukuṭa; a cock that has been caponed; also Sanskritised as vadhri-kukkuṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
vṛndāvana, see bṛndāvana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृषतापशासन
vṛṣatāpa-śāsana (EI 13), same as tāmra-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृषविंशोपक
vṛṣa-viṃśopaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 39), name of a coin (probably bearing the figure of a bull); cf. viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृत्ति|वृत्तिः
vṛtti (SITI), means; livelihood, occupation; grant of land for one's livelihood.<BR> (SII 3), land granted for service.<BR> (EI 17, 31; CITD), share; share in a village granted to a Brāhmaṇa as a free gift.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वु
Vud̤hā-leṅkā (EI 28), Od̤iyā; official designation; cf. Leṅkā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुलापिका
vulāpikā (LP), tax for the maintenance of the camp-followers; cf. Gujarātī val̤āmaṇ vulāyiyā; also volāpika, vulā-viyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुलावी
vulāvī (LP), same as volāpana; a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुलाविया
Vulāviyā (LP), a camp-follower; cf. Gujarātī Vul̤āviyā. See vulāpikā and Volāpika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वुंवक
vuṃvaka (EI 14), name of a measure.<BR> Cf. ‘rūpakas to be levied on each vuṃvaka of the distillers’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 309).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्य|व्यः
Vya (PJS), abbreviation of Vyavahārin, especially in medieval Jain inscriptions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्या
Vyā (PJS), abbreviation of Vyāpārin (merchant) or Vyāsa (exponent or reciter of epic and Puranic texts) especially in medieval Jain inscriptions. Cf. vyā-bhū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याभू
vyā-bhū (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vyāmiśra-bhūmi; ‘mixed [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-382" target="_blank">Page-382+ 40</a>] land’; land containing different categories such as cultivable, fallow, homestead, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=381" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याचरण
vyācaraṇa (EI 15), meaning uncertain; probably, commerce.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याघ्रचर्मन्|व्याघ्रचर्म्मन्
vyāghra-carman (IE 8-5; EI 12, 28), tiger's skin [which was the king's monopoly]; tax probably payable by hunters in tiger's skin; refers to the right to keep tiger's skins without surrendering them to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याज|व्याजः
vyāja, vyājaka (LP), interest; cf. dvika-śata-vyājena, ‘at 2 per cent interest’. See vyājī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याजी
vyājī (HRS), as suggested by the Arthaśāstra, (1) compensation fee levied upon the sale of liquors, royal merchandise, mining products, salt and sugar; (2) charge paid for minting coins; (3) subsidiary charge over and above the regular fines. See vyāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याकरणदानमण्डप
vyākaraṇa-dāna-maṇḍapa (SITI), hall in the Śiva temple at Tiruvor̤r̤iyūr, where Sanskrit grammar is taught with the belief that the Māheśvara-sūtras, on which Sanskrit grammar is founded, were composed by the god Śiva.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याख्यावृत्ति
vyākhyā-vṛtti (SITI), land set apart to meet the expenses of expounding the Purāṇas and other śāstras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यक्त|व्यक्तः
vyakta (CII 1), experienced.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यामिश्रभूमि
vyāmiśra-bhūmi (IE 8-1), an area consisting of different kinds of land such as cultivated land, homestead land, fallow land, etc. See vyā-bhū.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यञ्जन|व्यंजन|व्यंजनं|व्यञ्जनं
vyañjana, cf. věñjanam, viñjanam (SITI), condiment; vegetable relish; condiments and curry in food offerings; cf. věñjana-bhaṇḍāram.<BR> (CII 1), a letter or an implication.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Vyantara, see Yakṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापादित|व्यापादितः
vyāpādita (LP), ‘much harassed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापार|व्यापारः
vyāpāra (SII 1), a trade.<BR> (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXVI, p. 20), administration. Cf. mudrā-vyāpāra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापारकरण
vyāpāra-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), the department of commerce.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापारिन्
Vyāpārin (EI 22; SII 1), a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यापृत|व्यापृतः
Vyāpṛta (IE 8-3; EI 6), cf. Vāpata (EI 9), a governor; a superintendent; cf. also official designations like Hasty-aśva-naubala-vyāpṛta or ˚vyāpṛtaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यास|व्यासः
Vyāsa (EI 11; PJS), a reciter or exponent; a Brāhmaṇa [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-383" target="_blank">Page-383+ 40</a>] who recites or expounds the epics and Purāṇas in public. Cf. Paurāṇika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=382" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यसन|व्यसनं
vyasana (CII 1), misfortune.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्याषेध
vyāṣedha (LP), vyāṣedhaḥ kāritaḥ or niṣedhaḥ kāritaḥ, ‘proved the contrary^1 [in the court that it was his own land and not ḍohalikā land’]; vahamāna-bhūmi-vyāṣedha, ‘no one should stop him when he is ploughing his own piece of land’.<BR> (LP), seizure; confiscation as government property.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यतिकर|व्यतिकरः
vyatikara (LP), ‘in connection with’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यतीपात|व्यतीपातः
vyatīpāta (IA 19), used in relation to eclipses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यव
Vyava (LP), abbreviation of Vyavahārika in the sense of a dealer, a money-lender, a merchant.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवच्छिन्न|व्यवच्छिन्नं|व्यवछिन्न
vyavacchinna, fixed (Select Inscriptions, p. 237); demarcated.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहार|व्यवहारः
vyavahāra, cf. vyavahāra-pade (LP), ‘as a tax from merchants’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहाराभिलेखितक
Vyavahār-ābhilekhitaka (EI 30), the clerk who writes down the statements of cases in a court of law.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहरमाण
vyavaharamāṇa (LP), current.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहरण
vyavaharaṇa (EI 11), administration.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारपत्र
vyavahāra-patra (LP), a deed relating to a loan or debt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारसमता
vyavahāra-samatā (CII 1), impartiality in judicial proceedings.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारिक|व्यवहारिकः
Vyavahārika (EI 7, 32), an administrator; same as Vyava-hārin (q. v.) or Vyavahartṛ; see also Vyava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवहारिन्
Vyavahārin (EI 19, 24, 28, 29; BL; LL; HD), an administrator; sometimes explained as ‘a controlling officer’; same as Vyavahārika. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 60, 63.<BR> (LL), a merchant. See also Vyava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यवस्था
vyavasthā, cf. vyavasthai (EI 24; SITI), regulations; rules of proper conduct; a settlement or arrangement; a deed of agreement.<BR> (EI 22; SII 2), a resolution; a declaration.<BR> (EI 32), an agreement.<BR> (SII 3), conditions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यय|व्ययं|व्ययः
vyaya (HRS), government expenditure; cf. Tamil viyā-yam (SITI), expenditure, as opposed to āyam or income.<BR> (IE 7-1-2), ‘twelve’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्ययकरण|व्ययकरणः
vyaya-karaṇa, cf. karaṇa (LP), the department of expenditure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्योमन्
vyoman (IE 7-1-2; EI 33), ‘cypher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=383" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्यूह|व्यूहः
vyūha (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व्युषित
Vyuṣita (Prakrit Vivutha), sometimes taken to be Vyuṣṭa (CII 1); ‘one who is away from his residence’. See IHQ, 1962, pp. 222 ff.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

याग|यागः
yāga (EI 31), a ceremony.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यक्ष|यक्षः
Yakṣa (CII 4; HA), a semi-divine being; a demi-god belonging to the class of vyantara-devatās according to Jain mythology.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यज्ञविद्या
yajña-vidyā (EI 8), knowledge regarding the performance of sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यदा
yadā tad=āpi (LP), ‘only’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यादवचक्रवर्तिन्
Yādava-cakravartin (IE 8-2), title assumed by kings of the Yādava dynasty; see Cakravartin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यागमण्डप
yāga-maṇḍapa (SITI), sacrificial hall in a temple; same as yāga-śālā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यागशाला
yāga-śālā (SITI), same as yāga-maṇḍapa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यक्षद्वार
yakṣa-dvāra, gateway adorned with Yakṣa figures (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 107).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यम|यमः
yama (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

याम|यामः
yāma (EI 7-1-2), ‘eight’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Yāma-ceṭī (Tripathi, History of Kanauj, p. 137), probably, a female attendant to the ghaṭī-yantra (q. v.); cf. Yāmakinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=559" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
Yāmakinī, cf. Yāma-ceṭī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=560" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमल|यमलं|यमलः
yamala (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलपत्र|यमलपत्रः
yamala-patra (LP), treaty of alliance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलिकामलि
yamalikāmali (EI 24), a tax probably on a pair of prize bullocks (yamala-kambalin; cf. varabalīvarda); also spelt yamalikambali, yamalikāmbali. See valadī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलिकम्बलि
yamalikambali (IE 8-5), name of a tax; also spelt yama-likāmbali, yamalikāmali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यमलिकाम्बलि
yamalikāmbali (HRS), a tax known from the Gāhaḍavāla records; also spelt yamalikamabali, yamalikāmali (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यानक|यानकं
yānaka (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 253, note 4), probably a cart-road.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यानिका
yānikā, same as yānaka, probably, a cart road (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV. p. 253, note 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यन्त्र|यंत्र|यंत्रं|यन्त्रं
yantra (SITI), a mechanical contrivance, as for diverting water.<BR> (HA), a mystic diagram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यन्त्रकुटी
yantra-kuṭī (IE 8-8; EI 30), an oil mill or manufactory.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=384" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यशस्
yaśas (CII 1), glory in this life; cf. yaśo vā kīrtir = vā. See kīrti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यष्टि|यष्टिः
yaṣṭi (EI 33; CII 4; ML), a memorial pillar; a relic pillar raised in memory of the dead.<BR> Cf. jaṣṭi (EI 19), a land measure.<BR> Cf. laṣṭi (EI 16), a memorial pillar.<BR> Cf. śilā-yaṣṭi (LL), a stone pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

याष्टिक
Yāṣṭika (HD), staff bearer; an attendant on the king. See Rājataraṅgiṇī, VI. 203; Pāṇini, IV. 4. 59. See Vetrika, Piśuna-vetrika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यष्टिप्रातिष्ठानक
Yaṣṭi-prātiṣṭhānaka (ML), the erection of a pillar; same as Sanskrit yaṣṭi-pratiṣṭhāpana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथाकालभाविन्
yathākāla-bhāvin (IE 8-3), same as vartamāna-bhaviṣyat, yathāsambadhyamānaka; also written as yathā-kāl-ādhyāsin (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथाकालाध्यासिन्
yathākāl-ādhyāsin (EI 4, 23), ‘one who may be employed [in the area including the gift land] from time to time’; one who may be associated with the area about the gift land in different periods of time; same as yathākāla-bhāvin, vartamāna-bhaviṣyat, yathā-sambadhyamānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथासम्बध्यमानक
yathā-sambadhyamānaka (IA 9), same as yathākāla-bhāvin, vartamāna-bhaviṣyat, yathākāl-ādhyāsin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यठि
yaṭhi (CII 4), Prakrit; same as Sanskrit yaṣṭi (q. v.); a memorial pillar.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यति|यतिः
Yati (BL), a monk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यात्रा
yātrā (EI 11; CII 4), festival; the festival of a deity; same as yātr-otsava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यात्रादान
yātrā-dāna (EI 27), gift or levy for running a festival.<BR> (SITI), propitiatory gift made before starting on an expedition of conquest by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यात्रोत्सव|यात्रोत्सवः
yātr-otsava (IE 8-5; EI 3, 9), same as yātrā (q. v.); the festival of a deity; festival in honour of a deity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यौत
yauta (CII 1), a respite; cf. yautaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यव|यवः
yava, one-fifteenth of a māṣa (JNSI, Vol. XVI, p. 45); equal to 2 dhānyamāṣas (ibid., p. 48); (1/3) of a rati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यावदेकपात्र
Yāvadeka-pātra (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVII, p. 122, text lines 4-5), official designation. See Pātra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यवन|यवनः
Yavana (EI 26; CII 1), originally, an Ionian Greek; then, people of Greek nationality; ultimately, any foreigner.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यवुग
Yavuga (EI 14), royal title of foreign origin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योग|योगः
yoga (CII 4), meditation; a philosophical system. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-386" target="_blank">Page-386+ 40</a>]<BR> (EI 18), a council or corporation.<BR> (CII 3; IA 17), addition of the longitudes of the sun and moon; an astrological element.<BR> Cf. yogaṃ yuñjantām, ‘let them obtain the association [of the gods]’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 208. Cf. yuj.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=385" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगक्षेम|योगक्षेमं|योगक्षेमः
yoga-kṣema (IA 7; LP), death; cf. jāta-yoga-kṣema, dead.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगपट्ट|योगपट्टं
yoga-paṭṭa (EI 14), band used by the ascetics to keep their limbs in a position of rigidity.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगपट्टक
yoga-paṭṭaka, cf. joga-vaṭṭigě (IA 14), explained as ‘a garment worn during contemplation’; same as yoga-paṭṭa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगपीठ|योगपीठं
yoga-pīṭha (IA 10), a holy place where an ascetic obtained perfection (siddhi) by his austerities; also called siddha-pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योगिन्
yogin, cf. yogīndra (SII 1) a [Jain] ascetic.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योजन|योजनं
yojana (CII 1, 4), name of a measure of distance; a distance of about nine miles.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

योनिपट्ट
yoni-paṭṭa, same as gaurī-paṭṭa; see pīṭha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युद्धित
yuddhita, ‘onewho died fighting’ (Ep. Ind., XXXI, p. 324).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युध्य
yudhya (EI 4), name of a sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग|युगं|युगः
yuga (IE 7-1-2), ‘four’; rarely, 2 or 12.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग|युगं|युगः
yuga, yugā (EI 1), meaning doubtful; cf. yugā in the sense of ‘a voucher’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगा
yugā (CII 4), a voucher.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगादि
yug-ādi (CII 4; IA 18), name applied to certain tithis; day of the commencement of a yuga; e. g. Vaiśākha-sudi 3, regarded as the commencement of the Kṛta-yuga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगादितिथि
yugādi-tithi (EI 13), see yug-ādi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगादिपर्वन्
Yugādi-parvan (EI 14), name of an auspicious time; same as yugādi-tithi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगल|युगलं
yugala (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युगन्धरी
yugandharī (EI 11), same as javār (jawār), millet.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग्म|युग्मं
yugma (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युग्यचर्य
Yugyacarya (CII 1), a charioteer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युज्
yuj (CII 1), cf. vṛddhir=yujyatām, ‘should devote themselves for an increase’; śāśvataṃ samayam=[etad]=yuñjyuḥ, ‘they may strive for this at all times’. Cf. yoga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युक्त|युक्तं|युक्तः
Yukta (EI 8-3; HD), an officer in general; also an official designation (CII, Vol. 1, p. 4); the word used in Rock Edict III of Aśoka is explained by some scholars as the designation of a class of officers, although there also the word may be understood in the sense of ‘an officer’; but it is an official designation [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-387" target="_blank">Page-387+ 22</a>] in passages like yukta-niyukta-vāsāvak-ādhikārika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXI, p. 144) where it may be the same as Āyuktaka.<BR> Cf. Yuktaka, Āyukta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=386" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युक्तक
Yuktaka (IE 8-3; HD), same as Yukta, Āyukta or Āyuktaka. See Ep. Ind., Vol. VII, pp. 26, 39-40.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यूप|यूपः
yūpa (EI 2, 24, 33), sacrificial pillar; it was sometimes made of stone and inscribed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यूथी
yūthī, also spelt yūtī (IA 17), generally written as yūti or pūti; cf. tṛṇa-yūti (or pūti)-gocara-paryanta, ‘as far as grass land and pasture land’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यूति|यूतिः
yūti, cf. sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta (IE 8-5); also written as pūti; a word of uncertain import; probably, ‘[land] reserved [for growing grass, etc.]’ Cf. go-yūti, tṛṇa-yūti, kāṣṭha-yūti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युवमहाराज
Yuvamahārāja (IE 8-2; EI 3, 20, 24), modification of Yuvarāja; designation of the heir-apparent or crown-prince; same as Mahāyuvarāja.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

युवराज|युवराजः
Yuvarāja (IE 8-2, CII 3, 4; HD; ASLV), designation of the heir-apparent or crown-prince. See Arthaśāstra, I. 12 (mentioned among the 18 tīrthas); cf. CII, Vol. II, Part i, p. 40.<BR> Cf. Tamil Tuvarāśan̤ (EI 4), also Duvarāja.<BR> Cf. Mahāyuvarāja (EI 32), same as Yuvamahārāja (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=387" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभटच्छात्रप्रावेश्य
a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya (EI 26, 27; CII 3), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya, Chātra (literally, ‘the umbrella-bearer’) being used for Cāṭa probably meaning ‘the leader of a group of Bhaṭas (i. e. Pāiks or Piādas)’; same as a-prāveśya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभटप्रावेश्य
a-bhaṭa-prāveśya , same as a-prāveśya, etc. Cf. Prakrit a-bhaḍa-papesa (Select Inscriptions, p. 435).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभृतप्रवेश्य
a-bhṛta-praveśya (EI 24), same as a-bhaṭa-prāveśya; cf. a-prāveśya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धि
abhyantara-siddhi (EI 22), same as abhyantara-siddhyā, abhyantara-siddhika; refers to internal revenue income or taxes to be paid to local authorities; cf. sa-bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धिक
abhyantara-siddhika , (EI 20) same as abhyantara-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्धिसहित
abhyantara-siddhi-sahita (EI 27), same as abhyantara-siddhi, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभ्यन्तरसिद्ध्या
abhyantara-siddhyā , ‘together with the internal income or taxes to be paid to the local authorities’; cf. abhyantara-siddhika and sa-bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 398.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रादित्यकालीय
ā-candr-āditya-kālīya (IE), ‘to be enjoyed as long as the moon and sun endure’ (i. e. permanently); epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्कक्षितिसमकालम्
ā-candr-ārka-kṣiti-sama-kālam , ‘as long as the moon, the sun and the earth exist’ (i. e. permanently).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्क
ā-candr-ārka (IE; SITI), ‘in perpetuity.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्कार्णवक्षितिस्थितिसमकालीन
ā-candr-ārk-ārṇava-kṣiti-sthiti-sama-kālīna (EI), ‘to last as long as the moon, the sun, the seas and the earth endure’ (i. e. permanently); cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 134.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रार्कार्णवक्षितिसरित्पर्वतसमकालीन
ā-candr-ārk-ārṇava-kṣiti-sarit-parvata-sama-kālīna , ‘to be enjoyed as long as the moon, the sun, the seas, the earth, the rivers and hills exist (i. e. permanently)’; cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 134.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचन्द्रतारकम्
ā-candra-tārakam , ‘as long as the moon and stars endure’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 149, text line 12), i. e. permanently.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचारासनचर्माङ्गार
a-cār-āsana-carm-āṅgāra (IE; EI 27), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation to supply conveyance, accommodation, hide (i. e. hide-seats) and charcoal free of charges to the touring officers on their visit. The word cāra meaning [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-389" target="_blank">Page-389+ 40</a>] ‘passage or conveyance’ is sometimes substituted by pāra meaning ‘ferrying’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=388" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचारसिद्धिक
a-cāra-siddhika (EI 26), explained by some as ‘without grazing right for the royal cattle’. Cf. a-vāra-siddhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचर्माङ्गारक
a-carm-āṅgāraka , refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation to supply hide-seats and charcoal to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring royal officers on their visit. Cf. Prakrit a-camm-aṅgālaka (Select Inscriptions, p. 409).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचाटभटगोचर
a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-gocara (EI 22), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचाटभटप्रवेश
a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa (EI 27, 29; CII 3), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the entry of the Cāṭas (leaders of groups of Pāiks and Piādas) and the Bhaṭas (Pāiks and Piādas); cf. a-bhaṭa-praveśa, a-bhaṭa-chātra-prāveśya, a-bhṛta-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचाटभटप्रावेश्य
a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya (CII 3, 4), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-pra- veśa; refers to the freedom of the gift land from being entered by the Bhaṭas (the king's Pāiks and Piādas) and the Cāḷa (the leader of a group of Pāiks and Piādas); cf. Chātra in place of Cāṭa in a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya; also Bhṛta for Bhaṭa in a-bhṛta-praveśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचट्टभट्टप्रवेश
a-caṭṭa-bhaṭṭa-praveśa (EI 27), same as a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अचुल्लककूरखट्वाग्रहण
a-cullaka-kūra-khaṭvā-grahaṇa , similar to a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अदुग्धदधिग्रहण
a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa , refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation of supplying milk and curs to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officials on their visit. Cf. Prakrit a-dudha-dadhi-gahaṇa (Select Inscriptions, p. 439).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहरीतकशाकपुष्पग्रहण
a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa , refers to the freedom of the gift land from the supply of myrobalan, vegetables and flowers to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers on their visit. Cf. Prakrit a-haritaka-sāka-pupha-gahaṇa (Select Inscriptions, p. 439).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहरीतपर्णशाकपुष्पफलदुग्धदधिघृततक्रग्रहण
a-harīta-parṇa-śāka-puṣpa-phala-dugdha-dadhi-ghṛta-takra-grahaṇa , similar to a-harītaka-śāka-puṣpa-grahaṇa and a-dugdha-dadhi-grahaṇa, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहस्तप्रक्षेपणीय
a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīya (EI 11, 23), same as a a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc. Cf. samasta-rājakīyānām=a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अहिरण्यधान्यप्रणयप्रदेय
a-hiraṇya-dhānya-praṇaya-pradeya (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the gift land from the payment of revenue in cash, the king's grain share and the benevolence or emergency imposts. Cf. Prakrit a-hiraṇṇa-dhaṇṇa-ppaṇaya-ppadeya (Select Inscriptions, pp. 408-09).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=389" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरद
a-karada (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the donee of the gift land from paying taxes in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरदायिन्
a-karadāyin (EI 26, 27), same as a-karada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरवातोत्तर
a-kara-vāt-ottara (IE; EI 32), sometimes with āvāta, vāt-ādeya, bhūt-opātta-pratyāya, etc., in place of vāt-ottara; cf. sa-bhūta-vāta- (or pāta)-pratyāya, etc; ‘free from the collections resulting from storms (e. g. uprooted trees, fruits, etc.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकरविष्टिकोञ्जल्ल
a-kara-viṣṭi-koñjalla (IE), refers to the freedom of the donee of the gift land from the payment of taxes and the obligation to supply free labour and koñjalla (kāñji) to the king's labourers. Cf. Select Inscriptions, p. 439.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अखट्वाचुल्लकवैनाशिक
a-khaṭvā-cullaka-vaināśika , cf. Prakrit a-khaṭṭa-collaka-veṇesika (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation to supply cots, food and attendant or fuel to the touring royal officers on their visit or to the king or landlord on occasions. Cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्कर
a-kiñcit-kara , ‘not to pay even a small amount as rent or tax’; epithet of gift land; same as a-kiñcit-pragrāhya. It has to be noted that sometimes a small amount of tax was fixed for the gift lands. Cf. kara-śāsana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्करग्राह्य
a-kiñcit-kara-grāhya (EI 27), same as a-kiñcit-kara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्प्रग्राह्य
a-kiñcit-pragrāhya (EI 29), refers to the freedom of the gift land from the payment of taxes and the obligation of supplying articles to the king or landlord on occasions and to the touring officers on their visit; same as a-kiñcit-kara, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकिञ्चित्प्रतिकर
a-kiñcit-pratikara (EI 23), ‘[land] free from any yield of revenue’; cf. utpratikara. But pratikara also means ‘compensation’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अकूरचुल्लकवैनाशिखट्वावास
a-kūra-cullaka-vaināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa (or ˚saṃvāsa) , cf. a-kūra-yollaka-venesi-khaṭṭ-āvāsa (EI 26); refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation of supplying boiled or unboiled rice, pots or fire-places for cooking, attendant or fuel, cot and shelter to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers on their visit; same as a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-saṃvāsa, etc. See sāmant-āmātya-dūtānām=anyeṣām c=ābhyupāgame śayanīy-āsana-siddh-ānnaṃ na dāpayet (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 171).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणगुडक्षोभ
a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha (EI 26), same as a-lavaṇa-khātaka, guḍa or sugar being added to lavaṇa or salt; cf. a-lavaṇa-klinna-khātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणखातक
a-lavaṇa-khātaka , cf. Prakrit a-loṇa-khādaka (EI 7), refers [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-391" target="_blank">Page-391+ 40</a>] to the freedom of the gift land from being dug out or its trees being pierced for salt.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=390" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्लिन्नखनक
a-lavaṇa-klinna-khanaka (EI 26), same as a-lavaṇa-klinna-kreṇi-khanaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्लिन्नखातक
a-lavaṇa-klinna-khātaka , same as a-lavaṇa-khātaka, klinna, sometimes wrongly spelt kliṇva, probably, ‘toddy, sugar, etc.’ being added to lavaṇa or salt. Cf. a-lavaṇa-guḍa-kṣobha, a-lavaṇa-klinna-kreṇi-khanaka, etc. Cf. Select Inscriptions, p. 408.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्लिण्वक्रेणिखनक
a-lavaṇa-kliṇva(nna)-kreṇi-khanaka (EI 26, 27), same as a-lavaṇa-klinna-khātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलवणक्रेणिखनक
a-lavaṇa-kreṇi-khanaka (EI 23), same as a-lavaṇa-klinna-khātaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलेखनीप्रवेशतया
a-lekhanī-praveśatayā (EI 29), probably refers to the absence of the right to re-grant the gift land to any other party on the part of the king and to alienate the gift land on the part of the donee; lekhanī-praveśa may mean that the gift land should not be made the subject of another document.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाच्छेद्य|अनाछेद्य
anācchedya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 267, note), ‘unresumable’; but since anāhāra, ‘unresumable’, is sometimes used in the same context, probably, ‘uncurtailable’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनादेश्य
anādeśya (EI 12), same as anirdeśya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनाहार|अनाहारः
anāhāra , ‘unresumable’ (Ind. Ep., p. 395), cf. anācchedya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनङ्गुलिप्रक्षेपणीय
anaṅguli-prakṣepaṇīya (EI 23), also called anaṅguli-prekṣaṇīya same as a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनङ्गुलिप्रेक्षणीय
anaṅguli-prekṣaṇīya (EI 23), same as anaṅguli-prakṣepaṇīya, a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनासेध्य
anāsedhya (Ep. Ind., Vol. II, p. 267, note 4), refers to the freedom of the people associated with the gift land from legal restraints.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनवमर्श्य
anavamarśya , refers to the freedom of the gift land from troubles associated with the visit of royal agents. Cf. Prakrit anomasa (Select Inscriptions, pp. 192, 194).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपारम्पर
a-pārampara , same as a-paramparā-balīvarda or a-paraṃ-parā-balīvarda-grahaṇa, a privilege of the donee of rent-free land (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 42).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरम्पराबलीवर्द
a-paramparā-balīvarda (SITI), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the supply of bullocks primarily for the conveyance of royal officers on tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरम्पराबलीवर्दग्रहण
a-paramparā-balīvarda-grahaṇa (EI 26), same as a-pāram-para, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=391" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरम्परागोबलीवर्द
a-paramparā-go-balīvarda (EI 22, 26, 27), same as a-pāram-para, etc., in which go (cow) has been added to balīvarda (bullock).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपरिपन्थ्य
a-paripanthya , ‘without opposition’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपशुमेध्य
a-paśu-medhya (Select Inscriptions, p. 414), refers to the freedom from the supply of animals for sacrifice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अप्रावेश्य
a-prāveśya , refers to the freedom of the gift land from the entry of royal agents; same as a-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc. Cf. Prakrit a-pāvesa (Select Inscriptions, pp. 192, 194).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुष्पक्षीरग्रहण
a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇa (EI 26), same as a-puṣpa-kṣīra-san-doha, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुष्पक्षीरग्रहणीय
a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya , refers to the freedom of the gift land from the supply, of flowers and milk to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers on their visit; same as a-puṣpa-kṣīra-sandoha, etc. Cf. Prakrit a-puppha-kkhīra-gahaṇi (Select Inscriptions, p. 409).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुष्पक्षीरसन्दोह
a-puṣpa-kṣīra-sandoha (EI 26, 27), same as a-puṣpa-kṣīra-grahaṇīya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रधनं|अपुत्रधन
aputra-dhanaṃ nāsti , ‘there is no confiscation, by the king, of the property of persons dying without a son’; cf. aputrā-sahita, etc. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अपुत्रासहित
aputrā-sahita (IE), ‘together with the right to confiscate the property of persons dying without leaving any son’; epithet of gift village. Cf. aputra-dhanaṃ nāsti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अराष्ट्रसांविनयिक
a-rāṣṭra-sāṃvinayika (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the gift land from the administrative control to which the district in which it was situated was subject. Cf. Prakrit a-raṭha-saṃ-vinayika (Select Inscriptions, pp. 92, 94). See bhoga-sambandha-nirvacanīya, grāma-nilaya-nāḍa-sarva-bādhā-parithāreṇa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

असन्नरप्रवृत्तिविनिवृत्ताचार
asan-nara-pravṛtti-vinivṛtt-ācāra (Ind. Ant., Vol. XI p. 113, text lines 36-37), translated as ‘the established customs [of the gift land] are withheld from [injury by] the enterprise of wicked men.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभागिक
aṣṭa-bhāgika , ‘paying one-eighth of the produce [in place of the usual one-sixth]’. Cf. Prakrit aṭha-bhāgiya (Select Inscriptions, p. 70).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टभोगतेजःस्वाम्यदण्डशुल्कयुक्त
aṣṭabhoga-tejaḥsvāmya-daṇḍaśulka-yukta (Ind. Ant., Vol XIX, p. 247, text line 102), mentioned along with nidhi-nikṣepa pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣprakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita. See aṣṭa-bhoga, tejaḥ-svāmya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टादशजातिपरिहार
aṣṭādaśa-jāti-parihāra , the eighteen (i. e. all or various) kinds [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-393" target="_blank">Page-393+ 40</a>] of exemptions [usually enjoyed by rent-free holdings]. Cf. Prakrit aṭṭhārasa-jāti-parihāra (Select Inscriptions., pp. 439-40).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=392" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अतृणकाष्ठग्रहण
a-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-grahaṇa (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the donee of the gift village from the supply of grass and fuel to the king or landlord on occasions or to the touring officers on their visit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवह|अवहः
a-vaha (EI 26), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation of carrying loads of the touring officers, etc., or of supplying a horse to them free of charges.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवारसिद्धिक
a-vāra-siddhika (IE), refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation to supply unpaid labour in turn. Cf. a-cāra-siddhika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भागभोगपशुहिरण्यकरशुल्क
bhāga-bhoga-paśu-hiraṇya-kara-śulka (EI 20), ‘together with [the right to] the share of the produce, periodical offerings, cattle or animals [for sacrificial purposes], tax in cash, tax in kind and tolls’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाविष्यत्कररहित
bhāviṣyat-kara-rahita (EI 24), ‘without all the taxes to be levied in future.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भोगसम्बन्धनिर्वचनीय
bhogasambandha-nirvacanīya (EI 12), ‘the relations [of the gift land] with the administrative unit (i. e. bhoga, to which it belonged) should not be reckoned [since the land is granted after separating it from the district] (bhogād=uddhṛtya)’. Cf. a-rāṣṭra-sāṃvinayika, grāma-nilaya-nā ḍa-sarva-bādhā-parihāreṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिच्छिद्रनायेन
bhūmi-cchidra-nāyena or ˚cchidra-pidhāna-vyāyena , ‘in accordance with the principle of cultivating the land for the first time and enjoying it free of taxes as a result’. The word chidra in the first means ‘cultivation’ and chidra-pidhāna in the second ‘reclamation of uncultivable land for the first time.’ Sometimes vidhāna is wrongly used for pidhāna. See Ind. Ep., pp. 397-98.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतभविष्यद्वर्तमाननिःशेषादात्यसहित
bhūta-bhaviṣyad-vartamāna-niḥśeṣ-ādātya-sahita , ‘together with the arrears of taxes and with the present and future taxes in their entirety’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रार्ककालिकं
candr-ārka-kālikaṃ śulkam=ādeyaṃ samasta-rājye n=āsti , ‘there is no collection of tolls in the whole kingdom as long as the moon and the sun exist’. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 237.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चन्द्रार्कस्थितिकालं
candr-ārka-sthiti-kālaṃ yāvat , ‘as long as the moon and sun endure (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text lines 21-22); sometimes candr-ārka-ksiti˚, candr-ārk-ārṇāva-kṣīti-sarit-parvata˚, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चलुःसीमावच्छिन्न
catuḥ-sīm-āvacchinna , same as sva-sīm-āvachinna, catur-aghāṭa-viśuddha, etc. Cf. Majumdar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=393" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुःसीमा
catuḥ-sīmā yāvat , same as catuḥ-sīmā-paryanta, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुराघाटविशुद्ध
catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha , ‘with the boundaries well demarcated’; same as catuḥ-sīm-āvacchina, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 396.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुराघाटान्तर्वर्तिजलपाषाणनिधिनिक्षेपशुल्कादिसर्वतेजःस्वाम्यसहित
catur-āghāṭ-āntarvarti-jala-pāṣāṇa-nidhi-nikṣepa-śulk-ādi-sarva-tejaḥsvāmya-sahita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 40, text lines 37-38). See tejaḥ-svāmya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चतुष्कण्टकविशुद्ध
catuṣ-kaṇṭaka-viśuddha (EI 23), cf. catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha; probably refers to the custom of demarcating a plot of land by planting thorny shrubs on the borders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौरवर्जम्
caura-varjam , also quoted as cora-varjam, cora-daṇḍa-varjam, cora-rājāpathyakāri-varjam, etc.; according to some ‘with immunity from the police tax’, while others take it to be related to a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa and think that the policemen were prohibited from entering a gift village except in connection with the apprehension of criminals; may also mean ‘without any right to inflict punishment of thieves, etc., or to levy fines from thieves, etc.’ See CII, Vol. III, p. 109.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरदण्डवर्ज
cora-daṇḍa-varja (EI 27), same as caura-varja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चोरवर्ज
cora-varja (IE), ‘without the right to punish the thieves and to realise stolen articles’; cf. sa-caur-oddharaṇa. But see also cauravarjam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देशमर्यादारुवणान्विल
deśa-maryād-āruvaṇ-ānvita (Ind. Ant. Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line 103), refers to the right to levy the tax called āruvaṇa (Sanskrit ṣaṭ-paṇa) according to the local custom.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवब्राह्मणभुक्तिवर्ज
deva-Brāhmaṇa-bhukti-varja (EI 23, 30), ‘excluding the property of the gods (i. e. temples) and Brāhmaṇas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देवकुलपुष्करिण्याधिकं
devakula-puṣkariṇy-ādhikaṃ kārayitvā , refers to the right of the donee to build temples and excavate tanks in the gift land without the permission of the king or landlord as was necessary in the case of ordinary tenants. Cf. Majumdar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोगौडसमेत
go-gauḍa-sameta , ‘together with the cattle and herdsmen [of state farms] or with the grazing tax’; epithet of gift village. Go-gauḍa may be the same as go-kara. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामनिलयनाडसर्वबाधापरिहारेण
grāma-nilaya-nāḍa-sarva-bādhā-parihāreṇa (EI 9), ‘with the exemption of all troubles connected with [the administration of] the village, subdivision (literally, habitation) and district [in which the gift land is situated]’. Cf. a-rāṣṭra-sāṃvinayika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गृहावतरणहरितपक्वसस्येक्षुचारणलवनोपमर्दनरोचिकाचिटोलाग्रहणपीठकपीठिकाखट्वापहरणकाष्ठेन्धन
gṛh-āvataraṇa-harita-pakva-sasy-ekṣu-cāraṇa-lavan-opamardana-rocikā-ciṭolā-grahaṇa-pīṭhaka-pīṭhikā-khaṭv-āpaharaṇa-kāṣṭh-endhana-ghāsa-bus-ādikaṃ na kenacit=[kartavyaṃ] pragrāhyaṃ [ca] , [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-395" target="_blank">Page-395+ 40</a>] ‘no one should enter into the donce's house, should graze one's cattle on the green crops in his fields, should harvest the ripe crops in his fields, should crush his sugar-cane, should accept rocikā and ciṭolā from him, should take stools, seats and cots from him and should take wood, fuel, grass, chaff, etc., from him’. For gṛh-āvataraṇa, see umbara-bheda. Words like rocikā, ciṭolā, etc., are not intelligible, although they certainly refer to certain obligations or levies. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=394" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुवाकनारिकेलादिकं
guvāka-nārikel-ādikaṃ laggāvayitvā , refers to the right of planting arecanut and coconut palms in the gift land without the permission of the king or landlord as was necessary in the case of ordinary tenants; cf. sa-guvāka-nārikela. Cf. Majumdar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हस्तिदण्डवरबलीवर्द
hastidaṇḍa-varabalīvarda-coṭāla-andhā(rthā ?)ruvā-pratyandhā-(rthā ?)ruvā-adattā-padātijīva-ahidaṇḍa-ānta(tu ?)rāvaḍḍi-bandha-daṇḍa-vijayavandāpanā-mārgaṇika-prabhṛti-bhaviṣyat-kara-sahita , refers to the donee's right to enjoy various taxes the nature of some of which is doubtful. These include the tax for keeping elephants and prize bullocks, tax for the maintenance of the king's Padātis (footmen or Pāiks), tax on the professional snake-charmers, ransom in lieu of imprisonment, presents to be made to the king on his return from a victorious campaign and tax to be paid for using the road in the gift village for the transit of articles of merchandise. See the expressions separately as noticed above. See also suvarṇa-daṇḍa-ahidaṇḍa … below. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जनधनसहित
jana-dhana-sahita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘together with the tenants and revenue income [of the village]’; some as sa-jana-dhana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशलतापूतहस्तोदकेन
kuśa-latā-pūta-hast-odakena , cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc. See Ind. Ep., p. 395<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महादोषविवर्जित
mahādoṣa-vivarjita (EI 23), ‘excluding fines for great crimes’; cf. doṣa and daṇḍa-doṣa (fines) noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुक्तोपरिकर
mukt-oparikara (EI 29), free from minor taxes or without freedom from them. Cf. s-oparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नानावृक्षसमेत
nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta , ‘together with the various trees’; epithet of gift village. Some of the trees not to be enjoyed by unprivileged tenants were mango, madhūka, jack, coconut, arecanut, palmyra palm, sīsu, tamarind tree, etc. But the group was different in different parts of the country. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=395" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नवनिधानसहित
nava-nidhāna-sahita (IA 11), probably, ‘with the taxes fixed afresh’, though nidhāna is often the same as nikṣepa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधिनिक्षेपपाषाणारामादिचतुष्प्रकारबीरवणपारिखायसहित
nidhi-nikṣepa-pāṣāṇ-ārām-ādi-catuṣprakāra-bīravaṇa-pārikh-āya-sahita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247), mentioned along with aṣṭabhoga-tejassvāmy-daṇḍaśulka-yukta. See the expressions as separately noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधिनिक्षेपापुत्रकधनदण्डोपजातकसहित
nidhi-nikṣep-āputrakadhana-daṇḍ-opajātaka-sahita , ‘together with the right to enjoy treasure-trove and the occasional finds and accumulations on the land and to confiscate the property of persons dying without leaving any son, and to enjoy the right to appropriate the income derived from fines’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., 406.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधिनिक्षेपसहित
nidhi-nikṣepa-sahita , see sa-vṛkṣamālā-nīdhi-nikṣepa-sahita.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निध्युपनिधिहस्तिदन्तव्याघ्रचर्मनानावनचरसमेत
nidhy-upanidhi-hastidanta-vyāghracarma-nānāvanacara-sameta , refers to the right of the donee to treasure-troves, occasional finds or accumulations on the ground, elephants’ tusks, tiger's skin and certain prized animals without surrendering them to the king as ordinary tenants had to do; epithet of the gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निषिद्धचाटभटप्रवेश
niṣiddha-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa (EI 22), same as a-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिहृतपङ्गोत्कोट
parihṛta-paṅg-otkoṭa (EI 33), ‘exempted from the levies called paṅga and utkoṭa’. See the words as separately^1 noticed.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परिहृतसर्वपीड
parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa (EI 27, 29), ‘free from all troubles’; same as sarva-pīḍā-varjita, sarva-bādhā-vivarjita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फलरतिक
phalaratika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), refers probably to the right to enjoy all kinds of fruits in the gift land without special permission that was necessary for ordinary tenants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रसिद्धचतुःसीमावच्छिन्न
prasiddha-catuḥ-sīm-āvacchinna , ‘demarcated by the well-known boundaries on all the sides’; epithet of the gift land. Cf. catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषिद्धचाटभटप्रवेश
pratiṣiddha-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśa (EI 23, 27), same as a-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रतिषिद्धचाटादिप्रवेश
pratiṣiddha-cāṭ-ādi-praveśa (I. E., p. 395), same as a-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वभुज्यमानदेवब्राह्मणक्षेत्रखण्डलकं
pūrva-bhujyamāna-deva-brāhmaṇa-kṣetra-khaṇḍalakaṃ varjayitvā (or vihāya) , see Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135; same as deva-brāhmaṇa-bhukti-varja, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 398.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वभुक्तकभुज्यमानदेवब्रह्मदायवर्जित
pūrva-bhuktaka-bhujyamāna-deva-brahma-dāya-varjita (EI 23), same as deva-brāhmaṇa-bhukti-varja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पूर्वप्रत्तदेवब्रह्मदेयरहित
pūrva-pratta-deva-brahma-deya-rahita , sometimes with dāya in place of deya; refers to the absence of the donee's right to have [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-397" target="_blank">Page-397+ 40</a>] any control over that land in the gift village which was already a rent-free holding in the possession of gods or Brāhmaṇas; same as deva-brahmaṇa-bhukti-varja, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 398.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=396" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्रादिसन्ततिक्रमेण
putra-pautrādi-santati-krameṇa , same as putra-pautr-ānvaya-kram-opabhogya, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 399.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्राद्यन्वयोपभोगा
putra-pautr-ādy-anvay-opabhogā, ˚ānugaminī, etc.; same as putra-pautr-ānugamaka. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 394-95.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्रानुगमक
putra-pautr-ānugamaka , ‘the donce's right of enjoying the gift land should pass on to his sons and grandsons’; epithet of gift land; same as putra-pautr-ānvaya-kram-opabhogya, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 392.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुत्रपौत्रान्वयक्रमोपभोग्य
putra-pautr-ānvaya-kram-opabhogya , refers to the permanent nature of a gift of land to be enjoyed by the donee as well as his descendants; same as putra-putr-ānugamaka (I. E., p. 398).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजभाव्यसर्वप्रत्यायसमेत
rāja-bhāvya-sarva-pratyāya-sameta (EI 23), bhāvya being often changed to ābhāvya; same as a-kiñcit-pragrāhya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजग्राह्यसमस्तप्रत्यायसमन्वित
rāja-grāhya-samasta-pratyāya-samanvita (EI 22), same as a-kiñcit-pragrāhya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजपुरुषैर्
rāja-rājapuruṣair=apy=anaṅguli-nirdeśyam , same as srava-rāja-kīyānām=a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīyaḥ, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 400.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजसेवकानां
rājasevakānāṃ vasatidaṇḍa-prayāṇadaṇḍau na staḥ , refers to the freedom of the gift village from the obligation to provide accommodation and conveyance, etc., to the royal officers on tour; cf. a-kūra-chullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, a-paraṃparā-balīvarda, etc. See CII, Vol. III, p. 98, note 2.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राज्ञाराजपुरुषैर्
rājñā rājapuruṣair=apy=anaṅguli-prakṣepaṇīya (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247, text lines 103-04), same as sarva-rājakīyānām=a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīyaḥ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रम्य|रम्यः
ramya (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), refers to the fact that the gift land had nothing unpleasant about it.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋणादायादिसम्बन्धवर्जित
ṛṇ-ādāy-ādi-sambandha-varjita (EI 23), refers to the freedom of the gift land from confiscation for the realisation of debts incurred by the donee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सबाह्याभ्यन्तरादाय
sa-bāhy-ābhyantar-ādāya , ‘together with the external and internal income or taxes to be paid to the state and to the village authorities’; epithet of the gift village; cf. abhyantara-siddhyā, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभोग
sa-bhoga (EI 27; IA 9), ‘together with the aṣṭa-bhoga’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभूतपातप्रत्याय
sa-bhūta-pāta-pratyāya (CII 3), refers to the income from the gift land as a result of some action of nature's agencies. Sometimes vāta and āvāta are found for pāta probably in the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-398" target="_blank">Page-398+ 40</a>] sense of ‘a storm’ (cf. udvāta) and also upātta, ‘realised’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=397" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभूतवातप्रत्याय
sa-bhūta-vāta-pratyāya (EI 23), with pāta sometimes in place of vāta; ‘together with the income arising out of a change of the natural phenomena (such as due to earthquakes, storms, etc.)’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सभूतोपात्तप्रत्याय
sa-bhūt-opātta-pratyāya (EI 23), same as sa-bhūta-vāta-pra-tyāya, etc. The word upātta means ‘realised’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सचौरोद्धरण
sa-caur-oddharaṇa (EI 12, 23, 29), ‘together with the right to punish thieves and recover stolen property or fines’; epithet of gift villages. Cf. caura-varja, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदण्डदोष
sa-daṇḍa-doṣa (EI 23), ‘together with [the right to] levy fines for crimes’; the meaning of doṣa is really doubtful in the context.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदण्डनिग्रह
sa-daṇḍa-nigraha (EI 24), refers to the king's power to punish [culprits] by fines or corporal punishment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदशापचार
sa-daś-āpacāra , same as sa-daś-āparādha; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदशापराध
sa-daś-āparādha (EI 27), also quoted as sa-daś-āpacāra; ‘together with the right to punish and realise fines for the ten offences (murder, theft, etc.)’; epithet of gift village; cf. sahya-daś-āparādha probably meaning that the crimes committed in the gift village should not be punished by the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदेयमेय
sa-deya-meya (EI 7), same as sa-dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सधान्यहिरण्यादेय
sa-dhānya-hiraṇy-ādeya (EI 11, 12, 23; IA 9), ‘together with the king's grain share and taxes in cash’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साधऊर्ध्व
s-ādha-ūrdhva , ‘together with what is [produced or found] below and above the ground’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सागमनिरमप्रवेश
s-āgama-nirama-praveśa , ‘together with approaches, ingress and egress’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगर्तावस्कर
sa-gart-āvaskara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), mentioned along with s-oṣara. The word avaskara (also avakara) probably means ‘a mound’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगर्तोषर
sa-gart-oṣara (EI 27, 29), ‘together with pits and saline spots or barren lands’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगिरिगहननिधान
sa-giri-gahana-nidhāna (EI 24), ‘together with hills, forests and deposits’. See also nidhāna noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगोकुल
sa-gokula , ‘together with the cowpens’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगोप्रचार
sa-gopracāra (EI 12), ‘together with the pasture lands’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगुल्मलता
sa-gulma-latā (EI 12), same as sa-gulma-latāka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=398" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगुल्मलताक
sa-gulma-latāka , ‘together with shrubs and creepers’; epithet of the gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सगुवाकनारिकेर
sa-guvāka-nārikera (EI 12), sometimes with nālikela in place of nārikera; ‘together with the arecanut and coconut palms’; epithet of gift land; see guvāka-nārikel-ādikaṃ laggāvayitvā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहट्टघट्टसतर
sa-haṭṭa-ghaṭṭa-sa-tara (EI 22), ‘together with market-places and ferries (or passes) and with ferry-dues’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहिरण्यभागभोग
sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga (EI 23), same as sa-deya-meya, etc. See the words as separately noticed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहिरण्यभागभोगोपरिकरसर्वादायसमेत
sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhog-oparikara-sarv-ādāya-sameta (EI 23), ‘together with all levies such as hiraṇya, bhāga, bhoga and upa-rikara’. See the various words as noticed separately.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सहिरण्यादान
sa-hiraṇy-ādāna (EI 26), ‘together with levies in cash’; privilege of the donee of rent-free and.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सह्यदशापराध
sahya-daś-āparādha (IE), see sa-daś-āparādha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजलस्थल
sa-jala-sthala (EI 12, 27, 29), ‘together with land and waters [of the gift village]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजलस्थलारण्य
sa-jala-sthal-āraṇya (EI 23), ‘together with the land, waters and jungles [of the gift village]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजलस्थलसहित
sa-jala-sthala-sahita (EI 23), same as sa-jala-sthala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजनधन
sa-jana-dhana (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139), same as jana-dhana-sahita. Cf. sa-jana (ibid., Vol. V, p. 185).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सजाङ्गलानूप
sa-jāṅgal-ānūpa (EI 12), ‘together with arid and marshy lands’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सझाटविटप
sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa , ‘together with bushes and shrubs (or branches)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकरोत्कर
sa-kar-otkara = Prakrit sa-kar-ukara (EI 7); refers to a piece of land granted with the donee's right to enjoy major and minor taxes; cf. s-odraṅga-s-oparikara and sa-kḷpt-opakḷpta, etc. See kar-otkara as noticed separately above; also cf. kāru-kara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखल्लौन्नत
sa-khalla-unnata = sa-khall-onnata (EI 12), ‘together with low and high lands’; epithet of gift land. Khalla is Od̤iyā khāl ‘low land’. Cf. sa-nimn-onnata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखण्डपालीय
sa-khaṇḍapālīya , ‘together with the tax for the maintenance of the swordsmen’; epithet of gift village; cf. padāti-jivya, tax for the maintenance of Pāiks or footmen. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखटविटप
sa-khaṭa-viṭapa (EI 12), mistake for sa-jhāṭa-vitapa or sa-kheṭa-viṭapa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखेटघट्टनदीतरस्थानादिगुल्मक
sa-kheṭa-ghaṭṭa-nadītara-sthān-ādi-gulmaka (EI 29), ‘together with the military, police or customs outposts in the hamlets, [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-400" target="_blank">Page-400+ 40</a>] landing places on the banks of rivers (or passes in the hilly tracts) and ferrying stations’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=399" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखेटविटप
sa-kheṭa-viṭapa , ‘together with outposts and bushes’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखिलनाल
sa-khila-nāla , ‘together with the fallow and cultivated lands’; epithet of gift village; same as sa-khila-polācya. See Majumdar, Ins. Beng., Vol. III, p. 125.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखिलपोलाच्य
sa-khila-polācya , ‘together with fallow and cultivated land’; same as sa-khila-nāla. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सखिलोपखिल
sa-khil-opakhila , ‘together with land which is fallow and partially fallow’. Pakhila in the same context is a mistake for upakhila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकॢप्त
sa-kḷpta (EI 24), ‘together with the tax on permanent tenants or the fixed revenue’; same as s-odraṅga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकॢप्तोपकॢप्तक
sa-kḷpt-opakḷptaka (EI 24, 27), refers to the freedom of the gift land from the payment of fixed taxes on permanent tenants as well as occasional^1 taxes or taxes on temporary tenants; same as s-odraṅga-s-oparikara.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सकृतप्रान्त
sa-kṛta-prānta , cf. Prakrit sa-kutu-ppanta (EI 26), ‘together with the demarcated boundaries’; epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलवण
sa-lavaṇa (EI 12), ‘together with salt (i. e. the right to enjoy salt produced in the land). Cf. a-lavaṇa-khātaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलवणाकर
sa-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 12), ‘together with the salt pits’. Cf. a-lavaṇa-khātaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलोहाद्याकर
sa-loh-ādy-ākara , together with the mines of metals, etc.’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सलोहलवणाकर
sa-loha-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 23, 26), ‘together with the mines and salt-pits’, epithet of gift land. Cf. sa-loh-ādy-ākara, a-lavaṇa-khātaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समधूकचूतवनवाटिकाविटपतृनयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त
sa-madhūka-cūta-vana-vāṭikā-viṭapa-tṛna-yūti-gocara-paryanta , ‘together with the madhūka and mango trees, forests, gardens, bushes (or, branches), grass yūti (grass land) and including the pasture land’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 396. It is better to take sa-madhūka-cūṭa-vana-vāṭikā-viṭapa and tṛnayūti-gocara-paryanta separately.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समधूकाम्रवनवाटिकाविटपतृणयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त
sa-madhūk-āmra-vana-vāṭikā-viṭapa-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta (EI 24), ‘together with the madhuka and mango trees, forests, gardens, shrubs and as far as and the grass yuli (grass land) and pasture lands’. See sa-madhūka-cūta … , above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समन्दिरप्राकार
sa-mandira-prākāra , ‘together with temples and walls’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-401" target="_blank">Page-401+ 40</a>] trees and areas covered by jungles (or areas covered with mango and madhūka plantations)’; see Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=400" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समञ्चमहाकरण
sa-mañca-mahākaraṇa (EI 26), ‘together with mañca (probably, platforms for the collection of tolls) and mahākaraṇa (official documents)’; epithet of the gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सामन्तामात्यदूतानाम्
sāmant-āmātya-dūtānām=anyeṣām c=ābhyupāgame śayanīy-āsana-siddhānnaṃ na dāpayet , refers to the obligation of the people to supply beds, seats and boiled or unboiled rice to feudatory rulers, ministers, messengers and others encamped in a village; see a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭv-āvāsa, etc. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 171.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तभागभोगकरहिरण्यादिप्रत्यायसमेत
samasta-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi-pratyāya-sameta , ‘together with all incomes including the king's grain share, the periodical offerings to be made to the king or landlord and to the touring officers, taxes in grains, taxes in cash, etc.’; epithet of gift land; same as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc. See Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तभागभोगकरहिरण्यादायसमेत
samasta-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādāya-sameta (EI 23), same as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तराजकीयानाम्
samasta-rājakīyānām=apraveśya , same as a-bhaṭa-praveśa, a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-praveśya, a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya, etc. (Ind. Ep., p. 398).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तराजकीयानम्
samasta-rājakīyānam=ahasta-prakṣepaṇīya (CII 3), same as ā-bhaṭa-praveśa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तराजप्रत्यादायसमेत
samasta-rājapratyādāya-sameta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 129), same as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तोत्पत्तिसहित
samast-otpatti-sahita (EI 12), ‘together with all the produce or income’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समस्तोत्पत्तिशुल्कोत्पत्तिसहित
samast-otpatti-śulk-otpatti-sahita (EI 23), ‘together with all the produce of the land and the income arising from tolls’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्स्यकच्छप
sa-matsya-kacchapa (EI 12), ‘together with the right to catch fish and tortoises’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समत्स्याकर
sa-matsy-ākara (EI 24), 26), ‘together with the sources of fish (e. g., rivers, tanks, etc)’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्हलालमकसमन्वित
samhalātamaka-samanvita (EI 9), the reading is apparently wrong; meaning uncertain.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समीनतोय
sa-mīna-toya (EI 24), ‘together with fish and the waters’ or ‘together with the waters containing fish.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रमधूक
s-āmra-madhūka (IE; EI 12, 27, 29), ‘together with the mango and madhūka trees’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रमधुवन
s-āmra-madhu-vana (EI 12), same as s-āmra-madhū-van-ākīrṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रमधुवनाकीर्ण
s-āmra-madhu-van-ākīrṇa , see Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=401" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साम्रपनस
s-āmra-panasa (EI 12), ‘together with mango and jack trees’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुछितदेयभागभोगकरहिरण्यादि
samucita-deya-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi (EI 23), same as sa-hiraṇya-bhāga-bhoga, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समुदयबाह्याद्यस्तम्ब
samudayabāhy-ādyastamba (EI 23), ‘[land] covered with original shrubs (i. e. never cultivated) and not yielding any revenue [to the State].’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समूल|समूलं
sa-mūla (EI 13), ‘together with the root crops’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निधानालीपक
sa-nidhān-ālīpaka-kumārīsāhas-āputrādhana-pradhān-āpradhāna-doṣa-samanvita (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 274), see the words as noticed separately above. The word doṣa here means ‘fines’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिधि
sa-nidhi (EI 27), refers to the freedom of the donee of the gift land from the obligation of surrendering to the king underground treasures in the land on their discovery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिधिनिधान
sa-nidhi-nidhāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139), same as sa-nidhi-nikṣepa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिधिनिक्षेप
sa-nidhi-nikṣepa , see nidhi, nikṣepa, nidhāna, ālipaka, etc., as noticed separately. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 396.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिध्युपनिधि
sa-nidhy-upanidhi (EI 26), same as sa-nidhi-nikṣepa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिम्नोन्नत
sa-nimn-onnata (IA 16), same as sa-khall-onnata.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनिर्गमप्रवेश
sa-nirgama-praveśa (EI 12), ‘together with ingress and egress’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सानूपजाङ्गल
s-ānūpa-jāṅgala (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 34, text line 5), same as sa-jāṅgal-ānūpa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपद्रारण्य
sa-padr-āraṇya (EI 23, 24), same as sa-padr-āraṇyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपद्रारण्यक
sa-padr-āraṇyaka (EI 12), ‘together with habitations and jungles’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपल्लिक
sa-pallika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘together with its hamlets’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपरिकर
sa-parikara (EI 23), same as or a mistake for s-oparikara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सपर्णाकर
sa-parṇ-ākara (EI 26), ‘together with the fields growing betel leaves’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सप्रतीहार
sa-pratīhāra , ‘together with the tax for the maintenance of the watchmen of the city gates’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वबाधापरिहार
sarva-bādhā-parihāra (EI 23, 24), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वबाधाविवर्जित
sarva-bādhā-vivarjita (EI 24), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाभ्यन्तरसिद्धि
sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi (EI 20; IA 19), ‘together with the entire internal revenue income or all the taxes to be paid to local authorities’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वाभ्यन्तरसिद्ध्या
sarv-ābhyantara-siddhyā (IA 18), same as sarv-ābhyantara-siddhi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादानदित्यविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहीन
sarv-ādāna-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna (CII 4), ‘free [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-403" target="_blank">Page-403+ 40</a>] from all levies, ditya, forced labour and prātibhedikā’. See ditya and prātibhedikā as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=402" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादानसङ्ग्राह्य
sarv-ādāna-saṅgrāhya (6II 4), ‘with the right to levy all the dues’; same as sarv-ādāya-sameta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादानविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहीन
sarv-ādāna-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna (CII 4), ‘free from the payment of all imposts and the obligation regarding unpaid labour and prātibhedikā’; epithet of gift village. See prāti-bhedikā as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादायसमेत
sarv-ādāya-sameta (EI 23), same as sarv-ādāna-saṅgrāhya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वादेयविशुद्ध
sarv-ādeya-viśuddha (CII 4), ‘with all kinds of taxes fixed’; same as sarv-ādāya-sameta (cf. sarv-āya-viśuddha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदित्यविष्टिजेमककरभरपरिहीन
sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-jemaka-kara-bhara-parihīna (CII 4), ‘free from the burden of all the ditya, forced labour, jemaka and taxes’. See ditya and jemaka as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदित्यविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहीन
sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna (EI 9; CII 4), ‘free from all kinds of ditya, forced labour and prātibhedikā’. See the words as noticed separately.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वदित्यविष्टिप्रातिभेदिकापरिहृत
sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihṛta (Ep. Ind., Vol. VI, p. 298, text lines 201-21), same as sarva-ditya-viṣṭi-prātibhedikā-parihīna. See the words as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजातभोगनिरस्त
sarva-jāta-bhoga-nirasta , refers to a grant of land with all kinds of royal rights abrogated. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 390.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजातभोग
sarva-jāta-bhoga (EI 24), ‘together with all kinds of privileges to be enjoyed’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वजातपारिहारिक
sarva-jāta-pārihārika , cf. Prakrit sava-jāta-pārihārika (Select Inscriptions, pp. 92, 94), ‘endowed with all kinds of exemptions.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वकरपरिहार
sarva-kara-parihāra (EI 23, 27), ‘exemption from all taxes.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वकरसमेत
sarva-kara-sameta (EI EI 23, 27), ‘together with all taxes.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपङ्गपरिहृत
sarva-paṅga-parihṛta (EI 33), ‘free from all levies falling in the category of paṅga’. See paṅga noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपरिहारकारुदेय
sarva-parihāra-kārudeya (EI 24), refers to all kinds of exemptions including the dues from artisans.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपिडापरिहृत
sarva-piḍā-parihṛta (EI 23), same as sarva-pīḍā-varjita, sarva-pīḍā-vivarjita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपीडावर्जित
sarva-pīḍā-varjita (EI 23), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, sarva-bādhā-vivarjita, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वपीडाविवर्जित
sarva-pīḍā-vivarjita (EI 27), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वराजकीयानाम्
sarva-rājakīyānām = a-hasta-prakṣepaṇīyaḥ (CII 3), same as [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-404" target="_blank">Page-404+ 40</a>] a-bhaṭa-praveśa, a-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya, a-bhaṭa-cchātra-prāveśya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=403" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्ववाधाविवर्जित
sarva-vādhā-vivarjita , with vādhā in the place of bādhā; same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, sarva-pīḍā-varjita, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वविष्टिपरिहारपरिहृत
sarva-viṣṭi-parihāra-parihṛta (EI 23, 24, 26), ‘endowed with the exemptions from all kinds of unpaid labour’; epithet of the gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वायसहित
sarv-āya-sahita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XIX, p. 247, text line 203), ‘together with the entire income.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वायविशुद्ध
sarv-āya-viśuddha (EI 23), ‘having fixed and regular income.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोपद्रववर्जित
sarv-opadrava-varjita (EI 24), same as parihṛta-sarva-pīḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोपरिकरादानसहित
sarv-oparikar-ādāna-sahita , ‘together with the right to levy all minor taxes or taxes on temporary tenants’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोपरिकरकरादानसमेत
sarv-oparikara-kar-ādāna-sameta (EI 23), ‘together with all the levies falling in the categories of uparikara and kara’. See kara and uparikara as noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वोत्पत्तिसहित
sarv-otpatti-sahita (EI 23), ‘together with whatever is produced (i. e. crops or income).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्वेष्टिपरिहारपरिहृत
sarv-eṣṭi-parihāra-parihṛta (EI 27), sarv-eṣṭi may be a mistake for sarva-viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससैबर
sa-saibara (EI 17), also written sa-śaivara; ‘together with unassessed arable lands or the tax on farm-houses’; cf. śaivara and saibara noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससर्वपल्लिक
sa-sarva-pallika (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 129), ‘together with all the hamlets’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससर्वाशनेक्षुकर्पासशणाम्रमधूकादिभूरुह
sa-sarv-āśan-ekṣu-karpāsa-śaṇ-āmra-madhūk-ādi-bhūruha , ‘together with aśana (pītaśāla), sugarcane, cotton-plants, hemp-plants, mango, madhūka and other trees’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ससाटविटप
sa-sāṭa-viṭapa (EI 12), mistake or wrong reading of sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साष्टादशप्रकृत्य्
s-āṣṭādaśa-prakṛty=opeta (EI 2), ‘together with the eighteen (i. e. all) kinds of tenants (i. e. tenants belonging to all the communities)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सस्थावरजङ्गम
sa-sthāvara-jaṅgama , ‘together with the immovable and movable belongings [of the gift village]’. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतल
sa-tala (EI 12, 29), ‘together with the surface of the ground’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतालक
sa-tālaka (EI 12), ‘together with palmyra palms’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=404" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतन्तलिक
sa-tantalika (EI 12), ‘together with tamarind trees’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतन्तुवायगोकुटशौण्डिकादिप्रकृतिक
sa-tantuvāya-gokuṭa-śauṇḍik-ādi-prakṛtika , ‘together with such tenants as the weavers, cowherds or milkmen and vintners’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 393.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतर
sa-tara (EI 22), see sa-haṭṭa-ghaṭṭa-sa-tara.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

साटविविटपसमन्वित
s-āṭavi-viṭapa-samanvita (EI 23), ‘together with forests and shrubs’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतृणकाष्ठोदकोपेत
sa-tṛṇa-kāṣṭh-odak-opeta (EI 24), ‘together with the grass, fuel and waters [of the gift village]’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवनस्पत्युदकासीहारकुल्लकपानीयसमेत
sa-vanaspaty-udak-āsīhāra-kullaka-pānīya-sameta ‘together with the fruit-trees and various kinds of water courses’; epithet of gift land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवनश्वभ्रनिधान
sa-vana-śvabhra-nidhāna , ‘together with forests, pits and mines’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवातभूतप्रत्याय
sa-vāta-bhūta-pratyāya (EI 11; IA 9), same as sa-bhūta-vāta-pratyāya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सविटपलता
sa-viṭapa-latā (EI 24), ‘together with shrubs and creepers’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सविटपारण्य
sa-viṭap-āraṇya , ‘together with bushes and jungles’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवृक्षमालाकुल
sa-vṛkṣamālā-kula (EI 23; IA 11), ‘together with various gardens or plantations’. See nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सवृक्षमालानिधिनिक्षेपसहित
sa-vṛkṣamālā-nidhi-nikṣepa-sahita (EI 23), see sa-vṛkṣamālā-kula and sa-nidhi-nikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीमान्तर्गतवस्तुसहित
sīm-āntargata-vastu-sahita , ‘together with [all] things within the boundaries’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सीसूमधूकतालप्रभृतिनानावृक्षसमेत
sīsū-madhūka-tāla-prabhṛti-nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta , refers to the right to use various trees in the gift village without the king's permission which was necessary for the ordinary tenants. See nānā-vṛkṣa-sameta, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep. p. 401.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोद्देश
s-oddeśa (EI 12, 29), ‘together with the space above the surface of the ground’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोद्रङ्ग
s-odraṅga (EI 12, 27, 29), ‘together with the tax called udraṅga’. Udraṅga is = uddhāra, Tamil uttāra, fixed taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपजातान्यवस्तुक
s-opajāt-ānya-vastuka (EI 26), ‘together with all the articles that may be produced [in the gift land] other than those mentioned.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपनिधि
s-opanidhi (EI 12, 27), refers to the freedom of the donee of the gift land from the obligation of surrendering to the king any valuables found on it; cf. niṣepa in sa-nidhi-nikṣepa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=405" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपरिकर
s-oparikara (EI 12, 27, 29), sometimes quoted as sa-pari-kara; ‘together with minor taxes or taxes realisable from temporary tenants’; epithet of gift village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोपरिकरदण्ड
s-oparikara-daṇḍa (EI 27), ‘together with minor taxes (or the tax on temporary tenants) and fines.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोर्ध्वाधः
s-ordhv-ādhaḥ (EI 23), same as s-ādha-ūrdhva (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोर्ध्वाधश्
s-ordhv-ādhaś=catur-āghāṭa viśuddha (EI 24), see s-ordhv-ādhaḥ and catur-āghāṭa-viśuddha. Āghāṭa is often written āghāṭana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोषर
s-oṣara (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘together with barren lands (or saline spots)’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोषरावस्करस्थाननिवातलवणाकर
s-oṣar-āvaskara-sthāna-nivāta-lavaṇ-ākara (EI 22), see the various words as noticed above. Nivāta = āvāta.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोत्पध्यमानविष्टि
s-otpadhyamāna-viṣṭi (EI 11), same as s-otpadyamāna-viṣṭika (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोत्पध्यमानविष्टिक
s-otpadhyamāna-viṣṭika (EI 23, IA 11), ‘together with the right to get unpaid labour whenever that may be due from the tenants’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकृष्ट
su-kṛṣṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135), ‘well-cultivated’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुल्कदण्डदाण
śulka-daṇḍa-dāṇa-kāruka-maulika-śrotra-nidhi-nikṣepa-jala-paṣāṇa-tejaḥ-svāmyam=ity-ādy-aṣṭa-bhoga-sahitam , ‘together with right to the enjoyment of the gift land in eight ways such as the rights to tolls, fines (or obligations), customs duties, taxes on artisans, fixed revenue, rent of public buildings, treasure-trove, occasional finds or deposits, fishing, quarrying and tejaḥ-svāmya (full authority arising out of ownership).’ See the various words as noticed above. Cf. Ind. Ep., Vol. XXXII, p. 42.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुपल्लिकापेत
su-pallik-āpeta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 139), same as sa-pallika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णदण्डअहिदण्ड
suvarṇadaṇḍa-ahidaṇḍa-vartmadaṇḍa-vandāpanā-vijayandāpanā-tṛṇodaka-śāsanārdhika-cara(vara ?)balīvard-ārthāruvā-pratyarthāruvā-padātijīvya-ādattā-āturāvaḍḍi-bhaviṣyat-kar-ādi-sahita , refers to the right of the donee to levy various taxes, the nature of some of which is uncertain (see the different expressions as noticed above). These include tax on the goldsmiths and snake-charmers, tolls to be collected for using the road passing through the gift village for the transit of articles of merchandise, presents to be made to the king or landlord on occasions, especially on his return from a victorious campaign, etc. See hastidaṇḍa-varabalīvarda … above. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 402.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वच्छन्दोपभोगेन्
svacchand-opabhogen=opabhoktum , refers to the right of the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-407" target="_blank">Page-407+ 40</a>] donee to enjoy the gift land according to his own free will. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 399.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=406" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमापर्यन्त
sva-sīmā-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as its boundaries’; epithet of gift land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणगोचरगोयूतिपर्यन्त
sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-gocara-goyūti-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as the grass land on the boundaries as well as the pasture lands and goyūti’. Goyūti may be an enclosure for cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणकाष्ठयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त
sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-kāṣṭha-yūti-gocara-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as the yūti (preserve) of grass and wood as well as the pasture lands on the boundaries’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त
sva-sīmā-tṛṇayūti-gocara-paryanta (EI 23), ‘as far as the preserve of grass as well as the pasture lands on the boundaries’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणगोयूथीगोचरपर्यन्त
sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-goyūthī-gocara-paryanta , same as sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta, yūthī being a synonym of yūti (also spelt pūti), probably meaning ‘a preserve’. See sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-gocara-goyūti-paryanta, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 394.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमातृणयूतिगोचरपर्यन्त
sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti-gocara-paryanta , ‘as far as its boundaries, the yūti of grass and pasture land’; cf. Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वसीमावच्छिन्न
sva-sīm-āvacchinna , ‘with its boundaries demarcated’; epithet of gift village. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 395.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभेद्याघाणकमल्लकवुन्दकदण्डदोषप्राप्तादाय
talabhedyā-ghāṇaka-mallaka-vundaka-daṇḍadoṣa-prāpt-ādāya (Ind. Ant., Vol. XVIII, p. 83, text lines 19-20), see the words as noticed separately above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलभेद्यागोवाटिका
talabhedyā-govāṭikā-śākamuṣṭi-tailapalikā-kumbhapūrak-ākāśotpati-pātāla-nidhi-nikṣhepa-devāyatan-odyāna-taḍāga-vāpī-kup-ādi-sahita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXII, p. 155).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिलदर्भोदकपवित्रपाणिना
tila-darbh-odaka-pavitra-pāṇinā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 135, text line 23), cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणकाष्ठोदकोपेत
tṛṇa-kāṣṭh-odak-opeta (EI 23), ‘together with grass and fuel and the waters’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तृणपूति
tṛṇa-pūti(or yūti)-gocara-paryanta (EI 12), epithet of gift land; see sva-sīmā-tṛṇa-yūti (or pūti)-gocara-paryanta, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकपूर्वम्
udaka-pūrvam , cf. udak-ātisargeṇa, udakena, tila-darbh-odaka-pavitra-pāṇinā, kuśa-lalā-pūta-hast-odakena, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उदकेन
udakena , cf. udaka-pūrvam, etc. Cf. Ind. Ep., pp. 136-37.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उद्बलिक
udbalika , ‘free from land tax’; cf. utpratikara. Cf. Prakrit ubalika (Select Inscriptions, p. 70).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उम्बरभेदः|उम्बरभेद
umbara-bhedaḥ rājapuruṣāṇām=āvāsako jemakaś=ca n=āsti , ‘there is no entry of royal officers into a house with its door [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-408" target="_blank">Page-408+ 37</a>] closed (referring especially to the houses of merchants away from home on business tours abroad) nor should there be any provision for their accommodation and meals’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 232-33.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=407" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उञ्छकरभरादिविवर्जित
uñcha-kara-bhar-ādi-vivarjita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 89); see uñcha, etc., as noticed separately above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उर्ध्वाधःसिद्धियुत
urdhv-ādhaḥ-siddhi-yuta (IA 18), ‘together with the income from fruits and roots.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्प्रतिकर
utpratikara (EI 23), same as a-kiñcit-pratikara; cf. udbalika.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वनवाटिकातृणजन्तुगोचरपर्यन्त
vana-vāṭikā-tṛṇa-jantu-gocara-paryanta (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXIII p. 229), ‘including forests, gardens, grass fields and pasture lands for cattle and animals.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वास्तुक्षेत्रजलाधारगर्तामार्गसमन्वित
vāstu-kṣetra-jalādhāra-gartā-mārga-samanvita (EI 22), ‘together with homestead lands, tanks, pits, pathways and roads’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वातोडरीय
vātoḍarīya (EI 22), epithet of gift land; probably a corruption of vāt-ottarīya; cf. sa-bhūta-vāt-ādeya, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथादीयमान
yathādīyamāna-bhāgabhogakara-paravaṇikara-kūṭaka-prabhṛti-samast-ādāya , sometimes with turuṣka-daṇḍa and kumāra-gady-āṇaka in place of kūṭaka, and hiraṇya, jalakara, gokara, nidhi-nikṣepa, yamali-kambali, etc., added to the list. Bhāga-bhoga-kara means ‘taxes in general together with the king's share of grains and the periodical offerings payable to him.’ For pravaṇi-kara, kūṭaka and yamalikambali, see the words as noticed above. Turuṣkadaṇḍa was a tax levied from the Muhammadan subjects or for the defence of the kingdom from Muhammadan attacks and Kumāra-gadyāṇa may be a tax of one gaḍyāṇa levied on the occasion of a prince's birth. Hiraṇya is ‘tax in cash’, jala-kara fishing tax, go-kara grazing tax, nidhi treasure-trove and nikṣepa valuables found or accumulated on the land. Cf. Ind. Ep., p. 397.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथाप्रदीयमानभागभोगहिरण्यादिक
yathā-pradīyamāna-bhāga-bhoga-hiraṇy-ādika (EI 23), ‘whatever is payable as bhāga-bhoga, hiraṇya, etc.’ See the words as noticed separately; also yathā-samucita-bhāga-bhoga-kara-hiraṇy-ādi-sarva-rāja-bhāvya-pratyāya (Ind. Ep., p. 394).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यथोत्पद्यमानभागभोगादिक
yath-otpadyamāna-bhāga-bhog-ādika (EI 23), ‘with the power to realise bhāga, bhoga, etc., whenever they become due.’ See the words as noticed separately above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=408" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अभिषेकक्काणिक्कै
abhiṣeka-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; presents offered to a king at the time of his coronation.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आचार्यपूजनै
ācārya-pūjanai (SITI), honorarium payable to priests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुतरि
accu-tar̤i, accu-ttar̤i (SITI), Tamil; a variety of loom; tax payable on looms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चुवरि
accu-vari (SITI), Tamil; probably, the same as pŏn-vari; duty payable for minting gold or metal into coins; cf. akkaśālai-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारप्पेरु
adhikāra-pper̤u (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; probably, presents offered to an officer.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अधिकारवर्त्तनै
adhikāra-varttanai (SITI), customary payments made to an officer at stipulated periods.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिमैक्काशु
aḍimai-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; fee collected from temple servants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिक्काशु
aḍi-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax collected from stall-keepers in markets.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आडिप्पच्चै
āḍi-ppaccai (SITI), Tamil; probably, prerequisites^1 payable in grain in the month of Āḍi after the harvest.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिरैप्पाट्टम्
ādirai-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on cattle; cf. attir̤ai-pāṭṭam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आडुक्कलैप्पुरम्
āḍukkalai-ppur̤am (SITI), Tamil; an endowment^1 for the kitchen expenses of a temple.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कशालैवरि
akkaśālai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax payable to the mint for minting coins; cf. accu-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आलमञ्जि
āl̤-amañji (SII 12), a levy; explained as ‘workmen pressed into service without wages’ (SITI); Sanskrit viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्लायमान्यम्
al̤l̤āya-mānyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; probably, the right to receive a handful of grain or a prescribed quantity of an article sold in the market as wages for measuring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आल्नेल्
āl̤-něl, āṇěl (SITI), Tamil; a tax payable in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अल्पमिरै
alpamirai (SITI), Tamil; a minor tax payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलु|अलुः
al̤u (SITI), Tamil; a variety of market dues; probably, the same as al̤l̤u and al̤l̤āya-mānyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलुगल्शरक्कु
al̤ugal-śarakku (SITI), Tamil; the right of collecting the refuse and waste thrown in the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=409" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आल्वरि
āl̤-vari (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; poll-tax. See per-kkaḍamai, per-vāśi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आ
ān̤ai-ccālai (SITI), Tamil; ‘an elephant stable’; tax payable for the maintenance of the elephant stable.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आण्डे
āṇḍ-el̤̣uttu-ttevai (SITI), Tamil, a tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्गाडिक्कूलि
aṅgāḍi-kkūli, aṅgāḍi-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on bazars, shops, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्नियायवावदण्डइरै
anniyāya-vāva-daṇḍa-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; penal tax imposed on some unauthorised item of occupation or enjoyment.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरविनियोगम्
antara-viniyogam (SITI), Sanskrit; individual share to make up the shortage in the total revenue occasioned by the grant of exemptions of antar-āyam or ul̤-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरायम्
antar-āyam (SITI), Sanskrit; internal revenue; taxes levied by a local body; also called ul̤-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्तरायक्काशु
antarāya-kkāśu, antarāya-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; internal taxes; minor taxes like the profession tax, etc., payable to the village assembly.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनुवर्त्तनै
anuvarttanai (SITI), a class of contingent dues which come under the head varttanai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरक्कल्
arakkal (SITI), Tamil; an instalment of land-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरन्दै
arandai (EI 18), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरशुप्पेरु
araśu-pper̤u (SITI), Tamil; same as mahārāja-prayojana; probably, fees collected for payment for the performance of police duties in the rural areas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आराय्च्चि
ārāycci, kāriyav-ārāycci (SITI), Tamil; cess paid for the superintendence of transactions.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्चनाभोग
arcanā-bhoga, arcanā-vṛtti (SITI), Sanskrit; land set apart for meeting the expenses of worship (arcanā) in the village temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिको
arikol̤̣i, ariśi-ttuṇḍam (SITI), taxes of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिकूलि
arikūli (SITI), Tamil; dues payable in handfuls of the stalks harvested.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिमुक्कै
arimukkai (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिप्पदिक्कावल्
arippadikkāval (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरिशिक्काणम्
ariśi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax for husking paddy into rice.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्रङ्करैत्तेवै
ār̤r̤aṅkarai-ttevai (SITI), Tamil; tax for keeping the river-bund in repair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=410" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्रुक्कुलै
ār̤r̤u-kkulai (SITI), Tamil; ‘river-bund’; tax to repair breaches in the river-bund.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आर्रुक्कालमञ्जि
ār̤r̤ukkāl-amañji (SITI), Tamil; unpaid labour to keep the channel from the river in good repair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अरुन्तोडु
aruntoḍu (SITI), Tamil; ‘eating-plate’; a tax payable according to the number of eating plates in feeding houses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुविकल्कासु
āśuvikal̤-kāsu, āśuva-kkāśu, āśuva-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable by the Ājīvakas or for maintaining^1 Ājīvaka monks.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आट्चिप्पाट्टम्
āṭci-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; probably, a succession tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आतीरै
ātīrai (SITI), Tamil; probably, the expenses for the ārdrā festival in the month of Mārgal̤̣i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अटियुरै
aṭiyur̤ai (SITI), Tamil; offerings made at the feet of a high personage; written differently as aḍiyir̤ai, aḍiyar̤ai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आट्टैक्कानिक्कै
āṭṭai-kkānikkai (SITI), Tamil; annual contribution or presents.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अत्तिरैप्पाट्टम्
attir̤ai-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on cattle; cf. ādiraipāṭṭam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टणैक्काल्
aṭṭaṇaikkāl (SITI), Tamil; a kind of stand or pedestal (probably of eight legs).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आट्टुक्कीरै
āṭṭukk-īr̤ai, āṭṭir̤ai (SITI) Tamil; tax on sheep; also called āṭṭu-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अट्टुक्किरै
aṭṭukkir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; tax on charities.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आवणम्
āvaṇam (SITI), Tamil a document; generally, a saledeed; also called vilaiy-āvaṇam.; cf. āvaṇa-kkal̤ari (SITI), place where documents like the sale-deeds, etc., are registered; a registration office.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अवसरवर्त्तनै
avasara-varttanai (SITI), presents payable to an Avasara, an officer of the royal household having the duty of bringing to the notice of the king anything that demanded his immediate attention.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आयम्
āyam (SITI); ‘income’; tax in general.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बण्णिगितेरे
baṇṇigitěre , Kannaḍa; a kind of levy (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिल्कोडे
bil̤koḍě (EI 28), Kannaḍa; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिराड
birāḍa (EI 24), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बण्णिगे
baṇṇigě (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भत्ताय
bhatt-āya (SII 11-1), same as Sanskrit bhakt-āya.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिट्टि
biṭṭi (SII 11-1), same as Sanskrit viṣṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बित्तुकट्टे
bittu-kaṭṭě , Kannaḍa; same as bittu-vaṭṭa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बित्तुवट्ट
bittu-vaṭṭa , a portion of the produce from the land irrigated [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-412" target="_blank">Page-412+ 40</a>] by a tank, granted to a person who excavated or repaired the tank (A. R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 10).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=411" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ब्राह्मणराशक्काणम्
brāhmaṇa-rāśa(rāja)-kkāṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax payable by the Brāhmaṇa (purohita) to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चक्रकाणिक्कै
cakra-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; profession-tax paid by the potters; also called tirigai-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दण्डकाणम्
daṇḍa-kāṇam (SII 13), fines.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दशबन्ध|दशबन्धः
daśabandha (SITI), Sanskrit; tax or cess levied to keep the sources of water supply, like the tank, etc., in good repair.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यादाय
dhāny-ādāya (SITI), Sanskrit; tax payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यवर्ग
dhānya-varga , cf. tāniya-varakkam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरडु
eraḍu dogarāca-ppaṇṇu (EI 30), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एच्चोरु
eccor̤u (SII 13), a tax or the obligation of free feeding.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडैवरि
eḍai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on weights.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडुत्तुक्कोट्टै
eḍuttu-kkoṭṭai (SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एडुत्तुक्कोट्टि
eḍuttukkoṭṭi (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एलवै
elavai (SITI), also spelt ělavai; Tamil; death-duty; fee for crematorium^1.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ए
ěl̤̣uttu-viniyogam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; dues payable as ěl̤̣uttu for the village-accountant to be apportioned among the villagers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एणिक्काणम्
eṇi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; ladder tax evidently levied on toddy-drawers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एण्णेय्
ěṇṇěy (SITI), Tamil; tax levied on the oil-trade; obligation for the supply of oil.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरडुबिल्कोदे
eraḍu-bil̤koḍě (IE 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिआयम्
eri-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; income from fishing in the tank, etc.; amount payable by the owners of the fields irrigated by the tank for its upkeep.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिईवु
eri-īvu (SITI), Tamil; share in the expenses of the maintenance of the tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एर्क्कडमै
er-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax on ploughs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एर्प्पोन्
er-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax to be paid in cash for each plough; also called er-kkaṇikkai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरुमैप्पोन्
erumai-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax payable on buffaloes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिक्काडि
erikkāḍi (SII 12), tank cess of one kāḍi of paddy per field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

एरिमीन्पाट्टम्
eri-mīn̤-pāṭṭam (SII 12), a tax; income from fish in the tank.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेज्जुङ्क
hějjuṅka , same as pěrjuṅka, Kannaḍa; name of tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडङ्गैवरि
iḍaṅgai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax paid by the members of the iḍaṅgai community or the left-hand classes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=412" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडैप्पाट्टम्
iḍai-ppāṭṭam , also called iḍai-ppūṭci (SITI), Tanmil; tax on herdsmen or cattle-breeders.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडैत्तुरै
iḍaittur̤ai , also spelt iḍator̤ai (SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडैयर्वरि
iḍaiyar-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on shepherds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इलैवाणियप्पाट्टम्
ilaivāṇiya-ppāṭṭam (SITI), tax on the sellers of betel-leaves.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडतोरै
iḍator̤ai , see iḍaittur̤ai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इलक्कुलम्
ilakkulam (SII 13), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इळम्पुञ्जै
il̤am-puñjai, īl̤am-puṭci (SITI), Tamil; tax for toddy-drawing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इलाञ्जनैप्पेरु
ilāñjanai-pper̤u , also called lāñjinai-pper̤u, lāñjanai-pper̤u (SITI), Tamil; fee for affixing the royal seal; ilāñjanai = Sanskrit lāñchana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इल्वरि
ilvari (SITI), Tamil; house-tax; cf. manai-ppaṇam, manav-ir̤ai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इनवरि
inavari (SII 12), inavari-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; communal tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरै
ir̤ai (SII 13; SITI), Tamil; a general term denoting revenue income and the taxes to be paid to government; land tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैद्रव्यम्
ir̤ai-dravyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; explained as a lump sum paid in lieu of land tax; amount payable in commutation of the taxes payable on landed property.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैकावल्
$4ir̤ai-kāval (SITI), Tamil; amount of deposit which yielded interest per annum equal to the tax due on the land; sometimes regarded as a tax for police duties.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैयिलिमुदल्
ir̤aiyili-mudal (SII 13), same as ir̤ai-dravyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरैयिलिक्काशु
ir̤aiyili-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; amount paid for compounding taxes in order to make the land tax-free; also regarded as the amount payable to meet the shortage in the revenue occasioned by the grant of exemption from tax on certain lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईरङ्कोल्लि
īraṅkolli, īraṅkol̤l̤i (SITI), Tamil; ‘a washerman’; tax payable by washermen.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरवु
iravu (EI 30), Tamil; royal dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इरुप्पुक्कट्टि
iruppu-kkaṭṭi (SITI), Tamil; probably, the cake of the Mahua seeds after the extraction of oil, largely used as soap; tax for the manufacture and sale of such cakes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इशैक्किडाय्
iśai-kkiḍāy (SITI), Tamil; ‘beautiful ram’; dues to be paid for the ram kept for show; cf. al̤̣ag-erudu-kkāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जोडि
joḍi , also spelt śoḍi (SITI), Tamil; name of a small quitrent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडैवडैक्काय्
kaḍai-vaḍaikkāy (SITI), Tamil; tax on arecanuts brought for sale.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=413" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कडमै
kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; revenue, tax to be paid to the government in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कदिर्क्काणम्
kaḍir-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax paid in sheaves of corn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काडुकावल्
kāḍu-kāval (SITI), Tamil; tax for the preservation and maintenance of forests.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कणक्कमिकुदि
kaṇakka-mikudi (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कल्लवलिक
kal̤l̤avalika (EI 28), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानिक
kānika , Kannaḍa; also called kāṇika-kaně.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कनिकेकप्प
kanikě-kappa, kappa-kānikě, etc.; customary presents; presents from inferior to superior (EI 33).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिक्कै
kāṇikkai (EI 17, 21; SITI), Tamil; presents or customary payment as offerings to the king and other high officials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कण्णालक्काणम्
kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam (SII 13; EI 28), marriage fee; collected by the village assembly; same as vivāha-ppaṇam; cf. ugappār-pŏn.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः
kan̤n̤ār-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; profession tax payable by a brazier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कानुक
kānuka (CITD), same as kāṇika, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कप्प
kappa (EI 33), Kannaḍa; tolls;<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करणिक्कजोडि
karaṇikka-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), quit-rent of the Karaṇam or Karṇam (village-accountant or Paṭvārī).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काराण्मै
kārāṇmai (SITI), Tamil; a tenure with the hereditary right of enjoyment; cultivation right; tax for the same; also known as kārāṇkil̤amai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारियप्पेरु
kāriya-pper̤u (SITI), Tamil; probably, the same as kāriya-vārāycci, ārāycci.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कारियवाराय्च्चि
kāriya-vārāycci (SITI), Tamil; cess paid for the superintendence of transactions; same as ārāycci.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्कडमै
kār̤-kaḍamai (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्प्पूरविलै
karppūra-vilai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; sale-price paid for temple lands; price paid for cultivation rights of temple lands and in commutation of the taxes thereon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्त्तिगैक्काशु
kārttigai-kkāśu, kārttigai-kkāṇi, kārttigai-ppaccai, kārttigaiy-ariśi (SITI), Tamil; payments in kind in the month of Kārttigai, i. e. during the harvest; cf. āḍi-ppaccai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुविपणम्
karuvi-paṇam, karivi-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on the implements in cash, probably paid by the barbers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुवूलवरि
karuvūla-vari (SITI), Tamil; fee for the safe-custody of precious articles in the treasury; or fee for the watch of the treasury.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशायम्
kāś-āyam (SITI), kāśu-āyam; Tamil-Sanskrit; tax and [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-415" target="_blank">Page-415+ 40</a>] dues payable in coin; also called kāśāya-vargam, kāśu-vargam and kāśu-kaḍamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=414" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशुकडमै
kāśu-kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काट्चि
kāṭci (SITI), Tamil; presents offered to a highly superior person at the time of meeting.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काट्चियेरदुक्काशु
kāṭciy-ěrudu-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on bulls kept for show.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काट्टाल्काशु
kāṭṭāl̤-kāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टणम्
kaṭṭaṇam (SITI), Tamil; periodical presents made to superiors by their subordinates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टायम्
kaṭṭ-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; consolidated amount payable for the minor taxes; also written as kaṇḍ-āyam; sometimes taken as the compulsory payment of certain dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कत्तिगैप्पच्चै
kattigai-ppaccai (SII 12), see kārtigai-kkāśu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कत्तिक्काणम्
katti-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on weapons like sword, etc., or tax on the manufacture of swords or arms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टुक्कुत्तगै
kaṭṭu-kkuttagai (SITI), Tamil; rent fixed at the time of farming out the land; payment of consolidated rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कट्टुमुक्कै
kaṭṭumukkai (SITI), Tamil; ‘three handfuls in the bundle’; a contribution of three handfuls for every bundle of paddy stalks harvested, which were payable to the temples; cf. arimukkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कावल्पेरु
kāval-per̤u (SII 12), name of a tax; cf. kāval-kāni, the right to guard temples.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कि
kil̤̣-ir̤ai (SITI; SII 12), Tamil; minor taxes, or tax fixed at a lower rate.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

की
kīl̤̣-ir̤ai-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; small cesses and taxes like mīn-pāṭṭam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कीर्रुवरि
kīr̤r̤u-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on thatched sheds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

किरुकुल
kirukula (SITI), Tamil; commercial tax or tolls on retail articles; also called kirukūla-viśeṣam; cf. kūlam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोडिक्कडमि
kŏḍi-kkaḍami (SITI), Tamil; explained as a tax for the cultivation of the medicinal plant kŏḍi-veli, otherwise known as citra-mūlam; probably, the same as kodi-kkaḍamai, tax on new cloth; cf. tiru-ppudiyidu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्कूलि
kol-kūli (SITI), Tamil; tax for measuring or weighing.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्निरैकूलि
kol-nir̤ai-kūli (SITI), Tamil; tax on articles measured by weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्मुरैप्पाडु
kŏl̤mur̤ai-ppāḍu (SITI), Tamil; customary dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलु
kŏl̤u (SITI), Tamil; tax on ploughshares.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल्वरि
kŏl̤vari (SITI), Tamil; tax in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=415" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोमुरै
ko-mur̤ai (SITI), Tamil; revenue due to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोपदवारम्
ko-pada-vāram (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax due to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टैक्कूलि
koṭṭai-kkūli (SITI); ‘wages on nuts’; probably, charges for the upkeep of forts; cf. koṭṭai-magamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोट्टैमगमै
koṭṭai-magamai (SITI), Tamil; tax for the maintenance of forts.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोयिल्वाशि
koyil-vāśi (SITI), Tamil; minor taxes payable to the palace.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुडिक्काणम्
kuḍi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; fee paid by the tenants; probably, the same as kuḍi-kkāśu and kuḍi-ppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुडिमै
kuḍimai (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; taxes in general (with the exception of land revenue) payable to the state for the protection of the civil rights it offers; tenancy tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैमार्रु
kuḍirai-mār̤r̤u (SITI), Tamil; tax on horses.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैप्पन्दि
kuḍirai-ppandi (SITI), Tamil; ‘a stable’; tax for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैवरि
kuḍirai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on horses; also known as kudirai-mār̤r̤u, kudiraiv-ilāḍam; probably the same as kudirai-ppandi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुदिरैविलाडम्
kuḍiraiv-ilāḍam (SITI), Tamil; ‘horse-shoe’; fee for shoeing horses; probably connected with kudirai-ppandi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलवडै
kul̤avaḍai (EI 17), tax for the enjoyment of the tank and its income.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूलम्
kūlam (SITI), Tamil; tax on grains and pulses; cf. kirukulam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमरकच्चाणम्
kumara-kaccāṇam (SITI), Tamil; explained as a tax payable in coin for the maintenance of the temple of Kumāra or Subrahamaṇya; but same as kumāra-gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कूर्ररिशि
kūr̤r̤ariśi (SITI), Tamil; obligation of husking paddy belonging to the temple into rice and the charges to be met for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुर्रुनेल्
kur̤r̤u-něl, kūr̤r̤u-něllu (SITI), Tamil; tax for husking paddy payable to king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुशक्काणम्
kuśa-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on potters; also known as tirigaiāyam, śakkara-kkāṇikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लञ्जनैप्पेरु
lañjanai-pper̤u, lañjinai-pper̤u , see ilañjanai-pper̤u.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडैक्कूलि
māḍai-kkūli (SITI), Tamil; tax for minting gold into coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मादाप्पडि
māḍā-ppaḍi (SITI), Tamil; allowances payable monthly; also called mādārikka, mādan and mādārikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडुकाणिक्कै
māḍu-kāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; obligation of supplying draught cattle to the visiting^1 nobles by the tenants.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=416" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मगमै
magamai, maganmai, magaṇmai (SITI), Tamil; small portion of the income or of the value of articles of merchandise collected as voluntary contribution by the merchants from among themselves for the maintenance of temples, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मगन्मै
maganmai (SITI), Tamil; poll-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मक्कल्पेरु
makkal̤-per̤u (SITI), Tamil; one's obligations as a citizen; probably, dues payable to a temple, or poll-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लायिमघमै
mallāyi-maghamai (SITI), Tamil; probably a customary collection in the market.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मामगम्
māmagam (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash probably for the great Māgha (Mahāmāgha) festival; or, a mistake for mārgam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनैमेय्प्पान्कोल्लुमिरै
manai-meyppān-kol̤l̤um-ir̤ai , tax for the supervisor of houses or the building-supervisor; cf. meyppān (SITI), Tamil; ‘shepherd; grazier;’ a supervisor; probably related to kaṇkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मनैप्पणम्
manai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; house tax; also called manai-vari. Cf. ilvari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म|मः
man̤aiy-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; house-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्दैप्पणम्
mandai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on cattle grazing in the village common.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्डलमुदन्मैप्पेरु
maṇḍala-mudanmai-pper̤u (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; fee for presents offered to the rulers of the maṇḍala or district.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्मदिल्
maṇ-madil (SITI), Tamil; ‘high wall or rampart made of mud’; tax for the erection and upkeep of such a wall.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पदक्कु
māppadakku (SITI), Tamil; payment at the rate of one padakku or two kuruṇi for every mā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पणम्
māppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; a tax payable at the rate of one paṇam for every mā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पट्टडै
māppaṭṭaḍai (SITI), Tamil; tax probably for the penning of cattle; may also be mara-ppaṭṭaḍai, ‘a timber depot’; tax payable for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरक्कडमै
mara-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable for trees.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरमञ्जाडि
mara-mañjāḍi (SITI), Tamil; tax of one mañjāḍi for every tree.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मार्गादायम्
mārg-ādāyam (SITI), Sanskrit; tolls on the articles in transit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरियादि
mariyādi (SITI), Tamil; customary dues; also spelt mar-jādi, mariśādi, maruśādi, etc., and used in the sense of manner, way, extent, limit.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माट्टुक्करै
māṭṭukkar̤ai (SITI), Tamil; probably, a tax on cattle (cows and buffaloes).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=417" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माविन्दक्कडमै
māvinda-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेलडि
melaḍi (SITI), Tamil; taxes paid in kind.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्विट्टियवड्दारवुल
melviṭṭiya-vaḍḍāravul̤a , cf. vaḍḍāravul̤a.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेल्वेट्टप्पेरु
mel-věṭṭa-pper̤u (SITI), land set apart for meeting expenses of public works (věṭṭi).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मे
men̤i-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; poll-tax; tax on individuals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेरै
merai (SITI), Tamil; portion of the crop given at the threshing floor to certain village officers and servants as perquisite.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेर्पाडिकावल्
mer-pāḍi-kāval (SITI), Tamil; policing duty over the nāḍu. See nāḍu-kāval.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मेट्टुनिलम्
meṭṭu-nilam (SITI), Tamil; ‘high land’; tax payable for the cultivation of such land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिलगुतरगु
mil̤agu-taragu (SITI), Tamil; brokerage on pepper trade.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोनम्पाट्टम्
monampāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदर्रिरमन्
mudar̤r̤iraman, mudal-tiramam (SITI), Tamil; tax (payable in cash) of uncertain import; tiramam is the coin called dramma (from Greek drachma).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुल्लडिशिन्नम्
mul̤l̤aḍiśinnam (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a tax of uncertain import; probably, payment for clue in detection.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मूङ्गिल्वरि
mūṅgil-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax on bamboos.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुत्तावणम्
muttāvaṇam (SITI), Tamil; a tax probably on the sale of pearls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुकावल्
nāḍu-kāval (SITI), Tamil; ‘policing duty of the nāḍu’; tax payable by the residents in the division for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाडुतलैयारिक्कम्
nāḍu-talaiyārikkam (SITI), Tamil; police-tax of the nāḍu; same as nāḍu-kāval.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्किडा
nal-kiḍā, nar̤-kiḍā (SITI), Tamil; cess for the upkeep of the show-ram; or, tax for show-rams.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्लेरुदु
nall-ěrudu (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; cess for the maintenance of a model bull, which was probably also used for breeding purposes; cf. al̤̣agerudu-kkāśu, kāṭci-ěrudu-kkāśu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्लेरुमै
nall-erumai (SITI), tax for the maintenance of specimen buffaloes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नर्किडा
nar̤-kiḍā (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टुक्कणक्कुवरि
nāṭṭu-kkaṇakku-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax payable for the maintenance of the revenue accounts of the nāḍu or the country as a whole.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाटुक्काणिक्कै
nāṭu-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; presents payable to or by the assembly of the nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=418" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टुपाति
nāṭṭupāti (SITI), Tamil; nāḍu-upādi; the obligations to be met and taxes payable to the local assembly of the nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाट्टुविनियोगम्
nāṭṭu-viniyogam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; individual share payable to make up the shortage in the total revenue by the grant of exemptions by the assembly of the nāḍu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेल्लायम्
něll-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax payable in paddy; also known as něr̤-kaḍamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेय्
něy (SITI), Tamil; tax on the traders in ghee; same as něy-vilai; cf. also eṇṇěy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निलत्तिरप्पुकडमै
nilattir̤appu-kaḍamai (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीराणिक्कवरि
nīrāṇikka-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax for the supervision of the regulation of water supply in a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीर्क्काणम्
nīr-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; water-cess; also known as nīr-vilai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीर्निलैक्काशु
nīr-nilai-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tank-cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निरुणिसुङ्क
niruṇi-suṅka (SII 11-1), water tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नीर्विलै
nīr-vilai (SITI), Tamil; water-cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नूलायम्
nūl-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on cotton thread for weaving cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओलिवण्णार्पारै
ol̤i-vaṇṇār̤-pār̤ai (SITI), Tamil; tax payable by the washerman calculated on the number of washing stones.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पच्चैप्पणम्
paccai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil; payment in cash towards the obligation of paccai payable in kind; also referred to as paccai-ppāṭṭam. Cf. Kārttigai-paccai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडैप्पणम्
paḍai-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax for the maintenance of an army unit or fee from the army; also known as paḍai-kkāṇikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पडन्क
paḍan-kal̤̣i (SITI), Tamil; an obligation of uncertain import.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडवरि
pāḍavari (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on metallic mirrors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदवारम्
padavāram , also spelt paduvāram (SITI), Tamil; fee payable for exchanging landed property; transfer fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाडिक्कावल्
pāḍikkāval (SITI), Tamil; ‘watch or the police duties of the village’; contribution for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुवारम्
paduvāram , cf. padavāram.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प|पं|पः
pal̤̣anel (SII 13), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पालिक्कप्पाट्टम्
pālikka-ppāṭṭam (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणवर्गम्
paṇa-vargam (SITI), Sanskrit; class of taxes payable in cash; same as kāśāya-vargam; cf. paṇam, coin, money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=419" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणवाशि
paṇa-vāśi (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; discount payable for the exchange of coins; amount payable to make up the wear in the coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चवारवूरिडुवरि
pañca-vārav-ūr-iḍu-vari (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; levied by the pañca-vāriyam (the five committees) of the local assembly (ūr).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चुप्पीलि
pañcu-ppīli (SITI EI 24), Tamil; tax on cotton; also referred to as pāñjupili.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्डवेट्टि
paṇḍa-věṭṭi (SITI), Tamil; a variety of věṭṭi, probably for the temple lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाण्डिवरि
pāṇḍivari (SITI), Tamil; probably tax on carts drawn by bulls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणिक्कोत्तु
paṇi-kkŏttu (SITI), Tamil; ‘village servants’; cess collected for their maintenance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्कुरुणि
paṇ-kur̤uṇi (SITI), Tamil; cess payable at the rate of one kur̤uṇi of the produce for each field.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पन्नाय
pannāya (IE 8-5; EI 27), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारैक्काणम्
pār̤ai-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax on washing stone payable by washermen; sometimes explained as the tax on quarries.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परैत्तरि
par̤ai-ttar̤i (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; a variety of handloom; the tax for the same.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परैयिरै
par̤aiy-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; a tax [payable in cash] probably for tomtoms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशानम्
paśānam (EI 23), name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाशिप्पाट्टम्
pāśi-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; tax on fishing; same as mīn-pāṭṭam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टाडैआयम्
paṭṭāḍai-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on silk cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टाडैनूलायम्
paṭṭāḍai-nūl-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on silk thread used for weaving cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टडैवरि
paṭṭaḍai-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax probably for the use of the threshing floor.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टम्
pāṭṭam (SITI EI 21), Tamil; tax or rent; payable probably for an industry or a profession.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाट्टनेल्
pāṭṭa-něl (SITI), Tamil; paddy to be paid by the tenant to the landlord as per terms of lease.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टयक्काणिक्कै
paṭṭaya-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; fee for the issue of royal charters.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिक्काडि
paṭṭi-kkāḍi (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in grain at the rate of one kāḍi for each paṭṭi of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिक्काल्
paṭṭi-kkāl (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash at the rate of one fourth (probably of paṇam) for each paṭṭi of land.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=420" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिगैक्काणम्
paṭṭigai-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; obligation to pay at the rate of one kāṇam for each paṭṭi of land; probably, the same as paṭṭaya-kkāṇikkai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टिप्पोन्
paṭṭi-ppŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पट्टित्तण्डम्
paṭṭi-ttaṇḍam (SITI), Tamil; probably, punitive tax of a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावै
pāvai (EI 8-5), similar to Persian nazarāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेज्जुङ्क
pějjuṅka (EI 8-5), Kannaḍa; name of tax; also spelt pěrjuṅka, pěrujuṅka, hějjuṅka; probably derived from piriya-suṅka = Sanskrit bṛhac-chulka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्जुङ्क
pěrjuṅka , cf. pějjuñka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेर्क्कडमै
pěr-kkaḍamai (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; explained as poll tax, the same as āl̤vari; (also called pervāśi); but may be a payment to be made on the occasion of the naming ceremony of a child.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुजुङ्क
pěrujuṅka , cf. pějjuṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पेरुम्पाडिकावल्
perum-pāḍi-kāval (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; police duties of a larger area, as distinct from the śir̤u-pāḍi-kāval for the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिदाना
pidā-nāl̤̣i (EI 28), Tamil; same as pudā-nāl̤̣i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो
pŏn̤-vari (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रचण्डकाणिक्कै
pracaṇḍa-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; a variety of military cess; this is found mentioned along with other military cessess like paḍai-ppaṇam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रधानिजोडि
pradhāni-joḍi (SII 2; SITI), the chief minister's quit-rent.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुडान
puḍā-nal̤̣i (SITI), Tamil; probably, a local cess on each door or gate or house; also, mentioned as pidā-nāl̤̣i.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुलवरि
pulavari (SITI), Tamil; ‘tax on a pulam (piece of land)’; probably to be corrected as pulvari meaning ‘tax on grass.’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुल्लवरि
pullavari (SITI), tax payable for grazing cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुल्लन्दि
pullandi (SITI), Tamil; an obligation probably connected with the pasture land in the form of fine on stray cattle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पु
pul̤̣ugu-kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; fee for meeting the expenses of coating the image of gods with civet; also known as pul̤̣uguvari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरक्कडमै
pur̤a-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; external taxes, i. e., taxes and fees payable to the state.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवायम्
pur̤av-āyam (SITI), Tamil; revenue from external sources, collected mainly in cash.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवेट्टि
pur̤avěṭṭi (SITI), Tamil; a variety of věṭṭi for public work, probably outside the area in question.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=421" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवु
puravu (SITI), Tamil; land revenue.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवुनेल्
puravu-něl (SITI), Tamil; revenue paid in paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुरवुपोन्
puravu-pŏn (SITI), Tamil; revenue paid in gold.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शक्करक्काणिक्कै
śakkara-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; tax on potters; also known as tirigai-āyam; cf. kuśa-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शण्डालप्पेरु
śaṇḍāla-pper̤u (SITI), Tamil; a local cess or tax collected from or for the Caṇḍālas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्धिविग्रहप्पेरु
sandhivigraha-pper̤u (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; fee payable to the village madhyastha; also a fee payable to the document writers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शट्टुवरि
śaṭṭu-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax for the grazing ground in the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शवैक्कडमै
śavai-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; taxes payable to the sabhā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक्कायम्
śekk-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on oil-presses; also called śekk-ir̤ai and śekku-kkaḍamai (SII 12).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक्कुकडमै
śekku-kaḍamai (SII 12), same as śekk-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेक्कुम
śekku-man̤r̤āḍi (SITI), Tamil; a tax or cess; probably related to śekku.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सेङ्कोडिक्काणम्
seṅkŏḍi-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; explained as ‘the tax on the cultivation of the medicinal plant known variously as śeṅgŏḍi, kŏḍiveli and citramūlam’; see also kŏḍi-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टियार्मगमै
śeṭṭiyār-magamai (SITI), Tamil; voluntary contribution (magamai) of the merchants.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेट्टियिरै
śeṭṭiy-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; tax on merchants; also known as śeṭṭ-ir̤ai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेवकक्काशु
śevaka-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; fee for the maintenance of the soldiers; or, tax levied on the soldier.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्कुडिमै
śil-kuḍimai (SITI), minor taxes and cesses payable to the local authority.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्लन्तरायम्
śill-antar-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; minor taxes which fall in the group of antar-āyam or ul̤-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिलायम्
śil-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; same as śill-ir̤ai, śil-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्लिरै
śill-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; same as sil-āyam, śil-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिल्वरि
śil-vari (SITI; EI 27), Tamil; minor taxes; same as śil-āyam, śil-ir̤ai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिर्रायम्
śir̤r̤-āyam (SITI), Tamil; minor taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरुप्पाडिकावल्
śir̤u-ppāḍi-kāval (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शिरुशुङ्गम्
śiru-śuṅgam (SITI), Tamil; minor tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शोडि
śoḍi , see joḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=422" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शो
śŏn̤a-vari (SITI), Tamil; same as pŏn-vari; explained as ‘tax payable in gold’; but may be professional tax payable by the goldsmiths; cf. suvarṇa-daṇḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुडुकाट्टुप्पाट्टम्
śuḍu-kāṭṭu-ppāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; fee payable by a prostitute, especially those accompanying the army.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शूलवरि
śūla-vari (EI 25; SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; a tax payable for the unkeep probably of a Śiva temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुङ्क
suṅka (EI 12), same as Sanskrit śulka, tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुर्रायक्काशु
śur̤r̤-āya-kkāśu (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वर्णादायम्
svarṇ-ādāyam (SITI), Sanskrit; revenue in gold; taxes payable in coin; or, profession^1 tax payable by the goldsmiths.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शडक्कडमै
śaḍa-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax on shepherds.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैक्काणम्
tal̤ai-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; fee or tax on the tal̤ai or foot-binding used by toddy-tappers.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तलैयारिक्कम्
talaiyārikkam (SITI), Tamil; tax payable for the maintenance of the village watchman; same as talaiyāri-kkāṇi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डलिर्कडमै
taṇḍalir̤-kaḍamai, taṇḍar̤-kaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; fee payable for the maintenance of tax-collectors; or, tax on bill-collectors.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डक्काणम्
taṇḍa-kkāṇam, taṇḍa-kkur̤am, etc. (SITI), in which taṇḍa is punitive tax and kur̤r̤am fines for crimes committed.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त|तं|तः
tan̤iyāl̤ (SII 12), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तानियवरक्कम्
tāniya-varakkam, dhānya-varga (SITI), Sanskrit; ‘the grain group’; class of taxes payable in grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्णीर्क्काणम्
taṇṇīr-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; water-cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरगिपाट्टम्
taragi-pāṭṭam (SII 12), brokerage fee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरविडुनेल्
tarav-iḍu-něl (SITI), Tamil; paddy given in lieu of wages.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवु
taravu (SITI), Tamil; ‘that which has been given’; collection of debt or tax on pressure; also a dun; also used in the sense of ‘order or instruction’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरवुकोल्लुदल्
taravu-kŏl̤l̤udal (SITI), Tamil; ‘to obtain a receipt for anything given’; collection of tax exercising pressure.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिअक्कवे
tar̤i-akkave (SII 13), same as tar̤i-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिइरै
tar̤i-ir̤ai (SII 12, 13), same as tar̤i-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक्कडमै
tar̤i-kkaḍamai (SII 12), same as tar̤i-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिक्कुरै
tar̤i-kkur̤ai (SITI), same as tar̤i-ppuḍavai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरिप्पुडवै
tar̤i-ppuḍavai (SITI), Tamil; tax on looms payable in the shape of cloth.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तरितलै
tar̤i-tal̤ai (SITI), Tamil; tax on looms; probably, the same as tar̤i-kkaḍamai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=423" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टार्पाट्टम्
taṭṭār-pāṭṭam, taṭṭāra-ppāṭṭam (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; tax on goldsmiths. Cf. suvarṇa-daṇḍa noticed above.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टोलि
taṭṭ-ŏli (SITI), Tamil; mentioned along with taṭṭār-pāṭṭam; probably, tax on the smiths or the workshop of the artisans like the blacksmiths.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तट्टुक्काणम्
taṭṭu-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; same as taṭṭār-pāṭṭam; ‘fee for hammering’; probably also the same as taṭṭukk-āyam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेवै
tevai (SII 12), a levy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिङ्गल्काशु
tiṅgal̤-kāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax payable every month; cf. tiṅgaṭ-cor̤u, tiṅgal̤-něy, tiṅgal̤-mogam, etc. Cf. also māda-ppaḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरिगैआयम्
tirigai-āyam (SITI), tax payable by the potter for his trade; cf. tirigai, a potter's wheel.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरुमुगक्काणम्
tiru-muga-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; expenses as wages, etc., payable to the person who brings the tiru-mugam (royal order) to a village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिवु
tivul̤̣-desa (EI 30), Tamil; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तीयेरिशोरु
tīyer̤i-śor̤u (SII 13), Tamil; literally, ‘offering in fire’; supposed to be the name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोलोट्टु
tol-ŏṭṭu (SITI), Tamil; a fee probably connected with hides and skins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोनिक्कडमै
loni-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; tax on boats.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोरणक्काणिक्कै
toraṇa-kkāṇikkai (SITI), Tamil; presents for decorating the village with arches, etc.; or tax on gates.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोट्टप्पुरवु
toṭṭa-ppuravu (SITI), Tamil; tax on garden lands.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलाक्कूलि
tulā-kkūli (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; fee for weighing in balance.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूशकत्तरि
tūśaka-ttar̤i (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on looms weaving tent-materials.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उगप्पार्पोन्
ugappār-pŏn (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in gold on joyous occasions like marriage; probably the same as kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उलवुकाट्चि
ulavu-kāṭci (SITI), Tamil; probably, presents offered to the king or other exalted persons when going in procession round the village.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्गु
ulgu (SITI), Tamil; customs duties; tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्लियक्कूलि
ulliya-kkūli (SITI), Tamil; probably, water-fee for irrigation from wells; tax or wages for well-digging.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उलुप्पै
uluppai (SITI), Tamil; presents of fruits, articles of food, etc., offered to great personages; free supplies made by the people or subordinates to officials on tour.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उल्वरि
ul̤-vari (SITI), Tamil; internal revenue^1; taxes levied^2 [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-425" target="_blank">Page-425+ 40</a>] by the local body; same as antar-āyam; orders issued by the government fixing the amount of such taxes.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR>[2] Correction submitted by Dr. Sampada Savardekar on 20210207. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/csl-corrections/issues/51.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=424" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उप्पुक्काशु
uppu-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; salt-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उरल्वरि
ural-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax or fee for the maintenance of the mortar for husking paddy.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊरेट्टु
ūr-ěṭṭu (SITI), Tamil; ‘committee of eight members of the village assembly (ūr)’; taxes payable for the expenses of the committee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊरिडुवरिप्पाडु
ūr-iḍu-varippāḍu (SII 13; SITI), Tamil; tax levied by the village assembly (ūr).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्क्कडमै
ūr-kkaḍamai (SITI), Tamil; obligations and taxes payable to the village assembly (ūr).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्त्तनिशु
ūr-ttaniśu (SII 13), a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊशिवाशि
ūśi-vāśi (SITI), Tamil; tax probably connected with tailoring.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उवच्चवरि
uvacca-vari (SITI), Tamil; tax payable by or for the maintenance of the uvaccar (drummers in temple service).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उवच्चक्काणि
uvacca-kkāṇi (SITI), Tamil; rent-free land given to the uvaccan̤ for serving as drummer in a temple.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वड्डरावुल
vaḍḍarāvul̤a, vaḍḍāravul̤a (EI 19, 28; IE 8-8), Kannaḍa; name of a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वगैन्दकाशु
vagainda-kāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in cash for marking the details, as of land; fees for subdivision of land; also the fee for settlement, as of a dispute.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वालमञ्जाडि
vāla-mañjāḍi (SITI), Tamil; probably the same as vāla-vari and vāla-kkāṇam; tax of a mañjāḍi on the units of measurement in the length of a house-site.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलङ्गैइडङ्गैमगन्मै
valaṅgai-iḍaṅgai-maganmai (SITI), Tamil; tax on the right-hand and left-hand castes, to be paid by all able-bodied men capable of bearing arms.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
val̤̣inaḍaikk-iḍum-paṇam (SITI), Tamil; road cess.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
val̤̣iy-āyam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; tolls on the roadways.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
val̤̣udiy-accu-vargam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; group of taxes payable in Pāṇḍya coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वण्णार्वरि
vaṇṇār-vari, vaṇṇāra-ppār̤ai (SITI), Tamil; tax on washer-men.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

व|वं|वः
van̤-pāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; fixed rent in kind due under a lease-deed which does not provide for any relief against loss due to drought.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरि
vari (SITI), Tamil; tax, revenue register, order of the [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-426" target="_blank">Page-426+ 40</a>] king and his officer fixing the revenue; cf. vari-ppŏttagam, tax register; officer maintaining the same; also Vari-kkūr̤u-śeyvār, Varrikkukkūr̤u-śeyvār (SITI), Tamil; officers grading the cultivable land and fixing the tax payable thereon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=425" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वरिशै
variśai (SITI), Tamil; village dues; cess payable by or to the local authority.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशलिल्पोन्दकुडिमै
vāśalil-ponda-kuḍimai (SITI), Tamil; ‘burden of citizenship dues at the gate’; taxes, probably other than the land revenue, payable to the state.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्काणिक्कै
vāśal-kāṇikkai , (SITI), Tamil; presents offered to the palace, probably annually.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्कु
vāśal-kul̤̣i-ppaṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; probably, door-tax, i. e., house-tax based on the main doorways.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्पणम्
vāśal-paṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; periodical payment due to the palace; door-tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्तिरमम्
vāśal-tiramam (SITI), Tamil; door-tax; tiramam is the same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्विनियोगम्
vāśal-viniyogam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; same as vāśal-paṇam, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टम्
vaṭṭam (SITI), money-changers’ commission; trade discount.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वट्टिना
vaṭṭi-nāl̤̣i (SITI), Tamil; probably, a tax payable at the rate of one nāl̤̣i for each vaṭṭi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाय्क्काल्पाट्टम्
vāykkāl-pāṭṭam (SITI), Tamil; channel cess; fee for keeping the channels in good repairs.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिक्काशु
veli-kkāśu (SITI), Tamil; tax (payable in cash) of uncertain import; cf. veli-kkul̤̣i-ppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिप्पयरु
veli-ppayaru (SII 12; SITI), same as veli-kkāśu<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेल्लानिरै
vel̤l̤ān-ir̤ai (SITI), Tamil; cultivation tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेण्डुगोल्
veṇḍugol̤, veṇḍukol̤ (SII 12; SITI), Tamil; supplication; petition; fee for the same; also known as veṇḍukol̤-vari.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेट्टि
věṭṭi (SII 12, 13), same as Sanskrit viṣṭi, ‘unpaid labour’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेट्टिवेदिनै
věṭṭi-vedinai (SII 13), explained as a tax.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेयदिकाणम्
veyadi-kāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax payable in grains, probably on thatched sheds; or, may be related to veyněl (collection of bamboo-grain from forests).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विभूतिकाणिक्कै
vibhūti-kāṇikkai (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; contribution paid voluntarily to a temple by its devotees while receiving the sacred ashes, later collected as compulsory dues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=426" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडैप्पेर्
viḍai-pper̤, viḍai-pper̤u (SITI), Tamil; perquisites payable on the receipt of a reply to a petition to the king.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विल्पणम्
vil-paṇam (SITI), Tamil-Sanskrit; sale-tax; also explained as a tax on bows or on archery.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विप्रविनोदिवरि
vipravinodi-vari (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; tax from or for the maintenance of the Vipravinodins (Brāhmaṇa magicians).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरशेषै
vīra-śeṣai (SITI); EI 22), sometimes supposed to be the name of a tax; but see vīra-śeṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विर्पणम्
vir̤-paṇam (SITI), vil-paṇam; Tamil-Sanskrit; tax on bows and arrows; may also be a tax on sales.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विरुत्तुप्पट्टिगै
viruttu-ppaṭṭigai (SITI), Tamil; tax probably on profits and the income from interest.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशक्काणम्
viśa-kkāṇam (SITI), Tamil; tax or share in the produce as remuneration due to a Viyavan̤ or village headman.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विशेषायम्
viśeṣ-āyam, viśeṣ-ādāyam (SITI), Sanskrit; a special group of taxes.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विवाहप्पणम्
vivāha-ppaṇam (SITI), Sanskrit-Tamil; marriage fee; cf. kaṇṇāla-kkāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=427" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अच्चु
accu , Tamil; name of a coin; money; tax or income.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आछु
āchu , same as āsu; cf. accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आड
āḍa , also spelt aḍḍa; name of a coin; half of a fanam; cf. aḍḍaga and aḍḍuga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडतालीसगानी
aḍatālīsa-gānī , 6 aṭha-gānīs; billon coin equal to the silver ṭaṅka and to 48 copper jitals.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्ड
aḍḍa , same as aḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डचिन्न
aḍḍa-cinna , cf. āḍa or aḍḍa and cinna or sinna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डग
aḍḍaga , also spelt aḍḍuga; same as āḍa, aḍḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अड्डुग
aḍḍuga , same as aḍḍaga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिक्काशु
aḍi-kkāśu , ‘tax collected from the stall-keepers in the market’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अडिमैक्काशु
aḍimai-kkāśu , ‘fee collected from the temple servants (or for their maintenance)’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आदिवराहद्रम्म
ādivarāha-dramma , ‘a dramma issued by Ādivarāha (Patīhāra Bhoja I, c. 836-85 A. D.)’; same as śrīmad-ādivarāha-dramma; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आद्यमाष
ādya-māṣa , the original māṣa of 5 ratis as opposed to the later māṣa of various weights upto 10 ratis. Cf. māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आजीवककाशु
ājīvaka-kāśu , same as Tamil āśuva-kkāśu; ‘tax collected from the Ājivakas (or for the maintenance of the Ājīvaka monks)’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्कम्
akkam , one-twelfth of a kāśu (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्ष|अक्षं|अक्षः
akṣa , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अलगच्चु
al̤ag-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अम्बिलिगद्याण
ambili-gadyāṇa , see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अमुदनच्चु
amudan-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अनैअच्चु
anai-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आणक|आणकः
āṇaka , Sanskritized form of Muhammadan āna = English anna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अण्दिक
aṇḍika, aṇḍikā , (1/4) of a māṣa; also regarded as the same as paṇa which was (1/12) or (1/16) of a dīnāra or suvarṇa in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अङ्कगद्याण
aṅka-gadyāṇa , see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अन्न|अन्नं|अन्नः
anna , Anglicised form of Muhammadan āna; (1/16) of rupee, property, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्धककिनी
ardha-kākinī , half of a kākinī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=428" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अर्णिका
arṇikā , equal to 2 māṣas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अष्टमिका
aṣṭamikā , same as śatamāna.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आसु
āsu , cf. accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

आशुवक्काशु
āśuva-kkāśu , same as ājīvaka-kāśu (q. v.); see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अठगानी
aṭha-gānī , billon coin equal to 8 jitals and to (1/6) of a silver ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

औरेउस्
aureus , Roman gold coin (124 grains); same as the gold denareus (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बदर|बदरं|बदरः
badara , same as tola or tolaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बडिमाडुवुलु
baḍi-māḍuvulu , see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बलोत्र
balotra , name applied to an Indian silver coin by the Muslim chroniclers of the early medieval period.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बराड्
barāḍ , modified form of varāṭaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बारह्गानी
bārah-gānī , 1(1/2) aṭha-gānīs; billon coin equal to 12 copper jitals and to (1/4) of the silver ṭaṅka<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बेल्लियद्रम्म
bel̤l̤iya-dramma , Kannaḍa; ‘silver dramma’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भाग|भागः
bhāga , see hāga, pāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भैरवगद्याण
bhairava-gadyāṇa ‘a gadyāṇa minted by a goldsmith named Bhairava’; cf. bṛhat-bhairava-gadyāṇa; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भीमप्रियद्रम्म
bhīmapriya-dramma , ‘a dramma minted by a goldsmith named Bhīma’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भुजबलमाडै
bhujabala-māḍai , ‘a māḍai issued by a ruler named or entitled Bhujabala’; see māḍa, māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बिन्दुक
binduka , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बृहत्भैरवगद्याण
bṛhat-bhairava-gadyāṇa , ‘the bigger bhairava-gadyāṇa (q. v.)’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

बु
bud̤ī , Bengali name for a unit equal to 5 gaṇḍās; cf. voḍī, voḍrī, kapardaka-voḍī; also kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामर|चामरं|चामरः
cāmara , also called cāmara-māḍa; probably ‘a māḍa bearing the figure of a fly-whisk’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चामरमाड
cāmara-māḍa , see cāmara and māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चर्सम्
carsam (karṣa ?) , equal to 4 māḍas; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चस्ह्
cash , Anglicised spelling of kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चस्त्
‘cast’ , see ‘die-struck’ and ‘punch-marked’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौबीसगानी
caubīsa-gānī , 3 aṭha-gānīs; billon coin equal to 24 copper jitals and to (1/2) of a silver ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चौगानी
cau-gānī , (1/2) of an aṭha-gānī; billon coin equal to 4 copper jitals and to (1/12) of a silver ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवल
cavala , also spelt cavela; (1/8) of a pagoda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चवेल
cavěla , same as cavala.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

छगानी
cha-gānī , (3/4) of an aṭha-gānī; billon coin equal 6 copper jitals and to (1/8) of a silver ṭaṅka; same as s̤as̤ghānī and śāśukāni.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चीनक्कनक्कम्
cīna-kkanakkam , Tamil; ‘Chinese gold coin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिन्न|चिन्नः
cinna , also spelt sinna; same as fanam (q. v.); (1/8) of a pagoda (q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=429" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

चिरविद
ciravida , Telugu; supposed to be a kind of gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाम्
dām , derivative of dramma (q. v.); copper coin, (1/40) of a Mughal rupee (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम|दमः
dama , same as dāma or dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाम
dāma , same as dām or dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्म
damma , same as dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

डाङ्ग्
ḍāṅg , corrupt form of ṭanka (q. v.); cf. dāṅk.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दाङ्क्
dāṅk , corrupt form of ṭaṅka (q. v.); cf. ḍāṅg.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दरिच्
daric , gold coin of ancient Iran (about 133 grains); double daric = Greek stater or tetradrachma, four times the drachma in weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दायद्रम्म
dāya-dramma , ‘tax or money to be paid’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देह्लीटाल्
dehlīwāl , see jītal.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

देनरिउस्
denarius , name of the Roman silver (also gold) coin; equal to Greek drachma; origin of the Indian coin name dīnāra, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानक|धानकं|धानकः
dhānaka , same as māṣa; cf. hemadhānyaka; same as dhānika (q. v.); also called aṇḍika and regarded as equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or (1/12) of suvarṇa (JNSI, Vol. II, p. 8).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धानिक
dhānika , equal to 4 kārṣāpaṇas or 64 paṇas according to the Kṛtyakalpataru.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धान्यमाष
dhānya-māṣa , (1/2) of yava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

धरण|धरणं|धरणः
dharaṇa , old silver coin of 32 ratis (about 58 grains); also called kārṣāpaṇa and purāṇa; 24 (actually about 20) ratis in weight and half of gadyāṇa in value according to medieval authorities; otherwise called dramma, śāna or ṭaṅka; sometimes regarded as a gold coin or weight equal to ten palas or 40 suvarṇas or niṣkas (3200 ratis); cf. śalamāna (silver) = 10 dharaṇas (320 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ध्वंशि
dhvaṃśi , same as vaṃśya; a minute unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिद्रछ्म
didrachma , ‘two-drachma’, ‘double drachma’; see drachma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिएस्त्रुच्क्
‘die-struck’ , coins on which the symbols and legends were impressed by means of an anvil and a single punch, both bearing negative representations, by placing a blank on the socket in the anvil and striking the punch placed on it by a hammer; see punch-marked.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनार
dināra , also spelt dinnāra; generally spelt dīnāra (q. v.); a cowrie-shell according to the Kashmir chronicle.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दीनार|दीनारः
dīnāra , derived from Roman denarius (124 grains); name of a gold coin equal to 16 silver coins called rūpaka, etc. (about 20 ratis); a silver coin according to the Kṛtyakalpataru; sometimes called kāśu in Tamil, etc.; sometimes regarded as half of satera or sateraka (Greek stater); see dināra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=430" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारि
dināri , generally spelt as dīnāra; local modification of the Roman denarius prevalent in the Ikṣvāku kingdom in the Krishna-Guntur region.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिनारिमाषक
dināri-māṣaka , same as dināri, or one-sixteenth of a dināri or dīnāra in weight or value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिन्नार
dinnāra , see dināra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिरमम्
diramam , Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोड्डवराह
doḍḍa-varāha , see varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दोगानी
do-gānī , (1/4) of an aṭha-gānī; billon coin equal to 2 copper jitals and to (1/24) of a silver ṭaṅka; same as du-gānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्र
dra , abbreviation of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रछ्म
drachma , Greek silver coin; equal to 6 obols; Attic standard 67 grains, but the Indo-Greek standard was soon modified, their coins of 37 or 38 grains being called drachma or hemi-drachma by different scholars; origin of the Indian coin name dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षण|द्रक्षणं
drakṣaṇa , same as draṃkṣana or tola; equal to 8 māṣas (80 ratis); cf. drakṣuṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रक्षुण
drakṣuṇa , same as drakṣaṇa or tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रंक्षण|द्रङ्क्षण|द्रङ्क्षणं
draṃkṣaṇa , same as tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम
drama , same as dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्म|द्रम्मं
dramma , Indian form of Greek drachma; a silver coin (1/16) of a gold niṣka according to the Līlāvatī; name applied to the Śaka-type silver purāṇa, dharaṇa or kārṣāpaṇa (about 20 ratis, also called rūpaka); copper coin (dām) regarded as (1/40) of a Mughal rupee; money in general; the name first occurs on the Yaudheya coins.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मार्ध
dramm-ārdha , half of dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रम्मत्रिभाग
dramma-tribhāga , one-third of dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

द्रङ्ग|द्रङ्गः
draṅga , variant of dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुगानी
du-gānī , billon coin equal to 2 copper jitals and to (1/24) of silver ṭaṅka; same as do-gānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुक्र
dukra , (1/5) of a phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दुकानी
dukānī , (1/2) of a phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअदिया
fadiyā , see phadiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋअनम्
fanam , Anglicised form of Tamil paṇam (q. v.); Sanskrit paṇa (q. v.); a gold coin equal to (1/20) of a varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग|गं|गः
ga , abbreviation of gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधैया
gadhaiyā , same as gadhiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधैयापैसा
gadhaiyā-paisā , same as ghadhiyā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदिआणक
gadiāṇaka , cf. kumāra-gadiāṇaka, name of a tax; same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधिया
gadhiyā , also spelt gadhaiyā; copper coin imitated from old Sasanian issues.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=431" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गधियापैसा
gadhiyā-paisā , same as gadhiyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गदियाण
gadiyāṇa , same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्या
gadyā , abbreviation of gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यान
gadyāna , same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याण
gadyāṇa , a gold coin or weight; generally regarded as 48 ratis (about 88 grains) in weight; sometimes called ‘the gold gadyāṇa’; sometimes regarded as a coin like a farthing, equal to (1/4) or (1/5) of the paikamu (q. v.); regarded in some places as equal to 20 vals, 8 māṣas or (1/2) tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्यानक|गद्यानकं|गद्यानकः
gadyānaka , same as gadyāṇaka or gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याणक|गद्याणकः
gadyāṇaka , same as gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गद्याणपोन्नु
gadyāṇa-ponnu , ‘gadyāṇa of gold’; same as pon-gadyāṇa; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डा
gaṇḍā , equal to 4 cowrie-shells; (1/20) of a paṇa; cf. gaṇḍaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डगोपालन्माडै
gaṇḍagopālan̤-māḍai , ‘māḍa issued or minted by Gaṇḍagopāla’; see māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डक|गंडक|गंडकः|गण्डकः
gaṇḍaka , same as gaṇḍā. Cf. kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डमाड
gaṇḍa-māḍa , probably ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a rhinoceros’ or an abbreviation of Gaṇḍagopālan-māḍai (q. v.); sometimes characterised by the epithet ‘small’; sometimes also called kārṣāpaṇa, niṣka and gaṇḍa-niṣka; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गण्डनिष्क
gaṇḍa-niṣka , same as gaṇḍa; see māḍa and niṣka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गन्धहस्तिमाड
gandhahasti-māḍa^1 , same as gandhavāraṇa-māḍa; probably, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of an elephant in rut’; see māḍa.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Dhaval Patel on 20160121. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/CORRECTIONS/issues/243. note: sh.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गानी
gānī , cf. aṭha-gānī, billon coin equal to 8 copper jitals and to (1/6) of a silver ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गरद्रम्म
gara-dramma , see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गावगद्याण
gāva-gadyāṇa , see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

घटितहीनद्रम्माः
ghaṭita-hīna-drammāḥ , ‘drammas (money) that are wanting’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोलका
golakā , same as gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गोलक्कै
gol̤akkai , Tamil; same as golakā (gulikā).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रासग्रह
grāsagraha , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुलिका
gulikā , same as golakā, etc.; a small coin apparently globular or circular in shape; supposed to be a coin issued by the Śambhuvarāya chiefs and also by the Pāṇḍyas; cf. vīra-champan-kul̤igai and val̤l̤āl-val̤̣i-tir̤antān̤-gul̤ikai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुञ्जा|गुंजा
guñjā , same as rati or raktikā (1-83 or about 1(3/4) grains).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हाग
hāga , Kannaḍa; same as Sanskrit bhāga; probably (1/4) of the standard coin; see pāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हंसपद|हंसपदः
haṃsapada , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=432" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेम|हेमं|हेमः
hema , same as māṣa; cf. hema-dhānyaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमधान्यक|हेमधान्यकः
hema-dhānyaka , same as māṣa; see hema and dhānaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमटङ्क
hema-ṭaṅka , ‘a gold ṭaṅka (q. v.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हेमिद्रछ्म
hemi-drachma , Greek; same as Sanskrit dramm-ārdha (q. v.); see drachma, dramma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

होन्
hon , variant spelling of hūn; same as varāha, gadyāṇa (gold gadyāṇa) and pagoda (star pagoda); cf. suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

हून्
hūn , same as hon or varāha (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईलक्करुङ्काशु
īl̤a-kkaruṅ-kāśu , ‘Ceylonese coin’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ईलक्काशु
īl̤a-kkāśu , ‘Ceylonese coin’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इनवरिक्काशु
inavari-kkāśu , ‘communual tax in cash’; see kāśu<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जगदलंगद्याण
jagadal̤aṃ-gadyāṇa , see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जैथल
jaithala , same as jītal (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णश्रेष्ठिश्रीमल्लप्रिय
jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-śrīmalla-priya , possibly, ‘an old coin of the mint of Śreṣṭhin Śrīmalla’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णश्रेष्ठिविश्वमल्लप्रिय
jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya , same as jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya; possibly, ‘an old coin of the mint of Śreṣṭhin Viśvamalla’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीतल्
jītal , a copper coin, (1/48) of a silver ṭanka of the Delhi Sult̤āns; also called delhīwāl; (1/3) of a silver tār which was itself (1/6) of a fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

जीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय
jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya , same as jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya, possibly, ‘an old coin of the mint of Viśvamalla’; cf. vīsala-priya-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः
kad̤ā , Bengali, etc; cowrie-shell regarded as coin; (1/4) of gaṇḍā and (1/80) of paṇa in some areas. Cf. kapardaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहण
kāhaṇa , Bengali, etc; also spelt kahāṇa and kāhāṇa; same as kāhāpaṇa = kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कहाण
kahāṇa , same as kāhaṇa = kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहाण
kāhāṇa , same as kāhaṇa = kārṣāpaṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काहापण
kāhāpaṇa , same as Sanskrit kārṣāpaṇa and modern kāhaṇ, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काक|काकं|काकः
kāka , same as kākinī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काकनिका
kākanikā , same as kakanī, kakinī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ककिनी
kākinī , equal to 20 cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī; (1/4) of a paṇa; same as bud̤ī. Cf. gaṇḍā<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क|कं|कः
kal̤̣añju , Tamil; name of a weight or coin weighing 10 mañjāḍis (32 ratis theoretically); sometimes called suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणम्
kāṇam , Tamil; name of a coin; a gold coin or weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिके
kāṇikě , also spelt kāṇiki; (1/64) part of a coin; money or tolls.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काणिकि
kāṇiki , same as kāṇikě (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=433" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्द|कपर्दः|कपर्द्द|कपर्द्दः
kaparda , same as kapardaka, etc.; cowrie-shell used as coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दक|कपर्दकः|कपर्द्दक|कपर्द्दकः
kapardaka , also called kaparda, kapardikā, kapardī, etc.; cowrie-shell used as coin. Cf. kad̤ā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकपुराण
kapardaka-purāṇa , ‘a purāṇa (q. v.) counted in kapardakas’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दकवोडी
kapardaka-voḍī , ‘a voḍī counted in kapardakas’; cf. bud̤ī and voḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दी|कपर्द्दी
kapardī , same as kapardikā, kapardaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कपर्दिका
kapardikā , same as kapardī, kapardaka, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्ष|कर्षः
karṣa , name of a weight equal to 80 ratis or about 146 grains; sometimes regarded 100 ratis or about 183 grains; sometimes also regarded as 120 ratis in weight; a coin (cf. kārṣāpaṇa).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कार्षापण|कार्षापणं|कार्षापणः
kārṣāpaṇa , silver coin weighing 32 ratis (about 58 grains), also called purāṇa or dharaṇa; copper coin of 80 ratis or about 146 grains (sometimes 100 ratis or about 183 grains), also called paṇa; Śaka-type silver coin of about 20 ratis, also called rūpaka, dramma, etc.; gold coin of 80 ratis (cf. suvarṇa); name applied to gaṇḍa māḍa (probably (1/2) tola in weight), also called niṣka (q. v.); same as kāhaṇa, etc.; cf. karṣa of 120 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कर्षार्ध
karṣ-ārdha , ‘half of a karṣa (q. v.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

करुङ्काशु
karuṅ-kāśu , ‘Ceylonese coin’; see kāśu, īl̤̣a-kkāśu, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

काशु
kāśu , Tamil; spelt in English as cash; name of a copper coin, (1/100) of a fanam; sometimes called dīnāra; money; tax; cf. kāśu-kaḍamai, ‘tax in coins’; also Sanskrit karṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कठारिअङ्कुशगद्याण
kaṭhāri-aṅkuśa-gadyāṇa , probably, ‘a gadyāṇa bearing the representation of a dagger and a goad’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोल|कोलं|कोलः
kola , same as tola; equal to 2 śāṇas.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोलक्कै
kol̤akkai , Tamil; same as golakā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोमरिनगद्याण
kŏmarina-gadyāṇa , same as kumāra-gadyāṇa; name of a tax; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कोवै
kovai , Tamil; name of a gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्रोड|क्रोडं|क्रोडः
kroḍa , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णल|कृष्णलः
kṛṣṇala , same as rati or guñjā (about 1(3/4) grains); regarded as equal to 3 ratis by the Kṛtyakalpataru which seems to confuse rati with yava.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कृष्णराजरूपक
kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka , ‘rūpaka issued by Kṛṣṇarāja (Kalacuri Kṛṣṇa, sixth century A. D.)’; see rūpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रक|क्षुद्रकः
kṣudraka , same as draṃkṣaṇa or tola (q. v.); cf. kṣudrama.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

क्षुद्रम
kṣudrama , variant of kṣudraka; same as tola (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=434" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमारगद्याणक
kumāra-gadyāṇaka , name of a tax; see gadyāṇa; cf. koma-rina-gadyāṇa and kumara-kaccāṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुमरकच्चाणम्
kumara-kaccāṇam , Tamil; same as kumāra-gadyāṇaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलिगै
kul̤igai , same as gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

कुलोत्तुङ्गमाड
kulottuṅga-māḍa , ‘māḍa issued by Kulottuṅga (i. e. Col̤̣a-Cālukya Kulottuṅga I, 1070-1120 A. D.)’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लागिद्रम्माः
lāgi-drammāḥ , ‘expenses incurred’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहडिया
lohaḍiyā , equal to 20 pāvīsās or 100 cowrie-shells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोहितक|लोहितकं|लोहितकः
lohitaka , equal to 3 māṣas (30 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

लोक्किगद्याण
lokki-gadyāṇa , ‘gadyāṇa minted at Lokki (modern Lakkundi in the Dharwar District, Mysore State)’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माड|माडः
māḍa , Telugu; gold or silver coin, 40 ratis (about 73 grains) in weight; half of a dīnāra; half of a pagoda, or tenth of a paṇa (fanam) in value; same as māḍha, māḍhā, māḍai; 50 per cent; cf. gaṇḍa-māḍa also called kārṣāpaṇa and gaṇḍa-niṣka; Tamil modification of Sanskrit māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडबदिपातुक
māḍa-badipātuka , fraction of a māḍa; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माडै
māḍai , Tamil; same as māḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माढ
māḍha , Od̤iyā; also spelt māḍhā; same as māḍa, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

महापण
mahāpaṇa , cf. māppaṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लनन्दिमाड
malla-nandi-māḍa , probably, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a wrestler and a bull’, or ‘māḍa minted by Mallanandin’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मल्लमाड
malla-māḍa , possibly, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a wrestler’, or an abbreviation of malla-nandi-māḍa; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मंक्षुण|मङ्क्षुण|मङ्क्षुणं
maṃkṣuṇa , equal to 7 māṣas (70 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मण्ड|मंडं|मण्डं|मंडः|मण्डः
maṇḍa , equal to 5 māṣas (50 ratis); cf. māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मञ्जाडि
mañjāḍi , (1/10) of a kal̤añju, (1/100) of a śatamāna; sometimes regarded as 5(1/2) grains in weight, but may be about 4 grains also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माप्पणम्
māppaṇam , same as Sanskrit mahāpaṇa; may be also ‘tax of one paṇa per mā measure of grains’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मरीचि|मरीचिः
marīci , a minute unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माष|माषः
māṣa , name of a weight or a coin weighing 5 ratis originally; later regarded as 10 ratis in weight; (1/4) of a śāna and (1/8) of a śatamāna; sometimes regarded as (1/20) of a paṇa of 100 ratis (i. e. 5 ratis); a gold coin (as opposed to the silver māṣaka) according to the Kṛtyakalpataru; cf. ādya-māṣa, māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

माषक|माषकः
māṣaka , same as māṣa; according to the Kṛtyakalpataru, a silver coin as opposed to the gold māṣa<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मृड|मृडः
mṛḍa , name of a weight like māñjāḍi (q. v.). Cf. pṛḍa, pruḍ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=435" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मुदल्तिरमम्
mudal-tiramam, mudar̤r̤iramam , Tamil; ‘tax payable in cash’; cf. tiramam = dramma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नला
nalā , same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्काशु
nal-kāśu , see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नल्लानैअच्चु
nall-ānai-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाना
nānā , same as nāṇaka; cf. Kuṣāṇa coins bearing the representation of the West Asian mother-goddess Nana.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणै
nāṇai , same as nāṇaka, nānā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाणक|नाणकं
nāṇaka , a coin; see nāṇai, nānā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नत्काशु
nat-kāśu , see kāsu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नेल्लूर्माडै
nellūr-māḍai , ‘the Nellore māḍai’; see māḍa, māḍai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

निष्क|निष्कं|निष्कः
niṣka , gold coin or weight equal to one karṣa (80 ratis or about 146 grains) of 16 māṣas or to 4 or 108 or 150 suvarṇas (q. v.); silver coin equal to one śatamāna (320 ratis); sometimes identified with māḍa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ओबोल्
obol , Greek coin; (1/6) of drachma (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पादविंशोपक
pāda-viṃśopaka , ‘one-fourth of a viṃśopaka (q. v.)’; cf. pāvīsā which is the same as paisā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पद्मनिधिमल्लमाड
padmanidhi-malla-māḍa , probably, ‘maḍa bearing the figure of a wrestler meant for depositing in a temple treasury’; but cf. malla-māḍa, etc.; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पदुच्चलागैअच्चु
paduccalāgai-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाग
pāga , same as Kannaḍa hāga; (1/4) of the standard coin; probably the same as Sanskrit bhāga.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पगोद
pagoda , also called ‘star pagoda’; Anglicised form of the name of the gold coin called gadyāṇa, hūn (hon) or varāha; since the word pagoda also meant ‘a temple’, the coin seems to have been so named owing to the representation of a temple or a deity on it; pagoda may be a corruption of bhagavatī meaning ‘the mother-goddess’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैकमु
paikamu , Telugu; supposed to be a small coin equal to (1/4) or (1/5) of a gadyāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पैसा
paisā , (1/64) or (1/100) of a rupee; same as pāvīsā = Sanskrit pāda-viṃśaka (˚viṃśatika or ˚viṃśopaka).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल|पलं|पलः
pala , weight of 320 ratis (cf. śatamāna); equal to 4 or 5 suvarṇas according to the Yājñavalkyasmṛti.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलमुदलानैअच्चु
pal̤amudal-ānai-accu , same as palañśalāgai; see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलम्पुल्लिमाडै
pal̤am-pul̤l̤i-māḍai , see māḍa, māḍai, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलञ्जलागैअच्चु
pal̤añjalāgai-accu , same as palañśalāgai; see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलङ्काशु
palaṅ-kāśu , see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=436" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलञ्शलागै
pal̤añ-śalāgai , Tamil; a kind of coin (accu) probably of the shape of a śalākā. Cf. śrī-yakki-pal̤añ-śalāgai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पलार्ध
pal-ārdha , (1/2) of a pala (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण|पणः
paṇa , same as the copper kārṣāpaṇa, 80 ratis in weight according to Manu, etc.; equal to 80 cowrie-shells according to the Līlāvatī; regarded in East India during the late medieval period as equal to 80 cowrie-shells and (1/16) of a kāhaṇ = kārṣāpaṇa (q. v.); (1/16) of a suvarṇa according to some; (1/48) of a kārṣāpaṇa according to the Kṛtyakalpataru; same as Tamil paṇam (q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणम्
paṇam , Tamil; spelt fanam in English; same as Sanskrit paṇa (q. v.); but in Tamil, a small gold coin or money in general; cf. paṇa-vargam, ‘taxes in cash’, also called kāś-āya-vargam (literally, ‘taxes payable in kāśu, i. e. cash or money’).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणपुराण
paṇa-purāṇa , ‘purāṇa (q. v.) counted in paṇas (q. v.)’; cf. kapardaka-purāṇa and kapardaka-voḍi.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पणवाशि
paṇa-vāśi , Tamil; ‘discount for the exchange of coins’; see paṇam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पण्चालवच्चु
paṇcālav-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पञ्चियकद्रम
pañciyaka-drama , probably, ‘dramma minted by the pañca or pañcakula i. e. the Pañcāyat Board’; or ‘dramma equal to five copper coins’; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पाणि|पाणिः
pāṇi , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परमेष्ठिगद्याण
parameṣṭhi-gadyāṇa , see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पर्ताब्
partāb , name of a gold coin; a half pagoda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

परुमुलैवराहन्
parumul̤ai-varāhan , see varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पारुत्थ
pāruttha , a silver coin equal to 8 drammas of copper or billon; cf. poruttha-dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पौर|पौरं|पौरः
paura , cf. purāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पावीसा
pāvīsā , (1/20) of a lohaḍiyā; same as Sanskrit pāda-viṃśaka (˚viṃśatika or ˚viṃśopaka) and modern paisā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फदिया
phadiyā , same as phadyaka; a copper coin about two annas in value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

फद्यक
phadyaka , same as phadiyā (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचु|पिचुः
picu , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पिचुल|पिचुलः
picula , equal to 6 maṣas (60 ratis).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्
pon , also spelt pon̤ in Tamil; same as hon (i. e. hūn or varāha); same as ‘gold’ māḍai, gadyāṇa, etc.; money. Cf. Tamil pon-bhaṇḍāram, pon-paṇḍāra-vāśal; also pon-vargam, pon-vari, etc., meaning ‘taxes payable in gold or coins’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=437" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पो
pon̤ , Tamil; see pon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोन्गद्याण
pon-gadyāṇa , ‘gold gadyāṇa’; same as gadyāṇa-ponnu; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पोरुत्थद्रम्म
poruttha-dramma , see dramma; cf. pāruttha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रताप|प्रतापः
pratāpa , same as partāb.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पृड
pṛḍa , a variant of mṛḍa (q. v.). Cf. pruḍ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रियश्राहगजमल्लगद्याण
priyaśrāha-gajamalla-gadyāṇa , probably, gadyāṇa minted by Priyaśrāha and Gajamalla (or Gajamalla of Priyaśrāha); see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

प्रुड्
pruḍ , a variant of mṛḍa (q. v.). Cf. pṛḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुल्लिगुलिकैवराहन्
pul̤l̤i-gul̤ikai-varāhan , see gulikā and varāha.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुन्छ्मर्केद्
‘punch-marked’ , name applied to old Indian coins of copper and silver, on which the symbols were punched by different punches as was not the case with the die-struck and cast coins. Similar coins were sometimes cast from dies also.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पुराण|पुराणं|पुराणः
purāṇa , a silver coin also called dharaṇa and kārṣāpaṇa, 32 ratis (about 58 grains) in weight; name applied to the silver punch-marked coins and also to the Śaka-type silver coins weighing about 20 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजमाड
rājarāja-māḍa , Telugu; ‘māḍa or māḍai issued by king Rājarāja (Col̤̣a Rājarāja I, 985-1016 A. D.)’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राजराजन्माडै
rājarājan-māḍai , Tamil; same as rājarāja-māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रजेन्द्रचो
rajendracol̤̣a-māḍa , ‘māḍa issued by king Rājendra-col̤̣a (Rājendra I, 1016-43 A. D.)’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रक्तिका
raktikā , modern rati; a little above 1(3/4) grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिपणम्
rāśi-paṇam , ‘current good coins’; also called rāśi-ppon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

राशिप्पोन्
rāśi-ppon , same as rāśi-paṇam (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रति|रतिः
rati , same as raktikā; a little above 1(3/4) grains.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रौप्यटङ्क
raupya-ṭaṅka , ‘a silver ṭaṅka (q. v.)’; a silver kārṣāpaṇa so called in South India according to Nārada.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेकैप्पोन्
rekai-ppon , regarded as the name of a gold coin of the Vijayanagara times so called probably for bearing linear marks (rekhā); may be ‘revenue income in cash’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रेखा
rekhā , cf. rekai-ppon.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुद्रदामक
rudradāmaka , ‘kārṣāpaṇa issued by Rudradāman’; name applied to the silver coins issued by the Śaka rulers of Western India; its later imitations were called rūpaka, dramma, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप|रूपं
rūpa , same as rūpaka or rūpyaka (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपक|रूपकं|रूपकः
rūpaka , silver coin; silver coin (1/16) (about 20 ratis) of a gold dīnāra, etc.; also called dramma, purāṇa, kārṣāpaṇa, etc.; same as modern rupee; cf. kṛṣṇarāja-rūpaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=438" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रुपेए
rupee , English form of rūpīya (q. v.); silver coin equal to 16 annas and 64 paisās.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूपीय
rūpīya(rūpīah) , Muhammadan name of rūpya, rūpaka or rūpyaka (q. v.); same as modern rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रूप्य|रूप्यं
rūpya , same as rūpaka or rūpyaka (q. v.); same as modern rupee.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाहणिकाटि
śāhaṇikāṭi , supposed to be the name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शलागै
śalāgai , Tamil; name of a coin also called pal̤añśalāgai (accu); probably had the shape of a śalākā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शलाका
śalākā , same as Tamil śalāgai.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सम्बिरणिप्पलङ्गाशु
sambiraṇippalaṅ-gāśu , see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाण|शाणं|शाणः
śāṇa , name of a weight or a coin 40 ratis in weight; equal to 4 māṣas; sometimes regarded as 32 ratis and called niṣka and ṭaṅka; rarely also regarded as equal to 24 or 20 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानपाद|शानपादः
śāṇa-pāda , same as māṣa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शानक
śāṇaka , same as śāṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सर्षप|सर्षपः
sarṣapa , sometimes called ‘red sarṣapa’; a small unit of measurement.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाशुकानि
śāśukāni , also called śāśukāni-ṭaṅka; same as s̤as̤ghānī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शाशुकानिटङ्क
śāśukāni-ṭaṅka^1 , same as śāśukāni or s̤as̤ghānī.<BR>[1] Correction submitted by Jim Funderburk on 20160315. Reference: https://github.com/sanskrit-lexicon/CORRECTIONS/issues/252. note: waNka is Sanskrit word (hatchet). See SASukAni in IEG for waNka spelling..<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
s̤as̤ghānī , Tughlaq coin, 4 jītals in weight and value.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शतमान|शतमानः
śatamāna , the weight of 320 ratis; literally, ‘a hundred units of measurement’, the unit probably being the mañjāḍi (q. v.); also called pala and niṣka (320 ratis of gold or silver); during the medieval period, sometimes regarded as 160 ratis; name sometimes applied to an ancient gold coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतेर|सतेरः
satera , also spelt sateraka; probably the same as Greek stater; regarded as equal to 2 dīnāras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतेरक
sateraka , same as satera (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सौवर्ण|सौवर्णं|सौवर्णः
sauvarṇa , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शेनपकक्कुलिगै
śenapaka-kkul̤igai , see kul̤igai, gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिग्लोस्
siglos , name of the silver coin (86.45 grains) of ancient Irān.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सिन्न
sinna , same as cinna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

???
ṣaḍ-voḍḍika-dramma (JUPHS, Vol. XVIII, p. 200), copper dramma equal to 6 voḍḍikas or 120 cowrie-shells.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=560" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

षोडशी
ṣoḍaśī , also called ṣoḍaśikā; probably, one-sixteenth of the standard silver coin in weight or value; cf. paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सोडशिका
ṣoḍaśikā , same as ṣoḍaśī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शो
śol̤̣iya-kkāśu , ‘the Col̤̣a kāśu (copper coin)’; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रेष्ठिजीर्णविश्वमल्लप्रिय
śreṣṭhi-jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya , probably a mistake for jīrṇa-śreṣṭhi-viśvamalla-priya, ‘old coin minted by Śreṣṭhin Viśvamalla’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=439" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीमदादिवराहद्रम्म
śrīmad-ādivarāha-dramma , ‘dramma issued by śrīmad-Ādivarāha’; cf. ādivarāha-dramma; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

श्रीयक्किपलञ्शलागै
śrī-yakki-pal̤añ-śalāgai , cf. yakki-accu, pal̤añ-śalāgai, śalākā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्ततेर्
stater , Greek silver and gold coin; silver stater was also called tetradrachma; gold stater had the same weight as Persian double daric (265 grains).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शुक्ति|शुक्तिः
śukti , same as śatamāna (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुरभिमाड
surabhi-māḍa , probably, ‘māḍa bearing the figure of a cow’; see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्ण|सुवर्णं|सुवर्णः|सुवर्ण्ण
suvarṇa , weight of 16 māṣas or 80 ratis (about 146 grains); 16 kārṣāpaṇas or rūpakas or 48 paṇas according to different authorities; called picu, pāṇi, kroḍa, binduka, viḍālapadaka, haṃsapada, grāsagraha and tola; also called niṣka; (1/4) of pala; gold coin weighing 80 ratis; name applied to Tamil kal̤̣añju (about 32 ratis or 58 grains theoretically).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुवर्णगद्याण
suvarṇa-gadyāṇa , ‘gold gadyāṇa’; see gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाका
ṭākā , modern Bengali form of ṭaṇkā (from ṭaṅkaka); silver coin; money; written in old Bengali as taṅkā; see ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टं|ट|टः
ṭaṃ , abbreviation of ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तण्डुल|तंडुल|तंडुलः|तण्डुलः
taṇḍula , (1/2) of a dhānya-māṣa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ताङ्क्
ṭāṅk , also called ṭāṅkī; same as ṭanka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्क|टंक|टंकं|टंकः|टङ्कः
ṭaṅka , a coin in general; a silver coin (often one tola in weight); same as śāna; equal to 4 silver fanams, silver coin of the Delhi Sul̤tāns, 96 or 100 ratis in weight; a small copper coin; (1/2) of a rupee. There were gold and copper taṅkas; see hema-ṭaṅka and raupya-ṭaṅka. Cf. ṭāṅk, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टङ्कक|टंकक|टंककः|टङ्ककः
ṭaṅkaka , same as ṭaṅka (q. v.); name of a silver coin; sometimes mentioned as bearing the figure of the Bhagavat.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

टाङ्की
ṭāṅkī , same as ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तार्
tār , name of a silver coin, equal to (1/6) of a gold fanam.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तेत्रद्रछ्म
tetradrachma , ‘four-drachma’; quadruple drachma; see drachma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तिरम
tirama , Tamil form of dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोल|तोलं|तोलः
tola , also spelt tolaka; 80 ratis in weight; same as suvarṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तोलक|तोलकं
tolaka , same as kola or tola; 80 ratis in weight.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

त्रिशूलकाशु
triśūla-kāśu , probably, ‘kāśu bearing the representation of a trident’; possibly issued by the authorities of a Śiva temple; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुलैप्पोन्
tul̤ai-ppon , Tamil; ‘correct weight’ or ‘good current coin’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तुरैमि
turai-min̤n̤ar-pon , a kind of pon (i. e. hon, gadyāṇa or varāha).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=440" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उण्डिअच्चु
uṇḍi-accu , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उप्पुक्काशु
uppu-kkāśu , ‘salt money’; name of a tax; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्कलञ्जू
ūr-kal̤añjū , see kal̤̣añju.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऊर्काशु
ūr-kāśu , see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

उत्तमगण्डमाड
uttama-gaṇḍa-māḍa , probably ‘good (i. e. new) gaṇḍamāḍa’ or ‘gaṇḍa-māḍa issued by king Uttama (i. e. Uttama-col̤̣a, 980-85 A. D.); see māḍa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वगैन्दकाशु
vagainda-kāśu , name of a tax; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्
val , sometimes regarded as (1/20) of a gadyāṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वल्ल|वल्लः
valla , equal to 3 ratis.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलाल्व
val̤āl-val̤̣i-tir̤antān-gul̤ikai , Pāṇḍya coin supposed to be issued by Jaṭāvarman Sundara-pāṇḍya I; see gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वलुदियच्चुवर्गम्
val̤udiy-accu-vargam , see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराह|वराहः
varāha , a gold coin; same as hūn or hon (q. v.); also called pagoda (q. v.) or ‘star pagoda’.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहगद्याण
varāha-gadyāṇa , same as varāha (q. v.), gadyāṇa or pagoda (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहपणम्
varāha-paṇam , probably ‘money calculated in varāha (q. v.).’<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहविंशोपक
varāha-viṃśopaka , (1/20) of a varāha; see varāha and viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराहन्पुल्लिकुलिगै
varāhan-pul̤l̤i-kul̤igai , see varāha and gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराटका
varāṭakā , same as varāṭaka or varāṭikā.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वराटिका
varāṭikā , cowrie-shell used as a coin; money.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्पणम्
vāśal-paṇam , ‘door-tax’; periodical payment due to the palace; same as vāśal-tiramam; see paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वाशल्तिरमम्
vāśal-tiramam , ‘door-tax’; same as vāśal-paṇam; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वटक|वटकः
vaṭaka , same as draṃkṣaṇa or tola.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेल्लि|वेल्लिः
věl̤l̤i , name of a coin.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिक्काशु
věli-kkāśu , same as věli-ppayar̤u; name of a tax; see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वेलिप्पयरु
věli-ppayar̤u , same as věli-kkāśu (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विडालपदक|विडालपदकं
viḍālapadaka , same as suvarṇa (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहद्रम्म
vigraha-dramma , ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigraha’; same as vigrahapāla-dramma, etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहद्रम्मविस्वोवक
vigraha-dramma-visvovaka , ‘(1/20) of the vigraha-dramma’; see dramma and viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालद्रम्म
vigrahapāla-dramma , ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigrahapāla’; same as vigraha-dramma (q. v.), etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालसत्कद्रम्म
vigrahapāla-satka-dramma , same as vigrahapāla-dramma (q. v.), etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहपालीयद्रम्म
vigrahapālīya-dramma , ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigrahapāla’; same as vigraha-dramma (q. v.), etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=441" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विग्रहतुङ्गीयद्रम्म
vigrahatuṅgīya-dramma , ‘dramma issued or minted by Vigrahatuṅga’; cf. vigraha-dramma, etc.; see dramma.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विजयराजटङ्क
vijayarāja-ṭaṅka , ‘ṭaṅka issued by Vijayarāja’; see ṭaṅka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विल्पणम्
vil-paṇam , ‘sales tax’, or ‘tax on bows or archery’; see paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशतिक|विंशतिकः
viṃśatika , regarded as equal to 20 māṣas; cf. viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंसोपक
viṃsopaka , corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विंशोपक
viṃśopaka , (1/20) of the standard silver coin of about 20 ratis; same as visvovaka, visopaka, vīsovā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरचम्पन्गुलिगै
vīracampan-gul̤l̤igai , gulikā of the Śambhuvarāya king Vīracampa; see gulikā, etc.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीरपञ्चालन्काशु
vīrapañcālan-kāśu , see kāśu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसलप्रियद्रम्म
vīsala-priya-dramma , also called vīsala-prī-dramma; cf. jīrṇa-viśvamalla-priya, Vīsala being the same as Viśvamalla.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विसोपक
visopaka , corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वीसोवा
vīsovā , corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

विस्वोवक
visvovaka , corruption of viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोडी
voḍī , also called voḍikā and voḍrī; sometimes regarded as a cowrie-shell used as coin; but really, the unit equal to 5 gaṇḍās = 20 cowries. Cf. bud̤ī, kapardaka-voḍī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोडिका
voḍikā , same as voḍī. Cf. bud̤ī and kapardaka-voḍī (q. v.).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वोड्री
voḍrī , same as voḍī.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

वृषविंशोपक
vṛṣa-viṃśopaka , ‘a viṃśopaka bearing the figure of a bull’; see viṃśopaka.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यादवरायन्पणम्
yādavarāyan-paṇam , ‘coin issued by the Yādavarāyas’; see paṇa.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यक्किअच्चु
yakki-accu , ‘accu bearing the figure of a Yakṣī (a village goddess)’; see accu.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

यव|यवः
yava , (1/15) of māṣa; (1/3) of rati.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=442" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समे
Same as Sthān-ācārya (EI 17), a temple priest.<BR> (EI 8; IA 14), an architect; used in the sense of ‘a master’, i. e. ‘a master-mason’; cf. Ācāri (EI 17), an artisan. Pāli Ācariya is explained as ‘a master goldsmith’ in the P. T. S.Pāli-Eng. Dict.<BR> (HA; IA 19), Jain; a Sādhu who has the right of both reading the sacred texts publicly and explaining them authoritatively.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=004" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समे
Same as paṭṭaka (q.v.); cf. Paṭṭa-lekhin, etc.<BR> (ASLV), an account book. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=-245" target="_blank">Page-245+ 40</a>]<BR> (LP), abbreviation of Paṭṭadhara; probably one who has the charter for collecting government revenues; cf. Paṭṭakila.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=244" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

समे
Same as paṭṭa; cf. rāja-paṭṭī (EI 4).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=IEG&page=246" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=ieg" target="_blank">Correction</a>

